B001C049V001	1	49	1	And Jacob called unto his sons, and said, Gather yourselves together, that I may tell you that which shall befall you in the last days.
B001C049V002	1	49	2	Gather yourselves together, and hear, you sons of Jacob; and hearken unto Israel your father.
B001C049V003	1	49	3	Reuben, you are my firstborn, my might, and the beginning of my strength, the excellency of dignity, and the excellency of power:
B001C049V004	1	49	4	Unstable as water, you shall not excel; because you went up to your father's bed; then you defiled it: he went up to my couch.
B001C049V005	1	49	5	Simeon and Levi are brothers; instruments of cruelty are in their habitations.
B001C049V006	1	49	6	O my soul, come not into their secret; unto their assembly, my spirit, be not united: for in their anger they slew a man, and in their self-will they dug down a wall.
B001C049V007	1	49	7	Cursed be their anger, for it was fierce; and their wrath, for it was cruel: I will divide them in Jacob, and scatter them in Israel.
B001C049V008	1	49	8	Judah, you are he whom your brothers shall praise: your hand shall be on the neck of your enemies; your father's children shall bow down before you.
B001C049V009	1	49	9	Judah is a lion's whelp: from the prey, my son, you are gone up: he stooped down, he crouched as a lion, and as a lioness; who shall rouse him up?
B001C049V010	1	49	10	The scepter shall not depart from Judah, nor a lawgiver from between his feet, until Shiloh comes; and unto him shall the gathering of the people be.
B001C049V011	1	49	11	Binding his foal unto the vine, and his donkeyâ€™s colt unto the choice vine; he washed his garments in wine, and his clothes in the blood of grapes:
B001C049V012	1	49	12	His eyes shall be red with wine, and his teeth white with milk.
B001C049V013	1	49	13	Zebulun shall dwell at the shore of the sea; and he shall be for a haven of ships; and his border shall be unto Sidon.
B001C049V014	1	49	14	Issachar is a strong donkey crouching down between two burdens:
B001C049V015	1	49	15	And he saw that rest was good, and the land that it was pleasant; and bowed his shoulder to bear, and became a servant unto forced labor.
B001C049V016	1	49	16	Dan shall judge his people, as one of the tribes of Israel.
B001C049V017	1	49	17	Dan shall be a serpent by the way, an adder in the path, that bites the horseâ€™s heels, so that his rider shall fall backward.
B001C049V018	1	49	18	I have waited for your salvation, O LORD.
B001C049V019	1	49	19	Gad, a troop shall overcome him: but he shall overcome at the last.
B001C049V020	1	49	20	Out of Asher his food shall be fat, and he shall yield royal dainties.
B001C049V021	1	49	21	Naphtali is a hind let loose: he gives beautiful words.
B001C049V022	1	49	22	Joseph is a fruitful bough, even a fruitful bough by a well; whose branches run over the wall:
B001C049V023	1	49	23	The archers have fiercely attacked him, and shot at him, and hated him:
B001C049V024	1	49	24	But his bow abode in strength, and the arms of his hands were made strong by the hands of the mighty God of Jacob; (from there is the Shepherd, the Rock of Israel:)
B001C049V025	1	49	25	Even by the God of your father, who shall help you; and by the Almighty, who shall bless you with blessings of heaven above, blessings of the deep that lies beneath, blessings of the breasts, and of the womb:
B001C049V026	1	49	26	The blessings of your father have prevailed above the blessings of my ancestors unto the utmost bounds of the everlasting hills: they shall be on the head of Joseph, and on the crown of the head of him that was separate from his brothers.
B001C049V027	1	49	27	Benjamin is ravenous as a wolf: in the morning he shall devour the prey, and at night he shall divide the spoil.
B001C049V028	1	49	28	All these are the twelve tribes of Israel: and this is it that their father spoke unto them, and blessed them; every one according to his blessing he blessed them.
B001C049V029	1	49	29	And he charged them, and said unto them, I am to be gathered unto my people: bury me with my fathers in the cave that is in the field of Ephron the Hittite,
B001C049V030	1	49	30	In the cave that is in the field of Machpelah, which is before Mamre, in the land of Canaan, which Abraham bought with the field of Ephron the Hittite for a possession as a burying place.
B001C049V031	1	49	31	There they buried Abraham and Sarah his wife; there they buried Isaac and Rebekah his wife; and there I buried Leah.
B001C049V032	1	49	32	The purchase of the field and of the cave that is in it was from the children of Heth.
B001C049V033	1	49	33	And when Jacob had made an end of commanding his sons, he gathered up his feet into the bed, and died, and was gathered unto his people.
B001C050V001	1	50	1	And Joseph fell upon his father's face, and wept upon him, and kissed him.
B001C050V002	1	50	2	And Joseph commanded his servants the physicians to embalm his father: and the physicians embalmed Israel.
B001C050V003	1	50	3	And forty days were fulfilled for him; for so are fulfilled the days of those who are embalmed: and the Egyptians mourned for him three score and ten days.
B001C050V004	1	50	4	And when the days of his mourning were past, Joseph spoke unto the house of Pharaoh, saying, If now I have found grace in your eyes, speak, I pray you, in the ears of Pharaoh, saying,
B001C050V005	1	50	5	My father made me swear, saying, Lo, I die: in my grave which I have dug for me in the land of Canaan, there shall you bury me. Now therefore let me go up, I pray you, and bury my father, and I will come again.
B001C050V006	1	50	6	And Pharaoh said, Go up, and bury your father, according as he made you swear.
B001C050V007	1	50	7	And Joseph went up to bury his father: and with him went up all the servants of Pharaoh, the elders of his house, and all the elders of the land of Egypt,
B001C050V008	1	50	8	And all the house of Joseph, and his brothers, and his father's house: only their little ones, and their flocks, and their herds, they left in the land of Goshen.
B001C050V009	1	50	9	And there went up with him both chariots and horsemen: and it was a very great company.
B001C050V010	1	50	10	And they came to the threshing floor of Atad, which is beyond Jordan, and there they mourned with a great and very strong lamentation: and he made a mourning for his father seven days.
B001C050V011	1	50	11	And when the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, saw the mourning in the threshing floor of Atad, they said, This is a mourning to the Egyptians: therefore the name of it was called Abelmizraim, which is beyond Jordan.
B001C050V012	1	50	12	And his sons did unto him according as he commanded them:
B001C050V013	1	50	13	For his sons carried him into the land of Canaan, and buried him in the cave of the field of Machpelah, which Abraham bought with the field for a possession of a burying place from Ephron the Hittite, before Mamre.
B001C050V014	1	50	14	And Joseph returned into Egypt, he, and his brothers, and all that went up with him to bury his father, after he had buried his father.
B001C050V015	1	50	15	And when Joseph's brothers saw that their father was dead, they said, Joseph will perhaps hate us, and will certainly pay back to us all the evil which we did unto him.
B001C050V016	1	50	16	And they sent a messenger unto Joseph, saying, Your father did command before he died, saying,
B001C050V017	1	50	17	So shall you say unto Joseph, Forgive, I pray you now, the trespass of your brothers, and their sin; for they did unto you evil: and now, we pray you, forgive the trespass of the servants of the God of your father. And Joseph wept when they spoke unto him.
B001C050V018	1	50	18	And his brothers also went and fell down before his face; and they said, Behold, we are your servants.
B001C050V019	1	50	19	And Joseph said unto them, Fear not: for am I in the place of God?
B001C050V020	1	50	20	But as for you, you thought evil against me; but God meant it unto good, to bring to pass, as it is this day, to save many people alive.
B001C050V021	1	50	21	Now therefore fear not: I will nourish you, and your little ones. And he comforted them, and spoke kindly unto them.
B001C050V022	1	50	22	And Joseph dwelt in Egypt, he, and his father's house: and Joseph lived a hundred and ten years.
B001C050V023	1	50	23	And Joseph saw Ephraim's children of the third generation: the children also of Machir the son of Manasseh were brought up upon Joseph's knees.
B001C050V024	1	50	24	And Joseph said unto his brothers, I die: and God will surely visit you, and bring you out of this land unto the land which he swore to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob.
B001C050V025	1	50	25	And Joseph took an oath of the children of Israel, saying, God will surely visit you, and you shall carry up my bones from here.
B001C050V026	1	50	26	So Joseph died, being a hundred and ten years old: and they embalmed him, and he was put in a coffin in Egypt.
B002C001V001	2	1	1	Now these are the names of the children of Israel, who came into Egypt; every man and his household came with Jacob.
B002C001V002	2	1	2	Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah,
B002C001V003	2	1	3	Issachar, Zebulun, and Benjamin,
B002C001V004	2	1	4	Dan, and Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.
B002C001V005	2	1	5	And all persons that were direct offspring of Jacob were seventy souls: for Joseph was in Egypt already.
B002C001V006	2	1	6	And Joseph died, and all his brethren, and all that generation.
B002C001V007	2	1	7	And the children of Israel were fruitful, and increased abundantly, and multiplied, and grew exceedingly mighty; and the land was filled with them.
B002C001V008	2	1	8	Now there arose up a new king over Egypt, who knew not Joseph.
B002C001V009	2	1	9	And he said unto his people, Behold, the people of the children of Israel are more and mightier than we:
B002C001V010	2	1	10	Come, let us deal wisely with them; lest they multiply, and it come to pass, that, when there come upon us any war, they join also unto our enemies, and fight against us, and so escape out of the land.
B002C001V011	2	1	11	Therefore they did set over them taskmasters to afflict them with their burdens. And they built for Pharaoh treasure cities, Pithom and Raamses.
B002C001V012	2	1	12	But the more they afflicted them, the more they multiplied and grew. And they were grieved because of the children of Israel.
B002C001V013	2	1	13	And the Egyptians made the children of Israel to serve with rigor:
B002C001V014	2	1	14	And they made their lives bitter with hard bondage, in mortar, and in brick, and in all manner of service in the field: all their service, in which they made them serve, was with rigor.
B002C001V015	2	1	15	And the king of Egypt spoke to the Hebrew midwives, of whom the name of the one was Shiphrah, and the name of the other Puah:
B002C001V016	2	1	16	And he said, When you serve as a midwife to the Hebrew women, and see them upon the stools; if it be a son, then you shall kill him: but if it be a daughter, then she shall live.
B002C001V017	2	1	17	But the midwives feared God, and did not as the king of Egypt commanded them, but saved the male children alive.
B002C001V018	2	1	18	And the king of Egypt called for the midwives, and said unto them, Why have you done this thing, and have saved the male children alive?
B002C001V019	2	1	19	And the midwives said unto Pharaoh, Because the Hebrew women are not as the Egyptian women; for they are vigorous, and are delivered before the midwives come in unto them.
B002C001V020	2	1	20	Therefore God dealt well with the midwives: and the people multiplied, and grew very mighty.
B002C001V021	2	1	21	And it came to pass, because the midwives feared God, that he gave them families.
B002C001V022	2	1	22	And Pharaoh charged all his people, saying, Every son that is born you shall cast into the river, and every daughter you shall save alive.
B002C002V001	2	2	1	And there went a man of the house of Levi, and took to wife a daughter of Levi.
B002C002V002	2	2	2	And the woman conceived, and bore a son: and when she saw him that he was a fine child, she hid him three months.
B002C002V003	2	2	3	And when she could no longer hide him, she took for him an ark of bulrushes, and daubed it with tar and with pitch, and put the child in it; and she laid it among the reeds by the river's bank.
B002C002V004	2	2	4	And his sister stood far off, to know what would be done to him.
B002C002V005	2	2	5	And the daughter of Pharaoh came down to wash herself at the river; and her maidens walked along by the river's side; and when she saw the ark among the reeds, she sent her maid to get it.
B002C002V006	2	2	6	And when she had opened it, she saw the child: and, behold, the babe wept. And she had compassion on him, and said, This is one of the Hebrews' children.
B002C002V007	2	2	7	Then said his sister to Pharaoh's daughter, Shall I go and call to you a nurse of the Hebrew women, that she may nurse the child for you?
B002C002V008	2	2	8	And Pharaoh's daughter said to her, Go. And the girl went and called the child's mother.
B002C002V009	2	2	9	And Pharaoh's daughter said unto her, Take this child away, and nurse it for me, and I will give you your wages. And the woman took the child, and nursed it.
B002C002V010	2	2	10	And the child grew, and she brought him unto Pharaoh's daughter, and he became her son. And she called his name Moses: and she said, Because I drew him out of the water.
B002C002V011	2	2	11	And it came to pass in those days, when Moses was grown, that he went out unto his brethren, and looked on their burdens: and he spied an Egyptian smiting a Hebrew, one of his brethren.
B002C002V012	2	2	12	And he looked this way and that way, and when he saw that there was no man, he slew the Egyptian, and hid him in the sand.
B002C002V013	2	2	13	And when he went out the second day, behold, two men of the Hebrews strove together: and he said to him that did the wrong, Why strike you your fellow?
B002C002V014	2	2	14	And he said, Who made you a prince and a judge over us? do you intend to kill me, as you killed the Egyptian? And Moses feared, and said, Surely this thing is known.
B002C002V015	2	2	15	Now when Pharaoh heard this thing, he sought to slay Moses. But Moses fled from the face of Pharaoh, and dwelt in the land of Midian: and he sat down by a well.
B002C002V016	2	2	16	Now the priest of Midian had seven daughters: and they came and drew water, and filled the troughs to water their father's flock.
B002C002V017	2	2	17	And the shepherds came and drove them away: but Moses stood up and helped them, and watered their flock.
B002C002V018	2	2	18	And when they came to Reuel their father, he said, How is it that you are come so soon today?
B002C002V019	2	2	19	And they said, An Egyptian delivered us out of the hand of the shepherds, and also drew water enough for us, and watered the flock.
B002C002V020	2	2	20	And he said unto his daughters, And where is he? why is it that you have left the man? call him, that he may eat bread.
