B002C031V018	2	31	18	And he gave unto Moses, when he had made an end of speaking with him upon mount Sinai, two tables of testimony, tables of stone, written with the finger of God.
B002C032V001	2	32	1	And when the people saw that Moses delayed to come down out of the mount, the people gathered themselves together unto Aaron, and said unto him, Up, make us gods, who shall go before us; for as for this Moses, the man that brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we know not what has become of him.
B002C032V002	2	32	2	And Aaron said unto them, Break off the golden earrings, which are in the ears of your wives, of your sons, and of your daughters, and bring them unto me.
B002C032V003	2	32	3	And all the people broke off the golden earrings which were in their ears, and brought them unto Aaron.
B002C032V004	2	32	4	And he received them from their hand, and fashioned it with an engraving tool, after he had made it a molten calf: and they said, These be your gods, O Israel, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt.
B002C032V005	2	32	5	And when Aaron saw it, he built an altar before it; and Aaron made proclamation, and said, Tomorrow is a feast to the LORD.
B002C032V006	2	32	6	And they rose up early on the next day, and offered burnt offerings, and brought peace offerings; and the people sat down to eat and to drink, and rose up to play.
B002C032V007	2	32	7	And the LORD said unto Moses, 
B002C032V008	2	32	8	
        
B002C032V009	2	32	9	And the LORD said unto Moses, 
B002C032V010	2	32	10	
        
B002C032V011	2	32	11	And Moses besought the LORD his God, and said, LORD, why does your wrath grow hot against your people, whom you have brought forth out of the land of Egypt with great power, and with a mighty hand?
B002C032V012	2	32	12	Why should the Egyptians speak, and say, For mischief did he bring them out, to slay them in the mountains, and to consume them from the face of the earth? Turn from your fierce wrath, and change from this evil against your people.
B002C032V013	2	32	13	Remember Abraham, Isaac, and Israel, your servants, to whom you swore by your own self, and said unto them, I will multiply your descendants as the stars of heaven, and all this land that I have spoken of will I give unto your descendants, and they shall inherit it forever.
B002C032V014	2	32	14	And the LORD turned from the evil which he thought to do unto his people.
B002C032V015	2	32	15	And Moses turned, and went down from the mount, and the two tables of the testimony were in his hand: the tables were written on both their sides; on the one side and on the other were they written.
B002C032V016	2	32	16	And the tables were the work of God, and the writing was the writing of God, engraved upon the tables.
B002C032V017	2	32	17	And when Joshua heard the noise of the people as they shouted, he said unto Moses, There is a noise of war in the camp.
B002C032V018	2	32	18	And he said, It is not the voice of them that shout for mastery, neither is it the voice of them that cry for being overcome: but the noise of them that sing do I hear.
B002C032V019	2	32	19	And it came to pass, as soon as he came near unto the camp, that he saw the calf, and the dancing: and Moses' anger grew hot, and he cast the tables out of his hands, and broke them beneath the mount.
B002C032V020	2	32	20	And he took the calf which they had made, and burnt it in the fire, and ground it to powder, and scattered it upon the water, and made the children of Israel drink of it.
B002C032V021	2	32	21	And Moses said unto Aaron, What did this people unto you, that you have brought so great a sin upon them?
B002C032V022	2	32	22	And Aaron said, Let not the anger of my lord grow hot: you know the people, that they are set on mischief.
B002C032V023	2	32	23	For they said unto me, Make us gods, who shall go before us: for as for this Moses, the man that brought us up out of the land of Egypt, we know not what has become of him.
B002C032V024	2	32	24	And I said unto them, Whosoever has any gold, let them break it off. So they gave it to me: then I cast it into the fire, and there came out this calf.
B002C032V025	2	32	25	And when Moses saw that the people were naked; (for Aaron had let them be naked unto their shame among their enemies:)
B002C032V026	2	32	26	Then Moses stood in the gate of the camp, and said, Who is on the LORD'S side? let him come unto me. And all the sons of Levi gathered themselves together unto him.
B002C032V027	2	32	27	And he said unto them, Thus says the LORD God of Israel, Put every man his sword by his side, and go in and out from gate to gate throughout the camp, and slay every man his brother, and every man his companion, and every man his neighbor.
B002C032V028	2	32	28	And the children of Levi did according to the word of Moses: and there fell of the people that day about three thousand men.
