B004C029V040	4	29	40	And Moses told the children of Israel according to all that the LORD commanded Moses.
B004C030V001	4	30	1	And Moses spoke unto the heads of the tribes concerning the children of Israel, saying, This is the thing which the LORD has commanded.
B004C030V002	4	30	2	If a man vows a vow unto the LORD, or swears an oath to bind his soul with a bond; he shall not break his word, he shall do according to all that proceeds out of his mouth.
B004C030V003	4	30	3	If a woman also vows a vow unto the LORD, and binds herself by a bond, being in her father's house in her youth;
B004C030V004	4	30	4	And her father hears her vow, and her bond with which she has bound her soul, and her father shall hold his peace at her: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond with which she has bound her soul shall stand.
B004C030V005	4	30	5	But if her father forbids her in the day that he hears; not any of her vows, or of her bonds with which she has bound her soul, shall stand: and the LORD shall forgive her, because her father forbade her.
B004C030V006	4	30	6	And if she had indeed a husband, when she vowed, or uttered anything out of her lips, with which she bound her soul;
B004C030V007	4	30	7	And her husband heard it, and held his peace at her in the day that he heard it: then her vows shall stand, and her bonds with which she bound her soul shall stand.
B004C030V008	4	30	8	But if her husband forbade her on the day that he heard it; then he shall make her vow which she vowed, and that which she uttered with her lips, with which she bound her soul, of none effect: and the LORD shall forgive her.
B004C030V009	4	30	9	But every vow of a widow, and of her that is divorced, with which they have bound their souls, shall stand against her.
B004C030V010	4	30	10	And if she vowed in her husband's house, or bound her soul by a bond with an oath;
B004C030V011	4	30	11	And her husband heard it, and held his peace at her, and forbade her not: then all her vows shall stand, and every bond with which she bound her soul shall stand.
B004C030V012	4	30	12	But if her husband has truly made them void on the day he heard them; then whatsoever proceeded out of her lips concerning her vows, or concerning the bond of her soul, shall not stand: her husband has made them void; and the LORD shall forgive her.
B004C030V013	4	30	13	Every vow, and every binding oath to afflict the soul, her husband may establish it, or her husband may make it void.
B004C030V014	4	30	14	But if her husband altogether holds his peace at her from day to day; then he establishes all her vows, or all her bonds, which are upon her: he confirms them, because he held his peace at her in the day that he heard them.
B004C030V015	4	30	15	But if he shall in any way make them void after that he has heard them; then he shall bear her iniquity.
B004C030V016	4	30	16	These are the statutes, which the LORD commanded Moses, between a man and his wife, between the father and his daughter, being yet in her youth in her father's house.
B004C031V001	4	31	1	And the LORD spoke unto Moses, saying,
B004C031V002	4	31	2	
        
B004C031V003	4	31	3	And Moses spoke unto the people, saying, Arm some of yourselves unto war, and let them go against the Midianites, and avenge the LORD of Midian.
B004C031V004	4	31	4	Of every tribe a thousand, throughout all the tribes of Israel, shall you send to the war.
B004C031V005	4	31	5	So there were delivered out of the thousands of Israel, a thousand of every tribe, twelve thousand armed for war.
B004C031V006	4	31	6	And Moses sent them to the war, a thousand of every tribe, them and Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, to the war, with the holy instruments, and the trumpets to blow in his hand.
B004C031V007	4	31	7	And they warred against the Midianites, as the LORD commanded Moses; and they slew all the males.
B004C031V008	4	31	8	And they slew the kings of Midian, besides the rest of them that were slain; namely, Evi, and Rekem, and Zur, and Hur, and Reba, five kings of Midian: Balaam also the son of Beor they slew with the sword.
B004C031V009	4	31	9	And the children of Israel took all the women of Midian captives, and their little ones, and took the spoil of all their cattle, and all their flocks, and all their goods.
B004C031V010	4	31	10	And they burnt all their cities in which they dwelt, and all their encampments, with fire.
B004C031V011	4	31	11	And they took all the spoil, and all the prey, both of people and of animals.
B004C031V012	4	31	12	And they brought the captives, and the prey, and the spoil, unto Moses, and Eleazar the priest, and unto the congregation of the children of Israel, unto the camp at the plains of Moab, which are by the Jordan near Jericho.
B004C031V013	4	31	13	And Moses, and Eleazar the priest, and all the leaders of the congregation, went forth to meet them outside the camp.
B004C031V014	4	31	14	And Moses was angry with the officers of the army, with the captains over thousands, and captains over hundreds, who came from the battle.
B004C031V015	4	31	15	And Moses said unto them, Have you saved all the women alive?
B004C031V016	4	31	16	Behold, these caused the children of Israel, through the counsel of Balaam, to commit trespass against the LORD in the matter of Peor, and there was a plague among the congregation of the LORD.
B004C031V017	4	31	17	Now therefore kill every male among the little ones, and kill every woman that has known man by lying with him.
B004C031V018	4	31	18	But all the young girls, that have not known a man by lying with him, keep alive for yourselves.
B004C031V019	4	31	19	And you must abide outside the camp seven days: whosoever has killed any person, and whosoever has touched any slain, purify both yourselves and your captives on the third day, and on the seventh day.
B004C031V020	4	31	20	And purify all your clothing, and all that is made of skins, and all work of goats' hair, and all things made of wood.
B004C031V021	4	31	21	And Eleazar the priest said unto the men of war who went to the battle, This is the ordinance of the law which the LORD commanded Moses;
B004C031V022	4	31	22	Only the gold, and the silver, the bronze, the iron, the tin, and the lead,
B004C031V023	4	31	23	Everything that can endure the fire, you shall make it go through the fire, and it shall be clean: nevertheless it shall be purified with the water of purification: and all that cannot endure the fire you shall make go through the water.
B004C031V024	4	31	24	And you shall wash your clothes on the seventh day, and you shall be clean, and afterward you shall come into the camp
B004C031V025	4	31	25	And the LORD spoke unto Moses, saying,
B004C031V026	4	31	26	
        
B004C031V027	4	31	27	
        
B004C031V028	4	31	28	
        
B004C031V029	4	31	29	
        
B004C031V030	4	31	30	
        
B004C031V031	4	31	31	And Moses and Eleazar the priest did as the LORD commanded Moses.
B004C031V032	4	31	32	And the booty, being the rest of the prey which the men of war had caught, was six hundred thousand and seventy thousand and five thousand sheep,
B004C031V033	4	31	33	And three score and twelve thousand cattle,
B004C031V034	4	31	34	And three score and one thousand donkeys,
B004C031V035	4	31	35	And thirty and two thousand persons in all, of women that had not known man by lying with him.
B004C031V036	4	31	36	And the half, which was the portion of them that went out to war, was in number three hundred thousand and seven and thirty thousand and five hundred sheep:
B004C031V037	4	31	37	And the LORD'S tribute of the sheep was six hundred and three score and fifteen.
B004C031V038	4	31	38	And the cattle were thirty and six thousand; of which the LORD'S tribute was three score and twelve.
B004C031V039	4	31	39	And the donkeys were thirty thousand and five hundred; of which the LORD'S tribute was three score and one.
B004C031V040	4	31	40	And the persons were sixteen thousand; of which the LORD'S tribute was thirty and two persons.
B004C031V041	4	31	41	And Moses gave the tribute, which was the LORD'S heave offering, unto Eleazar the priest, as the LORD commanded Moses.
B004C031V042	4	31	42	And of the children of Israel's half, which Moses divided from the men that fought,
B004C031V043	4	31	43	(Now the half that pertained unto the congregation was three hundred thousand and thirty thousand and seven thousand and five hundred sheep,
B004C031V044	4	31	44	And thirty and six thousand cattle,
B004C031V045	4	31	45	And thirty thousand donkeys and five hundred,
B004C031V046	4	31	46	And sixteen thousand persons;)
B004C031V047	4	31	47	Even of the children of Israel's half, Moses took one portion of fifty, both of persons and of animals, and gave them unto the Levites, who have charge of the tabernacle of the LORD; as the LORD commanded Moses.
B004C031V048	4	31	48	And the officers who were over thousands of the army, the captains of thousands, and captains of hundreds, came near unto Moses:
B004C031V049	4	31	49	And they said unto Moses, your servants have taken the sum of the men of war who are under our charge, and there lacks not one man of us.
B004C031V050	4	31	50	We have therefore brought an offering for the LORD, what every man has gotten, of ornaments of gold, chains, and bracelets, rings, earrings, and necklaces, to make an atonement for ourselves before the LORD.
B004C031V051	4	31	51	And Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold from them, even all crafted ornaments.
B004C031V052	4	31	52	And all the gold of the offering that they offered up to the LORD, of the captains of thousands, and of the captains of hundreds, was sixteen thousand seven hundred and fifty shekels.
B004C031V053	4	31	53	(For the men of war had taken spoil, every man for himself.)
B004C031V054	4	31	54	And Moses and Eleazar the priest took the gold of the captains of thousands and of hundreds, and brought it into the tabernacle of meeting, for a memorial for the children of Israel before the LORD.
B004C032V001	4	32	1	Now the children of Reuben and the children of Gad had a very great multitude of cattle: and when they saw the land of Jazer, and the land of Gilead, that, behold, the place was a place for cattle;
B004C032V002	4	32	2	The children of Gad and the children of Reuben came and spoke unto Moses, and to Eleazar the priest, and unto the leaders of the congregation, saying,
B004C032V003	4	32	3	Ataroth, and Dibon, and Jazer, and Nimrah, and Heshbon, and Elealeh, and Shebam, and Nebo, and Beon,
B004C032V004	4	32	4	Even the country which the LORD defeated before the congregation of Israel, is a land for cattle, and your servants have cattle:
B004C032V005	4	32	5	Therefore, said they, if we have found grace in your sight, let this land be given unto your servants for a possession, and bring us not over Jordan.
B004C032V006	4	32	6	And Moses said unto the children of Gad and to the children of Reuben, Shall your brethren go to war, and shall you sit here?
B004C032V007	4	32	7	And why discourage you the heart of the children of Israel from going over into the land which the LORD has given them?
B004C032V008	4	32	8	Thus did your fathers, when I sent them from Kadeshbarnea to see the land.
B004C032V009	4	32	9	For when they went up unto the valley of Eshcol, and saw the land, they discouraged the heart of the children of Israel, that they should not go into the land which the LORD had given them.
B004C032V010	4	32	10	And the LORD'S anger was kindled the same time, and he swore, saying,
B004C032V011	4	32	11	
        
B004C032V012	4	32	12	
        
B004C032V013	4	32	13	And the LORD'S anger was kindled against Israel, and he made them wander in the wilderness forty years, until all the generation, that had done evil in the sight of the LORD, was consumed.
B004C032V014	4	32	14	And, behold, you are risen up in your fathers' stead, a brood of sinful men, to increase still more the fierce anger of the LORD toward Israel.
B004C032V015	4	32	15	For if you turn away from following him, he will yet again leave them in the wilderness; and you shall destroy all this people.
B004C032V016	4	32	16	And they came near unto him, and said, We will build sheepfolds here for our flocks, and cities for our little ones:
B004C032V017	4	32	17	But we ourselves will go ready armed before the children of Israel, until we have brought them unto their place: and our little ones shall dwell in the fortified cities because of the inhabitants of the land.
B004C032V018	4	32	18	We will not return unto our houses, until the children of Israel have inherited every man his inheritance.
B004C032V019	4	32	19	For we will not inherit with them on the other side of Jordan, and beyond; because our inheritance is fallen to us on this side of Jordan eastward.
B004C032V020	4	32	20	And Moses said unto them, If you will do this thing, if you will go armed before the LORD to war,
B004C032V021	4	32	21	And will go all of you armed over Jordan before the LORD, until he has driven out his enemies from before him,
B004C032V022	4	32	22	And the land is subdued before the LORD: then afterward you shall return, and be guiltless before the LORD, and before Israel; and this land shall be your possession before the LORD.
B004C032V023	4	32	23	But if you will not do so, behold, you have sinned against the LORD: and be sure your sin will find you out.
B004C032V024	4	32	24	Build you cities for your little ones, and folds for your sheep; and do that which has proceeded out of your mouth.
B004C032V025	4	32	25	And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben spoke unto Moses, saying, your servants will do as my lord commands.
B004C032V026	4	32	26	Our little ones, our wives, our flocks, and all our cattle, shall be there in the cities of Gilead:
B004C032V027	4	32	27	But your servants will pass over, every man armed for war, before the LORD to battle, as my lord says.
B004C032V028	4	32	28	So concerning them Moses commanded Eleazar the priest, and Joshua the son of Nun, and the chief fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel:
B004C032V029	4	32	29	And Moses said unto them, If the children of Gad and the children of Reuben will pass with you over Jordan, every man armed to battle, before the LORD, and the land shall be subdued before you; then you shall give them the land of Gilead for a possession:
B004C032V030	4	32	30	But if they will not pass over with you armed, they shall have possessions among you in the land of Canaan.
B004C032V031	4	32	31	And the children of Gad and the children of Reuben answered, saying, As the LORD has said unto your servants, so will we do.
B004C032V032	4	32	32	We will pass over armed before the LORD into the land of Canaan, that the possession of our inheritance on this side of Jordan may be ours.
B004C032V033	4	32	33	And Moses gave unto them, even to the children of Gad, and to the children of Reuben, and unto half the tribe of Manasseh the son of Joseph, the kingdom of Sihon king of the Amorites, and the kingdom of Og king of Bashan, the land, with the cities thereof within the borders, even the cities of the surrounding country.
B004C032V034	4	32	34	And the children of Gad built Dibon, and Ataroth, and Aroer,
B004C032V035	4	32	35	And Atroth Shophan, and Jazer, and Jogbehah,
B004C032V036	4	32	36	And Bethnimrah, and Bethharan, fortified cities: and folds for sheep.
B004C032V037	4	32	37	And the children of Reuben built Heshbon, and Elealeh, and Kiriathaim,
B004C032V038	4	32	38	And Nebo, and Baalmeon, (their names being changed,) and Sibmah: and gave other names unto the cities which they built.
B004C032V039	4	32	39	And the children of Machir the son of Manasseh went to Gilead, and took it, and dispossessed the Amorites who were in it.
B004C032V040	4	32	40	And Moses gave Gilead unto Machir the son of Manasseh; and he dwelt therein.
B004C032V041	4	32	41	And Jair the son of Manasseh went and took the small towns thereof, and called them Havothjair.
B004C032V042	4	32	42	And Nobah went and took Kenath, and the villages thereof, and called it Nobah, after his own name.
B004C033V001	4	33	1	These are the journeys of the children of Israel, who went forth out of the land of Egypt with their armies under the hand of Moses and Aaron.
B004C033V002	4	33	2	And Moses wrote their starting points of their journeys by the commandment of the LORD: and these are their journeys according to their starting points.
B004C033V003	4	33	3	And they departed from Rameses in the first month, on the fifteenth day of the first month; the next day after the passover the children of Israel went out with boldness in the sight of all the Egyptians.
B004C033V004	4	33	4	For the Egyptians buried all their firstborn, which the LORD had smitten among them: upon their gods also the LORD executed judgments.
B004C033V005	4	33	5	And the children of Israel set out from Rameses, and encamped at Succoth.
B004C033V006	4	33	6	And they departed from Succoth, and encamped at Etham, which is in the edge of the wilderness.
B004C033V007	4	33	7	And they set out from Etham, and turned again unto Pihahiroth, which is east of Baalzephon: and they encamped before Migdol.
B004C033V008	4	33	8	And they departed from before Pihahiroth, and passed through the midst of the sea into the wilderness, and went three days' journey in the wilderness of Etham, and encamped at Marah.
B004C033V009	4	33	9	And they set out from Marah, and came unto Elim: and in Elim were twelve fountains of water, and three score and ten palm trees; and they encamped there.
B004C033V010	4	33	10	And they set out from Elim, and encamped by the Red sea.
B004C033V011	4	33	11	And they set out from the Red sea, and encamped in the wilderness of Sin.
B004C033V012	4	33	12	And they took their journey out of the wilderness of Sin, and encamped at Dophkah.
B004C033V013	4	33	13	And they departed from Dophkah, and encamped at Alush.
B004C033V014	4	33	14	And they set out from Alush, and encamped at Rephidim, where there was no water for the people to drink.
B004C033V015	4	33	15	And they departed from Rephidim, and encamped in the wilderness of Sinai.
B004C033V016	4	33	16	And they set out from the desert of Sinai, and encamped at Kibrothhattaavah.
B004C033V017	4	33	17	And they departed from Kibrothhattaavah, and encamped at Hazeroth.
B004C033V018	4	33	18	And they departed from Hazeroth, and encamped at Rithmah.
B004C033V019	4	33	19	And they departed from Rithmah, and encamped at Rimmonperez.
B004C033V020	4	33	20	And they departed from Rimmonperez, and encamped at Libnah.
B004C033V021	4	33	21	And they set out from Libnah, and encamped at Rissah.
B004C033V022	4	33	22	And they journeyed from Rissah, and encamped at Kehelathah.
B004C033V023	4	33	23	And they went from Kehelathah, and encamped at mount Shepher.
B004C033V024	4	33	24	And they set out from mount Shepher, and encamped at Haradah.
B004C033V025	4	33	25	And they set out from Haradah, and encamped at Makheloth.
B004C033V026	4	33	26	And they set out from Makheloth, and encamped at Tahath.
B004C033V027	4	33	27	And they departed from Tahath, and encamped at Terah.
B004C033V028	4	33	28	And they set out from Terah, and encamped at Mithkah.
B004C033V029	4	33	29	And they went from Mithkah, and encamped at Hashmonah.
B004C033V030	4	33	30	And they departed from Hashmonah, and encamped at Moseroth.
B004C033V031	4	33	31	And they departed from Moseroth, and encamped at Benejaakan.
B004C033V032	4	33	32	And they set out from Benejaakan, and encamped at Horhaggidgad.
B004C033V033	4	33	33	And they went from Horhaggidgad, and encamped at Jotbathah.
B004C033V034	4	33	34	And they set out from Jotbathah, and encamped at Abronah.
B004C033V035	4	33	35	And they departed from Abronah, and encamped at Eziongeber.
B004C033V036	4	33	36	And they set out from Eziongeber, and encamped in the wilderness of Zin, which is Kadesh.
B004C033V037	4	33	37	And they set out from Kadesh, and encamped at mount Hor, in the edge of the land of Edom.
B004C033V038	4	33	38	And Aaron the priest went up into mount Hor at the commandment of the LORD, and died there, in the fortieth year after the children of Israel were come out of the land of Egypt, in the first day of the fifth month.
B004C033V039	4	33	39	And Aaron was a hundred and twenty and three years old when he died on mount Hor.
B004C033V040	4	33	40	And king of Arad, the Canaanite, who dwelt in the south in the land of Canaan, heard of the coming of the children of Israel.
B004C033V041	4	33	41	And they departed from mount Hor, and encamped at Zalmonah.
B004C033V042	4	33	42	And they departed from Zalmonah, and encamped at Punon.
B004C033V043	4	33	43	And they departed from Punon, and encamped at Oboth.
B004C033V044	4	33	44	And they departed from Oboth, and encamped at Iyeabarim, at the border of Moab.
B004C033V045	4	33	45	And they departed from Iyim, and encamped at Dibongad.
B004C033V046	4	33	46	And they set out from Dibongad, and encamped at Almondiblathaim.
B004C033V047	4	33	47	And they set out from Almondiblathaim, and encamped in the mountains of Abarim, before Nebo.
B004C033V048	4	33	48	And they departed from the mountains of Abarim, and encamped in the plains of Moab by the Jordan near Jericho.
B004C033V049	4	33	49	And they encamped by the Jordan, from Bethjeshimoth even unto Abelshittim in the plains of Moab.
B004C033V050	4	33	50	And the LORD spoke unto Moses in the plains of Moab by the Jordan near Jericho, saying,
