B004C036V001	4	36	1	And the chief fathers of the families of the children of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, of the families of the sons of Joseph, came near, and spoke before Moses, and before the leaders, the chief fathers of the children of Israel:
B004C036V002	4	36	2	And they said, The LORD commanded my lord to give the land for an inheritance by lot to the children of Israel: and my lord was commanded by the LORD to give the inheritance of Zelophehad our brother unto his daughters.
B004C036V003	4	36	3	And if they are married to any of the sons of the other tribes of the children of Israel, then shall their inheritance be taken from the inheritance of our fathers, and shall be put to the inheritance of the tribe to which they are received: so shall it be taken from the lot of our inheritance.
B004C036V004	4	36	4	And when the jubilee of the children of Israel shall be, then shall their inheritance be put unto the inheritance of the tribe to which they are received: so shall their inheritance be taken away from the inheritance of the tribe of our fathers.
B004C036V005	4	36	5	And Moses commanded the children of Israel according to the word of the LORD, saying, The tribe of the sons of Joseph has spoken correctly.
B004C036V006	4	36	6	This is the thing which the LORD does command concerning the daughters of Zelophehad, saying, 
B004C036V007	4	36	7	
        
B004C036V008	4	36	8	
        
B004C036V009	4	36	9	
        
B004C036V010	4	36	10	Even as the LORD commanded Moses, so did the daughters of Zelophehad:
B004C036V011	4	36	11	For Mahlah, Tirzah, and Hoglah, and Milcah, and Noah, the daughters of Zelophehad, were married unto their father's brothers' sons:
B004C036V012	4	36	12	And they were married into the families of the sons of Manasseh the son of Joseph, and their inheritance remained in the tribe of the family of their father.
B004C036V013	4	36	13	These are the commandments and the judgments, which the LORD commanded by the hand of Moses unto the children of Israel in the plains of Moab by the Jordan near Jericho.
B005C001V001	5	1	1	These are the words which Moses spoke unto all Israel on this side of Jordan in the wilderness, in the plain over against Suph, between Paran, and Tophel, and Laban, and Hazeroth, and Dizahab.
B005C001V002	5	1	2	(There are eleven days' journey from Horeb by the way of mount Seir unto Kadeshbarnea.)
B005C001V003	5	1	3	And it came to pass in the fortieth year, in the eleventh month, on the first day of the month, that Moses spoke unto the children of Israel, according unto all that the LORD had given him in commandment unto them;
B005C001V004	5	1	4	After he had slain Sihon the king of the Amorites, who dwelt in Heshbon, and Og the king of Bashan, who dwelt at Astaroth in Edrei:
B005C001V005	5	1	5	On this side of Jordan, in the land of Moab, began Moses to declare this law, saying,
B005C001V006	5	1	6	The LORD our God spoke unto us in Horeb, saying, 
B005C001V007	5	1	7	
        
B005C001V008	5	1	8	
        
B005C001V009	5	1	9	And I spoke unto you at that time, saying, I am not able to bear you myself alone:
B005C001V010	5	1	10	The LORD your God has multiplied you, and, behold, you are this day as the stars of heaven for multitude.
B005C001V011	5	1	11	(The LORD God of your fathers make you a thousand times so many more than you are, and bless you, as he has promised you!)
B005C001V012	5	1	12	How can I myself alone bear your weight, and your burden, and your strife?
B005C001V013	5	1	13	Take you wise men, and understanding, and known among your tribes, and I will make them rulers over you.
B005C001V014	5	1	14	And you answered me, and said, The thing which you have spoken is good for us to do.
B005C001V015	5	1	15	So I took the heads of your tribes, wise men, and known, and made them heads over you, captains over thousands, and captains over hundreds, and captains over fifties, and captains over tens, and officers among your tribes.
B005C001V016	5	1	16	And I charged your judges at that time, saying, Hear the causes between your brethren, and judge righteously between every man and his brother, and the stranger that is with him.
B005C001V017	5	1	17	You shall not respect persons in judgment; but you shall hear the small as well as the great; you shall not be afraid of the face of man; for the judgment is God's: and the cause that is too hard for you, bring it unto me, and I will hear it.
B005C001V018	5	1	18	And I commanded you at that time all the things which you should do.
B005C001V019	5	1	19	And when we departed from Horeb, we went through all that great and terrible wilderness, which you saw by the way of the mountain of the Amorites, as the LORD our God commanded us; and we came to Kadeshbarnea.
B005C001V020	5	1	20	And I said unto you, you are come unto the mountain of the Amorites, which the LORD our God does give unto us.
B005C001V021	5	1	21	Behold, the LORD your God has set the land before you: go up and possess it, as the LORD God of your fathers has said unto you; fear not, neither be discouraged.
B005C001V022	5	1	22	And you came near unto me every one of you, and said, We will send men before us, and they shall search us out the land, and bring us word again by what way we must go up, and into what cities we shall come.
B005C001V023	5	1	23	And the saying pleased me well: and I took twelve men of you, one of each tribe:
B005C001V024	5	1	24	And they turned and went up into the mountain, and came unto the valley of Eshcol, and searched it out.
B005C001V025	5	1	25	And they took of the fruit of the land in their hands, and brought it down unto us, and brought us word again, and said, It is a good land which the LORD our God does give us.
B005C001V026	5	1	26	Nevertheless you would not go up, but rebelled against the commandment of the LORD your God:
B005C001V027	5	1	27	And you murmured in your tents, and said, Because the LORD hated us, he has brought us forth out of the land of Egypt, to deliver us into the hand of the Amorites, to destroy us.
B005C001V028	5	1	28	Where shall we go up? our brethren have discouraged our heart, saying, The people are greater and taller than we; the cities are great and walled up to heaven; and moreover we have seen the sons of the Anakim there.
B005C001V029	5	1	29	Then I said unto you, Dread not, neither be afraid of them.
B005C001V030	5	1	30	The LORD your God who goes before you, he shall fight for you, according to all that he did for you in Egypt before your eyes;
B005C001V031	5	1	31	And in the wilderness, where you have seen how that the LORD your God bore you, as a man does bear his son, in all the way that you went, until you came into this place.
B005C001V032	5	1	32	Yet in this thing you did not believe the LORD your God,
B005C001V033	5	1	33	Who went in the way before you, to search you out a place to pitch your tents in, in fire by night, to show you by what way you should go, and in a cloud by day.
