B005C006V001	5	6	1	Now these are the commandments, the statutes, and the judgments, which the LORD your God commanded to teach you, that you might do them in the land where you go to possess it:
B005C006V002	5	6	2	That you might fear the LORD your God, to keep all his statutes and his commandments, which I command you, you, and your son, and your son's son, all the days of your life; and that your days may be prolonged.
B005C006V003	5	6	3	Hear therefore, O Israel, and observe to do it; that it may be well with you, and that you may increase mightily, as the LORD God of your fathers has promised you, in the land that flows with milk and honey.
B005C006V004	5	6	4	Hear, O Israel: The LORD our God is one LORD:
B005C006V005	5	6	5	And you shall love the LORD your God with all your heart, and with all your soul, and with all your might.
B005C006V006	5	6	6	And these words, which I command you this day, shall be in your heart:
B005C006V007	5	6	7	And you shall teach them diligently unto your children, and shall talk of them when you sit in your house, and when you walk by the way, and when you lie down, and when you rise up.
B005C006V008	5	6	8	And you shall bind them for a sign upon your hand, and they shall be as frontlets between your eyes.
B005C006V009	5	6	9	And you shall write them upon the doorposts of your house, and on your gates.
B005C006V010	5	6	10	And it shall be, when the LORD your God shall have brought you into the land which he swore unto your fathers, to Abraham, to Isaac, and to Jacob, to give you great and beautiful cities, which you built not,
B005C006V011	5	6	11	And houses full of all good things, which you filled not, and wells dug, which you dug not, vineyards and olive trees, which you planted not; when you shall have eaten and be full;
B005C006V012	5	6	12	Then beware lest you forget the LORD, who brought you forth out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage.
B005C006V013	5	6	13	You shall fear the LORD your God, and serve him, and shall swear by his name.
B005C006V014	5	6	14	You shall not go after other gods, of the gods of the people who are round about you;
B005C006V015	5	6	15	(For the LORD your God is a jealous God among you) lest the anger of the LORD your God be kindled against you, and destroy you from off the face of the earth.
B005C006V016	5	6	16	You shall not test the LORD your God, as you tested him in Massah.
B005C006V017	5	6	17	You shall diligently keep the commandments of the LORD your God, and his testimonies, and his statutes, which he has commanded you.
B005C006V018	5	6	18	And you shall do that which is right and good in the sight of the LORD: that it may be well with you, and that you may go in and possess the good land which the LORD swore unto your fathers,
B005C006V019	5	6	19	To cast out all your enemies from before you, as the LORD has spoken.
B005C006V020	5	6	20	And when your son asks you in time to come, saying, What mean the testimonies, and the statutes, and the judgments, which the LORD our God has commanded you?
B005C006V021	5	6	21	Then you shall say unto your son, We were Pharaoh's slaves in Egypt; and the LORD brought us out of Egypt with a mighty hand:
B005C006V022	5	6	22	And the LORD showed signs and wonders, great and grievous, upon Egypt, upon Pharaoh, and upon all his household, before our eyes:
B005C006V023	5	6	23	And he brought us out from there, that he might bring us in, to give us the land which he swore unto our fathers.
B005C006V024	5	6	24	And the LORD commanded us to do all these statutes, to fear the LORD our God, for our good always, that he might preserve us alive, as it is at this day.
B005C006V025	5	6	25	And it shall be righteousness for us, if we observe to do all these commandments before the LORD our God, as he has commanded us.
B005C007V001	5	7	1	When the LORD your God shall bring you into the land to which you go to possess it, and has cast out many nations before you, the Hittites, and the Girgashites, and the Amorites, and the Canaanites, and the Perizzites, and the Hivites, and the Jebusites, seven nations greater and mightier than you;
B005C007V002	5	7	2	And when the LORD your God shall deliver them over to you; you shall strike them, and utterly destroy them; you shall make no covenant with them, nor show mercy unto them:
B005C007V003	5	7	3	Neither shall you make marriages with them; your daughter you shall not give unto his son, nor his daughter shall you take unto your son.
B005C007V004	5	7	4	For they will turn away your son from following me, that they may serve other gods: so will the anger of the LORD be kindled against you, and destroy you suddenly.
B005C007V005	5	7	5	But thus shall you deal with them; you shall destroy their altars, and break down their images, and cut down their idol poles, and burn their graven images with fire.
B005C007V006	5	7	6	For you are a holy people unto the LORD your God: the LORD your God has chosen you to be a special people unto himself, above all people that are upon the face of the earth.
B005C007V007	5	7	7	The LORD did not set his love upon you, nor choose you, because you were more in number than any people; for you were the fewest of all people:
B005C007V008	5	7	8	But because the LORD loved you, and because he would keep the oath which he had sworn unto your fathers, has the LORD brought you out with a mighty hand, and redeemed you out of the house of bondage, from the hand of Pharaoh king of Egypt.
B005C007V009	5	7	9	Know therefore that the LORD your God, he is God, the faithful God, who keeps covenant and mercy with them that love him and keep his commandments to a thousand generations;
B005C007V010	5	7	10	And repays them that hate him to their face, to destroy them: he will not be slack to him that hates him, he will repay him to his face.
B005C007V011	5	7	11	You shall therefore keep the commandments, and the statutes, and the judgments, which I command you this day, to do them.
B005C007V012	5	7	12	Therefore it shall come to pass, if you hearken to these judgments, and keep, and do them, that the LORD your God shall keep with you the covenant and the mercy which he swore unto your fathers:
B005C007V013	5	7	13	And he will love you, and bless you, and multiply you: he will also bless the fruit of your womb, and the fruit of your land, your grain, and your wine, and your oil, the increase of your cattle, and the flocks of your sheep, in the land which he swore unto your fathers to give you.
B005C007V014	5	7	14	You shall be blessed above all people: there shall not be male or female barren among you, or among your cattle.
B005C007V015	5	7	15	And the LORD will take away from you all sickness, and will put none of the evil diseases of Egypt, which you know, upon you; but will lay them upon all them that hate you.
B005C007V016	5	7	16	And you shall consume all the people whom the LORD your God shall deliver you; your eye shall have no pity upon them: neither shall you serve their gods; for that will be a snare unto you.
B005C007V017	5	7	17	If you shall say in your heart, These nations are more than I; how can I dispossess them?
B005C007V018	5	7	18	You shall not be afraid of them: but shall well remember what the LORD your God did unto Pharaoh, and unto all Egypt;
B005C007V019	5	7	19	The great trials which your eyes saw, and the signs, and the wonders, and the mighty hand, and the outstretched arm, whereby the LORD your God brought you out: so shall the LORD your God do unto all the people of whom you are afraid.
B005C007V020	5	7	20	Moreover the LORD your God will send the hornet among them, until they that are left, and hide themselves from you, be destroyed.
B005C007V021	5	7	21	You shall not be frightened by them: for the LORD your God is among you, a mighty God and terrible.
B005C007V022	5	7	22	And the LORD your God will drive out those nations before you little by little: you may not consume them at once, lest the wild animals of the field become too numerous for you.
B005C007V023	5	7	23	But the LORD your God shall deliver them unto you, and shall destroy them with a mighty destruction, until they are destroyed.
B005C007V024	5	7	24	And he shall deliver their kings into your hand, and you shall destroy their name from under heaven: there shall no man be able to stand before you, until you have destroyed them.
B005C007V025	5	7	25	The graven images of their gods shall you burn with fire: you shall not desire the silver or gold that is on them, nor take it unto you, lest you be snared by it: for it is an abomination to the LORD your God.
B005C007V026	5	7	26	Neither shall you bring an abomination into your house, lest you become an accursed thing like it: but you shall utterly detest it, and you shall utterly abhor it; for it is an accursed thing.
B005C008V001	5	8	1	All the commandments which I command you this day shall you observe to do, that you may live, and multiply, and go in and possess the land which the LORD swore unto your fathers.
B005C008V002	5	8	2	And you shall remember all the way which the LORD your God led you these forty years in the wilderness, to humble you, and to test you, to know what was in your heart, whether you would keep his commandments, or not.
B005C008V003	5	8	3	And he humbled you, and allowed you to hunger, and fed you with manna, which you knew not, neither did your fathers know; that he might make you know that man does not live by bread only, but by every word that proceeds out of the mouth of the LORD does man live.
B005C008V004	5	8	4	Your clothing grew not old upon you, neither did your foot swell, these forty years.
B005C008V005	5	8	5	You shall also consider in your heart, that, as a man chastens his son, so the LORD your God chastens you.
B005C008V006	5	8	6	Therefore you shall keep the commandments of the LORD your God, to walk in his ways, and to fear him.
B005C008V007	5	8	7	For the LORD your God brings you into a good land, a land of brooks of water, of fountains and depths that spring out of valleys and hills;
B005C008V008	5	8	8	A land of wheat, and barley, and vines, and fig trees, and pomegranates; a land of olive oil, and honey;
B005C008V009	5	8	9	A land in which you shall eat bread without scarceness, you shall not lack anything in it; a land whose stones are iron, and out of whose hills you may dig copper.
B005C008V010	5	8	10	When you have eaten and are full, then you shall bless the LORD your God for the good land which he has given you.
B005C008V011	5	8	11	Beware that you forget not the LORD your God, in not keeping his commandments, and his judgments, and his statutes, which I command you this day:
B005C008V012	5	8	12	Lest when you have eaten and are full, and have built fine houses, and dwelt in them;
B005C008V013	5	8	13	And when your herds and your flocks multiply, and your silver and your gold is multiplied, and all that you have is multiplied;
B005C008V014	5	8	14	Then your heart be lifted up, and you forget the LORD your God, who brought you forth out of the land of Egypt, from the house of bondage;
B005C008V015	5	8	15	Who led you through that great and terrible wilderness, in which were fiery serpents, and scorpions, and thirsty land, where there was no water; who brought you forth water out of the rock of flint;
B005C008V016	5	8	16	Who fed you in the wilderness with manna, which your fathers knew not, that he might humble you, and that he might test you, to do you good in the end;
B005C008V017	5	8	17	And you say in your heart, My power and the might of my hand has gotten me this wealth.
B005C008V018	5	8	18	But you shall remember the LORD your God: for it is he that gives you power to get wealth, that he may establish his covenant which he swore unto your fathers, as it is this day.
B005C008V019	5	8	19	And it shall be, if you do at all forget the LORD your God, and walk after other gods, and serve them, and worship them, I testify against you this day that you shall surely perish.
B005C008V020	5	8	20	As the nations which the LORD destroys before your face, so shall you perish; because you would not be obedient unto the voice of the LORD your God.
