B005C011V012	5	11	12	A land which the LORD your God cares for: the eyes of the LORD your God are always upon it, from the beginning of the year even unto the end of the year.
B005C011V013	5	11	13	And it shall come to pass, if you shall hearken diligently unto my commandments which I command you this day, to love the LORD your God, and to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul,
B005C011V014	5	11	14	That I will give you the rain of your land in its due season, the first rain and the latter rain, that you may gather in your grain, and your wine, and your oil.
B005C011V015	5	11	15	And I will send grass in your fields for your cattle, that you may eat and be full.
