B006C015V007	6	15	7	And the border went up toward Debir from the valley of Achor, and so northward, turning toward Gilgal, that is before the ascent to Adummim, which is on the south side of the valley: and the border passed toward the waters of Enshemesh, and ended at Enrogel:
B006C015V008	6	15	8	And the border went up by the valley of the son of Hinnom unto the south slope of the Jebusite; the same is Jerusalem: and the border went up to the top of the mountain that lies before the valley of Hinnom westward, which is at the end of the valley of the giants northward:
B006C015V009	6	15	9	And the border extended from the top of the hill unto the fountain of the water of Nephtoah, and went out to the cities of mount Ephron; and the border went around to Baalah, which is Kiriathjearim:
B006C015V010	6	15	10	And the border turned from Baalah westward unto mount Seir, and passed along to the side of mount Jearim, which is Chesalon, on the north side, and went down to Bethshemesh, and passed on to Timnah:
B006C015V011	6	15	11	And the border went out unto the side of Ekron northward: and the border went around to Shikkeron, and passed along to mount Baalah, and went out to Jabneel; and the end of the border was at the sea.
B006C015V012	6	15	12	And the west border was to the Great Sea, and its coast. This is the boundary round about the children of Judah according to their families.
B006C015V013	6	15	13	And unto Caleb the son of Jephunneh he gave a portion among the children of Judah, according to the commandment of the LORD to Joshua, even the city of Arba, the father of Anak, which city is Hebron.
B006C015V014	6	15	14	And Caleb drove out from there the three sons of Anak, Sheshai, and Ahiman, and Talmai, the children of Anak.
B006C015V015	6	15	15	And he went up there to the inhabitants of Debir: and the name of Debir before was Kiriathsepher.
B006C015V016	6	15	16	And Caleb said, He that smites Kiriathsepher, and takes it, to him will I give Achsah my daughter as wife.
B006C015V017	6	15	17	And Othniel the son of Kenaz, the brother of Caleb, took it: and he gave him Achsah his daughter as wife.
B006C015V018	6	15	18	And it came to pass, as she came unto him, that she moved him to ask of her father a field: and she dismounted off her donkey; and Caleb said unto her, What do you wish?
B006C015V019	6	15	19	She answered, Give me a blessing; for you have given me the South land; give me also springs of water. And he gave her the upper springs, and the lower springs.
B006C015V020	6	15	20	This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Judah according to their families.
B006C015V021	6	15	21	And the furthermost cities of the tribe of the children of Judah toward the border of Edom in the South were Kabzeel, and Eder, and Jagur,
B006C015V022	6	15	22	And Kinah, and Dimonah, and Adadah,
B006C015V023	6	15	23	And Kedesh, and Hazor, and Ithnan,
B006C015V024	6	15	24	Ziph, and Telem, and Bealoth,
B006C015V025	6	15	25	And Hazor, Hadattah, and Kerioth, and Hezron, which is Hazor,
B006C015V026	6	15	26	Amam, and Shema, and Moladah,
B006C015V027	6	15	27	And Hazargaddah, and Heshmon, and Bethpelet,
B006C015V028	6	15	28	And Hazarshual, and Beersheba, and Biziothiah,
B006C015V029	6	15	29	Baalah, and Iim, and Ezem,
B006C015V030	6	15	30	And Eltolad, and Chesil, and Hormah,
B006C015V031	6	15	31	And Ziklag, and Madmannah, and Sansannah,
B006C015V032	6	15	32	And Lebaoth, and Shilhim, and Ain, and Rimmon: all the cities are twenty and nine, with their villages:
B006C015V033	6	15	33	And in the lowland, Eshtaol, and Zorah, and Ashnah,
B006C015V034	6	15	34	And Zanoah, and Engannim, Tappuah, and Enam,
B006C015V035	6	15	35	Jarmuth, and Adullam, Socoh, and Azekah,
B006C015V036	6	15	36	And Shaaraim, and Adithaim, and Gederah, and Gederothaim; fourteen cities with their villages:
B006C015V037	6	15	37	Zenan, and Hadashah, and Migdalgad,
B006C015V038	6	15	38	And Dilean, and Mizpeh, and Joktheel,
B006C015V039	6	15	39	Lachish, and Bozkath, and Eglon,
B006C015V040	6	15	40	And Cabbon, and Lahmam, and Kitlish,
B006C015V041	6	15	41	And Gederoth, Bethdagon, and Naamah, and Makkedah; sixteen cities with their villages:
B006C015V042	6	15	42	Libnah, and Ether, and Ashan,
B006C015V043	6	15	43	And Iphtah, and Ashnah, and Nezib,
B006C015V044	6	15	44	And Keilah, and Achzib, and Mareshah; nine cities with their villages:
B006C015V045	6	15	45	Ekron, with its towns and its villages:
B006C015V046	6	15	46	From Ekron even unto the sea, all that lay near Ashdod, with their villages:
B006C015V047	6	15	47	Ashdod with its towns and its villages, Gaza with its towns and its villages, unto the river of Egypt, and the great sea, and its coastline:
B006C015V048	6	15	48	And in the mountains, Shamir, and Jattir, and Socoh,
B006C015V049	6	15	49	And Dannah, and Kiriathsannah, which is Debir,
B006C015V050	6	15	50	And Anab, and Eshtemoh, and Anim,
B006C015V051	6	15	51	And Goshen, and Holon, and Giloh; eleven cities with their villages:
B006C015V052	6	15	52	Arab, and Dumah, and Eshan,
B006C015V053	6	15	53	And Janim, and Bethtappuah, and Aphekah,
B006C015V054	6	15	54	And Humtah, and Kiriatharba, which is Hebron, and Zior; nine cities with their villages:
B006C015V055	6	15	55	Maon, Carmel, and Ziph, and Juttah,
B006C015V056	6	15	56	And Jezreel, and Jokdeam, and Zanoah,
B006C015V057	6	15	57	Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah; ten cities with their villages:
B006C015V058	6	15	58	Halhul, Bethzur, and Gedor,
B006C015V059	6	15	59	And Maarath, and Bethanoth, and Eltekon; six cities with their villages:
B006C015V060	6	15	60	Kiriathbaal, which is Kiriathjearim, and Rabbah; two cities with their villages:
B006C015V061	6	15	61	In the wilderness, Betharabah, Middin, and Secacah,
B006C015V062	6	15	62	And Nibshan, and the city of Salt, and Engedi; six cities with their villages.
B006C015V063	6	15	63	As for the Jebusites the inhabitants of Jerusalem, the children of Judah could not drive them out: but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Judah at Jerusalem unto this day.
B006C016V001	6	16	1	And the lot of the children of Joseph fell from the Jordan by Jericho, unto the water of Jericho on the east, to the wilderness that goes up from Jericho throughout mount Bethel.
B006C016V002	6	16	2	Then goes out from Bethel to Luz, and passes along to the borders of the Archites to Ataroth,
B006C016V003	6	16	3	Then goes down westward to the border of the Japhletites, unto the border of lower Bethhoron, to Gezer: and it ends at the sea.
B006C016V004	6	16	4	So the children of Joseph, Manasseh and Ephraim, took their inheritance.
B006C016V005	6	16	5	And the border of the children of Ephraim according to their families was thus: even the border of their inheritance on the east side was Atarothaddar, unto upper Bethhoron;
B006C016V006	6	16	6	And the border went out toward the sea by Michmethah on the north side; and the border turned about eastward unto Taanathshiloh, and passed by it on the east to Janoah;
B006C016V007	6	16	7	And it went down from Janoah to Ataroth, and to Naarah, and came to Jericho, and came out at the Jordan.
B006C016V008	6	16	8	The border went out from Tappuah westward to the brook Kanah; and ended at the sea. This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Ephraim by their families.
B006C016V009	6	16	9	And the separate cities for the children of Ephraim were among the inheritance of the children of Manasseh, all the cities with their villages.
B006C016V010	6	16	10	And they drove not out the Canaanites that dwelt in Gezer: but the Canaanites dwell among the Ephraimites unto this day, and serve under forced labor.
B006C017V001	6	17	1	There was also a lot for the tribe of Manasseh; for he was the firstborn of Joseph; for Machir the firstborn of Manasseh, the father of Gilead: because he was a man of war, therefore he was given Gilead and Bashan.
B006C017V002	6	17	2	There was also a lot for the rest of the children of Manasseh according to their families; for the children of Abiezer, and for the children of Helek, and for the children of Asriel, and for the children of Shechem, and for the children of Hepher, and for the children of Shemida: these were the male children of Manasseh the son of Joseph according to their families.
B006C017V003	6	17	3	But Zelophehad, the son of Hepher, the son of Gilead, the son of Machir, the son of Manasseh, had no sons, but only daughters: and these are the names of his daughters, Mahlah, and Noah, Hoglah, Milcah, and Tirzah.
B006C017V004	6	17	4	And they came near before Eleazar the priest, and before Joshua the son of Nun, and before the leaders, saying, The LORD commanded Moses to give us an inheritance among our brethren. Therefore according to the commandment of the LORD he gave them an inheritance among the brethren of their father.
B006C017V005	6	17	5	And there fell ten portions to Manasseh, besides the land of Gilead and Bashan, which were on the other side of Jordan;
B006C017V006	6	17	6	Because the daughters of Manasseh had an inheritance among his sons: and the rest of Manasseh's sons had the land of Gilead.
B006C017V007	6	17	7	And the territory of Manasseh was from Asher to Michmethath, that lies east of Shechem; and the border went along on the south to the inhabitants of Entappuah.
B006C017V008	6	17	8	Now Manasseh had the land of Tappuah: but Tappuah on the border of Manasseh belonged to the children of Ephraim;
B006C017V009	6	17	9	And the border descended to the brook Kanah, south of the brook: these cities of Ephraim are among the cities of Manasseh: the border of Manasseh also was on the north side of the brook, and the end of it was at the sea:
B006C017V010	6	17	10	Southward it was Ephraim's, and northward it was Manasseh's, and the sea was its border; and they joined together in Asher on the north, and in Issachar on the east.
B006C017V011	6	17	11	And Manasseh had in Issachar and in Asher Bethshean and its villages, and Ibleam and its villages, and the inhabitants of Dor and its villages, and the inhabitants of Endor and its villages, and the inhabitants of Taanach and its villages, and the inhabitants of Megiddo and its villages, even three regions.
B006C017V012	6	17	12	Yet the children of Manasseh could not drive out the inhabitants of those cities; but the Canaanites would persist to dwell in that land.
B006C017V013	6	17	13	Yet it came to pass, when the children of Israel grew strong, that they put the Canaanites to forced labor; but did not utterly drive them out.
B006C017V014	6	17	14	And the children of Joseph spoke unto Joshua, saying, Why have you given us only one lot and one portion to inherit, seeing we are a great people, since the LORD has blessed us until now?
B006C017V015	6	17	15	And Joshua answered them, If you are a great people, then get up to the forest country, and clear ground for yourself there in the land of the Perizzites and of the giants, if mount Ephraim is too narrow for you.
B006C017V016	6	17	16	But the children of Joseph said, The hill is not enough for us: and all the Canaanites that dwell in the land of the valley have chariots of iron, both they who are of Bethshean and its villages, and they who are in the valley of Jezreel.
B006C017V017	6	17	17	And Joshua spoke unto the house of Joseph, even to Ephraim and to Manasseh, saying, You are a great people, and have great power: you shall not have one lot only:
B006C017V018	6	17	18	But the mountain country shall be yours; for it is a forest, and you shall cut it down: and all the borders of it shall be yours: for you shall drive out the Canaanites, though they have iron chariots, and though they are strong.
B006C018V001	6	18	1	And the whole congregation of the children of Israel assembled together at Shiloh, and set up the tabernacle of meeting there. And the land was subdued before them.
B006C018V002	6	18	2	And there remained among the children of Israel seven tribes, which had not yet received their inheritance.
B006C018V003	6	18	3	And Joshua said unto the children of Israel, How long will you hesitate to go to possess the land, which the LORD God of your fathers has given you?
B006C018V004	6	18	4	Pick out from among you three men from each tribe: and I will send them, and they shall rise, and go through the land, and survey it according to their inheritance; and they shall come again to me.
B006C018V005	6	18	5	And they shall divide it into seven parts: Judah shall continue in their territory on the south, and the house of Joseph shall continue in their territory on the north.
B006C018V006	6	18	6	You shall therefore survey the land into seven parts, and bring the description here to me, that I may cast lots for you here before the LORD our God.
B006C018V007	6	18	7	But the Levites have no part among you; for the priesthood of the LORD is their inheritance: and Gad, and Reuben, and the half the tribe of Manasseh, have received their inheritance beyond the Jordan on the east, which Moses the servant of the LORD gave them.
B006C018V008	6	18	8	And the men arose, and went away: and Joshua charged them that went to survey the land, saying, Go and walk through the land, and survey it, and come again to me, that I may here cast lots for you before the LORD in Shiloh.
B006C018V009	6	18	9	And the men went and passed through the land, and surveyed it by cities into seven parts in a book, and came again to Joshua to the host at Shiloh.
B006C018V010	6	18	10	And Joshua cast lots for them in Shiloh before the LORD: and there Joshua divided the land unto the children of Israel according to their divisions.
B006C018V011	6	18	11	And the lot of the tribe of the children of Benjamin came up according to their families: and the territory of their lot came out between the children of Judah and the children of Joseph.
B006C018V012	6	18	12	And their border on the north side was from the Jordan; and the border went up to the side of Jericho on the north side, and went up through the mountains westward; and it ended at the wilderness of Bethaven.
B006C018V013	6	18	13	And the border went over from there toward Luz, to the side of Luz, which is Bethel, southward; and the border descended to Atarothadar, near the hill that lies on the south side of lower Bethhoron.
B006C018V014	6	18	14	And the border extended from there, and turned the corner at the sea southward, from the hill that lies before Bethhoron southward; and ended at Kiriathbaal, which is Kiriathjearim, a city of the children of Judah: this was the west side.
B006C018V015	6	18	15	And the south side was from the end of Kiriathjearim, and the border extended on the west, and went out to the spring of the waters of Nephtoah:
B006C018V016	6	18	16	And the border came down to the end of the mountain that lies before the valley of the son of Hinnom, and which is in the valley of the giants on the north, and descended to the valley of Hinnom, to the side of the Jebusites on the south, and descended to Enrogel,
B006C018V017	6	18	17	And it went around from the north, and went forth to Enshemesh, and went forth toward Geliloth, which is opposite the ascent of Adummim, and descended to the stone of Bohan the son of Reuben,
B006C018V018	6	18	18	And passed along toward the north side of Arabah, and went down unto Arabah:
B006C018V019	6	18	19	And the border passed along to the side of Bethhoglah: and the end of the border was at the north bay of the salt sea at the south end of Jordan: this was the south border.
B006C018V020	6	18	20	And Jordan was the border of it on the east side. This was the inheritance of the children of Benjamin, by the boundaries all around, according to their families.
B006C018V021	6	18	21	Now the cities of the tribe of the children of Benjamin according to their families were Jericho, and Bethhoglah, and Emikkeziz.
B006C018V022	6	18	22	And Betharabah, and Zemaraim, and Bethel,
B006C018V023	6	18	23	And Avvim, and Parah, and Ophrah,
B006C018V024	6	18	24	And Chepharharmmonai, and Ophni, and Geba; twelve cities with their villages:
B006C018V025	6	18	25	Gibeon, and Ramah, and Beeroth,
B006C018V026	6	18	26	And Mizpeh, and Chephirah, and Mozah,
B006C018V027	6	18	27	And Rekem, and Irpeel, and Taralah,
B006C018V028	6	18	28	And Zelah, Haleph, and Jebus, which is Jerusalem, Gibeah, and Kiriath; fourteen cities with their villages. This is the inheritance of the children of Benjamin according to their families.
B006C019V001	6	19	1	And the second lot came forth to Simeon, even for the tribe of the children of Simeon according to their families: and their inheritance was within the inheritance of the children of Judah.
B006C019V002	6	19	2	And they had in their inheritance Beersheba, and Sheba, and Moladah,
B006C019V003	6	19	3	And Hazarshual, and Balah, and Ezem,
B006C019V004	6	19	4	And Eltolad, and Bethul, and Hormah,
B006C019V005	6	19	5	And Ziklag, and Bethmarcaboth, and Hazarsusah,
B006C019V006	6	19	6	And Bethlebaoth, and Sharuhen; thirteen cities and their villages:
B006C019V007	6	19	7	Ain, Remmon, and Ether, and Ashan; four cities and their villages:
B006C019V008	6	19	8	And all the villages that were round about these cities to Baalathbeer, Ramath of the South. This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Simeon according to their families.
B006C019V009	6	19	9	Out of the portion of the children of Judah was the inheritance of the children of Simeon: for the portion of the children of Judah was too much for them: therefore the children of Simeon had their inheritance within their inheritance.
B006C019V010	6	19	10	And the third lot came up for the children of Zebulun according to their families: and the border of their inheritance was unto Sarid:
B006C019V011	6	19	11	And their border went up toward the sea, and Maralah, and reached to Dabbesheth, and reached to the brook that is east of Jokneam;
B006C019V012	6	19	12	And turned from Sarid eastward toward the sun rising unto the border of Chislothtabor, and then goes out to Daberath, and then up to Japhia.
B006C019V013	6	19	13	And from there passes on along on the east to Gathhepher, to Ethkazin, and goes on to Remmon and bends toward Neah;
B006C019V014	6	19	14	And the border went around to the north side of Hannathon: and ends in the valley of Iphtahel:
B006C019V015	6	19	15	And Kattath, and Nahallal, and Shimron, and Idalah, and Bethlehem: twelve cities with their villages.
B006C019V016	6	19	16	This is the inheritance of the children of Zebulun according to their families, these cities with their villages.
B006C019V017	6	19	17	And the fourth lot came out to Issachar, for the children of Issachar according to their families.
B006C019V018	6	19	18	And their border went to Jezreel, and included Chesulloth, and Shunem,
B006C019V019	6	19	19	And Hapharaim, and Shion, and Anaharath,
B006C019V020	6	19	20	And Rabbith, and Kishion, and Ebez,
B006C019V021	6	19	21	And Remeth, and Engannim, and Enhaddah, and Bethpazzez;
B006C019V022	6	19	22	And the border reaches to Tabor, and Shahazumah, and Bethshemesh; and the end of their border was at the Jordan: sixteen cities with their villages.
B006C019V023	6	19	23	This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Issachar according to their families, the cities and their villages.
B006C019V024	6	19	24	And the fifth lot came out for the tribe of the children of Asher according to their families.
B006C019V025	6	19	25	And their territory included Helkath, and Hali, and Beten, and Achshaph,
B006C019V026	6	19	26	And Alammelech, and Amad, and Mishal; and reaches to Carmel westward, and to Shihorlibnath;
B006C019V027	6	19	27	And turns toward the sun rising to Bethdagon, and reaches to Zebulun, and to the valley of Iphtahel toward the north side of Bethemek, and Neiel, and continues to Cabul on the left,
B006C019V028	6	19	28	And Ebron, and Rehob, and Hammon, and Kanah, even unto greater Sidon;
B006C019V029	6	19	29	And then the border turns to Ramah, and to the fortified city of Tyre; and the border turns to Hosah; and the end is at the sea by the region of Achzib:
B006C019V030	6	19	30	Ummah also, and Aphek, and Rehob: twenty and two cities with their villages.
B006C019V031	6	19	31	This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Asher according to their families, these cities with their villages.
B006C019V032	6	19	32	The sixth lot came out to the children of Naphtali, even for the children of Naphtali according to their families.
B006C019V033	6	19	33	And their border was from Heleph, from the oak in Zaanannim, and Adami, Nekeb, and Jabneel, unto Lakum; and it ended at the Jordan:
B006C019V034	6	19	34	And then the border turns westward to Aznothtabor, and goes from there to Hukkok, and reaches to Zebulun on the south side, and reaches to Asher on the west side, and to Judah by the Jordan toward the sun rising.
B006C019V035	6	19	35	And the fortified cities are Ziddim, Zer, and Hammath, Rakkath, and Chinnereth,
B006C019V036	6	19	36	And Adamah, and Ramah, and Hazor,
B006C019V037	6	19	37	And Kedesh, and Edrei, and Enhazor,
B006C019V038	6	19	38	And Iron, and Migdalel, Horem, and Bethanath, and Bethshemesh; nineteen cities with their villages.
B006C019V039	6	19	39	This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Naphtali according to their families, the cities and their villages.
B006C019V040	6	19	40	And the seventh lot came out for the tribe of the children of Dan according to their families.
B006C019V041	6	19	41	And the border of their inheritance was Zorah, and Eshtaol, and Irshemesh,
B006C019V042	6	19	42	And Shaalabbin, and Aijalon, and Ithlah,
B006C019V043	6	19	43	And Elon, and Thimnah, and Ekron,
B006C019V044	6	19	44	And Eltekeh, and Gibbethon, and Baalath,
B006C019V045	6	19	45	And Jehud, and Beneberak, and Gathrimmon,
B006C019V046	6	19	46	And Mejarkon, and Rakkon, with the region near Japho.
B006C019V047	6	19	47	And the border of the children of Dan went out beyond these: therefore the children of Dan went up to fight against Leshem, and took it, and struck it with the edge of the sword, and possessed it, and dwelt therein, and called Leshem, Dan, after the name of Dan their father.
B006C019V048	6	19	48	This is the inheritance of the tribe of the children of Dan according to their families, these cities with their villages.
B006C019V049	6	19	49	When they had finished dividing the land for inheritance according to their borders, the children of Israel gave an inheritance to Joshua the son of Nun among them:
B006C019V050	6	19	50	According to the word of the LORD they gave him the city for which he asked, even Timnathserah in mount Ephraim: and he built the city, and dwelt therein.
B006C019V051	6	19	51	These are the inheritances, which Eleazar the priest, and Joshua the son of Nun, and the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel, divided for an inheritance by lot in Shiloh before the LORD, at the door of the tabernacle of meeting. So they finished dividing the country.
B006C020V001	6	20	1	The LORD also spoke unto Joshua, saying,
B006C020V002	6	20	2	
        
B006C020V003	6	20	3	
        
B006C020V004	6	20	4	
        
B006C020V005	6	20	5	
        
B006C020V006	6	20	6	
        
B006C020V007	6	20	7	And they appointed Kedesh in Galilee in mount Naphtali, and Shechem in mount Ephraim, and Kiriatharba, which is Hebron, in the mountain of Judah.
B006C020V008	6	20	8	And on the other side of Jordan east of Jericho, they assigned Bezer in the wilderness upon the plain out of the tribe of Reuben, and Ramoth in Gilead out of the tribe of Gad, and Golan in Bashan out of the tribe of Manasseh.
B006C020V009	6	20	9	These were the cities appointed for all the children of Israel, and for the stranger that sojourns among them, that whosoever kills any person accidentally might flee there, and not die by the hand of the avenger of blood, until he stood before the congregation.
B006C021V001	6	21	1	Then came near the heads of the fathers of the Levites unto Eleazar the priest, and unto Joshua the son of Nun, and unto the heads of the fathers of the tribes of the children of Israel;
B006C021V002	6	21	2	And they spoke unto them at Shiloh in the land of Canaan, saying, The LORD commanded by the hand of Moses to give us cities to dwell in, with the pasture lands for our cattle.
B006C021V003	6	21	3	And the children of Israel gave unto the Levites out of their inheritance, at the commandment of the LORD, these cities and their pasture lands.
B006C021V004	6	21	4	And the lot came out for the families of the Kohathites: and the children of Aaron the priest, who were of the Levites, had by lot out of the tribe of Judah, and out of the tribe of Simeon, and out of the tribe of Benjamin, thirteen cities.
B006C021V005	6	21	5	And the rest of the children of Kohath had by lot out of the families of the tribe of Ephraim, and out of the tribe of Dan, and out of the half tribe of Manasseh, ten cities.
B006C021V006	6	21	6	And the children of Gershon had by lot out of the families of the tribe of Issachar, and out of the tribe of Asher, and out of the tribe of Naphtali, and out of the half tribe of Manasseh in Bashan, thirteen cities.
B006C021V007	6	21	7	The children of Merari by their families had out of the tribe of Reuben, and out of the tribe of Gad, and out of the tribe of Zebulun, twelve cities.
B006C021V008	6	21	8	And the children of Israel gave by lot unto the Levites these cities with their pasture lands, as the LORD commanded by the hand of Moses.
B006C021V009	6	21	9	And they gave out of the tribe of the children of Judah, and out of the tribe of the children of Simeon, these cities which are here mentioned by name,
B006C021V010	6	21	10	Which the children of Aaron, being of the families of the Kohathites, who were of the children of Levi, had: for theirs was the first lot.
B006C021V011	6	21	11	And they gave them the city of Arba the father of Anak, which city is Hebron, in the hill country of Judah, with the pasture lands round about it.
B006C021V012	6	21	12	But the fields of the city, and its villages, they gave to Caleb the son of Jephunneh for his possession.
B006C021V013	6	21	13	Thus they gave to the children of Aaron the priest Hebron with its pasture lands, to be a city of refuge for the slayer; and Libnah with its pasture lands,
B006C021V014	6	21	14	And Jattir with its pasture lands, and Eshtemoa with its pasture lands,
B006C021V015	6	21	15	And Holon with its pasture lands, and Debir with its pasture lands,
B006C021V016	6	21	16	And Ain with its pasture lands, and Juttah with its pasture lands, and Bethshemesh with its pasture lands; nine cities out of those two tribes.
B006C021V017	6	21	17	And out of the tribe of Benjamin, Gibeon with its pasture lands, Geba with its pasture lands,
B006C021V018	6	21	18	Anathoth with its pasture lands, and Almon with its pasture lands; four cities.
B006C021V019	6	21	19	All the cities of the children of Aaron, the priests, were thirteen cities with their pasture lands.
B006C021V020	6	21	20	And the families of the children of Kohath, the Levites who remained of the children of Kohath, even they had the cities of their lot out of the tribe of Ephraim.
B006C021V021	6	21	21	For they gave them Shechem with its pasture lands in mount Ephraim, to be a city of refuge for the slayer; and Gezer with its pasture lands,
B006C021V022	6	21	22	And Kibzaim with its pasture lands, and Bethhoron with its pasture lands; four cities.
B006C021V023	6	21	23	And out of the tribe of Dan, Eltekeh with its pasture lands, Gibbethon with its pasture lands,
B006C021V024	6	21	24	Aijalon with its pasture lands, Gathrimmon with its pasture lands; four cities.
B006C021V025	6	21	25	And out of the half tribe of Manasseh, Taanach with its pasture lands, and Gathrimmon with its pasture lands; two cities.
B006C021V026	6	21	26	All the cities were ten with their pasture lands for the families of the children of Kohath that remained.
B006C021V027	6	21	27	And unto the children of Gershon, of the families of the Levites, out of the other half tribe of Manasseh they gave Golan in Bashan with its pasture lands, to be a city of refuge for the slayer; and Beeshterah with its pasture lands; two cities.
B006C021V028	6	21	28	And out of the tribe of Issachar, Kishion with its pasture lands, Daberath with its pasture lands,
B006C021V029	6	21	29	Jarmuth with its pasture lands, Engannim with its pasture lands; four cities.
B006C021V030	6	21	30	And out of the tribe of Asher, Mishal with its pasture lands, Abdon with its pasture lands,
B006C021V031	6	21	31	Helkath with its pasture lands, and Rehob with its pasture lands; four cities.
B006C021V032	6	21	32	And out of the tribe of Naphtali, Kedesh in Galilee with its pasture lands, to be a city of refuge for the slayer; and Hammothdor with its pasture lands, and Kartan with its pasture lands; three cities.
B006C021V033	6	21	33	All the cities of the Gershonites according to their families were thirteen cities with their pasture lands.
B006C021V034	6	21	34	And unto the families of the children of Merari, the rest of the Levites, out of the tribe of Zebulun, Jokneam with its pasture lands, and Kartah with its pasture lands,
B006C021V035	6	21	35	Dimnah with its pasture lands, Nahalal with its pasture lands; four cities.
B006C021V036	6	21	36	And out of the tribe of Reuben, Bezer with its pasture lands, and Jahaz with its pasture lands,
B006C021V037	6	21	37	Kedemoth with its pasture lands, and Mephaath with its pasture lands; four cities.
B006C021V038	6	21	38	And out of the tribe of Gad, Ramoth in Gilead with its pasture lands, to be a city of refuge for the slayer; and Mahanaim with its pasture lands,
B006C021V039	6	21	39	Heshbon with its pasture lands, Jazer with its pasture lands; four cities in all.
B006C021V040	6	21	40	So all the cities for the children of Merari by their families, who were remaining of the families of the Levites, were by their lot twelve cities.
B006C021V041	6	21	41	All the cities of the Levites within the possession of the children of Israel were forty and eight cities with their pasture lands.
B006C021V042	6	21	42	These cities were every one with their pasture lands round about them: thus were all these cities.
B006C021V043	6	21	43	And the LORD gave unto Israel all the land which he swore to give unto their fathers; and they possessed it, and dwelt there.
B006C021V044	6	21	44	And the LORD gave them rest round about, according to all that he swore unto their fathers: and there stood not a man of all their enemies before them; the LORD delivered all their enemies into their hand.
B006C021V045	6	21	45	There failed not any of any good thing which the LORD had spoken unto the house of Israel; all came to pass.
B006C022V001	6	22	1	Then Joshua called the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasseh,
B006C022V002	6	22	2	And said unto them, you have kept all that Moses the servant of the LORD commanded you, and have obeyed my voice in all that I commanded you:
B006C022V003	6	22	3	You have not left your brethren these many days unto this day, but have kept the charge of the commandment of the LORD your God.
B006C022V004	6	22	4	And now the LORD your God has given rest unto your brethren, as he promised them: therefore now return, and get you unto your tents, and unto the land of your possession, which Moses the servant of the LORD gave you on the other side of Jordan.
B006C022V005	6	22	5	But take diligent heed to do the commandment and the law, which Moses the servant of the LORD charged you, to love the LORD your God, and to walk in all his ways, and to keep his commandments, and to cleave unto him, and to serve him with all your heart and with all your soul.
B006C022V006	6	22	6	So Joshua blessed them, and sent them away: and they went unto their tents.
B006C022V007	6	22	7	Now to the one half of the tribe of Manasseh Moses had given possession in Bashan: but unto the other half thereof gave Joshua among their brethren on this side of Jordan, westward. And when Joshua sent them away also unto their tents, then he blessed them,
B006C022V008	6	22	8	And he spoke unto them, saying, Return with much riches unto your tents, and with very much cattle, with silver, and with gold, and with bronze, and with iron, and with very much clothing: divide the spoil of your enemies with your brethren.
B006C022V009	6	22	9	And the children of Reuben and the children of Gad and the half tribe of Manasseh returned, and departed from the children of Israel out of Shiloh, which is in the land of Canaan, to go unto the country of Gilead, to the land of their possession, which they had possessed, according to the word of the LORD by the hand of Moses.
B006C022V010	6	22	10	And when they came unto the borders of Jordan, that are in the land of Canaan, the children of Reuben and the children of Gad and the half tribe of Manasseh built there an altar by the Jordan, a great altar to see.
B006C022V011	6	22	11	And the children of Israel were told, Behold, the children of Reuben and the children of Gad and the half tribe of Manasseh have built an altar near the border of the land of Canaan, in the area of the Jordan, on the side of the children of Israel.
B006C022V012	6	22	12	And when the children of Israel heard of it, the whole congregation of the children of Israel gathered themselves together at Shiloh, to go up to war against them.
B006C022V013	6	22	13	And the children of Israel sent unto the children of Reuben, and to the children of Gad, and to the half tribe of Manasseh, into the land of Gilead, Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest,
B006C022V014	6	22	14	And with him ten leaders, of each chief house a leader throughout all the tribes of Israel; and every one was a head of the house of their fathers among the thousands of Israel.
B006C022V015	6	22	15	And they came unto the children of Reuben, and to the children of Gad, and to the half tribe of Manasseh, unto the land of Gilead, and they spoke with them, saying,
B006C022V016	6	22	16	Thus says the whole congregation of the LORD, What trespass is this that you have committed against the God of Israel, to turn away this day from following the LORD, in that you have built you an altar, that you might rebel this day against the LORD?
B006C022V017	6	22	17	Is the iniquity of Peor too little for us, from which we are not cleansed until this day, although there was a plague in the congregation of the LORD,
B006C022V018	6	22	18	But that you must turn away this day from following the LORD? and it will be, seeing you rebel today against the LORD, that tomorrow he will be angry with the whole congregation of Israel.
B006C022V019	6	22	19	Nevertheless, if the land of your possession is unclean, then pass over unto the land of the possession of the LORD, in which the LORD'S tabernacle dwells, and take possession among us: but rebel not against the LORD, nor rebel against us, in building you an altar besides the altar of the LORD our God.
B006C022V020	6	22	20	Did not Achan the son of Zerah commit a trespass in the accursed thing, and wrath fell on all the congregation of Israel? and that man perished not alone in his iniquity.
B006C022V021	6	22	21	Then the children of Reuben and the children of Gad and the half tribe of Manasseh answered, and said unto the heads of the thousands of Israel,
B006C022V022	6	22	22	The LORD God of gods, the LORD God of gods, he knows, and Israel he shall know; if it be in rebellion, or if in transgression against the LORD, (save us not this day,)
B006C022V023	6	22	23	That we have built us an altar to turn from following the LORD, or if to offer thereon burnt offerings or grain offerings, or if to offer peace offerings thereon, let the LORD himself require an account;
B006C022V024	6	22	24	And if we have not rather done it for fear of this thing, saying, In time to come your children might speak unto our children, saying, What have you to do with the LORD God of Israel?
B006C022V025	6	22	25	For the LORD has made the Jordan a border between us and you, you children of Reuben and children of Gad; you have no part in the LORD: so shall your children make our children cease from fearing the LORD.
B006C022V026	6	22	26	Therefore we said, Let us now prepare to build us an altar, not for burnt offering, nor for sacrifice:
B006C022V027	6	22	27	But that it may be a witness between us and you, and our generations after us, that we might do the service of the LORD before him with our burnt offerings, and with our sacrifices, and with our peace offerings; that your children may not say to our children in time to come, you have no part in the LORD.
B006C022V028	6	22	28	Therefore said we, that it shall be, when they should so say to us or to our generations in time to come, that we may say again, Behold the pattern of the altar of the LORD, which our fathers made, not for burnt offerings, nor for sacrifices; but it is a witness between us and you.
B006C022V029	6	22	29	God forbid that we should rebel against the LORD, and turn this day from following the LORD, to build an altar for burnt offerings, for grain offerings, or for sacrifices, besides the altar of the LORD our God that is before his tabernacle.
B006C022V030	6	22	30	And when Phinehas the priest, and the leaders of the congregation and heads of the thousands of Israel who were with him, heard the words that the children of Reuben and the children of Gad and the children of Manasseh spoke, it pleased them.
B006C022V031	6	22	31	And Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest said unto the children of Reuben, and to the children of Gad, and to the children of Manasseh, This day we perceive that the LORD is among us, because you have not committed this trespass against the LORD: now you have delivered the children of Israel out of the hand of the LORD.
B006C022V032	6	22	32	And Phinehas the son of Eleazar the priest, and the leaders, returned from the children of Reuben, and from the children of Gad, out of the land of Gilead, unto the land of Canaan, to the children of Israel, and brought them word again.
B006C022V033	6	22	33	And the thing pleased the children of Israel; and the children of Israel blessed God, and did not intend to go up against them in battle, to destroy the land in which the children of Reuben and Gad dwelt.
B006C022V034	6	22	34	And the children of Reuben and the children of Gad called the altar Ed: for it shall be a witness between us that the LORD is God.
B006C023V001	6	23	1	And it came to pass a long time after the LORD had given rest unto Israel from all their enemies round about, that Joshua grew old and stricken in age.
B006C023V002	6	23	2	And Joshua called for all Israel, and for their elders, and for their heads, and for their judges, and for their officers, and said unto them, I am old and stricken in age:
B006C023V003	6	23	3	And you have seen all that the LORD your God has done unto all these nations because of you; for the LORD your God is he that has fought for you.
B006C023V004	6	23	4	Behold, I have divided unto you by lot these nations that remain, to be an inheritance for your tribes, from the Jordan, with all the nations that I have cut off, even unto the Great Sea westward.
B006C023V005	6	23	5	And the LORD your God, he shall expel them from before you, and drive them from out of your sight; and you shall possess their land, as the LORD your God has promised unto you.
B006C023V006	6	23	6	Be you therefore very courageous to keep and to do all that is written in the book of the law of Moses, that you turn not aside from it to the right hand or to the left;
B006C023V007	6	23	7	That you mix not among these nations, these that remain among you; neither make mention of the name of their gods, nor cause to swear by them, neither serve them, nor bow yourselves unto them:
B006C023V008	6	23	8	But cleave unto the LORD your God, as you have done unto this day.
B006C023V009	6	23	9	For the LORD has driven out from before you great nations and strong: but as for you, no man has been able to stand before you unto this day.
B006C023V010	6	23	10	One man of you shall chase a thousand: for the LORD your God, he it is that fights for you, as he has promised you.
B006C023V011	6	23	11	Take good heed therefore unto yourselves, that you love the LORD your God.
B006C023V012	6	23	12	Else if you do in any way go back, and cleave unto the remnant of these nations, even these that remain among you, and shall make marriages with them, and go in unto them, and they to you:
B006C023V013	6	23	13	Know for a certainty that the LORD your God will no more drive out any of these nations from before you; but they shall be snares and traps unto you, and scourges in your sides, and thorns in your eyes, until you perish from off this good land which the LORD your God has given you.
B006C023V014	6	23	14	And, behold, this day I am going the way of all the earth: and you know in all your hearts and in all your souls, that not one thing has failed of all the good things which the LORD your God spoke concerning you; all are come to pass unto you, and not one thing has failed thereof.
B006C023V015	6	23	15	Therefore it shall come to pass, that as all good things are come upon you, which the LORD your God promised you; so shall the LORD bring upon you all evil things, until he has destroyed you from off this good land which the LORD your God has given you.
B006C023V016	6	23	16	When you have transgressed the covenant of the LORD your God, which he commanded you, and have gone and served other gods, and bowed yourselves to them; then shall the anger of the LORD be kindled against you, and you shall perish quickly from off the good land which he has given unto you.
B006C024V001	6	24	1	And Joshua gathered all the tribes of Israel to Shechem, and called for the elders of Israel, and for their heads, and for their judges, and for their officers; and they presented themselves before God.
B006C024V002	6	24	2	And Joshua said unto all the people, Thus says the LORD God of Israel, 
