B007C015V005	7	15	5	And when he had set the torches on fire, he let them go into the standing grain of the Philistines, and burnt up both the shocks, and also the standing grain, with the vineyards and olives.
B007C015V006	7	15	6	Then the Philistines said, Who has done this? And they answered, Samson, the son-in-law of the Timnite, because he had taken his wife, and given her to his companion. And the Philistines came up, and burnt her and her father with fire.
B007C015V007	7	15	7	And Samson said unto them, Though you have done this, yet will I be avenged of you, and after that I will cease.
