B007C021V001	7	21	1	Now the men of Israel had sworn in Mizpah, saying, There shall not any of us give his daughter unto Benjamin as wife.
B007C021V002	7	21	2	And the people came to the house of God, and abode there till evening before God, and lifted up their voices, and wept greatly;
B007C021V003	7	21	3	And said, O LORD God of Israel, why is this come to pass in Israel, that there should be today one tribe lacking in Israel?
B007C021V004	7	21	4	And it came to pass the next day, that the people rose early, and built there an altar, and offered burnt offerings and peace offerings.
B007C021V005	7	21	5	And the children of Israel said, Who is there among all the tribes of Israel that came not up with the congregation unto the LORD? For they had made a great oath concerning him that came not up to the LORD to Mizpah, saying, He shall surely be put to death.
B007C021V006	7	21	6	And the children of Israel grieved for Benjamin their brother, and said, There is one tribe cut off from Israel this day.
