B008C001V001	8	1	1	Now it came to pass in the days when the judges ruled, that there was a famine in the land. And a certain man of Bethlehemjudah went to sojourn in the country of Moab, he, and his wife, and his two sons.
B008C001V002	8	1	2	And the name of the man was Elimelech, and the name of his wife Naomi, and the name of his two sons Mahlon and Chilion, Ephrathites of Bethlehemjudah. And they came into the country of Moab, and continued there.
B008C001V003	8	1	3	And Elimelech Naomi's husband died; and she was left, and her two sons.
B008C001V004	8	1	4	And they took them wives of the women of Moab; the name of the one was Orpah, and the name of the other Ruth: and they dwelled there about ten years.
B008C001V005	8	1	5	And Mahlon and Chilion died also both of them; and the woman was left without her two sons and her husband.
B008C001V006	8	1	6	Then she arose with her daughters-in-law, that she might return from the country of Moab: for she had heard in the country of Moab how that the Lord had visited his people in giving them food.
B008C001V007	8	1	7	Therefore she went forth out of the place where she was, and her two daughters-in-law with her; and they went on the way to return unto the land of Judah.
B008C001V008	8	1	8	And Naomi said unto her two daughters-in-law, Go, return each of you to her mother's house: the LORD deal kindly with you, as you have dealt with the dead, and with me.
B008C001V009	8	1	9	The LORD grant you that you may find rest, each of you in the house of her husband. Then she kissed them; and they lifted up their voices, and wept.
B008C001V010	8	1	10	And they said unto her, Surely we will return with you unto your people.
B008C001V011	8	1	11	And Naomi said, Turn again, my daughters: why will you go with me? are there yet any more sons in my womb, that they may be your husbands?
B008C001V012	8	1	12	Turn again, my daughters, go your way; for I am too old to have a husband. If I should say, I have hope, if I should have a husband also tonight, and should also bear sons;
B008C001V013	8	1	13	Would you tarry for them till they were grown? would you refrain from having husbands? nay, my daughters; for it grieves me much for your sakes that the hand of the LORD has gone out against me.
B008C001V014	8	1	14	And they lifted up their voices, and wept again: and Orpah kissed her mother-in-law; but Ruth clung to her.
B008C001V015	8	1	15	And she said, Behold, your sister-in-law has gone back unto her people, and unto her gods: return you after your sister-in-law.
B008C001V016	8	1	16	And Ruth said, Entreat me not to leave you, or to return from following after you: for where you go, I will go; and where you lodge, I will lodge: your people shall be my people, and your God my God:
B008C001V017	8	1	17	Where you die, will I die, and there will I be buried: the LORD do so to me, and more also, if anything but death parts you and me.
B008C001V018	8	1	18	When she saw that she was steadfastly minded to go with her, then she ceased speaking unto her.
B008C001V019	8	1	19	So they two went until they came to Bethlehem. And it came to pass, when they were come to Bethlehem, that all the city was stirred because of them, and they said, Is this Naomi?
B008C001V020	8	1	20	And she said unto them, Call me not Naomi, call me Mara: for the Almighty has dealt very bitterly with me.
B008C001V021	8	1	21	I went out full, and the LORD has brought me home again empty: why then call you me Naomi, seeing the LORD has testified against me, and the Almighty has afflicted me?
B008C001V022	8	1	22	So Naomi returned, and Ruth the Moabitess, her daughter-in-law, with her, who returned out of the country of Moab: and they came to Bethlehem in the beginning of barley harvest.
B008C002V001	8	2	1	And Naomi had a kinsman of her husband's, a mighty man of wealth, of the family of Elimelech; and his name was Boaz.
B008C002V002	8	2	2	And Ruth the Moabitess said unto Naomi, Let me now go to the field, and glean ears of grain after him in whose sight I shall find grace. And she said unto her, Go, my daughter.
B008C002V003	8	2	3	And she went, and came, and gleaned in the field after the reapers: and she happened to come to a part of the field belonging unto Boaz, who was of the kindred of Elimelech.
B008C002V004	8	2	4	And, behold, Boaz came from Bethlehem, and said unto the reapers, The LORD be with you. And they answered him, The LORD bless you.
B008C002V005	8	2	5	Then said Boaz unto his servant that was set over the reapers, Whose young woman is this?
B008C002V006	8	2	6	And the servant that was set over the reapers answered and said, It is the Moabite young woman that came back with Naomi out of the country of Moab:
B008C002V007	8	2	7	And she said, I pray you, let me glean and gather after the reapers among the sheaves: so she came, and has continued even from the morning until now, except that she tarried a little in the house.
B008C002V008	8	2	8	Then said Boaz unto Ruth, Will you not hear, my daughter? Go not to glean in another field, neither go from here, but abide here close by my maidens:
B008C002V009	8	2	9	Let your eyes be on the field that they do reap, and go after them: have I not charged the young men that they shall not touch you? and when you are thirsty, go unto the vessels, and drink of that which the young men have drawn.
B008C002V010	8	2	10	Then she fell on her face, and bowed herself to the ground, and said unto him, Why have I found grace in your eyes, that you should take knowledge of me, seeing I am a stranger?
B008C002V011	8	2	11	And Boaz answered and said unto her, It has fully been shown me, all that you have done unto your mother-in-law since the death of your husband: and how you have left your father and your mother, and the land of your birth, and are come unto a people which you knew not before.
B008C002V012	8	2	12	The LORD recompense your work, and a full reward be given you of the LORD God of Israel, under whose wings you have come to trust.
B008C002V013	8	2	13	Then she said, Let me find favor in your sight, my lord; for you have comforted me, and you have spoken kindly unto your handmaid, though I be not like unto one of your handmaidens.
B008C002V014	8	2	14	And Boaz said unto her, At mealtime come here, and eat of the bread, and dip your morsel in the vinegar. And she sat beside the reapers: and he passed to her parched grain, and she did eat, and was satisfied, and left.
B008C002V015	8	2	15	And when she rose up to glean, Boaz commanded his young men, saying, Let her glean even among the sheaves, and reproach her not:
B008C002V016	8	2	16	And let fall also some of the handfuls on purpose for her, and leave them, that she may glean them, and rebuke her not.
B008C002V017	8	2	17	So she gleaned in the field until evening, and beat out what she had gleaned: and it was about an ephah of barley.
B008C002V018	8	2	18	And she took it up, and went into the city: and her mother-in-law saw what she had gleaned: and she brought forth, and gave to her what she had reserved after she was satisfied.
B008C002V019	8	2	19	And her mother-in-law said unto her, Where have you gleaned today? and where did you work? blessed be he that did take knowledge of you. And she showed her mother-in-law with whom she had worked, and said, The man's name with whom I worked today is Boaz.
B008C002V020	8	2	20	And Naomi said unto her daughter-in-law, Blessed be he of the LORD, who has not left off his kindness to the living and to the dead. And Naomi said unto her, The man is near of kin unto us, one of our closest kinsmen.
B008C002V021	8	2	21	And Ruth the Moabitess said, He said unto me also, You shall keep near by my young men, until they have ended all my harvest.
B008C002V022	8	2	22	And Naomi said unto Ruth her daughter-in-law, It is good, my daughter, that you go out with his maidens, that they encounter you not in any other field.
B008C002V023	8	2	23	So she kept close by the maidens of Boaz to glean unto the end of barley harvest and of wheat harvest; and dwelt with her mother-in-law.
B008C003V001	8	3	1	Then Naomi her mother-in-law said unto her, My daughter, shall I not seek rest for you, that it may be well with you?
B008C003V002	8	3	2	And now is not Boaz of our kindred, with whose maidens you were? Behold, he winnows barley tonight in the threshingfloor.
B008C003V003	8	3	3	Wash yourself therefore, and anoint yourself, and put your best clothes upon you, and get down to the floor: but make not yourself known unto the man, until he shall have finished eating and drinking.
B008C003V004	8	3	4	And it shall be, when he lies down, that you shall mark the place where he shall lie, and you shall go in, and uncover his feet, and lay down; and he will tell you what you shall do.
B008C003V005	8	3	5	And she said unto her, All that you say unto me I will do.
B008C003V006	8	3	6	And she went down unto the floor, and did according to all that her mother-in-law bade her.
B008C003V007	8	3	7	And when Boaz had eaten and drunk, and his heart was merry, he went to lie down at the end of the heap of grain: and she came softly, and uncovered his feet, and laid herself down.
B008C003V008	8	3	8	And it came to pass at midnight, that the man was startled, and turned himself: and, behold, a woman lay at his feet.
B008C003V009	8	3	9	And he said, Who are you? And she answered, I am Ruth your handmaid: spread therefore your skirt over your handmaid; for you are a near kinsman.
B008C003V010	8	3	10	And he said, Blessed be you of the LORD, my daughter: for you have showed more kindness in the latter end than at the beginning, in that you followed not young men, whether poor or rich.
B008C003V011	8	3	11	And now, my daughter, fear not; I will do to you all that you require: for all the city of my people does know that you are a virtuous woman.
B008C003V012	8	3	12	And now it is true that I am your near kinsman: however there is a kinsman nearer than I.
B008C003V013	8	3	13	Tarry this night, and it shall be in the morning, that if he will perform unto you the part of a kinsman, well; let him do the kinsman's part: but if he will not do the part of a kinsman to you, then will I do the part of a kinsman to you, as the LORD lives: lie down until the morning.
B008C003V014	8	3	14	And she lay at his feet until the morning: and she rose up before one could recognize another. And he said, Let it not be known that a woman came into the floor.
B008C003V015	8	3	15	Also he said, Bring the cloak that you have upon you, and hold it. And when she held it, he measured six measures of barley, and laid it on her: and she went into the city.
B008C003V016	8	3	16	And when she came to her mother-in-law, she said, How are you, my daughter? And she told her all that the man had done to her.
B008C003V017	8	3	17	And she said, These six measures of barley he gave me; for he said to me, Go not empty unto your mother-in-law.
B008C003V018	8	3	18	Then said she, Sit still, my daughter, until you know how the matter will fall: for the man will not rest, until he has finished the thing this day.
B008C004V001	8	4	1	Then went Boaz up to the gate, and sat down there: and, behold, the kinsman of whom Boaz spoke came by; unto whom he said, Ho, such a one! turn aside, sit down here. And he turned aside, and sat down.
B008C004V002	8	4	2	And he took ten men of the elders of the city, and said, Sit down here. And they sat down.
B008C004V003	8	4	3	And he said unto the kinsman, Naomi, that is come again out of the country of Moab, sells a parcel of land, which was our brother Elimelech's:
B008C004V004	8	4	4	And I thought to advise you, saying, Buy it before the inhabitants, and before the elders of my people. If you will redeem it, redeem it: but if you will not redeem it, then tell me, that I may know: for there is none to redeem it besides you; and I am after you. And he said, I will redeem it.
B008C004V005	8	4	5	Then said Boaz, The day you buy the field of the hand of Naomi, you must buy it also from Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of the dead, to raise up the name of the dead through his inheritance.
B008C004V006	8	4	6	And the kinsman said, I cannot redeem it for myself, lest I mar my own inheritance: redeem you my right to yourself; for I cannot redeem it.
B008C004V007	8	4	7	Now this was the manner in former time in Israel concerning redeeming and concerning exchanging, for to confirm all things; a man took off his shoe, and gave it to his neighbor: and this was a testimony in Israel.
B008C004V008	8	4	8	Therefore the kinsman said unto Boaz, Buy it for yourself. So he took off his shoe.
B008C004V009	8	4	9	And Boaz said unto the elders, and unto all the people, You are witnesses this day, that I have bought all that was Elimelech's, and all that was Chilion's and Mahlon's, of the hand of Naomi.
B008C004V010	8	4	10	Moreover Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of Mahlon, have I purchased to be my wife, to raise up the name of the dead through his inheritance, that the name of the dead be not cut off from among his brethren, and from the gate of this place: you are witnesses this day.
B008C004V011	8	4	11	And all the people that were at the gate, and the elders, said, We are witnesses. The LORD make the woman that is come into your house like Rachel and like Leah, which two did build the house of Israel: and may you do worthily in Ephrathah, and be famous in Bethlehem:
B008C004V012	8	4	12	And let your house be like the house of Perez, whom Tamar bore unto Judah, of the children which the LORD shall give you of this young woman.
B008C004V013	8	4	13	So Boaz took Ruth, and she was his wife: and when he went in unto her, the LORD gave her conception, and she bore a son.
B008C004V014	8	4	14	And the women said unto Naomi, Blessed be the LORD, who has not left you this day without a kinsman, that his name may be famous in Israel.
B008C004V015	8	4	15	And he shall be unto you a restorer of your life, and a nourisher of your old age: for your daughter-in-law, who loves you, who is better to you than seven sons, has borne him.
B008C004V016	8	4	16	And Naomi took the child, and laid it in her bosom, and became nurse unto it.
B008C004V017	8	4	17	And the women her neighbors gave it a name, saying, There is a son born to Naomi; and they called his name Obed: he is the father of Jesse, the father of David.
B008C004V018	8	4	18	Now these are the generations of Perez: Perez begat Hezron,
B008C004V019	8	4	19	And Hezron begat Ram, and Ram begat Amminadab,
B008C004V020	8	4	20	And Amminadab begat Nahshon, and Nahshon begat Salmon,
B008C004V021	8	4	21	And Salmon begat Boaz, and Boaz begat Obed,
B008C004V022	8	4	22	And Obed begat Jesse, and Jesse begat David.
B009C001V001	9	1	1	Now there was a certain man of Ramathaimzophim, of mount Ephraim, and his name was Elkanah, the son of Jeroham, the son of Elihu, the son of Tohu, the son of Zuph, an Ephraimite:
B009C001V002	9	1	2	And he had two wives; the name of the one was Hannah, and the name of the other Peninnah: and Peninnah had children, but Hannah had no children.
B009C001V003	9	1	3	And this man went up out of his city yearly to worship and to sacrifice unto the LORD of hosts in Shiloh. And the two sons of Eli, Hophni and Phinehas, the priests of the LORD, were there.
B009C001V004	9	1	4	And when the time was that Elkanah offered, he gave to Peninnah his wife, and to all her sons and her daughters, portions:
B009C001V005	9	1	5	But unto Hannah he gave a worthy portion; for he loved Hannah: but the LORD had shut up her womb.
B009C001V006	9	1	6	And her adversary also provoked her severely to make her fret, because the LORD had shut up her womb.
B009C001V007	9	1	7	And as year by year, when she went up to the house of the LORD, so she provoked her; therefore she wept, and did not eat.
B009C001V008	9	1	8	Then said Elkanah her husband to her, Hannah, why weep you? and why eat you not? and why is your heart grieved? am not I better to you than ten sons?
B009C001V009	9	1	9	So Hannah rose up after they had eaten in Shiloh, and after they had drunk. Now Eli the priest sat upon a seat by a door post of the temple of the LORD.
B009C001V010	9	1	10	And she was in bitterness of soul, and prayed unto the LORD, and wept bitterly.
B009C001V011	9	1	11	And she vowed a vow, and said, O LORD of hosts, if you will indeed look on the affliction of your handmaid, and remember me, and not forget your handmaid, but will give unto your handmaid a male child, then I will give him unto the LORD all the days of his life, and there shall no razor come upon his head.
B009C001V012	9	1	12	And it came to pass, as she continued praying before the LORD, that Eli observed her mouth.
B009C001V013	9	1	13	Now Hannah spoke in her heart; only her lips moved, but her voice was not heard: therefore Eli thought she had been drunk.
B009C001V014	9	1	14	And Eli said unto her, How long will you be drunk? put away your wine from you.
B009C001V015	9	1	15	And Hannah answered and said, No, my lord, I am a woman of a sorrowful spirit: I have drunk neither wine nor strong drink, but have poured out my soul before the LORD.
B009C001V016	9	1	16	Count not your handmaid for a daughter of Belial: for out of the abundance of my complaint and grief have I been speaking.
B009C001V017	9	1	17	Then Eli answered and said, Go in peace: and the God of Israel grant you your petition that you have asked of him.
B009C001V018	9	1	18	And she said, Let your handmaid find grace in your sight. So the woman went her way, and did eat, and her countenance was no more sad.
B009C001V019	9	1	19	And they rose up in the morning early, and worshiped before the LORD, and returned, and came to their house to Ramah: and Elkanah knew Hannah his wife; and the LORD remembered her.
B009C001V020	9	1	20	Therefore it came to pass, when the time was come about after Hannah had conceived, that she bore a son, and called his name Samuel, saying, Because I have asked him of the LORD.
B009C001V021	9	1	21	And the man Elkanah, and all his house, went up to offer unto the LORD the yearly sacrifice, and his vow.
B009C001V022	9	1	22	But Hannah went not up; for she said unto her husband, I will not go up until the child is weaned, and then I will bring him, that he may appear before the LORD, and there abide forever.
B009C001V023	9	1	23	And Elkanah her husband said unto her, Do what seems to you good; tarry until you have weaned him; only the LORD establish his word. So the woman abode, and nursed her son until she weaned him.
B009C001V024	9	1	24	And when she had weaned him, she took him up with her, with three bullocks, and one ephah of flour, and a skin of wine, and brought him unto the house of the LORD in Shiloh: and the child was young.
B009C001V025	9	1	25	And they slew a bullock, and brought the child to Eli.
B009C001V026	9	1	26	And she said, Oh my lord, as your soul lives, my lord, I am the woman that stood by you here, praying unto the LORD.
B009C001V027	9	1	27	For this child I prayed; and the LORD has given me my petition which I asked of him:
B009C001V028	9	1	28	Therefore also I have lent him to the LORD; as long as he lives he shall be lent to the LORD. And he worshiped the LORD there.
B009C002V001	9	2	1	And Hannah prayed, and said, My heart rejoices in the LORD, my horn is exalted in the LORD: my mouth boasts over my enemies; because I rejoice in your salvation.
B009C002V002	9	2	2	There is none holy as the LORD: for there is none beside you: neither is there any rock like our God.
B009C002V003	9	2	3	Talk no more so very proudly; let not arrogance come out of your mouth: for the LORD is a God of knowledge, and by him actions are weighed.
B009C002V004	9	2	4	The bows of the mighty men are broken, and they that stumbled are clothed with strength.
B009C002V005	9	2	5	They that were full have hired out themselves for bread; and they that were hungry ceased to hunger: so that the barren has borne seven; and she that has many children has grown feeble.
B009C002V006	9	2	6	The LORD kills, and makes alive: he brings down to the grave, and brings up.
B009C002V007	9	2	7	The LORD makes poor, and makes rich: he brings low, and lifts up.
B009C002V008	9	2	8	He raises up the poor out of the dust, and lifts up the beggar from the rubbish, to set them among princes, and to make them inherit the throne of glory: for the pillars of the earth are the LORD's, and he has set the world upon them.
B009C002V009	9	2	9	He will keep the feet of his saints, and the wicked shall be silent in darkness; for by strength shall no man prevail.
B009C002V010	9	2	10	The adversaries of the LORD shall be broken to pieces; out of heaven shall he thunder upon them: the LORD shall judge the ends of the earth; and he shall give strength unto his king, and exalt the horn of his anointed.
B009C002V011	9	2	11	And Elkanah went to Ramah to his house. And the child did minister unto the LORD before Eli the priest.
B009C002V012	9	2	12	Now the sons of Eli were sons of Belial; they knew not the LORD.
B009C002V013	9	2	13	And the priests' custom with the people was, that, when any man offered sacrifice, the priest's servant came, while the flesh was boiling, with a fleshhook of three teeth in his hand;
B009C002V014	9	2	14	And he thrust it into the pan, or kettle, or caldron, or pot; all that the fleshhook brought up the priest took for himself. So they did in Shiloh, unto all the Israelites that came there.
B009C002V015	9	2	15	Also before they burned the fat, the priest's servant came, and said to the man that sacrificed, Give meat to roast for the priest; for he will not have boiled meat from you, but raw.
B009C002V016	9	2	16	And if any man said unto him, Let them not fail to burn the fat first, and then take as much as your soul desires; then he would answer him, Nay; but you shall give it to me now: and if not, I will take it by force.
