B009C002V018	9	2	18	But Samuel ministered before the LORD, being a child, girded with a linen ephod.
B009C002V019	9	2	19	Moreover his mother made him a little coat, and brought it to him from year to year, when she came up with her husband to offer the yearly sacrifice.
B009C002V020	9	2	20	And Eli blessed Elkanah and his wife, and said, The LORD give you offspring of this woman for the loan which is lent to the LORD. And they went unto their own home.
B009C002V021	9	2	21	And the LORD visited Hannah, so that she conceived, and bore three sons and two daughters. And the child Samuel grew before the LORD.
B009C002V022	9	2	22	Now Eli was very old, and heard all that his sons did unto all Israel; and how they lay with the women that assembled at the door of the tabernacle of meeting.
B009C002V023	9	2	23	And he said unto them, Why do you such things? for I hear of your evil dealings by all these people.
B009C002V024	9	2	24	Nay, my sons; for it is no good report that I hear: you make the LORD's people to transgress.
