B009C003V001	9	3	1	And the child Samuel ministered unto the LORD before Eli. And the word of the LORD was rare in those days; there was no open vision.
B009C003V002	9	3	2	And it came to pass at that time, when Eli was lying down in his place, and his eyes had begun to grow dim, that he could not see;
B009C003V003	9	3	3	And before the lamp of God went out in the temple of the LORD, where the ark of God was, and Samuel was lying down to sleep;
B009C003V004	9	3	4	That the LORD called, 
B009C003V005	9	3	5	And he ran unto Eli, and said, Here am I; for you called me. And he said, I called not; lie down again. And he went and lay down.
B009C003V006	9	3	6	And the LORD called yet again, 
B009C003V007	9	3	7	Now Samuel did not yet know the LORD, neither was the word of the LORD yet revealed unto him.
B009C003V008	9	3	8	And the LORD called Samuel again the third time. And he arose and went to Eli, and said, Here am I; for you did call me. And Eli perceived that the LORD had called the child.
B009C003V009	9	3	9	Therefore Eli said unto Samuel, Go, lie down: and it shall be, if he calls you, that you shall say, Speak, LORD; for your servant hears. So Samuel went and lay down in his place.
B009C003V010	9	3	10	And the LORD came, and stood, and called as at other times, 
