B010C022V001	10	22	1	And David spoke unto the LORD the words of this song in the day that the LORD had delivered him out of the hand of all his enemies, and out of the hand of Saul:
B010C022V002	10	22	2	And he said, The LORD is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer;
B010C022V003	10	22	3	The God of my rock; in him will I trust: he is my shield, and the horn of my salvation, my high tower, and my refuge, my savior; you save me from violence.
B010C022V004	10	22	4	I will call on the LORD, who is worthy to be praised: so shall I be saved from my enemies.
B010C022V005	10	22	5	When the waves of death surrounded me, the floods of ungodly men made me afraid;
B010C022V006	10	22	6	The sorrows of Sheol surrounded me; the snares of death confronted me;
B010C022V007	10	22	7	In my distress I called upon the LORD, and cried to my God: and he did hear my voice out of his temple, and my cry did enter into his ears.
B010C022V008	10	22	8	Then the earth shook and trembled; the foundations of heaven moved and shook, because he was angry.
