B010C022V015	10	22	15	And he sent out arrows, and scattered them; lightning, and vanquished them.
B010C022V016	10	22	16	And the channels of the sea appeared, the foundations of the world were discovered, at the rebuking of the LORD, at the blast of the breath of his nostrils.
B010C022V017	10	22	17	He sent from above, he took me; he drew me out of many waters;
B010C022V018	10	22	18	He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them that hated me: for they were too strong for me.
B010C022V019	10	22	19	They confronted me in the day of my calamity: but the LORD was my stay.
B010C022V020	10	22	20	He brought me forth also into a broad place: he delivered me, because he delighted in me.
B010C022V021	10	22	21	The LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness: according to the cleanness of my hands has he recompensed me.
B010C022V022	10	22	22	For I have kept the ways of the LORD, and have not wickedly departed from my God.
B010C022V023	10	22	23	For all his judgments were before me: and as for his statutes, I did not depart from them.
B010C022V024	10	22	24	I was also upright before him, and have kept myself from my iniquity.
B010C022V025	10	22	25	Therefore the LORD has recompensed me according to my righteousness; according to my cleanness in his eyesight.
B010C022V026	10	22	26	With the merciful you will show yourself merciful, and with the upright man you will show yourself upright.
B010C022V027	10	22	27	With the pure you will show yourself pure; and with the devious you will show yourself shrewd.
B010C022V028	10	22	28	And the afflicted people you will save: but your eyes are upon the haughty, that you may bring them down.
B010C022V029	10	22	29	For you are my lamp, O LORD: and the LORD will enlighten my darkness.
B010C022V030	10	22	30	For by you I can run against a troop: by my God have I leaped over a wall.
B010C022V031	10	22	31	As for God, his way is perfect; the word of the LORD is proven: he is a buckler to all them that trust in him.
B010C022V032	10	22	32	For who is God, except the LORD? and who is a rock, except our God?
B010C022V033	10	22	33	God is my strength and power: and he makes my way perfect.
B010C022V034	10	22	34	He makes my feet like hindsâ€™ feet: and sets me upon my high places.
B010C022V035	10	22	35	He teaches my hands to make war; so that a bow of steel is broken by my arms.
B010C022V036	10	22	36	You have also given me the shield of your salvation: and your gentleness has made me great.
B010C022V037	10	22	37	You have enlarged my path under me; so that my feet did not slip.
B010C022V038	10	22	38	I have pursued my enemies, and destroyed them; and turned not again until I had consumed them.
B010C022V039	10	22	39	And I have consumed them, and wounded them, that they could not arise: yea, they are fallen under my feet.
B010C022V040	10	22	40	For you have girded me with strength to battle: them that rose up against me have you subdued under me.
B010C022V041	10	22	41	You have also given me the necks of my enemies, that I might destroy them that hate me.
B010C022V042	10	22	42	They looked, but there was none to save; even unto the LORD, but he answered them not.
B010C022V043	10	22	43	Then did I beat them as small as the dust of the earth, I did stamp them as the mire of the street, and did spread them abroad.
B010C022V044	10	22	44	You also have delivered me from the strivings of my people, you have kept me to be head of the nations: a people whom I knew not shall serve me.
B010C022V045	10	22	45	Strangers shall submit themselves unto me: as soon as they hear, they shall be obedient unto me.
B010C022V046	10	22	46	Strangers shall fade away, and they shall be afraid coming out of their hiding places.
B010C022V047	10	22	47	The LORD lives; and blessed be my rock; and exalted be God, the rock of my salvation.
B010C022V048	10	22	48	It is God that avenges me, and that brings down the people under me,
B010C022V049	10	22	49	And that brings me forth from my enemies: you also have lifted me up on high above them that rose up against me: you have delivered me from the violent man.
B010C022V050	10	22	50	Therefore I will give thanks unto you, O LORD, among the nations, and I will sing praises unto your name.
