B011C001V022	11	1	22	And, lo, while she yet talked with the king, Nathan the prophet also came in.
B011C001V023	11	1	23	And they told the king, saying, Behold Nathan the prophet. And when he was come in before the king, he bowed himself before the king with his face to the ground.
B011C001V024	11	1	24	And Nathan said, My lord, O king, have you said, Adonijah shall reign after me, and he shall sit upon my throne?
B011C001V025	11	1	25	For he has gone down this day, and has slain oxen and fatlings and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the kingâ€™s sons, and the captains of the army, and Abiathar the priest; and, behold, they eat and drink before him, and say, God save king Adonijah.
B011C001V026	11	1	26	But me, even me your servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and your servant Solomon, has he not invited.
B011C001V027	11	1	27	Is this thing done by my lord the king, and you have not showed it unto your servant, who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after him?
B011C001V028	11	1	28	Then king David answered and said, Call me Bath-sheba. And she came into the kingâ€™s presence, and stood before the king.
