B011C007V026	11	7	26	And it was a handbreadth thick, and the brim thereof was shaped like the brim of a cup, with flowers of lilies: it contained two thousand baths.
B011C007V027	11	7	27	And he made ten stands of bronze; four cubits was the length of one stand, and four cubits the breadth thereof, and three cubits the height of it.
B011C007V028	11	7	28	And the work of the stands was on this manner: they had panels, and the panels were between the frames:
B011C007V029	11	7	29	And on the panels that were between the frames were lions, oxen, and cherubim: and upon the frames there was a pedestal above: and beneath the lions and oxen were wreaths made of hammered work.
