B013C001V015	13	1	15	And the Hivite, and the Arkite, and the Sinite,
B013C001V016	13	1	16	And the Arvadite, and the Zemarite, and the Hamathite.
B013C001V017	13	1	17	The sons of Shem; Elam, and Asshur, and Arpachshad, and Lud, and Aram, and Uz, and Hul, and Gether, and Meshech.
B013C001V018	13	1	18	And Arpachshad begat Shelah, and Shelah begat Eber.
B013C001V019	13	1	19	And unto Eber were born two sons: the name of the one was Peleg; because in his days the earth was divided: and his brotherâ€™s name was Joktan.
B013C001V020	13	1	20	And Joktan begat Almodad, and Sheleph, and Hazarmaveth, and Jerah,
B013C001V021	13	1	21	Hadoram also, and Uzal, and Diklah,
B013C001V022	13	1	22	And Ebal, and Abimael, and Sheba,
B013C001V023	13	1	23	And Ophir, and Havilah, and Jobab. All these were the sons of Joktan.
B013C001V024	13	1	24	Shem, Arpachshad, Shelah,
B013C001V025	13	1	25	Eber, Peleg, Reu,
B013C001V026	13	1	26	Serug, Nahor, Terah,
B013C001V027	13	1	27	Abram; the same is Abraham.
B013C001V028	13	1	28	The sons of Abraham; Isaac, and Ishmael.
B013C001V029	13	1	29	These are their generations: The firstborn of Ishmael, Nebaioth; then Kedar, and Adbeel, and Mibsam,
B013C001V030	13	1	30	Mishma, and Dumah, Massa, Hadad, and Tema,
B013C001V031	13	1	31	Jetur, Naphish, and Kedemah. These are the sons of Ishmael.
B013C001V032	13	1	32	Now the sons of Keturah, Abrahamâ€™s concubine: she bore Zimran, and Jokshan, and Medan, and Midian, and Ishbak, and Shuah. And the sons of Jokshan; Sheba, and Dedan.
B013C001V033	13	1	33	And the sons of Midian; Ephah, and Epher, and Hanoch, and Abida, and Eldaah. All these are the sons of Keturah.
B013C001V034	13	1	34	And Abraham begat Isaac. The sons of Isaac; Esau and Israel.
B013C001V035	13	1	35	The sons of Esau; Eliphaz, Reuel, and Jeush, and Jalam, and Korah.
B013C001V036	13	1	36	The sons of Eliphaz; Teman, and Omar, Zephi, and Gatam, Kenaz, and Timna, and Amalek.
B013C001V037	13	1	37	The sons of Reuel; Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah.
B013C001V038	13	1	38	And the sons of Seir; Lotan, and Shobal, and Zibeon, and Anah, and Dishon, and Ezer, and Dishan.
B013C001V039	13	1	39	And the sons of Lotan; Hori, and Homam: and Timna was Lotanâ€™s sister.
B013C001V040	13	1	40	The sons of Shobal; Alian, and Manahath, and Ebal, Shephi, and Onam. And the sons of Zibeon; Aiah, and Anah.
B013C001V041	13	1	41	The sons of Anah; Dishon. And the sons of Dishon; Hamran, and Eshban, and Ithran, and Cheran.
B013C001V042	13	1	42	The sons of Ezer; Bilhan, and Zavan, and Jaakan. The sons of Dishan; Uz, and Aran.
B013C001V043	13	1	43	Now these are the kings that reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the children of Israel; Bela the son of Beor: and the name of his city was Dinhabah.
B013C001V044	13	1	44	And when Bela was dead, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his stead.
B013C001V045	13	1	45	And when Jobab was dead, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his stead.
B013C001V046	13	1	46	And when Husham was dead, Hadad the son of Bedad, who defeated Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Avith.
B013C001V047	13	1	47	And when Hadad was dead, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his stead.
B013C001V048	13	1	48	And when Samlah was dead, Shaul of Rehoboth by the river reigned in his stead.
B013C001V049	13	1	49	And when Shaul was dead, Baal-hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his stead.
B013C001V050	13	1	50	And when Baal-hanan was dead, Hadad reigned in his stead: and the name of his city was Pai; and his wifeâ€™s name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab.
B013C001V051	13	1	51	Hadad died also. And the chiefs of Edom were; chief Timnah, chief Aliah, chief Jetheth,
B013C001V052	13	1	52	Chief Oholibamah, chief Elah, chief Pinon,
B013C001V053	13	1	53	Chief Kenaz, chief Teman, chief Mibzar,
B013C001V054	13	1	54	Chief Magdiel, chief Iram. These are the chiefs of Edom.
B013C002V001	13	2	1	These are the sons of Israel; Reuben, Simeon, Levi, and Judah, Issachar, and Zebulun,
B013C002V002	13	2	2	Dan, Joseph, and Benjamin, Naphtali, Gad, and Asher.
B013C002V003	13	2	3	The sons of Judah; Er, and Onan, and Shelah: which three were born unto him of the daughter of Shua the Canaanitess. And Er, the firstborn of Judah, was evil in the sight of the LORD; and he slew him.
B013C002V004	13	2	4	And Tamar his daughter-in-law bore him Perez and Zerah. All the sons of Judah were five.
B013C002V005	13	2	5	The sons of Perez; Hezron, and Hamul.
B013C002V006	13	2	6	And the sons of Zerah; Zimri, and Ethan, and Heman, and Calcol, and Dara: five of them in all.
B013C002V007	13	2	7	And the sons of Carmi; Achar, the troubler of Israel, who transgressed in the devoted thing.
B013C002V008	13	2	8	And the sons of Ethan; Azariah.
B013C002V009	13	2	9	The sons also of Hezron, that were born unto him; Jerahmeel, and Ram, and Chelubai.
B013C002V010	13	2	10	And Ram begat Amminadab; and Amminadab begat Nahshon, prince of the children of Judah;
B013C002V011	13	2	11	And Nahshon begat Salma, and Salma begat Boaz,
B013C002V012	13	2	12	And Boaz begat Obed, and Obed begat Jesse.
B013C002V013	13	2	13	And Jesse begat his firstborn Eliab, and Abinadab the second, and Shimea the third,
B013C002V014	13	2	14	Nethanel the fourth, Raddai the fifth.
B013C002V015	13	2	15	Ozem the sixth, David the seventh:
B013C002V016	13	2	16	Whose sisters were Zeruiah, and Abigail. And the sons of Zeruiah; Abishai, and Joab, and Asahel, three.
B013C002V017	13	2	17	And Abigail bore Amasa: and the father of Amasa was Jether the Ishmaelite.
B013C002V018	13	2	18	And Caleb the son of Hezron begat children of Azubah his wife, and of Jerioth: her sons are these; Jesher, and Shobab, and Ardon.
B013C002V019	13	2	19	And when Azubah was dead, Caleb took unto him Ephrath, who bore him Hur.
B013C002V020	13	2	20	And Hur begat Uri, and Uri begat Bezalel.
B013C002V021	13	2	21	And afterward Hezron went in to the daughter of Machir the father of Gilead, whom he married when he was threescore years old; and she bore him Segub.
B013C002V022	13	2	22	And Segub begat Jair, who had three and twenty cities in the land of Gilead.
B013C002V023	13	2	23	And Geshur and Aram took the towns of Jair from them, with Kenath, and its villages, even threescore towns. All these belonged to the sons of Machir the father of Gilead.
B013C002V024	13	2	24	And after Hezron was dead in Caleb-ephratah, then Abiah Hezronâ€™s wife bore him Ashur the father of Tekoa.
B013C002V025	13	2	25	And the sons of Jerahmeel the firstborn of Hezron were, Ram the firstborn, and Bunah, and Oren, and Ozem, and Ahijah.
B013C002V026	13	2	26	Jerahmeel had also another wife, whose name was Atarah; she was the mother of Onam.
B013C002V027	13	2	27	And the sons of Ram the firstborn of Jerahmeel were, Maaz, and Jamin, and Eker.
B013C002V028	13	2	28	And the sons of Onam were, Shammai, and Jada. And the sons of Shammai; Nadab, and Abishur.
B013C002V029	13	2	29	And the name of the wife of Abishur was Abihail, and she bore him Ahban, and Molid.
B013C002V030	13	2	30	And the sons of Nadab; Seled, and Appaim: but Seled died without children.
B013C002V031	13	2	31	And the sons of Appaim; Ishi. And the sons of Ishi; Sheshan. And the children of Sheshan; Ahlai.
B013C002V032	13	2	32	And the sons of Jada the brother of Shammai; Jether, and Jonathan: and Jether died without children.
B013C002V033	13	2	33	And the sons of Jonathan; Peleth, and Zaza. These were the sons of Jerahmeel.
B013C002V034	13	2	34	Now Sheshan had no sons, but daughters. And Sheshan had a servant, an Egyptian, whose name was Jarha.
B013C002V035	13	2	35	And Sheshan gave his daughter to Jarha his servant as his wife; and she bore him Attai.
B013C002V036	13	2	36	And Attai begat Nathan, and Nathan begat Zabad,
B013C002V037	13	2	37	And Zabad begat Ephlal, and Ephlal begat Obed,
B013C002V038	13	2	38	And Obed begat Jehu, and Jehu begat Azariah,
B013C002V039	13	2	39	And Azariah begat Helez, and Helez begat Eleasah,
B013C002V040	13	2	40	And Eleasah begat Sismai, and Sismai begat Shallum,
B013C002V041	13	2	41	And Shallum begat Jekamiah, and Jekamiah begat Elishama.
B013C002V042	13	2	42	Now the sons of Caleb the brother of Jerahmeel were, Mesha his firstborn, who was the father of Ziph; and the sons of Mareshah the father of Hebron.
B013C002V043	13	2	43	And the sons of Hebron; Korah, and Tappuah, and Rekem, and Shema.
B013C002V044	13	2	44	And Shema begat Raham, the father of Jorkeam: and Rekem begat Shammai.
B013C002V045	13	2	45	And the son of Shammai was Maon: and Maon was the father of Beth-zur.
B013C002V046	13	2	46	And Ephah, Calebâ€™s concubine, bore Haran, and Moza, and Gazez: and Haran begat Gazez.
B013C002V047	13	2	47	And the sons of Jahdai; Regem, and Jotham, and Gesham, and Pelet, and Ephah, and Shaaph.
B013C002V048	13	2	48	Maachah, Calebâ€™s concubine, bore Sheber, and Tirhanah.
B013C002V049	13	2	49	She bore also Shaaph the father of Madmannah, Sheva the father of Machbenah, and the father of Gibea: and the daughter of Caleb was Achsah.
B013C002V050	13	2	50	These were the sons of Caleb the son of Hur, the firstborn of Ephratah; Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim,
B013C002V051	13	2	51	Salma the father of Bethlehem, Hareph the father of Beth-gader.
B013C002V052	13	2	52	And Shobal the father of Kiriath-jearim had sons; Haroeh, and half of the Menuhoth.
B013C002V053	13	2	53	And the families of Kiriath-jearim; the Ithrites, and the Puthites, and the Shumathites, and the Mishraites; of them came the Zorathites, and the Eshtaolites.
B013C002V054	13	2	54	The sons of Salma; Bethlehem, and the Netophathites, Ataroth, of the house of Joab, and half of the Manahathites, the Zorites.
B013C002V055	13	2	55	And the families of the scribes who dwelt at Jabez; the Tirathites, the Shimeathites, and Sucathites. These are the Kenites that came of Hammath, the father of the house of Rechab.
B013C003V001	13	3	1	Now these were the sons of David, who were born unto him in Hebron; the firstborn Amnon, of Ahinoam the Jezreelitess; the second Daniel, of Abigail the Carmelitess:
B013C003V002	13	3	2	The third, Absalom the son of Maachah the daughter of Talmai king of Geshur: the fourth, Adonijah the son of Haggith:
B013C003V003	13	3	3	The fifth, Shephatiah of Abital: the sixth, Ithream by Eglah his wife.
B013C003V004	13	3	4	These six were born unto him in Hebron; and there he reigned seven years and six months: and in Jerusalem he reigned thirty and three years.
B013C003V005	13	3	5	And these were born unto him in Jerusalem; Shimea, and Shobab, and Nathan, and Solomon, four, of Bath-shua the daughter of Ammiel:
B013C003V006	13	3	6	Ibhar also, and Elishama, and Eliphelet,
B013C003V007	13	3	7	And Nogah, and Nepheg, and Japhia,
B013C003V008	13	3	8	And Elishama, and Eliada, and Eliphelet, nine.
B013C003V009	13	3	9	These were all the sons of David, beside the sons of the concubines, and Tamar their sister.
B013C003V010	13	3	10	And Solomonâ€™s son was Rehoboam, Abijah his son, Asa his son, Jehoshaphat his son,
B013C003V011	13	3	11	Joram his son, Ahaziah his son, Joash his son,
B013C003V012	13	3	12	Amaziah his son, Azariah his son, Jotham his son,
B013C003V013	13	3	13	Ahaz his son, Hezekiah his son, Manasseh his son,
B013C003V014	13	3	14	Amon his son, Josiah his son.
B013C003V015	13	3	15	And the sons of Josiah were, the firstborn Johanan, the second Jehoiakim, the third Zedekiah, the fourth Shallum.
B013C003V016	13	3	16	And the sons of Jehoiakim: Jeconiah his son, Zedekiah his son.
B013C003V017	13	3	17	And the sons of Jeconiah; the captive, Shealtiel his son,
B013C003V018	13	3	18	Malchiram also, and Pedaiah, and Shenazar, Jekamiah, Hoshama, and Nedabiah.
B013C003V019	13	3	19	And the sons of Pedaiah were, Zerubbabel, and Shimei: and the sons of Zerubbabel; Meshullam, and Hananiah, and Shelomith their sister:
B013C003V020	13	3	20	And Hashubah, and Ohel, and Berechiah, and Hasadiah, Jushab-hesed, five.
B013C003V021	13	3	21	And the sons of Hananiah; Pelatiah, and Jeshaiah: the sons of Rephaiah, the sons of Arnan, the sons of Obadiah, the sons of Shecaniah.
B013C003V022	13	3	22	And the sons of Shecaniah; Shemaiah: and the sons of Shemaiah; Hattush, and Igal, and Bariah, and Neariah, and Shaphat, six.
B013C003V023	13	3	23	And the sons of Neariah; Elioenai, and Hizkiah, and Azrikam, three.
B013C003V024	13	3	24	And the sons of Elioenai were, Hodaviah, and Eliashib, and Pelaiah, and Akkub, and Johanan, and Delaiah, and Anani, seven.
B013C004V001	13	4	1	The sons of Judah; Perez, Hezron, and Carmi, and Hur, and Shobal.
B013C004V002	13	4	2	And Reaiah the son of Shobal begat Jahath; and Jahath begat Ahumai, and Lahad. These are the families of the Zorathites.
B013C004V003	13	4	3	And these were the sons of the father of Etam; Jezreel, and Ishma, and Idbash: and the name of their sister was Hazelelponi:
B013C004V004	13	4	4	And Penuel the father of Gedor, and Ezer the father of Hushah. These are the sons of Hur, the firstborn of Ephrathah, the father of Bethlehem.
B013C004V005	13	4	5	And Ashur the father of Tekoa had two wives, Helah and Naarah.
B013C004V006	13	4	6	And Naarah bore him Ahuzzam, and Hepher, and Temeni, and Haahashtari. These were the sons of Naarah.
B013C004V007	13	4	7	And the sons of Helah were, Zereth, and Izhar, and Ethnan.
B013C004V008	13	4	8	And Koz begat Anub, and Zobebah, and the families of Aharhel the son of Harum.
B013C004V009	13	4	9	And Jabez was more honorable than his brethren: and his mother called his name Jabez, saying, Because I bore him with sorrow.
B013C004V010	13	4	10	And Jabez called on the God of Israel, saying, Oh that you would bless me indeed, and enlarge my border, and that your hand might be with me, and that you would keep me from evil, that it may not grieve me! And God granted him that which he requested.
B013C004V011	13	4	11	And Chelub the brother of Shuhah begat Mehir, who was the father of Eshton.
B013C004V012	13	4	12	And Eshton begat Beth-rapha, and Paseah, and Tehinnah the father of Ir-nahash. These are the men of Recah.
B013C004V013	13	4	13	And the sons of Kenaz; Othniel, and Seraiah: and the sons of Othniel; Hathath.
B013C004V014	13	4	14	And Meonothai begat Ophrah: and Seraiah begat Joab, the father of the valley of Harashim; for they were craftsmen.
B013C004V015	13	4	15	And the sons of Caleb the son of Jephunneh; Iru, Elah, and Naam: and the sons of Elah, even Kenaz.
B013C004V016	13	4	16	And the sons of Jehallelel; Ziph, and Ziphah, Tiria, and Asarel.
B013C004V017	13	4	17	And the sons of Ezra were, Jether, and Mered, and Epher, and Jalon: and Meredâ€™s wife bore Miriam, and Shammai, and Ishbah the father of Eshtemoa.
B013C004V018	13	4	18	And his wife Jehudijah bore Jered the father of Gedor, and Heber the father of Soco, and Jekuthiel the father of Zanoah. And these are the sons of Bithiah the daughter of Pharaoh, who Mered took.
B013C004V019	13	4	19	And the sons of his wife Hodiah the sister of Naham, the father of Keilah the Garmite, and Eshtemoa the Maachathite.
B013C004V020	13	4	20	And the sons of Shimon were, Amnon, and Rinnah, Ben-hanan, and Tilon. And the sons of Ishi were, Zoheth, and Ben-zoheth.
B013C004V021	13	4	21	The sons of Shelah the son of Judah were, Er the father of Lecah, and Laadah the father of Mareshah, and the families of the house of them that wrought fine linen, of the house of Ashbea,
B013C004V022	13	4	22	And Jokim, and the men of Cozeba, and Joash, and Saraph, who had the dominion in Moab, and Jashubi-lehem. And these are ancient records.
B013C004V023	13	4	23	These were the potters, and those that dwelt at Netaim and Gederah: there they dwelt with the king for his work.
B013C004V024	13	4	24	The sons of Simeon were, Nemuel, and Jamin, Jarib, Zerah, and Shaul:
B013C004V025	13	4	25	Shallum his son, Mibsam his son, Mishma his son.
B013C004V026	13	4	26	And the sons of Mishma; Hammuel his son, Zaccur his son, Shimei his son.
B013C004V027	13	4	27	And Shimei had sixteen sons and six daughters; but his brothers had not many children, neither did all their family multiply, like the children of Judah.
B013C004V028	13	4	28	And they dwelt at Beer-sheba, and Moladah, and Hazar-shual,
B013C004V029	13	4	29	And at Bilhah, and at Ezem, and at Tolad,
B013C004V030	13	4	30	And at Bethuel, and at Hormah, and at Ziklag,
B013C004V031	13	4	31	And at Beth-marcaboth, and Hazar-susim, and at Beth-biri, and at Shaaraim. These were their cities unto the reign of David.
B013C004V032	13	4	32	And their villages were, Etam, and Ain, Rimmon, and Tochen, and Ashan, five cities:
B013C004V033	13	4	33	And all their villages that were round about the same cities, unto Baal. These were their dwelling places, and they kept their genealogy.
B013C004V034	13	4	34	And Meshobab, and Jamlech, and Joshah the son of Amaziah,
B013C004V035	13	4	35	And Joel, and Jehu the son of Joshibiah, the son of Seraiah, the son of Asiel,
B013C004V036	13	4	36	And Elioenai, and Jaakobah, and Jeshohaiah, and Asaiah, and Adiel, and Jesimiel, and Benaiah,
B013C004V037	13	4	37	And Ziza the son of Shiphi, the son of Allon, the son of Jedaiah, the son of Shimri, the son of Shemaiah;
B013C004V038	13	4	38	These mentioned by their names were princes in their families: and the house of their fathers increased greatly.
B013C004V039	13	4	39	And they went to the entrance of Gedor, even unto the east side of the valley, to seek pasture for their flocks.
B013C004V040	13	4	40	And they found rich and good pasture, and the land was broad, and quiet, and peaceable; for they of Ham had dwelt there formerly.
B013C004V041	13	4	41	And these recorded by name came in the days of Hezekiah king of Judah, and destroyed their tents, and the Meunim that were found there, and destroyed them utterly unto this day, and dwelt in their place: because there was pasture there for their flocks.
B013C004V042	13	4	42	And some of them, even of the sons of Simeon, five hundred men, went to mount Seir, having for their leaders Pelatiah, and Neariah, and Rephaiah, and Uzziel, the sons of Ishi.
B013C004V043	13	4	43	And they destroyed the rest of the Amalekites that had escaped, and dwelt there unto this day.
B013C005V001	13	5	1	Now the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel, (for he was the firstborn; but, since he defiled his fatherâ€™s bed, his birthright was given unto the sons of Joseph the son of Israel: and the genealogy is not to be recorded according to the birthright.
B013C005V002	13	5	2	For Judah prevailed above his brethren, and from him came the prince; but the birthright was Josephâ€™s:)
B013C005V003	13	5	3	The sons, I say, of Reuben the firstborn of Israel were, Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.
B013C005V004	13	5	4	The sons of Joel; Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son,
B013C005V005	13	5	5	Micah his son, Reaiah his son, Baal his son,
B013C005V006	13	5	6	Beerah his son, whom Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria carried away captive: he was prince of the Reubenites.
B013C005V007	13	5	7	And his brethren by their families, when the genealogy of their generations was recorded, were the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah,
B013C005V008	13	5	8	And Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who dwelt in Aroer, even unto Nebo and Baal-meon:
B013C005V009	13	5	9	And eastward he settled as far as the entrance of the wilderness from the river Euphrates: because their cattle were multiplied in the land of Gilead.
B013C005V010	13	5	10	And in the days of Saul they made war with the Hagrites, who fell by their hand: and they dwelt in their tents throughout all the east land of Gilead.
B013C005V011	13	5	11	And the children of Gad dwelt next to them, in the land of Bashan as far as Salcah:
B013C005V012	13	5	12	Joel the chief, and Shapham the next, and Janai, and Shaphat in Bashan.
B013C005V013	13	5	13	And their brethren of the house of their fathers were, Michael, and Meshullam, and Sheba, and Jorai, and Jacan, and Zia, and Heber, seven.
B013C005V014	13	5	14	These are the children of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz;
B013C005V015	13	5	15	Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, chief of the house of their fathers.
B013C005V016	13	5	16	And they dwelt in Gilead in Bashan, and in its towns, and in all the pasture lands of Sharon, within their borders.
B013C005V017	13	5	17	All these were recorded by genealogies in the days of Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel.
B013C005V018	13	5	18	The sons of Reuben, and the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh, of valiant men, men able to bear shield and sword, and to shoot with bow, and skilful in war, were four and forty thousand seven hundred and threescore, that went out to the war.
B013C005V019	13	5	19	And they made war with the Hagrites, with Jetur, and Nephish, and Nodab.
B013C005V020	13	5	20	And they were helped against them, and the Hagrites were delivered into their hand, and all that were with them: for they cried to God in the battle, and he heeded their prayer; because they put their trust in him.
B013C005V021	13	5	21	And they took away their cattle; of their camels fifty thousand, and of sheep two hundred and fifty thousand, and of donkeys two thousand, and of men a hundred thousand.
B013C005V022	13	5	22	For there fell down many slain, because the war was of God. And they dwelt in their place until the captivity.
B013C005V023	13	5	23	And the children of the half tribe of Manasseh dwelt in the land: they increased from Bashan to Baal-hermon and Senir, and to mount Hermon.
B013C005V024	13	5	24	And these were the heads of the house of their fathers, even Epher, and Ishi, and Eliel, and Azriel, and Jeremiah, and Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty men of valor, famous men, and heads of the house of their fathers.
B013C005V025	13	5	25	And they transgressed against the God of their fathers, and played the harlot with the gods of the people of the land, whom God destroyed before them.
B013C005V026	13	5	26	And the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and the spirit of Tilgath-pilneser king of Assyria, and he carried them away, even the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasseh, and brought them unto Halah, and Habor, and Hara, and to the river Gozan, unto this day.
B013C006V001	13	6	1	The sons of Levi; Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.
B013C006V002	13	6	2	And the sons of Kohath; Amram, Izhar, and Hebron, and Uzziel.
B013C006V003	13	6	3	And the children of Amram; Aaron, and Moses, and Miriam. The sons also of Aaron; Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
