B013C007V008	13	7	8	And the sons of Becher; Zemirah, and Joash, and Eliezer, and Elioenai, and Omri, and Jeremoth, and Abiah, and Anathoth, and Alameth. All these are the sons of Becher.
B013C007V009	13	7	9	And the number of them, according to their genealogy by their generations, heads of the house of their fathers, mighty men of valor, was twenty thousand and two hundred.
B013C007V010	13	7	10	The sons also of Jediael; Bilhan: and the sons of Bilhan; Jeush, and Benjamin, and Ehud, and Chenaanah, and Zethan, and Tarshish, and Ahishahar.
B013C007V011	13	7	11	All these the sons of Jediael, according to the heads of their fathers, mighty men of valor, were seventeen thousand and two hundred soldiers, fit to go out for war and battle.
B013C007V012	13	7	12	Shuppim also, and Huppim, the children of Ir, and Hushim, the sons of Aher.
B013C007V013	13	7	13	The sons of Naphtali; Jahziel, and Guni, and Jezer, and Shallum, the sons of Bilhah.
B013C007V014	13	7	14	The sons of Manasseh; Ashriel, whom she bore: (but his concubine the Aramitess bore Machir the father of Gilead:
B013C007V015	13	7	15	And Machir took as his wife the sister of Huppim and Shuppim, whose sisterâ€™s name was Maacah;) and the name of the second was Zelophehad: and Zelophehad had only daughters.
