B013C009V001	13	9	1	So all Israel were recorded by genealogies; and, behold, they were written in the book of the kings of Israel and Judah, who were carried away to Babylon for their transgression.
B013C009V002	13	9	2	Now the first inhabitants that dwelt in their possessions in their cities were, the Israelites, the priests, Levites, and the Nethinim.
B013C009V003	13	9	3	And in Jerusalem dwelt some of the children of Judah, and some of the children of Benjamin, and some of the children of Ephraim, and Manasseh;
B013C009V004	13	9	4	Uthai the son of Ammihud, the son of Omri, the son of Imri, the son of Bani, of the children of Perez the son of Judah.
B013C009V005	13	9	5	And of the Shilonites; Asaiah the firstborn, and his sons.
B013C009V006	13	9	6	And of the sons of Zerah; Jeuel, and their brethren, six hundred and ninety.
