B013C015V018	13	15	18	And with them their brethren of the second order, Zechariah, Ben, and Jaaziel, and Shemiramoth, and Jehiel, and Unni, Eliab, and Benaiah, and Maaseiah, and Mattithiah, and Eliphelehu, and Mikneiah, and Obed-edom, and Jeiel, the gatekeepers.
B013C015V019	13	15	19	So the singers, Heman, Asaph, and Ethan, were appointed to sound with cymbals of bronze;
B013C015V020	13	15	20	And Zechariah, and Aziel, and Shemiramoth, and Jehiel, and Unni, and Eliab, and Maaseiah, and Benaiah, with harps according to Alamoth;
B013C015V021	13	15	21	And Mattithiah, and Eliphelehu, and Mikneiah, and Obed-edom, and Jeiel, and Azaziah, with lyres according to the Sheminith, to lead.
B013C015V022	13	15	22	And Chenaniah, chief of the Levites, in music: he instructed about the music, because he was skillful.
B013C015V023	13	15	23	And Berechiah and Elkanah were doorkeepers for the ark.
B013C015V024	13	15	24	And Shebaniah, and Jehoshaphat, and Nethanel, and Amasai, and Zechariah, and Benaiah, and Eliezer, the priests, did blow with the trumpets before the ark of God: and Obed-edom and Jehiah were doorkeepers for the ark.
B013C015V025	13	15	25	So David, and the elders of Israel, and the captains over thousands, went to bring up the ark of the covenant of the LORD out of the house of Obed-edom with joy.
