B013C017V015	13	17	15	According to all these words, and according to all this vision, so did Nathan speak unto David.
B013C017V016	13	17	16	And David the king came and sat before the LORD, and said, Who am I, O LORD God, and what is my house, that you have brought me this far?
B013C017V017	13	17	17	And yet this was a small thing in your eyes, O God; for you have also spoken of your servantâ€™s house for a great while to come, and have regarded me according to the estate of a man of high degree, O LORD God.
B013C017V018	13	17	18	What can David speak more to you for the honor of your servant? for you know your servant.
B013C017V019	13	17	19	O LORD, for your servantâ€™s sake, and according to your own heart, have you done all this greatness, in making known all these great things.
B013C017V020	13	17	20	O LORD, there is none like you, neither is there any God beside you, according to all that we have heard with our ears.
B013C017V021	13	17	21	And what one nation in the earth is like your people Israel, whom God went to redeem to be his own people, to make you a name of greatness and awesomeness, by driving out nations from before your people, whom you have redeemed out of Egypt?
B013C017V022	13	17	22	For your people Israel did you make your own people forever; and you, LORD, became their God.
B013C017V023	13	17	23	Therefore now, LORD, let the thing that you have spoken concerning your servant and concerning his house be established forever, and do as you have said.
B013C017V024	13	17	24	Let it even be established, that your name may be magnified forever, saying, The LORD of hosts is the God of Israel, even a God to Israel: and let the house of David your servant be established before you.
B013C017V025	13	17	25	For you, O my God, have told your servant that you will build him a house: therefore your servant has found in his heart to pray before you.
B013C017V026	13	17	26	And now, LORD, you are God, and have promised this goodness unto your servant:
B013C017V027	13	17	27	Now therefore let it please you to bless the house of your servant, that it may be before you forever: for you bless, O LORD, and it shall be blessed forever.
B013C018V001	13	18	1	Now after this it came to pass, that David defeated the Philistines, and subdued them, and took Gath and her towns out of the hand of the Philistines.
B013C018V002	13	18	2	And he defeated Moab; and the Moabites became Davidâ€™s servants, and brought tribute.
