B013C022V017	13	22	17	David also commanded all the princes of Israel to help Solomon his son, saying,
B013C022V018	13	22	18	Is not the LORD your God with you? and has he not given you rest on every side? for he has given the inhabitants of the land into my hand; and the land is subdued before the LORD, and before his people.
B013C022V019	13	22	19	Now set your heart and your soul to seek the LORD your God; arise therefore, and build you the sanctuary of the LORD God, to bring the ark of the covenant of the LORD, and the holy vessels of God, into the house that is to be built to the name of the LORD.
B013C023V001	13	23	1	So when David was old and full of days, he made Solomon his son king over Israel.
B013C023V002	13	23	2	And he gathered together all the princes of Israel, with the priests and the Levites.
B013C023V003	13	23	3	Now the Levites were numbered from the age of thirty years and upward: and their number, man by man, was thirty and eight thousand.
B013C023V004	13	23	4	Of which, twenty and four thousand were to look after the work of the house of the LORD; and six thousand were officers and judges:
B013C023V005	13	23	5	Moreover four thousand were gatekeepers; and four thousand praised the LORD with the instruments which I made, said David, for praise.
B013C023V006	13	23	6	And David divided them into divisions among the sons of Levi, namely, Gershon, Kohath, and Merari.
B013C023V007	13	23	7	Of the Gershonites were, Ladan, and Shimei.
B013C023V008	13	23	8	The sons of Ladan; the chief was Jehiel, and Zetham, and Joel, three.
B013C023V009	13	23	9	The sons of Shimei; Shelomoth, and Haziel, and Haran, three. These were the heads of the fathersâ€™ houses of Ladan.
B013C023V010	13	23	10	And the sons of Shimei were, Jahath, Zina, and Jeush, and Beriah. These four were the sons of Shimei.
B013C023V011	13	23	11	And Jahath was the chief, and Zizah the second: but Jeush and Beriah had not many sons; therefore they were in one reckoning, as one fatherâ€™s house.
B013C023V012	13	23	12	The sons of Kohath; Amram, Izhar, Hebron, and Uzziel, four.
B013C023V013	13	23	13	The sons of Amram; Aaron and Moses: and Aaron was separated, that he should sanctify the most holy things, he and his sons forever, to burn incense before the LORD, to minister unto him, and to give the blessing in his name forever.
B013C023V014	13	23	14	Now concerning Moses the man of God, his sons were named of the tribe of Levi.
B013C023V015	13	23	15	The sons of Moses were, Gershom, and Eliezer.
B013C023V016	13	23	16	Of the sons of Gershom, Shebuel was the chief.
B013C023V017	13	23	17	And the sons of Eliezer were, Rehabiah the chief. And Eliezer had no other sons; but the sons of Rehabiah were very many.
B013C023V018	13	23	18	Of the sons of Izhar; Shelomith the chief.
B013C023V019	13	23	19	Of the sons of Hebron; Jeriah the first, Amariah the second, Jahaziel the third, and Jekameam the fourth.
B013C023V020	13	23	20	Of the sons of Uzziel; Micah the first, and Issiah the second.
B013C023V021	13	23	21	The sons of Merari; Mahli, and Mushi. The sons of Mahli; Eleazar, and Kish.
B013C023V022	13	23	22	And Eleazar died, and had no sons, but daughters: and their brethren the sons of Kish took them.
B013C023V023	13	23	23	The sons of Mushi; Mahli, and Eder, and Jeremoth, three.
B013C023V024	13	23	24	These were the sons of Levi by their fathersâ€™ houses; even the heads of their fathersâ€™ houses, as they were counted individually by the number of their names, that did the work for the service of the house of the LORD, from the age of twenty years and upward.
B013C023V025	13	23	25	For David said, The LORD God of Israel has given rest unto his people, that they may dwell in Jerusalem forever:
B013C023V026	13	23	26	And also unto the Levites; they shall no more carry the tabernacle, nor any vessels of it for the service thereof.
B013C023V027	13	23	27	For by the last words of David the Levites were numbered from twenty years old and above:
B013C023V028	13	23	28	Because their office was to wait on the sons of Aaron for the service of the house of the LORD, in the courts, and in the chambers, and in the purifying of all holy things, and the work of the service of the house of God;
B013C023V029	13	23	29	Both for the showbread, and for the fine flour for meal offering, and for the unleavened cakes, and for that which is baked in the pan, and for that which is mixed with all kinds of measures and sizes;
B013C023V030	13	23	30	And to stand every morning to thank and praise the LORD, and likewise at evening;
B013C023V031	13	23	31	And to offer all burnt sacrifices unto the LORD on the sabbaths, on the new moons, and on the set feasts, by number, according to that required of them, continually before the LORD:
B013C023V032	13	23	32	And that they should attend to the needs of the tabernacle of meeting, and the needs of the holy place, and the needs of the sons of Aaron their brethren, in the service of the house of the LORD.
B013C024V001	13	24	1	Now these are the divisions of the sons of Aaron. The sons of Aaron; Nadab, and Abihu, Eleazar, and Ithamar.
B013C024V002	13	24	2	But Nadab and Abihu died before their father, and had no children: therefore Eleazar and Ithamar executed the priestâ€™s office.
B013C024V003	13	24	3	And David distributed them, both Zadok of the sons of Eleazar, and Ahimelech of the sons of Ithamar, according to their offices in their service.
B013C024V004	13	24	4	And there were more chief men found of the sons of Eleazar than of the sons of Ithamar; and thus were they divided. Among the sons of Eleazar there were sixteen heads of their fathersâ€™ houses, and eight heads of their fathersâ€™ houses among the sons of Ithamar.
B013C024V005	13	24	5	Thus were they divided by lot, one group as another; for the officials of the sanctuary, and officials of the house of God, were of the sons of Eleazar, and of the sons of Ithamar.
B013C024V006	13	24	6	And Shemaiah the son of Nethanel the scribe, one of the Levites, wrote them down before the king, and the leaders, and Zadok the priest, and Ahimelech the son of Abiathar, and before the heads of the fathersâ€™ houses of the priests and Levites: one fatherâ€™s house being taken for Eleazar, and one taken for Ithamar.
