B013C024V025	13	24	25	The brother of Micah was Isshiah: of the sons of Isshiah; Zechariah.
B013C024V026	13	24	26	The sons of Merari were Mahli and Mushi: the sons of Jaaziah; Beno.
B013C024V027	13	24	27	The sons of Merari by Jaaziah; Beno, and Shoham, and Zaccur, and Ibri.
B013C024V028	13	24	28	Of Mahli came Eleazar, who had no sons.
B013C024V029	13	24	29	Concerning Kish: the son of Kish was Jerahmeel.
B013C024V030	13	24	30	The sons also of Mushi; Mahli, and Eder, and Jerimoth. These were the sons of the Levites according to the house of their fathers.
B013C024V031	13	24	31	These likewise cast lots even as their brethren the sons of Aaron in the presence of David the king, and Zadok, and Ahimelech, and the heads of the fathersâ€™ houses of the priests and Levites; the principal fathers did even as their younger brethren.
B013C025V001	13	25	1	Moreover David and the captains of the army separated for the service some of the sons of Asaph, and of Heman, and of Jeduthun, who should prophesy with harps, with lyres, and with cymbals: and the number of the workmen according to their service was:
B013C025V002	13	25	2	Of the sons of Asaph; Zaccur, and Joseph, and Nethaniah, and Asharelah, the sons of Asaph under the direction of Asaph, who prophesied according to the order of the king.
B013C025V003	13	25	3	Of Jeduthun: the sons of Jeduthun; Gedaliah, and Zeri, and Jeshaiah, Shemei, Hashabiah, and Mattithiah, six, under the hands of their father Jeduthun, who prophesied with a harp, to give thanks and to praise the LORD.
B013C025V004	13	25	4	Of Heman: the sons of Heman; Bukkiah, Mattaniah, Uzziel, Shebuel, and Jerimoth, Hananiah, Hanani, Eliathah, Giddalti, and Romamti-ezer, Joshbekashah, Mallothi, Hothir, and Mahazioth:
B013C025V005	13	25	5	All these were the sons of Heman the kingâ€™s seer in the words of God, to exalt the horn. And God gave to Heman fourteen sons and three daughters.
B013C025V006	13	25	6	All these were under the direction of their father in the music in the house of the LORD, with cymbals, lyres, and harps, for the service of the house of God, according to the kingâ€™s order to Asaph, Jeduthun, and Heman.
B013C025V007	13	25	7	So the number of them, with their brethren that were instructed in the songs of the LORD, even all that were skillful, was two hundred fourscore and eight.
