B014C016V014	14	16	14	And they buried him in his own sepulcher, which he had made for himself in the city of David, and laid him in the bed which was filled with sweet ointments and various kinds of spices prepared by the perfumerâ€™s art: and they made a very great fire in honor of him.
B014C017V001	14	17	1	And Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his stead, and strengthened himself against Israel.
B014C017V002	14	17	2	And he placed forces in all the fortified cities of Judah, and set garrisons in the land of Judah, and in the cities of Ephraim, which Asa his father had taken.
B014C017V003	14	17	3	And the LORD was with Jehoshaphat, because he walked in the first ways of his father David, and sought not unto Baalim;
B014C017V004	14	17	4	But sought to the LORD God of his father, and walked in his commandments, and not after the doings of Israel.
