B014C018V001	14	18	1	Now Jehoshaphat had riches and honor in abundance, and made a marriage alliance with Ahab.
B014C018V002	14	18	2	And after certain years he went down to Ahab to Samaria. And Ahab killed sheep and oxen for him in abundance, and for the people that he had with him, and persuaded him to go up with him to Ramoth-gilead.
B014C018V003	14	18	3	And Ahab king of Israel said unto Jehoshaphat king of Judah, Will you go with me to Ramoth-gilead? And he answered him, I am as you are, and my people as your people; and we will be with you in the war.
B014C018V004	14	18	4	And Jehoshaphat said unto the king of Israel, Inquire, I pray you, for the word of the LORD today.
