B015C008V026	15	8	26	I even weighed unto their hand six hundred and fifty talents of silver, and silver articles worth a hundred talents, and of gold a hundred talents;
B015C008V027	15	8	27	Also twenty bowls of gold, worth a thousand darics; and two vessels of fine polished bronze, as precious as gold.
B015C008V028	15	8	28	And I said unto them, You are holy unto the LORD; the articles are holy also; and the silver and the gold are a freewill offering unto the LORD God of your fathers.
B015C008V029	15	8	29	Watch, and keep them, until you weigh them before the leaders of the priests and the Levites, and heads of the fathersâ€™ houses of Israel, at Jerusalem, in the chambers of the house of the LORD.
B015C008V030	15	8	30	So the priests and the Levites took the weight of the silver, and the gold, and the articles, to bring them to Jerusalem unto the house of our God.
B015C008V031	15	8	31	Then we departed from the river of Ahava on the twelfth day of the first month, to go unto Jerusalem: and the hand of our God was upon us, and he delivered us from the hand of the enemy, and of such as lay in wait by the way.
B015C008V032	15	8	32	And we came to Jerusalem, and abode there three days.
B015C008V033	15	8	33	Now on the fourth day were the silver and the gold and the articles weighed in the house of our God by the hand of Meremoth the son of Uriah the priest; and with him was Eleazar the son of Phinehas; and with them was Jozabad the son of Jeshua, and Noadiah the son of Binnui, Levites;
B015C008V034	15	8	34	With the number and weight of everything: and all the weight was recorded at that time.
B015C008V035	15	8	35	Also the children of those that had been carried away, who had come out of the captivity, offered burnt offerings unto the God of Israel, twelve bullocks for all Israel, ninety and six rams, seventy and seven lambs, twelve male goats for a sin offering: all this was a burnt offering unto the LORD.
B015C008V036	15	8	36	And they delivered the kingâ€™s orders unto the kingâ€™s satraps, and to the governors on this side the river: and they aided the people, and the house of God.
B015C009V001	15	9	1	Now when these things were done, the leaders came to me, saying, The people of Israel, and the priests, and the Levites, have not separated themselves from the people of the lands, in regard to their abominations, even of the Canaanites, the Hittites, the Perizzites, the Jebusites, the Ammonites, the Moabites, the Egyptians, and the Amorites.
B015C009V002	15	9	2	For they have taken of their daughters as wives for themselves, and for their sons: so that the holy race has mixed itself with the people of those lands: yea, the hand of the leaders and rulers has been foremost in this trespass.
B015C009V003	15	9	3	And when I heard this thing, I tore my garment and my mantle, and plucked off the hair of my head and of my beard, and sat down appalled.
B015C009V004	15	9	4	Then were assembled unto me every one that trembled at the words of the God of Israel, because of the transgression of those that had been carried away; and I sat appalled until the evening sacrifice.
B015C009V005	15	9	5	And at the evening sacrifice I arose up from my heaviness; and having torn my garment and my mantle, I fell upon my knees, and spread out my hands unto the LORD my God,
B015C009V006	15	9	6	And said, O my God, I am ashamed and blush to lift up my face to you, my God: for our iniquities have risen higher than our head, and our trespass has grown up unto the heavens.
B015C009V007	15	9	7	Since the days of our fathers have we been in a great trespass unto this day; and for our iniquities have we, our kings, and our priests, been delivered into the hand of the kings of the lands, to the sword, to captivity, and to plunder, and to humiliation, as it is this day.
B015C009V008	15	9	8	And now for a little while grace has been shown from the LORD our God, to leave us a remnant to escape, and to give us security in his holy place, that our God may enlighten our eyes, and give us a little reviving in our bondage.
B015C009V009	15	9	9	For we were slaves; yet our God has not forsaken us in our bondage, but has extended mercy unto us in the sight of the kings of Persia, to give us a reviving, to rebuild the house of our God, and to repair its ruins, and to give us a wall in Judah and in Jerusalem.
B015C009V010	15	9	10	And now, O our God, what shall we say after this? for we have forsaken your commandments,
B015C009V011	15	9	11	Which you have commanded by your servants the prophets, saying, The land, unto which you go to possess it, is an unclean land with the filthiness of the people of the lands, with their abominations, which have filled it from one end to another with their uncleanness.
B015C009V012	15	9	12	Now therefore give not your daughters unto their sons, neither take their daughters unto your sons, nor seek their peace or their wealth forever: that you may be strong, and eat the good of the land, and leave it for an inheritance to your children forever.
B015C009V013	15	9	13	And after all that is come upon us for our evil deeds, and for our great trespass, seeing that you our God has punished us less than our iniquities deserve, and has given us such deliverance as this;
B015C009V014	15	9	14	Should we again break your commandments, and join in marriage with the people of these abominations? would not you be angry with us till you had consumed us, so that there should be no remnant nor escaping?
B015C009V015	15	9	15	O LORD God of Israel, you are righteous: for we remain yet escaped, as it is this day: behold, we are before you in our trespasses: for we cannot stand before you because of this.
B015C010V001	15	10	1	Now when Ezra had prayed, and when he had confessed, weeping and casting himself down before the house of God, there assembled unto him out of Israel a very great congregation of men and women and children: for the people wept bitterly.
B015C010V002	15	10	2	And Shecaniah the son of Jehiel, one of the sons of Elam, answered and said unto Ezra, We have trespassed against our God, and have married foreign wives of the people of the land: yet now there is hope in Israel concerning this thing.
B015C010V003	15	10	3	Now therefore let us make a covenant with our God to put away all the wives, and such as are born of them, according to the counsel of my lord, and of those that tremble at the commandment of our God; and let it be done according to the law.
B015C010V004	15	10	4	Arise; for this matter belongs unto you: we also will be with you: be of good courage, and do it.
B015C010V005	15	10	5	Then arose Ezra, and made the leading priests, the Levites, and all Israel, to swear that they should do according to this word. And they swore.
B015C010V006	15	10	6	Then Ezra rose up from before the house of God, and went into the chamber of Jehohanan the son of Eliashib: and when he came there, he did eat no bread, nor drink water: for he mourned because of the transgression of them that had been carried away.
B015C010V007	15	10	7	And they made proclamation throughout Judah and Jerusalem unto all the children of the captivity, that they should gather themselves together unto Jerusalem;
B015C010V008	15	10	8	And that whosoever would not come within three days, according to the order of the leaders and the elders, all his substance should be forfeited, and he himself separated from the congregation of those that had been carried away.
B015C010V009	15	10	9	Then all the men of Judah and Benjamin gathered themselves together unto Jerusalem within three days. It was the ninth month, on the twentieth day of the month; and all the people sat in the open square before the house of God, trembling because of this matter, and because of the heavy rain.
B015C010V010	15	10	10	And Ezra the priest stood up, and said unto them, You have transgressed, and have taken foreign wives, to increase the trespass of Israel.
B015C010V011	15	10	11	Now therefore make confession unto the LORD God of your fathers, and do his pleasure: and separate yourselves from the people of the land, and from the foreign wives.
B015C010V012	15	10	12	Then all the congregation answered and said with a loud voice, As you has said, so must we do.
B015C010V013	15	10	13	But the people are many, and it is a time of heavy rain, and we are not able to stand outside, neither is this a work of one day or two: for we are many that have transgressed in this thing.
B015C010V014	15	10	14	Let now our rulers of all the congregation stand, and let all them who have taken foreign wives in our cities come at appointed times, and with them the elders of every city, and the judges thereof, until the fierce wrath of our God for this matter is turned from us.
B015C010V015	15	10	15	Only Jonathan the son of Asahel and Jahzeiah the son of Tikvah opposed this matter: and Meshullam and Shabbethai the Levite supported them.
B015C010V016	15	10	16	And the children of the captivity did so. And Ezra the priest, with certain heads of the fathersâ€™ houses, according to their fathersâ€™ houses, and each of them by name, were set apart, and sat down in the first day of the tenth month to examine the matter.
B015C010V017	15	10	17	And they finished with all the men that had taken foreign wives by the first day of the first month.
B015C010V018	15	10	18	And among the sons of the priests there were found that had taken foreign wives: namely, of the sons of Jeshua the son of Jozadak, and his brethren; Maaseiah, and Eliezer, and Jarib, and Gedaliah.
B015C010V019	15	10	19	And they gave their promise that they would put away their wives; and being guilty, they offered a ram of the flock for their trespass.
B015C010V020	15	10	20	And of the sons of Immer; Hanani, and Zebadiah.
B015C010V021	15	10	21	And of the sons of Harim; Maaseiah, and Elijah, and Shemaiah, and Jehiel, and Uzziah.
B015C010V022	15	10	22	And of the sons of Pashhur; Elioenai, Maaseiah, Ishmael, Nethanel, Jozabad, and Elasah.
B015C010V023	15	10	23	Also of the Levites; Jozabad, and Shimei, and Kelaiah, (the same is Kelita,) Pethahiah, Judah, and Eliezer.
B015C010V024	15	10	24	Of the singers also; Eliashib: and of the gatekeepers; Shallum, and Telem, and Uri.
B015C010V025	15	10	25	Moreover of Israel: of the sons of Parosh; Ramiah, and Izziah, and Malchijah, and Mijamin, and Eleazar, and Malchijah, and Benaiah.
B015C010V026	15	10	26	And of the sons of Elam; Mattaniah, Zechariah, and Jehiel, and Abdi, and Jeremoth, and Elijah.
B015C010V027	15	10	27	And of the sons of Zattu; Elioenai, Eliashib, Mattaniah, and Jeremoth, and Zabad, and Aziza.
B015C010V028	15	10	28	Of the sons also of Bebai; Jehohanan, Hananiah, Zabbai, and Athlai.
B015C010V029	15	10	29	And of the sons of Bani; Meshullam, Malluch, and Adaiah, Jashub, and Sheal, and Jeremoth.
B015C010V030	15	10	30	And of the sons of Pahath-moab; Adna, and Chelal, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattaniah, Bezalel, and Binnui, and Manasseh.
B015C010V031	15	10	31	And of the sons of Harim; Eliezer, Isshijah, Malchijah, Shemaiah, Shimeon,
