B016C010V026	16	10	26	And Ahiah, Hanan, Anan,
B016C010V027	16	10	27	Malluch, Harim, Baanah.
B016C010V028	16	10	28	And the rest of the people, the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, the Nethinim, and all they that had separated themselves from the people of the lands unto the law of God, their wives, their sons, and their daughters, every one having knowledge, and having understanding;
B016C010V029	16	10	29	They joined with their brethren, their nobles, and entered into a curse, and into an oath, to walk in Godâ€™s law, which was given by Moses the servant of God, and to observe and do all the commandments of the LORD our Lord, and his ordinances and his statutes;
B016C010V030	16	10	30	And that we would not give our daughters unto the people of the land, nor take their daughters for our sons:
B016C010V031	16	10	31	And if the people of the land bring in wares or any grain on the sabbath day to sell, that we would not buy it from them on the sabbath, or on the holy day: and that we would forego the crops of the seventh year, and the exaction of every debt.
B016C010V032	16	10	32	Also we made ordinances for us, to charge ourselves yearly with the third part of a shekel for the service of the house of our God;
B016C010V033	16	10	33	For the showbread, and for the continual grain offering, and for the continual burnt offering, of the sabbaths, of the new moons, for the set feasts, and for the holy things, and for the sin offerings to make an atonement for Israel, and for all the work of the house of our God.
B016C010V034	16	10	34	And we cast the lots among the priests, the Levites, and the people, for the wood offering, to bring it into the house of our God, according to our fathersâ€™ houses, at times appointed year by year, to burn upon the altar of the LORD our God, as it is written in the law:
B016C010V035	16	10	35	And to bring the firstfruits of our ground, and the firstfruits of all fruit of all trees, year by year, unto the house of the LORD:
B016C010V036	16	10	36	Also the firstborn of our sons, and of our cattle, as it is written in the law, and the firstlings of our herds and of our flocks, to bring to the house of our God, unto the priests that minister in the house of our God:
B016C010V037	16	10	37	And that we should bring the firstfruits of our dough, and our offerings, and the fruit of all manner of trees, of wine and of oil, unto the priests, to the chambers of the house of our God; and the tithes of our ground unto the Levites, that the same Levites might have the tithes in all the cities of our work.
B016C010V038	16	10	38	And the priest the son of Aaron shall be with the Levites, when the Levites take tithes: and the Levites shall bring up the tithe of the tithes unto the house of our God, to the chambers, into the storehouse.
B016C010V039	16	10	39	For the children of Israel and the children of Levi shall bring the offering of the grain, of the new wine, and the oil, unto the chambers, where are the vessels of the sanctuary, and the priests that minister, and the gatekeepers, and the singers: and we will not forsake the house of our God.
B016C011V001	16	11	1	And the rulers of the people dwelt at Jerusalem: the rest of the people also cast lots, to bring one of ten to dwell in Jerusalem the holy city, and nine tenths to dwell in other cities.
B016C011V002	16	11	2	And the people blessed all the men, that willingly offered themselves to dwell at Jerusalem.
B016C011V003	16	11	3	Now these are the leaders of the province that dwelt in Jerusalem: but in the cities of Judah dwelt everyone in his own possession in their cities; Israel, the priests, and the Levites, and the Nethinim, and the children of Solomonâ€™s servants.
B016C011V004	16	11	4	And at Jerusalem dwelt certain of the children of Judah, and of the children of Benjamin. Of the children of Judah; Athaiah the son of Uzziah, the son of Zechariah, the son of Amariah, the son of Shephatiah, the son of Mahalalel, of the children of Perez;
B016C011V005	16	11	5	And Maaseiah the son of Baruch, the son of Col-hozeh, the son of Hazaiah, the son of Adaiah, the son of Joiarib, the son of Zechariah, the son of Shilonite.
B016C011V006	16	11	6	All the sons of Perez that dwelt at Jerusalem were four hundred threescore and eight valiant men.
B016C011V007	16	11	7	And these are the sons of Benjamin; Sallu the son of Meshullam, the son of Joed, the son of Pedaiah, the son of Kolaiah, the son of Maaseiah, the son of Ithiel, the son of Jeshaiah.
B016C011V008	16	11	8	And after him Gabbai, Sallai, nine hundred twenty and eight.
B016C011V009	16	11	9	And Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer: and Judah the son of Hassenuah was second over the city.
B016C011V010	16	11	10	Of the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, Jachin.
B016C011V011	16	11	11	Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, the son of Meshullam, the son of Zadok, the son of Meraioth, the son of Ahitub, was the ruler of the house of God.
B016C011V012	16	11	12	And their brethren that did the work of the house were eight hundred twenty and two: and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, the son of Pelaliah, the son of Amzi, the son of Zechariah, the son of Pashhur, the son of Malchijah,
B016C011V013	16	11	13	And his brethren, heads of the fathersâ€™ houses, two hundred forty and two: and Amashai the son of Azarel, the son of Ahzai, the son of Meshillemoth, the son of Immer.
B016C011V014	16	11	14	And their brethren, mighty men of valor, a hundred twenty and eight: and their overseer was Zabdiel, the son of Haggedolim.
B016C011V015	16	11	15	Also of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, the son of Azrikam, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Bunni;
B016C011V016	16	11	16	And Shabbethai and Jozabad, of the heads of the Levites, had the oversight of the outside business of the house of God.
B016C011V017	16	11	17	And Mattaniah the son of Mica, the son of Zabdi, the son of Asaph, was the leader to begin the thanksgiving in prayer: and Bakbukiah the second among his brethren, and Abda the son of Shammua, the son of Galal, the son of Jeduthun.
B016C011V018	16	11	18	All the Levites in the holy city were two hundred fourscore and four.
B016C011V019	16	11	19	Moreover the gatekeepers, Akkub, Talmon, and their brethren that kept the gates, were a hundred seventy and two.
B016C011V020	16	11	20	And the rest of Israel, of the priests, and the Levites, were in all the cities of Judah, every one in his inheritance.
B016C011V021	16	11	21	But the Nethinim dwelt in Ophel: and Ziha and Gispa were over the Nethinim.
B016C011V022	16	11	22	The overseer also of the Levites at Jerusalem was Uzzi the son of Bani, the son of Hashabiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Mica, of the sons of Asaph, the singers, were over the business of the house of God.
B016C011V023	16	11	23	For it was the kingâ€™s commandment concerning them, that a certain portion should be for the singers, as required every day.
B016C011V024	16	11	24	And Pethahiah the son of Meshezabel, of the children of Zerah the son of Judah, was at the kingâ€™s hand in all matters concerning the people.
B016C011V025	16	11	25	And for the villages, with their fields, some of the children of Judah dwelt at Kiriath-arba, and in its villages, and at Dibon, and in its villages, and at Jekabzeel, and in its villages,
B016C011V026	16	11	26	And at Jeshua, and at Moladah, and at Beth-pelet,
B016C011V027	16	11	27	And at Hazar-shual, and at Beer-sheba, and in its villages,
B016C011V028	16	11	28	And at Ziklag, and at Meconah, and in its villages,
B016C011V029	16	11	29	And at En-rimmon, and at Zorah, and at Jarmuth,
B016C011V030	16	11	30	Zanoah, Adullam, and in their villages, at Lachish, and its fields, at Azekah, and in its villages. And they dwelt from Beer-sheba unto the valley of Hinnom.
B016C011V031	16	11	31	The children also of Benjamin from Geba dwelt at Michmash, and Aija, and Beth-el, and in their villages,
B016C011V032	16	11	32	And at Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah,
B016C011V033	16	11	33	Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim,
B016C011V034	16	11	34	Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat,
B016C011V035	16	11	35	Lod, and Ono, the valley of craftsmen.
B016C011V036	16	11	36	And of the Levites were divisions in Judah, and in Benjamin.
B016C012V001	16	12	1	Now these are the priests and the Levites that went up with Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and Jeshua: Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra,
B016C012V002	16	12	2	Amariah, Malluch, Hattush,
B016C012V003	16	12	3	Shecaniah, Rehum, Meremoth,
B016C012V004	16	12	4	Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah,
B016C012V005	16	12	5	Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah,
B016C012V006	16	12	6	Shemaiah, and Joiarib, Jedaiah,
B016C012V007	16	12	7	Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Jedaiah. These were the heads of the priests and of their brethren in the days of Jeshua.
B016C012V008	16	12	8	Moreover the Levites: Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah, who was over the thanksgiving, he and his brethren.
B016C012V009	16	12	9	Also Bakbukiah and Unno, their brethren, stood opposite them in the service.
B016C012V010	16	12	10	And Jeshua begat Joiakim, Joiakim also begat Eliashib, and Eliashib begat Joiada,
B016C012V011	16	12	11	And Joiada begat Jonathan, and Jonathan begat Jaddua.
B016C012V012	16	12	12	And in the days of Joiakim were priests, the heads of the fathersâ€™ houses: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah;
B016C012V013	16	12	13	Of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan;
B016C012V014	16	12	14	Of Malluchi, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph;
B016C012V015	16	12	15	Of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai;
B016C012V016	16	12	16	Of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam;
B016C012V017	16	12	17	Of Abijah, Zichri; of Miniamin, of Moadiah, Piltai;
B016C012V018	16	12	18	Of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan;
B016C012V019	16	12	19	And of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi;
B016C012V020	16	12	20	Of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber;
B016C012V021	16	12	21	Of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; of Jedaiah, Nethanel.
B016C012V022	16	12	22	The Levites in the days of Eliashib, Joiada, and Johanan, and Jaddua, were recorded heads of the fathersâ€™ houses: also the priests, to the reign of Darius the Persian.
B016C012V023	16	12	23	The sons of Levi, the heads of the fathersâ€™ houses, were written in the book of the chronicles, even until the days of Johanan the son of Eliashib.
B016C012V024	16	12	24	And the heads of the Levites: Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and Jeshua the son of Kadmiel, with their brethren opposite them, to praise and to give thanks, according to the commandment of David the man of God, watch corresponding with watch.
B016C012V025	16	12	25	Mattaniah, and Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, Akkub, were gatekeepers keeping the watch at the storehouses of the gates.
B016C012V026	16	12	26	These were in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua, the son of Jozadak, and in the days of Nehemiah the governor, and of Ezra the priest, the scribe.
B016C012V027	16	12	27	And at the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the Levites out of all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem, to keep the dedication with gladness, both with thanksgivings, and with singing, with cymbals, lyres, and harps.
B016C012V028	16	12	28	And the sons of the singers gathered themselves together, both out of the countryside round about Jerusalem, and from the villages of the Netophathites;
B016C012V029	16	12	29	Also from the house of Gilgal, and out of the fields of Geba and Azmaveth: for the singers had built them villages round about Jerusalem.
B016C012V030	16	12	30	And the priests and the Levites purified themselves, and purified the people, and the gates, and the wall.
B016C012V031	16	12	31	Then I brought up the leaders of Judah upon the wall, and appointed two great companies of them that gave thanks, of which one went on the right hand upon the wall toward the refuse gate:
B016C012V032	16	12	32	And after them went Hoshaiah, and half of the leaders of Judah,
B016C012V033	16	12	33	And Azariah, Ezra, and Meshullam,
B016C012V034	16	12	34	Judah, and Benjamin, and Shemaiah, and Jeremiah,
B016C012V035	16	12	35	And certain of the priestsâ€™ sons with trumpets; namely, Zechariah the son of Jonathan, the son of Shemaiah, the son of Mattaniah, the son of Micaiah, the son of Zaccur, the son of Asaph:
B016C012V036	16	12	36	And his brethren, Shemaiah, and Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel, and Judah, Hanani, with the musical instruments of David the man of God, and Ezra the scribe went before them.
B016C012V037	16	12	37	And at the fountain gate, which was opposite them, they went up by the stairs of the city of David, at the ascent of the wall, above the house of David, even unto the water gate eastward.
B016C012V038	16	12	38	And the other company of them that gave thanks went the opposite of them, and I followed them, with half of the people upon the wall, going past the tower of the ovens even unto the broad wall;
B016C012V039	16	12	39	And from above the gate of Ephraim, and above the old gate, and above the fish gate, and the tower of Hananeel, and the tower of the hundred, even unto the sheep gate: and they stopped at the gate of the guard.
B016C012V040	16	12	40	So stood the two companies of them that gave thanks in the house of God, and I, and half of the rulers with me:
B016C012V041	16	12	41	And the priests; Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah, and Hananiah, with trumpets;
B016C012V042	16	12	42	And Maaseiah, and Shemaiah, and Eleazar, and Uzzi, and Jehohanan, and Malchijah, and Elam, and Ezer. And the singers sang loudly, with Jezrahiah as their leader.
B016C012V043	16	12	43	Also that day they offered great sacrifices, and rejoiced: for God had made them rejoice with great joy: the wives also and the children rejoiced: so that the joy of Jerusalem was heard even afar off.
B016C012V044	16	12	44	And at that time were some appointed over the chambers for the stores, for the offerings, for the firstfruits, and for the tithes, to gather into them out of the fields of the cities the portions required by the law for the priests and Levites: for Judah rejoiced for the priests and for the Levites who ministered.
B016C012V045	16	12	45	And both the singers and the gatekeepers kept the charge of their God, and the charge of the purification, according to the commandment of David, and of Solomon his son.
B016C012V046	16	12	46	For in the days of David and Asaph of old there was a leader of the singers, and songs of praise and thanksgiving unto God.
B016C012V047	16	12	47	And all Israel in the days of Zerubbabel, and in the days of Nehemiah, gave the portions for the singers and the gatekeepers, every day their portion: and they set apart holy things for the Levites; and the Levites set them apart for the children of Aaron.
B016C013V001	16	13	1	On that day they read in the book of Moses in the hearing of the people; and in it was found written, that the Ammonite and the Moabite should not come into the congregation of God forever;
B016C013V002	16	13	2	Because they met not the children of Israel with bread and with water, but hired Balaam against them, that he should curse them: however our God turned the curse into a blessing.
B016C013V003	16	13	3	Now it came to pass, when they had heard the law, that they separated from Israel all the mixed multitude.
B016C013V004	16	13	4	And before this, Eliashib the priest, having the oversight of the chamber of the house of our God, was allied unto Tobiah:
B016C013V005	16	13	5	And he had prepared for him a great chamber, where previously they stored the grain offerings, the frankincense, and the vessels, and the tithes of the grain, the new wine, and the oil, which was commanded to be given to the Levites, and the singers, and the gatekeepers; and the offerings of the priests.
B016C013V006	16	13	6	But in all this time I was not at Jerusalem: for in the two and thirtieth year of Artaxerxes king of Babylon came I unto the king, and after certain days obtained I leave of the king:
B016C013V007	16	13	7	And I came to Jerusalem, and discovered the evil that Eliashib did for Tobiah, in preparing him a chamber in the courts of the house of God.
B016C013V008	16	13	8	And it grieved me greatly: therefore I cast forth all the household goods of Tobiah out of the chamber.
B016C013V009	16	13	9	Then I commanded, and they cleansed the chambers: and there I brought again the articles of the house of God, with the grain offering and the frankincense.
B016C013V010	16	13	10	And I perceived that the portions of the Levites had not been given them: for the Levites and the singers, that did the work, were fled every one to his field.
B016C013V011	16	13	11	Then contended I with the rulers, and said, Why is the house of God forsaken? And I gathered them together, and set them in their place.
B016C013V012	16	13	12	Then brought all Judah the tithe of the grain and the new wine and the oil unto the storehouse.
B016C013V013	16	13	13	And I made treasurers over the storehouse, Shelemiah the priest, and Zadok the scribe, and of the Levites, Pedaiah: and next to them was Hanan the son of Zaccur, the son of Mattaniah: for they were counted faithful, and their duty was to distribute unto their brethren.
B016C013V014	16	13	14	Remember me, O my God, concerning this, and wipe not out my good deeds that I have done for the house of my God, and for its service.
B016C013V015	16	13	15	In those days saw I in Judah some treading wine presses on the sabbath, and bringing in sheaves, and loading donkeys; and also wine, grapes, and figs, and all manner of burdens, which they brought into Jerusalem on the sabbath day: and I testified against them about the day in which they sold provisions.
B016C013V016	16	13	16	There dwelt men of Tyre also there, who brought fish, and all manner of wares, and sold on the sabbath unto the people of Judah, and in Jerusalem.
B016C013V017	16	13	17	Then I contended with the nobles of Judah, and said unto them, What evil thing is this that you do, and profane the sabbath day?
B016C013V018	16	13	18	Did not your fathers thus, and did not our God bring all this evil upon us, and upon this city? yet you bring more wrath upon Israel by profaning the sabbath.
B016C013V019	16	13	19	And it came to pass, that when the gates of Jerusalem began to be dark before the sabbath, I commanded that the gates should be shut, and charged that they should not be opened till after the sabbath: and some of my servants set I at the gates, that there should no burden be brought in on the sabbath day.
B016C013V020	16	13	20	So the merchants and sellers of all kinds of wares lodged outside of Jerusalem once or twice.
B016C013V021	16	13	21	Then I testified against them, and said unto them, Why lodge you before the wall? if you do so again, I will lay hands on you. From that time forth came they no more on the sabbath.
B016C013V022	16	13	22	And I commanded the Levites that they should cleanse themselves, and that they should come and keep the gates, to sanctify the sabbath day. Remember me, O my God, concerning this also, and spare me according to the greatness of your mercy.
B016C013V023	16	13	23	In those days also saw I Jews that had married wives of Ashdod, of Ammon, and of Moab:
B016C013V024	16	13	24	And their children spoke half in the speech of Ashdod, and could not speak in the language of Judah, but according to the language of each people.
B016C013V025	16	13	25	And I contended with them, and pronounced them cursed, and struck certain of them, and plucked off their hair, and made them swear by God, saying, You shall not give your daughters unto their sons, nor take their daughters unto your sons, or for yourselves.
B016C013V026	16	13	26	Did not Solomon king of Israel sin by these things? yet among many nations was there no king like him, who was beloved of his God, and God made him king over all Israel: nevertheless even him did foreign women cause to sin.
B016C013V027	16	13	27	Shall we then hearken unto you to do all this great evil, to transgress against our God in marrying foreign wives?
B016C013V028	16	13	28	And one of the sons of Jehoiada, the son of Eliashib the high priest, was son-in-law to Sanballat the Horonite: therefore I chased him from me.
B016C013V029	16	13	29	Remember them, O my God, because they have defiled the priesthood, and the covenant of the priesthood, and of the Levites.
B016C013V030	16	13	30	Thus cleansed I them from everything foreign, and assigned the duties of the priests and the Levites, each one to his service;
B016C013V031	16	13	31	And provided for the wood offering, at appointed times, and for the firstfruits. Remember me, O my God, for good.
B017C001V001	17	1	1	Now it came to pass in the days of Ahasuerus, (this is Ahasuerus who reigned, from India even unto Ethiopia, over a hundred and seven and twenty provinces:)
B017C001V002	17	1	2	That in those days, when king Ahasuerus sat on the throne of his kingdom, which was in Shushan the citadel,
B017C001V003	17	1	3	In the third year of his reign, he made a feast unto all his princes and his servants; the powers of Persia and Media, the nobles and princes of the provinces, being before him:
B017C001V004	17	1	4	When he showed the riches of his glorious kingdom and the honor of his excellent majesty many days, even a hundred and fourscore days.
B017C001V005	17	1	5	And when these days were completed, the king made a feast unto all the people that were present in Shushan the citadel, both unto great and small, seven days, in the court of the garden of the king's palace;
B017C001V006	17	1	6	Where there were white, green, and blue hangings, fastened with cords of fine linen and purple to silver rings and pillars of marble: the couches were of gold and silver, upon a pavement of red, and blue, and white and black marble.
B017C001V007	17	1	7	And they gave them drink in vessels of gold, (the vessels being different one from another,) and royal wine in abundance, according to the bounty of the king.
B017C001V008	17	1	8	And the drinking was according to the law; none did compel: for so the king had ordered all the officers of his house, that they should do according to every man's pleasure.
B017C001V009	17	1	9	Also Vashti the queen made a feast for the women in the royal house which belonged to king Ahasuerus.
B017C001V010	17	1	10	On the seventh day, when the heart of the king was merry with wine, he commanded Mehuman, Biztha, Harbona, Bigtha, and Abagtha, Zethar, and Carcas, the seven chamberlains that served in the presence of Ahasuerus the king,
B017C001V011	17	1	11	To bring Vashti the queen before the king with the crown royal, to show the people and the princes her beauty: for she was fair to look upon.
B017C001V012	17	1	12	But queen Vashti refused to come at the king's commandment by his eunuchs: therefore was the king very angry, and his anger burned within him.
B017C001V013	17	1	13	Then the king said to the wise men, who knew the times, (for so was the king's manner toward all that knew law and judgment:
B017C001V014	17	1	14	And next to him was Carshena, Shethar, Admatha, Tarshish, Meres, Marsena, and Memucan, the seven princes of Persia and Media, who saw the king's face, and who sat first in the kingdom;)
B017C001V015	17	1	15	What shall we do unto queen Vashti according to law, because she has not obeyed the commandment of king Ahasuerus by the eunuchs?
B017C001V016	17	1	16	And Memucan answered before the king and the princes, Vashti the queen has not done wrong to the king only, but also to all the princes, and to all the people that are in all the provinces of king Ahasuerus.
B017C001V017	17	1	17	For this deed of the queen shall become known to all women, so that they shall despise their husbands in their eyes, when it shall be said, King Ahasuerus commanded Vashti the queen to be brought in before him, but she came not.
B017C001V018	17	1	18	Likewise shall the ladies of Persia and Media say this day unto all the king's princes, who have heard of the deed of the queen. Thus shall there arise too much contempt and wrath.
B017C001V019	17	1	19	If it please the king, let there go a royal commandment from him, and let it be written among the laws of the Persians and the Medes, that it be not altered, That Vashti come no more before king Ahasuerus; and let the king give her royal estate unto another that is better than she.
B017C001V020	17	1	20	And when the king's decree which he shall make shall be published throughout all his empire, (for it is great,) all the wives shall give to their husbands honor, both to great and small.
B017C001V021	17	1	21	And the saying pleased the king and the princes; and the king did according to the word of Memucan:
B017C001V022	17	1	22	For he sent letters into all the king's provinces, into every province according to the writing thereof, and to every people after their language, that every man should bear rule in his own house, and that it should be published according to the language of every people.
B017C002V001	17	2	1	After these things, when the wrath of king Ahasuerus was abated, he remembered Vashti, and what she had done, and what was decreed against her.
B017C002V002	17	2	2	Then said the king's servants that ministered unto him, Let there be beautiful young virgins sought out for the king:
B017C002V003	17	2	3	And let the king appoint officers in all the provinces of his kingdom, that they may gather together all the beautiful young virgins unto Shushan the citadel, to the house of the women, unto the custody of Hegai the king's eunuch, keeper of the women; and let their beautifying ointments be given them:
B017C002V004	17	2	4	And let the maiden who pleases the king be queen instead of Vashti. And the thing pleased the king; and he did so.
B017C002V005	17	2	5	Now in Shushan the citadel there was a certain Jew, whose name was Mordecai, the son of Jair, the son of Shimei, the son of Kish, a Benjamite;
B017C002V006	17	2	6	Who had been carried away from Jerusalem with the captives who had been carried away with Jeconiah king of Judah, whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried away.
B017C002V007	17	2	7	And he had brought up Hadassah, that is, Esther, his uncle's daughter: for she had neither father nor mother, and the maiden was fair and beautiful; whom Mordecai, when her father and mother were dead, took as his own daughter.
B017C002V008	17	2	8	So it came to pass, when the king's commandment and his decree was heard, and when many maidens were gathered together unto Shushan the citadel, to the custody of Hegai, that Esther was brought also unto the king's house, to the custody of Hegai, keeper of the women.
B017C002V009	17	2	9	And the maiden pleased him, and she obtained kindness of him; and he speedily gave her her beautifying ointments, with such things as belonged to her, and seven maidens, who were suitable to be given her, out of the king's house: and he moved her and her maidens unto the best place of the house of the women.
B017C002V010	17	2	10	Esther had not revealed her people nor her kindred: for Mordecai had charged her that she should not show it.
B017C002V011	17	2	11	And Mordecai walked every day before the court of the women's house, to know how Esther did, and what should become of her.
B017C002V012	17	2	12	Now when every maiden's turn was come to go in to king Ahasuerus, after she had been there twelve months, according to the regulations for the women, (for so were the days of their beautification accomplished, six months with oil of myrrh, and six months with perfumes, and with other preparations for beautifying women;)
B017C002V013	17	2	13	Then thus came every maiden unto the king; whatsoever she desired was given her to go with her out of the house of the women unto the king's house.
B017C002V014	17	2	14	In the evening she went, and the next day she returned into the second house of the women, to the custody of Shaashgaz, the king's eunuch, who kept the concubines: she came in unto the king no more, except the king delighted in her, and that she were called by name.
B017C002V015	17	2	15	Now when the turn of Esther, the daughter of Abihail the uncle of Mordecai, who had taken her for his daughter, was come to go in unto the king, she required nothing but what Hegai the king's eunuch, the keeper of the women, advised. And Esther obtained favor in the sight of all them that looked upon her.
B017C002V016	17	2	16	So Esther was taken unto king Ahasuerus into his royal house in the tenth month, which is the month Tebeth, in the seventh year of his reign.
B017C002V017	17	2	17	And the king loved Esther more than all the women, and she obtained grace and favor in his sight more than all the virgins; so that he set the royal crown upon her head, and made her queen instead of Vashti.
B017C002V018	17	2	18	Then the king made a great feast unto all his princes and his servants, even Esther's feast; and he made a holiday in all the provinces, and gave gifts, according to the liberality of the king.
B017C002V019	17	2	19	And when the virgins were gathered together the second time, then Mordecai sat in the king's gate.
B017C002V020	17	2	20	Esther had not yet made known her kindred nor her people; as Mordecai had charged her: for Esther obeyed the command of Mordecai, just as when she was brought up with him.
B017C002V021	17	2	21	In those days, while Mordecai sat in the king's gate, two of the king's eunuchs, Bigthan and Teresh, of those who kept the door, were angry, and sought to lay hands on king Ahasuerus.
B017C002V022	17	2	22	And the thing was known to Mordecai, who told it unto Esther the queen; and Esther informed the king of it in Mordecai's name.
B017C002V023	17	2	23	And when inquiry was made into the matter, it was confirmed; therefore they were both hanged on a tree: and it was written in the book of the chronicles before the king.
B017C003V001	17	3	1	After these things did king Ahasuerus promote Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, and advanced him, and set his seat above all the princes that were with him.
B017C003V002	17	3	2	And all the king's servants, that were in the king's gate, bowed, and paid homage to Haman: for the king had so commanded concerning him. But Mordecai bowed not, nor paid him homage.
B017C003V003	17	3	3	Then the king's servants, who were in the king's gate, said unto Mordecai, Why transgress you the king's commandment?
B017C003V004	17	3	4	Now it came to pass, when they spoke daily unto him, and he hearkened not unto them, that they told Haman, to see whether Mordecai's words would stand: for he had told them that he was a Jew.
B017C003V005	17	3	5	And when Haman saw that Mordecai bowed not, nor paid him homage, then was Haman full of wrath.
B017C003V006	17	3	6	And he disdained to lay hands on Mordecai alone; for they had made known to him the people of Mordecai: therefore Haman sought to destroy all the Jews that were throughout the whole kingdom of Ahasuerus, even the people of Mordecai.
B017C003V007	17	3	7	In the first month, that is, the month Nisan, in the twelfth year of king Ahasuerus, they cast Pur, that is, the lot, before Haman from day to day, and from month to month, to the twelfth month, that is, the month Adar.
B017C003V008	17	3	8	And Haman said unto king Ahasuerus, There is a certain people scattered abroad and dispersed among the people in all the provinces of your kingdom; and their laws are different from all people; neither keep they the king's laws: therefore it is not for the king's profit to tolerate them.
B017C003V009	17	3	9	If it please the king, let it be written that they may be destroyed: and I will pay ten thousand talents of silver to the hands of those that have the charge of the business, to bring it into the king's treasuries.
B017C003V010	17	3	10	And the king took his ring from his hand, and gave it unto Haman the son of Hammedatha the Agagite, the Jews' enemy.
B017C003V011	17	3	11	And the king said unto Haman, The silver is given to you, the people also, to do with them as it seems good to you.
B017C003V012	17	3	12	Then were the king's scribes called on the thirteenth day of the first month, and there was written according to all that Haman had commanded unto the king's satraps, and to the governors that were over every province, and to the rulers of every people of every province according to the writing thereof, and to every people according to their language; in the name of king Ahasuerus was it written, and sealed with the king's ring.
B017C003V013	17	3	13	And the letters were sent by couriers into all the king's provinces, to destroy, to kill, and to cause to perish, all Jews, both young and old, little children and women, in one day, even upon the thirteenth day of the twelfth month, which is the month Adar, and to take the spoil of them for a prey.
B017C003V014	17	3	14	The copy of the writing for a commandment to be given in every province was published unto all people, that they should be ready against that day.
B017C003V015	17	3	15	The couriers went out, being hastened by the king's commandment, and the decree was given in Shushan the citadel. And the king and Haman sat down to drink; but the city Shushan was perplexed.
B017C004V001	17	4	1	When Mordecai perceived all that was done, Mordecai tore his clothes, and put on sackcloth with ashes, and went out into the midst of the city, and cried with a loud and a bitter cry;
B017C004V002	17	4	2	And came even before the king's gate: for none might enter into the king's gate clothed with sackcloth.
B017C004V003	17	4	3	And in every province, wherever the king's commandment and his decree came, there was great mourning among the Jews, and fasting, and weeping, and wailing; and many lay in sackcloth and ashes.
B017C004V004	17	4	4	So Esther's maids and her eunuchs came and told it to her. Then was the queen exceedingly grieved; and she sent garments to clothe Mordecai, and to take away his sackcloth from him: but he received it not.
B017C004V005	17	4	5	Then called Esther for Hathach, one of the king's eunuchs, whom he had appointed to attend to her, and gave him a command concerning Mordecai, to learn what it was, and why it was.
B017C004V006	17	4	6	So Hathach went forth to Mordecai unto the street of the city, which was before the king's gate.
B017C004V007	17	4	7	And Mordecai told him of all that had happened unto him, and of the sum of the money that Haman had promised to pay to the king's treasuries for the Jews, to destroy them.
B017C004V008	17	4	8	Also he gave him the copy of the writing of the decree that was given at Shushan to destroy them, to show it unto Esther, and to declare it unto her, and to charge her that she should go in unto the king, to make supplication unto him, and to make request before him for her people.
B017C004V009	17	4	9	And Hathach came and told Esther the words of Mordecai.
B017C004V010	17	4	10	Again Esther spoke unto Hathach, and gave him command concerning Mordecai;
B017C004V011	17	4	11	All the king's servants, and the people of the king's provinces, do know, that whosoever, whether man or woman, shall come unto the king into the inner court, who is not called, there is one law of his to put him to death, except such to whom the king shall hold out the golden scepter, that he may live: but I have not been called to come in unto the king these thirty days.
B017C004V012	17	4	12	And they told to Mordecai Esther's words.
B017C004V013	17	4	13	Then Mordecai commanded to answer Esther, Think not to yourself that you shall escape in the king's house, more than all the Jews.
B017C004V014	17	4	14	For if you altogether hold your peace at this time, then shall relief and deliverance arise to the Jews from another place; but you and your father's house shall be destroyed: and who knows whether you are come to the kingdom for such a time as this?
B017C004V015	17	4	15	Then Esther told them to return Mordecai this answer,
B017C004V016	17	4	16	Go, gather together all the Jews that are present in Shushan, and fast for me, and neither eat nor drink three days, night or day: I also and my maidens will fast likewise; and so will I go in unto the king, which is not according to the law: and if I perish, I perish.
B017C004V017	17	4	17	So Mordecai went his way, and did according to all that Esther had commanded him.
B017C005V001	17	5	1	Now it came to pass on the third day, that Esther put on her royal apparel, and stood in the inner court of the king's house, opposite the king's house: and the king sat upon his royal throne in the royal house, opposite the entrance of the house.
B017C005V002	17	5	2	And it was so, when the king saw Esther the queen standing in the court, that she obtained favor in his sight: and the king held out to Esther the golden scepter that was in his hand. So Esther drew near, and touched the top of the scepter.
B017C005V003	17	5	3	Then said the king unto her, What do you wish, queen Esther? and what is your request? it shall be even given you to the half of the kingdom.
B017C005V004	17	5	4	And Esther answered, If it seem good unto the king, let the king and Haman come this day unto the banquet that I have prepared for him.
B017C005V005	17	5	5	Then the king said, Cause Haman to make haste, that he may do as Esther has said. So the king and Haman came to the banquet that Esther had prepared.
B017C005V006	17	5	6	And the king said unto Esther at the banquet of wine, What is your petition? and it shall be granted you: and what is your request? even to the half of the kingdom it shall be performed.
B017C005V007	17	5	7	Then answered Esther, and said, My petition and my request is;
B017C005V008	17	5	8	If I have found favor in the sight of the king, and if it please the king to grant my petition, and to perform my request, let the king and Haman come to the banquet that I shall prepare for them, and I will do tomorrow as the king has said.
B017C005V009	17	5	9	Then went Haman forth that day joyful and with a glad heart: but when Haman saw Mordecai in the king's gate, that he stood not up, nor trembled before him, he was full of indignation against Mordecai.
B017C005V010	17	5	10	Nevertheless Haman restrained himself: and when he came home, he sent and called for his friends, and Zeresh his wife.
B017C005V011	17	5	11	And Haman told them of the glory of his riches, and the multitude of his children, and all the things in which the king had promoted him, and how he had advanced him above the princes and servants of the king.
B017C005V012	17	5	12	Haman said moreover, Yea, Esther the queen did let no man come in with the king unto the banquet that she had prepared but myself; and tomorrow I am invited unto her also with the king.
B017C005V013	17	5	13	Yet all this avails me nothing, so long as I see Mordecai the Jew sitting at the king's gate.
B017C005V014	17	5	14	Then said Zeresh his wife and all his friends unto him, Let a gallows be made of fifty cubits high, and tomorrow speak you unto the king that Mordecai may be hanged thereon: then go you in merrily with the king unto the banquet. And the thing pleased Haman; and he caused the gallows to be made.
B017C006V001	17	6	1	On that night the king could not sleep, and he commanded to be brought the book of records of the chronicles; and they were read before the king.
B017C006V002	17	6	2	And it was found written, that Mordecai had told of Bigthana and Teresh, two of the king's eunuchs, the keepers of the door, who sought to lay hand on king Ahasuerus.
B017C006V003	17	6	3	And the king said, What honor and dignity has been bestowed upon Mordecai for this? Then said the king's servants that ministered unto him, There is nothing done for him.
B017C006V004	17	6	4	And the king said, Who is in the court? Now Haman had come into the outer court of the king's house, to ask the king to hang Mordecai on the gallows that he had prepared for him.
B017C006V005	17	6	5	And the king's servants said unto him, Behold, Haman stands in the court. And the king said, Let him come in.
B017C006V006	17	6	6	So Haman came in. And the king said unto him, What shall be done unto the man whom the king delights to honor? Now Haman thought in his heart, To whom would the king delight to do honor more than to myself?
B017C006V007	17	6	7	And Haman answered the king, For the man whom the king delights to honor,
