B018C042V001	18	42	1	Then Job answered the LORD, and said,
B018C042V002	18	42	2	I know that you can do everything, and that no thought can be withheld from you.
B018C042V003	18	42	3	
        
B018C042V004	18	42	4	
        
B018C042V005	18	42	5	I have heard of you by the hearing of the ear: but now my eye sees you.
B018C042V006	18	42	6	Therefore I abhor myself, and repent in dust and ashes.
B018C042V007	18	42	7	And it was so, that after the LORD had spoken these words unto Job, the LORD said to Eliphaz the Temanite, 
B018C042V008	18	42	8	
        
B018C042V009	18	42	9	So Eliphaz the Temanite and Bildad the Shuhite and Zophar the Naamathite went, and did according as the LORD commanded them: the LORD also accepted Job.
B018C042V010	18	42	10	And the LORD restored the fortunes of Job, when he prayed for his friends: also the LORD gave Job twice as much as he had before.
B018C042V011	18	42	11	Then came there unto him all his brethren, and all his sisters, and all they that had been of his acquaintance before, and did eat bread with him in his house: and they consoled him, and comforted him over all the trouble that the LORD had brought upon him: every man also gave him a piece of money, and everyone a ring of gold.
B018C042V012	18	42	12	So the LORD blessed the latter end of Job more than his beginning: for he had fourteen thousand sheep, and six thousand camels, and a thousand yoke of oxen, and a thousand female donkeys.
B018C042V013	18	42	13	He had also seven sons and three daughters.
B018C042V014	18	42	14	And he called the name of the first, Jemimah; and the name of the second, Keziah; and the name of the third, Keren-happuch.
B018C042V015	18	42	15	And in all the land were no women found so beautiful as the daughters of Job: and their father gave them inheritance among their brethren.
B018C042V016	18	42	16	After this lived Job a hundred and forty years, and saw his sons, and his sonsâ€™ sons, even four generations.
B018C042V017	18	42	17	So Job died, being old and full of days.
B019C001V001	19	1	1	Blessed is the man that walks not in the counsel of the ungodly, nor stands in the way of sinners, nor sits in the seat of the scornful.
B019C001V002	19	1	2	But his delight is in the law of the LORD; and in his law does he meditate day and night.
B019C001V003	19	1	3	And he shall be like a tree planted by the rivers of water, that brings forth its fruit in its season; his leaf also shall not wither; and whatsoever he does shall prosper.
B019C001V004	19	1	4	The ungodly are not so: but are like the chaff which the wind drives away.
B019C001V005	19	1	5	Therefore the ungodly shall not stand in the judgment, nor sinners in the congregation of the righteous.
B019C001V006	19	1	6	For the LORD knows the way of the righteous: but the way of the ungodly shall perish.
B019C002V001	19	2	1	Why do the nations rage, and the people imagine a vain thing?
B019C002V002	19	2	2	The kings of the earth set themselves, and the rulers take counsel together, against the LORD, and against his anointed, saying,
B019C002V003	19	2	3	Let us break their bands asunder, and cast away their cords from us.
B019C002V004	19	2	4	He that sits in the heavens shall laugh: the Lord shall have them in derision.
B019C002V005	19	2	5	Then shall he speak unto them in his wrath, and distress them in his great displeasure.
B019C002V006	19	2	6	
        
B019C002V007	19	2	7	I will declare the decree: the LORD has said unto me, 
B019C002V008	19	2	8	
        
B019C002V009	19	2	9	
        
B019C002V010	19	2	10	Be wise now therefore, O you kings: be instructed, you judges of the earth.
B019C002V011	19	2	11	Serve the LORD with fear, and rejoice with trembling.
B019C002V012	19	2	12	Kiss the Son, lest he be angry, and you perish in the way, when his wrath is kindled but a little. Blessed are all they that put their trust in him.
B019C003V001	19	3	1	
        
B019C003V002	19	3	2	Many there be who say of my soul, There is no help for him in God. Selah.
B019C003V003	19	3	3	But you, O LORD, are a shield for me; my glory, and the lifter up of my head.
B019C003V004	19	3	4	I cried unto the LORD with my voice, and he heard me out of his holy hill. Selah.
B019C003V005	19	3	5	I laid me down and slept; I awaked; for the LORD sustained me.
B019C003V006	19	3	6	I will not be afraid of ten thousands of people, that have set themselves against me round about.
B019C003V007	19	3	7	Arise, O LORD; save me, O my God: for you have smitten all my enemies upon the cheek bone; you have broken the teeth of the ungodly.
B019C003V008	19	3	8	Salvation belongs unto the LORD: your blessing is upon your people. Selah.
B019C004V001	19	4	1	
        
B019C004V002	19	4	2	O you sons of men, how long will you turn my glory into shame? how long will you love vanity, and seek after falsehood? Selah.
B019C004V003	19	4	3	But know that the LORD has set apart him that is godly for himself: the LORD will hear when I call unto him.
B019C004V004	19	4	4	Stand in awe, and sin not: commune with your own heart upon your bed, and be still. Selah.
B019C004V005	19	4	5	Offer the sacrifices of righteousness, and put your trust in the LORD.
B019C004V006	19	4	6	There are many that say, Who will show us any good? LORD, lift up the light of your countenance upon us.
B019C004V007	19	4	7	You have put gladness in my heart, more than in the time that their grain and their wine increased.
B019C004V008	19	4	8	I will both lay me down in peace, and sleep: for you, LORD, only make me dwell in safety.
B019C005V001	19	5	1	
        
B019C005V002	19	5	2	Hearken unto the voice of my cry, my King, and my God: for unto you will I pray.
B019C005V003	19	5	3	My voice shall you hear in the morning, O LORD; in the morning will I direct my prayer unto you, and will look up.
B019C005V004	19	5	4	For you are not a God that has pleasure in wickedness: neither shall evil dwell with you.
B019C005V005	19	5	5	The foolish shall not stand in your sight: you hate all workers of iniquity.
B019C005V006	19	5	6	You shall destroy them that speak falsehood: the LORD will abhor the bloody and deceitful man.
B019C005V007	19	5	7	But as for me, I will come into your house in the multitude of your mercy: and in your fear will I worship toward your holy temple.
B019C005V008	19	5	8	Lead me, O LORD, in your righteousness because of my enemies; make your way straight before my face.
B019C005V009	19	5	9	For there is no faithfulness in their mouth; their inward part is pure wickedness; their throat is an open sepulcher; they flatter with their tongue.
B019C005V010	19	5	10	Destroy them, O God; let them fall by their own counsels; cast them out in the multitude of their transgressions; for they have rebelled against you.
B019C005V011	19	5	11	But let all those that put their trust in you rejoice: let them ever shout for joy, because you defend them: let them also that love your name be joyful in you.
B019C005V012	19	5	12	For you, LORD, will bless the righteous; with favor will you surround him with a shield.
B019C006V001	19	6	1	
        
B019C006V002	19	6	2	Have mercy upon me, O LORD; for I am weak: O LORD, heal me; for my bones are troubled.
B019C006V003	19	6	3	My soul is also greatly troubled: but you, O LORD, how long?
B019C006V004	19	6	4	Return, O LORD, deliver my soul: oh save me for your mercies' sake.
B019C006V005	19	6	5	For in death there is no remembrance of you: in the grave who shall give you thanks?
B019C006V006	19	6	6	I am weary with my groaning; all the night make I my bed wet with tears; I water my couch with my tears.
B019C006V007	19	6	7	My eye is consumed because of grief; it grows old because of all my enemies.
B019C006V008	19	6	8	Depart from me, all you workers of iniquity; for the LORD has heard the voice of my weeping.
B019C006V009	19	6	9	The LORD has heard my supplication; the LORD will receive my prayer.
B019C006V010	19	6	10	Let all my enemies be ashamed and greatly troubled: let them return and be ashamed suddenly.
B019C007V001	19	7	1	
        
B019C007V002	19	7	2	Lest they tear my soul like a lion, rending it in pieces, while there is none to deliver.
B019C007V003	19	7	3	O LORD my God, if I have done this; if there be iniquity in my hands;
B019C007V004	19	7	4	If I have rewarded evil unto him that was at peace with me; (yea, I have delivered him that without cause is my enemy:)
B019C007V005	19	7	5	Let the enemy persecute my soul, and take it; yea, let him tread down my life upon the earth, and lay my honor in the dust. Selah.
B019C007V006	19	7	6	Arise, O LORD, in your anger, lift up yourself because of the rage of my enemies: and awake for me to the judgment that you have commanded.
B019C007V007	19	7	7	So shall the congregation of the people surround you: for their sakes therefore return you on high.
B019C007V008	19	7	8	The LORD shall judge the people: judge me, O LORD, according to my righteousness, and according to my integrity that is in me.
B019C007V009	19	7	9	Oh let the wickedness of the wicked come to an end; but establish the just: for the righteous God tests the minds and hearts.
B019C007V010	19	7	10	My defense is with God, who saves the upright in heart.
B019C007V011	19	7	11	God judges the righteous, and God is angry with the wicked every day.
B019C007V012	19	7	12	If he turns not, he will whet his sword; he has bent his bow, and made it ready.
B019C007V013	19	7	13	He has also prepared for himself the instruments of death; he makes ready his arrows against the persecutors.
B019C007V014	19	7	14	Behold, he brought forth iniquity, and has conceived mischief, and brought forth falsehood.
B019C007V015	19	7	15	He made a pit, and dug it, and has fallen into the ditch which he made.
B019C007V016	19	7	16	His mischief shall return upon his own head, and his violent dealing shall come down upon his own crown.
B019C007V017	19	7	17	I will praise the LORD according to his righteousness: and will sing praise to the name of the LORD most high.
B019C008V001	19	8	1	
        
B019C008V002	19	8	2	Out of the mouth of babes and infants have you ordained strength because of your enemies, that you might still the enemy and the avenger.
B019C008V003	19	8	3	When I consider your heavens, the work of your fingers, the moon and the stars, which you have ordained;
B019C008V004	19	8	4	What is man, that you are mindful of him? and the son of man, that you visit him?
B019C008V005	19	8	5	For you have made him a little lower than the angels, and have crowned him with glory and honor.
B019C008V006	19	8	6	You made him to have dominion over the works of your hands; you have put all things under his feet:
B019C008V007	19	8	7	All sheep and oxen, yea, and the beasts of the field;
B019C008V008	19	8	8	The fowl of the air, and the fish of the sea, and whatsoever passes through the paths of the seas.
B019C008V009	19	8	9	O LORD our Lord, how excellent is your name in all the earth!
B019C009V001	19	9	1	
        
B019C009V002	19	9	2	I will be glad and rejoice in you: I will sing praise to your name, O most High.
B019C009V003	19	9	3	When my enemies are turned back, they shall fall and perish at your presence.
B019C009V004	19	9	4	For you have maintained my right and my cause; you sat in the throne judging right.
B019C009V005	19	9	5	You have rebuked the nations, you have destroyed the wicked, you have put out their name forever and ever.
B019C009V006	19	9	6	O you enemy, destructions are come to an everlasting end: and you have destroyed cities; their memory is perished with them.
B019C009V007	19	9	7	But the LORD shall endure forever: he has prepared his throne for judgment.
B019C009V008	19	9	8	And he shall judge the world in righteousness, he shall minister judgment to the people in uprightness.
B019C009V009	19	9	9	The LORD also will be a refuge for the oppressed, a refuge in times of trouble.
B019C009V010	19	9	10	And they that know your name will put their trust in you: for you, LORD, have not forsaken them that seek you.
B019C009V011	19	9	11	Sing praises to the LORD, who dwells in Zion: declare among the people his doings.
B019C009V012	19	9	12	When he avenges blood, he remembers them: he forgets not the cry of the humble.
B019C009V013	19	9	13	Have mercy upon me, O LORD; consider my trouble which I suffer from them that hate me, you that lift me up from the gates of death:
B019C009V014	19	9	14	That I may show forth all your praise in the gates of the daughter of Zion: I will rejoice in your salvation.
B019C009V015	19	9	15	The nations are sunk down in the pit that they made: in the net which they hid is their own foot taken.
B019C009V016	19	9	16	The LORD is known by the judgment which he executes: the wicked is snared in the work of his own hands. Higgaion. Selah.
B019C009V017	19	9	17	The wicked shall be turned into sheol, and all the nations that forget God.
B019C009V018	19	9	18	For the needy shall not always be forgotten: the expectation of the poor shall not perish forever.
B019C009V019	19	9	19	Arise, O LORD; let not man prevail: let the nations be judged in your sight.
B019C009V020	19	9	20	Put them in fear, O LORD: that the nations may know themselves to be but men. Selah.
B019C010V001	19	10	1	Why stand you afar off, O LORD? why hide you yourself in times of trouble?
B019C010V002	19	10	2	The wicked in his pride does persecute the poor: let them be taken in the devices that they have imagined.
B019C010V003	19	10	3	For the wicked boasts of his heart's desire, and blesses the covetous, whom the LORD abhors.
B019C010V004	19	10	4	The wicked, through the pride of his countenance, will not seek after God: God is not in any of his thoughts.
B019C010V005	19	10	5	His ways are always prosperous; your judgments are far above, out of his sight: as for all his enemies, he sneers at them.
B019C010V006	19	10	6	He has said in his heart, I shall not be moved: for I shall never be in adversity.
B019C010V007	19	10	7	His mouth is full of cursing and deceit and fraud: under his tongue is mischief and vanity.
B019C010V008	19	10	8	He sits in the lurking places of the villages: in the secret places does he murder the innocent: his eyes are secretly set against the poor.
B019C010V009	19	10	9	He lies in wait secretly as a lion in his den: he lies in wait to catch the poor: he does catch the poor, when he draws him into his net.
B019C010V010	19	10	10	He crouches, and lies low, that the poor may fall by his strength.
B019C010V011	19	10	11	He has said in his heart, God has forgotten: he hides his face; he will never see it.
B019C010V012	19	10	12	Arise, O LORD; O God, lift up your hand: forget not the humble.
B019C010V013	19	10	13	Why does the wicked renounce God? he has said in his heart, You will not require it.
B019C010V014	19	10	14	You have seen it: for you behold mischief and spite, to repay it with your hand: the poor commits himself unto you; you are the helper of the fatherless.
B019C010V015	19	10	15	Break the arm of the wicked and the evil man: seek out his wickedness till you find none.
B019C010V016	19	10	16	The LORD is King forever and ever: the nations are perished out of his land.
B019C010V017	19	10	17	LORD, you have heard the desire of the humble: you will prepare their heart, you will cause your ear to hear:
B019C010V018	19	10	18	To judge the fatherless and the oppressed, that the man of the earth may no more oppress.
B019C011V001	19	11	1	
        
B019C011V002	19	11	2	For, lo, the wicked bend their bow, they make ready their arrow upon the string, that they may secretly shoot at the upright in heart.
B019C011V003	19	11	3	If the foundations be destroyed, what can the righteous do?
B019C011V004	19	11	4	The LORD is in his holy temple, the LORD'S throne is in heaven: his eyes behold, his eyelids test, the children of men.
B019C011V005	19	11	5	The LORD tests the righteous: but the wicked and him that loves violence his soul hates.
B019C011V006	19	11	6	Upon the wicked he shall rain snares, fire and brimstone, and a horrible tempest: this shall be the portion of their cup.
B019C011V007	19	11	7	For the righteous LORD loves righteousness; his countenance does behold the upright.
B019C012V001	19	12	1	
        
B019C012V002	19	12	2	They speak vanity every one with his neighbor: with flattering lips and with a double heart do they speak.
B019C012V003	19	12	3	The LORD shall cut off all flattering lips, and the tongue that speaks proud things:
B019C012V004	19	12	4	Who have said, With our tongue will we prevail; our lips are our own: who is lord over us?
B019C012V005	19	12	5	
        
B019C012V006	19	12	6	The words of the LORD are pure words: as silver tested in a furnace of earth, purified seven times.
B019C012V007	19	12	7	You shall keep them, O LORD, you shall preserve them from this generation forever.
B019C012V008	19	12	8	The wicked prowl on every side, when vile men are exalted.
B019C013V001	19	13	1	
        
B019C013V002	19	13	2	How long shall I take counsel in my soul, having sorrow in my heart daily? how long shall my enemy be exalted over me?
B019C013V003	19	13	3	Consider and hear me, O LORD my God: lighten my eyes, lest I sleep the sleep of death;
B019C013V004	19	13	4	Lest my enemy say, I have prevailed against him; and those that trouble me rejoice when I am moved.
B019C013V005	19	13	5	But I have trusted in your mercy; my heart shall rejoice in your salvation.
B019C013V006	19	13	6	I will sing unto the LORD, because he has dealt bountifully with me.
B019C014V001	19	14	1	
        
B019C014V002	19	14	2	The LORD looked down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there were any that did understand, and seek God.
B019C014V003	19	14	3	They are all gone aside, they are all together become filthy: there is none that does good, no, not one.
B019C014V004	19	14	4	Have all the workers of iniquity no knowledge? who eat up my people as they eat bread, and call not upon the LORD.
B019C014V005	19	14	5	There were they in great fear: for God is in the generation of the righteous.
B019C014V006	19	14	6	You have shamed the counsel of the poor, but the LORD is his refuge.
B019C014V007	19	14	7	Oh that the salvation of Israel were come out of Zion! when the LORD brings back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel shall be glad.
B019C015V001	19	15	1	
        
B019C015V002	19	15	2	He that walks uprightly, and works righteousness, and speaks the truth in his heart.
B019C015V003	19	15	3	He that backbites not with his tongue, nor does evil to his neighbor, nor takes up a reproach against his neighbor.
B019C015V004	19	15	4	In whose eyes a vile person is despised; but he honors them that fear the LORD. He that swears to his own hurt, and changes not.
B019C015V005	19	15	5	He that puts not out his money at interest, nor takes reward against the innocent. He that does these things shall never be moved.
B019C016V001	19	16	1	
        
B019C016V002	19	16	2	O my soul, you have said unto the LORD, You are my Lord: my goodness reaches not to you;
B019C016V003	19	16	3	But to the saints that are in the earth, and to the noble, in whom is all my delight.
B019C016V004	19	16	4	Their sorrows shall be multiplied that hasten after another god: their drink offerings of blood will I not offer, nor take up their names upon my lips.
B019C016V005	19	16	5	The LORD is the portion of my inheritance and of my cup: you maintain my lot.
B019C016V006	19	16	6	The lines are fallen unto me in pleasant places; yea, I have a goodly heritage.
B019C016V007	19	16	7	I will bless the LORD, who has given me counsel: my heart also instructs me in the night seasons.
B019C016V008	19	16	8	I have set the LORD always before me: because he is at my right hand, I shall not be moved.
B019C016V009	19	16	9	Therefore my heart is glad, and my glory rejoices: my flesh also shall rest in hope.
B019C016V010	19	16	10	For you will not leave my soul in sheol; neither will you allow your Holy One to see corruption.
B019C016V011	19	16	11	You will show me the path of life: in your presence is fullness of joy; at your right hand there are pleasures forevermore.
B019C017V001	19	17	1	
        
B019C017V002	19	17	2	Let my vindication come forth from your presence; let your eyes behold the things that are right.
B019C017V003	19	17	3	You have proved my heart; you have visited me in the night; you have tested me, and shall find nothing; I have purposed that my mouth shall not transgress.
B019C017V004	19	17	4	Concerning the works of men, by the word of your lips I have kept myself from the paths of the destroyer.
B019C017V005	19	17	5	Hold up my steps in your paths, that my feet slip not.
B019C017V006	19	17	6	I have called upon you, for you will hear me, O God: incline your ear unto me, and hear my speech.
B019C017V007	19	17	7	Show your marvelous lovingkindness, O you that save by your right hand them who put their trust in you from those that rise up against them.
B019C017V008	19	17	8	Keep me as the apple of the eye, hide me under the shadow of your wings,
B019C017V009	19	17	9	From the wicked that oppress me, from my deadly enemies, who surround me.
B019C017V010	19	17	10	They are enclosed in their own fat hearts: with their mouth they speak proudly.
B019C017V011	19	17	11	They have now surrounded us in our steps: they have set their eyes, crouching down to the earth;
B019C017V012	19	17	12	Like as a lion that is greedy of its prey, and as it were a young lion lurking in secret places.
B019C017V013	19	17	13	Arise, O LORD, confront him, cast him down: deliver my soul from the wicked, by your sword:
B019C017V014	19	17	14	From men by your hand, O LORD, from men of the world, who have their portion in this life, and whose belly you fill with your hid treasure: they are full of children, and leave the rest of their substance to their babes.
B019C017V015	19	17	15	As for me, I will behold your face in righteousness: I shall be satisfied, when I awake, with your likeness.
B019C018V001	19	18	1	
        
B019C018V002	19	18	2	The LORD is my rock, and my fortress, and my deliverer; my God, my strength, in whom I will trust; my shield, and the horn of my salvation, and my high tower.
B019C018V003	19	18	3	I will call upon the LORD, who is worthy to be praised: so shall I be saved from my enemies.
B019C018V004	19	18	4	The sorrows of death surrounded me, and the floods of ungodly men made me afraid.
B019C018V005	19	18	5	The sorrows of sheol surrounded me: the snares of death confronted me.
B019C018V006	19	18	6	In my distress I called upon the LORD, and cried unto my God: he heard my voice out of his temple, and my cry came before him, even into his ears.
B019C018V007	19	18	7	Then the earth shook and trembled; the foundations also of the hills moved and were shaken, because he was angry.
B019C018V008	19	18	8	There went up a smoke out of his nostrils, and fire out of his mouth devoured: coals were kindled by it.
B019C018V009	19	18	9	He bowed the heavens also, and came down: and darkness was under his feet.
B019C018V010	19	18	10	And he rode upon a cherub, and did fly: yea, he did fly upon the wings of the wind.
B019C018V011	19	18	11	He made darkness his secret place; his canopy round about him were dark waters and thick clouds of the skies.
B019C018V012	19	18	12	At the brightness that was before him his thick clouds passed, with hailstones and coals of fire.
B019C018V013	19	18	13	The LORD also thundered in the heavens, and the Highest gave his voice; hail stones and coals of fire.
B019C018V014	19	18	14	Yea, he sent out his arrows, and scattered them; and he shot out lightnings, and vanquished them.
B019C018V015	19	18	15	Then the channels of the sea were seen, and the foundations of the world were uncovered at your rebuke, O LORD, at the blast of the breath of your nostrils.
B019C018V016	19	18	16	He sent from above, he took me, he drew me out of many waters.
B019C018V017	19	18	17	He delivered me from my strong enemy, and from them who hated me: for they were too strong for me.
B019C018V018	19	18	18	They confronted me in the day of my calamity: but the LORD was my stay.
B019C018V019	19	18	19	He brought me forth also into a large place; he delivered me, because he delighted in me.
B019C018V020	19	18	20	The LORD rewarded me according to my righteousness; according to the cleanness of my hands has he recompensed me.
B019C018V021	19	18	21	For I have kept the ways of the LORD, and have not wickedly departed from my God.
B019C018V022	19	18	22	For all his judgments were before me, and I did not put away his statutes from me.
B019C018V023	19	18	23	I was also upright before him, and I kept myself from my iniquity.
B019C018V024	19	18	24	Therefore has the LORD recompensed me according to my righteousness, according to the cleanness of my hands in his eyesight.
B019C018V025	19	18	25	With the merciful you will show yourself merciful; with an upright man you will show yourself upright;
B019C018V026	19	18	26	With the pure you will show yourself pure; and with the devious you will show yourself shrewd.
B019C018V027	19	18	27	For you will save the humble people; but will bring down haughty looks.
B019C018V028	19	18	28	For you will light my lamp: the LORD my God will enlighten my darkness.
B019C018V029	19	18	29	For by you I have advanced against a troop; and by my God have I leaped over a wall.
B019C018V030	19	18	30	As for God, his way is perfect: the word of the LORD is proven: he is a shield to all those that trust in him.
B019C018V031	19	18	31	For who is God except the LORD? or who is a rock except our God?
B019C018V032	19	18	32	It is God that girds me with strength, and makes my way perfect.
B019C018V033	19	18	33	He makes my feet like hinds' feet, and sets me upon my high places.
B019C018V034	19	18	34	He teaches my hands to make war, so that a bow of bronze is bent by my arms.
B019C018V035	19	18	35	You have also given me the shield of your salvation: and your right hand has held me up, and your gentleness has made me great.
B019C018V036	19	18	36	You have enlarged my path under me, that my feet did not slip.
B019C018V037	19	18	37	I have pursued my enemies, and overtaken them: neither did I turn again till they were consumed.
B019C018V038	19	18	38	I have wounded them that they were not able to rise: they are fallen under my feet.
B019C018V039	19	18	39	For you have girded me with strength unto the battle: you have subdued under me those that rose up against me.
B019C018V040	19	18	40	You have also given me the necks of my enemies; that I might destroy them that hate me.
B019C018V041	19	18	41	They cried, but there was none to save them: even unto the LORD, but he answered them not.
B019C018V042	19	18	42	Then did I beat them as fine as the dust before the wind: I did cast them out as the dirt in the streets.
B019C018V043	19	18	43	You have delivered me from the strivings of the people; and you have made me the head of the nations: a people whom I have not known shall serve me.
B019C018V044	19	18	44	As soon as they hear of me, they shall obey me: the foreigners shall submit themselves unto me.
B019C018V045	19	18	45	The foreigners shall fade away, and be frightened out of their fortresses.
B019C018V046	19	18	46	The LORD lives; and blessed be my rock; and let the God of my salvation be exalted.
B019C018V047	19	18	47	It is God that avenges me, and subdues the people under me.
B019C018V048	19	18	48	He delivers me from my enemies: yea, you lift me up above those that rise up against me: you have delivered me from the violent man.
B019C018V049	19	18	49	Therefore will I give thanks unto you, O LORD, among the nations, and sing praises unto your name.
B019C018V050	19	18	50	Great deliverance gives he to his king; and shows mercy to his anointed, to David, and to his descendants forevermore.
B019C019V001	19	19	1	
        
B019C019V002	19	19	2	Day unto day utters speech, and night unto night shows knowledge.
B019C019V003	19	19	3	There is no speech nor language, where their voice is not heard.
B019C019V004	19	19	4	Their line is gone out through all the earth, and their words to the end of the world. In them has he set a tabernacle for the sun,
B019C019V005	19	19	5	Which is as a bridegroom coming out of his chamber, and rejoices as a strong man to run a race.
B019C019V006	19	19	6	Its going forth is from the end of the heaven, and its circuit unto the ends of it: and there is nothing hid from the heat thereof.
B019C019V007	19	19	7	The law of the LORD is perfect, converting the soul: the testimony of the LORD is sure, making wise the simple.
B019C019V008	19	19	8	The statutes of the LORD are right, rejoicing the heart: the commandment of the LORD is pure, enlightening the eyes.
B019C019V009	19	19	9	The fear of the LORD is clean, enduring forever: the judgments of the LORD are true and righteous altogether.
B019C019V010	19	19	10	More to be desired are they than gold, yea, than much fine gold: sweeter also than honey and the honeycomb.
B019C019V011	19	19	11	Moreover by them is your servant warned: and in keeping of them there is great reward.
B019C019V012	19	19	12	Who can understand his errors? cleanse me from secret faults.
B019C019V013	19	19	13	Keep back your servant also from presumptuous sins; let them not have dominion over me: then shall I be upright, and I shall be innocent of great transgression.
B019C019V014	19	19	14	Let the words of my mouth, and the meditation of my heart, be acceptable in your sight, O LORD, my strength, and my redeemer.
B019C020V001	19	20	1	
        
B019C020V002	19	20	2	Send you help from the sanctuary, and strengthen you out of Zion;
B019C020V003	19	20	3	Remember all your offerings, and accept your burnt sacrifice; Selah.
B019C020V004	19	20	4	Grant you according to your own heart, and fulfill all your plans.
B019C020V005	19	20	5	We will rejoice in your salvation, and in the name of our God we will set up our banners: the LORD fulfill all your petitions.
B019C020V006	19	20	6	Now know I that the LORD saves his anointed; he will hear him from his holy heaven with the saving strength of his right hand.
B019C020V007	19	20	7	Some trust in chariots, and some in horses: but we will remember the name of the LORD our God.
B019C020V008	19	20	8	They are brought down and fallen: but we are risen, and stand upright.
B019C020V009	19	20	9	Save, LORD: let the king hear us when we call.
B019C021V001	19	21	1	
        
B019C021V002	19	21	2	You have given him his heart's desire, and have not withheld the request of his lips. Selah.
B019C021V003	19	21	3	For you meet him with the blessings of goodness: you set a crown of pure gold on his head.
B019C021V004	19	21	4	He asked life of you, and you gave it to him, even length of days forever and ever.
B019C021V005	19	21	5	His glory is great in your salvation: honor and majesty have you laid upon him.
B019C021V006	19	21	6	For you have made him most blessed forever: you have made him exceedingly glad with your presence.
B019C021V007	19	21	7	For the king trusts in the LORD, and through the mercy of the most High he shall not be moved.
B019C021V008	19	21	8	Your hand shall find out all your enemies: your right hand shall find out those that hate you.
B019C021V009	19	21	9	You shall make them as a fiery oven in the time of your anger: the LORD shall swallow them up in his wrath, and the fire shall devour them.
B019C021V010	19	21	10	Their offspring shall you destroy from the earth, and their descendants from among the children of men.
B019C021V011	19	21	11	For they intended evil against you: they devised a mischievous act, which they are not able to perform.
B019C021V012	19	21	12	Therefore shall you make them turn their back, when you shall make ready your arrows upon your strings toward their face.
B019C021V013	19	21	13	Be exalted, LORD, in your own strength: so will we sing and praise your power.
B019C022V001	19	22	1	
        
B019C022V002	19	22	2	O my God, I cry in the daytime, but you hear not; and in the night season, and am not silent.
B019C022V003	19	22	3	But you are holy, O you that inhabit the praises of Israel.
B019C022V004	19	22	4	Our fathers trusted in you: they trusted, and you did deliver them.
B019C022V005	19	22	5	They cried unto you, and were delivered: they trusted in you, and were not disappointed.
B019C022V006	19	22	6	But I am a worm, and no man; a reproach of men, and despised of the people.
B019C022V007	19	22	7	All they that see me laugh me to scorn: they shoot out the lip, they shake the head, saying,
B019C022V008	19	22	8	He trusted in the LORD that he would deliver him: let him deliver him, seeing he delighted in him.
B019C022V009	19	22	9	But you are he that took me out of the womb: you did make me hope when I was upon my mother's breasts.
B019C022V010	19	22	10	I was cast upon you from birth: you are my God from my mother's womb.
B019C022V011	19	22	11	Be not far from me; for trouble is near; for there is none to help.
B019C022V012	19	22	12	Many bulls have compassed me: strong bulls of Bashan have beset me round about.
B019C022V013	19	22	13	They gaped on me with their mouths, as a ravening and a roaring lion.
B019C022V014	19	22	14	I am poured out like water, and all my bones are out of joint: my heart is like wax; it is melted in the midst of my body.
B019C022V015	19	22	15	My strength is dried up like a potsherd; and my tongue clings to my jaws; and you have brought me to the dust of death.
B019C022V016	19	22	16	For dogs have compassed me: the assembly of the wicked have enclosed me: they pierced my hands and my feet.
B019C022V017	19	22	17	I can count all my bones: they look and stare upon me.
B019C022V018	19	22	18	They part my garments among them, and cast lots for my clothing.
B019C022V019	19	22	19	But be not far from me, O LORD: O my strength, haste you to help me.
B019C022V020	19	22	20	Deliver my soul from the sword; my life from the power of the dog.
B019C022V021	19	22	21	Save me from the lion's mouth: for you have heard me from the horns of the wild oxen.
B019C022V022	19	22	22	I will declare your name unto my brethren: in the midst of the congregation will I praise you.
B019C022V023	19	22	23	You that fear the LORD, praise him; all you descendants of Jacob, glorify him; and fear him, all you descendants of Israel.
B019C022V024	19	22	24	For he has not despised nor abhorred the affliction of the afflicted; neither has he hid his face from him; but when he cried unto him, he heard.
B019C022V025	19	22	25	My praise shall be of you in the great congregation: I will pay my vows before them that fear him.
B019C022V026	19	22	26	The meek shall eat and be satisfied: they shall praise the LORD that seek him: your heart shall live forever.
B019C022V027	19	22	27	All the ends of the world shall remember and turn unto the LORD: and all the kindreds of the nations shall worship before you.
B019C022V028	19	22	28	For the kingdom is the LORD'S: and he is the governor among the nations.
B019C022V029	19	22	29	All the prosperous of earth shall eat and worship: all they that go down to the dust shall bow before him: and none can keep alive his own soul.
B019C022V030	19	22	30	A posterity shall serve him; it shall be accounted to the Lord for a generation.
B019C022V031	19	22	31	They shall come, and shall declare his righteousness unto a people that shall be born, that he has done this.
B019C023V001	19	23	1	
        
B019C023V002	19	23	2	He makes me to lie down in green pastures: he leads me beside the still waters.
B019C023V003	19	23	3	He restores my soul: he leads me in the paths of righteousness for his name's sake.
B019C023V004	19	23	4	Yea, though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil: for you are with me; your rod and your staff they comfort me.
B019C023V005	19	23	5	You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies: you anoint my head with oil; my cup runs over.
B019C023V006	19	23	6	Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life: and I will dwell in the house of the LORD forever.
B019C024V001	19	24	1	
        
B019C024V002	19	24	2	For he has founded it upon the seas, and established it upon the floods.
B019C024V003	19	24	3	Who shall ascend into the hill of the LORD? or who shall stand in his holy place?
B019C024V004	19	24	4	He that has clean hands, and a pure heart; who has not lifted up his soul unto vanity, nor sworn deceitfully.
B019C024V005	19	24	5	He shall receive the blessing from the LORD, and righteousness from the God of his salvation.
B019C024V006	19	24	6	This is the generation of them that seek him, that seek your face, O Jacob. Selah.
B019C024V007	19	24	7	Lift up your heads, O you gates; and be you lifted up, you everlasting doors; and the King of glory shall come in.
B019C024V008	19	24	8	Who is this King of glory? The LORD strong and mighty, the LORD mighty in battle.
B019C024V009	19	24	9	Lift up your heads, O you gates; even lift them up, you everlasting doors; and the King of glory shall come in.
B019C024V010	19	24	10	Who is this King of glory? The LORD of hosts, he is the King of glory. Selah.
B019C025V001	19	25	1	
        
B019C025V002	19	25	2	O my God, I trust in you: let me not be ashamed, let not my enemies triumph over me.
B019C025V003	19	25	3	Yea, let none that wait on you be ashamed: let them be ashamed who transgress without cause.
B019C025V004	19	25	4	Show me your ways, O LORD; teach me your paths.
B019C025V005	19	25	5	Lead me in your truth, and teach me: for you are the God of my salvation; on you do I wait all the day.
B019C025V006	19	25	6	Remember, O LORD, your tender mercies and your lovingkindnesses; for they have been ever of old.
B019C025V007	19	25	7	Remember not the sins of my youth, nor my transgressions: according to your mercy remember me for your goodness' sake, O LORD.
B019C025V008	19	25	8	Good and upright is the LORD: therefore will he teach sinners in the way.
B019C025V009	19	25	9	The meek will he guide in justice: and the meek will he teach his way.
B019C025V010	19	25	10	All the paths of the LORD are mercy and truth unto such as keep his covenant and his testimonies.
B019C025V011	19	25	11	For your name's sake, O LORD, pardon my iniquity; for it is great.
B019C025V012	19	25	12	What man is he that fears the LORD? him shall he teach in the way that he shall choose.
B019C025V013	19	25	13	His soul shall dwell at ease; and his descendants shall inherit the earth.
B019C025V014	19	25	14	The secret of the LORD is with them that fear him; and he will show them his covenant.
B019C025V015	19	25	15	My eyes are ever toward the LORD; for he shall pluck my feet out of the net.
B019C025V016	19	25	16	Turn you unto me, and have mercy upon me; for I am desolate and afflicted.
B019C025V017	19	25	17	The troubles of my heart are enlarged: O bring me out of my distresses.
B019C025V018	19	25	18	Look upon my affliction and my pain; and forgive all my sins.
B019C025V019	19	25	19	Consider my enemies; for they are many; and they hate me with cruel hatred.
B019C025V020	19	25	20	O keep my soul, and deliver me: let me not be ashamed; for I put my trust in you.
B019C025V021	19	25	21	Let integrity and uprightness preserve me; for I wait on you.
B019C025V022	19	25	22	Redeem Israel, O God, out of all his troubles.
B019C026V001	19	26	1	
        
B019C026V002	19	26	2	Examine me, O LORD, and prove me; try my heart and my mind.
B019C026V003	19	26	3	For your lovingkindness is before my eyes: and I have walked in your truth.
B019C026V004	19	26	4	I have not sat with vain persons, neither will I go in with hypocrites.
B019C026V005	19	26	5	I have hated the congregation of evildoers; and will not sit with the wicked.
B019C026V006	19	26	6	I will wash my hands in innocence: so will I go about your altar, O LORD:
B019C026V007	19	26	7	That I may proclaim with the voice of thanksgiving, and tell of all your wondrous works.
B019C026V008	19	26	8	LORD, I have loved the habitation of your house, and the place where your honor dwells.
B019C026V009	19	26	9	Gather not my soul with sinners, nor my life with bloody men:
B019C026V010	19	26	10	In whose hands is mischief, and their right hand is full of bribes.
B019C026V011	19	26	11	But as for me, I will walk in my integrity: redeem me, and be merciful unto me.
B019C026V012	19	26	12	My foot stands in an even place: in the congregations will I bless the LORD.
B019C027V001	19	27	1	
        
B019C027V002	19	27	2	When the wicked, even my enemies and my foes, came upon me to eat up my flesh, they stumbled and fell.
B019C027V003	19	27	3	Though a host should encamp against me, my heart shall not fear: though war should rise against me, in this will I be confident.
B019C027V004	19	27	4	One thing have I desired of the LORD, that will I seek after; that I may dwell in the house of the LORD all the days of my life, to behold the beauty of the LORD, and to inquire in his temple.
B019C027V005	19	27	5	For in the time of trouble he shall hide me in his pavilion: in the secret place of his tabernacle shall he hide me; he shall set me up upon a rock.
B019C027V006	19	27	6	And now shall my head be lifted up above my enemies round about me: therefore will I offer in his tabernacle sacrifices of joy; I will sing, yea, I will sing praises unto the LORD.
B019C027V007	19	27	7	Hear, O LORD, when I cry with my voice: have mercy also upon me, and answer me.
B019C027V008	19	27	8	When you said, Seek my face; my heart said unto you, your face, LORD, will I seek.
B019C027V009	19	27	9	Hide not your face far from me; put not your servant away in anger: you have been my help; leave me not, neither forsake me, O God of my salvation.
B019C027V010	19	27	10	When my father and my mother forsake me, then the LORD will take me up.
B019C027V011	19	27	11	Teach me your way, O LORD, and lead me in a level path, because of my enemies.
B019C027V012	19	27	12	Deliver me not over unto the will of my enemies: for false witnesses are risen up against me, and such as breathe out cruelty.
B019C027V013	19	27	13	I would have fainted, unless I had believed to see the goodness of the LORD in the land of the living.
B019C027V014	19	27	14	Wait on the LORD: be of good courage, and he shall strengthen your heart: wait, I say, on the LORD.
B019C028V001	19	28	1	
        
B019C028V002	19	28	2	Hear the voice of my supplications, when I cry unto you, when I lift up my hands toward your holy sanctuary.
B019C028V003	19	28	3	Draw me not away with the wicked, and with the workers of iniquity, who speak peace to their neighbors, but mischief is in their hearts.
B019C028V004	19	28	4	Give them according to their deeds, and according to the wickedness of their endeavors: give them after the work of their hands; render to them what they deserve.
B019C028V005	19	28	5	Because they regard not the works of the LORD, nor the operation of his hands, he shall destroy them, and not build them up.
B019C028V006	19	28	6	Blessed be the LORD, because he has heard the voice of my supplications.
B019C028V007	19	28	7	The LORD is my strength and my shield; my heart trusted in him, and I am helped: therefore my heart greatly rejoices; and with my song will I praise him.
B019C028V008	19	28	8	The LORD is their strength, and he is the saving strength of his anointed.
B019C028V009	19	28	9	Save your people, and bless your inheritance: feed them also, and lift them up forever.
B019C029V001	19	29	1	
        
B019C029V002	19	29	2	Give unto the LORD the glory due unto his name; worship the LORD in the beauty of holiness.
B019C029V003	19	29	3	The voice of the LORD is upon the waters: the God of glory thunders: the LORD is upon many waters.
B019C029V004	19	29	4	The voice of the LORD is powerful; the voice of the LORD is full of majesty.
B019C029V005	19	29	5	The voice of the LORD breaks the cedars; yea, the LORD breaks the cedars of Lebanon.
B019C029V006	19	29	6	He makes them also to skip like a calf; Lebanon and Sirion like a young wild ox.
B019C029V007	19	29	7	The voice of the LORD divides the flames of fire.
B019C029V008	19	29	8	The voice of the LORD shakes the wilderness; the LORD shakes the wilderness of Kadesh.
B019C029V009	19	29	9	The voice of the LORD makes the hinds to calve, and strips bare the forests: and in his temple does every one speak of his glory.
B019C029V010	19	29	10	The LORD sits upon the flood; yea, the LORD sits as King forever.
B019C029V011	19	29	11	The LORD will give strength unto his people; the LORD will bless his people with peace.
B019C030V001	19	30	1	
        
B019C030V002	19	30	2	O LORD my God, I cried unto you, and you have healed me.
B019C030V003	19	30	3	O LORD, you have brought up my soul from the grave: you have kept me alive, that I should not go down to the pit.
B019C030V004	19	30	4	Sing unto the LORD, O you saints of his, and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.
B019C030V005	19	30	5	For his anger endures but for a moment; in his favor is life: weeping may endure for a night, but joy comes in the morning.
B019C030V006	19	30	6	And in my prosperity I said, I shall never be moved.
B019C030V007	19	30	7	LORD, by your favor you have made my mountain to stand strong: you did hide your face, and I was troubled.
B019C030V008	19	30	8	I cried to you, O LORD; and unto the LORD I made supplication.
B019C030V009	19	30	9	What profit is there in my blood, when I go down to the pit? Shall the dust praise you? shall it declare your truth?
B019C030V010	19	30	10	Hear, O LORD, and have mercy upon me: LORD, be my helper.
B019C030V011	19	30	11	You have turned for me my mourning into dancing: you have put off my sackcloth, and girded me with gladness;
B019C030V012	19	30	12	To the end that my glory may sing praise to you, and not be silent. O LORD my God, I will give thanks unto you forever.
B019C031V001	19	31	1	
        
B019C031V002	19	31	2	Bow down your ear to me; deliver me speedily: be my strong rock, for a house of defense to save me.
B019C031V003	19	31	3	For you are my rock and my fortress; therefore for your name's sake lead me, and guide me.
B019C031V004	19	31	4	Pull me out of the net that they have laid secretly for me: for you are my strength.
B019C031V005	19	31	5	Into your hand I commit my spirit: you have redeemed me, O LORD God of truth.
B019C031V006	19	31	6	I have hated them that regard vain idols: but I trust in the LORD.
B019C031V007	19	31	7	I will be glad and rejoice in your mercy: for you have considered my trouble; you have known my soul in adversities;
B019C031V008	19	31	8	And have not shut me up into the hand of the enemy: you have set my feet in a wide place.
B019C031V009	19	31	9	Have mercy upon me, O LORD, for I am in trouble: my eye is consumed with grief, yea, my soul and my body.
B019C031V010	19	31	10	For my life is spent with grief, and my years with sighing: my strength fails because of my iniquity, and my bones are consumed.
B019C031V011	19	31	11	I was a reproach among all my enemies, but especially among my neighbors, and a horror to my acquaintance: they that did see me outside fled from me.
B019C031V012	19	31	12	I am forgotten as a dead man out of mind: I am like a broken vessel.
B019C031V013	19	31	13	For I have heard the slander of many: fear was on every side: while they took counsel together against me, they devised to take away my life.
B019C031V014	19	31	14	But I trusted in you, O LORD: I said, you are my God.
B019C031V015	19	31	15	My times are in your hand: deliver me from the hand of my enemies, and from them that persecute me.
B019C031V016	19	31	16	Make your face to shine upon your servant: save me for your mercies' sake.
B019C031V017	19	31	17	Let me not be ashamed, O LORD; for I have called upon you: let the wicked be ashamed, and let them be silent in the grave.
B019C031V018	19	31	18	Let the lying lips be put to silence; who speak grievous things proudly and contemptuously against the righteous.
B019C031V019	19	31	19	Oh how great is your goodness, which you have laid up for them that fear you; which you have wrought for them that trust in you before the sons of men!
B019C031V020	19	31	20	You shall hide them in the secret of your presence from the pride of man: you shall keep them secretly in a pavilion from the strife of tongues.
B019C031V021	19	31	21	Blessed be the LORD: for he has showed me his marvelous kindness in a strong city.
B019C031V022	19	31	22	For I said in my haste, I am cut off from before your eyes: nevertheless you heard the voice of my supplications when I cried unto you.
B019C031V023	19	31	23	O love the LORD, all you his saints: for the LORD preserves the faithful, and plentifully repays the proud doer.
B019C031V024	19	31	24	Be of good courage, and he shall strengthen your heart, all you that hope in the LORD.
B019C032V001	19	32	1	
        
B019C032V002	19	32	2	Blessed is the man unto whom the LORD imputes not iniquity, and in whose spirit there is no guile.
B019C032V003	19	32	3	When I kept silence, my bones grew old through my groaning all the day long.
B019C032V004	19	32	4	For day and night your hand was heavy upon me: my strength is turned into the drought of summer. Selah.
B019C032V005	19	32	5	I acknowledged my sin unto you, and my iniquity have I not hid. I said, I will confess my transgressions unto the LORD; and you forgave the iniquity of my sin. Selah.
B019C032V006	19	32	6	For this shall every one that is godly pray unto you in a time when you may be found: surely in the floods of great waters they shall not come near unto him.
B019C032V007	19	32	7	You are my hiding place; you shall preserve me from trouble; you shall surround me about with songs of deliverance. Selah.
B019C032V008	19	32	8	I will instruct you and teach you in the way which you shall go: I will guide you with my eye.
B019C032V009	19	32	9	Be you not as the horse, or as the mule, which have no understanding: whose mouth must be held in with bit and bridle, else they come not near unto you.
B019C032V010	19	32	10	Many sorrows shall be to the wicked: but he that trusts in the LORD, mercy shall surround him.
B019C032V011	19	32	11	Be glad in the LORD, and rejoice, you righteous: and shout for joy, all you that are upright in heart.
B019C033V001	19	33	1	Rejoice in the LORD, O you righteous: for praise is fitting for the upright.
B019C033V002	19	33	2	Praise the LORD with harp: sing unto him with the psaltery and an instrument of ten strings.
B019C033V003	19	33	3	Sing unto him a new song; play skillfully with a loud noise.
B019C033V004	19	33	4	For the word of the LORD is right; and all his works are done in truth.
B019C033V005	19	33	5	He loves righteousness and justice: the earth is full of the goodness of the LORD.
B019C033V006	19	33	6	By the word of the LORD were the heavens made; and all the host of them by the breath of his mouth.
B019C033V007	19	33	7	He gathers the waters of the sea together as a heap: he lays up the depth in storehouses.
B019C033V008	19	33	8	Let all the earth fear the LORD: let all the inhabitants of the world stand in awe of him.
B019C033V009	19	33	9	For he spoke, and it was done; he commanded, and it stood fast.
B019C033V010	19	33	10	The LORD brings the counsel of the nations to nothing: he makes the devices of the people of none effect.
B019C033V011	19	33	11	The counsel of the LORD stands forever, the thoughts of his heart to all generations.
B019C033V012	19	33	12	Blessed is the nation whose God is the LORD; and the people whom he has chosen for his own inheritance.
B019C033V013	19	33	13	The LORD looks from heaven; he beholds all the sons of men.
B019C033V014	19	33	14	From the place of his habitation he looks upon all the inhabitants of the earth.
B019C033V015	19	33	15	He fashions their hearts alike; he considers all their works.
B019C033V016	19	33	16	There is no king saved by the multitude of a host: a mighty man is not delivered by much strength.
B019C033V017	19	33	17	A horse is a vain thing for safety: neither shall he deliver any by his great strength.
B019C033V018	19	33	18	Behold, the eye of the LORD is upon them that fear him, upon them that hope in his mercy;
B019C033V019	19	33	19	To deliver their soul from death, and to keep them alive in famine.
B019C033V020	19	33	20	Our soul waits for the LORD: he is our help and our shield.
B019C033V021	19	33	21	For our heart shall rejoice in him, because we have trusted in his holy name.
B019C033V022	19	33	22	Let your mercy, O LORD, be upon us, according as we hope in you.
B019C034V001	19	34	1	
        
B019C034V002	19	34	2	My soul shall make its boast in the LORD: the humble shall hear thereof, and be glad.
B019C034V003	19	34	3	O magnify the LORD with me, and let us exalt his name together.
B019C034V004	19	34	4	I sought the LORD, and he heard me, and delivered me from all my fears.
B019C034V005	19	34	5	They looked unto him, and were radiant: and their faces were not ashamed.
B019C034V006	19	34	6	This poor man cried, and the LORD heard him, and saved him out of all his troubles.
B019C034V007	19	34	7	The angel of the LORD encamps round about them that fear him, and delivers them.
B019C034V008	19	34	8	O taste and see that the LORD is good: blessed is the man that trusts in him.
B019C034V009	19	34	9	O fear the LORD, you his saints: for there is no lack to them that fear him.
B019C034V010	19	34	10	The young lions do lack, and suffer hunger: but they that seek the LORD shall not lack any good thing.
B019C034V011	19	34	11	Come, you children, hearken unto me: I will teach you the fear of the LORD.
B019C034V012	19	34	12	What man is he that desires life, and loves many days, that he may see good?
B019C034V013	19	34	13	Keep your tongue from evil, and your lips from speaking deceit.
B019C034V014	19	34	14	Depart from evil, and do good; seek peace, and pursue it.
B019C034V015	19	34	15	The eyes of the LORD are upon the righteous, and his ears are open unto their cry.
B019C034V016	19	34	16	The face of the LORD is against them that do evil, to cut off the remembrance of them from the earth.
B019C034V017	19	34	17	The righteous cry, and the LORD hears, and delivers them out of all their troubles.
B019C034V018	19	34	18	The LORD is near unto them that are of a broken heart; and saves such as be of a contrite spirit.
B019C034V019	19	34	19	Many are the afflictions of the righteous: but the LORD delivers him out of them all.
B019C034V020	19	34	20	He keeps all his bones: not one of them is broken.
B019C034V021	19	34	21	Evil shall slay the wicked: and they that hate the righteous shall be desolate.
B019C034V022	19	34	22	The LORD redeems the soul of his servants: and none of them that trust in him shall be desolate.
B019C035V001	19	35	1	
        
B019C035V002	19	35	2	Take hold of shield and buckler, and stand up for my help.
B019C035V003	19	35	3	Draw out also the spear, and stop the way against them that persecute me: say unto my soul, I am your salvation.
B019C035V004	19	35	4	Let them be confounded and put to shame that seek after my soul: let them be turned back and brought to confusion that devise my hurt.
B019C035V005	19	35	5	Let them be as chaff before the wind: and let the angel of the LORD chase them.
B019C035V006	19	35	6	Let their way be dark and slippery: and let the angel of the LORD persecute them.
B019C035V007	19	35	7	For without cause have they hid for me their net in a pit, which without cause they have dug for my soul.
B019C035V008	19	35	8	Let destruction come upon him unawares; and let his net that he has hid catch himself: into that very destruction let him fall.
B019C035V009	19	35	9	And my soul shall be joyful in the LORD: it shall rejoice in his salvation.
B019C035V010	19	35	10	All my bones shall say, LORD, who is like unto you, who delivers the poor from him that is too strong for him, yea, the poor and the needy from him that plunders him?
B019C035V011	19	35	11	False witnesses did rise up; they laid to my charge things that I knew not.
B019C035V012	19	35	12	They rewarded me evil for good to the sorrow of my soul.
B019C035V013	19	35	13	But as for me, when they were sick, my clothing was sackcloth: I humbled my soul with fasting; and my prayer returned into my own bosom.
B019C035V014	19	35	14	I behaved myself as though he had been my friend or brother: I bowed down heavily, as one that mourns for his mother.
B019C035V015	19	35	15	But in my adversity they rejoiced, and gathered themselves together: yea, the attackers gathered themselves together against me, and I knew it not; they did tear me, and ceased not:
B019C035V016	19	35	16	With hypocritical mockers at feasts, they gnashed upon me with their teeth.
B019C035V017	19	35	17	Lord, how long will you look on? rescue my soul from their destructions, my precious life from the lions.
B019C035V018	19	35	18	I will give you thanks in the great congregation: I will praise you among many people.
B019C035V019	19	35	19	Let not them that are my enemies wrongfully rejoice over me: neither let them wink with the eye that hate me without a cause.
B019C035V020	19	35	20	For they speak not peace: but they devise deceitful matters against them that are quiet in the land.
B019C035V021	19	35	21	Yea, they opened their mouth wide against me, and said, Aha, aha, our eye has seen it.
B019C035V022	19	35	22	This you have seen, O LORD: keep not silence: O LORD, be not far from me.
B019C035V023	19	35	23	Stir up yourself, and awake to my defense, even unto my cause, my God and my Lord.
B019C035V024	19	35	24	Judge me, O LORD my God, according to your righteousness; and let them not rejoice over me.
B019C035V025	19	35	25	Let them not say in their hearts, Ah, so would we have it: let them not say, We have swallowed him up.
B019C035V026	19	35	26	Let them be ashamed and brought to confusion together that rejoice at my hurt: let them be clothed with shame and dishonor that magnify themselves against me.
B019C035V027	19	35	27	Let them shout for joy, and be glad, that favor my righteous cause: yea, let them say continually, Let the LORD be magnified, who has pleasure in the prosperity of his servant.
B019C035V028	19	35	28	And my tongue shall speak of your righteousness and of your praise all the day long.
B019C036V001	19	36	1	
        
B019C036V002	19	36	2	For he flatters himself in his own eyes, until his iniquity is found to be hateful.
B019C036V003	19	36	3	The words of his mouth are iniquity and deceit: he has ceased to be wise, and to do good.
B019C036V004	19	36	4	He devises mischief upon his bed; he sets himself in a way that is not good; he abhors not evil.
B019C036V005	19	36	5	Your mercy, O LORD, is in the heavens; and your faithfulness reaches unto the clouds.
B019C036V006	19	36	6	Your righteousness is like the great mountains; your judgments are a great deep: O LORD, you preserve man and beast.
B019C036V007	19	36	7	How excellent is your lovingkindness, O God! therefore the children of men put their trust under the shadow of your wings.
B019C036V008	19	36	8	They shall be abundantly satisfied with the fullness of your house; and you shall make them drink of the river of your pleasures.
B019C036V009	19	36	9	For with you is the fountain of life: in your light shall we see light.
B019C036V010	19	36	10	O continue your lovingkindness unto them that know you; and your righteousness to the upright in heart.
B019C036V011	19	36	11	Let not the foot of pride come against me, and let not the hand of the wicked remove me.
B019C036V012	19	36	12	There are the workers of iniquity fallen: they are cast down, and shall not be able to rise.
B019C037V001	19	37	1	
        
B019C037V002	19	37	2	For they shall soon be cut down like the grass, and wither as the green herb.
B019C037V003	19	37	3	Trust in the LORD, and do good; so shall you dwell in the land, and verily you shall be fed.
B019C037V004	19	37	4	Delight yourself also in the LORD; and he shall give you the desires of your heart.
B019C037V005	19	37	5	Commit your way unto the LORD; trust also in him; and he shall bring it to pass.
B019C037V006	19	37	6	And he shall bring forth your righteousness as the light, and your justice as the noonday.
B019C037V007	19	37	7	Rest in the LORD, and wait patiently for him: fret not yourself because of him who prospers in his way, because of the man who brings wicked devices to pass.
B019C037V008	19	37	8	Cease from anger, and forsake wrath: fret not yourself in any way to do evil.
B019C037V009	19	37	9	For evildoers shall be cut off: but those that wait upon the LORD, they shall inherit the earth.
B019C037V010	19	37	10	For yet a little while, and the wicked shall not be: yea, you shall diligently consider his place, and it shall not be.
B019C037V011	19	37	11	But the meek shall inherit the earth; and shall delight themselves in the abundance of peace.
B019C037V012	19	37	12	The wicked plots against the just, and gnashes upon him with his teeth.
B019C037V013	19	37	13	The Lord shall laugh at him: for he sees that his day is coming.
B019C037V014	19	37	14	The wicked have drawn out the sword, and have bent their bow, to cast down the poor and needy, and to slay such as be of upright behavior.
B019C037V015	19	37	15	Their sword shall enter into their own heart, and their bows shall be broken.
B019C037V016	19	37	16	A little that a righteous man has is better than the riches of many wicked.
B019C037V017	19	37	17	For the arms of the wicked shall be broken: but the LORD upholds the righteous.
B019C037V018	19	37	18	The LORD knows the days of the upright: and their inheritance shall be forever.
B019C037V019	19	37	19	They shall not be ashamed in the evil time: and in the days of famine they shall be satisfied.
B019C037V020	19	37	20	But the wicked shall perish, and the enemies of the LORD shall be as the fat of lambs: they shall vanish; into smoke shall they vanish away.
B019C037V021	19	37	21	The wicked borrows, and pays not again: but the righteous shows mercy, and gives.
B019C037V022	19	37	22	For such as be blessed of him shall inherit the earth; and they that be cursed of him shall be cut off.
B019C037V023	19	37	23	The steps of a good man are ordered by the LORD: and he delights in his way.
B019C037V024	19	37	24	Though he falls, he shall not be utterly cast down: for the LORD upholds him with his hand.
B019C037V025	19	37	25	I have been young, and now am old; yet have I not seen the righteous forsaken, nor his offspring begging bread.
B019C037V026	19	37	26	He is ever merciful, and lends; and his descendants are blessed.
B019C037V027	19	37	27	Depart from evil, and do good; and dwell forevermore.
B019C037V028	19	37	28	For the LORD loves justice, and forsakes not his saints; they are preserved forever: but the descendants of the wicked shall be cut off.
B019C037V029	19	37	29	The righteous shall inherit the land, and dwell therein forever.
B019C037V030	19	37	30	The mouth of the righteous speaks wisdom, and his tongue talks of justice.
B019C037V031	19	37	31	The law of his God is in his heart; none of his steps shall slide.
B019C037V032	19	37	32	The wicked watches the righteous, and seeks to slay him.
B019C037V033	19	37	33	The LORD will not leave him in his hand, nor condemn him when he is judged.
B019C037V034	19	37	34	Wait on the LORD, and keep his way, and he shall exalt you to inherit the land: when the wicked are cut off, you shall see it.
B019C037V035	19	37	35	I have seen the wicked in great power, and spreading himself like a green bay tree.
B019C037V036	19	37	36	Yet he passed away, and, lo, he was not: yea, I sought him, but he could not be found.
B019C037V037	19	37	37	Mark the perfect man, and behold the upright: for the end of that man is peace.
B019C037V038	19	37	38	But the transgressors shall be destroyed together: the end of the wicked shall be cut off.
B019C037V039	19	37	39	But the salvation of the righteous is of the LORD: he is their strength in the time of trouble.
B019C037V040	19	37	40	And the LORD shall help them, and deliver them: he shall deliver them from the wicked, and save them, because they trust in him.
B019C038V001	19	38	1	
        
B019C038V002	19	38	2	For your arrows stick fast in me, and your hand presses me down.
B019C038V003	19	38	3	There is no soundness in my flesh because of your anger; neither is there any rest in my bones because of my sin.
B019C038V004	19	38	4	For my iniquities are gone over my head: as a heavy burden they are too heavy for me.
B019C038V005	19	38	5	My wounds are foul and are corrupt because of my foolishness.
B019C038V006	19	38	6	I am troubled; I am bowed down greatly; I go mourning all the day long.
B019C038V007	19	38	7	For my loins are filled with a loathsome disease: and there is no soundness in my flesh.
B019C038V008	19	38	8	I am feeble and utterly broken: I have groaned by reason of the turmoil of my heart.
B019C038V009	19	38	9	Lord, all my desire is before you; and my groaning is not hid from you.
B019C038V010	19	38	10	My heart pants, my strength fails me: as for the light of my eyes, it also is gone from me.
B019C038V011	19	38	11	My lovers and my friends stand aloof from my plague; and my kinsmen stand afar off.
B019C038V012	19	38	12	They also that seek after my life lay snares for me: and they that seek my hurt speak mischievous things, and plan deceit all the day long.
B019C038V013	19	38	13	But I, as a deaf man, heard not; and I was as a dumb man that opens not his mouth.
B019C038V014	19	38	14	Thus I was as a man that hears not, and in whose mouth are no reproofs.
B019C038V015	19	38	15	For in you, O LORD, do I hope: you will hear, O Lord my God.
B019C038V016	19	38	16	For I said, Hear me, lest otherwise they should rejoice over me: when my foot slips, they magnify themselves against me.
B019C038V017	19	38	17	For I am ready to fall, and my sorrow is continually before me.
B019C038V018	19	38	18	For I will declare my iniquity; I will be sorry for my sin.
B019C038V019	19	38	19	But my enemies are vigorous, and they are strong: and they that hate me wrongfully are multiplied.
B019C038V020	19	38	20	They also that render evil for good are my adversaries; because I follow the thing that is good.
B019C038V021	19	38	21	Forsake me not, O LORD: O my God, be not far from me.
B019C038V022	19	38	22	Make haste to help me, O Lord my salvation.
B019C039V001	19	39	1	
        
B019C039V002	19	39	2	I was dumb with silence, I held my peace, even from good; and my sorrow was stirred.
B019C039V003	19	39	3	My heart was hot within me, while I was meditating the fire burned: then spoke I with my tongue,
B019C039V004	19	39	4	LORD, make me to know my end, and the measure of my days, what it is; that I may know how frail I am.
B019C039V005	19	39	5	Behold, you have made my days as a handbreadth; and my age is as nothing before you: verily every man at his best state is altogether vanity. Selah.
B019C039V006	19	39	6	Surely every man walks in a vain show: surely they are in turmoil in vain: he heaps up riches, and knows not who shall gather them.
B019C039V007	19	39	7	And now, Lord, what do I wait for? my hope is in you.
B019C039V008	19	39	8	Deliver me from all my transgressions: make me not the reproach of the foolish.
B019C039V009	19	39	9	I was dumb, I opened not my mouth; because you did it.
B019C039V010	19	39	10	Remove your scourge away from me: I am consumed by the blow of your hand.
B019C039V011	19	39	11	When you with rebukes do correct man for iniquity, you make his beauty melt away like a moth: surely every man is vanity. Selah.
B019C039V012	19	39	12	Hear my prayer, O LORD, and give ear unto my cry; hold not your peace at my tears: for I am a stranger with you, and a sojourner, as all my fathers were.
B019C039V013	19	39	13	O spare me, that I may recover strength, before I go away, and be no more.
B019C040V001	19	40	1	
        
B019C040V002	19	40	2	He brought me up also out of a horrible pit, out of the miry clay, and set my feet upon a rock, and established my steps.
B019C040V003	19	40	3	And he has put a new song in my mouth, even praise unto our God: many shall see it, and fear, and shall trust in the LORD.
B019C040V004	19	40	4	Blessed is that man that makes the LORD his trust, and respects not the proud, nor such as turn aside to lies.
B019C040V005	19	40	5	Many, O LORD my God, are your wonderful works which you have done, and your thoughts which are toward us: they cannot be recounted in order unto you: if I would declare and speak of them, they are more than can be numbered.
B019C040V006	19	40	6	Sacrifice and offering you did not desire; my ears have you opened: burnt offering and sin offering have you not required.
B019C040V007	19	40	7	Then said I, Lo, I come: in the volume of the book it is written of me,
B019C040V008	19	40	8	I delight to do your will, O my God: yea, your law is within my heart.
B019C040V009	19	40	9	I have preached righteousness in the great congregation: lo, I have not restrained my lips, O LORD, you know.
B019C040V010	19	40	10	I have not hid your righteousness within my heart; I have declared your faithfulness and your salvation: I have not concealed your lovingkindness and your truth from the great congregation.
B019C040V011	19	40	11	Withhold not your tender mercies from me, O LORD: let your lovingkindness and your truth continually preserve me.
B019C040V012	19	40	12	For innumerable evils have surrounded me: my iniquities have taken hold upon me, so that I am not able to look up; they are more than the hairs of my head: therefore my heart fails me.
B019C040V013	19	40	13	Be pleased, O LORD, to deliver me: O LORD, make haste to help me.
B019C040V014	19	40	14	Let them be ashamed and confounded together that seek after my soul to destroy it; let them be driven backward and put to shame that wish me evil.
B019C040V015	19	40	15	Let them be desolate as a reward for their shame that say unto me, Aha, aha.
B019C040V016	19	40	16	Let all those that seek you rejoice and be glad in you: let such as love your salvation say continually, The LORD be magnified.
B019C040V017	19	40	17	But I am poor and needy; yet the Lord thinks upon me: you are my help and my deliverer; make no tarrying, O my God.
B019C041V001	19	41	1	
        
B019C041V002	19	41	2	The LORD will preserve him, and keep him alive; and he shall be blessed upon the earth: and you will not deliver him unto the will of his enemies.
B019C041V003	19	41	3	The LORD will strengthen him upon the bed of languishing: you will restore his bed in his sickness.
B019C041V004	19	41	4	I said, LORD, be merciful unto me: heal my soul; for I have sinned against you.
B019C041V005	19	41	5	My enemies speak evil of me, When shall he die, and his name perish?
B019C041V006	19	41	6	And if he comes to see me, he speaks vanity: his heart gathers iniquity to itself; when he goes abroad, he tells it.
B019C041V007	19	41	7	All that hate me whisper together against me: against me do they devise my hurt.
B019C041V008	19	41	8	An evil disease, say they, clings close unto him: and now that he lies down he shall rise up no more.
B019C041V009	19	41	9	Yea, my own familiar friend, in whom I trusted, who did eat of my bread, has lifted up his heel against me.
B019C041V010	19	41	10	But you, O LORD, be merciful unto me, and raise me up, that I may repay them.
B019C041V011	19	41	11	By this I know that you favor me, because my enemy does not triumph over me.
B019C041V012	19	41	12	And as for me, you uphold me in my integrity, and set me before your face forever.
B019C041V013	19	41	13	Blessed be the LORD God of Israel from everlasting, and to everlasting. Amen, and Amen.
B019C042V001	19	42	1	
        
B019C042V002	19	42	2	My soul thirsts for God, for the living God: when shall I come and appear before God?
B019C042V003	19	42	3	My tears have been my food day and night, while they continually say unto me, Where is your God?
B019C042V004	19	42	4	When I remember these things, I pour out my soul within me: for I had gone with the multitude, I went with them to the house of God, with the voice of joy and praise, with a multitude that kept holyday.
B019C042V005	19	42	5	Why are you cast down, O my soul? and why are you disturbed within me? hope in God: for I shall yet praise him for the help of his countenance.
B019C042V006	19	42	6	O my God, my soul is cast down within me: therefore will I remember you from the land of Jordan, and of the Hermonites, from the hill Mizar.
B019C042V007	19	42	7	Deep calls unto deep at the noise of your waterfalls: all your waves and your billows are gone over me.
B019C042V008	19	42	8	Yet the LORD will command his lovingkindness in the daytime, and in the night his song shall be with me, and my prayer unto the God of my life.
B019C042V009	19	42	9	I will say unto God my rock, Why have you forgotten me? why go I mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?
B019C042V010	19	42	10	As with a sword in my bones, my enemies reproach me; while they say daily unto me, Where is your God?
B019C042V011	19	42	11	Why are you cast down, O my soul? and why are you disturbed within me? hope in God: for I shall yet praise him, who is the health of my countenance, and my God.
B019C043V001	19	43	1	Judge me, O God, and plead my cause against an ungodly nation: O deliver me from the deceitful and unjust man.
B019C043V002	19	43	2	For you are the God of my strength: why do you cast me off? why go I mourning because of the oppression of the enemy?
B019C043V003	19	43	3	O send out your light and your truth: let them lead me; let them bring me unto your holy hill, and to your tabernacles.
B019C043V004	19	43	4	Then will I go unto the altar of God, unto God my exceeding joy: yea, upon the harp will I praise you, O God my God.
B019C043V005	19	43	5	Why are you cast down, O my soul? and why are you disturbed within me? hope in God: for I shall yet praise him, who is the health of my countenance, and my God.
B019C044V001	19	44	1	
        
B019C044V002	19	44	2	How you did drive out the nations with your hand, and planted them; how you did afflict the people, and cast them out.
B019C044V003	19	44	3	For they got not the land in possession by their own sword, neither did their own arm save them: but your right hand, and your arm, and the light of your countenance, because you had favor unto them.
B019C044V004	19	44	4	You are my King, O God: command deliverances for Jacob.
B019C044V005	19	44	5	Through you will we push down our enemies: through your name will we tread them under that rise up against us.
B019C044V006	19	44	6	For I will not trust in my bow, neither shall my sword save me.
B019C044V007	19	44	7	But you have saved us from our enemies, and have put them to shame that hated us.
B019C044V008	19	44	8	In God we boast all the day long, and praise your name forever. Selah.
B019C044V009	19	44	9	But you have cast off, and put us to shame; and go not forth with our armies.
B019C044V010	19	44	10	You make us to turn back from the enemy: and they who hate us take spoil for themselves.
B019C044V011	19	44	11	You have given us like sheep appointed for food; and have scattered us among the nations.
B019C044V012	19	44	12	You sell your people for nothing, and do not increase your wealth by their price.
B019C044V013	19	44	13	You make us a reproach to our neighbors, a scorn and a derision to them that are round about us.
B019C044V014	19	44	14	You make us a byword among the nations, a shaking of the head among the people.
B019C044V015	19	44	15	My confusion is continually before me, and the shame of my face has covered me,
B019C044V016	19	44	16	For the voice of him that reproaches and blasphemes; because of the enemy and avenger.
B019C044V017	19	44	17	All this is come upon us; yet have we not forgotten you, neither have we dealt falsely in your covenant.
B019C044V018	19	44	18	Our heart is not turned back, neither have our steps declined from your way;
B019C044V019	19	44	19	Though you have severely broken us in the place of jackals, and covered us with the shadow of death.
B019C044V020	19	44	20	If we have forgotten the name of our God, or stretched out our hands to a strange god;
B019C044V021	19	44	21	Shall not God search this out? for he knows the secrets of the heart.
B019C044V022	19	44	22	Yea, for your sake are we killed all the day long; we are counted as sheep for the slaughter.
B019C044V023	19	44	23	Awake, why sleep you, O Lord? arise, cast us not off forever.
B019C044V024	19	44	24	Why hide you your face, and forget our affliction and our oppression?
B019C044V025	19	44	25	For our soul is bowed down to the dust: our body cleaves unto the earth.
B019C044V026	19	44	26	Arise for our help, and redeem us for your mercies' sake.
B019C045V001	19	45	1	
        
B019C045V002	19	45	2	You are fairer than the children of men: grace is poured into your lips: therefore God has blessed you forever.
B019C045V003	19	45	3	Gird your sword upon your thigh, O most mighty, with your glory and your majesty.
B019C045V004	19	45	4	And in your majesty ride prosperously because of truth and meekness and righteousness; and your right hand shall teach you awesome things.
B019C045V005	19	45	5	Your arrows are sharp in the heart of the king's enemies; by which the people fall under you.
B019C045V006	19	45	6	Your throne, O God, is forever and ever: the scepter of your kingdom is a righteous scepter.
B019C045V007	19	45	7	You love righteousness, and hate wickedness: therefore God, your God, has anointed you with the oil of gladness above your fellows.
B019C045V008	19	45	8	All your garments smell of myrrh, and aloes, and cassia, out of the ivory palaces, by which they have made you glad.
B019C045V009	19	45	9	Kings' daughters were among your honorable women: at your right hand did stand the queen in gold of Ophir.
B019C045V010	19	45	10	Hearken, O daughter, and consider, and incline your ear; forget also your own people, and your father's house;
B019C045V011	19	45	11	So shall the king greatly desire your beauty: since he is your Lord, worship him.
B019C045V012	19	45	12	And the daughter of Tyre shall be there with a gift; even the rich among the people shall entreat your favor.
B019C045V013	19	45	13	The king's daughter is all glorious within the palace: her clothing is of woven gold.
B019C045V014	19	45	14	She shall be brought unto the king in robes of needlework: the virgins, her companions that follow her, shall be brought unto you.
B019C045V015	19	45	15	With gladness and rejoicing shall they be brought: they shall enter into the king's palace.
B019C045V016	19	45	16	Instead of your fathers shall be your children, whom you may make princes in all the earth.
B019C045V017	19	45	17	I will make your name to be remembered in all generations: therefore shall the people praise you forever and ever.
B019C046V001	19	46	1	
        
B019C046V002	19	46	2	Therefore we will not fear, though the earth be removed, and though the mountains be carried into the midst of the sea;
B019C046V003	19	46	3	Though the waters thereof roar and be troubled, though the mountains shake with the swelling thereof. Selah.
B019C046V004	19	46	4	There is a river, the streams of which shall make glad the city of God, the holy place of the tabernacle of the most High.
B019C046V005	19	46	5	God is in the midst of her; she shall not be moved: God shall help her, and that right early.
B019C046V006	19	46	6	The nations raged, the kingdoms were moved: he uttered his voice, the earth melted.
B019C046V007	19	46	7	The LORD of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.
B019C046V008	19	46	8	Come, behold the works of the LORD, what desolations he has made in the earth.
B019C046V009	19	46	9	He makes wars to cease unto the end of the earth; he breaks the bow, and cuts the spear in two; he burns the chariot in the fire.
B019C046V010	19	46	10	
        
B019C046V011	19	46	11	The LORD of hosts is with us; the God of Jacob is our refuge. Selah.
B019C047V001	19	47	1	
        
B019C047V002	19	47	2	For the LORD most high is awesome; he is a great King over all the earth.
B019C047V003	19	47	3	He shall subdue the people under us, and the nations under our feet.
B019C047V004	19	47	4	He shall choose our inheritance for us, the excellency of Jacob whom he loved. Selah.
B019C047V005	19	47	5	God has gone up with a shout, the LORD with the sound of a trumpet.
B019C047V006	19	47	6	Sing praises to God, sing praises: sing praises unto our King, sing praises.
B019C047V007	19	47	7	For God is the King of all the earth: sing you praises with understanding.
B019C047V008	19	47	8	God reigns over the nations: God sits upon the throne of his holiness.
B019C047V009	19	47	9	The princes of the people are gathered together, even the people of the God of Abraham: for the shields of the earth belong unto God: he is greatly exalted.
B019C048V001	19	48	1	
        
B019C048V002	19	48	2	Beautiful for elevation, the joy of the whole earth, is mount Zion, on the sides of the north, the city of the great King.
B019C048V003	19	48	3	God is known in her palaces for a refuge.
B019C048V004	19	48	4	For, lo, the kings were assembled, they passed by together.
B019C048V005	19	48	5	They saw it, and so they marveled; they were troubled, and hastened away.
B019C048V006	19	48	6	Fear took hold upon them there, and pain, as of a woman in travail.
B019C048V007	19	48	7	You break the ships of Tarshish with an east wind.
B019C048V008	19	48	8	As we have heard, so have we seen in the city of the LORD of hosts, in the city of our God: God will establish it forever. Selah.
B019C048V009	19	48	9	We have thought of your lovingkindness, O God, in the midst of your temple.
B019C048V010	19	48	10	According to your name, O God, so is your praise unto the ends of the earth: your right hand is full of righteousness.
B019C048V011	19	48	11	Let mount Zion rejoice, let the daughters of Judah be glad, because of your judgments.
B019C048V012	19	48	12	Walk about Zion, and go round about her: number the towers thereof.
B019C048V013	19	48	13	Mark you well her bulwarks, consider her palaces; that you may tell it to the generation following.
B019C048V014	19	48	14	For this God is our God forever and ever: he will be our guide even unto death.
B019C049V001	19	49	1	
        
B019C049V002	19	49	2	Both low and high, rich and poor, together.
B019C049V003	19	49	3	My mouth shall speak of wisdom; and the meditation of my heart shall be of understanding.
B019C049V004	19	49	4	I will incline my ear to a proverb: I will disclose my riddles upon the harp.
B019C049V005	19	49	5	Why should I fear in the days of evil, when the iniquity at my heels shall surround me?
B019C049V006	19	49	6	They that trust in their wealth, and boast themselves in the multitude of their riches;
B019C049V007	19	49	7	None of them can by any means redeem his brother, nor give to God a ransom for him:
B019C049V008	19	49	8	(For the redemption of their soul is precious, and it ceases forever:)
B019C049V009	19	49	9	That he should still live forever, and not see corruption.
B019C049V010	19	49	10	For he sees that wise men die, likewise the fool and the senseless person perish, and leave their wealth to others.
B019C049V011	19	49	11	Their inward thought is, that their houses shall continue forever, and their dwelling places to all generations; they call their lands after their own names.
B019C049V012	19	49	12	Nevertheless man being in honor abides not: he is like the beasts that perish.
B019C049V013	19	49	13	This their way is their folly: yet their posterity approve their sayings. Selah.
B019C049V014	19	49	14	Like sheep they are laid in the grave; death shall feed on them; and the upright shall have dominion over them in the morning; and their beauty shall consume in the grave from their dwelling.
B019C049V015	19	49	15	But God will redeem my soul from the power of the grave: for he shall receive me. Selah.
B019C049V016	19	49	16	Be not afraid when one is made rich, when the glory of his house is increased;
B019C049V017	19	49	17	For when he dies he shall carry nothing away: his glory shall not descend after him.
B019C049V018	19	49	18	Though while he lived he blessed his soul: and men will praise you, when you do well for yourself.
B019C049V019	19	49	19	He shall go to the generation of his fathers; they shall never see light.
B019C049V020	19	49	20	Man that is in honor, and understands not, is like the beasts that perish.
B019C050V001	19	50	1	
        
B019C050V002	19	50	2	Out of Zion, the perfection of beauty, God has shined.
B019C050V003	19	50	3	Our God shall come, and shall not keep silence: a fire shall devour before him, and it shall be very tempestuous round about him.
B019C050V004	19	50	4	He shall call to the heavens from above, and to the earth, that he may judge his people.
B019C050V005	19	50	5	
        
B019C050V006	19	50	6	And the heavens shall declare his righteousness: for God is judge himself. Selah.
B019C050V007	19	50	7	
        
B019C050V008	19	50	8	
        
B019C050V009	19	50	9	
        
B019C050V010	19	50	10	
        
B019C050V011	19	50	11	
        
B019C050V012	19	50	12	
        
B019C050V013	19	50	13	
        
B019C050V014	19	50	14	
        
B019C050V015	19	50	15	
        
B019C050V016	19	50	16	But unto the wicked God says, 
B019C050V017	19	50	17	
        
B019C050V018	19	50	18	
        
B019C050V019	19	50	19	
        
