B019C051V001	19	51	1	
        
B019C051V002	19	51	2	Wash me thoroughly from my iniquity, and cleanse me from my sin.
B019C051V003	19	51	3	For I acknowledge my transgressions: and my sin is ever before me.
B019C051V004	19	51	4	Against you, you only, have I sinned, and done this evil in your sight: that you might be justified when you speak, and be blameless when you judge.
B019C051V005	19	51	5	Behold, I was brought forth in iniquity, and in sin did my mother conceive me.
B019C051V006	19	51	6	Behold, you desire truth in the inward parts: and in the hidden part you shall make me to know wisdom.
B019C051V007	19	51	7	Purge me with hyssop, and I shall be clean: wash me, and I shall be whiter than snow.
B019C051V008	19	51	8	Make me to hear joy and gladness; that the bones which you have broken may rejoice.
B019C051V009	19	51	9	Hide your face from my sins, and blot out all my iniquities.
B019C051V010	19	51	10	Create in me a clean heart, O God; and renew a right spirit within me.
B019C051V011	19	51	11	Cast me not away from your presence; and take not your holy Spirit from me.
B019C051V012	19	51	12	Restore unto me the joy of your salvation; and uphold me with a free spirit.
B019C051V013	19	51	13	Then will I teach transgressors your ways; and sinners shall be converted unto you.
B019C051V014	19	51	14	Deliver me from the guilt of bloodshed, O God, God of my salvation: and my tongue shall sing aloud of your righteousness.
B019C051V015	19	51	15	O Lord, open my lips; and my mouth shall show forth your praise.
B019C051V016	19	51	16	For you desire not sacrifice; else would I give it: you delight not in burnt offering.
B019C051V017	19	51	17	The sacrifices of God are a broken spirit: a broken and a contrite heart, O God, you will not despise.
B019C051V018	19	51	18	Do good in your good pleasure unto Zion: build you the walls of Jerusalem.
B019C051V019	19	51	19	Then shall you be pleased with the sacrifices of righteousness, with burnt offering and whole burnt offering: then shall they offer bullocks upon your altar.
B019C052V001	19	52	1	
        
B019C052V002	19	52	2	Your tongue devises evil; like a sharp razor, working deceitfully.
B019C052V003	19	52	3	You love evil more than good; and lying rather than to speak righteousness. Selah.
B019C052V004	19	52	4	You love all devouring words, O you deceitful tongue.
B019C052V005	19	52	5	God shall likewise destroy you forever, he shall take you away, and pluck you out of your dwelling place, and root you out of the land of the living. Selah.
B019C052V006	19	52	6	The righteous also shall see, and fear, and shall laugh at him:
B019C052V007	19	52	7	Lo, this is the man that made not God his strength; but trusted in the abundance of his riches, and strengthened himself in his wickedness.
B019C052V008	19	52	8	But I am like a green olive tree in the house of God: I trust in the mercy of God forever and ever.
B019C052V009	19	52	9	I will praise you forever, because you have done it: and I will wait on your name; for it is good before your saints.
B019C053V001	19	53	1	
        
B019C053V002	19	53	2	God looked down from heaven upon the children of men, to see if there were any that did understand, that did seek God.
B019C053V003	19	53	3	Every one of them is gone back: they are altogether become filthy; there is none that does good, no, not one.
B019C053V004	19	53	4	Have the workers of iniquity no knowledge? who eat up my people as they eat bread: they have not called upon God.
B019C053V005	19	53	5	There were they in great fear, where no fear was: for God has scattered the bones of him that encamps against you: you have put them to shame, because God has despised them.
B019C053V006	19	53	6	Oh that the salvation of Israel were come out of Zion! When God brings back the captivity of his people, Jacob shall rejoice, and Israel shall be glad.
B019C054V001	19	54	1	
        
B019C054V002	19	54	2	Hear my prayer, O God; give ear to the words of my mouth.
B019C054V003	19	54	3	For strangers are risen up against me, and oppressors seek after my soul: they have not set God before them. Selah.
B019C054V004	19	54	4	Behold, God is my helper: the Lord is with them that uphold my soul.
B019C054V005	19	54	5	He shall reward evil unto my enemies: cut them off in your truth.
B019C054V006	19	54	6	I will freely sacrifice unto you: I will praise your name, O LORD; for it is good.
B019C054V007	19	54	7	For he has delivered me out of all trouble: and my eye has seen his desire upon my enemies.
B019C055V001	19	55	1	
        
B019C055V002	19	55	2	Attend unto me, and hear me: I mourn in my complaint, and make a noise;
B019C055V003	19	55	3	Because of the voice of the enemy, because of the oppression of the wicked: for they cast iniquity upon me, and in wrath they hate me.
B019C055V004	19	55	4	My heart is greatly pained within me: and the terrors of death are fallen upon me.
B019C055V005	19	55	5	Fearfulness and trembling are come upon me, and horror has overwhelmed me.
B019C055V006	19	55	6	And I said, Oh that I had wings like a dove! for then would I fly away, and be at rest.
B019C055V007	19	55	7	Lo, then would I wander far off, and remain in the wilderness. Selah.
B019C055V008	19	55	8	I would hasten my escape from the windy storm and tempest.
B019C055V009	19	55	9	Destroy, O Lord, and confuse their tongues: for I have seen violence and strife in the city.
B019C055V010	19	55	10	Day and night they go about it upon the walls thereof: mischief also and sorrow are in the midst of it.
B019C055V011	19	55	11	Wickedness is in the midst thereof: deceit and guile depart not from her streets.
B019C055V012	19	55	12	For it was not an enemy that reproached me; then I could have borne it: neither was it he that hated me that did magnify himself against me; then I would have hid myself from him:
B019C055V013	19	55	13	But it was you, a man my equal, my guide, and my close friend.
B019C055V014	19	55	14	We took sweet counsel together, and walked unto the house of God in company.
B019C055V015	19	55	15	Let death seize upon them, and let them go down alive into the grave: for wickedness is in their dwellings, and among them.
B019C055V016	19	55	16	As for me, I will call upon God; and the LORD shall save me.
B019C055V017	19	55	17	Evening, and morning, and at noon, will I pray, and cry aloud: and he shall hear my voice.
B019C055V018	19	55	18	He has delivered my soul in peace from the battle that was against me: for there were many against me.
B019C055V019	19	55	19	God shall hear, and afflict them, even he that abides of old. Selah. Because they do not change, therefore they fear not God.
B019C055V020	19	55	20	He has put forth his hands against such as were at peace with him: he has broken his covenant.
B019C055V021	19	55	21	The words of his mouth were smoother than butter, but war was in his heart: his words were softer than oil, yet were they drawn swords.
B019C055V022	19	55	22	Cast your burden upon the LORD, and he shall sustain you: he shall never permit the righteous to be moved.
B019C055V023	19	55	23	But you, O God, shall bring them down into the pit of destruction: bloody and deceitful men shall not live out half their days; but I will trust in you.
B019C056V001	19	56	1	
        
B019C056V002	19	56	2	My enemies would daily swallow me up: for they are many that fight against me, O most High.
B019C056V003	19	56	3	Whenever I am afraid, I will trust in you.
B019C056V004	19	56	4	In God, I will praise his word, in God, I have put my trust; I will not fear what flesh can do unto me.
B019C056V005	19	56	5	Every day they twist my words: all their thoughts are against me for evil.
B019C056V006	19	56	6	They gather themselves together, they hide themselves, they mark my steps, when they wait for my soul.
B019C056V007	19	56	7	Shall they escape by iniquity? in your anger cast down the people, O God.
B019C056V008	19	56	8	You number my wanderings: put you my tears into your bottle: are they not in your book?
B019C056V009	19	56	9	When I cry unto you, then shall my enemies turn back: this I know; for God is for me.
B019C056V010	19	56	10	In God will I praise his word: in the LORD will I praise his word.
B019C056V011	19	56	11	In God have I put my trust: I will not be afraid what man can do unto me.
B019C056V012	19	56	12	Your vows are upon me, O God: I will render praises unto you.
B019C056V013	19	56	13	For you have delivered my soul from death: will not you deliver my feet from falling, that I may walk before God in the light of the living?
B019C057V001	19	57	1	
        
B019C057V002	19	57	2	I will cry unto God most high; unto God who performs all things for me.
B019C057V003	19	57	3	He shall send from heaven, and save me from the reproach of him that would swallow me up. Selah. God shall send forth his mercy and his truth.
B019C057V004	19	57	4	My soul is among lions: and I lie even among them that are set on fire, even the sons of men, whose teeth are spears and arrows, and their tongue a sharp sword.
B019C057V005	19	57	5	Be exalted, O God, above the heavens; let your glory be above all the earth.
B019C057V006	19	57	6	They have prepared a net for my steps; my soul is bowed down: they have dug a pit before me, into the midst of which they are fallen themselves. Selah.
B019C057V007	19	57	7	My heart is fixed, O God, my heart is fixed: I will sing and give praise.
B019C057V008	19	57	8	Awake, my glory; awake, psaltery and harp: I myself will awake early.
B019C057V009	19	57	9	I will praise you, O Lord, among the people: I will sing unto you among the nations.
B019C057V010	19	57	10	For your mercy is great unto the heavens, and your truth unto the clouds.
B019C057V011	19	57	11	Be exalted, O God, above the heavens: let your glory be above all the earth.
B019C058V001	19	58	1	
        
B019C058V002	19	58	2	Yea, in heart you work wickedness; you weigh out the violence of your hands in the earth.
B019C058V003	19	58	3	The wicked are estranged from the womb: they go astray as soon as they are born, speaking lies.
B019C058V004	19	58	4	Their poison is like the poison of a serpent: they are like the deaf adder that stops its ear;
B019C058V005	19	58	5	Which will not hearken to the voice of charmers, charming ever so wisely.
B019C058V006	19	58	6	Break their teeth, O God, in their mouth: break out the great teeth of the young lions, O LORD.
B019C058V007	19	58	7	Let them melt away as waters which run continually: when he bends his bow to shoot his arrows, let them be as cut in pieces.
B019C058V008	19	58	8	As a snail who melts, let every one of them pass away: like the untimely birth of a woman, that they may not see the sun.
B019C058V009	19	58	9	Before your pots can feel the burning thorns, he shall take them away as with a whirlwind, both living, and in his wrath.
B019C058V010	19	58	10	The righteous shall rejoice when he sees the vengeance: he shall wash his feet in the blood of the wicked.
B019C058V011	19	58	11	So that a man shall say, Verily there is a reward for the righteous: verily he is a God who judges in the earth.
B019C059V001	19	59	1	
        
B019C059V002	19	59	2	Deliver me from the workers of iniquity, and save me from bloodthirsty men.
B019C059V003	19	59	3	For, lo, they lie in wait for my soul: the mighty are gathered against me; not for my transgression, nor for my sin, O LORD.
B019C059V004	19	59	4	They run and prepare themselves apart from my fault: awake to help me, and behold.
B019C059V005	19	59	5	You therefore, O LORD God of hosts, the God of Israel, awake to punish all the nations: be not merciful to any wicked transgressors. Selah.
B019C059V006	19	59	6	They return at evening: they make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city.
B019C059V007	19	59	7	Behold, they bellow out with their mouths: swords are in their lips: for who, say they, does hear?
B019C059V008	19	59	8	But you, O LORD, shall laugh at them; you shall have all the nations in derision.
B019C059V009	19	59	9	Because of your strength will I wait upon you: for God is my defense.
B019C059V010	19	59	10	The God of my mercy shall meet me: God shall let me see my desire upon my enemies.
B019C059V011	19	59	11	Slay them not, lest my people forget: scatter them by your power; and bring them down, O Lord our shield.
B019C059V012	19	59	12	For the sin of their mouth and the words of their lips let them even be taken in their pride: and for the cursing and lying which they speak.
B019C059V013	19	59	13	Consume them in wrath, consume them, that they may not be: and let them know that God rules in Jacob unto the ends of the earth. Selah.
B019C059V014	19	59	14	And at evening let them return; and let them make a noise like a dog, and go round about the city.
B019C059V015	19	59	15	Let them wander up and down for food, and growl if they are not satisfied.
B019C059V016	19	59	16	But I will sing of your power; yea, I will sing aloud of your mercy in the morning: for you have been my defense and refuge in the day of my trouble.
B019C059V017	19	59	17	Unto you, O my Strength, will I sing: for God is my defense, and the God of my mercy.
B019C060V001	19	60	1	
        
B019C060V002	19	60	2	You have made the earth to tremble; you have broken it: heal the breaches thereof; for it shakes.
B019C060V003	19	60	3	You have shown your people hard things: you have made us to drink the wine of astonishment.
B019C060V004	19	60	4	You have given a banner to them that fear you, that it may be displayed because of the truth. Selah.
B019C060V005	19	60	5	That your beloved may be delivered; save with your right hand, and hear me.
B019C060V006	19	60	6	God has spoken in his holiness; 
B019C060V007	19	60	7	
        
B019C060V008	19	60	8	
        
B019C060V009	19	60	9	Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?
B019C060V010	19	60	10	Will not you, O God, who had cast us off? and you, O God, who did not go out with our armies?
B019C060V011	19	60	11	Give us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.
B019C060V012	19	60	12	Through God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
B019C061V001	19	61	1	
        
B019C061V002	19	61	2	From the end of the earth will I cry unto you, when my heart is overwhelmed: lead me to the rock that is higher than I.
B019C061V003	19	61	3	For you have been a shelter for me, and a strong tower from the enemy.
B019C061V004	19	61	4	I will abide in your tabernacle forever: I will trust in the shelter of your wings. Selah.
B019C061V005	19	61	5	For you, O God, have heard my vows: you have given me the heritage of those that fear your name.
B019C061V006	19	61	6	You will prolong the king's life: and his years as many generations.
B019C061V007	19	61	7	He shall abide before God forever: O prepare mercy and truth, which may preserve him.
B019C061V008	19	61	8	So will I sing praise unto your name forever, that I may daily perform my vows.
B019C062V001	19	62	1	
        
B019C062V002	19	62	2	He only is my rock and my salvation; he is my defense; I shall not be greatly moved.
B019C062V003	19	62	3	How long will you imagine evil against a man? you shall be slain all of you: as a leaning wall shall you be, and as a tottering fence.
B019C062V004	19	62	4	They only consult to cast him down from his excellency: they delight in lies: they bless with their mouth, but they curse inwardly. Selah.
B019C062V005	19	62	5	My soul, wait you only upon God; for my expectation is from him.
B019C062V006	19	62	6	He only is my rock and my salvation: he is my defense; I shall not be moved.
B019C062V007	19	62	7	In God is my salvation and my glory: the rock of my strength, and my refuge, is in God.
B019C062V008	19	62	8	Trust in him at all times; you people, pour out your heart before him: God is a refuge for us. Selah.
B019C062V009	19	62	9	Surely men of low degree are vanity, and men of high degree are a lie: if laid on the balance, they are altogether lighter than vanity.
B019C062V010	19	62	10	Trust not in oppression, and hope not vainly in robbery: if riches increase, set not your heart upon them.
B019C062V011	19	62	11	God has spoken once; twice have I heard this; that power belongs unto God.
B019C062V012	19	62	12	Also unto you, O Lord, belongs mercy: for you render to every man according to his work.
B019C063V001	19	63	1	
        
B019C063V002	19	63	2	To see your power and your glory, so as I have seen you in the sanctuary.
B019C063V003	19	63	3	Because your lovingkindness is better than life, my lips shall praise you.
B019C063V004	19	63	4	Thus will I bless you while I live: I will lift up my hands in your name.
B019C063V005	19	63	5	My soul shall be satisfied as with marrow and fatness; and my mouth shall praise you with joyful lips:
B019C063V006	19	63	6	When I remember you upon my bed, and meditate on you in the night watches.
B019C063V007	19	63	7	Because you have been my help, therefore in the shadow of your wings will I rejoice.
B019C063V008	19	63	8	My soul follows close after you: your right hand upholds me.
B019C063V009	19	63	9	But those that seek my soul, to destroy it, shall go into the lower parts of the earth.
B019C063V010	19	63	10	They shall fall by the sword: they shall be a portion for foxes.
B019C063V011	19	63	11	But the king shall rejoice in God; every one that swears by him shall glory: but the mouth of them that speak lies shall be stopped.
B019C064V001	19	64	1	
        
B019C064V002	19	64	2	Hide me from the secret counsel of the wicked; from the insurrection of the workers of iniquity:
B019C064V003	19	64	3	Who whet their tongue like a sword, and bend their bows to shoot their arrows, even bitter words:
B019C064V004	19	64	4	That they may shoot in secret at the perfect: suddenly do they shoot at him, and fear not.
B019C064V005	19	64	5	They encourage themselves in an evil matter: they talk of laying snares secretly; they say, Who shall see them?
B019C064V006	19	64	6	They search out iniquities; they accomplish a diligent search: both the inward thought of every one of them, and the heart, are deep.
B019C064V007	19	64	7	But God shall shoot at them with an arrow; suddenly shall they be wounded.
B019C064V008	19	64	8	So they shall make their own tongue to fall upon themselves: all that see them shall flee away.
B019C064V009	19	64	9	And all men shall fear, and shall declare the work of God; for they shall wisely consider his doings.
B019C064V010	19	64	10	The righteous shall be glad in the LORD, and shall trust in him; and all the upright in heart shall glory.
B019C065V001	19	65	1	
        
B019C065V002	19	65	2	O you that hears prayer, unto you shall all flesh come.
B019C065V003	19	65	3	Iniquities prevail against me: as for our transgressions, you shall purge them away.
B019C065V004	19	65	4	Blessed is the man whom you choose, and cause to approach unto you, that he may dwell in your courts: we shall be satisfied with the goodness of your house, even of your holy temple.
B019C065V005	19	65	5	By awesome deeds in righteousness will you answer us, O God of our salvation; who is the confidence of all the ends of the earth, and of them that are afar off upon the sea:
B019C065V006	19	65	6	Who by his strength established the mountains; being girded with power:
B019C065V007	19	65	7	Who stills the noise of the seas, the noise of their waves, and the tumult of the people.
B019C065V008	19	65	8	They also that dwell in the uttermost parts are afraid at your signs: you make the outgoings of the morning and evening to rejoice.
B019C065V009	19	65	9	You visit the earth, and water it: you greatly enrich it with the river of God, which is full of water: you prepare them grain, when you have so provided for it.
B019C065V010	19	65	10	You water its ridges abundantly: you settle its furrows: you make it soft with showers: you bless its growth.
B019C065V011	19	65	11	You crown the year with your goodness; and your paths drop fatness.
B019C065V012	19	65	12	They drop upon the pastures of the wilderness: and the little hills rejoice on every side.
B019C065V013	19	65	13	The pastures are clothed with flocks; the valleys also are covered over with grain; they shout for joy, they also sing.
B019C066V001	19	66	1	
        
B019C066V002	19	66	2	Sing forth the honor of his name: make his praise glorious.
B019C066V003	19	66	3	Say unto God, How awesome are you in your works! through the greatness of your power shall your enemies submit themselves unto you.
B019C066V004	19	66	4	All the earth shall worship you, and shall sing unto you; they shall sing to your name. Selah.
B019C066V005	19	66	5	Come and see the works of God: he is awesome in his doing toward the children of men.
B019C066V006	19	66	6	He turned the sea into dry land: they went through the flood on foot: there did we rejoice in him.
B019C066V007	19	66	7	He rules by his power forever; his eyes behold the nations: let not the rebellious exalt themselves. Selah.
B019C066V008	19	66	8	O bless our God, you people, and make the voice of his praise to be heard:
B019C066V009	19	66	9	Who holds our soul in life, and allows not our feet to be moved.
B019C066V010	19	66	10	For you, O God, have proved us: you have tried us, as silver is tried.
B019C066V011	19	66	11	You brought us into the net; you laid affliction upon our backs.
B019C066V012	19	66	12	You have caused men to ride over our heads; we went through fire and through water: but you brought us out into a wealthy place.
B019C066V013	19	66	13	I will go into your house with burnt offerings: I will pay you my vows,
B019C066V014	19	66	14	Which my lips have uttered, and my mouth has spoken, when I was in trouble.
B019C066V015	19	66	15	I will offer unto you burnt sacrifices of fatlings, with the incense of rams; I will offer bullocks with goats. Selah.
B019C066V016	19	66	16	Come and hear, all you that fear God, and I will declare what he has done for my soul.
B019C066V017	19	66	17	I cried unto him with my mouth, and he was extolled with my tongue.
B019C066V018	19	66	18	If I regard iniquity in my heart, the Lord will not hear me:
B019C066V019	19	66	19	But verily God has heard me; he has attended to the voice of my prayer.
B019C066V020	19	66	20	Blessed be God, who has not turned away my prayer, nor his mercy from me.
B019C067V001	19	67	1	
        
B019C067V002	19	67	2	That your way may be known upon earth, your saving health among all nations.
B019C067V003	19	67	3	Let the people praise you, O God; let all the people praise you.
B019C067V004	19	67	4	O let the nations be glad and sing for joy: for you shall judge the people righteously, and govern the nations upon earth. Selah.
B019C067V005	19	67	5	Let the people praise you, O God; let all the people praise you.
B019C067V006	19	67	6	Then shall the earth yield her increase; and God, even our own God, shall bless us.
B019C067V007	19	67	7	God shall bless us; and all the ends of the earth shall fear him.
B019C068V001	19	68	1	
        
B019C068V002	19	68	2	As smoke is driven away, so drive them away: as wax melts before the fire, so let the wicked perish at the presence of God.
B019C068V003	19	68	3	But let the righteous be glad; let them rejoice before God: yea, let them exceedingly rejoice.
B019C068V004	19	68	4	Sing unto God, sing praises to his name: extol him that rides upon the heavens by his name, the LORD, and rejoice before him.
B019C068V005	19	68	5	A father of the fatherless, and a judge of the widows, is God in his holy habitation.
B019C068V006	19	68	6	God sets the solitary in families: he brings out those who are bound with chains: but the rebellious dwell in a dry land.
B019C068V007	19	68	7	O God, when you went forth before your people, when you did march through the wilderness; Selah:
B019C068V008	19	68	8	The earth shook, the heavens also dropped rain at the presence of God: even Sinai itself was moved at the presence of God, the God of Israel.
B019C068V009	19	68	9	You, O God, did send a plentiful rain, by which you did confirm your inheritance, when it was weary.
B019C068V010	19	68	10	Your congregation has dwelt therein: you, O God, have provided of your goodness for the poor.
B019C068V011	19	68	11	The Lord gave the word: great was the company of those that published it.
B019C068V012	19	68	12	Kings of armies did flee in haste: and she that tarried at home divided the spoil.
B019C068V013	19	68	13	Though you have slept among the sheepfolds, yet shall you be as the wings of a dove covered with silver, and her feathers with yellow gold.
B019C068V014	19	68	14	When the Almighty scattered kings in it, it was white as snow in Zalmon.
B019C068V015	19	68	15	The hill of God is as the hill of Bashan; a high hill as the hill of Bashan.
B019C068V016	19	68	16	Why leap you, you high hills? this is the hill which God desires to dwell in; yea, the LORD will dwell in it forever.
B019C068V017	19	68	17	The chariots of God are twenty thousand, even thousands of angels: the Lord is among them, as in Sinai, in the holy place.
B019C068V018	19	68	18	You have ascended on high, you have led captivity captive: you have received gifts for men; yea, for the rebellious also, that the LORD God might dwell among them.
B019C068V019	19	68	19	Blessed be the Lord, who daily loads us with benefits, even the God of our salvation. Selah.
B019C068V020	19	68	20	He that is our God is the God of salvation; and unto GOD the Lord belong the escape from death.
B019C068V021	19	68	21	But God shall wound the head of his enemies, and the hairy scalp of such a one as goes on still in his trespasses.
B019C068V022	19	68	22	The Lord said, 
B019C068V023	19	68	23	
        
B019C068V024	19	68	24	They have seen your goings, O God; even the goings of my God, my King, in the sanctuary.
B019C068V025	19	68	25	The singers went before, the players on instruments followed after; among them were the damsels playing with timbrels.
B019C068V026	19	68	26	Bless you God in the congregations, even the Lord, from the fountain of Israel.
B019C068V027	19	68	27	There is little Benjamin, their leader, the princes of Judah and their company, the princes of Zebulun, and the princes of Naphtali.
B019C068V028	19	68	28	Your God has commanded your strength: strengthen, O God, that which you have done for us.
B019C068V029	19	68	29	Because of your temple at Jerusalem shall kings bring presents unto you.
B019C068V030	19	68	30	Rebuke the company of spearmen, the multitude of the bulls, with the calves of the people, till every one submits himself with pieces of silver: scatter you the people that delight in war.
B019C068V031	19	68	31	Princes shall come out of Egypt; Ethiopia shall soon stretch out her hands unto God.
B019C068V032	19	68	32	Sing unto God, you kingdoms of the earth; O sing praises unto the Lord; Selah:
B019C068V033	19	68	33	To him that rides upon the heaven of heavens, which were of old; lo, he does send out his voice, and that a mighty voice.
B019C068V034	19	68	34	Ascribe you strength unto God: his excellency is over Israel, and his strength is in the clouds.
B019C068V035	19	68	35	O God, you are awesome out of your holy places: the God of Israel is he that gives strength and power unto his people. Blessed be God.
B019C069V001	19	69	1	
        
B019C069V002	19	69	2	I sink in deep mire, where there is no standing: I have come into deep waters, where the floods overflow me.
B019C069V003	19	69	3	I am weary from my crying: my throat is dried: my eyes fail while I wait for my God.
B019C069V004	19	69	4	They that hate me without a cause are more than the hairs of my head: they that would destroy me, being my enemies wrongfully, are mighty: then I restored that which I took not away.
B019C069V005	19	69	5	O God, you know my foolishness; and my sins are not hid from you.
B019C069V006	19	69	6	Let not them that wait on you, O Lord GOD of hosts, be ashamed for my sake: let not those that seek you be disgraced for my sake, O God of Israel.
B019C069V007	19	69	7	Because for your sake I have borne reproach; shame has covered my face.
B019C069V008	19	69	8	I have become a stranger unto my brethren, and an alien unto my motherâ€™s children.
B019C069V009	19	69	9	For the zeal of your house has eaten me up; and the reproaches of them that reproached you are fallen upon me.
B019C069V010	19	69	10	When I wept, and chastened my soul with fasting, that was to my reproach.
B019C069V011	19	69	11	I made sackcloth also my garment; and I became a proverb to them.
B019C069V012	19	69	12	They that sit in the gate speak against me; and I was the song of the drunkards.
B019C069V013	19	69	13	But as for me, my prayer is unto you, O LORD, in an acceptable time: O God, in the multitude of your mercy hear me, in the truth of your salvation.
B019C069V014	19	69	14	Deliver me out of the mire, and let me not sink: let me be delivered from them that hate me, and out of the deep waters.
B019C069V015	19	69	15	Let not the floodwater overflow me, neither let the deep swallow me up, and let not the pit shut its mouth upon me.
B019C069V016	19	69	16	Hear me, O LORD; for your lovingkindness is good: turn unto me according to the multitude of your tender mercies.
B019C069V017	19	69	17	And hide not your face from your servant; for I am in trouble: hear me speedily.
B019C069V018	19	69	18	Draw near unto my soul, and redeem it: deliver me because of my enemies.
B019C069V019	19	69	19	You have known my reproach, and my shame, and my dishonor: my adversaries are all before you.
B019C069V020	19	69	20	Reproach has broken my heart; and I am full of heaviness: and I looked for some to take pity, but there was none; and for comforters, but I found none.
B019C069V021	19	69	21	They gave me also gall for my food; and in my thirst they gave me vinegar to drink.
B019C069V022	19	69	22	Let their table become a snare before them: and that which should have been for their welfare, let it become a trap.
B019C069V023	19	69	23	Let their eyes be darkened, that they see not; and make their loins continually to shake.
B019C069V024	19	69	24	Pour out your indignation upon them, and let your wrathful anger take hold of them.
B019C069V025	19	69	25	Let their habitation be desolate; and let none dwell in their tents.
B019C069V026	19	69	26	For they persecute him whom you have smitten; and they talk of the grief of those whom you have wounded.
B019C069V027	19	69	27	Add iniquity unto their iniquity: and let them not come into your righteousness.
B019C069V028	19	69	28	Let them be blotted out of the book of the living, and not be written with the righteous.
B019C069V029	19	69	29	But I am poor and sorrowful: let your salvation, O God, set me up on high.
B019C069V030	19	69	30	I will praise the name of God with a song, and will magnify him with thanksgiving.
B019C069V031	19	69	31	This also shall please the LORD better than an ox or bullock that has horns and hoofs.
B019C069V032	19	69	32	The humble shall see this, and be glad: and your hearts shall live that seek God.
B019C069V033	19	69	33	For the LORD hears the poor, and despises not his prisoners.
B019C069V034	19	69	34	Let the heaven and earth praise him, the seas, and every thing that moves therein.
B019C069V035	19	69	35	For God will save Zion, and will build the cities of Judah: that they may dwell there, and have it in possession.
B019C069V036	19	69	36	The children also of his servants shall inherit it: and they that love his name shall dwell therein.
B019C070V001	19	70	1	
        
B019C070V002	19	70	2	Let them be ashamed and confounded that seek after my soul: let them be turned backward, and put to confusion, that desire my hurt.
B019C070V003	19	70	3	Let them be turned back for a reward of their shame that say, Aha, aha.
B019C070V004	19	70	4	Let all those that seek you rejoice and be glad in you: and let such as love your salvation say continually, Let God be magnified.
B019C070V005	19	70	5	But I am poor and needy: make haste unto me, O God: you are my help and my deliverer; O LORD, make no tarrying.
B019C071V001	19	71	1	In you, O LORD, do I put my trust: let me never be put to confusion.
B019C071V002	19	71	2	Deliver me in your righteousness, and cause me to escape: incline your ear unto me, and save me.
B019C071V003	19	71	3	Be my strong habitation, to which I may continually resort: you have given commandment to save me; for you are my rock and my fortress.
B019C071V004	19	71	4	Deliver me, O my God, out of the hand of the wicked, out of the hand of the unrighteous and cruel man.
B019C071V005	19	71	5	For you are my hope, O Lord GOD: you are my trust from my youth.
B019C071V006	19	71	6	By you have I been upheld from birth: you are he that took me out of my mother's womb: my praise shall be continually of you.
B019C071V007	19	71	7	I am as a wonder unto many; but you are my strong refuge.
B019C071V008	19	71	8	Let my mouth be filled with your praise and with your honor all the day.
B019C071V009	19	71	9	Cast me not off in the time of old age; forsake me not when my strength fails.
B019C071V010	19	71	10	For my enemies speak against me; and they that lay wait for my soul take counsel together,
B019C071V011	19	71	11	Saying, God has forsaken him: persecute and take him; for there is none to deliver him.
B019C071V012	19	71	12	O God, be not far from me: O my God, make haste for my help.
B019C071V013	19	71	13	Let them be confounded and consumed that are adversaries to my soul; let them be covered with reproach and dishonor that seek my hurt.
B019C071V014	19	71	14	But I will hope continually, and will yet praise you more and more.
B019C071V015	19	71	15	My mouth shall show forth your righteousness and your salvation all the day; for I know not the limits thereof.
B019C071V016	19	71	16	I will go in the strength of the Lord GOD: I will make mention of your righteousness, even of yours only.
B019C071V017	19	71	17	O God, you have taught me from my youth: and to this day have I declared your wondrous works.
B019C071V018	19	71	18	Now also when I am old and gray headed, O God, forsake me not; until I have showed your strength unto this generation, and your power to every one that is to come.
B019C071V019	19	71	19	Your righteousness also, O God, is very high, who has done great things: O God, who is like unto you!
B019C071V020	19	71	20	You, who have showed me great and severe troubles, shall revive me again, and shall bring me up again from the depths of the earth.
B019C071V021	19	71	21	You shall increase my greatness, and comfort me on every side.
B019C071V022	19	71	22	I will also praise you with the psaltery, even your truth, O my God: unto you will I sing with the harp, O you Holy One of Israel.
B019C071V023	19	71	23	My lips shall greatly rejoice when I sing unto you; and my soul, which you have redeemed.
B019C071V024	19	71	24	My tongue also shall talk of your righteousness all the day long: for they are confounded, for they are brought unto shame, that seek my hurt.
B019C072V001	19	72	1	
        
B019C072V002	19	72	2	He shall judge your people with righteousness, and your poor with justice.
B019C072V003	19	72	3	The mountains shall bring peace to the people, and the little hills, by righteousness.
B019C072V004	19	72	4	He shall judge the poor of the people, he shall save the children of the needy, and shall break in pieces the oppressor.
B019C072V005	19	72	5	They shall fear you as long as the sun and moon endure, throughout all generations.
B019C072V006	19	72	6	He shall come down like rain upon the mown grass: as showers that water the earth.
B019C072V007	19	72	7	In his days shall the righteous flourish; and abundance of peace so long as the moon endures.
B019C072V008	19	72	8	He shall have dominion also from sea to sea, and from the river unto the ends of the earth.
B019C072V009	19	72	9	They that dwell in the wilderness shall bow before him; and his enemies shall lick the dust.
B019C072V010	19	72	10	The kings of Tarshish and of the coasts shall bring presents: the kings of Sheba and Seba shall offer gifts.
B019C072V011	19	72	11	Yea, all kings shall fall down before him: all nations shall serve him.
B019C072V012	19	72	12	For he shall deliver the needy when he cries; the poor also, and him that has no helper.
B019C072V013	19	72	13	He shall spare the poor and needy, and shall save the souls of the needy.
B019C072V014	19	72	14	He shall redeem their souls from deceit and violence: and precious shall their blood be in his sight.
B019C072V015	19	72	15	And he shall live, and to him shall be given of the gold of Sheba: prayer also shall be made for him continually; and daily shall he be praised.
B019C072V016	19	72	16	There shall be a handful of grain in the earth upon the top of the mountains; the fruit thereof shall shake like Lebanon: and they of the city shall flourish like the grass of the earth.
B019C072V017	19	72	17	His name shall endure forever: his name shall be continued as long as the sun: and men shall be blessed in him: all nations shall call him blessed.
B019C072V018	19	72	18	Blessed be the LORD God, the God of Israel, who only does wondrous things.
B019C072V019	19	72	19	And blessed be his glorious name forever: and let the whole earth be filled with his glory; Amen, and Amen.
B019C072V020	19	72	20	The prayers of David the son of Jesse are ended.
B019C073V001	19	73	1	
        
B019C073V002	19	73	2	But as for me, my feet were almost gone; my steps had nearly slipped.
B019C073V003	19	73	3	For I was envious at the foolish, when I saw the prosperity of the wicked.
B019C073V004	19	73	4	For there are no pains in their death: but their strength is firm.
B019C073V005	19	73	5	They are not in trouble as other men; neither are they plagued like other men.
B019C073V006	19	73	6	Therefore pride surrounds them as a chain; violence covers them as a garment.
B019C073V007	19	73	7	Their eyes stand out with abundance: they have more than heart could wish.
B019C073V008	19	73	8	They are corrupt, and speak wickedly concerning oppression: they speak loftily.
B019C073V009	19	73	9	They set their mouth against the heavens, and their tongue walks through the earth.
B019C073V010	19	73	10	Therefore his people return here: and waters of a full cup are wrung out to them.
B019C073V011	19	73	11	And they say, How does God know? and is there knowledge in the most High?
B019C073V012	19	73	12	Behold, these are the ungodly, who prosper in the world; they increase in riches.
B019C073V013	19	73	13	Verily I have cleansed my heart in vain, and washed my hands in innocence.
B019C073V014	19	73	14	For all the day long have I been plagued, and chastened every morning.
B019C073V015	19	73	15	If I say, I will speak thus; behold, I would have been untrue to the generation of your children.
B019C073V016	19	73	16	When I thought to know this, it was too painful for me;
B019C073V017	19	73	17	Until I went into the sanctuary of God; then understood I their end.
B019C073V018	19	73	18	Surely you did set them in slippery places: you cast them down into destruction.
B019C073V019	19	73	19	How are they brought into desolation, as in a moment! they are utterly consumed with terrors.
B019C073V020	19	73	20	As a dream when one awakes; so, O Lord, when you awake, you shall despise their image.
B019C073V021	19	73	21	Thus my soul was grieved, and I was pierced in my heart.
B019C073V022	19	73	22	So foolish was I, and ignorant: I was as a beast before you.
B019C073V023	19	73	23	Nevertheless I am continually with you: you have held me by my right hand.
B019C073V024	19	73	24	You shall guide me with your counsel, and afterward receive me to glory.
B019C073V025	19	73	25	Whom have I in heaven but you? and there is none upon earth that I desire besides you.
B019C073V026	19	73	26	My flesh and my heart fails: but God is the strength of my heart, and my portion forever.
B019C073V027	19	73	27	For, lo, they that are far from you shall perish: you have destroyed all them that go after idols, departing from you.
B019C073V028	19	73	28	But it is good for me to draw near to God: I have put my trust in the Lord GOD, that I may declare all your works.
B019C074V001	19	74	1	
        
B019C074V002	19	74	2	Remember your congregation, which you have purchased of old; the tribe of your inheritance, which you have redeemed; this mount Zion, where you have dwelt.
B019C074V003	19	74	3	Lift up your feet unto the perpetual desolations; even all that the enemy has done wickedly in the sanctuary.
B019C074V004	19	74	4	Your enemies roar in the midst of your congregations; they set up their banners for signs.
B019C074V005	19	74	5	A man was famous according as he had lifted up axes upon the thick trees.
B019C074V006	19	74	6	But now they break down its carved work at once with axes and hammers.
B019C074V007	19	74	7	They have cast fire into your sanctuary, they have defiled by casting down the dwelling place of your name to the ground.
B019C074V008	19	74	8	They said in their hearts, Let us destroy them together: they have burned up all the meeting places of God in the land.
B019C074V009	19	74	9	We see not our signs: there is no more any prophet: neither is there among us any that knows how long.
B019C074V010	19	74	10	O God, how long shall the adversary reproach? shall the enemy blaspheme your name forever?
B019C074V011	19	74	11	Why withdraw you your hand, even your right hand? pluck it out of your bosom.
B019C074V012	19	74	12	For God is my King of old, working salvation in the midst of the earth.
B019C074V013	19	74	13	You did divide the sea by your strength: you broke the heads of the serpents in the waters.
B019C074V014	19	74	14	You broke the heads of leviathan in pieces, and gave him to be food to the people inhabiting the wilderness.
B019C074V015	19	74	15	You did break open the fountain and the flood: you dried up mighty rivers.
B019C074V016	19	74	16	The day is yours, the night also is yours: you have prepared the light and the sun.
B019C074V017	19	74	17	You have set all the borders of the earth: you have made summer and winter.
B019C074V018	19	74	18	Remember this, that the enemy has reproached, O LORD, and that the foolish people have blasphemed your name.
B019C074V019	19	74	19	O deliver not the soul of your turtledove unto the multitude of the wicked: forget not the congregation of your poor forever.
B019C074V020	19	74	20	Have respect unto the covenant: for the dark places of the earth are full of the habitations of cruelty.
B019C074V021	19	74	21	O let not the oppressed return ashamed: let the poor and needy praise your name.
B019C074V022	19	74	22	Arise, O God, plead your own cause: remember how the foolish man reproaches you daily.
B019C074V023	19	74	23	Forget not the voice of your enemies: the tumult of those that rise up against you increases continually.
B019C075V001	19	75	1	
        
B019C075V002	19	75	2	
        
B019C075V003	19	75	3	
        
B019C075V004	19	75	4	
        
B019C075V005	19	75	5	
        
B019C075V006	19	75	6	For promotion comes neither from the east, nor from the west, nor from the south.
B019C075V007	19	75	7	But God is the judge: he puts down one, and sets up another.
B019C075V008	19	75	8	For in the hand of the LORD there is a cup, and the wine is red; it is fully mixed; and he pours out of the same: but the dregs thereof, all the wicked of the earth shall drain them down, and drink them.
B019C075V009	19	75	9	But I will declare this forever; I will sing praises to the God of Jacob.
B019C075V010	19	75	10	All the strength of the wicked also will I cut off; but the strength of the righteous shall be exalted.
B019C076V001	19	76	1	
        
B019C076V002	19	76	2	In Salem also is his tabernacle, and his dwelling place in Zion.
B019C076V003	19	76	3	There broke he the arrows of the bow, the shield, and the sword, and the battle. Selah.
B019C076V004	19	76	4	You are more glorious and excellent than the mountains of prey.
B019C076V005	19	76	5	The stouthearted are plundered, they have slept their sleep: and none of the men of might can lift their hands.
B019C076V006	19	76	6	At your rebuke, O God of Jacob, both the chariot and horse are cast into a dead sleep.
B019C076V007	19	76	7	You, even you, are to be feared: and who may stand in your sight when once you are angry?
B019C076V008	19	76	8	You did cause judgment to be heard from heaven; the earth feared, and was still,
B019C076V009	19	76	9	When God arose to judgment, to save all the meek of the earth. Selah.
B019C076V010	19	76	10	Surely the wrath of man shall praise you: the remainder of wrath shall you restrain.
B019C076V011	19	76	11	Vow, and pay unto the LORD your God: let all that be round about him bring presents unto him that ought to be feared.
B019C076V012	19	76	12	He shall cut off the spirit of princes: he is fearful to the kings of the earth.
B019C077V001	19	77	1	
        
B019C077V002	19	77	2	In the day of my trouble I sought the Lord: my sore ran in the night, and ceased not: my soul refused to be comforted.
B019C077V003	19	77	3	I remembered God, and was troubled: I complained, and my spirit was overwhelmed. Selah.
B019C077V004	19	77	4	You hold my eyes from closing: I am so troubled that I cannot speak.
B019C077V005	19	77	5	I have considered the days of old, the years of ancient times.
B019C077V006	19	77	6	I call to remembrance my song in the night: I commune with my own heart: and my spirit made diligent search.
B019C077V007	19	77	7	Will the Lord cast off forever? and will he be favorable no more?
B019C077V008	19	77	8	Is his mercy ceased forever? does his promise fail forevermore?
B019C077V009	19	77	9	Has God forgotten to be gracious? has he in anger shut up his tender mercies? Selah.
B019C077V010	19	77	10	And I said, This is my infirmity: but I will remember the years of the right hand of the most High.
B019C077V011	19	77	11	I will remember the works of the LORD: surely I will remember your wonders of old.
B019C077V012	19	77	12	I will meditate also on all your work, and talk of your doings.
B019C077V013	19	77	13	Your way, O God, is in the sanctuary: who is so great a God as our God?
B019C077V014	19	77	14	You are the God that does wonders: you have declared your strength among the people.
B019C077V015	19	77	15	You have with your arm redeemed your people, the sons of Jacob and Joseph. Selah.
B019C077V016	19	77	16	The waters saw you, O God, the waters saw you; they were afraid: the depths also were troubled.
B019C077V017	19	77	17	The clouds poured out water: the skies sent out a sound: your arrows also went abroad.
B019C077V018	19	77	18	The voice of your thunder was in the heaven: the lightnings lighted up the world: the earth trembled and shook.
B019C077V019	19	77	19	Your way is in the sea, and your path in the great waters, and your footsteps are not known.
B019C077V020	19	77	20	You led your people like a flock by the hand of Moses and Aaron.
B019C078V001	19	78	1	
        
B019C078V002	19	78	2	I will open my mouth in a parable: I will utter dark sayings of old:
B019C078V003	19	78	3	Which we have heard and known, and our fathers have told us.
B019C078V004	19	78	4	We will not hide them from their children, showing to the generation to come the praises of the LORD, and his strength, and his wonderful works that he has done.
B019C078V005	19	78	5	For he established a testimony in Jacob, and appointed a law in Israel, which he commanded our fathers, that they should make them known to their children:
B019C078V006	19	78	6	That the generation to come might know them, even the children who should be born; who should arise and declare them to their children:
B019C078V007	19	78	7	That they might set their hope in God, and not forget the works of God, but keep his commandments:
B019C078V008	19	78	8	And might not be as their fathers, a stubborn and rebellious generation; a generation that set not their heart aright, and whose spirit was not steadfast with God.
B019C078V009	19	78	9	The children of Ephraim, being armed, and carrying bows, turned back in the day of battle.
B019C078V010	19	78	10	They kept not the covenant of God, and refused to walk in his law;
B019C078V011	19	78	11	And forgot his works, and his wonders that he had shown them.
B019C078V012	19	78	12	Marvelous things did he in the sight of their fathers, in the land of Egypt, in the field of Zoan.
B019C078V013	19	78	13	He divided the sea, and caused them to pass through; and he made the waters to stand up as a heap.
B019C078V014	19	78	14	In the daytime also he led them with a cloud, and all the night with a light of fire.
B019C078V015	19	78	15	He split the rocks in the wilderness, and gave them drink as out of the great depths.
B019C078V016	19	78	16	He brought streams also out of the rock, and caused waters to run down like rivers.
B019C078V017	19	78	17	And they sinned yet more against him by provoking the most High in the wilderness.
B019C078V018	19	78	18	And they tested God in their heart by asking food for their lust.
B019C078V019	19	78	19	Yea, they spoke against God; they said, Can God furnish a table in the wilderness?
B019C078V020	19	78	20	Behold, he struck the rock, that the waters gushed out, and the streams overflowed; can he give bread also? can he provide meat for his people?
B019C078V021	19	78	21	Therefore the LORD heard this, and was angry: so a fire was kindled against Jacob, and anger also came up against Israel;
B019C078V022	19	78	22	Because they believed not in God, and trusted not in his salvation:
B019C078V023	19	78	23	Though he had commanded the clouds from above, and opened the doors of heaven,
B019C078V024	19	78	24	And had rained down manna upon them to eat, and had given them of the grain of heaven.
B019C078V025	19	78	25	Man did eat angels' food: he sent them food to the full.
B019C078V026	19	78	26	He caused an east wind to blow in the heaven: and by his power he brought in the south wind.
B019C078V027	19	78	27	He rained meat also upon them as dust, and feathered fowls as the sand of the sea:
B019C078V028	19	78	28	And he let it fall in the midst of their camp, round about their habitations.
B019C078V029	19	78	29	So they did eat, and were well filled: for he gave them their own desire;
B019C078V030	19	78	30	They were not separated from their desire. But while their food was yet in their mouths,
B019C078V031	19	78	31	The wrath of God came upon them, and slew the strongest of them, and struck down the chosen men of Israel.
B019C078V032	19	78	32	For all this they sinned still, and believed not despite his wondrous works.
B019C078V033	19	78	33	Therefore their days did he consume in vanity, and their years in trouble.
B019C078V034	19	78	34	When he slew them, then they sought him: and they returned and inquired early after God.
B019C078V035	19	78	35	And they remembered that God was their rock, and the high God their redeemer.
B019C078V036	19	78	36	Nevertheless they did flatter him with their mouth, and they lied unto him with their tongues.
B019C078V037	19	78	37	For their heart was not right with him, neither were they steadfast in his covenant.
B019C078V038	19	78	38	But he, being full of compassion, forgave their iniquity, and destroyed them not: yea, many a time turned he his anger away, and did not stir up all his wrath.
B019C078V039	19	78	39	For he remembered that they were but flesh; a wind that passes away, and comes not again.
B019C078V040	19	78	40	How often did they provoke him in the wilderness, and grieve him in the desert!
B019C078V041	19	78	41	Yea, they turned back and tested God, and limited the Holy One of Israel.
B019C078V042	19	78	42	They remembered not his hand, nor the day when he delivered them from the enemy.
B019C078V043	19	78	43	How he had worked his signs in Egypt, and his wonders in the field of Zoan:
B019C078V044	19	78	44	And had turned their rivers into blood; and their streams, that they could not drink.
B019C078V045	19	78	45	He sent swarms of flies among them, which devoured them; and frogs, which destroyed them.
B019C078V046	19	78	46	He gave also their increase unto the caterpillar, and their labor unto the locust.
B019C078V047	19	78	47	He destroyed their vines with hail, and their sycamore trees with frost.
B019C078V048	19	78	48	He gave up their cattle also to the hail, and their flocks to fiery thunderbolts.
B019C078V049	19	78	49	He cast upon them the fierceness of his anger, wrath, and indignation, and trouble, by sending avenging angels among them.
B019C078V050	19	78	50	He made a way to his anger; he spared not their soul from death, but gave their life over to the pestilence;
B019C078V051	19	78	51	And struck down all the firstborn in Egypt; the chief of their strength in the tabernacles of Ham:
B019C078V052	19	78	52	But made his own people to go forth like sheep, and guided them in the wilderness like a flock.
B019C078V053	19	78	53	And he led them on safely, so that they feared not: but the sea overwhelmed their enemies.
B019C078V054	19	78	54	And he brought them to the border of his sanctuary, even to this mountain, which his right hand had purchased.
B019C078V055	19	78	55	He cast out the nations also before them, and divided them an inheritance by line, and made the tribes of Israel to dwell in their tents.
B019C078V056	19	78	56	Yet they tested and provoked the most high God, and kept not his testimonies:
B019C078V057	19	78	57	But turned back, and dealt unfaithfully like their fathers: they were turned aside like a deceitful bow.
B019C078V058	19	78	58	For they provoked him to anger with their high places, and moved him to jealousy with their graven images.
B019C078V059	19	78	59	When God heard this, he was full of anger, and greatly abhorred Israel:
B019C078V060	19	78	60	So that he forsook the tabernacle of Shiloh, the tent which he placed among men;
B019C078V061	19	78	61	And delivered his strength into captivity, and his glory into the enemy's hand.
B019C078V062	19	78	62	He gave his people over also unto the sword; and was angry with his inheritance.
B019C078V063	19	78	63	The fire consumed their young men; and their maidens were not given to marriage.
B019C078V064	19	78	64	Their priests fell by the sword; and their widows made no lamentation.
B019C078V065	19	78	65	Then the Lord awaked as one out of sleep, and like a mighty man that shouts by reason of wine.
B019C078V066	19	78	66	And he struck his enemies and beat them back: he put them to a perpetual reproach.
B019C078V067	19	78	67	Moreover he refused the tabernacle of Joseph, and chose not the tribe of Ephraim:
B019C078V068	19	78	68	But chose the tribe of Judah, the mount Zion which he loved.
B019C078V069	19	78	69	And he built his sanctuary like high palaces, like the earth which he has established forever.
B019C078V070	19	78	70	He chose David also his servant, and took him from the sheepfolds:
B019C078V071	19	78	71	From following the ewes great with young he brought him to feed Jacob his people, and Israel his inheritance.
B019C078V072	19	78	72	So he fed them according to the integrity of his heart; and guided them by the skillfulness of his hands.
B019C079V001	19	79	1	
        
B019C079V002	19	79	2	The dead bodies of your servants have they given to be food unto the fowls of heaven, the flesh of your saints unto the beasts of the earth.
B019C079V003	19	79	3	Their blood have they shed like water round about Jerusalem; and there was none to bury them.
B019C079V004	19	79	4	We have become a reproach to our neighbors, a scorn and derision to them that are round about us.
B019C079V005	19	79	5	How long, LORD? will you be angry forever? shall your jealousy burn like fire?
B019C079V006	19	79	6	Pour out your wrath upon the nations that have not known you, and upon the kingdoms that have not called upon your name.
B019C079V007	19	79	7	For they have devoured Jacob, and laid waste his dwelling place.
B019C079V008	19	79	8	O remember not against us former iniquities: let your tender mercies speedily precede us: for we are brought very low.
B019C079V009	19	79	9	Help us, O God of our salvation, for the glory of your name: and deliver us, and purge away our sins, for your name's sake.
B019C079V010	19	79	10	Why should the nations say, Where is their God? let him be known among the nations in our sight by the revenging of the blood of your servants which is shed.
B019C079V011	19	79	11	Let the sighing of the prisoner come before you; according to the greatness of your power preserve you those that are appointed to die;
B019C079V012	19	79	12	And render unto our neighbors sevenfold into their bosom their reproach, with which they have reproached you, O Lord.
B019C079V013	19	79	13	So we your people and sheep of your pasture will give you thanks forever: we will show forth your praise to all generations.
B019C080V001	19	80	1	
        
B019C080V002	19	80	2	Before Ephraim and Benjamin and Manasseh stir up your strength, and come and save us.
B019C080V003	19	80	3	Restore us, O God, and cause your face to shine; and we shall be saved.
B019C080V004	19	80	4	O LORD God of hosts, how long will you be angry against the prayer of your people?
B019C080V005	19	80	5	You feed them with the bread of tears; and give them tears to drink in great measure.
B019C080V006	19	80	6	You make us a strife unto our neighbors: and our enemies laugh among themselves.
B019C080V007	19	80	7	Restore us, O God of hosts, and cause your face to shine; and we shall be saved.
B019C080V008	19	80	8	You have brought a vine out of Egypt: you have cast out the nations, and planted it.
B019C080V009	19	80	9	You prepared room before it, and did cause it to take deep root, and it filled the land.
B019C080V010	19	80	10	The hills were covered with the shadow of it, and the boughs thereof were like the goodly cedars.
B019C080V011	19	80	11	It sent out its boughs unto the sea, and its branches unto the river.
B019C080V012	19	80	12	Why have you then broken down its hedges, so that all they who pass by the way do pluck its fruit?
B019C080V013	19	80	13	The boar out of the wood does waste it, and the wild beast of the field does devour it.
B019C080V014	19	80	14	Return, we beseech you, O God of hosts: look down from heaven, and behold, and visit this vine;
B019C080V015	19	80	15	And the vineyard which your right hand has planted, and the branch that you made strong for yourself.
B019C080V016	19	80	16	It is burned with fire, it is cut down: they perish at the rebuke of your countenance.
B019C080V017	19	80	17	Let your hand be upon the man of your right hand, upon the son of man whom you made strong for yourself.
B019C080V018	19	80	18	Then will we not go back from you: revive us, and we will call upon your name.
B019C080V019	19	80	19	Restore us, O LORD God of hosts, cause your face to shine; and we shall be saved.
B019C081V001	19	81	1	
        
B019C081V002	19	81	2	Take a psalm, and bring here the timbrel, the pleasant harp with the psaltery.
B019C081V003	19	81	3	Blow the trumpet in the new moon, in the time appointed, on our solemn feast day.
B019C081V004	19	81	4	For this was a statute for Israel, and a law of the God of Jacob.
B019C081V005	19	81	5	This he ordained in Joseph for a testimony, when he went out through the land of Egypt: where I heard a language that I understood not.
B019C081V006	19	81	6	
        
B019C081V007	19	81	7	
        
