B019C082V001	19	82	1	
        
B019C082V002	19	82	2	
        
B019C082V003	19	82	3	
        
B019C082V004	19	82	4	
        
B019C082V005	19	82	5	
        
B019C082V006	19	82	6	
        
B019C082V007	19	82	7	
        
B019C082V008	19	82	8	Arise, O God, judge the earth: for you shall inherit all nations.
B019C083V001	19	83	1	
        
B019C083V002	19	83	2	For, lo, your enemies make a tumult: and they that hate you have lifted up the head.
B019C083V003	19	83	3	They have taken crafty counsel against your people, and consulted against your hidden ones.
B019C083V004	19	83	4	They have said, Come, and let us cut them off from being a nation; that the name of Israel may be no more in remembrance.
B019C083V005	19	83	5	For they have consulted together with one consent: they make a covenant against you:
B019C083V006	19	83	6	The tabernacles of Edom, and the Ishmaelites; of Moab, and the Hagrites;
B019C083V007	19	83	7	Gebal, and Ammon, and Amalek; the Philistines with the inhabitants of Tyre;
B019C083V008	19	83	8	Assyria also is joined with them: they have helped the children of Lot. Selah.
B019C083V009	19	83	9	Do unto them as unto the Midianites; as to Sisera, as to Jabin, at the brook of Kishon:
B019C083V010	19	83	10	Who perished at Endor: they became as refuse for the earth.
B019C083V011	19	83	11	Make their nobles like Oreb, and like Zeeb: yea, all their princes as Zebah, and as Zalmunna:
B019C083V012	19	83	12	Who said, Let us take to ourselves the houses of God in possession.
B019C083V013	19	83	13	O my God, make them like a wheel; as the stubble before the wind.
B019C083V014	19	83	14	As the fire burns wood, and as the flame sets the mountains on fire;
B019C083V015	19	83	15	So persecute them with your tempest, and make them afraid with your storm.
B019C083V016	19	83	16	Fill their faces with shame; that they may seek your name, O LORD.
B019C083V017	19	83	17	Let them be confounded and troubled forever; yea, let them be put to shame, and perish:
B019C083V018	19	83	18	That men may know that you, whose name alone is the LORD, are the most high over all the earth.
B019C084V001	19	84	1	
        
B019C084V002	19	84	2	My soul longs, yea, even faints for the courts of the LORD: my heart and my flesh cry out for the living God.
B019C084V003	19	84	3	Yea, the sparrow has found a house, and the swallow a nest for herself, where she may lay her young, even your altars, O LORD of hosts, my King, and my God.
B019C084V004	19	84	4	Blessed are they that dwell in your house: they will be still praising you. Selah.
B019C084V005	19	84	5	Blessed is the man whose strength is in you; in whose heart are the ways to them.
B019C084V006	19	84	6	Who passing through the valley of Baca makes it a well; the rain also fills the pools.
B019C084V007	19	84	7	They go from strength to strength, every one of them in Zion appears before God.
B019C084V008	19	84	8	O LORD God of hosts, hear my prayer: give ear, O God of Jacob. Selah.
B019C084V009	19	84	9	Behold, O God our shield, and look upon the face of your anointed.
B019C084V010	19	84	10	For a day in your courts is better than a thousand. I had rather be a doorkeeper in the house of my God, than to dwell in the tents of wickedness.
B019C084V011	19	84	11	For the LORD God is a sun and shield: the LORD will give grace and glory: no good thing will he withhold from them that walk uprightly.
B019C084V012	19	84	12	O LORD of hosts, blessed is the man that trusts in you.
B019C085V001	19	85	1	
        
B019C085V002	19	85	2	You have forgiven the iniquity of your people, you have covered all their sin. Selah.
B019C085V003	19	85	3	You have taken away all your anger: you have turned yourself from the fierceness of your anger.
B019C085V004	19	85	4	Restore us, O God of our salvation, and cause your anger toward us to cease.
B019C085V005	19	85	5	Will you be angry with us forever? will you draw out your anger to all generations?
B019C085V006	19	85	6	Will you not revive us again: that your people may rejoice in you?
B019C085V007	19	85	7	Show us your mercy, O LORD, and grant us your salvation.
B019C085V008	19	85	8	I will hear what God the LORD will speak: for he will speak peace unto his people, and to his saints: but let them not turn again to folly.
B019C085V009	19	85	9	Surely his salvation is near those that fear him; that glory may dwell in our land.
B019C085V010	19	85	10	Mercy and truth are met together; righteousness and peace have kissed each other.
B019C085V011	19	85	11	Truth shall spring out of the earth; and righteousness shall look down from heaven.
B019C085V012	19	85	12	Yea, the LORD shall give that which is good; and our land shall yield its increase.
B019C085V013	19	85	13	Righteousness shall go before him; and shall set us in the way of his steps.
B019C086V001	19	86	1	
        
B019C086V002	19	86	2	Preserve my soul; for I am holy: O you my God, save your servant that trusts in you.
B019C086V003	19	86	3	Be merciful unto me, O Lord: for I cry unto you daily.
B019C086V004	19	86	4	Rejoice the soul of your servant: for unto you, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.
B019C086V005	19	86	5	For you, Lord, are good, and ready to forgive; and abundant in mercy unto all them that call upon you.
B019C086V006	19	86	6	Give ear, O LORD, unto my prayer; and attend to the voice of my supplications.
B019C086V007	19	86	7	In the day of my trouble I will call upon you: for you will answer me.
B019C086V008	19	86	8	Among the gods there is none like unto you, O Lord; neither are there any works like unto your works.
B019C086V009	19	86	9	All nations which you have made shall come and worship before you, O Lord; and shall glorify your name.
B019C086V010	19	86	10	For you are great, and do wondrous things: you are God alone.
B019C086V011	19	86	11	Teach me your way, O LORD; I will walk in your truth: unite my heart to fear your name.
B019C086V012	19	86	12	I will praise you, O Lord my God, with all my heart: and I will glorify your name forevermore.
B019C086V013	19	86	13	For great is your mercy toward me: and you have delivered my soul from the depths of sheol.
B019C086V014	19	86	14	O God, the proud are risen against me, and the assemblies of violent men have sought after my soul; and have not set you before them.
B019C086V015	19	86	15	But you, O Lord, are a God full of compassion, and gracious, longsuffering, and abundant in mercy and truth.
B019C086V016	19	86	16	O turn unto me, and have mercy upon me; give your strength unto your servant, and save the son of your handmaid.
B019C086V017	19	86	17	Show me a sign for good; that they who hate me may see it, and be ashamed: because you, LORD, have helped me, and comforted me.
B019C087V001	19	87	1	
        
B019C087V002	19	87	2	The LORD loves the gates of Zion more than all the dwellings of Jacob.
B019C087V003	19	87	3	Glorious things are spoken of you, O city of God. Selah.
B019C087V004	19	87	4	
        
B019C087V005	19	87	5	And of Zion it shall be said, This and that man was born in her: and the highest himself shall establish her.
B019C087V006	19	87	6	The LORD shall count, when he registers the people, that this man was born there. Selah.
B019C087V007	19	87	7	As well the singers as the players on instruments shall be there: all my springs are in you.
B019C088V001	19	88	1	
        
B019C088V002	19	88	2	Let my prayer come before you: incline your ear unto my cry;
B019C088V003	19	88	3	For my soul is full of troubles: and my life draws near unto the grave.
B019C088V004	19	88	4	I am counted with them that go down into the pit: I am as a man that has no strength:
B019C088V005	19	88	5	Adrift among the dead, like the slain that lie in the grave, whom you remember no more: and they are cut off from your hand.
B019C088V006	19	88	6	You have laid me in the lowest pit, in darkness, in the deep.
B019C088V007	19	88	7	Your anger lies hard upon me, and you have afflicted me with all your waves. Selah.
B019C088V008	19	88	8	You have put away my acquaintance far from me; you have made me an abomination unto them: I am shut up, and I cannot come forth.
B019C088V009	19	88	9	My eye mourns by reason of affliction: LORD, I have called daily upon you, I have stretched out my hands unto you.
B019C088V010	19	88	10	Will you show wonders to the dead? shall the dead arise and praise you? Selah.
B019C088V011	19	88	11	Shall your lovingkindness be declared in the grave? or your faithfulness in destruction?
B019C088V012	19	88	12	Shall your wonders be known in the dark? and your righteousness in the land of forgetfulness?
B019C088V013	19	88	13	But unto you have I cried, O LORD; and in the morning shall my prayer come before you.
B019C088V014	19	88	14	LORD, why cast you off my soul? why hide you your face from me?
B019C088V015	19	88	15	I am afflicted and ready to die from my youth up: while I suffer your terrors I am distracted.
B019C088V016	19	88	16	Your fierce anger goes over me; your terrors have cut me off.
B019C088V017	19	88	17	They came round about me daily like water; they compassed me about together.
B019C088V018	19	88	18	Lover and friend have you put far from me, and my acquaintance into darkness.
B019C089V001	19	89	1	
        
B019C089V002	19	89	2	For I have said, Mercy shall be built up forever: your faithfulness shall you establish in the very heavens.
B019C089V003	19	89	3	
        
B019C089V004	19	89	4	
        
B019C089V005	19	89	5	And the heavens shall praise your wonders, O LORD: your faithfulness also in the congregation of the saints.
B019C089V006	19	89	6	For who in the heaven can be compared unto the LORD? who among the sons of the mighty can be likened unto the LORD?
B019C089V007	19	89	7	God is greatly to be feared in the assembly of the saints, and to be had in reverence of all them that are about him.
B019C089V008	19	89	8	O LORD God of hosts, who is a strong LORD like unto you? or to your faithfulness round about you?
B019C089V009	19	89	9	You rule the raging of the sea: when the waves thereof arise, you still them.
B019C089V010	19	89	10	You have broken Rahab in pieces, as one that is slain; you have scattered your enemies with your strong arm.
B019C089V011	19	89	11	The heavens are yours, the earth also is yours: as for the world and the fullness thereof, you have founded them.
B019C089V012	19	89	12	The north and the south, you have created them: Tabor and Hermon shall rejoice in your name.
B019C089V013	19	89	13	You have a mighty arm: strong is your hand, and high is your right hand.
B019C089V014	19	89	14	Righteousness and justice are the habitation of your throne: mercy and truth shall go before your face.
B019C089V015	19	89	15	Blessed are the people that know the joyful sound: they shall walk, O LORD, in the light of your countenance.
B019C089V016	19	89	16	In your name shall they rejoice all the day: and in your righteousness shall they be exalted.
B019C089V017	19	89	17	For you are the glory of their strength: and in your favor our horn shall be exalted.
B019C089V018	19	89	18	For the LORD is our defense; and the Holy One of Israel is our king.
B019C089V019	19	89	19	Then you spoke in a vision to your holy one, and said, 
