B019C089V037	19	89	37	
        
B019C089V038	19	89	38	But you have cast off and abhorred, you have been angry with your anointed.
B019C089V039	19	89	39	You have made void the covenant of your servant: you have profaned his crown by casting it to the ground.
B019C089V040	19	89	40	You have broken down all his hedges; you have brought his strongholds to ruin.
B019C089V041	19	89	41	All that pass by the way plunder him: he is a reproach to his neighbors.
B019C089V042	19	89	42	You have lifted up the right hand of his adversaries; you have made all his enemies to rejoice.
B019C089V043	19	89	43	You have also turned back the edge of his sword, and have not made him to stand in the battle.
B019C089V044	19	89	44	You have made his glory to cease, and cast his throne down to the ground.
B019C089V045	19	89	45	The days of his youth have you shortened: you have covered him with shame. Selah.
B019C089V046	19	89	46	How long, LORD? will you hide yourself forever? shall your anger burn like fire?
B019C089V047	19	89	47	Remember how short my time is: why have you made all men in vain?
B019C089V048	19	89	48	What man is he that lives, and shall not see death? shall he deliver his soul from the hand of the grave? Selah.
B019C089V049	19	89	49	Lord, where are your former lovingkindnesses, which you swore unto David in your truth?
B019C089V050	19	89	50	Remember, Lord, the reproach of your servants; how I do bear in my bosom the reproach of all the mighty people;
B019C089V051	19	89	51	With which your enemies have reproached, O LORD; with which they have reproached the footsteps of your anointed.
B019C089V052	19	89	52	Blessed be the LORD forevermore. Amen, and Amen.
B019C090V001	19	90	1	
        
B019C090V002	19	90	2	Before the mountains were brought forth, or ever you had formed the earth and the world, even from everlasting to everlasting, you are God.
B019C090V003	19	90	3	You turn man to destruction; and say, 
B019C090V004	19	90	4	For a thousand years in your sight are but as yesterday when it is past, and as a watch in the night.
B019C090V005	19	90	5	You carry them away as with a flood; they are like a sleep: in the morning they are like grass which grows up.
B019C090V006	19	90	6	In the morning it flourishes, and grows up; in the evening it is cut down, and withers.
B019C090V007	19	90	7	For we are consumed by your anger, and by your wrath are we troubled.
B019C090V008	19	90	8	You have set our iniquities before you, our secret sins in the light of your countenance.
B019C090V009	19	90	9	For all our days are passed away in your wrath: we spend our years as a tale that is told.
B019C090V010	19	90	10	The days of our years are threescore years and ten; and if by reason of strength they be fourscore years, yet is their strength labor and sorrow; for it is soon cut off, and we fly away.
B019C090V011	19	90	11	Who knows the power of your anger? even according to your fear, so is your wrath.
B019C090V012	19	90	12	So teach us to number our days, that we may apply our hearts unto wisdom.
B019C090V013	19	90	13	Return, O LORD, how long? and may you have compassion concerning your servants.
B019C090V014	19	90	14	O satisfy us early with your mercy; that we may rejoice and be glad all our days.
B019C090V015	19	90	15	Make us glad according to the days in which you have afflicted us, and the years in which we have seen evil.
B019C090V016	19	90	16	Let your work appear unto your servants, and your glory unto their children.
B019C090V017	19	90	17	And let the beauty of the LORD our God be upon us: and establish you the work of our hands upon us; yea, the work of our hands establish it.
B019C091V001	19	91	1	He that dwells in the secret place of the most High shall abide under the shadow of the Almighty.
B019C091V002	19	91	2	I will say of the LORD, He is my refuge and my fortress: my God; in him will I trust.
B019C091V003	19	91	3	Surely he shall deliver you from the snare of the fowler, and from the deadly pestilence.
B019C091V004	19	91	4	He shall cover you with his feathers, and under his wings shall you trust: his truth shall be your shield and buckler.
B019C091V005	19	91	5	You shall not be afraid for the terror by night; nor for the arrow that flies by day;
B019C091V006	19	91	6	Nor for the pestilence that walks in darkness; nor for the destruction that wastes at noonday.
B019C091V007	19	91	7	A thousand shall fall at your side, and ten thousand at your right hand; but it shall not come near you.
B019C091V008	19	91	8	Only with your eyes shall you behold and see the reward of the wicked.
B019C091V009	19	91	9	Because you have made the LORD, who is my refuge, even the most High, your habitation;
B019C091V010	19	91	10	There shall no evil befall you, neither shall any plague come near your dwelling.
B019C091V011	19	91	11	For he shall give his angels charge over you, to keep you in all your ways.
B019C091V012	19	91	12	They shall bear you up in their hands, lest you dash your foot against a stone.
B019C091V013	19	91	13	You shall tread upon the lion and adder: the young lion and the serpent shall you trample under feet.
B019C091V014	19	91	14	
        
B019C091V015	19	91	15	
        
B019C091V016	19	91	16	
        
B019C092V001	19	92	1	
        
B019C092V002	19	92	2	To show forth your lovingkindness in the morning, and your faithfulness every night,
B019C092V003	19	92	3	Upon an instrument of ten strings, and upon the psaltery; upon the harp with a melodious sound.
B019C092V004	19	92	4	For you, LORD, have made me glad through your work: I will triumph in the works of your hands.
B019C092V005	19	92	5	O LORD, how great are your works! and your thoughts are very deep.
B019C092V006	19	92	6	A senseless man knows not; neither does a fool understand this.
B019C092V007	19	92	7	When the wicked spring as the grass, and when all the workers of iniquity do flourish; it is that they shall be destroyed forever:
B019C092V008	19	92	8	But you, LORD, are most high forevermore.
B019C092V009	19	92	9	For, lo, your enemies, O LORD, for, lo, your enemies shall perish; all the workers of iniquity shall be scattered.
B019C092V010	19	92	10	But my horn shall you exalt like the horn of a wild ox: I shall be anointed with fresh oil.
B019C092V011	19	92	11	My eye also shall see my desire on my enemies, and my ears shall hear my desire of the wicked that rise up against me.
B019C092V012	19	92	12	The righteous shall flourish like the palm tree: he shall grow like a cedar in Lebanon.
B019C092V013	19	92	13	Those that are planted in the house of the LORD shall flourish in the courts of our God.
B019C092V014	19	92	14	They shall still bring forth fruit in old age; they shall be healthy and flourishing;
B019C092V015	19	92	15	To show that the LORD is upright: he is my rock, and there is no unrighteousness in him.
B019C093V001	19	93	1	The LORD reigns, he is clothed with majesty; the LORD is clothed with strength, with which he has girded himself: the world also is established, that it cannot be moved.
B019C093V002	19	93	2	Your throne is established of old: you are from everlasting.
B019C093V003	19	93	3	The floods have lifted up, O LORD, the floods have lifted up their voice; the floods lift up their waves.
B019C093V004	19	93	4	The LORD on high is mightier than the noise of many waters, yea, than the mighty waves of the sea.
B019C093V005	19	93	5	Your testimonies are very sure: holiness becomes your house, O LORD, forever.
B019C094V001	19	94	1	O LORD God, to whom vengeance belongs; O God, to whom vengeance belongs, show yourself.
B019C094V002	19	94	2	Lift up yourself, you judge of the earth: render a reward to the proud.
B019C094V003	19	94	3	LORD, how long shall the wicked, how long shall the wicked triumph?
B019C094V004	19	94	4	How long shall they utter and speak hard things? and all the workers of iniquity boast themselves?
B019C094V005	19	94	5	They break in pieces your people, O LORD, and afflict your heritage.
B019C094V006	19	94	6	They slay the widow and the stranger, and murder the fatherless.
B019C094V007	19	94	7	Yet they say, The LORD shall not see, neither shall the God of Jacob regard it.
B019C094V008	19	94	8	Understand, you senseless among the people: and you fools, when will you be wise?
B019C094V009	19	94	9	He that planted the ear, shall he not hear? he that formed the eye, shall he not see?
B019C094V010	19	94	10	He that chastises the nations, shall he not correct? he that teaches man knowledge, shall he not know?
B019C094V011	19	94	11	The LORD knows the thoughts of man, that they are vanity.
B019C094V012	19	94	12	Blessed is the man whom you chasten, O LORD, and teach him out of your law;
B019C094V013	19	94	13	That you may give him rest from the days of adversity, until the pit is dug for the wicked.
B019C094V014	19	94	14	For the LORD will not cast off his people, neither will he forsake his inheritance.
B019C094V015	19	94	15	But judgment shall return unto righteousness: and all the upright in heart shall follow it.
B019C094V016	19	94	16	Who will rise up for me against the evildoers? or who will stand up for me against the workers of iniquity?
B019C094V017	19	94	17	Unless the LORD had been my help, my soul had almost dwelt in silence.
B019C094V018	19	94	18	When I said, My foot slips; your mercy, O LORD, held me up.
B019C094V019	19	94	19	In the multitude of my thoughts within me your comforts delight my soul.
B019C094V020	19	94	20	Shall the throne of iniquity have fellowship with you, which frames mischief by a law?
B019C094V021	19	94	21	They gather themselves together against the soul of the righteous, and condemn the innocent blood.
B019C094V022	19	94	22	But the LORD is my defense; and my God is the rock of my refuge.
B019C094V023	19	94	23	And he shall bring upon them their own iniquity, and shall cut them off in their own wickedness; yea, the LORD our God shall cut them off.
B019C095V001	19	95	1	O come, let us sing unto the LORD: let us make a joyful noise to the rock of our salvation.
B019C095V002	19	95	2	Let us come before his presence with thanksgiving, and make a joyful noise unto him with psalms.
B019C095V003	19	95	3	For the LORD is a great God, and a great King above all gods.
B019C095V004	19	95	4	In his hand are the deep places of the earth: the strength of the hills is his also.
B019C095V005	19	95	5	The sea is his, and he made it: and his hands formed the dry land.
B019C095V006	19	95	6	O come, let us worship and bow down: let us kneel before the LORD our maker.
B019C095V007	19	95	7	For he is our God; and we are the people of his pasture, and the sheep of his hand. Today if you will hear his voice,
B019C095V008	19	95	8	
        
B019C095V009	19	95	9	
        
B019C095V010	19	95	10	
        
B019C095V011	19	95	11	
        
B019C096V001	19	96	1	O sing unto the LORD a new song: sing unto the LORD, all the earth.
B019C096V002	19	96	2	Sing unto the LORD, bless his name; show forth his salvation from day to day.
B019C096V003	19	96	3	Declare his glory among the nations, his wonders among all people.
B019C096V004	19	96	4	For the LORD is great, and greatly to be praised: he is to be feared above all gods.
B019C096V005	19	96	5	For all the gods of the nations are idols: but the LORD made the heavens.
B019C096V006	19	96	6	Honor and majesty are before him: strength and beauty are in his sanctuary.
B019C096V007	19	96	7	Give unto the LORD, O you families of the people, give unto the LORD glory and strength.
B019C096V008	19	96	8	Give unto the LORD the glory due unto his name: bring an offering, and come into his courts.
B019C096V009	19	96	9	O worship the LORD in the beauty of holiness: fear before him, all the earth.
B019C096V010	19	96	10	Say among the nations that the LORD reigns: the world also shall be established that it shall not be moved: he shall judge the people righteously.
B019C096V011	19	96	11	Let the heavens rejoice, and let the earth be glad; let the sea roar, and the fullness thereof.
B019C096V012	19	96	12	Let the field be joyful, and all that is in it: then shall all the trees of the wood rejoice
B019C096V013	19	96	13	Before the LORD: for he comes, for he comes to judge the earth: he shall judge the world with righteousness, and the people with his truth.
B019C097V001	19	97	1	The LORD reigns; let the earth rejoice; let the multitude of coastlands be glad.
B019C097V002	19	97	2	Clouds and darkness are round about him: righteousness and justice are the habitation of his throne.
B019C097V003	19	97	3	A fire goes before him, and burns up his enemies round about.
B019C097V004	19	97	4	His lightnings light up the world: the earth saw, and trembled.
B019C097V005	19	97	5	The hills melted like wax at the presence of the LORD, at the presence of the Lord of the whole earth.
B019C097V006	19	97	6	The heavens declare his righteousness, and all the people see his glory.
B019C097V007	19	97	7	Confounded be all they that serve graven images, that boast themselves of idols: worship him, all you gods.
B019C097V008	19	97	8	Zion heard, and was glad; and the daughters of Judah rejoiced because of your judgments, O LORD.
B019C097V009	19	97	9	For you, LORD, are high above all the earth: you are exalted far above all gods.
B019C097V010	19	97	10	You that love the LORD, hate evil: he preserves the souls of his saints; he delivers them out of the hand of the wicked.
B019C097V011	19	97	11	Light is sown for the righteous, and gladness for the upright in heart.
B019C097V012	19	97	12	Rejoice in the LORD, you righteous; and give thanks at the remembrance of his holiness.
B019C098V001	19	98	1	
        
B019C098V002	19	98	2	The LORD has made known his salvation: his righteousness has he openly showed in the sight of the nations.
B019C098V003	19	98	3	He has remembered his mercy and his truth toward the house of Israel: all the ends of the earth have seen the salvation of our God.
B019C098V004	19	98	4	Make a joyful noise unto the LORD, all the earth: make a loud noise, and rejoice, and sing praise.
B019C098V005	19	98	5	Sing unto the LORD with the harp; with the harp, and the voice of a psalm.
B019C098V006	19	98	6	With trumpets and the sound of a horn make a joyful noise before the LORD, the King.
B019C098V007	19	98	7	Let the sea roar, and the fullness thereof; the world, and they that dwell therein.
B019C098V008	19	98	8	Let the floods clap their hands: let the hills be joyful together
B019C098V009	19	98	9	Before the LORD; for he comes to judge the earth: with righteousness shall he judge the world, and the people with equity.
B019C099V001	19	99	1	The LORD reigns; let the people tremble: he sits between the cherubim; let the earth be moved.
B019C099V002	19	99	2	The LORD is great in Zion; and he is high above all the people.
B019C099V003	19	99	3	Let them praise your great and awesome name; for it is holy.
B019C099V004	19	99	4	The king's strength also loves justice; you do establish equity, you execute justice and righteousness in Jacob.
B019C099V005	19	99	5	Exalt you the LORD our God, and worship at his footstool; for he is holy.
B019C099V006	19	99	6	Moses and Aaron among his priests, and Samuel among them that call upon his name; they called upon the LORD, and he answered them.
B019C099V007	19	99	7	He spoke unto them in the pillar of cloud: they kept his testimonies, and the ordinance that he gave them.
B019C099V008	19	99	8	You answered them, O LORD our God: you were a God that forgave them, though you took vengeance on their wrongdoings.
B019C099V009	19	99	9	Exalt the LORD our God, and worship at his holy hill; for the LORD our God is holy.
B019C100V001	19	100	1	
        
B019C100V002	19	100	2	Serve the LORD with gladness: come before his presence with singing.
B019C100V003	19	100	3	Know you that the LORD he is God: it is he that has made us, and not we ourselves; we are his people, and the sheep of his pasture.
B019C100V004	19	100	4	Enter into his gates with thanksgiving, and into his courts with praise: be thankful unto him, and bless his name.
B019C100V005	19	100	5	For the LORD is good; his mercy is everlasting; and his truth endures to all generations.
B019C101V001	19	101	1	I will sing of mercy and justice: unto you, O LORD, will I sing.
B019C101V002	19	101	2	I will behave myself wisely in a perfect way. O when will you come unto me? I will walk within my house with a perfect heart.
B019C101V003	19	101	3	I will set no wicked thing before my eyes: I hate the work of them that turn aside; it shall not cleave to me.
B019C101V004	19	101	4	A perverse heart shall depart from me: I will not know a wicked person.
B019C101V005	19	101	5	Whoever secretly slanders his neighbor, him will I cut off: he that has a haughty look and a proud heart will I not endure.
B019C101V006	19	101	6	My eyes shall be upon the faithful of the land, that they may dwell with me: he that walks in a perfect way, he shall serve me.
B019C101V007	19	101	7	He that works deceit shall not dwell within my house: he that tells lies shall not tarry in my sight.
B019C101V008	19	101	8	I will early destroy all the wicked of the land; that I may cut off all wicked doers from the city of the LORD.
B019C102V001	19	102	1	
        
B019C102V002	19	102	2	Hide not your face from me in the day when I am in trouble; incline your ear unto me: in the day when I call answer me speedily.
B019C102V003	19	102	3	For my days are consumed like smoke, and my bones are burned as a hearth.
B019C102V004	19	102	4	My heart is smitten, and withered like grass; so that I forget to eat my bread.
B019C102V005	19	102	5	Because of the voice of my groaning my bones cling to my skin.
B019C102V006	19	102	6	I am like a vulture of the wilderness: I am like an owl of the desert.
B019C102V007	19	102	7	I watch, and am as a sparrow alone upon the house top.
B019C102V008	19	102	8	My enemies reproach me all the day; and they that rail against me are sworn against me.
B019C102V009	19	102	9	For I have eaten ashes like bread, and mingled my drink with weeping,
B019C102V010	19	102	10	Because of your indignation and your wrath: for you have lifted me up, and cast me down.
B019C102V011	19	102	11	My days are like a shadow that declines; and I am withered like grass.
B019C102V012	19	102	12	But you, O LORD, shall endure forever; and your remembrance unto all generations.
B019C102V013	19	102	13	You shall arise, and have mercy upon Zion: for the time to favor her, yea, the set time, is come.
B019C102V014	19	102	14	For your servants take pleasure in her stones, and favor the dust thereof.
B019C102V015	19	102	15	So the nations shall fear the name of the LORD, and all the kings of the earth your glory.
B019C102V016	19	102	16	When the LORD shall build up Zion, he shall appear in his glory.
B019C102V017	19	102	17	He will regard the prayer of the destitute, and not despise their prayer.
B019C102V018	19	102	18	This shall be written for the generation to come: and the people who shall be created shall praise the LORD.
B019C102V019	19	102	19	For he has looked down from the height of his sanctuary; from heaven did the LORD behold the earth;
B019C102V020	19	102	20	To hear the groaning of the prisoner; to loose those that are appointed to death;
B019C102V021	19	102	21	To declare the name of the LORD in Zion, and his praise in Jerusalem;
B019C102V022	19	102	22	When the people are gathered together, and the kingdoms, to serve the LORD.
B019C102V023	19	102	23	He weakened my strength in the way; he shortened my days.
B019C102V024	19	102	24	I said, O my God, take me not away in the midst of my days: your years are throughout all generations.
B019C102V025	19	102	25	Of old have you laid the foundation of the earth: and the heavens are the work of your hands.
B019C102V026	19	102	26	They shall perish, but you shall endure: yea, all of them shall grow old like a garment; as a vesture shall you change them, and they shall be changed:
B019C102V027	19	102	27	But you are the same, and your years shall have no end.
B019C102V028	19	102	28	The children of your servants shall continue, and their descendants shall be established before you.
B019C103V001	19	103	1	
        
B019C103V002	19	103	2	Bless the LORD, O my soul, and forget not all his benefits:
B019C103V003	19	103	3	Who forgives all your iniquities; who heals all your diseases;
B019C103V004	19	103	4	Who redeems your life from destruction; who crowns you with lovingkindness and tender mercies;
B019C103V005	19	103	5	Who satisfies your mouth with good things; so that your youth is renewed like the eagle's.
B019C103V006	19	103	6	The LORD executes righteousness and justice for all that are oppressed.
B019C103V007	19	103	7	He made known his ways unto Moses, his acts unto the children of Israel.
B019C103V008	19	103	8	The LORD is merciful and gracious, slow to anger, and abundant in mercy.
B019C103V009	19	103	9	He will not always chide: neither will he keep his anger forever.
B019C103V010	19	103	10	He has not dealt with us according to our sins; nor rewarded us according to our iniquities.
B019C103V011	19	103	11	For as the heaven is high above the earth, so great is his mercy toward them that fear him.
B019C103V012	19	103	12	As far as the east is from the west, so far has he removed our transgressions from us.
B019C103V013	19	103	13	Like as a father pities his children, so the LORD pities them that fear him.
B019C103V014	19	103	14	For he knows our frame; he remembers that we are dust.
B019C103V015	19	103	15	As for man, his days are as grass: as a flower of the field, so he flourishes.
B019C103V016	19	103	16	For the wind passes over it, and it is gone; and the place there shall know it no more.
B019C103V017	19	103	17	But the mercy of the LORD is from everlasting to everlasting upon them that fear him, and his righteousness unto children's children;
B019C103V018	19	103	18	To such as keep his covenant, and to those that remember his commandments to do them.
B019C103V019	19	103	19	The LORD has prepared his throne in the heavens; and his kingdom rules over all.
B019C103V020	19	103	20	Bless the LORD, you his angels, that excel in strength, that do his commandments, hearkening unto the voice of his word.
B019C103V021	19	103	21	Bless you the LORD, all you his hosts; you ministers of his, that do his pleasure.
B019C103V022	19	103	22	Bless the LORD, all his works in all places of his dominion: bless the LORD, O my soul.
B019C104V001	19	104	1	Bless the LORD, O my soul. O LORD my God, you are very great; you are clothed with honor and majesty.
B019C104V002	19	104	2	Who covers yourself with light as with a garment: who stretches out the heavens like a curtain:
B019C104V003	19	104	3	Who lays the beams of his chambers in the waters: who makes the clouds his chariot: who walks upon the wings of the wind:
B019C104V004	19	104	4	Who makes his angels spirits; his ministers a flaming fire:
B019C104V005	19	104	5	Who laid the foundations of the earth, that it should not be removed forever.
B019C104V006	19	104	6	You covered it with the deep as with a garment: the waters stood above the mountains.
B019C104V007	19	104	7	At your rebuke they fled; at the voice of your thunder they hastened away.
B019C104V008	19	104	8	They go up by the mountains; they go down by the valleys unto the place which you have founded for them.
B019C104V009	19	104	9	You have set a bound that they may not pass over; that they turn not again to cover the earth.
B019C104V010	19	104	10	He sends the springs into the valleys, which run among the hills.
B019C104V011	19	104	11	They give drink to every beast of the field: the wild donkeys quench their thirst.
B019C104V012	19	104	12	By them shall the fowls of the heaven have their habitation, which sing among the branches.
B019C104V013	19	104	13	He waters the hills from his chambers: the earth is satisfied with the fruit of your works.
B019C104V014	19	104	14	He causes the grass to grow for the cattle, and herb for the service of man: that he may bring forth food out of the earth;
B019C104V015	19	104	15	And wine that makes glad the heart of man, and oil to make his face to shine, and bread which strengthens man's heart.
B019C104V016	19	104	16	The trees of the LORD are full of sap; the cedars of Lebanon, which he has planted;
B019C104V017	19	104	17	Where the birds make their nests: as for the stork, the fir trees are her house.
B019C104V018	19	104	18	The high hills are a refuge for the wild goats; and the rocks for the badgers.
B019C104V019	19	104	19	He appointed the moon for seasons: the sun knows its going down.
B019C104V020	19	104	20	You make darkness, and it is night: in which all the beasts of the forest do creep forth.
B019C104V021	19	104	21	The young lions roar after their prey, and seek their food from God.
B019C104V022	19	104	22	The sun arises, they gather themselves together, and lay themselves down in their dens.
B019C104V023	19	104	23	Man goes forth unto his work and to his labor until the evening.
B019C104V024	19	104	24	O LORD, how manifold are your works! in wisdom have you made them all: the earth is full of your riches.
B019C104V025	19	104	25	So is this great and wide sea, which teems with things innumerable, both small and great.
B019C104V026	19	104	26	There go the ships: there is that leviathan, which you have made to play therein.
B019C104V027	19	104	27	These all wait upon you; that you may give them their food in due season.
B019C104V028	19	104	28	That which you give them they gather: you open your hand, they are filled with good.
B019C104V029	19	104	29	You hide your face, they are troubled: you take away their breath, they die, and return to their dust.
B019C104V030	19	104	30	You send forth your Spirit, they are created: and you renew the face of the earth.
B019C104V031	19	104	31	The glory of the LORD shall endure forever: the LORD shall rejoice in his works.
B019C104V032	19	104	32	He looks on the earth, and it trembles: he touches the hills, and they smoke.
B019C104V033	19	104	33	I will sing unto the LORD as long as I live: I will sing praise to my God while I have my being.
B019C104V034	19	104	34	My meditation of him shall be sweet: I will be glad in the LORD.
B019C104V035	19	104	35	Let the sinners be consumed out of the earth, and let the wicked be no more. Bless you the LORD, O my soul. Praise you the LORD.
B019C105V001	19	105	1	O give thanks unto the LORD; call upon his name: make known his deeds among the people.
B019C105V002	19	105	2	Sing unto him, sing psalms unto him: talk of all his wondrous works.
B019C105V003	19	105	3	Glory in his holy name: let the heart of them rejoice that seek the LORD.
B019C105V004	19	105	4	Seek the LORD, and his strength: seek his face evermore.
B019C105V005	19	105	5	Remember his marvelous works that he has done; his wonders, and the judgments of his mouth;
B019C105V006	19	105	6	O you offspring of Abraham his servant, you children of Jacob his chosen.
B019C105V007	19	105	7	He is the LORD our God: his judgments are in all the earth.
B019C105V008	19	105	8	He has remembered his covenant forever, the word which he commanded to a thousand generations.
B019C105V009	19	105	9	Which covenant he made with Abraham, and his oath unto Isaac;
B019C105V010	19	105	10	And confirmed the same unto Jacob for a law, and to Israel for an everlasting covenant:
B019C105V011	19	105	11	Saying, 
B019C105V012	19	105	12	When they were but a few men in number; yea, very few, and strangers in it.
B019C105V013	19	105	13	When they went from one nation to another, from one kingdom to another people;
B019C105V014	19	105	14	He allowed no man to do them wrong: yea, he reproved kings for their sakes;
B019C105V015	19	105	15	Saying, 
B019C105V016	19	105	16	Moreover he called for a famine upon the land: he broke every staff of bread.
B019C105V017	19	105	17	He sent a man before them, even Joseph, who was sold for a servant:
B019C105V018	19	105	18	Whose feet they hurt with fetters: he was laid in irons:
B019C105V019	19	105	19	Until the time that his word came: the word of the LORD tested him.
B019C105V020	19	105	20	The king sent and loosed him; even the ruler of the people, and let him go free.
B019C105V021	19	105	21	He made him lord of his house, and ruler of all his substance:
B019C105V022	19	105	22	To bind his princes at his pleasure; and teach his elders wisdom.
B019C105V023	19	105	23	Israel also came into Egypt; and Jacob sojourned in the land of Ham.
B019C105V024	19	105	24	And he increased his people greatly; and made them stronger than their enemies.
B019C105V025	19	105	25	He turned their heart to hate his people, to deal craftily with his servants.
B019C105V026	19	105	26	He sent Moses his servant; and Aaron whom he had chosen.
B019C105V027	19	105	27	They showed his signs among them, and wonders in the land of Ham.
B019C105V028	19	105	28	He sent darkness, and made it dark; and they rebelled not against his word.
B019C105V029	19	105	29	He turned their waters into blood, and slew their fish.
B019C105V030	19	105	30	Their land brought forth frogs in abundance, in the chambers of their kings.
B019C105V031	19	105	31	He spoke, and there came swarms of flies, and gnats in all their country.
B019C105V032	19	105	32	He gave them hail for rain, and flaming fire in their land.
B019C105V033	19	105	33	He struck their vines also and their fig trees; and broke the trees of their country.
B019C105V034	19	105	34	He spoke, and the locusts came, and young locusts, and that without number,
B019C105V035	19	105	35	And did eat up all the herbs in their land, and devoured the fruit of their ground.
B019C105V036	19	105	36	He struck also all the firstborn in their land, the first of all their strength.
B019C105V037	19	105	37	He brought them forth also with silver and gold: and there was not one feeble person among their tribes.
B019C105V038	19	105	38	Egypt was glad when they departed: for the fear of them fell upon them.
B019C105V039	19	105	39	He spread a cloud for a covering; and fire to give light in the night.
B019C105V040	19	105	40	The people asked, and he brought quail, and satisfied them with the bread of heaven.
B019C105V041	19	105	41	He opened the rock, and the waters gushed out; they ran in the dry places like a river.
B019C105V042	19	105	42	For he remembered his holy promise, and Abraham his servant.
B019C105V043	19	105	43	And he brought forth his people with joy, and his chosen with gladness:
B019C105V044	19	105	44	And gave them the lands of the nations: and they inherited the labor of the people;
B019C105V045	19	105	45	That they might observe his statutes, and keep his laws. Praise you the LORD.
B019C106V001	19	106	1	Praise you the LORD. O give thanks unto the LORD; for he is good: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C106V002	19	106	2	Who can utter the mighty acts of the LORD? who can show forth all his praise?
B019C106V003	19	106	3	Blessed are they that keep justice, and he that does righteousness at all times.
B019C106V004	19	106	4	Remember me, O LORD, with the favor that you bear unto your people: O visit me with your salvation;
B019C106V005	19	106	5	That I may see the good of your chosen, that I may rejoice in the gladness of your nation, that I may glory with your inheritance.
B019C106V006	19	106	6	We have sinned with our fathers, we have committed iniquity, we have done wickedly.
B019C106V007	19	106	7	Our fathers understood not your wonders in Egypt; they remembered not the multitude of your mercies; but rebelled against him at the sea, even at the Red sea.
B019C106V008	19	106	8	Nevertheless he saved them for his name's sake, that he might make his mighty power to be known.
B019C106V009	19	106	9	He rebuked the Red sea also, and it was dried up: so he led them through the depths, as through the wilderness.
B019C106V010	19	106	10	And he saved them from the hand of him that hated them, and redeemed them from the hand of the enemy.
B019C106V011	19	106	11	And the waters covered their enemies: there was not one of them left.
B019C106V012	19	106	12	Then believed they his words; they sang his praise.
B019C106V013	19	106	13	They soon forgot his works; they waited not for his counsel:
B019C106V014	19	106	14	But lusted exceedingly in the wilderness, and tested God in the desert.
B019C106V015	19	106	15	And he gave them their request; but sent leanness into their soul.
B019C106V016	19	106	16	They envied Moses also in the camp, and Aaron the saint of the LORD.
B019C106V017	19	106	17	The earth opened and swallowed up Dathan, and covered the company of Abiram.
B019C106V018	19	106	18	And a fire was kindled in their company; the flame burned up the wicked.
B019C106V019	19	106	19	They made a calf in Horeb, and worshiped the molten image.
B019C106V020	19	106	20	Thus they changed their glory into the image of an ox that eats grass.
B019C106V021	19	106	21	They forgot God their savior, who had done great things in Egypt;
B019C106V022	19	106	22	Wondrous works in the land of Ham, and awesome things by the Red sea.
B019C106V023	19	106	23	Therefore he said that he would destroy them, had not Moses his chosen stood before him in the breach, to turn away his wrath, lest he should destroy them.
B019C106V024	19	106	24	Yea, they despised the pleasant land, they believed not his word:
B019C106V025	19	106	25	But murmured in their tents, and hearkened not unto the voice of the LORD.
B019C106V026	19	106	26	Therefore he lifted up his hand against them, to overthrow them in the wilderness:
B019C106V027	19	106	27	To overthrow their descendants also among the nations, and to scatter them in the lands.
B019C106V028	19	106	28	They joined themselves also unto Baalpeor, and ate the sacrifices to the dead.
B019C106V029	19	106	29	Thus they provoked him to anger with their deeds: and the plague broke in upon them.
B019C106V030	19	106	30	Then stood up Phinehas, and executed judgment: and so the plague was stayed.
B019C106V031	19	106	31	And that was counted unto him for righteousness unto all generations forevermore.
B019C106V032	19	106	32	They angered him also at the waters of strife, so that it went ill with Moses for their sakes:
B019C106V033	19	106	33	Because they provoked his spirit, so that he spoke rashly with his lips.
B019C106V034	19	106	34	They did not destroy the nations, concerning whom the LORD commanded them:
B019C106V035	19	106	35	But were mixed among the nations, and learned their works.
B019C106V036	19	106	36	And they served their idols: which were a snare unto them.
B019C106V037	19	106	37	Yea, they sacrificed their sons and their daughters unto demons,
B019C106V038	19	106	38	And shed innocent blood, even the blood of their sons and of their daughters, whom they sacrificed unto the idols of Canaan: and the land was polluted with blood.
B019C106V039	19	106	39	Thus were they defiled with their own works, and played the harlot with their own deeds.
B019C106V040	19	106	40	Therefore was the wrath of the LORD kindled against his people, so much that he abhorred his own inheritance.
B019C106V041	19	106	41	And he gave them into the hand of the nations; and they that hated them ruled over them.
B019C106V042	19	106	42	Their enemies also oppressed them, and they were brought into subjection under their hand.
B019C106V043	19	106	43	Many times did he deliver them; but they provoked him with their counsel, and were brought low for their iniquity.
B019C106V044	19	106	44	Nevertheless he regarded their affliction, when he heard their cry:
B019C106V045	19	106	45	And he remembered for them his covenant, and relented according to the multitude of his mercies.
B019C106V046	19	106	46	He made them also to be pitied of all those that carried them captives.
B019C106V047	19	106	47	Save us, O LORD our God, and gather us from among the nations, to give thanks unto your holy name, and to triumph in your praise.
B019C106V048	19	106	48	Blessed be the LORD God of Israel from everlasting to everlasting: and let all the people say, Amen. Praise you the LORD.
B019C107V001	19	107	1	O give thanks unto the LORD, for he is good: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C107V002	19	107	2	Let the redeemed of the LORD say so, whom he has redeemed from the hand of the enemy;
B019C107V003	19	107	3	And gathered them out of the lands, from the east, and from the west, from the north, and from the south.
B019C107V004	19	107	4	They wandered in the wilderness in a solitary way; they found no city to dwell in.
B019C107V005	19	107	5	Hungry and thirsty, their soul fainted in them.
B019C107V006	19	107	6	Then they cried unto the LORD in their trouble, and he delivered them out of their distresses.
B019C107V007	19	107	7	And he led them forth by the right way, that they might go to a city of habitation.
B019C107V008	19	107	8	Oh that men would praise the LORD for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
B019C107V009	19	107	9	For he satisfies the longing soul, and fills the hungry soul with goodness.
B019C107V010	19	107	10	Such as sit in darkness and in the shadow of death, being bound in affliction and in irons;
B019C107V011	19	107	11	Because they rebelled against the words of God, and the counsel of the most High:
B019C107V012	19	107	12	Therefore he brought down their heart with labor; they fell down, and there was none to help.
B019C107V013	19	107	13	Then they cried unto the LORD in their trouble, and he saved them out of their distresses.
B019C107V014	19	107	14	He brought them out of darkness and the shadow of death, and broke their bands asunder.
B019C107V015	19	107	15	Oh that men would praise the LORD for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
B019C107V016	19	107	16	For he has broken the gates of bronze, and cut the bars of iron in two.
B019C107V017	19	107	17	Fools because of their transgression, and because of their iniquities, are afflicted.
B019C107V018	19	107	18	Their soul abhors all manner of food; and they draw near unto the gates of death.
B019C107V019	19	107	19	Then they cry unto the LORD in their trouble, and he saves them out of their distresses.
B019C107V020	19	107	20	He sent his word, and healed them, and delivered them from their destructions.
B019C107V021	19	107	21	Oh that men would praise the LORD for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
B019C107V022	19	107	22	And let them sacrifice the sacrifices of thanksgiving, and declare his works with rejoicing.
B019C107V023	19	107	23	They that go down to the sea in ships, that do business on great waters;
B019C107V024	19	107	24	These see the works of the LORD, and his wonders in the deep.
B019C107V025	19	107	25	For he commands, and raises the stormy wind, who lifts up the waves thereof.
B019C107V026	19	107	26	They mount up to the heaven, they go down again to the depths: their soul is melted because of trouble.
B019C107V027	19	107	27	They reel to and fro, and stagger like a drunken man, and are at their wit's end.
B019C107V028	19	107	28	Then they cry unto the LORD in their trouble, and he brings them out of their distresses.
B019C107V029	19	107	29	He makes the storm a calm, so that the waves thereof are still.
B019C107V030	19	107	30	Then are they glad because they are quiet; so he brings them unto their desired haven.
B019C107V031	19	107	31	Oh that men would praise the LORD for his goodness, and for his wonderful works to the children of men!
B019C107V032	19	107	32	Let them exalt him also in the congregation of the people, and praise him in the assembly of the elders.
B019C107V033	19	107	33	He turns rivers into a wilderness, and the water springs into dry ground;
B019C107V034	19	107	34	A fruitful land into barrenness, for the wickedness of them that dwell therein.
B019C107V035	19	107	35	He turns the wilderness into a pool of water, and dry ground into water springs.
B019C107V036	19	107	36	And there he makes the hungry to dwell, that they may prepare a city for habitation;
B019C107V037	19	107	37	And sow the fields, and plant vineyards, which may yield fruits of increase.
B019C107V038	19	107	38	He blesses them also, so that they are multiplied greatly; and permits not their cattle to decrease.
B019C107V039	19	107	39	Again, they are diminished and brought low through oppression, affliction, and sorrow.
B019C107V040	19	107	40	He pours contempt upon princes, and causes them to wander in the wilderness, where there is no way.
B019C107V041	19	107	41	Yet sets he the poor on high from affliction, and makes their families like a flock.
B019C107V042	19	107	42	The righteous shall see it, and rejoice: and all iniquity shall stop its mouth.
B019C107V043	19	107	43	Whoever is wise, and will observe these things, even they shall understand the lovingkindness of the LORD.
B019C108V001	19	108	1	
        
B019C108V002	19	108	2	Awake, harp and lyre: I myself will awake early.
B019C108V003	19	108	3	I will praise you, O LORD, among the people: and I will sing praises unto you among the nations.
B019C108V004	19	108	4	For your mercy is great above the heavens: and your truth reaches unto the clouds.
B019C108V005	19	108	5	Be you exalted, O God, above the heavens: and your glory above all the earth;
B019C108V006	19	108	6	That your beloved may be delivered: save with your right hand, and answer me.
B019C108V007	19	108	7	God has spoken in his holiness; 
B019C108V008	19	108	8	
        
B019C108V009	19	108	9	
        
B019C108V010	19	108	10	Who will bring me into the strong city? who will lead me into Edom?
B019C108V011	19	108	11	Will not you, O God, who has cast us off? and will not you, O God, go forth with our armies?
B019C108V012	19	108	12	Give us help from trouble: for vain is the help of man.
B019C108V013	19	108	13	Through God we shall do valiantly: for he it is that shall tread down our enemies.
B019C109V001	19	109	1	
        
B019C109V002	19	109	2	For the mouth of the wicked and the mouth of the deceitful are opened against me: they have spoken against me with a lying tongue.
B019C109V003	19	109	3	They surrounded me also with words of hatred; and fought against me without a cause.
B019C109V004	19	109	4	For my love they are my adversaries: but I give myself unto prayer.
B019C109V005	19	109	5	And they have rewarded me evil for good, and hatred for my love.
B019C109V006	19	109	6	Set you a wicked man over him: and let an accuser stand at his right hand.
B019C109V007	19	109	7	When he shall be judged, let him be condemned: and let his prayer become sin.
B019C109V008	19	109	8	Let his days be few; and let another take his office.
B019C109V009	19	109	9	Let his children be fatherless, and his wife a widow.
B019C109V010	19	109	10	Let his children be continually vagabonds, and beg: let them seek their bread also out of their desolate places.
B019C109V011	19	109	11	Let the extortioner catch all that he has; and let the strangers spoil his labor.
B019C109V012	19	109	12	Let there be none to extend mercy unto him: neither let there be any to favor his fatherless children.
B019C109V013	19	109	13	Let his posterity be cut off; and in the generation following let their name be blotted out.
B019C109V014	19	109	14	Let the iniquity of his fathers be remembered with the LORD; and let not the sin of his mother be blotted out.
B019C109V015	19	109	15	Let them be before the LORD continually, that he may cut off the memory of them from the earth.
B019C109V016	19	109	16	Because he remembered not to show mercy, but persecuted the poor and needy man, that he might even slay the broken in heart.
B019C109V017	19	109	17	As he loved cursing, so let it come unto him: as he delighted not in blessing, so let it be far from him.
B019C109V018	19	109	18	As he clothed himself with cursing as with his garment, so let it come into his body like water, and like oil into his bones.
B019C109V019	19	109	19	Let it be unto him as the garment which covers him, and for a belt with which he is girded continually.
B019C109V020	19	109	20	Let this be the reward of my adversaries from the LORD, and of them that speak evil against my soul.
B019C109V021	19	109	21	But take care of me, O GOD the Lord, for your name's sake: because your mercy is good, deliver me.
B019C109V022	19	109	22	For I am poor and needy, and my heart is wounded within me.
B019C109V023	19	109	23	I am gone like the shadow when it declines: I am shaken off like the locust.
B019C109V024	19	109	24	My knees are weak through fasting; and my flesh lacks fatness.
B019C109V025	19	109	25	I became also a reproach unto them: when they looked upon me they shook their heads.
B019C109V026	19	109	26	Help me, O LORD my God: O save me according to your mercy:
B019C109V027	19	109	27	That they may know that this is your hand; that you, LORD, have done it.
B019C109V028	19	109	28	Let them curse, but you bless: when they arise, let them be ashamed; but let your servant rejoice.
B019C109V029	19	109	29	Let my adversaries be clothed with shame, and let them cover themselves with their own confusion, as with a mantle.
B019C109V030	19	109	30	I will greatly praise the LORD with my mouth; yea, I will praise him among the multitude.
B019C109V031	19	109	31	For he shall stand at the right hand of the poor, to save him from those that condemn his soul.
B019C110V001	19	110	1	
        
B019C110V002	19	110	2	The LORD shall send the rod of your strength out of Zion: rule you in the midst of your enemies.
B019C110V003	19	110	3	Your people shall be willing in the day of your power, in the beauties of holiness from the womb of the morning: you have the dew of your youth.
B019C110V004	19	110	4	The LORD has sworn, and will not relent, 
B019C110V005	19	110	5	The Lord at your right hand shall strike through kings in the day of his wrath.
B019C110V006	19	110	6	He shall judge among the nations, he shall fill the places with the dead bodies; he shall crush the heads over many countries.
B019C110V007	19	110	7	He shall drink of the brook in the way: therefore shall he lift up the head.
B019C111V001	19	111	1	Praise you the LORD. I will praise the LORD with my whole heart, in the assembly of the upright, and in the congregation.
B019C111V002	19	111	2	The works of the LORD are great, sought out of all them that have pleasure in them.
B019C111V003	19	111	3	His work is honorable and glorious: and his righteousness endures forever.
B019C111V004	19	111	4	He has made his wonderful works to be remembered: the LORD is gracious and full of compassion.
B019C111V005	19	111	5	He has given food unto them that fear him: he will ever be mindful of his covenant.
B019C111V006	19	111	6	He has shown his people the power of his works, that he may give them the heritage of the nations.
B019C111V007	19	111	7	The works of his hands are truth and justice; all his commandments are sure.
B019C111V008	19	111	8	They stand fast forever and ever, and are done in truth and uprightness.
B019C111V009	19	111	9	He sent redemption unto his people: he has commanded his covenant forever: holy and awesome is his name.
B019C111V010	19	111	10	The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom: a good understanding have all they that do his commandments: his praise endures forever.
B019C112V001	19	112	1	Praise you the LORD. Blessed is the man that fears the LORD, that delights greatly in his commandments.
B019C112V002	19	112	2	His descendants shall be mighty upon earth: the generation of the upright shall be blessed.
B019C112V003	19	112	3	Wealth and riches shall be in his house: and his righteousness endures forever.
B019C112V004	19	112	4	Unto the upright there arises light in the darkness: he is gracious, and full of compassion, and righteous.
B019C112V005	19	112	5	A good man shows favor, and lends: he will guide his affairs with discretion.
B019C112V006	19	112	6	Surely he shall not be moved forever: the righteous shall be in everlasting remembrance.
B019C112V007	19	112	7	He shall not be afraid of evil tidings: his heart is fixed, trusting in the LORD.
B019C112V008	19	112	8	His heart is established, he shall not be afraid, until he sees his desire upon his enemies.
B019C112V009	19	112	9	He has dispersed, he has given to the poor; his righteousness endures forever; his strength shall be exalted with honor.
B019C112V010	19	112	10	The wicked shall see it, and be grieved; he shall gnash with his teeth, and melt away: the desire of the wicked shall perish.
B019C113V001	19	113	1	Praise you the LORD. Praise, O you servants of the LORD, praise the name of the LORD.
B019C113V002	19	113	2	Blessed be the name of the LORD from this time forth and forevermore.
B019C113V003	19	113	3	From the rising of the sun unto the going down of the same the LORD's name is to be praised.
B019C113V004	19	113	4	The LORD is high above all nations, and his glory above the heavens.
B019C113V005	19	113	5	Who is like unto the LORD our God, who dwells on high,
B019C113V006	19	113	6	Who humbles himself to behold the things that are in heaven, and in the earth!
B019C113V007	19	113	7	He raises up the poor out of the dust, and lifts the needy out of the ash heap;
B019C113V008	19	113	8	That he may set him with princes, even with the princes of his people.
B019C113V009	19	113	9	He makes the barren woman to keep house, and to be a joyful mother of children. Praise you the LORD.
B019C114V001	19	114	1	When Israel went out of Egypt, the house of Jacob from a people of strange language;
B019C114V002	19	114	2	Judah was his sanctuary, and Israel his dominion.
B019C114V003	19	114	3	The sea saw it, and fled: Jordan was driven back.
B019C114V004	19	114	4	The mountains skipped like rams, and the little hills like lambs.
B019C114V005	19	114	5	What ailed you, O you sea, that you fled? you Jordan, that you were driven back?
B019C114V006	19	114	6	You mountains, that you skipped like rams; and you little hills, like lambs?
B019C114V007	19	114	7	Tremble, you earth, at the presence of the Lord, at the presence of the God of Jacob;
B019C114V008	19	114	8	Who turned the rock into a pool of water, the flint into a fountain of waters.
B019C115V001	19	115	1	Not unto us, O LORD, not unto us, but unto your name give glory, for your mercy, and for your truth's sake.
B019C115V002	19	115	2	Why should the nations say, Where is now their God?
B019C115V003	19	115	3	But our God is in the heavens: he has done whatsoever he has pleased.
B019C115V004	19	115	4	Their idols are silver and gold, the work of men's hands.
B019C115V005	19	115	5	They have mouths, but they speak not: eyes have they, but they see not:
B019C115V006	19	115	6	They have ears, but they hear not: noses have they, but they smell not:
B019C115V007	19	115	7	They have hands, but they handle not: feet have they, but they walk not: neither speak they through their throat.
B019C115V008	19	115	8	They that make them are like unto them; so is every one that trusts in them.
B019C115V009	19	115	9	O Israel, trust you in the LORD: he is their help and their shield.
B019C115V010	19	115	10	O house of Aaron, trust in the LORD: he is their help and their shield.
B019C115V011	19	115	11	You that fear the LORD, trust in the LORD: he is their help and their shield.
B019C115V012	19	115	12	The LORD has been mindful of us: he will bless us; he will bless the house of Israel; he will bless the house of Aaron.
B019C115V013	19	115	13	He will bless them that fear the LORD, both small and great.
B019C115V014	19	115	14	The LORD shall increase you more and more, you and your children.
B019C115V015	19	115	15	You are blessed of the LORD who made heaven and earth.
B019C115V016	19	115	16	The heaven, even the heavens, are the LORD's: but the earth has he given to the children of men.
B019C115V017	19	115	17	The dead praise not the LORD, neither any that go down into silence.
B019C115V018	19	115	18	But we will bless the LORD from this time forth and forevermore. Praise the LORD.
B019C116V001	19	116	1	I love the LORD, because he has heard my voice and my supplications.
B019C116V002	19	116	2	Because he has inclined his ear unto me, therefore will I call upon him as long as I live.
B019C116V003	19	116	3	The sorrows of death surrounded me, and the pangs of sheol got hold upon me: I found trouble and sorrow.
B019C116V004	19	116	4	Then called I upon the name of the LORD; O LORD, I beseech you, deliver my soul.
B019C116V005	19	116	5	Gracious is the LORD, and righteous; yea, our God is merciful.
B019C116V006	19	116	6	The LORD preserves the simple: I was brought low, and he helped me.
B019C116V007	19	116	7	Return unto your rest, O my soul; for the LORD has dealt bountifully with you.
B019C116V008	19	116	8	For you have delivered my soul from death, my eyes from tears, and my feet from falling.
B019C116V009	19	116	9	I will walk before the LORD in the land of the living.
B019C116V010	19	116	10	I believed, therefore have I spoken: I was greatly afflicted:
B019C116V011	19	116	11	I said in my haste, All men are liars.
B019C116V012	19	116	12	What shall I render unto the LORD for all his benefits toward me?
B019C116V013	19	116	13	I will take the cup of salvation, and call upon the name of the LORD.
B019C116V014	19	116	14	I will pay my vows unto the LORD now in the presence of all his people.
B019C116V015	19	116	15	Precious in the sight of the LORD is the death of his saints.
B019C116V016	19	116	16	O LORD, truly I am your servant; I am your servant, and the son of your handmaid: you have loosed my bonds.
B019C116V017	19	116	17	I will offer to you the sacrifice of thanksgiving, and will call upon the name of the LORD.
B019C116V018	19	116	18	I will pay my vows unto the LORD now in the presence of all his people,
B019C116V019	19	116	19	In the courts of the LORD's house, in the midst of you, O Jerusalem. Praise you the LORD.
B019C117V001	19	117	1	O Praise the LORD, all you nations: praise him, all you people.
B019C117V002	19	117	2	For his merciful kindness is great toward us: and the truth of the LORD endures forever. Praise you the LORD.
B019C118V001	19	118	1	O give thanks unto the LORD; for he is good: because his mercy endures forever.
B019C118V002	19	118	2	Let Israel now say, that his mercy endures forever.
B019C118V003	19	118	3	Let the house of Aaron now say, that his mercy endures forever.
B019C118V004	19	118	4	Let them now that fear the LORD say, that his mercy endures forever.
B019C118V005	19	118	5	I called upon the LORD in distress: the LORD answered me, and set me in a broad place.
B019C118V006	19	118	6	The LORD is on my side; I will not fear: what can man do unto me?
B019C118V007	19	118	7	The LORD takes my part with them that help me: therefore shall I see my desire upon them that hate me.
B019C118V008	19	118	8	It is better to trust in the LORD than to put confidence in man.
B019C118V009	19	118	9	It is better to trust in the LORD than to put confidence in princes.
B019C118V010	19	118	10	All nations encompassed me about: but in the name of the LORD will I destroy them.
B019C118V011	19	118	11	They encompassed me about; yea, they encompassed me about: but in the name of the LORD I will destroy them.
B019C118V012	19	118	12	They encompassed me about like bees; they are quenched as the fire of thorns: for in the name of the LORD I will destroy them.
B019C118V013	19	118	13	You have thrust hard at me that I might fall: but the LORD helped me.
B019C118V014	19	118	14	The LORD is my strength and song, and is become my salvation.
B019C118V015	19	118	15	The voice of rejoicing and salvation is in the tabernacles of the righteous: the right hand of the LORD does valiantly.
B019C118V016	19	118	16	The right hand of the LORD is exalted: the right hand of the LORD does valiantly.
B019C118V017	19	118	17	I shall not die, but live, and declare the works of the LORD.
B019C118V018	19	118	18	The LORD has chastened me severely: but he has not given me over unto death.
B019C118V019	19	118	19	Open to me the gates of righteousness: I will go into them, and I will praise the LORD:
B019C118V020	19	118	20	This gate of the LORD, into which the righteous shall enter.
B019C118V021	19	118	21	I will praise you: for you have heard me, and have become my salvation.
B019C118V022	19	118	22	The stone which the builders rejected has become the head stone of the corner.
B019C118V023	19	118	23	This is the LORD'S doing; it is marvelous in our eyes.
B019C118V024	19	118	24	This is the day which the LORD has made; we will rejoice and be glad in it.
B019C118V025	19	118	25	Save now, I beseech you, O LORD: O LORD, I beseech you, send now prosperity.
B019C118V026	19	118	26	Blessed be he that comes in the name of the LORD: we have blessed you out of the house of the LORD.
B019C118V027	19	118	27	God is the LORD, who has showed us light: bind the sacrifice with cords, even unto the horns of the altar.
B019C118V028	19	118	28	You are my God, and I will praise you: you are my God, I will exalt you.
B019C118V029	19	118	29	O give thanks unto the LORD; for he is good: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C119V001	19	119	1	
        
B019C119V002	19	119	2	Blessed are they that keep his testimonies, and that seek him with the whole heart.
B019C119V003	19	119	3	They also do no iniquity: they walk in his ways.
B019C119V004	19	119	4	You have commanded us to keep your precepts diligently.
B019C119V005	19	119	5	O that my ways were directed to keep your statutes!
B019C119V006	19	119	6	Then shall I not be ashamed, when I have respect unto all your commandments.
B019C119V007	19	119	7	I will praise you with uprightness of heart, when I shall have learned your righteous judgments.
B019C119V008	19	119	8	I will keep your statutes: O forsake me not utterly.
B019C119V009	19	119	9	
        
B019C119V010	19	119	10	With my whole heart have I sought you: O let me not wander from your commandments.
B019C119V011	19	119	11	Your word have I hid in my heart, that I might not sin against you.
B019C119V012	19	119	12	Blessed are you, O LORD: teach me your statutes.
B019C119V013	19	119	13	With my lips have I declared all the judgments of your mouth.
B019C119V014	19	119	14	I have rejoiced in the way of your testimonies, as much as in all riches.
B019C119V015	19	119	15	I will meditate in your precepts, and have respect unto your ways.
B019C119V016	19	119	16	I will delight myself in your statutes: I will not forget your word.
B019C119V017	19	119	17	
        
B019C119V018	19	119	18	Open my eyes, that I may behold wondrous things out of your law.
B019C119V019	19	119	19	I am a stranger in the earth: hide not your commandments from me.
B019C119V020	19	119	20	My soul breaks for the longing that it has unto your judgments at all times.
B019C119V021	19	119	21	You have rebuked the proud that are cursed, who do err from your commandments.
B019C119V022	19	119	22	Remove from me reproach and contempt; for I have kept your testimonies.
B019C119V023	19	119	23	Princes also did sit and speak against me: but your servant did meditate in your statutes.
B019C119V024	19	119	24	Your testimonies also are my delight and my counselors.
B019C119V025	19	119	25	
        
B019C119V026	19	119	26	I have declared my ways, and you heard me: teach me your statutes.
B019C119V027	19	119	27	Make me to understand the way of your precepts: so shall I talk of your wondrous works.
B019C119V028	19	119	28	My soul melts for heaviness: strengthen me according unto your word.
B019C119V029	19	119	29	Remove from me the way of lying: and grant me your law graciously.
B019C119V030	19	119	30	I have chosen the way of truth: your judgments have I laid before me.
B019C119V031	19	119	31	I have clung unto your testimonies: O LORD, put me not to shame.
B019C119V032	19	119	32	I will run the way of your commandments, when you shall enlarge my heart.
B019C119V033	19	119	33	
        
B019C119V034	19	119	34	Give me understanding, and I shall keep your law; yea, I shall observe it with my whole heart.
B019C119V035	19	119	35	Make me to go in the path of your commandments; for therein do I delight.
B019C119V036	19	119	36	Incline my heart unto your testimonies, and not to covetousness.
B019C119V037	19	119	37	Turn away my eyes from beholding vanity; and revive me in your way.
B019C119V038	19	119	38	Establish your word unto your servant, who is devoted to your fear.
B019C119V039	19	119	39	Turn away my reproach which I fear: for your judgments are good.
B019C119V040	19	119	40	Behold, I have longed after your precepts: revive me in your righteousness.
B019C119V041	19	119	41	
        
B019C119V042	19	119	42	So shall I have an answer for him that reproaches me: for I trust in your word.
B019C119V043	19	119	43	And take not the word of truth utterly out of my mouth; for I have hoped in your judgments.
B019C119V044	19	119	44	So shall I keep your law continually forever and ever.
B019C119V045	19	119	45	And I will walk at liberty: for I seek your precepts.
B019C119V046	19	119	46	I will speak of your testimonies also before kings, and will not be ashamed.
B019C119V047	19	119	47	And I will delight myself in your commandments, which I have loved.
B019C119V048	19	119	48	My hands also will I lift up unto your commandments, which I have loved; and I will meditate in your statutes.
B019C119V049	19	119	49	
        
B019C119V050	19	119	50	This is my comfort in my affliction: for your word has revived me.
B019C119V051	19	119	51	The proud have had me greatly in derision: yet have I not turned from your law.
B019C119V052	19	119	52	I remembered your judgments of old, O LORD; and have comforted myself.
B019C119V053	19	119	53	Horror has taken hold upon me because of the wicked that forsake your law.
B019C119V054	19	119	54	Your statutes have been my songs in the house of my pilgrimage.
B019C119V055	19	119	55	I have remembered your name, O LORD, in the night, and have kept your law.
B019C119V056	19	119	56	This I had, because I kept your precepts.
B019C119V057	19	119	57	
        
B019C119V058	19	119	58	I entreated your favor with my whole heart: be merciful unto me according to your word.
B019C119V059	19	119	59	I thought on my ways, and turned my feet unto your testimonies.
B019C119V060	19	119	60	I made haste, and delayed not to keep your commandments.
B019C119V061	19	119	61	The bands of the wicked have robbed me: but I have not forgotten your law.
B019C119V062	19	119	62	At midnight I will rise to give thanks unto you because of your righteous judgments.
B019C119V063	19	119	63	I am a companion of all them that fear you, and of them that keep your precepts.
B019C119V064	19	119	64	The earth, O LORD, is full of your mercy: teach me your statutes.
B019C119V065	19	119	65	
        
B019C119V066	19	119	66	Teach me good judgment and knowledge: for I have believed your commandments.
B019C119V067	19	119	67	Before I was afflicted I went astray: but now have I kept your word.
B019C119V068	19	119	68	You are good, and do good; teach me your statutes.
B019C119V069	19	119	69	The proud have forged a lie against me: but I will keep your precepts with my whole heart.
B019C119V070	19	119	70	Their heart is as gross as grease; but I delight in your law.
B019C119V071	19	119	71	It is good for me that I have been afflicted; that I might learn your statutes.
B019C119V072	19	119	72	The law of your mouth is better unto me than thousands of gold and silver pieces.
B019C119V073	19	119	73	
        
B019C119V074	19	119	74	They that fear you will be glad when they see me; because I have hoped in your word.
B019C119V075	19	119	75	I know, O LORD, that your judgments are right, and that you in faithfulness have afflicted me.
B019C119V076	19	119	76	Let, I pray you, your merciful kindness be for my comfort, according to your word unto your servant.
B019C119V077	19	119	77	Let your tender mercies come unto me, that I may live: for your law is my delight.
B019C119V078	19	119	78	Let the proud be ashamed; for they dealt perversely with me without a cause: but I will meditate in your precepts.
B019C119V079	19	119	79	Let those that fear you turn unto me, and those that have known your testimonies.
B019C119V080	19	119	80	Let my heart be sound in your statutes; that I be not ashamed.
B019C119V081	19	119	81	
        
B019C119V082	19	119	82	My eyes fail for your word, saying, When will you comfort me?
B019C119V083	19	119	83	For I am become like a wineskin in the smoke; yet do I not forget your statutes.
B019C119V084	19	119	84	How many are the days of your servant? when will you execute judgment on them that persecute me?
B019C119V085	19	119	85	The proud have dug pits for me, which is not after your law.
B019C119V086	19	119	86	All your commandments are faithful: they persecute me wrongfully; help me.
B019C119V087	19	119	87	They had almost consumed me upon earth; but I forsook not your precepts.
B019C119V088	19	119	88	Revive me according to your lovingkindness; so shall I keep the testimony of your mouth.
B019C119V089	19	119	89	
        
B019C119V090	19	119	90	Your faithfulness is unto all generations: you have established the earth, and it abides.
B019C119V091	19	119	91	They continue this day according to your ordinances: for all are your servants.
B019C119V092	19	119	92	Unless your law had been my delights, I should then have perished in my affliction.
B019C119V093	19	119	93	I will never forget your precepts: for with them you have revived me.
B019C119V094	19	119	94	I am yours, save me; for I have sought your precepts.
B019C119V095	19	119	95	The wicked have waited for me to destroy me: but I will consider your testimonies.
B019C119V096	19	119	96	I have seen a limit to all perfection: but your commandment is exceedingly broad.
B019C119V097	19	119	97	
        
B019C119V098	19	119	98	You through your commandments have made me wiser than my enemies: for they are ever with me.
B019C119V099	19	119	99	I have more understanding than all my teachers: for your testimonies are my meditation.
B019C119V100	19	119	100	I understand more than the ancients, because I keep your precepts.
B019C119V101	19	119	101	I have refrained my feet from every evil way, that I might keep your word.
B019C119V102	19	119	102	I have not departed from your judgments: for you have taught me.
B019C119V103	19	119	103	How sweet are your words unto my taste! yea, sweeter than honey to my mouth!
B019C119V104	19	119	104	Through your precepts I get understanding: therefore I hate every false way.
B019C119V105	19	119	105	
        
B019C119V106	19	119	106	I have sworn, and I will perform it, that I will keep your righteous judgments.
B019C119V107	19	119	107	I am afflicted very much: revive me, O LORD, according unto your word.
B019C119V108	19	119	108	Accept, I beseech you, the freewill offerings of my mouth, O LORD, and teach me your judgments.
B019C119V109	19	119	109	My soul is continually in my hand: yet do I not forget your law.
B019C119V110	19	119	110	The wicked have laid a snare for me: yet I strayed not from your precepts.
B019C119V111	19	119	111	Your testimonies have I taken as a heritage forever: for they are the rejoicing of my heart.
B019C119V112	19	119	112	I have inclined my heart to perform your statutes always, even unto the end.
B019C119V113	19	119	113	
        
B019C119V114	19	119	114	You are my hiding place and my shield: I hope in your word.
B019C119V115	19	119	115	Depart from me, you evildoers: for I will keep the commandments of my God.
B019C119V116	19	119	116	Uphold me according unto your word, that I may live: and let me not be ashamed of my hope.
B019C119V117	19	119	117	Hold me up, and I shall be safe: and I will have respect unto your statutes continually.
B019C119V118	19	119	118	You have trodden down all them that stray from your statutes: for their deceit is falsehood.
B019C119V119	19	119	119	You put away all the wicked of the earth like dross: therefore I love your testimonies.
B019C119V120	19	119	120	My flesh trembles for fear of you; and I am afraid of your judgments.
B019C119V121	19	119	121	
        
B019C119V122	19	119	122	Be surety for your servant for good: let not the proud oppress me.
B019C119V123	19	119	123	My eyes fail for your salvation, and for the word of your righteousness.
B019C119V124	19	119	124	Deal with your servant according unto your mercy, and teach me your statutes.
B019C119V125	19	119	125	I am your servant; give me understanding, that I may know your testimonies.
B019C119V126	19	119	126	It is time for you, LORD, to work: for they have made void your law.
B019C119V127	19	119	127	Therefore I love your commandments above gold; yea, above fine gold.
B019C119V128	19	119	128	Therefore I esteem all your precepts concerning all things to be right; and I hate every false way.
B019C119V129	19	119	129	
        
B019C119V130	19	119	130	The entrance of your words gives light; it gives understanding unto the simple.
B019C119V131	19	119	131	I opened my mouth, and panted: for I longed for your commandments.
B019C119V132	19	119	132	Look upon me, and be merciful unto me, as you do unto those that love your name.
B019C119V133	19	119	133	Order my steps in your word: and let not any iniquity have dominion over me.
B019C119V134	19	119	134	Deliver me from the oppression of man: so will I keep your precepts.
B019C119V135	19	119	135	Make your face to shine upon your servant; and teach me your statutes.
B019C119V136	19	119	136	Rivers of waters run down my eyes, because they keep not your law.
B019C119V137	19	119	137	
        
B019C119V138	19	119	138	Your testimonies that you have commanded are righteous and very faithful.
B019C119V139	19	119	139	My zeal has consumed me, because my enemies have forgotten your words.
B019C119V140	19	119	140	Your word is very pure: therefore your servant loves it.
B019C119V141	19	119	141	I am small and despised: yet do I not forget your precepts.
B019C119V142	19	119	142	Your righteousness is an everlasting righteousness, and your law is the truth.
B019C119V143	19	119	143	Trouble and anguish have taken hold on me: yet your commandments are my delights.
B019C119V144	19	119	144	The righteousness of your testimonies is everlasting: give me understanding, and I shall live.
B019C119V145	19	119	145	I cried with my whole heart; hear me, O LORD: I will keep your statutes.
B019C119V146	19	119	146	I cried unto you; save me, and I shall keep your testimonies.
B019C119V147	19	119	147	I rose before the dawning of the morning, and cried: I hoped in your word.
B019C119V148	19	119	148	My eyes awake before the night watches, that I might meditate in your word.
B019C119V149	19	119	149	Hear my voice according unto your lovingkindness: O LORD, revive me according to your judgment.
B019C119V150	19	119	150	They draw near that follow after evil: they are far from your law.
B019C119V151	19	119	151	You are near, O LORD; and all your commandments are truth.
B019C119V152	19	119	152	Concerning your testimonies, I have known of old that you have founded them forever.
B019C119V153	19	119	153	
        
B019C119V154	19	119	154	Plead my cause, and deliver me: revive me according to your word.
B019C119V155	19	119	155	Salvation is far from the wicked: for they seek not your statutes.
B019C119V156	19	119	156	Great are your tender mercies, O LORD: revive me according to your judgments.
B019C119V157	19	119	157	Many are my persecutors and my enemies; yet do I not turn from your testimonies.
B019C119V158	19	119	158	I beheld the transgressors, and was grieved; because they kept not your word.
B019C119V159	19	119	159	Consider how I love your precepts: revive me, O LORD, according to your lovingkindness.
B019C119V160	19	119	160	Your word is true from the beginning: and every one of your righteous judgments endures forever.
B019C119V161	19	119	161	
        
B019C119V162	19	119	162	I rejoice at your word, as one that finds great spoil.
B019C119V163	19	119	163	I hate and abhor lying: but your law do I love.
B019C119V164	19	119	164	Seven times a day do I praise you because of your righteous judgments.
B019C119V165	19	119	165	Great peace have they who love your law: and nothing shall offend them.
B019C119V166	19	119	166	LORD, I have hoped for your salvation, and done your commandments.
B019C119V167	19	119	167	My soul has kept your testimonies; and I love them exceedingly.
B019C119V168	19	119	168	I have kept your precepts and your testimonies: for all my ways are before you.
B019C119V169	19	119	169	
        
B019C119V170	19	119	170	Let my supplication come before you: deliver me according to your word.
B019C119V171	19	119	171	My lips shall utter praise, when you have taught me your statutes.
B019C119V172	19	119	172	My tongue shall speak of your word: for all your commandments are righteousness.
B019C119V173	19	119	173	Let your hand help me; for I have chosen your precepts.
B019C119V174	19	119	174	I have longed for your salvation, O LORD; and your law is my delight.
B019C119V175	19	119	175	Let my soul live, and it shall praise you; and let your judgments help me.
B019C119V176	19	119	176	I have gone astray like a lost sheep; seek your servant; for I do not forget your commandments.
B019C120V001	19	120	1	
        
B019C120V002	19	120	2	Deliver my soul, O LORD, from lying lips, and from a deceitful tongue.
B019C120V003	19	120	3	What shall be given unto you? or what shall be done unto you, you false tongue?
B019C120V004	19	120	4	Sharp arrows of the mighty, with coals of juniper.
B019C120V005	19	120	5	Woe is me, that I sojourn in Meshech, that I dwell in the tents of Kedar!
B019C120V006	19	120	6	My soul has long dwelt with him that hates peace.
B019C120V007	19	120	7	I am for peace: but when I speak, they are for war.
B019C121V001	19	121	1	
        
B019C121V002	19	121	2	My help comes from the LORD, who made heaven and earth.
B019C121V003	19	121	3	He will not allow your foot to be moved: he that keeps you will not slumber.
B019C121V004	19	121	4	Behold, he that keeps Israel shall neither slumber nor sleep.
B019C121V005	19	121	5	The LORD is your keeper: the LORD is your shade upon your right hand.
B019C121V006	19	121	6	The sun shall not strike you by day, nor the moon by night.
B019C121V007	19	121	7	The LORD shall preserve you from all evil: he shall preserve your soul.
B019C121V008	19	121	8	The LORD shall preserve your going out and your coming in from this time forth, and even forevermore.
B019C122V001	19	122	1	
        
B019C122V002	19	122	2	Our feet shall stand within your gates, O Jerusalem.
B019C122V003	19	122	3	Jerusalem is built as a city that is compact together:
B019C122V004	19	122	4	Where the tribes go up, the tribes of the LORD, unto the testimony of Israel, to give thanks unto the name of the LORD.
B019C122V005	19	122	5	For there are set thrones of judgment, the thrones of the house of David.
B019C122V006	19	122	6	Pray for the peace of Jerusalem: they shall prosper that love you.
B019C122V007	19	122	7	Peace be within your walls, and prosperity within your palaces.
B019C122V008	19	122	8	For my brethren and companions' sakes, I will now say, Peace be within you.
B019C122V009	19	122	9	Because of the house of the LORD our God I will seek your good.
B019C123V001	19	123	1	
        
B019C123V002	19	123	2	Behold, as the eyes of servants look unto the hand of their masters, and as the eyes of a maiden unto the hand of her mistress; so our eyes wait upon the LORD our God, until he has mercy upon us.
B019C123V003	19	123	3	Have mercy upon us, O LORD, have mercy upon us: for we are exceedingly filled with contempt.
B019C123V004	19	123	4	Our soul is exceedingly filled with the scorn of those that are at ease, and with the contempt of the proud.
B019C124V001	19	124	1	
        
B019C124V002	19	124	2	If it had not been the LORD who was on our side, when men rose up against us:
B019C124V003	19	124	3	Then they would have swallowed us up alive, when their wrath was kindled against us:
B019C124V004	19	124	4	Then the waters would have overwhelmed us, the stream would have gone over our soul:
B019C124V005	19	124	5	Then the proud waters would have gone over our soul.
B019C124V006	19	124	6	Blessed be the LORD, who has not given us as a prey to their teeth.
B019C124V007	19	124	7	Our soul is escaped as a bird out of the snare of the fowlers: the snare is broken, and we are escaped.
B019C124V008	19	124	8	Our help is in the name of the LORD, who made heaven and earth.
B019C125V001	19	125	1	
        
B019C125V002	19	125	2	As the mountains are round about Jerusalem, so the LORD is round about his people from this time forth even forever.
B019C125V003	19	125	3	For the rod of the wicked shall not rest upon the lot of the righteous; lest the righteous put forth their hands unto iniquity.
B019C125V004	19	125	4	Do good, O LORD, unto those that be good, and to them that are upright in their hearts.
B019C125V005	19	125	5	As for such as turn aside unto their crooked ways, the LORD shall lead them forth with the workers of iniquity: but peace shall be upon Israel.
B019C126V001	19	126	1	
        
B019C126V002	19	126	2	Then was our mouth filled with laughter, and our tongue with singing: then said they among the nations, The LORD has done great things for them.
B019C126V003	19	126	3	The LORD has done great things for us; and we are glad.
B019C126V004	19	126	4	Turn again our captivity, O LORD, as the streams in the South.
B019C126V005	19	126	5	They that sow in tears shall reap in joy.
B019C126V006	19	126	6	He that goes forth weeping, bearing precious seed, shall doubtless come again with rejoicing, bringing his sheaves with him.
B019C127V001	19	127	1	
        
B019C127V002	19	127	2	It is vain for you to rise up early, to sit up late, to eat the bread of sorrows: for so he gives his beloved sleep.
B019C127V003	19	127	3	Lo, children are a heritage of the LORD: and the fruit of the womb is his reward.
B019C127V004	19	127	4	As arrows are in the hand of a mighty man; so are children of the youth.
B019C127V005	19	127	5	Happy is the man that has his quiver full of them: they shall not be ashamed, but they shall speak with the enemies in the gate.
B019C128V001	19	128	1	
        
B019C128V002	19	128	2	For you shall eat the labor of your hands: happy shall you be, and it shall be well with you.
B019C128V003	19	128	3	Your wife shall be as a fruitful vine by the sides of your house: your children like olive plants round about your table.
B019C128V004	19	128	4	Behold, thus shall the man be blessed that fears the LORD.
B019C128V005	19	128	5	The LORD shall bless you out of Zion: and you shall see the good of Jerusalem all the days of your life.
B019C128V006	19	128	6	Yea, you shall see your children's children, and peace upon Israel.
B019C129V001	19	129	1	
        
B019C129V002	19	129	2	Many a time have they afflicted me from my youth: yet they have not prevailed against me.
B019C129V003	19	129	3	The plowers plowed upon my back: they made long their furrows.
B019C129V004	19	129	4	The LORD is righteous: he has cut asunder the cords of the wicked.
B019C129V005	19	129	5	Let them all be confounded and turned back that hate Zion.
B019C129V006	19	129	6	Let them be as the grass upon the housetops, which withers before it grows up:
B019C129V007	19	129	7	With which the reaper fills not his hand; nor he that binds sheaves his bosom.
B019C129V008	19	129	8	Neither do they who go by say, The blessing of the LORD be upon you: we bless you in the name of the LORD.
B019C130V001	19	130	1	
        
B019C130V002	19	130	2	Lord, hear my voice: let your ears be attentive to the voice of my supplications.
B019C130V003	19	130	3	If you, LORD, should mark iniquities, O Lord, who shall stand?
B019C130V004	19	130	4	But there is forgiveness with you, that you may be feared.
B019C130V005	19	130	5	I wait for the LORD, my soul does wait, and in his word do I hope.
B019C130V006	19	130	6	My soul waits for the Lord more than they that watch for the morning: I say, more than they that watch for the morning.
B019C130V007	19	130	7	Let Israel hope in the LORD: for with the LORD there is mercy, and with him is abundant redemption.
B019C130V008	19	130	8	And he shall redeem Israel from all his iniquities.
B019C131V001	19	131	1	
        
B019C131V002	19	131	2	Surely I have behaved and quieted myself, as a child that is weaned of his mother: my soul is even as a weaned child.
B019C131V003	19	131	3	Let Israel hope in the LORD from this time forth and forever.
B019C132V001	19	132	1	
        
B019C132V002	19	132	2	How he swore unto the LORD, and vowed unto the mighty God of Jacob;
B019C132V003	19	132	3	Surely I will not come into the tabernacle of my house, nor go up into my bed;
B019C132V004	19	132	4	I will not give sleep to my eyes, or slumber to my eyelids,
B019C132V005	19	132	5	Until I find out a place for the LORD, a habitation for the mighty God of Jacob.
B019C132V006	19	132	6	Lo, we heard of it at Ephrathah: we found it in the fields of the woods.
B019C132V007	19	132	7	We will go into his tabernacles: we will worship at his footstool.
B019C132V008	19	132	8	Arise, O LORD, into your rest; you, and the ark of your strength.
B019C132V009	19	132	9	Let your priests be clothed with righteousness; and let your saints shout for joy.
B019C132V010	19	132	10	For your servant David's sake turn not away the face of your anointed.
B019C132V011	19	132	11	The LORD has sworn in truth unto David; he will not turn from it; 
B019C132V012	19	132	12	
        
B019C132V013	19	132	13	For the LORD has chosen Zion; he has desired it for his habitation.
B019C132V014	19	132	14	
        
B019C132V015	19	132	15	
        
B019C132V016	19	132	16	
        
B019C132V017	19	132	17	
        
B019C132V018	19	132	18	
        
B019C133V001	19	133	1	
        
B019C133V002	19	133	2	It is like the precious ointment upon the head, that ran down upon the beard, even Aaron's beard: that went down to the skirts of his garments;
B019C133V003	19	133	3	As the dew of Hermon, and as the dew that descended upon the mountains of Zion: for there the LORD commanded the blessing, even life forevermore.
B019C134V001	19	134	1	
        
B019C134V002	19	134	2	Lift up your hands in the sanctuary, and bless the LORD.
B019C134V003	19	134	3	The LORD that made heaven and earth bless you out of Zion.
B019C135V001	19	135	1	Praise you the LORD. Praise you the name of the LORD; praise him, O you servants of the LORD.
B019C135V002	19	135	2	You that stand in the house of the LORD, in the courts of the house of our God,
B019C135V003	19	135	3	Praise the LORD; for the LORD is good: sing praises unto his name; for it is pleasant.
B019C135V004	19	135	4	For the LORD has chosen Jacob unto himself, and Israel for his peculiar treasure.
B019C135V005	19	135	5	For I know that the LORD is great, and that our Lord is above all gods.
B019C135V006	19	135	6	Whatsoever the LORD pleased, that did he in heaven, and in earth, in the seas, and all deep places.
B019C135V007	19	135	7	He causes the vapors to ascend from the ends of the earth; he makes lightnings for the rain; he brings the wind out of his treasuries.
B019C135V008	19	135	8	Who struck the firstborn of Egypt, both of man and beast.
B019C135V009	19	135	9	Who sent signs and wonders into the midst of you, O Egypt, upon Pharaoh, and upon all his servants.
B019C135V010	19	135	10	Who struck great nations, and slew mighty kings;
B019C135V011	19	135	11	Sihon king of the Amorites, and Og king of Bashan, and all the kingdoms of Canaan:
B019C135V012	19	135	12	And gave their land for a heritage, a heritage unto Israel his people.
B019C135V013	19	135	13	Your name, O LORD, endures forever; and your memorial, O LORD, throughout all generations.
B019C135V014	19	135	14	For the LORD will judge his people, and he will have compassion on his servants.
B019C135V015	19	135	15	The idols of the nations are silver and gold, the work of men's hands.
B019C135V016	19	135	16	They have mouths, but they speak not; eyes have they, but they see not;
B019C135V017	19	135	17	They have ears, but they hear not; neither is there any breath in their mouths.
B019C135V018	19	135	18	They that make them are like unto them: so is every one that trusts in them.
B019C135V019	19	135	19	Bless the LORD, O house of Israel: bless the LORD, O house of Aaron:
B019C135V020	19	135	20	Bless the LORD, O house of Levi: you that fear the LORD, bless the LORD.
B019C135V021	19	135	21	Blessed be the LORD out of Zion, who dwells at Jerusalem. Praise you the LORD.
B019C136V001	19	136	1	O give thanks unto the LORD; for he is good: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V002	19	136	2	O give thanks unto the God of gods: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V003	19	136	3	O give thanks to the Lord of lords: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V004	19	136	4	To him who alone does great wonders: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V005	19	136	5	To him that by wisdom made the heavens: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V006	19	136	6	To him that stretched out the earth above the waters: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V007	19	136	7	To him that made great lights: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V008	19	136	8	The sun to rule by day: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V009	19	136	9	The moon and stars to rule by night: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V010	19	136	10	To him that struck Egypt in their firstborn: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V011	19	136	11	And brought out Israel from among them: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V012	19	136	12	With a strong hand, and with an outstretched arm: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V013	19	136	13	To him who divided the Red sea into parts: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V014	19	136	14	And made Israel to pass through the midst of it: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V015	19	136	15	But overthrew Pharaoh and his host in the Red sea: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V016	19	136	16	To him who led his people through the wilderness: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V017	19	136	17	To him who struck great kings: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V018	19	136	18	And slew famous kings: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V019	19	136	19	Sihon king of the Amorites: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V020	19	136	20	And Og the king of Bashan: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V021	19	136	21	And gave their land for a heritage: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V022	19	136	22	Even a heritage unto Israel his servant: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V023	19	136	23	Who remembered us in our low estate: for his mercy endures forever:
B019C136V024	19	136	24	And has redeemed us from our enemies: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V025	19	136	25	Who gives food to all flesh: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C136V026	19	136	26	O give thanks unto the God of heaven: for his mercy endures forever.
B019C137V001	19	137	1	By the rivers of Babylon, there we sat down, yea, we wept, when we remembered Zion.
B019C137V002	19	137	2	We hung our harps upon the willows in the midst thereof.
B019C137V003	19	137	3	For there they that carried us away captive required of us a song; and they that wasted us required of us mirth, saying, Sing us one of the songs of Zion.
B019C137V004	19	137	4	How shall we sing the LORD's song in a foreign land?
B019C137V005	19	137	5	If I forget you, O Jerusalem, let my right hand forget its cunning.
B019C137V006	19	137	6	If I do not remember you, let my tongue cleave to the roof of my mouth; if I prefer not Jerusalem above my chief joy.
B019C137V007	19	137	7	Remember, O LORD, the children of Edom in the day of Jerusalem; who said, Raze it, raze it, even to the foundation thereof.
B019C137V008	19	137	8	O daughter of Babylon, who are to be destroyed; happy shall he be, that rewards you as you have served us.
B019C137V009	19	137	9	Happy shall he be, that takes and dashes your little ones against the stones.
B019C138V001	19	138	1	
        
B019C138V002	19	138	2	I will worship toward your holy temple, and praise your name for your lovingkindness and for your truth: for you have magnified your word above all your name.
B019C138V003	19	138	3	In the day when I cried you answered me, and strengthened me with strength in my soul.
B019C138V004	19	138	4	All the kings of the earth shall praise you, O LORD, when they hear the words of your mouth.
B019C138V005	19	138	5	Yea, they shall sing in the ways of the LORD: for great is the glory of the LORD.
B019C138V006	19	138	6	Though the LORD be high, yet has he respect unto the lowly: but the proud he knows from afar.
B019C138V007	19	138	7	Though I walk in the midst of trouble, you will revive me: you shall stretch forth your hand against the wrath of my enemies, and your right hand shall save me.
B019C138V008	19	138	8	The LORD will perfect that which concerns me: your mercy, O LORD, endures forever: forsake not the works of your own hands.
B019C139V001	19	139	1	
        
B019C139V002	19	139	2	You know my downsitting and my uprising, you understand my thought afar off.
B019C139V003	19	139	3	You search out my path and my lying down, and are acquainted with all my ways.
B019C139V004	19	139	4	For there is not a word in my tongue, but, lo, O LORD, you know it altogether.
B019C139V005	19	139	5	You have hedged me behind and before, and laid your hand upon me.
B019C139V006	19	139	6	Such knowledge is too wonderful for me; it is high, I cannot attain unto it.
B019C139V007	19	139	7	Where shall I go from your Spirit? or where shall I flee from your presence?
B019C139V008	19	139	8	If I ascend up into heaven, you are there: if I make my bed in Sheol, behold, you are there.
B019C139V009	19	139	9	If I take the wings of the morning, and dwell in the uttermost parts of the sea;
B019C139V010	19	139	10	Even there shall your hand lead me, and your right hand shall hold me.
B019C139V011	19	139	11	If I say, Surely the darkness shall cover me; even the night shall be light about me.
B019C139V012	19	139	12	Yea, the darkness hides not from you; but the night shines as the day: the darkness and the light are both alike to you.
B019C139V013	19	139	13	For you have formed my inward parts: you have covered me in my mother's womb.
B019C139V014	19	139	14	I will praise you; for I am fearfully and wonderfully made: marvelous are your works; and that my soul knows right well.
B019C139V015	19	139	15	My frame was not hid from you, when I was made in secret, and skillfully wrought in the lowest parts of the earth.
B019C139V016	19	139	16	Your eyes did see my substance, being yet unformed; and in your book they were all written, the days fashioned for me, when as yet there were none of them.
B019C139V017	19	139	17	How precious also are your thoughts unto me, O God! how great is the sum of them!
B019C139V018	19	139	18	If I should count them, they are more in number than the sand: when I awake, I am still with you.
B019C139V019	19	139	19	Surely you will slay the wicked, O God: depart from me therefore, you bloody men.
B019C139V020	19	139	20	For they speak against you wickedly, and your enemies take your name in vain.
B019C139V021	19	139	21	Do not I hate them, O LORD, that hate you? and am not I grieved with those that rise up against you?
B019C139V022	19	139	22	I hate them with perfect hatred: I count them my enemies.
B019C139V023	19	139	23	Search me, O God, and know my heart: try me, and know my thoughts:
B019C139V024	19	139	24	And see if there be any wicked way in me, and lead me in the way everlasting.
B019C140V001	19	140	1	
        
B019C140V002	19	140	2	Who imagine evil in their heart; continually are they gathered together for war.
B019C140V003	19	140	3	They have sharpened their tongues like a serpent; adders' poison is under their lips. Selah.
B019C140V004	19	140	4	Keep me, O LORD, from the hands of the wicked; preserve me from the violent man; who have purposed to overthrow my paths.
B019C140V005	19	140	5	The proud have hid a snare for me, and cords; they have spread a net by the wayside; they have set traps for me. Selah.
B019C140V006	19	140	6	I said unto the LORD, you are my God: hear the voice of my supplications, O LORD.
B019C140V007	19	140	7	O GOD the Lord, the strength of my salvation, you have covered my head in the day of battle.
B019C140V008	19	140	8	Grant not, O LORD, the desires of the wicked: further not his wicked device; lest they exalt themselves. Selah.
B019C140V009	19	140	9	As for the head of those that compass me about, let the mischief of their own lips cover them.
B019C140V010	19	140	10	Let burning coals fall upon them: let them be cast into the fire; into deep pits, that they rise not up again.
B019C140V011	19	140	11	Let not an evil speaker be established in the earth: evil shall hunt the violent man to overthrow him.
B019C140V012	19	140	12	I know that the LORD will maintain the cause of the afflicted, and the right of the poor.
B019C140V013	19	140	13	Surely the righteous shall give thanks unto your name: the upright shall dwell in your presence.
B019C141V001	19	141	1	
        
B019C141V002	19	141	2	Let my prayer be set forth before you as incense; and the lifting up of my hands as the evening sacrifice.
B019C141V003	19	141	3	Set a watch, O LORD, before my mouth; keep watch over the door of my lips.
B019C141V004	19	141	4	Incline not my heart to any evil thing, to practice wicked works with men that work iniquity: and let me not eat of their delicacies.
B019C141V005	19	141	5	Let the righteous strike me; it shall be a kindness: and let him reprove me; it shall be an excellent oil, which shall not break my head: for yet my prayer also shall be against their evil.
B019C141V006	19	141	6	When their judges are overthrown in stony places, they shall hear my words; for they are sweet.
B019C141V007	19	141	7	Our bones are scattered at the grave's mouth, as when one cuts and splits wood upon the earth.
B019C141V008	19	141	8	But my eyes are unto you, O GOD the Lord: in you is my trust; leave not my soul destitute.
B019C141V009	19	141	9	Keep me from the snares which they have laid for me, and the traps of the workers of iniquity.
B019C141V010	19	141	10	Let the wicked fall into their own nets, while I thus escape.
B019C142V001	19	142	1	
        
B019C142V002	19	142	2	I poured out my complaint before him; I showed before him my trouble.
B019C142V003	19	142	3	When my spirit was overwhelmed within me, then you knew my path. In the way in which I walked have they secretly laid a snare for me.
B019C142V004	19	142	4	I looked on my right hand, and beheld, but there was no man that would acknowledge me: refuge failed me; no man cared for my soul.
B019C142V005	19	142	5	I cried unto you, O LORD: I said, you are my refuge and my portion in the land of the living.
B019C142V006	19	142	6	Attend unto my cry; for I am brought very low: deliver me from my persecutors; for they are stronger than I.
B019C142V007	19	142	7	Bring my soul out of prison, that I may praise your name: the righteous shall surround me; for you shall deal bountifully with me.
B019C143V001	19	143	1	
        
B019C143V002	19	143	2	And enter not into judgment with your servant: for in your sight shall no man living be justified.
B019C143V003	19	143	3	For the enemy has persecuted my soul; he has smitten my life down to the ground; he has made me to dwell in darkness, as those that have been long dead.
B019C143V004	19	143	4	Therefore is my spirit overwhelmed within me; my heart within me is desolate.
B019C143V005	19	143	5	I remember the days of old; I meditate on all your works; I ponder on the work of your hands.
B019C143V006	19	143	6	I stretch forth my hands unto you: my soul thirsts after you, as a thirsty land. Selah.
B019C143V007	19	143	7	Hear me speedily, O LORD: my spirit fails: hide not your face from me, lest I be like unto them that go down into the pit.
B019C143V008	19	143	8	Cause me to hear your lovingkindness in the morning; for in you do I trust: cause me to know the way in which I should walk; for I lift up my soul unto you.
B019C143V009	19	143	9	Deliver me, O LORD, from my enemies: I flee unto you to hide me.
B019C143V010	19	143	10	Teach me to do your will; for you are my God: your Spirit is good; lead me into the land of uprightness.
B019C143V011	19	143	11	Revive me, O LORD, for your name's sake: for your righteousness' sake bring my soul out of trouble.
B019C143V012	19	143	12	And in your mercy cut off my enemies, and destroy all them that afflict my soul: for I am your servant.
B019C144V001	19	144	1	
        
B019C144V002	19	144	2	My goodness, and my fortress; my high tower, and my deliverer; my shield, and he in whom I trust; who subdues my people under me.
B019C144V003	19	144	3	LORD, what is man, that you take knowledge of him! or the son of man, that you make account of him!
B019C144V004	19	144	4	Man is like to vanity: his days are as a shadow that passes away.
B019C144V005	19	144	5	Bow your heavens, O LORD, and come down: touch the mountains, and they shall smoke.
B019C144V006	19	144	6	Cast forth lightning, and scatter them: shoot out your arrows, and destroy them.
B019C144V007	19	144	7	Send your hand from above; rid me, and deliver me out of great waters, from the hand of foreigners;
B019C144V008	19	144	8	Whose mouth speaks vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood.
B019C144V009	19	144	9	I will sing a new song unto you, O God: upon a psaltery and an instrument of ten strings will I sing praises unto you.
B019C144V010	19	144	10	It is he that gives salvation unto kings: who delivers David his servant from the hurtful sword.
B019C144V011	19	144	11	Rid me, and deliver me from the hand of foreigners, whose mouth speaks vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood:
B019C144V012	19	144	12	That our sons may be as plants grown up in their youth; that our daughters may be as corner pillars, polished after the similitude of a palace:
B019C144V013	19	144	13	That our barns may be full, affording all manner of store: that our sheep may bring forth thousands and ten thousands in our streets:
B019C144V014	19	144	14	That our oxen may be strong to labor; that there be no breaking in, nor going out; that there be no outcry in our streets.
B019C144V015	19	144	15	Happy is that people, that is in such a state: yea, happy is that people, whose God is the LORD.
B019C145V001	19	145	1	
        
B019C145V002	19	145	2	Every day will I bless you; and I will praise your name forever and ever.
B019C145V003	19	145	3	Great is the LORD, and greatly to be praised; and his greatness is unsearchable.
B019C145V004	19	145	4	One generation shall praise your works to another, and shall declare your mighty acts.
B019C145V005	19	145	5	I will speak of the glorious honor of your majesty, and of your wondrous works.
B019C145V006	19	145	6	And men shall speak of the might of your wondrous acts: and I will declare your greatness.
B019C145V007	19	145	7	They shall abundantly utter the memory of your great goodness, and shall sing of your righteousness.
B019C145V008	19	145	8	The LORD is gracious, and full of compassion; slow to anger, and of great mercy.
B019C145V009	19	145	9	The LORD is good to all: and his tender mercies are over all his works.
B019C145V010	19	145	10	All your works shall praise you, O LORD; and your saints shall bless you.
B019C145V011	19	145	11	They shall speak of the glory of your kingdom, and talk of your power;
B019C145V012	19	145	12	To make known to the sons of men his mighty acts, and the glorious majesty of his kingdom.
B019C145V013	19	145	13	Your kingdom is an everlasting kingdom, and your dominion endures throughout all generations.
B019C145V014	19	145	14	The LORD upholds all that fall, and raises up all those that are bowed down.
B019C145V015	19	145	15	The eyes of all wait upon you; and you give them their food in due season.
B019C145V016	19	145	16	You open your hand, and satisfy the desire of every living thing.
B019C145V017	19	145	17	The LORD is righteous in all his ways, and holy in all his works.
B019C145V018	19	145	18	The LORD is near unto all them that call upon him, to all that call upon him in truth.
B019C145V019	19	145	19	He will fulfill the desire of them that fear him: he also will hear their cry, and will save them.
B019C145V020	19	145	20	The LORD preserves all them that love him: but all the wicked will he destroy.
B019C145V021	19	145	21	My mouth shall speak the praise of the LORD: and let all flesh bless his holy name forever and ever.
B019C146V001	19	146	1	Praise you the LORD. Praise the LORD, O my soul.
B019C146V002	19	146	2	While I live will I praise the LORD: I will sing praises unto my God while I have any being.
B019C146V003	19	146	3	Put not your trust in princes, nor in the son of man, in whom there is no help.
B019C146V004	19	146	4	His breath goes forth, he returns to his earth; in that very day his thoughts perish.
B019C146V005	19	146	5	Happy is he that has the God of Jacob for his help, whose hope is in the LORD his God:
B019C146V006	19	146	6	Who made heaven, and earth, the sea, and all that is therein: who keeps truth forever:
B019C146V007	19	146	7	Who executes justice for the oppressed: who gives food to the hungry. The LORD looses the prisoners:
B019C146V008	19	146	8	The LORD opens the eyes of the blind: the LORD raises them that are bowed down: the LORD loves the righteous:
B019C146V009	19	146	9	The LORD preserves the strangers; he relieves the fatherless and widow: but the way of the wicked he turns upside down.
B019C146V010	19	146	10	The LORD shall reign forever, even your God, O Zion, unto all generations. Praise you the LORD.
B019C147V001	19	147	1	Praise you the LORD: for it is good to sing praises unto our God; for it is pleasant; and praise is fitting.
B019C147V002	19	147	2	The LORD does build up Jerusalem: he gathers together the outcasts of Israel.
B019C147V003	19	147	3	He heals the broken in heart, and binds up their wounds.
B019C147V004	19	147	4	He determines the number of the stars; he calls them all by their names.
B019C147V005	19	147	5	Great is our Lord, and of great power: his understanding is infinite.
B019C147V006	19	147	6	The LORD lifts up the meek: he casts the wicked down to the ground.
B019C147V007	19	147	7	Sing unto the LORD with thanksgiving; sing praise upon the harp unto our God:
B019C147V008	19	147	8	Who covers the heaven with clouds, who prepares rain for the earth, who makes grass to grow upon the mountains.
B019C147V009	19	147	9	He gives to the beast its food, and to the young ravens that cry.
B019C147V010	19	147	10	He delights not in the strength of the horse: he takes not pleasure in the legs of a man.
B019C147V011	19	147	11	The LORD takes pleasure in them that fear him, in those that hope in his mercy.
B019C147V012	19	147	12	Praise the LORD, O Jerusalem; praise your God, O Zion.
B019C147V013	19	147	13	For he has strengthened the bars of your gates; he has blessed your children within you.
B019C147V014	19	147	14	He makes peace in your borders, and fills you with the finest of the wheat.
B019C147V015	19	147	15	He sends forth his commandment upon earth: his word runs very swiftly.
B019C147V016	19	147	16	He gives snow like wool: he scatters the frost like ashes.
B019C147V017	19	147	17	He casts forth his ice like morsels: who can stand before his cold?
B019C147V018	19	147	18	He sends out his word, and melts them: he causes his wind to blow, and the waters flow.
B019C147V019	19	147	19	He shows his word unto Jacob, his statutes and his judgments unto Israel.
B019C147V020	19	147	20	He has not dealt so with any nation: and as for his judgments, they have not known them. Praise you the LORD.
B019C148V001	19	148	1	Praise you the LORD. Praise you the LORD from the heavens: praise him in the heights.
B019C148V002	19	148	2	Praise him, all his angels: praise him, all his hosts.
B019C148V003	19	148	3	Praise him, sun and moon: praise him, all you stars of light.
B019C148V004	19	148	4	Praise him, you heavens of heavens, and you waters that be above the heavens.
B019C148V005	19	148	5	Let them praise the name of the LORD: for he commanded, and they were created.
B019C148V006	19	148	6	He has also established them forever and ever: he has made a decree which shall not pass.
B019C148V007	19	148	7	Praise the LORD from the earth, you sea creatures, and all deeps:
B019C148V008	19	148	8	Fire, and hail; snow, and vapors; stormy wind fulfilling his word:
B019C148V009	19	148	9	Mountains, and all hills; fruitful trees, and all cedars:
B019C148V010	19	148	10	Beasts, and all cattle; creeping things, and flying fowl:
B019C148V011	19	148	11	Kings of the earth, and all people; princes, and all judges of the earth:
B019C148V012	19	148	12	Both young men, and maidens; old men, and children:
B019C148V013	19	148	13	Let them praise the name of the LORD: for his name alone is excellent; his glory is above the earth and heaven.
B019C148V014	19	148	14	He also exalts the horn of his people, the praise of all his saints; even of the children of Israel, a people near unto him. Praise you the LORD.
B019C149V001	19	149	1	Praise you the LORD. Sing unto the LORD a new song, and his praise in the congregation of saints.
B019C149V002	19	149	2	Let Israel rejoice in him that made him: let the children of Zion be joyful in their King.
B019C149V003	19	149	3	Let them praise his name in the dance: let them sing praises unto him with the timbrel and harp.
B019C149V004	19	149	4	For the LORD takes pleasure in his people: he will beautify the meek with salvation.
B019C149V005	19	149	5	Let the saints be joyful in glory: let them sing aloud upon their beds.
B019C149V006	19	149	6	Let the high praises of God be in their mouth, and a two-edged sword in their hand;
B019C149V007	19	149	7	To execute vengeance upon the nations, and punishments upon the people;
B019C149V008	19	149	8	To bind their kings with chains, and their nobles with fetters of iron;
B019C149V009	19	149	9	To execute upon them the judgment written: this honor have all his saints. Praise you the LORD.
B019C150V001	19	150	1	Praise you the LORD. Praise God in his sanctuary: praise him in the firmament of his power.
B019C150V002	19	150	2	Praise him for his mighty acts: praise him according to his excellent greatness.
B019C150V003	19	150	3	Praise him with the sound of the trumpet: praise him with the lute and harp.
B019C150V004	19	150	4	Praise him with the timbrel and dance: praise him with stringed instruments and pipes.
B019C150V005	19	150	5	Praise him upon the loud cymbals: praise him upon the clashing cymbals.
B019C150V006	19	150	6	Let every thing that has breath praise the LORD. Praise you the LORD.
B020C001V001	20	1	1	The proverbs of Solomon the son of David, king of Israel;
B020C001V002	20	1	2	To know wisdom and instruction; to perceive the words of understanding;
B020C001V003	20	1	3	To receive the instruction of wisdom, justice, and judgment, and equity;
B020C001V004	20	1	4	To give prudence to the simple, to the young man knowledge and discretion.
B020C001V005	20	1	5	A wise man will hear, and will increase learning; and a man of understanding shall attain unto wise counsels:
B020C001V006	20	1	6	To understand a proverb, and the interpretation; the words of the wise, and their riddles.
B020C001V007	20	1	7	The fear of the LORD is the beginning of knowledge: but fools despise wisdom and instruction.
B020C001V008	20	1	8	My son, hear the instruction of your father, and forsake not the law of your mother:
B020C001V009	20	1	9	For they shall be an ornament of grace unto your head, and chains about your neck.
B020C001V010	20	1	10	My son, if sinners entice you, consent not.
B020C001V011	20	1	11	If they say, Come with us, let us lie in wait for blood, let us lurk secretly for the innocent without cause:
B020C001V012	20	1	12	Let us swallow them up alive as the grave; and whole, as those that go down into the pit:
B020C001V013	20	1	13	We shall find all kinds of precious substance, we shall fill our houses with spoil:
B020C001V014	20	1	14	Cast in your lot among us; let us all have one purse:
B020C001V015	20	1	15	My son, walk not in the way with them; refrain your foot from their path:
B020C001V016	20	1	16	For their feet run to evil, and make haste to shed blood.
B020C001V017	20	1	17	Surely in vain the net is spread in the sight of any bird.
B020C001V018	20	1	18	And they lie in wait for their own blood; they lurk secretly for their own lives.
B020C001V019	20	1	19	So are the ways of everyone that is greedy of gain; which takes away the life of its owners.
B020C001V020	20	1	20	Wisdom cries aloud outside; she raises her voice in the open square:
B020C001V021	20	1	21	She cries in the chief place of concourse, in the openings of the gates: in the city she utters her words, saying,
B020C001V022	20	1	22	How long, you simple ones, will you love simplicity? and the scoffers delight in their scoffing, and fools hate knowledge?
B020C001V023	20	1	23	Turn you at my reproof: behold, I will pour out my spirit unto you, I will make known my words unto you.
B020C001V024	20	1	24	Because I have called, and you refused; I have stretched out my hand, and no man regarded;
B020C001V025	20	1	25	But you have ignored all my counsel, and would have none of my reproof:
B020C001V026	20	1	26	I also will laugh at your calamity; I will mock when your fear comes;
B020C001V027	20	1	27	When your terror comes as desolation, and your destruction comes as a whirlwind; when distress and anguish comes upon you.
B020C001V028	20	1	28	Then shall they call upon me, but I will not answer; they shall seek me early, but they shall not find me:
B020C001V029	20	1	29	Because they hated knowledge, and did not choose the fear of the LORD:
B020C001V030	20	1	30	They would have none of my counsel: they despised all my reproof.
B020C001V031	20	1	31	Therefore shall they eat of the fruit of their own way, and be filled with their own devices.
B020C001V032	20	1	32	For the turning away of the simple shall slay them, and the prosperity of fools shall destroy them.
B020C001V033	20	1	33	But whosoever hearkens unto me shall dwell safely, and shall be secure from the fear of evil.
B020C002V001	20	2	1	My son, if you will receive my words, and lay up my commandments with you;
B020C002V002	20	2	2	So that you incline your ear unto wisdom, and apply your heart to understanding;
B020C002V003	20	2	3	Yea, if you cry after knowledge, and lift up your voice for understanding;
B020C002V004	20	2	4	If you seek her as silver, and search for her as for hid treasures;
B020C002V005	20	2	5	Then shall you understand the fear of the LORD, and find the knowledge of God.
B020C002V006	20	2	6	For the LORD gives wisdom: out of his mouth comes knowledge and understanding.
B020C002V007	20	2	7	He lays up sound wisdom for the righteous: he is a shield to them that walk uprightly.
B020C002V008	20	2	8	He keeps the paths of justice, and preserves the way of his saints.
B020C002V009	20	2	9	Then shall you understand righteousness, and justice, and equity; yea, every good path.
B020C002V010	20	2	10	When wisdom enters into your heart, and knowledge is pleasant unto your soul;
B020C002V011	20	2	11	Discretion shall preserve you, understanding shall keep you:
B020C002V012	20	2	12	To deliver you from the way of the evil man, from the man that speaks perverse things;
B020C002V013	20	2	13	Who leave the paths of uprightness, to walk in the ways of darkness;
B020C002V014	20	2	14	Who rejoice to do evil, and delight in the perverseness of the wicked;
B020C002V015	20	2	15	Whose ways are crooked, and who are perverse in their paths:
B020C002V016	20	2	16	To deliver you from the immoral woman, even from the seductress who flatters with her words;
B020C002V017	20	2	17	Who forsakes the companion of her youth, and forgets the covenant of her God.
B020C002V018	20	2	18	For her house leads unto death, and her paths unto the dead.
B020C002V019	20	2	19	None that go unto her return again, neither take they hold of the paths of life.
B020C002V020	20	2	20	That you may walk in the way of good men, and keep the paths of the righteous.
B020C002V021	20	2	21	For the upright shall dwell in the land, and the blameless shall remain in it.
B020C002V022	20	2	22	But the wicked shall be cut off from the earth, and the transgressors shall be rooted out of it.
B020C003V001	20	3	1	My son, forget not my law; but let your heart keep my commandments:
B020C003V002	20	3	2	For length of days, and long life, and peace, shall they add to you.
B020C003V003	20	3	3	Let not mercy and truth forsake you: bind them about your neck; write them upon the table of your heart:
B020C003V004	20	3	4	So shall you find favor and good understanding in the sight of God and man.
B020C003V005	20	3	5	Trust in the LORD with all your heart; and lean not unto your own understanding.
B020C003V006	20	3	6	In all your ways acknowledge him, and he shall direct your paths.
B020C003V007	20	3	7	Be not wise in your own eyes: fear the LORD, and depart from evil.
B020C003V008	20	3	8	It shall be health to your body, and strength to your bones.
B020C003V009	20	3	9	Honor the LORD with your substance, and with the firstfruits of all your increase:
B020C003V010	20	3	10	So shall your barns be filled with plenty, and your presses shall burst out with new wine.
B020C003V011	20	3	11	My son, despise not the chastening of the LORD; neither be weary of his correction:
B020C003V012	20	3	12	For whom the LORD loves he corrects; even as a father the son in whom he delights.
B020C003V013	20	3	13	Happy is the man that finds wisdom, and the man that gets understanding.
B020C003V014	20	3	14	For the gain from it is better than the gain from silver, and the profit thereof than fine gold.
B020C003V015	20	3	15	She is more precious than rubies: and all the things you can desire are not to be compared unto her.
B020C003V016	20	3	16	Length of days is in her right hand; and in her left hand riches and honor.
B020C003V017	20	3	17	Her ways are ways of pleasantness, and all her paths are peace.
B020C003V018	20	3	18	She is a tree of life to them that lay hold upon her: and happy is everyone that retains her.
B020C003V019	20	3	19	The LORD by wisdom has founded the earth; by understanding has he established the heavens.
B020C003V020	20	3	20	By his knowledge the depths are broken up, and the clouds drop down the dew.
B020C003V021	20	3	21	My son, let not them depart from your eyes: keep sound wisdom and discretion:
B020C003V022	20	3	22	So shall they be life unto your soul, and grace to your neck.
B020C003V023	20	3	23	Then shall you walk in your way safely, and your foot shall not stumble.
B020C003V024	20	3	24	When you lie down, you shall not be afraid: yea, you shall lie down, and your sleep shall be sweet.
B020C003V025	20	3	25	Be not afraid of sudden fear, neither of the ruin from the wicked, when it comes.
B020C003V026	20	3	26	For the LORD shall be your confidence, and shall keep your foot from being snared.
B020C003V027	20	3	27	Withhold not good from them to whom it is due, when it is in the power of your hand to do it.
B020C003V028	20	3	28	Say not unto your neighbor, Go, and come again, and tomorrow I will give; when you have it with you.
B020C003V029	20	3	29	Devise not evil against your neighbor, seeing he dwells securely by you.
B020C003V030	20	3	30	Strive not with a man without cause, if he has done you no harm.
B020C003V031	20	3	31	Envy you not the oppressor, and choose none of his ways.
B020C003V032	20	3	32	For the perverse is abomination to the LORD: but his secret is with the righteous.
B020C003V033	20	3	33	The curse of the LORD is in the house of the wicked: but he blesses the habitation of the just.
B020C003V034	20	3	34	Surely he scorns the scornful: but he gives grace unto the lowly.
B020C003V035	20	3	35	The wise shall inherit glory: but shame shall be the recompense of fools.
B020C004V001	20	4	1	Hear, you children, the instruction of a father, and attend to know understanding.
B020C004V002	20	4	2	For I give you good doctrine, forsake not my law.
B020C004V003	20	4	3	For I was my father's son, tender and the only one in the sight of my mother.
B020C004V004	20	4	4	He taught me also, and said unto me, Let your heart retain my words: keep my commandments, and live.
B020C004V005	20	4	5	Get wisdom, get understanding: forget it not; neither turn away from the words of my mouth.
B020C004V006	20	4	6	Forsake her not, and she shall preserve you: love her, and she shall keep you.
B020C004V007	20	4	7	Wisdom is the principal thing; therefore get wisdom: and with all your getting get understanding.
B020C004V008	20	4	8	Exalt her, and she shall promote you: she shall bring you to honor, when you do embrace her.
B020C004V009	20	4	9	She shall give to your head an ornament of grace: a crown of glory shall she deliver to you.
B020C004V010	20	4	10	Hear, O my son, and receive my sayings; and the years of your life shall be many.
B020C004V011	20	4	11	I have taught you in the way of wisdom; I have led you in right paths.
B020C004V012	20	4	12	When you go, your steps shall not be hindered; and when you run, you shall not stumble.
B020C004V013	20	4	13	Take fast hold of instruction; let her not go: keep her; for she is your life.
B020C004V014	20	4	14	Enter not into the path of the wicked, and go not in the way of evil men.
B020C004V015	20	4	15	Avoid it, pass not by it, turn from it, and pass away.
B020C004V016	20	4	16	For they sleep not, unless they have done mischief; and their sleep is taken away, unless they cause someone to fall.
B020C004V017	20	4	17	For they eat the bread of wickedness, and drink the wine of violence.
B020C004V018	20	4	18	But the path of the just is as the shining light, that shines more and more unto the perfect day.
B020C004V019	20	4	19	The way of the wicked is as darkness: they know not at what they stumble.
B020C004V020	20	4	20	My son, attend to my words; incline your ear unto my sayings.
B020C004V021	20	4	21	Let them not depart from your eyes; keep them in the midst of your heart.
B020C004V022	20	4	22	For they are life unto those that find them, and health to all their flesh.
B020C004V023	20	4	23	Keep your heart with all diligence; for out of it are the issues of life.
B020C004V024	20	4	24	Put away from you a deceitful mouth, and perverse lips put far from you.
B020C004V025	20	4	25	Let your eyes look directly forward, and let your eyelids look straight before you.
B020C004V026	20	4	26	Ponder the path of your feet, and let all your ways be established.
B020C004V027	20	4	27	Turn not to the right hand nor to the left: remove your foot from evil.
B020C005V001	20	5	1	My son, be attentive to my wisdom, and incline your ear to my understanding:
B020C005V002	20	5	2	That you may preserve discretion, and that your lips may keep knowledge.
B020C005V003	20	5	3	For the lips of an immoral woman drop as a honeycomb, and her mouth is smoother than oil:
B020C005V004	20	5	4	But her end is bitter as wormwood, sharp as a two-edged sword.
B020C005V005	20	5	5	Her feet go down to death; her steps take hold on sheol.
B020C005V006	20	5	6	Lest you should ponder the path of life, her ways are unstable, that you can not know them.
B020C005V007	20	5	7	Hear me now therefore, O you children, and depart not from the words of my mouth.
B020C005V008	20	5	8	Remove your way far from her, and come not near the door of her house:
B020C005V009	20	5	9	Lest you give your honor unto others, and your years unto the merciless:
B020C005V010	20	5	10	Lest strangers be filled with your wealth; and your labors go to the house of a foreigner;
B020C005V011	20	5	11	And you mourn at the last, when your flesh and your body are consumed,
B020C005V012	20	5	12	And say, How have I hated instruction, and my heart despised reproof;
B020C005V013	20	5	13	And have not obeyed the voice of my teachers, nor inclined my ear to them that instructed me!
B020C005V014	20	5	14	I was almost in utter ruin in the midst of the congregation and assembly.
B020C005V015	20	5	15	Drink waters out of your own cistern, and running waters out of your own well.
B020C005V016	20	5	16	Should your fountains be dispersed abroad, and rivers of waters in the streets?
B020C005V017	20	5	17	Let them be only for your own, and not for strangers with you.
B020C005V018	20	5	18	Let your fountain be blessed: and rejoice with the wife of your youth.
B020C005V019	20	5	19	Let her be as the loving deer and graceful doe; let her breasts satisfy you at all times; and be ravished always with her love.
B020C005V020	20	5	20	And why will you, my son, be infatuated with an immoral woman, and embrace the bosom of a seductress?
B020C005V021	20	5	21	For the ways of man are before the eyes of the LORD, and he ponders all his paths.
B020C005V022	20	5	22	His own iniquities shall take the wicked himself, and he shall be held with the cords of his sins.
B020C005V023	20	5	23	He shall die for lack of instruction; and in the greatness of his folly he shall go astray.
B020C006V001	20	6	1	My son, if you become surety for your friend, if you have struck your hand with a stranger,
B020C006V002	20	6	2	You are snared with the words of your mouth, you are taken with the words of your mouth.
B020C006V003	20	6	3	Do this now, my son, and deliver yourself, when you have come into the hand of your friend; go, humble yourself, and plead with your friend.
B020C006V004	20	6	4	Give not sleep to your eyes, nor slumber to your eyelids.
B020C006V005	20	6	5	Deliver yourself as a gazelle from the hand of the hunter, and as a bird from the hand of the fowler.
B020C006V006	20	6	6	Go to the ant, you sluggard; consider her ways, and be wise:
B020C006V007	20	6	7	Who having no guide, overseer, or ruler,
B020C006V008	20	6	8	Provides her food in the summer, and gathers her food in the harvest.
B020C006V009	20	6	9	How long will you sleep, O sluggard? when will you arise out of your sleep?
B020C006V010	20	6	10	Yet a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:
B020C006V011	20	6	11	So shall your poverty come upon you like a vagabond, and your want like an armed man.
B020C006V012	20	6	12	A worthless person, a wicked man, walks with a perverse mouth.
B020C006V013	20	6	13	He winks with his eyes, he signals with his feet, he motions with his fingers;
B020C006V014	20	6	14	Perversity is in his heart, he devises evil continually; he sows discord.
B020C006V015	20	6	15	Therefore shall his calamity come suddenly; suddenly shall he be broken without remedy.
B020C006V016	20	6	16	These six things does the LORD hate: yea, seven are an abomination unto him:
B020C006V017	20	6	17	A proud look, a lying tongue, and hands that shed innocent blood,
B020C006V018	20	6	18	A heart that devises wicked imaginations, feet that are swift in running to evil,
B020C006V019	20	6	19	A false witness that speaks lies, and he that sows discord among brethren.
B020C006V020	20	6	20	My son, keep your father's commandment, and forsake not the law of your mother:
B020C006V021	20	6	21	Bind them continually upon your heart, and tie them about your neck.
B020C006V022	20	6	22	When you go, it shall lead you; when you sleep, it shall keep you; and when you awake, it shall talk with you.
B020C006V023	20	6	23	For the commandment is a lamp; and the law is light; and reproofs of instruction are the way of life:
B020C006V024	20	6	24	To keep you from the evil woman, from the flattery of the tongue of a seductress.
B020C006V025	20	6	25	Lust not after her beauty in your heart; neither let her allure you with her eyelids.
B020C006V026	20	6	26	For by means of a harlot a man is reduced to a piece of bread: and the adulteress will prey upon his precious life.
B020C006V027	20	6	27	Can a man take fire in his bosom, and his clothes not be burned?
B020C006V028	20	6	28	Can one go upon hot coals, and his feet not be burned?
B020C006V029	20	6	29	So is he that goes in to his neighbor's wife; whosoever touches her shall not be innocent.
B020C006V030	20	6	30	Men do not despise a thief, if he steals to satisfy his soul when he is hungry;
B020C006V031	20	6	31	But if he is found, he shall restore sevenfold; he shall give up all the goods of his house.
B020C006V032	20	6	32	But whosoever commits adultery with a woman lacks understanding: he that does it destroys his own soul.
B020C006V033	20	6	33	A wound and dishonor shall he get; and his reproach shall not be wiped away.
B020C006V034	20	6	34	For jealousy causes the rage of a man: therefore he will not spare in the day of vengeance.
B020C006V035	20	6	35	He will not regard any ransom; neither will he be appeased, though you give many gifts.
B020C007V001	20	7	1	My son, keep my words, and lay up my commandments with you.
B020C007V002	20	7	2	Keep my commandments, and live; and my law as the apple of your eye.
B020C007V003	20	7	3	Bind them upon your fingers, write them upon the table of your heart.
B020C007V004	20	7	4	Say unto wisdom, you are my sister; and call understanding your kinswoman:
B020C007V005	20	7	5	That they may keep you from the immoral woman, from the seductress who flatters with her words.
B020C007V006	20	7	6	For at the window of my house I looked through my casement,
B020C007V007	20	7	7	And beheld among the simple ones, I discerned among the youths, a young man void of understanding,
B020C007V008	20	7	8	Passing through the street near her corner; and he went the way to her house,
B020C007V009	20	7	9	In the twilight, in the evening, in the black and dark night:
B020C007V010	20	7	10	And, behold, there met him a woman with the attire of a harlot, and subtle of heart.
B020C007V011	20	7	11	(She is loud and stubborn; her feet abide not in her house:
B020C007V012	20	7	12	Now is she outside, now in the streets, and lies in wait at every corner.)
B020C007V013	20	7	13	So she caught him, and kissed him, and with an impudent face said unto him,
B020C007V014	20	7	14	I have peace offerings with me; this day have I paid my vows.
B020C007V015	20	7	15	Therefore came I forth to meet you, diligently to seek your face, and I have found you.
B020C007V016	20	7	16	I have decked my bed with coverings of tapestry, with colored spreads, with fine linen of Egypt.
B020C007V017	20	7	17	I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.
B020C007V018	20	7	18	Come, let us take our fill of love until the morning: let us delight ourselves with love.
B020C007V019	20	7	19	For my husband is not at home, he has gone on a long journey:
B020C007V020	20	7	20	He has taken a bag of money with him, and will come home at the day appointed.
B020C007V021	20	7	21	With her enticing speech she caused him to yield, with the flattering of her lips she seduced him.
B020C007V022	20	7	22	He goes after her immediately, as an ox goes to the slaughter, or as a fool to the correction of the stocks;
B020C007V023	20	7	23	Till an arrow strikes through his liver; as a bird hastens to the snare, and knows not that it is for his life.
B020C007V024	20	7	24	Hearken unto me now therefore, O you children, and attend to the words of my mouth.
B020C007V025	20	7	25	Let not your heart turn aside to her ways, go not astray in her paths.
B020C007V026	20	7	26	For she has cast down many wounded: yea, many strong men have been slain by her.
B020C007V027	20	7	27	Her house is the way to sheol, going down to the chambers of death.
B020C008V001	20	8	1	Does not wisdom cry? and understanding put forth her voice?
B020C008V002	20	8	2	She stands in the top of high places, by the way in the places of the paths.
B020C008V003	20	8	3	She cries at the gates, at the entry of the city, at the entrance at the doors.
B020C008V004	20	8	4	Unto you, O men, I call; and my voice is to the sons of man.
B020C008V005	20	8	5	O you simple, understand wisdom: and, you fools, be of an understanding heart.
B020C008V006	20	8	6	Hear; for I will speak of excellent things; and from the opening of my lips shall come right things.
B020C008V007	20	8	7	For my mouth shall speak truth; and wickedness is an abomination to my lips.
B020C008V008	20	8	8	All the words of my mouth are in righteousness; there is nothing crooked or perverse in them.
B020C008V009	20	8	9	They are all plain to him that understands, and right to them that find knowledge.
B020C008V010	20	8	10	Receive my instruction, and not silver; and knowledge rather than choice gold.
B020C008V011	20	8	11	For wisdom is better than rubies; and all the things that may be desired are not to be compared to it.
B020C008V012	20	8	12	I wisdom dwell with prudence, and find out knowledge and discretion.
B020C008V013	20	8	13	The fear of the LORD is to hate evil: pride, and arrogance, and the evil way, and the perverse mouth, do I hate.
B020C008V014	20	8	14	Counsel is mine, and sound wisdom: I am understanding; I have strength.
B020C008V015	20	8	15	By me kings reign, and princes decree justice.
B020C008V016	20	8	16	By me princes rule, and nobles, even all the judges of the earth.
B020C008V017	20	8	17	I love them that love me; and those that seek me early shall find me.
B020C008V018	20	8	18	Riches and honor are with me; yea, durable riches and righteousness.
B020C008V019	20	8	19	My fruit is better than gold, yea, than fine gold; and my revenue than choice silver.
B020C008V020	20	8	20	I lead in the way of righteousness, in the midst of the paths of justice:
B020C008V021	20	8	21	That I may cause those that love me to inherit wealth; and I will fill their treasuries.
B020C008V022	20	8	22	The LORD possessed me in the beginning of his way, before his works of old.
B020C008V023	20	8	23	I was set up from everlasting, from the beginning, before the earth was.
B020C008V024	20	8	24	When there were no depths, I was brought forth; when there were no fountains abounding with water.
B020C008V025	20	8	25	Before the mountains were settled, before the hills was I brought forth:
B020C008V026	20	8	26	While as yet he had not made the earth, nor the fields, nor the first of the dust of the world.
B020C008V027	20	8	27	When he prepared the heavens, I was there: when he drew a circle upon the face of the depth:
B020C008V028	20	8	28	When he established the clouds above: when he strengthened the fountains of the deep:
B020C008V029	20	8	29	When he gave to the sea his decree, that the waters should not pass his command: when he appointed the foundations of the earth:
B020C008V030	20	8	30	Then I was by him, like a master workman: and I was daily his delight, rejoicing always before him;
B020C008V031	20	8	31	Rejoicing in the habitable part of his earth; and my delights were with the sons of men.
B020C008V032	20	8	32	Now therefore hearken unto me, O you children: for blessed are they that keep my ways.
B020C008V033	20	8	33	Hear instruction, and be wise, and refuse it not.
B020C008V034	20	8	34	Blessed is the man that hears me, watching daily at my gates, waiting at the posts of my doors.
B020C008V035	20	8	35	For whosoever finds me finds life, and shall obtain favor of the LORD.
B020C008V036	20	8	36	But he that sins against me wrongs his own soul: all they that hate me love death.
B020C009V001	20	9	1	Wisdom has built her house, she has hewn out her seven pillars:
B020C009V002	20	9	2	She has slaughtered her beasts; she has mixed her wine; she has also furnished her table.
B020C009V003	20	9	3	She has sent forth her maidens: she cries upon the highest places of the city,
B020C009V004	20	9	4	Whosoever is simple, let him turn in here: as for him that lacks understanding, she says to him,
B020C009V005	20	9	5	Come, eat of my bread, and drink of the wine which I have mixed.
B020C009V006	20	9	6	Forsake the foolish, and live; and go in the way of understanding.
B020C009V007	20	9	7	He that reproves a scoffer gets for himself shame: and he that rebukes a wicked man gets himself injury.
B020C009V008	20	9	8	Reprove not a scoffer, lest he hate you: rebuke a wise man, and he will love you.
B020C009V009	20	9	9	Give instruction to a wise man, and he will be yet wiser: teach a just man, and he will increase in learning.
B020C009V010	20	9	10	The fear of the LORD is the beginning of wisdom: and the knowledge of the Holy One is understanding.
B020C009V011	20	9	11	For by me your days shall be multiplied, and the years of your life shall be increased.
B020C009V012	20	9	12	If you are wise, you shall be wise for yourself: but if you scoff, you alone shall bear it.
B020C009V013	20	9	13	A foolish woman is boisterous: she is simple, and knows nothing.
B020C009V014	20	9	14	For she sits at the door of her house, on a seat in the high places of the city,
B020C009V015	20	9	15	To call those who pass by who go right on their ways:
B020C009V016	20	9	16	Whosoever is simple, let him turn in here: and as for him that lacks understanding, she says to him,
B020C009V017	20	9	17	Stolen waters are sweet, and bread eaten in secret is pleasant.
B020C009V018	20	9	18	But he knows not that the dead are there; and that her guests are in the depths of the grave.
B020C010V001	20	10	1	The proverbs of Solomon. A wise son makes a glad father: but a foolish son is the grief of his mother.
B020C010V002	20	10	2	Treasures of wickedness profit nothing: but righteousness delivers from death.
B020C010V003	20	10	3	The LORD will not allow the soul of the righteous to famish: but he casts away the desire of the wicked.
B020C010V004	20	10	4	He becomes poor who has a slack hand: but the hand of the diligent makes rich.
B020C010V005	20	10	5	He that gathers in summer is a wise son: but he that sleeps in harvest is a son that causes shame.
B020C010V006	20	10	6	Blessings are upon the head of the just: but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.
B020C010V007	20	10	7	The memory of the just is blessed: but the name of the wicked shall rot.
B020C010V008	20	10	8	The wise in heart will heed commandments: but a prating fool shall fall.
B020C010V009	20	10	9	He that walks uprightly walks securely: but he that perverts his ways shall be known.
B020C010V010	20	10	10	He that winks with the eye causes trouble: but a prating fool shall fall.
B020C010V011	20	10	11	The mouth of a righteous man is a well of life: but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.
B020C010V012	20	10	12	Hatred stirs up strife: but love covers all sins.
B020C010V013	20	10	13	In the lips of him that has understanding wisdom is found: but a rod is for the back of him that is void of understanding.
B020C010V014	20	10	14	Wise men lay up knowledge: but the mouth of the foolish is near destruction.
B020C010V015	20	10	15	The rich man's wealth is his strong city: the ruin of the poor is their poverty.
B020C010V016	20	10	16	The labor of the righteous leads to life: the fruit of the wicked to sin.
B020C010V017	20	10	17	He is in the way of life that keeps instruction: but he that refuses reproof goes astray.
B020C010V018	20	10	18	He that hides hatred with lying lips, and he that utters a slander, is a fool.
B020C010V019	20	10	19	In the multitude of words there lacks not sin: but he that refrains his lips is wise.
B020C010V020	20	10	20	The tongue of the just is as choice silver: the heart of the wicked is of little worth.
B020C010V021	20	10	21	The lips of the righteous feed many: but fools die for lack of wisdom.
B020C010V022	20	10	22	The blessing of the LORD, it makes rich, and he adds no sorrow with it.
B020C010V023	20	10	23	It is as sport to a fool to do wrong: but a man of understanding has wisdom.
B020C010V024	20	10	24	The fear of the wicked, it shall come upon him: but the desire of the righteous shall be granted.
B020C010V025	20	10	25	As the whirlwind passes, so is the wicked no more: but the righteous is an everlasting foundation.
B020C010V026	20	10	26	As vinegar to the teeth, and as smoke to the eyes, so is the sluggard to them that send him.
B020C010V027	20	10	27	The fear of the LORD prolongs days: but the years of the wicked shall be shortened.
B020C010V028	20	10	28	The hope of the righteous shall be gladness: but the expectation of the wicked shall perish.
B020C010V029	20	10	29	The way of the LORD is strength to the upright: but destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.
B020C010V030	20	10	30	The righteous shall never be removed: but the wicked shall not inhabit the land.
B020C010V031	20	10	31	The mouth of the just brings forth wisdom: but the perverse tongue shall be cut out.
B020C010V032	20	10	32	The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable: but the mouth of the wicked, what is perverse.
B020C011V001	20	11	1	A false balance is abomination to the LORD: but a just weight is his delight.
B020C011V002	20	11	2	When pride comes, then comes shame: but with the lowly is wisdom.
B020C011V003	20	11	3	The integrity of the upright shall guide them: but the perverseness of transgressors shall destroy them.
B020C011V004	20	11	4	Riches profit not in the day of wrath: but righteousness delivers from death.
B020C011V005	20	11	5	The righteousness of the perfect shall direct his way: but the wicked shall fall by his own wickedness.
B020C011V006	20	11	6	The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them: but transgressors shall be taken in their own lust.
B020C011V007	20	11	7	When a wicked man dies, his expectation shall perish: and the hope of unjust men perishes.
B020C011V008	20	11	8	The righteous is delivered out of trouble, and the wicked comes in his stead.
B020C011V009	20	11	9	A hypocrite with his mouth destroys his neighbor: but through knowledge shall the just be delivered.
B020C011V010	20	11	10	When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices: and when the wicked perish, there is shouting.
B020C011V011	20	11	11	By the blessing of the upright the city is exalted: but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.
B020C011V012	20	11	12	He that is void of wisdom despises his neighbor: but a man of understanding holds his peace.
B020C011V013	20	11	13	A talebearer reveals secrets: but he that is of a faithful spirit conceals the matter.
B020C011V014	20	11	14	Where no counsel is, the people fall: but in the multitude of counselors there is safety.
B020C011V015	20	11	15	He that is surety for a stranger shall suffer for it: and he that hates being surety is secure.
B020C011V016	20	11	16	A gracious woman retains honor: and strong men retain riches.
B020C011V017	20	11	17	The merciful man does good to his own soul: but he that is cruel troubles his own flesh.
B020C011V018	20	11	18	The wicked works a deceitful work: but to him that sows righteousness shall be a sure reward.
B020C011V019	20	11	19	As righteousness leads to life: so he that pursues evil pursues it to his own death.
B020C011V020	20	11	20	They that are of a perverse heart are abomination to the LORD: but such as are upright in their way are his delight.
B020C011V021	20	11	21	Though they join hand to hand, the wicked shall not be unpunished: but the descendants of the righteous shall be delivered.
B020C011V022	20	11	22	As a jewel of gold in a swine's snout, so is a beautiful woman who is without discretion.
B020C011V023	20	11	23	The desire of the righteous is only good: but the expectation of the wicked is wrath.
B020C011V024	20	11	24	There is one that scatters, and yet increases; and there is one that withholds more than is right, but it leads to poverty.
B020C011V025	20	11	25	The liberal soul shall be made rich: and he that waters shall be watered also himself.
B020C011V026	20	11	26	He that withholds grain, the people shall curse him: but blessing shall be upon the head of him that sells it.
B020C011V027	20	11	27	He that diligently seeks good procures favor: but he that seeks evil, it shall come unto him.
B020C011V028	20	11	28	He that trusts in his riches shall fall: but the righteous shall flourish as a branch.
B020C011V029	20	11	29	He that troubles his own house shall inherit the wind: and the fool shall be servant to the wise of heart.
B020C011V030	20	11	30	The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life; and he that wins souls is wise.
B020C011V031	20	11	31	Behold, the righteous shall be recompensed on the earth: much more the wicked and the sinner.
B020C012V001	20	12	1	Whosoever loves instruction loves knowledge: but he that hates reproof is senseless.
B020C012V002	20	12	2	A good man obtains favor of the LORD: but a man of wicked intentions will he condemn.
B020C012V003	20	12	3	A man shall not be established by wickedness: but the root of the righteous shall not be moved.
B020C012V004	20	12	4	A virtuous woman is a crown to her husband: but she that makes ashamed is like rottenness in his bones.
B020C012V005	20	12	5	The thoughts of the righteous are right: but the counsels of the wicked are deceitful.
B020C012V006	20	12	6	The words of the wicked are to lie in wait for blood: but the mouth of the upright shall deliver them.
B020C012V007	20	12	7	The wicked are overthrown, and are not: but the house of the righteous shall stand.
B020C012V008	20	12	8	A man shall be commended according to his wisdom: but he that is of a perverse heart shall be despised.
B020C012V009	20	12	9	He that is despised, and has a servant, is better than he that honors himself, and lacks bread.
B020C012V010	20	12	10	A righteous man regards the life of his animal: but the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.
B020C012V011	20	12	11	He that tills his land shall be satisfied with bread: but he that follows vain persons is void of understanding.
B020C012V012	20	12	12	The wicked desires the net of evil men: but the root of the righteous yields fruit.
B020C012V013	20	12	13	The wicked is snared by the transgression of his lips: but the just shall escape from trouble.
B020C012V014	20	12	14	A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth: and the recompense of a man's hands shall be rendered unto him.
B020C012V015	20	12	15	The way of a fool is right in his own eyes: but he that hearkens unto counsel is wise.
B020C012V016	20	12	16	A fool's wrath is at once known: but a prudent man covers shame.
B020C012V017	20	12	17	He that speaks truth shows forth righteousness: but a false witness, deceit.
B020C012V018	20	12	18	There is one that speaks like the piercings of a sword: but the tongue of the wise brings health.
B020C012V019	20	12	19	The lip of truth shall be established forever: but a lying tongue is but for a moment.
B020C012V020	20	12	20	Deceit is in the heart of them that imagine evil: but to the counselors of peace there is joy.
B020C012V021	20	12	21	There shall no evil happen to the just: but the wicked shall be filled with trouble.
B020C012V022	20	12	22	Lying lips are abomination to the LORD: but they that deal truly are his delight.
B020C012V023	20	12	23	A prudent man conceals knowledge: but the heart of fools proclaims foolishness.
B020C012V024	20	12	24	The hand of the diligent shall bear rule: but the slothful shall be put to forced labor.
B020C012V025	20	12	25	Heaviness in the heart of man makes him stoop: but a good word makes him glad.
B020C012V026	20	12	26	The righteous chooses his friends carefully: but the way of the wicked leads them astray.
B020C012V027	20	12	27	The slothful man roasts not that which he took in hunting: but the possessions of a diligent man are precious.
B020C012V028	20	12	28	In the way of righteousness is life; and in the pathway thereof there is no death.
B020C013V001	20	13	1	A wise son hears his father's instruction: but a scoffer hears not rebuke.
B020C013V002	20	13	2	A man shall eat good by the fruit of his mouth: but the soul of the transgressors feeds on violence.
B020C013V003	20	13	3	He that keeps his mouth keeps his life: but he that opens wide his lips shall have destruction.
B020C013V004	20	13	4	The soul of the sluggard desires, and has nothing: but the soul of the diligent shall be made rich.
B020C013V005	20	13	5	A righteous man hates lying: but a wicked man is loathsome, and comes to shame.
B020C013V006	20	13	6	Righteousness keeps him that is upright in the way: but wickedness overthrows the sinner.
B020C013V007	20	13	7	There is one that makes himself rich, yet has nothing: there is one that makes himself poor, yet has great riches.
B020C013V008	20	13	8	The ransom of a man's life are his riches: but the poor hears not rebuke.
B020C013V009	20	13	9	The light of the righteous rejoices: but the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.
B020C013V010	20	13	10	Only by pride comes strife: but with the well advised is wisdom.
B020C013V011	20	13	11	Wealth gotten by vanity shall be diminished: but he that gathers by labor shall increase.
B020C013V012	20	13	12	Hope deferred makes the heart sick: but when the desire is fulfilled, it is a tree of life.
B020C013V013	20	13	13	Whosoever despises the word shall be destroyed: but he that fears the commandment shall be rewarded.
B020C013V014	20	13	14	The law of the wise is a fountain of life, to depart from the snares of death.
B020C013V015	20	13	15	Good understanding gives favor: but the way of transgressors is hard.
B020C013V016	20	13	16	Every prudent man deals with knowledge: but a fool lays open his folly.
B020C013V017	20	13	17	A wicked messenger falls into trouble: but a faithful ambassador is health.
B020C013V018	20	13	18	Poverty and shame shall be to him that refuses instruction: but he that regards reproof shall be honored.
B020C013V019	20	13	19	The desire accomplished is sweet to the soul: but it is abomination to fools to depart from evil.
B020C013V020	20	13	20	He that walks with wise men shall be wise: but a companion of fools shall be destroyed.
B020C013V021	20	13	21	Evil pursues sinners: but to the righteous good shall be repaid.
B020C013V022	20	13	22	A good man leaves an inheritance to his children's children: but the wealth of the sinner is laid up for the just.
B020C013V023	20	13	23	Much food is in the fallow ground of the poor: but there is that is destroyed for lack of justice.
B020C013V024	20	13	24	He that spares his rod hates his son: but he that loves him chastens him early.
B020C013V025	20	13	25	The righteous eats to the satisfying of his soul: but the belly of the wicked shall go hungry.
B020C014V001	20	14	1	Every wise woman builds her house: but the foolish plucks it down with her hands.
B020C014V002	20	14	2	He that walks in his uprightness fears the LORD: but he that is perverse in his ways despises him.
B020C014V003	20	14	3	In the mouth of the foolish is a rod of pride: but the lips of the wise shall preserve them.
B020C014V004	20	14	4	Where no oxen are, the crib is clean: but much increase is by the strength of the ox.
B020C014V005	20	14	5	A faithful witness will not lie: but a false witness will utter lies.
B020C014V006	20	14	6	A scoffer seeks wisdom, and finds it not: but knowledge is easy unto him that understands.
B020C014V007	20	14	7	Go from the presence of a foolish man, when you perceive not in him the lips of knowledge.
B020C014V008	20	14	8	The wisdom of the prudent is to understand his way: but the folly of fools is deceit.
B020C014V009	20	14	9	Fools make a mockery of sin: but among the righteous there is favor.
B020C014V010	20	14	10	The heart knows its own bitterness; and a stranger does not share its joy.
B020C014V011	20	14	11	The house of the wicked shall be overthrown: but the tent of the upright shall flourish.
B020C014V012	20	14	12	There is a way which seems right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.
B020C014V013	20	14	13	Even in laughter the heart is sorrowful; and the end of that mirth is grief.
B020C014V014	20	14	14	The backslider in heart shall be filled with his own ways: and a good man shall be satisfied from above himself.
B020C014V015	20	14	15	The simple believes every word: but the prudent man looks well where he is going.
B020C014V016	20	14	16	A wise man fears, and departs from evil: but the fool rages, and is confident.
B020C014V017	20	14	17	He that is quickly angry deals foolishly: and a man of wicked intentions is hated.
B020C014V018	20	14	18	The simple inherit folly: but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.
B020C014V019	20	14	19	The evil bow before the good; and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.
B020C014V020	20	14	20	The poor is hated even of his own neighbor: but the rich has many friends.
B020C014V021	20	14	21	He that despises his neighbor sins: but he that has mercy on the poor, happy is he.
B020C014V022	20	14	22	Do they not err that devise evil? but mercy and truth shall be to them that devise good.
B020C014V023	20	14	23	In all labor there is profit: but the talk of the lips leads only to poverty.
B020C014V024	20	14	24	The crown of the wise is their riches: but the foolishness of fools is folly.
B020C014V025	20	14	25	A true witness delivers souls: but a deceitful witness speaks lies.
B020C014V026	20	14	26	In the fear of the LORD is strong confidence: and his children shall have a place of refuge.
B020C014V027	20	14	27	The fear of the LORD is a fountain of life, to turn one away from the snares of death.
B020C014V028	20	14	28	In the multitude of people is the king's honor: but in the lack of people is the destruction of the prince.
B020C014V029	20	14	29	He that is slow to wrath is of great understanding: but he that is hasty of spirit exalts folly.
B020C014V030	20	14	30	A sound heart is the life of the flesh: but envy the rottenness of the bones.
B020C014V031	20	14	31	He that oppresses the poor reproaches his Maker: but he that honors him has mercy on the poor.
B020C014V032	20	14	32	The wicked is driven away in his wickedness: but the righteous has hope in his death.
B020C014V033	20	14	33	Wisdom rests in the heart of him that has understanding: but that which is in the midst of fools is made known.
B020C014V034	20	14	34	Righteousness exalts a nation: but sin is a reproach to any people.
B020C014V035	20	14	35	The king's favor is toward a wise servant: but his wrath is against him that causes shame.
B020C015V001	20	15	1	A soft answer turns away wrath: but grievous words stir up anger.
B020C015V002	20	15	2	The tongue of the wise uses knowledge aright: but the mouth of fools pours out foolishness.
B020C015V003	20	15	3	The eyes of the LORD are in every place, beholding the evil and the good.
B020C015V004	20	15	4	A wholesome tongue is a tree of life: but perverseness therein is a breach in the spirit.
B020C015V005	20	15	5	A fool despises his father's instruction: but he that regards reproof is prudent.
B020C015V006	20	15	6	In the house of the righteous is much treasure: but in the income of the wicked is trouble.
B020C015V007	20	15	7	The lips of the wise disperse knowledge: but the heart of the foolish does not so.
B020C015V008	20	15	8	The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination to the LORD: but the prayer of the upright is his delight.
B020C015V009	20	15	9	The way of the wicked is an abomination unto the LORD: but he loves him that follows after righteousness.
B020C015V010	20	15	10	Correction is grievous unto him that forsakes the way: and he that hates reproof shall die.
B020C015V011	20	15	11	Sheol and destruction are before the LORD: how much more then the hearts of the children of men?
B020C015V012	20	15	12	A scoffer loves not one that reproves him: neither will he go unto the wise.
B020C015V013	20	15	13	A merry heart makes a cheerful countenance: but by sorrow of the heart the spirit is broken.
B020C015V014	20	15	14	The heart of him that has understanding seeks knowledge: but the mouth of fools feeds on foolishness.
B020C015V015	20	15	15	All the days of the afflicted are evil: but he that is of a merry heart has a continual feast.
B020C015V016	20	15	16	Better is little with the fear of the LORD than great treasure with trouble.
B020C015V017	20	15	17	Better is a dinner of herbs where love is, than a fatted ox with hatred.
B020C015V018	20	15	18	A wrathful man stirs up strife: but he that is slow to anger quiets strife.
B020C015V019	20	15	19	The way of the slothful man is as a hedge of thorns: but the way of the righteous is made a highway.
B020C015V020	20	15	20	A wise son makes a glad father: but a foolish man despises his mother.
B020C015V021	20	15	21	Folly is joy to him that is destitute of wisdom: but a man of understanding walks uprightly.
B020C015V022	20	15	22	Without counsel plans go wrong: but in the multitude of counselors they are established.
B020C015V023	20	15	23	A man has joy by the answer of his mouth: and a word spoken in due season, how good is it!
B020C015V024	20	15	24	The way of life leads above to the wise, that he may depart from sheol beneath.
B020C015V025	20	15	25	The LORD will destroy the house of the proud: but he will establish the boundary of the widow.
B020C015V026	20	15	26	The thoughts of the wicked are an abomination to the LORD: but the words of the pure are pleasant words.
B020C015V027	20	15	27	He that is greedy of gain troubles his own house; but he that hates bribes shall live.
B020C015V028	20	15	28	The heart of the righteous studies to answer: but the mouth of the wicked pours out evil things.
B020C015V029	20	15	29	The LORD is far from the wicked: but he hears the prayer of the righteous.
B020C015V030	20	15	30	The light of the eyes rejoices the heart: and a good report makes the bones healthy.
B020C015V031	20	15	31	The ear that hears the reproof of life abides among the wise.
B020C015V032	20	15	32	He that refuses instruction despises his own soul: but he that hears reproof gets understanding.
B020C015V033	20	15	33	The fear of the LORD is the instruction of wisdom; and before honor is humility.
B020C016V001	20	16	1	The preparations of the heart belong to man, but the answer of the tongue, is from the LORD.
B020C016V002	20	16	2	All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes; but the LORD weighs the spirits.
B020C016V003	20	16	3	Commit your works unto the LORD, and your thoughts shall be established.
B020C016V004	20	16	4	The LORD has made all things for himself: yea, even the wicked for the day of evil.
B020C016V005	20	16	5	Everyone that is proud in heart is an abomination to the LORD: though they join hand in hand, none shall be unpunished.
B020C016V006	20	16	6	By mercy and truth iniquity is purged: and by the fear of the LORD men depart from evil.
B020C016V007	20	16	7	When a man's ways please the LORD, he makes even his enemies to be at peace with him.
B020C016V008	20	16	8	Better is a little with righteousness than great revenues without justice.
B020C016V009	20	16	9	A man's heart plans his way: but the LORD directs his steps.
B020C016V010	20	16	10	A divine sentence is in the lips of the king: his mouth transgresses not in judgment.
B020C016V011	20	16	11	A just weight and balance are the LORD's: all the weights in the bag are his work.
B020C016V012	20	16	12	It is an abomination to kings to commit wickedness: for the throne is established by righteousness.
B020C016V013	20	16	13	Righteous lips are the delight of kings; and they love him that speaks what is right.
B020C016V014	20	16	14	The wrath of a king is as messengers of death: but a wise man will appease it.
B020C016V015	20	16	15	In the light of the king's countenance is life; and his favor is as a cloud of the latter rain.
B020C016V016	20	16	16	How much better is it to get wisdom than gold! and to get understanding rather to be chosen than silver!
B020C016V017	20	16	17	The highway of the upright is to depart from evil: he that keeps his way preserves his soul.
B020C016V018	20	16	18	Pride goes before destruction, and a haughty spirit before a fall.
B020C016V019	20	16	19	Better it is to be of a humble spirit with the lowly, than to divide the spoil with the proud.
B020C016V020	20	16	20	He that handles a matter wisely shall find good: and whosoever trusts in the LORD, happy is he.
B020C016V021	20	16	21	The wise in heart shall be called prudent: and the sweetness of the lips increases learning.
B020C016V022	20	16	22	Understanding is a wellspring of life unto him that has it: but the instruction of fools is folly.
B020C016V023	20	16	23	The heart of the wise teaches his mouth, and adds learning to his lips.
B020C016V024	20	16	24	Pleasant words are as a honeycomb, sweet to the soul, and health to the bones.
B020C016V025	20	16	25	There is a way that seems right unto a man, but the end thereof are the ways of death.
B020C016V026	20	16	26	He that labors labors for himself; for his mouth craves it of him.
B020C016V027	20	16	27	An ungodly man digs up evil: and in his lips there is as a burning fire.
B020C016V028	20	16	28	A perverse man sows strife: and a whisperer separates best friends.
B020C016V029	20	16	29	A violent man entices his neighbor, and leads him into the way that is not good.
B020C016V030	20	16	30	He shuts his eyes to devise perverse things: moving his lips he brings evil to pass.
B020C016V031	20	16	31	White hair is a crown of glory, if it is found in the way of righteousness.
B020C016V032	20	16	32	He that is slow to anger is better than the mighty; and he that rules his spirit than he that takes a city.
B020C016V033	20	16	33	The lot is cast into the lap; but its every decision is of the LORD.
B020C017V001	20	17	1	Better is a dry morsel, with quietness, than a house full of sacrifices with strife.
B020C017V002	20	17	2	A wise servant shall have rule over a son that causes shame, and shall have part of the inheritance among the brethren.
B020C017V003	20	17	3	The refining pot is for silver, and the furnace for gold: but the LORD tries the hearts.
B020C017V004	20	17	4	A wicked doer gives heed to false lips; and a liar gives ear to a mischievous tongue.
B020C017V005	20	17	5	Whosoever mocks the poor reproaches his Maker: and he that is glad at calamity shall not be unpunished.
B020C017V006	20	17	6	Children's children are the crown of old men; and the glory of children is their fathers.
B020C017V007	20	17	7	Excellent speech becomes not a fool: much less do lying lips a prince.
B020C017V008	20	17	8	A bribe is as a magic stone in the eyes of him that gives it: wherever he turns, he prospers.
B020C017V009	20	17	9	He that covers over a transgression seeks love; but he that repeats a matter separates close friends.
B020C017V010	20	17	10	A reproof enters more into a wise man than a hundred stripes into a fool.
B020C017V011	20	17	11	An evil man seeks only rebellion: therefore a cruel messenger shall be sent against him.
B020C017V012	20	17	12	Let a bear robbed of her whelps meet a man, rather than a fool in his folly.
B020C017V013	20	17	13	Whosoever rewards evil for good, evil shall not depart from his house.
B020C017V014	20	17	14	The beginning of strife is like releasing water: therefore leave off contention, before a quarrel starts.
B020C017V015	20	17	15	He that justifies the wicked, and he that condemns the just, even they both are abomination to the LORD.
B020C017V016	20	17	16	Why is there a price in the hand of a fool to get wisdom, seeing he has no heart for it?
B020C017V017	20	17	17	A friend loves at all times, and a brother is born for adversity.
B020C017V018	20	17	18	A man void of understanding gives pledge, and becomes surety in the presence of his neighbor.
B020C017V019	20	17	19	He who loves transgression loves strife: and he who exalts his gate seeks destruction.
B020C017V020	20	17	20	He that has a crooked heart finds no good: and he that has a perverse tongue falls into calamity.
B020C017V021	20	17	21	He that begets a fool does it to his sorrow: and the father of a fool has no joy.
B020C017V022	20	17	22	A merry heart does good like a medicine: but a broken spirit dries the bones.
B020C017V023	20	17	23	A wicked man takes a bribe out of the bosom to pervert the ways of justice.
B020C017V024	20	17	24	Wisdom is before him that has understanding; but the eyes of a fool are on the ends of the earth.
B020C017V025	20	17	25	A foolish son is a grief to his father, and bitterness to her that bore him.
B020C017V026	20	17	26	Also, to punish the just is not good, nor to flog princes for their integrity.
B020C017V027	20	17	27	He that has knowledge spares his words: and a man of understanding is of an excellent spirit.
B020C017V028	20	17	28	Even a fool, when he holds his peace, is counted wise: and he that shuts his lips is esteemed a man of understanding.
B020C018V001	20	18	1	A man, having separated himself, seeks his own desire, and rages against all sound wisdom.
B020C018V002	20	18	2	A fool has no delight in understanding, but that his heart may express itself.
B020C018V003	20	18	3	When the wicked comes, then comes also contempt, and with dishonor comes reproach.
B020C018V004	20	18	4	The words of a man's mouth are like deep waters, and the wellspring of wisdom like a flowing brook.
B020C018V005	20	18	5	It is not good to be partial to the wicked, or to overthrow the righteous in judgment.
B020C018V006	20	18	6	A fool's lips enter into contention, and his mouth calls for blows.
B020C018V007	20	18	7	A fool's mouth is his destruction, and his lips are the snare of his soul.
B020C018V008	20	18	8	The words of a talebearer are like tasty morsels, and they go down into the innermost parts of the body.
B020C018V009	20	18	9	He also that is slothful in his work is brother to him that is a great waster.
B020C018V010	20	18	10	The name of the LORD is a strong tower: the righteous runs into it, and is safe.
B020C018V011	20	18	11	The rich man's wealth is his strong city, and like a high wall in his own esteem.
B020C018V012	20	18	12	Before destruction the heart of man is haughty, and before honor is humility.
B020C018V013	20	18	13	He that answers a matter before he hears it, it is folly and shame unto him.
B020C018V014	20	18	14	The spirit of a man will sustain him in sickness; but a wounded spirit who can bear?
B020C018V015	20	18	15	The heart of the prudent gets knowledge; and the ear of the wise seeks knowledge.
B020C018V016	20	18	16	A man's gift makes room for him, and brings him before great men.
B020C018V017	20	18	17	He that speaks first in his own cause seems just; until his neighbor comes and examines him.
B020C018V018	20	18	18	The lot causes contentions to cease, and decides between the mighty.
B020C018V019	20	18	19	A brother offended is harder to be won than a strong city: and contentions are like the bars of a castle.
B020C018V020	20	18	20	A man's stomach shall be satisfied with the fruit of his mouth; and with the increase of his lips shall he be filled.
B020C018V021	20	18	21	Death and life are in the power of the tongue: and they that love it shall eat the fruit thereof.
B020C018V022	20	18	22	Whosoever finds a wife finds a good thing, and obtains favor of the LORD.
B020C018V023	20	18	23	The poor uses entreaties; but the rich answers roughly.
B020C018V024	20	18	24	A man that has friends must show himself friendly: and there is a friend that sticks closer than a brother.
B020C019V001	20	19	1	Better is the poor that walks in his integrity, than he that is perverse in his lips, and is a fool.
B020C019V002	20	19	2	Also, that the soul be without knowledge is not good; and he that hastens with his feet sins.
B020C019V003	20	19	3	The foolishness of man perverts his way: and his heart frets against the LORD.
B020C019V004	20	19	4	Wealth makes many friends; but the poor is separated from his neighbor.
B020C019V005	20	19	5	A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that speaks lies shall not escape.
B020C019V006	20	19	6	Many will entreat the favor of the prince: and every man is a friend to him that gives gifts.
B020C019V007	20	19	7	All the brethren of the poor do hate him: how much more do his friends go far from him? he pursues them with words, yet they are nothing to him.
B020C019V008	20	19	8	He that gets wisdom loves his own soul: he that keeps understanding shall find good.
B020C019V009	20	19	9	A false witness shall not be unpunished, and he that speaks lies shall perish.
B020C019V010	20	19	10	Luxury is not fitting for a fool; much less for a servant to have rule over princes.
B020C019V011	20	19	11	The discretion of a man delays his anger; and it is his glory to overlook a transgression.
B020C019V012	20	19	12	The king's wrath is as the roaring of a lion; but his favor is as dew upon the grass.
B020C019V013	20	19	13	A foolish son is the calamity of his father: and the contentions of a wife are a continual dripping.
B020C019V014	20	19	14	House and riches are the inheritance from fathers: and a prudent wife is from the LORD.
B020C019V015	20	19	15	Slothfulness casts into a deep sleep; and an idle soul shall suffer hunger.
B020C019V016	20	19	16	He that keeps the commandment keeps his own soul; but he that despises his ways shall die.
B020C019V017	20	19	17	He that has pity upon the poor lends unto the LORD; and that which he has given will he pay him again.
B020C019V018	20	19	18	Chasten your son while there is hope, and let not your soul spare for his crying.
B020C019V019	20	19	19	A man of great wrath shall suffer punishment: for if you deliver him, yet you must do it again.
B020C019V020	20	19	20	Hear counsel, and receive instruction, that you may be wise in your latter days.
B020C019V021	20	19	21	There are many plans in a man's heart; nevertheless the counsel of the LORD, that shall stand.
B020C019V022	20	19	22	The desire of a man is his kindness: and a poor man is better than a liar.
B020C019V023	20	19	23	The fear of the LORD leads to life: and he that has it shall abide satisfied; he shall not be visited with evil.
B020C019V024	20	19	24	A slothful man hides his hand in his dish, and will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.
B020C019V025	20	19	25	Smite a scoffer, and the simple will beware: and reprove one that has understanding, and he will understand knowledge.
B020C019V026	20	19	26	He that mistreats his father, and chases away his mother, is a son that causes shame, and brings reproach.
B020C019V027	20	19	27	Cease, my son, to hear the instruction that causes to stray from the words of knowledge.
B020C019V028	20	19	28	An ungodly witness scorns judgment: and the mouth of the wicked devours iniquity.
B020C019V029	20	19	29	Judgments are prepared for scoffers and stripes for the back of fools.
B020C020V001	20	20	1	Wine is a mocker, strong drink is raging: and whosoever is deceived thereby is not wise.
B020C020V002	20	20	2	The fear of a king is as the roaring of a lion: whosoever provokes him to anger sins against his own life.
B020C020V003	20	20	3	It is an honor for a man to cease from strife: but every fool will be meddling.
B020C020V004	20	20	4	The sluggard will not plow by reason of the cold; therefore shall he beg in harvest, and have nothing.
B020C020V005	20	20	5	Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water; but a man of understanding will draw it out.
B020C020V006	20	20	6	Most men will proclaim everyone his own goodness: but a faithful man who can find?
B020C020V007	20	20	7	The just man walks in his integrity: his children are blessed after him.
B020C020V008	20	20	8	A king that sits in the throne of judgment scatters away all evil with his eyes.
B020C020V009	20	20	9	Who can say, I have made my heart clean, I am pure from my sin?
B020C020V010	20	20	10	Diverse weights, and diverse measures, both of them are alike abomination to the LORD.
B020C020V011	20	20	11	Even a child is known by his acts, whether his work is pure, and whether it is right.
B020C020V012	20	20	12	The hearing ear, and the seeing eye, the LORD has made even both of them.
B020C020V013	20	20	13	Love not sleep, lest you come to poverty; open your eyes, and you shall be satisfied with bread.
B020C020V014	20	20	14	It is nothing, it is nothing, says the buyer: but when he is gone his way, then he boasts.
B020C020V015	20	20	15	There is gold, and a multitude of rubies: but the lips of knowledge are a precious jewel.
B020C020V016	20	20	16	Take his garment who is surety for a stranger: and hold it as a pledge of him for an immoral woman.
B020C020V017	20	20	17	Bread gained by deceit is sweet to a man; but afterwards his mouth shall be filled with gravel.
B020C020V018	20	20	18	Every purpose is established by counsel: and with good advice wage war.
B020C020V019	20	20	19	He that goes about as a talebearer reveals secrets: therefore associate not with him who flatters with his lips.
B020C020V020	20	20	20	Whosoever curses his father or his mother, his lamp shall be put out in utter darkness.
B020C020V021	20	20	21	An inheritance may be gotten hastily at the beginning; but the end thereof shall not be blessed.
B020C020V022	20	20	22	Say not, I will repay evil; but wait on the LORD, and he shall save you.
B020C020V023	20	20	23	Diverse weights are an abomination unto the LORD; and a false balance is not good.
B020C020V024	20	20	24	A manâ€™s steps are of the LORD; how can a man then understand his own way?
B020C020V025	20	20	25	It is a snare to the man to declare something is holy, and afterward to reconsider his vows.
B020C020V026	20	20	26	A wise king winnows the wicked, and drives the wheel over them.
B020C020V027	20	20	27	The spirit of man is the lamp of the LORD, searching all the inner depths of the heart.
B020C020V028	20	20	28	Mercy and truth preserve the king: and his throne is upheld by mercy.
B020C020V029	20	20	29	The glory of young men is their strength: and the beauty of old men is the gray head.
B020C020V030	20	20	30	Blows of a wound cleanse away evil: as do stripes the inner depths of the heart.
B020C021V001	20	21	1	The king's heart is in the hand of the LORD, as the rivers of water: he turns it wherever he will.
B020C021V002	20	21	2	Every way of a man is right in his own eyes: but the LORD weighs the hearts.
B020C021V003	20	21	3	To do righteousness and justice is more acceptable to the LORD than sacrifice.
B020C021V004	20	21	4	A haughty look, a proud heart, and the plowing of the wicked, is sin.
B020C021V005	20	21	5	The thoughts of the diligent lead only to plenty; but of everyone that is hasty, only to want.
B020C021V006	20	21	6	The getting of treasures by a lying tongue is a vanity tossed to and fro of them that seek death.
B020C021V007	20	21	7	The violence of the wicked shall destroy them; because they refuse to do justice.
B020C021V008	20	21	8	The way of man is perverse and strange: but as for the pure, his work is right.
B020C021V009	20	21	9	It is better to dwell in a corner of the housetop, than with a contentious woman in a whole house.
B020C021V010	20	21	10	The soul of the wicked desires evil: his neighbor finds no favor in his eyes.
B020C021V011	20	21	11	When the scoffer is punished, the simple is made wise: and when the wise is instructed, he receives knowledge.
B020C021V012	20	21	12	The righteous man wisely considers the house of the wicked: but God overthrows the wicked for their wickedness.
B020C021V013	20	21	13	Whosoever stops his ears at the cry of the poor, he also shall cry himself, but shall not be heard.
B020C021V014	20	21	14	A gift in secret averts anger: and a bribe in the bosom, strong wrath.
B020C021V015	20	21	15	It is joy to the just to do justice: but destruction shall be to the workers of iniquity.
B020C021V016	20	21	16	The man that wanders out of the way of understanding shall remain in the congregation of the dead.
B020C021V017	20	21	17	He that loves pleasure shall be a poor man: he that loves wine and oil shall not be rich.
B020C021V018	20	21	18	The wicked shall be a ransom for the righteous, and the transgressor for the upright.
B020C021V019	20	21	19	It is better to dwell in the wilderness, than with a contentious and angry woman.
B020C021V020	20	21	20	There is treasure to be desired and oil in the dwelling of the wise; but a foolish man spends it up.
B020C021V021	20	21	21	He that follows after righteousness and mercy finds life, righteousness, and honor.
B020C021V022	20	21	22	A wise man scales the city of the mighty, and casts down the stronghold in which they trust.
B020C021V023	20	21	23	Whosoever keeps his mouth and his tongue keeps his soul from troubles.
B020C021V024	20	21	24	Proud and haughty scoffer is his name, who deals in arrogant pride.
B020C021V025	20	21	25	The desire of the slothful kills him; for his hands refuse to labor.
B020C021V026	20	21	26	He covets greedily all the day long: but the righteous gives and spares not.
B020C021V027	20	21	27	The sacrifice of the wicked is abomination: how much more, when he brings it with a wicked mind?
B020C021V028	20	21	28	A false witness shall perish: but the man that hears speaks constantly.
B020C021V029	20	21	29	A wicked man hardens his face: but as for the upright, he considers his way.
B020C021V030	20	21	30	There is no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against the LORD.
B020C021V031	20	21	31	The horse is prepared for the day of battle: but safety is of the LORD.
B020C022V001	20	22	1	A good name is rather to be chosen than great riches, and loving favor rather than silver and gold.
B020C022V002	20	22	2	The rich and poor meet together: the LORD is the maker of them all.
B020C022V003	20	22	3	A prudent man foresees the evil, and hides himself: but the simple pass on, and are punished.
B020C022V004	20	22	4	By humility and the fear of the LORD are riches, and honor, and life.
B020C022V005	20	22	5	Thorns and snares are in the way of the perverse: he that does keep his soul shall be far from them.
B020C022V006	20	22	6	Train up a child in the way he should go: and when he is old, he will not depart from it.
B020C022V007	20	22	7	The rich rules over the poor, and the borrower is servant to the lender.
B020C022V008	20	22	8	He that sows iniquity shall reap trouble: and the rod of his anger shall fail.
B020C022V009	20	22	9	He that has a bountiful eye shall be blessed; for he gives of his bread to the poor.
B020C022V010	20	22	10	Cast out the scoffer, and contention shall go out; yea, strife and reproach shall cease.
B020C022V011	20	22	11	He that loves pureness of heart and has grace on his lips, the king shall be his friend.
B020C022V012	20	22	12	The eyes of the LORD preserve knowledge, and he overthrows the words of the transgressor.
B020C022V013	20	22	13	The slothful man says, There is a lion outside, I shall be slain in the streets.
B020C022V014	20	22	14	The mouth of immoral women is a deep pit: he that is abhorred of the LORD shall fall therein.
B020C022V015	20	22	15	Foolishness is bound in the heart of a child; but the rod of correction shall drive it far from him.
B020C022V016	20	22	16	He that oppresses the poor to increase his riches, and he that gives to the rich, shall surely come to poverty.
B020C022V017	20	22	17	Bow down your ear, and hear the words of the wise, and apply your heart unto my knowledge.
B020C022V018	20	22	18	For it is a pleasant thing if you keep them within you; they shall all be fitted on your lips.
B020C022V019	20	22	19	That your trust may be in the LORD, I have made known to you this day, even to you.
B020C022V020	20	22	20	Have not I written to you excellent things in counsels and knowledge,
B020C022V021	20	22	21	That I might make you know the certainty of the words of truth; that you might answer the words of truth to them that send unto you?
B020C022V022	20	22	22	Rob not the poor, because he is poor: neither oppress the afflicted in the gate:
B020C022V023	20	22	23	For the LORD will plead their cause, and spoil the soul of those that spoiled them.
B020C022V024	20	22	24	Make no friendship with an angry man; and with a furious man you shall not go:
B020C022V025	20	22	25	Lest you learn his ways, and get a snare to your soul.
B020C022V026	20	22	26	Be not one of them that gives pledges, or of them that become surety for debts.
B020C022V027	20	22	27	If you have nothing to pay, why should he take away your bed from under you?
B020C022V028	20	22	28	Remove not the ancient landmark, which your fathers have set.
B020C022V029	20	22	29	See you a man diligent in his business? he shall stand before kings; he shall not stand before obscure men.
B020C023V001	20	23	1	When you sit to eat with a ruler, consider diligently what is before you:
B020C023V002	20	23	2	And put a knife to your throat, if you are a man given to appetite.
B020C023V003	20	23	3	Be not desirous of his delicacies: for they are deceitful food.
B020C023V004	20	23	4	Labor not to be rich: cease from your own wisdom.
B020C023V005	20	23	5	Will you set your eyes upon that which is not? for riches certainly make themselves wings; they fly away as an eagle toward heaven.
B020C023V006	20	23	6	Eat not the bread of him that is stingy, neither desire you his delicacies:
B020C023V007	20	23	7	For as he thinks in his heart, so is he: Eat and drink, says he to you; but his heart is not with you.
B020C023V008	20	23	8	The morsel which you have eaten shall you vomit up, and waste your sweet words.
B020C023V009	20	23	9	Speak not in the ears of a fool: for he will despise the wisdom of your words.
B020C023V010	20	23	10	Remove not the old landmark; and enter not into the fields of the fatherless:
B020C023V011	20	23	11	For their redeemer is mighty; he shall plead their cause with you.
B020C023V012	20	23	12	Apply your heart unto instruction, and your ears to the words of knowledge.
B020C023V013	20	23	13	Withhold not correction from the child: for if you beat him with a rod, he shall not die.
B020C023V014	20	23	14	You shall beat him with the rod, and shall deliver his soul from sheol.
B020C023V015	20	23	15	My son, if your heart is wise, my heart shall rejoice, even mine.
B020C023V016	20	23	16	Yea, my inmost being shall rejoice, when your lips speak right things.
B020C023V017	20	23	17	Let not your heart envy sinners: but be in the fear of the LORD all the day long.
B020C023V018	20	23	18	For surely there is a future hope; and your expectation shall not be cut off.
B020C023V019	20	23	19	Hear you, my son, and be wise, and guide your heart in the way.
B020C023V020	20	23	20	Be not among winebibbers; among gluttonous eaters of meat:
B020C023V021	20	23	21	For the drunkard and the glutton shall come to poverty: and drowsiness shall clothe a man with rags.
B020C023V022	20	23	22	Hearken unto your father that begat you, and despise not your mother when she is old.
B020C023V023	20	23	23	Buy the truth, and sell it not; also wisdom, and instruction, and understanding.
B020C023V024	20	23	24	The father of the righteous shall greatly rejoice: and he that begets a wise child shall have joy in him.
B020C023V025	20	23	25	Your father and your mother shall be glad, and she that bore you shall rejoice.
B020C023V026	20	23	26	My son, give me your heart, and let your eyes observe my ways.
B020C023V027	20	23	27	For a harlot is a deep ditch; and a seductress is a narrow well.
B020C023V028	20	23	28	She also lies in wait as for a prey, and increases the unfaithful among men.
B020C023V029	20	23	29	Who has woe? who has sorrow? who has contentions? who has babbling? who has wounds without cause? who has redness of eyes?
B020C023V030	20	23	30	They that tarry long at the wine; they that go to seek mixed wine.
B020C023V031	20	23	31	Look not you upon the wine when it is red, when it gives its color in the cup, when it moves itself aright.
B020C023V032	20	23	32	At the last it bites like a serpent, and stings like an adder.
B020C023V033	20	23	33	Your eyes shall behold strange things, and your heart shall utter perverse things.
B020C023V034	20	23	34	Yea, you shall be as he that lies down in the midst of the sea, or as he that lies upon the top of a mast.
B020C023V035	20	23	35	They have stricken me, you shall say, and I was not sick; they have beaten me, and I felt it not: when shall I awake? I will seek it yet again.
B020C024V001	20	24	1	Be not envious against evil men, neither desire to be with them.
B020C024V002	20	24	2	For their heart studies destruction, and their lips talk of mischief.
B020C024V003	20	24	3	Through wisdom is a house built; and by understanding it is established:
B020C024V004	20	24	4	And by knowledge shall the chambers be filled with all precious and pleasant riches.
B020C024V005	20	24	5	A wise man is strong; yea, a man of knowledge increases strength.
B020C024V006	20	24	6	For by wise counsel you shall wage your war: and in a multitude of counselors there is safety.
B020C024V007	20	24	7	Wisdom is too lofty for a fool: he opens not his mouth in the gate.
B020C024V008	20	24	8	He that plans to do evil shall be called a mischievous person.
B020C024V009	20	24	9	The thought of foolishness is sin: and the scoffer is an abomination to men.
B020C024V010	20	24	10	If you faint in the day of adversity, your strength is small.
B020C024V011	20	24	11	Deliver those that are drawn toward death, hold back those that are stumbling to the slaughter;
B020C024V012	20	24	12	If you say, Behold, we knew it not; does not he that weighs the heart consider it? and he that keeps your soul, does not he know it? and shall not he render to every man according to his works?
B020C024V013	20	24	13	My son, eat honey because it is good; and the honeycomb, which is sweet to your taste:
B020C024V014	20	24	14	So shall the knowledge of wisdom be unto your soul: when you have found it, then there shall be a reward, and your hope shall not be cut off.
B020C024V015	20	24	15	Lie not in wait, O wicked man, against the dwelling of the righteous; spoil not his resting place:
B020C024V016	20	24	16	For a just man falls seven times, and rises up again: but the wicked shall fall by calamity.
B020C024V017	20	24	17	Rejoice not when your enemy falls, and let not your heart be glad when he stumbles:
B020C024V018	20	24	18	Lest the LORD sees it, and it displeases him, and he turns away his wrath from him.
B020C024V019	20	24	19	Fret not yourself because of evil men, neither be you envious at the wicked;
B020C024V020	20	24	20	For there shall be no reward to the evil man; the lamp of the wicked shall be put out.
B020C024V021	20	24	21	My son, fear the LORD and the king: and associate not with them that are given to change:
B020C024V022	20	24	22	For their calamity shall rise suddenly; and who knows the ruin of them both?
B020C024V023	20	24	23	These things also belong to the wise. It is not good to have partiality in judgment.
B020C024V024	20	24	24	He that says unto the wicked, you are righteous; him shall the people curse, nations shall abhor him:
B020C024V025	20	24	25	But to them that rebuke him shall be delight, and a good blessing shall come upon them.
B020C024V026	20	24	26	Every man shall kiss his lips who gives a right answer.
B020C024V027	20	24	27	Prepare your work outside, and make it fit for yourself in the field; and afterwards build your house.
B020C024V028	20	24	28	Be not a witness against your neighbor without cause; and deceive not with your lips.
B020C024V029	20	24	29	Say not, I will do so to him as he has done to me: I will render to the man according to his work.
B020C024V030	20	24	30	I went by the field of the slothful, and by the vineyard of the man void of understanding;
B020C024V031	20	24	31	And, lo, it was all grown over with thorns, and weeds had covered its face, and its stone wall was broken down.
B020C024V032	20	24	32	Then I saw, and considered it well: I looked upon it, and received instruction.
B020C024V033	20	24	33	Yet a little sleep, a little slumber, a little folding of the hands to sleep:
B020C024V034	20	24	34	So shall your poverty come like a robber; and your want like an armed man.
B020C025V001	20	25	1	These are also proverbs of Solomon, which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied.
B020C025V002	20	25	2	It is the glory of God to conceal a thing: but the honor of kings is to search out a matter.
B020C025V003	20	25	3	The heaven for height, and the earth for depth, and the heart of kings is unsearchable.
B020C025V004	20	25	4	Take away the dross from the silver, and there shall come forth a vessel for the refiner.
B020C025V005	20	25	5	Take away the wicked from before the king, and his throne shall be established in righteousness.
B020C025V006	20	25	6	Put not forth yourself in the presence of the king, and stand not in the place of great men:
B020C025V007	20	25	7	For better it is that it be said unto you, Come up here; than that you should be put lower in the presence of the prince whom your eyes have seen.
B020C025V008	20	25	8	Go not forth hastily to court, lest you know not what to do in the end, when your neighbor has put you to shame.
B020C025V009	20	25	9	Debate your cause with your neighbor himself; and disclose not a secret to another:
B020C025V010	20	25	10	Lest he that hears it put you to shame, and the evil report turns not away.
B020C025V011	20	25	11	A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in settings of silver.
B020C025V012	20	25	12	As an earring of gold, and an ornament of fine gold, so is a wise reprover upon an obedient ear.
B020C025V013	20	25	13	As the cold of snow in the time of harvest, so is a faithful messenger to them that send him: for he refreshes the soul of his masters.
B020C025V014	20	25	14	Whosoever boasts about himself of a gift not given is like clouds and wind without rain.
B020C025V015	20	25	15	By long patience is a prince persuaded, and a gentle tongue breaks the bone.
B020C025V016	20	25	16	Have you found honey? eat only as much as is sufficient for you, lest you be filled with it, and vomit it.
B020C025V017	20	25	17	Withdraw your foot from your neighbor's house; lest he be weary of you, and so hate you.
B020C025V018	20	25	18	A man that bears false witness against his neighbor is a club, and a sword, and a sharp arrow.
B020C025V019	20	25	19	Confidence in an unfaithful man in time of trouble is like a broken tooth, and a foot out of joint.
B020C025V020	20	25	20	As he that takes away a garment in cold weather, and as vinegar upon soda, so is he that sings songs to a heavy heart.
B020C025V021	20	25	21	If your enemy is hungry, give him bread to eat; and if he is thirsty, give him water to drink:
B020C025V022	20	25	22	For you shall heap coals of fire upon his head, and the LORD shall reward you.
B020C025V023	20	25	23	The north wind brings forth rain: so does a backbiting tongue an angry countenance.
B020C025V024	20	25	24	It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop, than with a contentious woman in a whole house.
B020C025V025	20	25	25	As cold water is to a thirsty soul, so is good news from a far country.
B020C025V026	20	25	26	A righteous man falling down before the wicked is as a muddied fountain, and a polluted spring.
B020C025V027	20	25	27	It is not good to eat much honey: so for men to search out their own glory is not glory.
B020C025V028	20	25	28	He that has no rule over his own spirit is like a city that is broken down, and without walls.
B020C026V001	20	26	1	As snow in summer, and as rain in harvest, so honor is not fitting for a fool.
B020C026V002	20	26	2	As the bird by flitting, as the swallow by flying, so the curse without cause shall not alight.
B020C026V003	20	26	3	A whip for the horse, a bridle for the donkey, and a rod for the fool's back.
B020C026V004	20	26	4	Answer not a fool according to his folly, lest you also be like unto him.
B020C026V005	20	26	5	Answer a fool according to his folly, lest he be wise in his own eyes.
B020C026V006	20	26	6	He that sends a message by the hand of a fool cuts off the feet, and drinks violence.
B020C026V007	20	26	7	The legs of the lame are not equal: so is a parable in the mouth of fools.
B020C026V008	20	26	8	As he that binds a stone in a sling, so is he that gives honor to a fool.
B020C026V009	20	26	9	As a thorn goes up into the hand of a drunkard, so is a parable in the mouth of fools.
B020C026V010	20	26	10	The great God that formed all things gives the fool his hire, and the transgressor his wages.
B020C026V011	20	26	11	As a dog returns to his vomit, so a fool returns to his folly.
B020C026V012	20	26	12	See a man wise in his own eyes? there is more hope of a fool than of him.
B020C026V013	20	26	13	The slothful man says, There is a lion in the way; a lion is in the streets.
B020C026V014	20	26	14	As the door turns upon its hinges, so does the slothful upon his bed.
B020C026V015	20	26	15	The slothful hides his hand in his dish; it grieves him to bring it again to his mouth.
B020C026V016	20	26	16	The sluggard is wiser in his own eyes than seven men that can answer reasonably.
B020C026V017	20	26	17	He that passes by, and meddles with a quarrel not belonging to him, is like one that takes a dog by the ears.
B020C026V018	20	26	18	As a madman who throws firebrands, arrows, and death,
B020C026V019	20	26	19	So is the man that deceives his neighbor, and says, Am I not jesting?
B020C026V020	20	26	20	Where no wood is, there the fire goes out: so where there is no talebearer, the strife ceases.
B020C026V021	20	26	21	As coals are to burning coals, and wood to fire; so is a contentious man to kindle strife.
B020C026V022	20	26	22	The words of a talebearer are tasty morsels, and they go down into the innermost parts of the body.
B020C026V023	20	26	23	Burning lips and a wicked heart are like a potsherd covered with silver dross.
B020C026V024	20	26	24	He that hates disguises it with his lips, and lays up deceit within himself;
B020C026V025	20	26	25	When he speaks graciously, believe him not: for there are seven abominations in his heart.
B020C026V026	20	26	26	Whosoeverâ€™s hatred is covered by deceit, his wickedness shall be revealed before the whole assembly.
B020C026V027	20	26	27	Whosoever digs a pit shall fall in it: and he that rolls a stone, it will return upon him.
B020C026V028	20	26	28	A lying tongue hates those that are afflicted by it; and a flattering mouth works ruin.
B020C027V001	20	27	1	Boast not yourself of tomorrow; for you know not what a day may bring forth.
B020C027V002	20	27	2	Let another man praise you, and not your own mouth; a stranger, and not your own lips.
B020C027V003	20	27	3	A stone is heavy, and the sand weighty; but a fool's wrath is heavier than them both.
B020C027V004	20	27	4	Wrath is cruel, and anger is outrageous; but which is able to stand before jealousy?
B020C027V005	20	27	5	Open rebuke is better than hidden love.
B020C027V006	20	27	6	Faithful are the wounds of a friend; but the kisses of an enemy are deceitful.
B020C027V007	20	27	7	The full soul loathes a honeycomb; but to the hungry soul every bitter thing is sweet.
B020C027V008	20	27	8	As a bird that wanders from her nest, so is a man that wanders from his place.
B020C027V009	20	27	9	Ointment and perfume rejoice the heart: so does the sweetness of a man's friend by hearty counsel.
B020C027V010	20	27	10	Your own friend, and your father's friend, forsake not; neither go into your brother's house in the day of your calamity: for better is a neighbor that is near than a brother far off.
B020C027V011	20	27	11	My son, be wise, and make my heart glad, that I may answer him that reproaches me.
B020C027V012	20	27	12	A prudent man foresees the evil, and hides himself; but the simple pass on, and are punished.
B020C027V013	20	27	13	Take his garment who is surety for a stranger, and hold it as a pledge of him for an immoral woman.
B020C027V014	20	27	14	He that blesses his friend with a loud voice, rising early in the morning, it shall be counted a curse to him.
B020C027V015	20	27	15	A continual dripping on a very rainy day and a contentious woman are alike.
B020C027V016	20	27	16	Whosoever restrains her restrains the wind, or grasps oil with his right hand.
B020C027V017	20	27	17	Iron sharpens iron; so a man sharpens the countenance of his friend.
B020C027V018	20	27	18	Whosoever keeps the fig tree shall eat its fruit: so he that waits on his master shall be honored.
B020C027V019	20	27	19	As in water face reflects face, so the heart of man to man.
B020C027V020	20	27	20	Sheol and destruction are never full; so the eyes of man are never satisfied.
B020C027V021	20	27	21	As the refining pot for silver, and the furnace for gold; so is a man judged by his praise.
B020C027V022	20	27	22	Though you should crush a fool in a mortar among grain with a pestle, yet will not his foolishness depart from him.
B020C027V023	20	27	23	Be diligent to know the state of your flocks, and look well to your herds.
B020C027V024	20	27	24	For riches are not forever: and does the crown endure to every generation?
B020C027V025	20	27	25	The hay appears, and the tender grass shows itself, and herbs of the mountains are gathered.
B020C027V026	20	27	26	The lambs are for your clothing, and the goats are for the price of the field.
B020C027V027	20	27	27	And you shall have goats' milk enough for your food, for the food of your household, and for the maintenance for your maidservants.
B020C028V001	20	28	1	The wicked flee when no man pursues: but the righteous are bold as a lion.
B020C028V002	20	28	2	For the transgression of a land many are the princes thereof: but by a man of understanding and knowledge its state shall be prolonged.
B020C028V003	20	28	3	A poor man that oppresses the poor is like a sweeping rain which leaves no food.
B020C028V004	20	28	4	They that forsake the law praise the wicked: but such as keep the law contend with them.
B020C028V005	20	28	5	Evil men understand not justice: but they that seek the LORD understand all things.
B020C028V006	20	28	6	Better is the poor who walks in his uprightness, than he that is perverse in his ways, though he be rich.
B020C028V007	20	28	7	Whosoever keeps the law is a wise son: but he that is a companion of gluttonous men shames his father.
B020C028V008	20	28	8	He that by usury and unjust gain increases his substance, he shall gather it for him that will pity the poor.
B020C028V009	20	28	9	He that turns away his ear from hearing the law, even his prayer shall be abomination.
B020C028V010	20	28	10	Whosoever causes the righteous to go astray in an evil way, he shall fall himself into his own pit: but the upright shall have good things in possession.
B020C028V011	20	28	11	The rich man is wise in his own eyes; but the poor that has understanding will find him out.
B020C028V012	20	28	12	When righteous men do rejoice, there is great glory: but when the wicked rise, men hide themselves.
B020C028V013	20	28	13	He that covers his sins shall not prosper: but whosoever confesses and forsakes them shall have mercy.
B020C028V014	20	28	14	Happy is the man that is reverent always: but he that hardens his heart shall fall into calamity.
B020C028V015	20	28	15	As a roaring lion, and a charging bear; so is a wicked ruler over the poor people.
B020C028V016	20	28	16	The prince that lacks understanding is also a great oppressor: but he that hates covetousness shall prolong his days.
B020C028V017	20	28	17	A man that does violence to the blood of any person shall flee to a pit; let no man help him.
B020C028V018	20	28	18	Whosoever walks uprightly shall be saved: but he that is perverse in his ways shall fall at once.
B020C028V019	20	28	19	He that tills his land shall have plenty of bread: but he that follows after worthless pursuits shall have poverty enough.
B020C028V020	20	28	20	A faithful man shall abound with blessings: but he that makes haste to be rich shall not go unpunished.
B020C028V021	20	28	21	To show partiality is not good: because for a piece of bread that man will transgress.
B020C028V022	20	28	22	He that hastens to be rich has an evil eye, and considers not that poverty shall come upon him.
B020C028V023	20	28	23	He that rebukes a man shall find more favor afterwards than he that flatters with the tongue.
B020C028V024	20	28	24	Whosoever robs his father or his mother, and says, It is no transgression; the same is the companion of a destroyer.
B020C028V025	20	28	25	He that is of a proud heart stirs up strife: but he that puts his trust in the LORD shall be prospered.
B020C028V026	20	28	26	He that trusts in his own heart is a fool: but whosoever walks wisely, he shall be delivered.
B020C028V027	20	28	27	He that gives unto the poor shall not lack: but he that hides his eyes shall have many a curse.
B020C028V028	20	28	28	When the wicked arise, men hide themselves: but when they perish, the righteous increase.
B020C029V001	20	29	1	He, that being often reproved hardens his neck, shall suddenly be destroyed, and that without remedy.
B020C029V002	20	29	2	When the righteous are in authority, the people rejoice: but when the wicked bears rule, the people mourn.
B020C029V003	20	29	3	Whosoever loves wisdom rejoices his father: but he that keeps company with harlots wastes his substance.
B020C029V004	20	29	4	The king by justice establishes the land: but he that receives bribes overthrows it.
B020C029V005	20	29	5	A man that flatters his neighbor spreads a net for his feet.
B020C029V006	20	29	6	In the transgression of an evil man there is a snare: but the righteous does sing and rejoice.
B020C029V007	20	29	7	The righteous considers the cause of the poor: but the wicked regards not such knowledge.
B020C029V008	20	29	8	Scornful men bring a city into a snare: but wise men turn away wrath.
B020C029V009	20	29	9	If a wise man contends with a foolish man, whether the foolish man rages or laughs, there is no rest.
B020C029V010	20	29	10	The bloodthirsty hate the upright: but the just seek his good.
B020C029V011	20	29	11	A fool utters all his mind: but a wise man keeps it in till afterwards.
B020C029V012	20	29	12	If a ruler hearkens to lies, all his servants are wicked.
B020C029V013	20	29	13	The poor and the deceitful man meet together: the LORD lightens both their eyes.
B020C029V014	20	29	14	The king that faithfully judges the poor, his throne shall be established forever.
B020C029V015	20	29	15	The rod and reproof give wisdom: but a child left to himself brings his mother to shame.
B020C029V016	20	29	16	When the wicked are multiplied, transgression increases: but the righteous shall see their fall.
B020C029V017	20	29	17	Correct your son, and he shall give you rest; yea, he shall give delight unto your soul.
B020C029V018	20	29	18	Where there is no vision, the people perish: but he that keeps the law, happy is he.
B020C029V019	20	29	19	A servant will not be corrected by words: for though he understands he will not answer.
B020C029V020	20	29	20	See you a man that is hasty in his words? there is more hope for a fool than for him.
B020C029V021	20	29	21	He that carefully brings up his servant from a child shall have him become his son in the end.
B020C029V022	20	29	22	An angry man stirs up strife, and a furious man abounds in transgression.
B020C029V023	20	29	23	A man's pride shall bring him low: but honor shall uphold the humble in spirit.
B020C029V024	20	29	24	Whosoever is partner with a thief hates his own soul: he hears cursing, and reveals it not.
B020C029V025	20	29	25	The fear of man brings a snare: but whosoever puts his trust in the LORD shall be safe.
B020C029V026	20	29	26	Many seek the ruler's favor; but every man's judgment comes from the LORD.
B020C029V027	20	29	27	An unjust man is an abomination to the just: and he that is upright in the way is abomination to the wicked.
B020C030V001	20	30	1	The words of Agur the son of Jakeh, even the prophecy: the man spoke unto Ithiel, even unto Ithiel and Ucal,
B020C030V002	20	30	2	Surely I am more senseless than any man, and have not the understanding of a man.
B020C030V003	20	30	3	I neither learned wisdom, nor have the knowledge of the holy.
B020C030V004	20	30	4	Who has ascended up into heaven, or descended? who has gathered the wind in his fists? who has bound the waters in a garment? who has established all the ends of the earth? what is his name, and what is his son's name, if you can tell?
B020C030V005	20	30	5	Every word of God is pure: he is a shield unto them that put their trust in him.
B020C030V006	20	30	6	Add not unto his words, lest he reprove you, and you be found a liar.
B020C030V007	20	30	7	Two things have I required of you; deny me not them before I die:
B020C030V008	20	30	8	Remove far from me vanity and lies: give me neither poverty nor riches; feed me with food needful for me:
B020C030V009	20	30	9	Lest I be full, and deny you, and say, Who is the LORD? or lest I be poor, and steal, and take the name of my God in vain.
B020C030V010	20	30	10	Accuse not a servant unto his master, lest he curse you, and you be found guilty.
B020C030V011	20	30	11	There is a generation that curses their father, and does not bless their mother.
B020C030V012	20	30	12	There is a generation that are pure in their own eyes, and yet are not washed from their filthiness.
B020C030V013	20	30	13	There is a generation, O how lofty are their eyes! and their eyelids are lifted up.
B020C030V014	20	30	14	There is a generation, whose teeth are as swords, and their jaw teeth as knives, to devour the poor from off the earth, and the needy from among men.
B020C030V015	20	30	15	The leach has two daughters, crying, Give, give. There are three things that are never satisfied, yea, four things say not, It is enough:
B020C030V016	20	30	16	The grave; and the barren womb; the earth that is not filled with water; and the fire that says not, It is enough.
B020C030V017	20	30	17	The eye that mocks at his father, and despises to obey his mother, the ravens of the valley shall pick it out, and the young vultures shall eat it.
B020C030V018	20	30	18	There are three things which are too wonderful for me, yea, four which I know not:
B020C030V019	20	30	19	The way of an eagle in the air; the way of a serpent upon a rock; the way of a ship in the midst of the sea; and the way of a man with a maiden.
B020C030V020	20	30	20	This is the way of an adulterous woman; she eats, and wipes her mouth, and says, I have done no wickedness.
B020C030V021	20	30	21	For three things the earth trembles, under four it cannot bear up:
B020C030V022	20	30	22	For a servant when he reigns; and a fool when he is filled with food;
B020C030V023	20	30	23	For an unloved woman when she is married; and a maidservant that is heir to her mistress.
B020C030V024	20	30	24	There are four things which are little upon the earth, but they are exceeding wise:
B020C030V025	20	30	25	The ants are a people not strong, yet they prepare their food in the summer;
B020C030V026	20	30	26	The badgers are but a feeble folk, yet they make their houses in the rocks;
B020C030V027	20	30	27	The locusts have no king, yet they go forth all of them by bands;
B020C030V028	20	30	28	The spider takes hold with its hands, and is in kings' palaces.
B020C030V029	20	30	29	There are three things which are stately in stride, yea, four are stately in their walk:
B020C030V030	20	30	30	A lion which is strongest among beasts, and turns not away from any;
B020C030V031	20	30	31	A greyhound; a male goat also; and a king, against whom there is no rising up.
B020C030V032	20	30	32	If you have done foolishly in lifting up yourself, or if you have thought evil, lay your hand upon your mouth.
B020C030V033	20	30	33	Surely the churning of milk brings forth butter, and the wringing of the nose brings forth blood: so the forcing of wrath brings forth strife.
B020C031V001	20	31	1	The words of king Lemuel, the prophecy that his mother taught him.
B020C031V002	20	31	2	What, my son? and what, the son of my womb? and what, the son of my vows?
B020C031V003	20	31	3	Give not your strength unto women, nor your ways to that which destroys kings.
B020C031V004	20	31	4	It is not for kings, O Lemuel, it is not for kings to drink wine; nor for princes strong drink:
B020C031V005	20	31	5	Lest they drink, and forget the law, and pervert the justice of any of the afflicted.
B020C031V006	20	31	6	Give strong drink unto him that is ready to perish, and wine unto those that be of heavy hearts.
B020C031V007	20	31	7	Let him drink, and forget his poverty, and remember his misery no more.
B020C031V008	20	31	8	Open your mouth for the dumb, for the cause of all who are left desolate.
B020C031V009	20	31	9	Open your mouth, judge righteously, and plead the cause of the poor and needy.
B020C031V010	20	31	10	Who can find a virtuous woman? for her price is far above rubies.
B020C031V011	20	31	11	The heart of her husband does safely trust in her, so that he shall have no lack of gain.
B020C031V012	20	31	12	She will do him good and not evil all the days of her life.
B020C031V013	20	31	13	She seeks wool, and flax, and works willingly with her hands.
B020C031V014	20	31	14	She is like the merchants' ships; she brings her food from afar.
B020C031V015	20	31	15	She rises also while it is yet night, and gives food to her household, and a portion to her maidservants.
B020C031V016	20	31	16	She considers a field, and buys it: with the fruit of her hands she plants a vineyard.
B020C031V017	20	31	17	She girds her loins with strength, and strengthens her arms.
B020C031V018	20	31	18	She perceives that her merchandise is good: her lamp goes not out by night.
B020C031V019	20	31	19	She lays her hands to the distaff, and her hands hold the spindle.
B020C031V020	20	31	20	She stretches out her hand to the poor; yea, she reaches forth her hands to the needy.
B020C031V021	20	31	21	She is not afraid of the snow for her household: for all her household are clothed with scarlet.
B020C031V022	20	31	22	She makes herself coverings of tapestry; her clothing is fine linen and purple.
B020C031V023	20	31	23	Her husband is known in the gates, when he sits among the elders of the land.
B020C031V024	20	31	24	She makes fine linen, and sells it; and delivers sashes unto the merchants.
B020C031V025	20	31	25	Strength and honor are her clothing; and she shall rejoice in time to come.
B020C031V026	20	31	26	She opens her mouth with wisdom; and on her tongue is the law of kindness.
B020C031V027	20	31	27	She looks well to the ways of her household, and eats not the bread of idleness.
B020C031V028	20	31	28	Her children arise up, and call her blessed; her husband also, and he praises her.
B020C031V029	20	31	29	Many daughters have done virtuously, but you excel them all.
B020C031V030	20	31	30	Charm is deceitful, and beauty is vain: but a woman that fears the LORD, she shall be praised.
B020C031V031	20	31	31	Give her of the fruit of her hands; and let her own works praise her in the gates.
B021C001V001	21	1	1	The words of the Preacher, the son of David, king in Jerusalem.
B021C001V002	21	1	2	Vanity of vanities, says the Preacher, vanity of vanities; all is vanity.
B021C001V003	21	1	3	What profit has a man of all his labor which he takes under the sun?
B021C001V004	21	1	4	One generation passes away, and another generation comes: but the earth abides forever.
B021C001V005	21	1	5	The sun also arises, and the sun goes down, and hastens to its place where it arose.
B021C001V006	21	1	6	The wind goes toward the south, and turns about unto the north; it whirls about continually, and the wind returns again according to its circuit.
B021C001V007	21	1	7	All the rivers run into the sea; yet the sea is not full; unto the place from where the rivers come, there they return again.
B021C001V008	21	1	8	All things are full of weariness; man cannot express it: the eye is not satisfied with seeing, nor the ear filled with hearing.
B021C001V009	21	1	9	The thing that has been, it is that which shall be; and that which is done is that which shall be done: and there is no new thing under the sun.
B021C001V010	21	1	10	Is there any thing of which it may be said, See, this is new? it has been already of old time, which was before us.
B021C001V011	21	1	11	There is no remembrance of former things; neither shall there be any remembrance of things that are to come with those that shall come after.
B021C001V012	21	1	12	I the Preacher was king over Israel in Jerusalem.
B021C001V013	21	1	13	And I gave my heart to seek and search out by wisdom concerning all things that are done under heaven: this severe burden has God given to the sons of man to be afflicted with.
B021C001V014	21	1	14	I have seen all the works that are done under the sun; and, behold, all is vanity and like grasping the wind.
B021C001V015	21	1	15	That which is crooked cannot be made straight: and that which is lacking cannot be numbered.
B021C001V016	21	1	16	I communed with my own heart, saying, Lo, I have come to greatness, and have gotten more wisdom than all they that have been before me in Jerusalem: yea, my heart had great experience of wisdom and knowledge.
B021C001V017	21	1	17	And I set my heart to know wisdom, and to know madness and folly: I perceived that this also is like grasping the wind.
B021C001V018	21	1	18	For in much wisdom is much grief: and he that increases knowledge increases sorrow.
B021C002V001	21	2	1	I said in my heart, Come now, I will test you with mirth, therefore enjoy pleasure: and, behold, this also is vanity.
B021C002V002	21	2	2	I said of laughter, It is mad: and of mirth, What use is it?
B021C002V003	21	2	3	I sought in my heart to give myself unto wine, yet acquainting my heart with wisdom; and to lay hold on folly, till I might see what was good for the sons of men, which they should do under heaven all the days of their life.
B021C002V004	21	2	4	I made myself great works; I built houses; I planted vineyards:
B021C002V005	21	2	5	I made myself gardens and orchards, and I planted trees in them with all kind of fruit:
B021C002V006	21	2	6	I made myself pools of water, with which to water the forest that brings forth trees:
B021C002V007	21	2	7	I got myself male and female servants, and had servants born in my house; also I had great possessions of great and small cattle more than all that were in Jerusalem before me:
B021C002V008	21	2	8	I gathered for myself also silver and gold, and the special treasures of kings and of the provinces: I got men singers and women singers, the delights of the sons of men, and musical instruments of all sorts.
B021C002V009	21	2	9	So I was great, and increased more than all that were before me in Jerusalem: also my wisdom remained with me.
B021C002V010	21	2	10	And whatsoever my eyes desired I kept not from them, I withheld not my heart from any joy; for my heart rejoiced in all my labor: and this was my reward of all my labor.
B021C002V011	21	2	11	Then I looked on all the works that my hands had made, and on the labor that I had expended on it: and, behold, all was vanity and like grasping the wind, and there was no profit under the sun.
B021C002V012	21	2	12	And I turned myself to behold wisdom, and madness, and folly: for what can a man do that comes after the king? even that which has been already done.
B021C002V013	21	2	13	Then I saw that wisdom excels folly, as far as light excels darkness.
B021C002V014	21	2	14	The wise man's eyes are in his head; but the fool walks in darkness: and I myself perceived also that one fate happens to them all.
B021C002V015	21	2	15	Then said I in my heart, As it happens to the fool, so it happens even to me; and why was I then more wise? Then I said in my heart, that this also is vanity.
B021C002V016	21	2	16	For there is no remembrance of the wise more than of the fool forever; seeing that which now is in the days to come shall all be forgotten. And how does the wise man die? as the fool.
B021C002V017	21	2	17	Therefore I hated life; because the work that is done under the sun is grievous unto me: for all is vanity and like grasping the wind.
B021C002V018	21	2	18	Yea, I hated all my labor in which I had toiled under the sun: because I must leave it unto the man that shall be after me.
B021C002V019	21	2	19	And who knows whether he shall be a wise man or a fool? yet shall he have rule over all my labor in which I have labored, and in which I have shown myself wise under the sun. This is also vanity.
B021C002V020	21	2	20	Therefore I gave my heart up to despair of all the labor in which I toiled under the sun.
B021C002V021	21	2	21	For there is a man whose labor is in wisdom, and in knowledge, and in equity; yet to a man that has not labored in it shall he leave it for his portion. This also is vanity and a great evil.
B021C002V022	21	2	22	For what has man for all his labor, and for the striving of his heart, with which he has labored under the sun?
B021C002V023	21	2	23	For all his days are sorrows, and his travail grief; yea, his heart takes not rest in the night. This is also vanity.
B021C002V024	21	2	24	There is nothing better for a man, than that he should eat and drink, and that he should make his soul enjoy good in his labor. This also I saw, that it was from the hand of God.
B021C002V025	21	2	25	For who can eat, or who else can have enjoyment, more than I?
B021C002V026	21	2	26	For God gives to a man that is good in his sight wisdom, and knowledge, and joy: but to the sinner he gives the work of gathering and heaping up, only that he may give to him that is good before God. This also is vanity and grasping of the wind.
B021C003V001	21	3	1	To every thing there is a season, and a time to every purpose under the heaven:
B021C003V002	21	3	2	A time to be born, and a time to die; a time to plant, and a time to pluck up that which is planted;
B021C003V003	21	3	3	A time to kill, and a time to heal; a time to break down, and a time to build up;
B021C003V004	21	3	4	A time to weep, and a time to laugh; a time to mourn, and a time to dance;
B021C003V005	21	3	5	A time to cast away stones, and a time to gather stones together; a time to embrace, and a time to refrain from embracing;
B021C003V006	21	3	6	A time to get, and a time to lose; a time to keep, and a time to cast away;
B021C003V007	21	3	7	A time to tear, and a time to sew; a time to keep silence, and a time to speak;
B021C003V008	21	3	8	A time to love, and a time to hate; a time of war, and a time of peace.
B021C003V009	21	3	9	What profit has he that works in that in which he labors?
B021C003V010	21	3	10	I have seen the task, which God has given to the sons of men to be occupied in it.
B021C003V011	21	3	11	He has made every thing beautiful in its time: also he has put eternity in menâ€™s hearts, so that no man can find out the work that God does from the beginning to the end.
B021C003V012	21	3	12	I know that there is no good in them, but for a man to rejoice, and to do good in his life.
B021C003V013	21	3	13	And also that every man should eat and drink, and enjoy the good of all his labor, it is the gift of God.
B021C003V014	21	3	14	I know that, whatsoever God does, it shall be forever: nothing can be added to it, nor any thing taken from it: and God does it, that men should fear before him.
B021C003V015	21	3	15	That which has been is now; and that which is to be has already been; and God requires that which is past.
B021C003V016	21	3	16	And moreover I saw under the sun the place of justice, that wickedness was there; and the place of righteousness, that iniquity was there.
B021C003V017	21	3	17	I said in my heart, God shall judge the righteous and the wicked: for there is a time for every purpose and for every work.
B021C003V018	21	3	18	I said in my heart concerning the condition of the sons of men, that God might reveal them, and that they might see that they themselves are beasts.
B021C003V019	21	3	19	For that which befalls the sons of men befalls beasts; the same thing befalls them: as the one dies, so dies the other; yea, they have all one breath; so that a man has no advantage over a beast: for all is vanity.
B021C003V020	21	3	20	All go unto one place; all are of the dust, and all turn to dust again.
B021C003V021	21	3	21	Who knows the spirit of man that goes upward, and the spirit of the beast that goes downward to the earth?
B021C003V022	21	3	22	Therefore I perceive that there is nothing better, than that a man should rejoice in his own works; for that is his lot: for who can bring him to see what shall be after him?
B021C004V001	21	4	1	So I returned, and considered all the oppressions that are done under the sun: and behold the tears of such as were oppressed, and they had no comforter; and on the side of their oppressors there was power; but they had no comforter.
B021C004V002	21	4	2	Therefore I praised the dead who are already dead more than the living who are yet alive.
B021C004V003	21	4	3	Yea, better is he than both, who has not yet been, who has not seen the evil work that is done under the sun.
B021C004V004	21	4	4	Again, I considered all toil, and every skillful work, that for this a man is envied by his neighbor. This is also vanity and grasping after the wind.
B021C004V005	21	4	5	The fool folds his hands together, and eats his own flesh.
B021C004V006	21	4	6	Better is a handful with quietness, than both hands full with toil and grasping for the wind.
B021C004V007	21	4	7	Then I returned, and I saw vanity under the sun.
B021C004V008	21	4	8	There is one alone, and there is not a second; yea, he has neither child nor brother: yet is there no end of all his labor; neither is his eye satisfied with riches; neither says he, For whom do I labor, and deprive my soul of good? This is also vanity, yea, it is a heavy travail.
B021C004V009	21	4	9	Two are better than one; because they have a good reward for their labor.
B021C004V010	21	4	10	For if they fall, the one will lift up his fellow: but woe to him that is alone when he falls; for he has not another to help him up.
B021C004V011	21	4	11	Again, if two lie together, then they have heat: but how can one be warm alone?
B021C004V012	21	4	12	And if one prevails against him, two shall withstand him; and a threefold cord is not quickly broken.
B021C004V013	21	4	13	Better is a poor and wise child than an old and foolish king, who will no longer be admonished.
B021C004V014	21	4	14	For out of prison he comes to reign; yet he that is born in his kingdom might become poor.
B021C004V015	21	4	15	I considered all the living who walk under the sun, with the second child that shall stand up in his place.
B021C004V016	21	4	16	There is no end of all the people, even of all that have been before them: they also that come after him shall not rejoice in him. Surely this also is vanity and grasping after the wind.
B021C005V001	21	5	1	Guard your steps when you go to the house of God, and be more ready to hear, than to give the sacrifice of fools: for they consider not that they do evil.
B021C005V002	21	5	2	Be not rash with your mouth, and let not your heart be hasty to utter anything before God: for God is in heaven, and you upon earth: therefore let your words be few.
B021C005V003	21	5	3	For a dream comes through much business; and a fool's voice is known by a multitude of words.
B021C005V004	21	5	4	When you vow a vow unto God, defer not to pay it; for he has no pleasure in fools: pay that which you have vowed.
B021C005V005	21	5	5	Better is it that you should not vow, than that you should vow and not pay.
B021C005V006	21	5	6	Permit not your mouth to cause your flesh to sin; neither say before the angel, that it was an error: why should God be angry at your voice, and destroy the work of your hands?
B021C005V007	21	5	7	For in the multitude of dreams and many words there are also many vanities: but you fear God.
B021C005V008	21	5	8	If you see the oppression of the poor, and violent perverting of justice and righteousness in a province, marvel not at the matter: for the high official is watched by a higher one ; and there are yet higher ones over them.
B021C005V009	21	5	9	Moreover the profit of the earth is for all: the king himself is served from the field.
B021C005V010	21	5	10	He that loves silver shall not be satisfied with silver; nor he that loves abundance, with increase: this is also vanity.
B021C005V011	21	5	11	When goods increase, they are increased that eat them: so what good is there to the owners, except the beholding of them with their eyes?
B021C005V012	21	5	12	The sleep of a laboring man is sweet, whether he eats little or much: but the abundance of the rich will not allow him to sleep.
B021C005V013	21	5	13	There is a great evil which I have seen under the sun, namely, riches kept by their owners to their hurt.
B021C005V014	21	5	14	But those riches are lost by a bad venture: when he begets a son, there is nothing in his hand.
B021C005V015	21	5	15	As he came forth of his mother's womb, naked shall he return to go as he came, and shall take nothing from his labor, which he may carry away in his hand.
B021C005V016	21	5	16	And this also is a great evil, that just as he came, so shall he go: and what profit has he who has labored for the wind?
B021C005V017	21	5	17	All his days also he eats in darkness, and he has much sorrow and wrath with his sickness.
B021C005V018	21	5	18	Behold that which I have seen: it is good and fitting for one to eat and to drink, and to enjoy the good of all his labor that he takes under the sun all the days of his life, which God gives him: for this is his lot.
B021C005V019	21	5	19	Every man also to whom God has given riches and wealth, and has given him power to eat of it, and to accept his lot, and to rejoice in his labor; this is the gift of God.
B021C005V020	21	5	20	For he shall not much remember the days of his life; because God keeps him busy with the joy of his heart.
B021C006V001	21	6	1	There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, and it is common among men:
B021C006V002	21	6	2	A man to whom God has given riches, wealth, and honor, so that he wants nothing for his soul of all that he desires, yet God gives him not power to eat of it, but a stranger eats it: this is vanity, and it is an evil affliction.
B021C006V003	21	6	3	If a man begets a hundred children, and lives many years, so that the days of his years are many, and his soul is not filled with good, and also that he has no burial; I say, that a stillborn birth is better than he.
B021C006V004	21	6	4	For he comes in with vanity, and departs in darkness, and his name shall be covered with darkness.
B021C006V005	21	6	5	Moreover he has not seen the sun, nor known any thing: this one has more rest than the other.
B021C006V006	21	6	6	Yea, though he lives a thousand years twice over, yet he has seen no good: do not all go to one place?
B021C006V007	21	6	7	All the labor of man is for his mouth, and yet the appetite is not filled.
B021C006V008	21	6	8	For what has the wise more than the fool? what has the poor, who knows to walk before the living?
B021C006V009	21	6	9	Better is the sight of the eyes than the wandering of the desire: this is also vanity and grasping after the wind.
B021C006V010	21	6	10	Whatever has been is named already, and it is known that this is man: neither may he contend with him that is mightier than he.
B021C006V011	21	6	11	Since there are many things that increase vanity, how is man the better?
B021C006V012	21	6	12	For who knows what is good for man in this life, all the days of his vain life which he spends like a shadow? for who can tell a man what shall be after him under the sun?
B021C007V001	21	7	1	A good name is better than precious ointment; and the day of death than the day of one's birth.
B021C007V002	21	7	2	It is better to go to the house of mourning, than to go to the house of feasting: for that is the end of all men; and the living will lay it to his heart.
B021C007V003	21	7	3	Sorrow is better than laughter: for by the sadness of the countenance the heart is made better.
B021C007V004	21	7	4	The heart of the wise is in the house of mourning; but the heart of fools is in the house of mirth.
B021C007V005	21	7	5	It is better to hear the rebuke of the wise, than for a man to hear the song of fools.
B021C007V006	21	7	6	For as the crackling of thorns under a pot, so is the laughter of the fool: this also is vanity.
B021C007V007	21	7	7	Surely oppression makes a wise man mad; and a bribe destroys the heart.
B021C007V008	21	7	8	Better is the end of a thing than the beginning thereof: and the patient in spirit is better than the proud in spirit.
B021C007V009	21	7	9	Be not hasty in your spirit to be angry: for anger rests in the bosom of fools.
B021C007V010	21	7	10	Say you not, What is the cause that the former days were better than these? for you do not inquire wisely concerning this.
B021C007V011	21	7	11	Wisdom is good with an inheritance: and by it there is profit to them that see the sun.
B021C007V012	21	7	12	For wisdom is a defense, and money is a defense: but the excellence of knowledge is, that wisdom gives life to them that have it.
B021C007V013	21	7	13	Consider the work of God: for who can make that straight, which he has made crooked?
B021C007V014	21	7	14	In the day of prosperity be joyful, but in the day of adversity consider: God also has set the one over against the other, to the end that man should find nothing that will come after him.
B021C007V015	21	7	15	All things have I seen in the days of my vanity: there is a just man that perishes in his righteousness, and there is a wicked man that prolongs his life in his wickedness.
B021C007V016	21	7	16	Be not overly righteous; neither make yourself overly wise: why should you destroy yourself?
B021C007V017	21	7	17	Be not overly wicked, neither be foolish: why should you die before your time?
B021C007V018	21	7	18	It is good that you should take hold of this; yea, also from this withhold not your hand: for he that fears God shall come forth of them all.
B021C007V019	21	7	19	Wisdom strengthens the wise more than ten mighty men who are in the city.
B021C007V020	21	7	20	For there is not a just man upon earth, that does good, and sins not.
B021C007V021	21	7	21	Also take not to heart all words that are spoken; lest you hear your servant curse you:
B021C007V022	21	7	22	For oftentimes also your own heart knows that you yourself likewise have cursed others.
B021C007V023	21	7	23	All this have I proved by wisdom: I said, I will be wise; but it was far from me.
B021C007V024	21	7	24	That which is far off, and exceedingly deep, who can find it out?
B021C007V025	21	7	25	I applied my heart to know, and to search, and to seek out wisdom, and the reason of things, and to know the wickedness of folly, even of foolishness and madness:
B021C007V026	21	7	26	And I find more bitter than death the woman whose heart is snares and nets, and her hands are fetters: whosoever pleases God shall escape from her; but the sinner shall be taken by her.
B021C007V027	21	7	27	Behold, this have I found, says the preacher, adding one thing to another, to find out the reason:
B021C007V028	21	7	28	Which yet my soul seeks, but I find not: one man among a thousand have I found; but a woman among all those have I not found.
B021C007V029	21	7	29	Lo, this only have I found, that God has made man upright; but they have sought out many devices.
B021C008V001	21	8	1	Who is as the wise man? and who knows the interpretation of a thing? a man's wisdom makes his face to shine, and the hardness of his face is changed.
B021C008V002	21	8	2	I counsel you to keep the king's commandment, and that for the sake of your oath to God.
B021C008V003	21	8	3	Be not hasty to go out of his presence: stand not for an evil thing; for he does whatsoever pleases him.
B021C008V004	21	8	4	Where the word of a king is, there is power: and who may say unto him, What are you doing?
B021C008V005	21	8	5	Whosoever keeps the commandment shall experience no evil thing: and a wise man's heart discerns both time and judgment.
B021C008V006	21	8	6	Because to every purpose there is time and judgment, therefore the misery of man is heavy upon him.
B021C008V007	21	8	7	For he knows not that which shall be: for who can tell him when it shall be?
B021C008V008	21	8	8	There is no man that has power over the spirit to retain the spirit; neither has he power in the day of death: and there is no release from that war; neither shall wickedness deliver those that are given to it.
B021C008V009	21	8	9	All this have I seen, and applied my heart unto every work that is done under the sun: there is a time in which one man rules over another to his own hurt.
B021C008V010	21	8	10	And so I saw the wicked buried, who had come and gone from the holy place, and they were forgotten in the city where they had so done: this is also vanity.
B021C008V011	21	8	11	Because sentence against an evil work is not executed speedily, therefore the heart of the sons of men is fully set in them to do evil.
B021C008V012	21	8	12	Though a sinner does evil a hundred times, and his days are prolonged, yet surely I know that it shall be well with them that fear God, who fear before him:
B021C008V013	21	8	13	But it shall not be well with the wicked, neither shall he prolong his days, which are as a shadow; because he fears not before God.
B021C008V014	21	8	14	There is a vanity which is done upon the earth; that there are just men, unto whom it happens according to the work of the wicked; again, there are wicked men, to whom it happens according to the work of the righteous: I said that this also is vanity.
B021C008V015	21	8	15	Then I commended mirth, because a man has no better thing under the sun, than to eat, and to drink, and to be merry: for that shall abide with him in his labor all the days of his life, which God gives him under the sun.
B021C008V016	21	8	16	When I applied my heart to know wisdom, and to see the business that is done upon the earth: (for also there is one who neither day nor night sees sleep with his eyes:)
B021C008V017	21	8	17	Then I beheld all the work of God, that a man cannot find out the work that is done under the sun: because though a man labors to seek it out, yet he shall not find it; yea moreover; though a wise man thinks to know it, yet shall he not be able to find it.
B021C009V001	21	9	1	For all this I considered in my heart even to declare all this, that the righteous, and the wise, and their works, are in the hand of God: no man knows either love or hatred by all that is before them.
B021C009V002	21	9	2	All things come alike to all: there is one event to the righteous, and to the wicked; to the good and to the clean, and to the unclean; to him that sacrifices, and to him that sacrifices not: as is the good, so is the sinner; and he that swears, as he that fears an oath.
B021C009V003	21	9	3	This is an evil among all things that are done under the sun, that there is one event unto all: yea, also the heart of the sons of men is full of evil, and madness is in their heart while they live, and after that they go to the dead.
B021C009V004	21	9	4	For to him that is joined to all the living there is hope: for a living dog is better than a dead lion.
B021C009V005	21	9	5	For the living know that they shall die: but the dead know not any thing, neither have they any more a reward; for the memory of them is forgotten.
B021C009V006	21	9	6	Also their love, and their hatred, and their envy, is now perished; neither have they any more a portion forever in any thing that is done under the sun.
B021C009V007	21	9	7	Go your way, eat your bread with joy, and drink your wine with a merry heart; for God now accepts your works.
B021C009V008	21	9	8	Let your garments be always white; and let your head lack no ointment.
B021C009V009	21	9	9	Live joyfully with the wife whom you love all the days of the life of your vanity, which he has given you under the sun, all the days of your vanity: for that is your portion in this life, and in your labor which you perform under the sun.
B021C009V010	21	9	10	Whatsoever your hand finds to do, do it with your might; for there is no work, nor device, nor knowledge, nor wisdom, in the grave, where you go.
B021C009V011	21	9	11	I returned, and saw under the sun, that the race is not to the swift, nor the battle to the strong, neither yet bread to the wise, nor yet riches to men of understanding, nor yet favor to men of skill; but time and chance happens to them all.
B021C009V012	21	9	12	For man also knows not his time: as the fish that are taken in an evil net, and as the birds that are caught in the snare; so are the sons of men snared in an evil time, when it falls suddenly upon them.
B021C009V013	21	9	13	This wisdom have I seen also under the sun, and it seemed great unto me:
B021C009V014	21	9	14	There was a little city, and few men within it; and there came a great king against it, and besieged it, and built great bulwarks against it:
B021C009V015	21	9	15	Now there was found in it a poor wise man, and he by his wisdom delivered the city; yet no man remembered that same poor man.
B021C009V016	21	9	16	Then said I, Wisdom is better than strength: nevertheless the poor man's wisdom is despised, and his words are not heard.
B021C009V017	21	9	17	The words of wise men are heard in quiet more than the cry of him that rules among fools.
B021C009V018	21	9	18	Wisdom is better than weapons of war: but one sinner destroys much good.
B021C010V001	21	10	1	Dead flies cause the ointment of the perfumer to send forth a foul odor: so does a little folly to him that is respected for wisdom and honor.
B021C010V002	21	10	2	A wise man's heart is at his right hand; but a fool's heart at his left.
B021C010V003	21	10	3	Yea also, when he that is a fool walks by the way, his wisdom fails him, and he says to every one that he is a fool.
B021C010V004	21	10	4	If the spirit of the ruler rises up against you, leave not your post; for yielding pacifies great offences.
B021C010V005	21	10	5	There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, as an error which proceeds from the ruler:
B021C010V006	21	10	6	Folly is set in great dignity, and the rich sit in low place.
B021C010V007	21	10	7	I have seen servants upon horses, and princes walking as servants upon the earth.
B021C010V008	21	10	8	He that digs a pit shall fall into it; and whosoever breaks through a wall, a serpent shall bite him.
B021C010V009	21	10	9	Whosoever quarries stones may be hurt by them; and he that splits wood shall be endangered by it.
B021C010V010	21	10	10	If the iron is blunt, and he does not sharpen the edge, then must he use more strength: but wisdom helps one to succeed.
B021C010V011	21	10	11	Surely the serpent will bite without enchantment; and a babbler is no better.
B021C010V012	21	10	12	The words of a wise man's mouth are gracious; but the lips of a fool will swallow him up.
B021C010V013	21	10	13	The beginning of the words of his mouth is foolishness: and the end of his talk is wicked madness.
B021C010V014	21	10	14	A fool also is full of words: a man cannot tell what shall be; and what shall be after him, who can tell him?
B021C010V015	21	10	15	The labor of the foolish wearies every one of them, because he knows not how to go to the city.
B021C010V016	21	10	16	Woe to you, O land, when your king is a child, and your princes feast in the morning!
B021C010V017	21	10	17	Blessed are you, O land, when your king is the son of nobles, and your princes feast at the proper time, for strength, and not for drunkenness!
B021C010V018	21	10	18	By much slothfulness the building decays; and through idleness of the hands the house leaks.
B021C010V019	21	10	19	A feast is made for laughter, and wine makes merry: but money answers all things.
B021C010V020	21	10	20	Curse not the king, no not even in your thought; and curse not the rich in your bedchamber: for a bird of the air shall carry the voice, and that which has wings shall tell the matter.
B021C011V001	21	11	1	Cast your bread upon the waters: for you shall find it after many days.
B021C011V002	21	11	2	Give a portion to seven, and also to eight; for you know not what evil shall be upon the earth.
B021C011V003	21	11	3	If the clouds are full of rain, they empty themselves upon the earth: and if the tree falls toward the south, or toward the north, in the place where the tree falls, there it shall be.
B021C011V004	21	11	4	He that observes the wind shall not sow; and he that regards the clouds shall not reap.
B021C011V005	21	11	5	As you know not what is the way of the wind, nor how the bones do grow in the womb of her that is with child: even so you know not the works of God who makes all.
B021C011V006	21	11	6	In the morning sow your seed, and in the evening withhold not your hand: for you know not which shall prosper, either this or that, or whether they both alike shall be good.
B021C011V007	21	11	7	Truly the light is sweet, and a pleasant thing it is for the eyes to behold the sun:
B021C011V008	21	11	8	But if a man lives many years, and rejoices in them all; yet let him remember the days of darkness; for they shall be many. All that comes is vanity.
B021C011V009	21	11	9	Rejoice, O young man, in your youth; and let your heart cheer you in the days of your youth, and walk in the ways of your heart, and in the sight of your eyes: but know that for all these things God will bring you into judgment.
B021C011V010	21	11	10	Therefore remove sorrow from your heart, and put away evil from your flesh: for childhood and youth are vanity.
B021C012V001	21	12	1	Remember now your Creator in the days of your youth, while the evil days come not, nor the years draw near, when you shall say, I have no pleasure in them;
B021C012V002	21	12	2	While the sun, or the light, or the moon, or the stars, be not darkened, nor the clouds return after the rain:
B021C012V003	21	12	3	In the day when the keepers of the house shall tremble, and the strong men shall bow themselves, and the grinders cease because they are few, and those that look out of the windows grow dim,
B021C012V004	21	12	4	And the doors shall be shut in the streets, when the sound of the grinding is low, and one shall rise up at the voice of the bird, and all the daughters of music shall be brought low;
B021C012V005	21	12	5	Also when they shall be afraid of that which is high, and terrors are in the way, and the almond tree shall blossom, and the grasshopper shall be a burden, and desire shall fail: because man goes to his eternal home, and the mourners go about the streets:
B021C012V006	21	12	6	Before the silver cord is loosed, or the golden bowl is broken, or the pitcher is broken at the fountain, or the wheel broken at the cistern.
B021C012V007	21	12	7	Then shall the dust return to the earth as it was: and the spirit shall return unto God who gave it.
B021C012V008	21	12	8	Vanity of vanities, says the preacher; all is vanity.
B021C012V009	21	12	9	And moreover, because the preacher was wise, he still taught the people knowledge; yea, he pondered, and sought out, and set in order many proverbs.
B021C012V010	21	12	10	The preacher sought to find acceptable words: and that which was written was upright, even words of truth.
B021C012V011	21	12	11	The words of the wise are as goads, and as nails firmly fixed by the masters of assemblies, which are given by one shepherd.
B021C012V012	21	12	12	And further, my son, be admonished by these: of making many books there is no end; and much study is a weariness of the flesh.
B021C012V013	21	12	13	Let us hear the conclusion of the whole matter: Fear God, and keep his commandments: for this is the whole duty of man.
B021C012V014	21	12	14	For God shall bring every work into judgment, including every secret thing, whether it be good, or whether it be evil.
B022C001V001	22	1	1	The song of songs, which is Solomon's.
B022C001V002	22	1	2	Let him kiss me with the kisses of his mouth: for your love is better than wine.
B022C001V003	22	1	3	Because of the fragrance of your good ointments your name is as ointment poured forth, therefore do the virgins love you.
B022C001V004	22	1	4	Draw me, we will run after you: the king has brought me into his chambers: we will be glad and rejoice in you, we will remember your love more than wine: the upright love you.
B022C001V005	22	1	5	I am dark, but lovely, O you daughters of Jerusalem, as the tents of Kedar, as the curtains of Solomon.
B022C001V006	22	1	6	Look not upon me, because I am dark, because the sun has darkened me: my mother's children were angry with me; they made me the keeper of the vineyards; but my own vineyard have I not kept.
B022C001V007	22	1	7	Tell me, O you whom my soul loves, where you feed, where you make your flock to rest at noon: for why should I be as one that turns aside by the flocks of your companions?
B022C001V008	22	1	8	If you know not, O you fairest among women, go your way forth in the footsteps of the flock, and feed your kids beside the shepherds' tents.
B022C001V009	22	1	9	I have compared you, O my love, to a mare of Pharaoh's chariots.
B022C001V010	22	1	10	Your cheeks are lovely with rows of jewels, your neck with chains of gold.
B022C001V011	22	1	11	We will make you ornaments of gold with studs of silver.
B022C001V012	22	1	12	While the king sits at his table, my perfume sends forth its fragrance.
B022C001V013	22	1	13	A bundle of myrrh is my beloved unto me; he shall lie all night between my breasts.
B022C001V014	22	1	14	My beloved is unto me as a cluster of henna blossoms in the vineyards of Engedi.
B022C001V015	22	1	15	Behold, you are fair, my love; behold, you are fair; you have doves' eyes.
B022C001V016	22	1	16	Behold, you are handsome, my beloved, yea, pleasant: also our bed is green.
B022C001V017	22	1	17	The beams of our house are cedar, and our rafters of fir.
B022C002V001	22	2	1	I am the rose of Sharon, and the lily of the valleys.
B022C002V002	22	2	2	As the lily among thorns, so is my love among the daughters.
B022C002V003	22	2	3	As the apple tree among the trees of the wood, so is my beloved among the sons. I sat down under his shadow with great delight, and his fruit was sweet to my taste.
B022C002V004	22	2	4	He brought me to the banqueting house, and his banner over me was love.
B022C002V005	22	2	5	Sustain me with cakes of raisins, refresh me with apples: for I am sick with love.
B022C002V006	22	2	6	His left hand is under my head, and his right hand does embrace me.
B022C002V007	22	2	7	I charge you, O you daughters of Jerusalem, by the gazelles or by the hinds of the field, that you stir not up, nor awake love, till it pleases.
B022C002V008	22	2	8	The voice of my beloved! behold, he comes leaping upon the mountains, skipping upon the hills.
B022C002V009	22	2	9	My beloved is like a gazelle or a young stag: behold, he stands behind our wall, he looks forth through the windows, showing himself through the lattice.
B022C002V010	22	2	10	My beloved spoke, and said unto me, Rise up, my love, my fair one, and come away.
B022C002V011	22	2	11	For, lo, the winter is past, the rain is over and gone;
B022C002V012	22	2	12	The flowers appear on the earth; the time of singing has come, and the voice of the turtledove is heard in our land;
B022C002V013	22	2	13	The fig tree puts forth its green figs, and the vines with the tender grapes give a good smell. Arise, my love, my fair one, and come away.
B022C002V014	22	2	14	O my dove, in the clefts of the rock, in the secret places of the cliff, let me see your face, let me hear your voice; for sweet is your voice, and your countenance is lovely.
B022C002V015	22	2	15	Catch us the foxes, the little foxes, that spoil the vines: for our vines have tender grapes.
B022C002V016	22	2	16	My beloved is mine, and I am his: he feeds his flock among the lilies.
B022C002V017	22	2	17	Until the day breaks, and the shadows flee away, turn, my beloved, and be like a gazelle or a young stag upon the mountains of Bether.
B022C003V001	22	3	1	By night on my bed I sought him whom my soul loves: I sought him, but I found him not.
B022C003V002	22	3	2	I will rise now, and go about the city in the streets, and in the squares I will seek him whom my soul loves: I sought him, but I found him not.
B022C003V003	22	3	3	The watchmen that go about the city found me: to whom I said, Saw you him whom my soul loves?
B022C003V004	22	3	4	It was but a little after I passed by them, when I found him whom my soul loves: I held him, and would not let him go, until I had brought him into my mother's house, and into the chamber of her that conceived me.
B022C003V005	22	3	5	I charge you, O you daughters of Jerusalem, by the gazelles or by the hinds of the field, that you stir not up, nor awake my love, till it pleases.
B022C003V006	22	3	6	Who is this that comes out of the wilderness like pillars of smoke, perfumed with myrrh and frankincense, with all the fragrant powders of the merchant?
B022C003V007	22	3	7	Behold the couch, which is Solomon's; threescore valiant men are about it, of the valiant of Israel.
B022C003V008	22	3	8	They all hold swords, being expert in war: every man has his sword upon his thigh because of fear in the night.
B022C003V009	22	3	9	King Solomon made himself a chariot of the wood of Lebanon.
B022C003V010	22	3	10	He made its posts of silver, its base of gold, the covering of its seat of purple, its interior being paved with love, by the daughters of Jerusalem.
B022C003V011	22	3	11	Go forth, O you daughters of Zion, and behold king Solomon with the crown with which his mother crowned him on the day of his wedding, and on the day of the gladness of his heart.
B022C004V001	22	4	1	Behold, you are fair, my love; behold, you are fair; you have doves' eyes behind your veil: your hair is like a flock of goats, going down from mount Gilead.
B022C004V002	22	4	2	Your teeth are like a flock of sheep that are even shorn, which came up from the washing; every one of which bears twins, and none is barren among them.
B022C004V003	22	4	3	Your lips are like a thread of scarlet, and your mouth is lovely: your temples are like a piece of pomegranate behind your veil.
B022C004V004	22	4	4	Your neck is like the tower of David built for an armory, on which there hang a thousand shields, all shields of mighty men.
B022C004V005	22	4	5	Your two breasts are like two fawns, twins of a gazelle, which feed among the lilies.
B022C004V006	22	4	6	Until the day breaks, and the shadows flee away, I will go up to the mountain of myrrh, and to the hill of frankincense.
B022C004V007	22	4	7	You are all fair, my love; there is no spot in you.
B022C004V008	22	4	8	Come with me from Lebanon, my spouse, with me from Lebanon: look from the top of Amana, from the top of Shenir and Hermon, from the lions' dens, from the mountains of the leopards.
B022C004V009	22	4	9	You have ravished my heart, my sister, my spouse; you have ravished my heart with one look of your eyes, with one jewel of your necklace.
B022C004V010	22	4	10	How fair is your love, my sister, my spouse! how much better is your love than wine! and the fragrance of your perfume than all spices!
B022C004V011	22	4	11	Your lips, O my spouse, drop like the honeycomb: honey and milk are under your tongue; and the fragrance of your garments is like the fragrance of Lebanon.
B022C004V012	22	4	12	A garden enclosed is my sister, my spouse; a spring shut up, a fountain sealed.
B022C004V013	22	4	13	Your plants are an orchard of pomegranates, with pleasant fruits; henna, with spikenard,
B022C004V014	22	4	14	Spikenard and saffron; calamus and cinnamon, with all trees of frankincense; myrrh and aloes, with all the chief spices:
B022C004V015	22	4	15	A fountain of gardens, a well of living waters, and streams from Lebanon.
B022C004V016	22	4	16	Awake, O north wind; and come, you south; blow upon my garden, that its spices may flow out. Let my beloved come into his garden, and eat its pleasant fruits.
B022C005V001	22	5	1	I have come into my garden, my sister, my spouse: I have gathered my myrrh with my spice; I have eaten my honeycomb with my honey; I have drunk my wine with my milk: eat, O friends; drink, yea, drink abundantly, O beloved.
B022C005V002	22	5	2	I sleep, but my heart wakes: it is the voice of my beloved that knocks, saying, Open to me, my sister, my love, my dove, my perfect one: for my head is filled with dew, and my locks with the drops of the night.
B022C005V003	22	5	3	I have put off my robe; how shall I put it on? I have washed my feet; how could I soil them?
B022C005V004	22	5	4	My beloved put in his hand by the latch of the door, and my heart was thrilled for him.
B022C005V005	22	5	5	I rose up to open to my beloved; and my hands dripped with myrrh, and my fingers with sweet smelling myrrh, upon the handles of the lock.
B022C005V006	22	5	6	I opened to my beloved; but my beloved had withdrawn himself, and was gone: my soul failed when he spoke: I sought him, but I could not find him; I called him, but he gave me no answer.
B022C005V007	22	5	7	The watchmen that went about the city found me, they struck me, they wounded me; the keepers of the walls took away my veil from me.
B022C005V008	22	5	8	I charge you, O daughters of Jerusalem, if you find my beloved, that you tell him, that I am sick with love.
B022C005V009	22	5	9	What is your beloved more than another beloved, O you fairest among women? what is your beloved more than another beloved, that you so charge us?
B022C005V010	22	5	10	My beloved is white and ruddy, the chiefest among ten thousand.
B022C005V011	22	5	11	His head is as the most fine gold, his locks are wavy, and black as a raven.
B022C005V012	22	5	12	His eyes are like doves by the rivers of waters, washed with milk, and fitly set.
B022C005V013	22	5	13	His cheeks are like a bed of spices, like sweet flowers: his lips like lilies, dripping sweet smelling myrrh.
B022C005V014	22	5	14	His arms are as rounded gold set with beryl: his body is as carved ivory overlaid with sapphires.
B022C005V015	22	5	15	His legs are pillars of marble, set upon bases of fine gold: his countenance is as Lebanon, excellent as the cedars.
B022C005V016	22	5	16	His mouth is most sweet: yea, he is altogether lovely. This is my beloved, and this is my friend, O daughters of Jerusalem.
B022C006V001	22	6	1	Where has your beloved gone, O you fairest among women? where has your beloved turned aside? that we may seek him with you.
B022C006V002	22	6	2	My beloved has gone down into his garden, to the beds of spices, to feed his flock in the gardens, and to gather lilies.
B022C006V003	22	6	3	I am my beloved's, and my beloved is mine: he feeds his flock among the lilies.
B022C006V004	22	6	4	You are beautiful, O my love, as Tirzah, lovely as Jerusalem, awesome as an army with banners.
B022C006V005	22	6	5	Turn away your eyes from me, for they have overcome me: your hair is as a flock of goats going down from Gilead.
B022C006V006	22	6	6	Your teeth are as a flock of sheep which go up from the washing, every one bears twins, and there is not one barren among them.
B022C006V007	22	6	7	As a piece of a pomegranate are your temples behind your veil.
B022C006V008	22	6	8	There are threescore queens, and fourscore concubines, and virgins without number.
B022C006V009	22	6	9	My dove, my perfect one, is the only one; she is the only one of her mother, she is the favorite one of her that bore her. The daughters saw her, and blessed her; yea, the queens and the concubines, and they praised her.
B022C006V010	22	6	10	Who is she that looks forth as the morning, fair as the moon, clear as the sun, and awesome as an army with banners?
B022C006V011	22	6	11	I went down into the garden of nuts to see the blossoms of the valley, and to see whether the vine had budded, and the pomegranates were in bloom.
B022C006V012	22	6	12	Before I was aware, my desire had made me as the chariots of my noble people.
B022C006V013	22	6	13	Return, return, O Shulamite; return, return, that we may look upon you. Why will you look upon the Shulamite? As upon a dance before two armies?.
B022C007V001	22	7	1	How beautiful are your feet in sandals, O prince's daughter! the curves of your thighs are like jewels, the work of the hands of a skillful craftsman.
B022C007V002	22	7	2	Your navel is like a round goblet, which lacks not blended drink: your belly is like a heap of wheat set about with lilies.
B022C007V003	22	7	3	Your two breasts are like two fawns that are twins of a gazelle.
B022C007V004	22	7	4	Your neck is as a tower of ivory; your eyes like the pools of Heshbon, by the gate of Bathrabbim: your nose is as the tower of Lebanon which looks toward Damascus.
B022C007V005	22	7	5	Your head crowns you like Carmel, and the hair of your head is like purple; the king is held captive by your tresses.
B022C007V006	22	7	6	How fair and how pleasant are you, O love, for your delights!
B022C007V007	22	7	7	This your stature is like to a palm tree, and your breasts to its clusters.
B022C007V008	22	7	8	I said, I will go up to the palm tree, I will take hold of its branches: may also your breasts be as clusters of the vine, and the fragrance of your breath like apples;
B022C007V009	22	7	9	And the roof of your mouth like the best wine for my beloved, that goes down sweetly, flowing gently over lips and teeth.
B022C007V010	22	7	10	I am my beloved's, and his desire is toward me.
B022C007V011	22	7	11	Come, my beloved, let us go forth into the field; let us lodge in the villages.
B022C007V012	22	7	12	Let us get up early to the vineyards; let us see if the vine has budded, whether the grape blossoms have opened, and the pomegranates are in bloom: there will I give you my loves.
B022C007V013	22	7	13	The mandrakes give a fragrance, and at our gates are all manner of pleasant fruits, new and old, which I have laid up for you, O my beloved.
B022C008V001	22	8	1	O that you were as my brother, that nursed at the breasts of my mother! if I should find you outside, I would kiss you; yea, I would not be despised.
B022C008V002	22	8	2	I would lead you, and bring you into my mother's house, who had instructed me: I would cause you to drink of spiced wine of the juice of my pomegranate.
B022C008V003	22	8	3	His left hand is under my head, and his right hand embraces me.
B022C008V004	22	8	4	I charge you, O daughters of Jerusalem, that you stir not up, nor awake my love, until it pleases.
B022C008V005	22	8	5	Who is this that comes up from the wilderness, leaning upon her beloved? I awakened you under the apple tree: there your mother brought you forth: there she brought you forth that bore you.
B022C008V006	22	8	6	Set me as a seal upon your heart, as a seal upon your arm: for love is as strong as death; jealousy is cruel as the grave: its flames are flames of fire, a most vehement flame.
B022C008V007	22	8	7	Many waters cannot quench love, neither can the floods drown it: if a man would give all the wealth of his house for love, it would utterly be rejected.
B022C008V008	22	8	8	We have a little sister, and she has no breasts: what shall we do for our sister in the day when she shall be spoken for?
B022C008V009	22	8	9	If she is a wall, we will build upon her towers of silver: and if she is a door, we will enclose her with boards of cedar.
B022C008V010	22	8	10	I am a wall, and my breasts like towers: then was I in his eyes as one that found favor.
B022C008V011	22	8	11	Solomon had a vineyard at Baalhamon; he let out the vineyard unto keepers; everyone for its fruit was to bring a thousand pieces of silver.
B022C008V012	22	8	12	My vineyard, which is mine, is before me: you, O Solomon, must have a thousand, and those that tend its fruit two hundred.
B022C008V013	22	8	13	You that dwell in the gardens, the companions listen for your voice: let me hear it.
B022C008V014	22	8	14	Make haste, my beloved, and be like a gazelle or a young stag upon the mountains of spices.
B023C001V001	23	1	1	The vision of Isaiah the son of Amoz, which he saw concerning Judah and Jerusalem in the days of Uzziah, Jotham, Ahaz, and Hezekiah, kings of Judah.
B023C001V002	23	1	2	Hear, O heavens, and give ear, O earth: for the LORD has spoken, 
B023C001V003	23	1	3	
        
B023C001V004	23	1	4	Ah sinful nation, a people laden with iniquity, a descendant of evildoers, children that are corrupters: they have forsaken the LORD, they have provoked the Holy One of Israel unto anger, they have turned away backward.
B023C001V005	23	1	5	Why should you be stricken any more? you will revolt more and more: the whole head is sick, and the whole heart faint.
