B023C011V001	23	11	1	And there shall come forth a rod out of the stem of Jesse, and a Branch shall grow out of his roots:
B023C011V002	23	11	2	And the spirit of the LORD shall rest upon him, the spirit of wisdom and understanding, the spirit of counsel and might, the spirit of knowledge and of the fear of the LORD;
B023C011V003	23	11	3	And his delight shall be in the fear of the LORD: and he shall not judge after the sight of his eyes, neither reprove after the hearing of his ears:
B023C011V004	23	11	4	But with righteousness shall he judge the poor, and decide with equity for the meek of the earth: and he shall strike the earth with the rod of his mouth, and with the breath of his lips shall he slay the wicked.
B023C011V005	23	11	5	And righteousness shall be the belt of his loins, and faithfulness the belt of his waist.
