B023C014V001	23	14	1	For the LORD will have mercy on Jacob, and will yet choose Israel, and set them in their own land: and the strangers shall be joined with them, and they shall cling to the house of Jacob.
B023C014V002	23	14	2	And the people shall take them, and bring them to their place: and the house of Israel shall possess them in the land of the LORD for servants and handmaids: and they shall take them captive, whose captives they were; and they shall rule over their oppressors.
B023C014V003	23	14	3	And it shall come to pass in the day that the LORD shall give you rest from your sorrow, and from your fear, and from the hard bondage in which you were made to serve.
B023C014V004	23	14	4	That you shall take up this proverb against the king of Babylon, and say, How has the oppressor ceased! the golden city ceased!
B023C014V005	23	14	5	The LORD has broken the staff of the wicked, and the scepter of the rulers.
B023C014V006	23	14	6	He who struck the people in wrath with a continual stroke, he that ruled the nations in anger, is persecuted, and none hinders.
B023C014V007	23	14	7	The whole earth is at rest, and is quiet: they break forth into singing.
B023C014V008	23	14	8	Yea, the cypress trees rejoice at you, and the cedars of Lebanon, saying, Since you were laid low, no hewer has come up against us.
B023C014V009	23	14	9	Sheol from beneath is excited for you to meet you at your coming: it stirs up the dead for you, even all the chief ones of the earth; it has raised up from their thrones all the kings of the nations.
B023C014V010	23	14	10	They all shall speak and say unto you, have you also become weak as we? have you become like unto us?
B023C014V011	23	14	11	Your pomp is brought down to the grave, and the sound of your harps: the maggot is spread under you, and the worms cover you.
B023C014V012	23	14	12	How are you fallen from heaven, O Lucifer, son of the morning! how are you cut down to the ground, who did weaken the nations!
B023C014V013	23	14	13	For you have said in your heart, I will ascend into heaven, I will exalt my throne above the stars of God: I will sit also upon the mount of the congregation, in the farthest sides of the north:
B023C014V014	23	14	14	I will ascend above the heights of the clouds; I will be like the most High.
B023C014V015	23	14	15	Yet you shall be brought down to sheol, to the sides of the pit.
B023C014V016	23	14	16	They that see you shall gaze upon you, and consider you, saying, Is this the man that made the earth to tremble, that did shake kingdoms;
B023C014V017	23	14	17	That made the world like a wilderness, and destroyed its cities; that opened not the house of his prisoners?
B023C014V018	23	14	18	All the kings of the nations, even all of them, lie in glory, everyone in his own tomb.
B023C014V019	23	14	19	But you are cast out of your sepulcher like an abominable branch, and as the garment of those that are slain, thrust through with a sword, that go down to the stones of the pit; as a corpse trodden underfoot.
