B023C023V001	23	23	1	The burden concerning Tyre. Wail, you ships of Tarshish; for it is laid waste, so that there is no house, no entering in: from the land of Kittim it is revealed to them.
B023C023V002	23	23	2	Be still, you inhabitants of the coast; you whom the merchants of Sidon, that pass over the sea, have replenished.
B023C023V003	23	23	3	And by great waters the grain of Sihor, the harvest of the river, is her revenue; and she is a marketplace of nations.
B023C023V004	23	23	4	Be ashamed, O Sidon: for the sea has spoken, even the strength of the sea, saying, I travail not, nor bring forth children, neither do I nourish up young men, nor bring up virgins.
B023C023V005	23	23	5	As at the report concerning Egypt, so shall they be greatly pained at the report of Tyre.
B023C023V006	23	23	6	Pass over to Tarshish; wail, you inhabitants of the coast.
B023C023V007	23	23	7	Is this your joyous city, whose antiquity is of ancient days? her own feet shall carry her afar off to dwell.
B023C023V008	23	23	8	Who has taken this counsel against Tyre, the crowning city, whose merchants are princes, whose traders are the honorable of the earth?
B023C023V009	23	23	9	The LORD of hosts has purposed it, to defile the pride of all glory, and to bring into contempt all the honorable of the earth.
B023C023V010	23	23	10	Pass through your land as a river, O daughter of Tarshish: there is no more strength.
B023C023V011	23	23	11	He stretched out his hand over the sea, he shook the kingdoms: the LORD has given a commandment against Canaan, to destroy its strongholds.
B023C023V012	23	23	12	And he said, 
B023C023V013	23	23	13	Behold the land of the Chaldeans; this people was not, till the Assyrian founded it for them that dwell in the wilderness: they set up its towers, they raised up its palaces; and he brought it to ruin.
B023C023V014	23	23	14	Wail, you ships of Tarshish: for your strength is laid waste.
B023C023V015	23	23	15	And it shall come to pass in that day, that Tyre shall be forgotten seventy years, according to the days of one king: after the end of seventy years it shall happen to Tyre as in the song of a harlot.
B023C023V016	23	23	16	Take an harp, go about the city, you harlot that has been forgotten; make sweet melody, sing many songs, that you may be remembered.
B023C023V017	23	23	17	And it shall come to pass after the end of seventy years, that the LORD will visit Tyre, and she shall return to her hire, and shall commit fornication with all the kingdoms of the world upon the face of the earth.
B023C023V018	23	23	18	And her merchandise and her hire shall be dedicated to the LORD: it shall not be treasured nor laid up; for her merchandise shall be for them that dwell before the LORD, to eat sufficiently, and for fine clothing.
B023C024V001	23	24	1	Behold, the LORD makes the earth empty, and makes it waste, and turns it upside down, and scatters abroad its inhabitants.
B023C024V002	23	24	2	And it shall be, as with the people, so with the priest; as with the servant, so with his master; as with the maid, so with her mistress; as with the buyer, so with the seller; as with the lender, so with the borrower; as with the creditor, so with the debtor.
B023C024V003	23	24	3	The land shall be utterly emptied, and utterly plundered: for the LORD has spoken this word.
B023C024V004	23	24	4	The earth mourns and fades away, the world languishes and fades away, the haughty people of the earth do languish.
B023C024V005	23	24	5	The earth also is defiled under its inhabitants; because they have transgressed the laws, changed the ordinance, broken the everlasting covenant.
B023C024V006	23	24	6	Therefore has the curse devoured the earth, and they that dwell in it are desolate: therefore the inhabitants of the earth are burned, and few men left.
B023C024V007	23	24	7	The new wine mourns, the vine languishes, all the merry-hearted do sigh.
B023C024V008	23	24	8	The mirth of timbrels ceases, the noise of them that rejoice ends, the joy of the harp ceases.
B023C024V009	23	24	9	They shall not drink wine with a song; strong drink shall be bitter to them that drink it.
B023C024V010	23	24	10	The city of confusion is broken down: every house is shut up, that no man may come in.
B023C024V011	23	24	11	There is a crying for wine in the streets; all joy is darkened, the mirth of the land is gone.
B023C024V012	23	24	12	In the city is left desolation, and the gate is stricken with destruction.
B023C024V013	23	24	13	When thus it shall be in the midst of the land among the people, there shall be like the shaking of an olive tree, and like the gleaning grapes when the vintage is done.
B023C024V014	23	24	14	They shall lift up their voice, they shall sing for the majesty of the LORD, they shall cry aloud from the sea.
B023C024V015	23	24	15	Therefore glorify the LORD in the east, even the name of the LORD God of Israel in the coastlands of the sea.
B023C024V016	23	24	16	From the uttermost part of the earth have we heard songs, even glory to the righteous. But I said, My leanness, my leanness, woe unto me! the treacherous dealers have dealt treacherously; yea, the treacherous dealers have dealt very treacherously.
B023C024V017	23	24	17	Fear, and the pit, and the snare, are upon you, O inhabitant of the earth.
B023C024V018	23	24	18	And it shall come to pass, that he who flees from the noise of the fear shall fall into the pit; and he that comes up out of the midst of the pit shall be taken in the snare: for the windows from on high are open, and the foundations of the earth do shake.
B023C024V019	23	24	19	The earth is utterly broken down, the earth is torn asunder, the earth is shaken exceedingly.
B023C024V020	23	24	20	The earth shall reel to and fro like a drunkard, and shall be removed like a hut; and its transgression shall be heavy upon it; and it shall fall, and not rise again.
B023C024V021	23	24	21	And it shall come to pass in that day, that the LORD shall punish the host of the exalted ones that are on high, and the kings of the earth upon the earth.
B023C024V022	23	24	22	And they shall be gathered together, as prisoners are gathered in the pit, and shall be shut up in the prison, and after many days shall they be punished.
B023C024V023	23	24	23	Then the moon shall be confounded, and the sun ashamed, when the LORD of hosts shall reign in mount Zion, and in Jerusalem, and before his elders gloriously.
B023C025V001	23	25	1	O LORD, you are my God; I will exalt you, I will praise your name; for you have done wonderful things; your counsels of old are faithfulness and truth.
B023C025V002	23	25	2	For you have made of a city a heap; of a fortified city a ruin: a palace of strangers to be no city; it shall never be built.
B023C025V003	23	25	3	Therefore shall the strong people glorify you, the city of the terrible nations shall fear you.
B023C025V004	23	25	4	For you have been a strength to the poor, a strength to the needy in his distress, a refuge from the storm, a shadow from the heat, for the blast of the terrible ones is as a storm against the wall.
B023C025V005	23	25	5	You shall bring down the noise of aliens, as the heat in a dry place; even the heat with the shadow of a cloud: the song of the terrible ones shall be brought low.
B023C025V006	23	25	6	And on this mountain shall the LORD of hosts make unto all people a feast of rich things, a feast of wines on the lees, of fat things full of marrow, of wines on the lees well refined.
B023C025V007	23	25	7	And he will destroy in this mountain the face of the covering cast over all people, and the veil that is spread over all nations.
B023C025V008	23	25	8	He will swallow up death in victory; and the Lord GOD will wipe away tears from off all faces; and the rebuke of his people shall he take away from off all the earth: for the LORD has spoken it.
B023C025V009	23	25	9	And it shall be said in that day, Lo, this is our God; we have waited for him, and he will save us: this is the LORD; we have waited for him, we will be glad and rejoice in his salvation.
B023C025V010	23	25	10	For in this mountain shall the hand of the LORD rest, and Moab shall be trodden down under him, even as straw is trodden down for the refuse heap.
B023C025V011	23	25	11	And he shall spread forth his hands in the midst of them, as he that swims spreads forth his hands to swim: and he shall bring down their pride together with the trickery of their hands.
B023C025V012	23	25	12	And the fortress of the high fort of your walls shall he bring down, lay low, and bring to the ground, even to the dust.
B023C026V001	23	26	1	In that day shall this song be sung in the land of Judah; We have a strong city; salvation will God appoint for walls and bulwarks.
B023C026V002	23	26	2	Open the gates, that the righteous nation which keeps the truth may enter in.
B023C026V003	23	26	3	You will keep him in perfect peace, whose mind is stayed on you: because he trusts in you.
B023C026V004	23	26	4	Trust in the LORD forever: for in the LORD GOD is everlasting strength:
B023C026V005	23	26	5	For he brings down them that dwell on high; the lofty city, he lays it low; he lays it low, even to the ground; he brings it even to the dust.
B023C026V006	23	26	6	The foot shall tread it down, even the feet of the poor, and the steps of the needy.
B023C026V007	23	26	7	The way of the just is uprightness: you, most upright, do smooth the path of the just.
B023C026V008	23	26	8	Yea, in the way of your judgments, O LORD, have we waited for you; the desire of our soul is to your name, and to the remembrance of you.
B023C026V009	23	26	9	With my soul have I desired you in the night; yea, with my spirit within me will I seek you early: for when your judgments are in the earth, the inhabitants of the world will learn righteousness.
B023C026V010	23	26	10	Let favor be showed to the wicked, yet will he not learn righteousness: in the land of uprightness will he deal unjustly, and will not behold the majesty of the LORD.
B023C026V011	23	26	11	LORD, when your hand is lifted up, they will not see: but they shall see, and be ashamed for their envy of the people; yea, the fire of your enemies shall devour them.
B023C026V012	23	26	12	LORD, you will ordain peace for us: for you also have done all our works in us.
B023C026V013	23	26	13	O LORD our God, other lords besides you have had dominion over us: but by you only will we make mention of your name.
B023C026V014	23	26	14	They are dead, they shall not live; they are deceased, they shall not rise: therefore have you visited and destroyed them, and made all their memory to perish.
B023C026V015	23	26	15	You have increased the nation, O LORD, you have increased the nation: you are glorified: you have enlarged all the borders of the land.
B023C026V016	23	26	16	LORD, in trouble have they visited you, they poured out a prayer when your chastening was upon them.
B023C026V017	23	26	17	Like a woman with child, that draws near the time of her delivery, is in pain, and cries out in her pangs; so have we been in your sight, O LORD.
B023C026V018	23	26	18	We have been with child, we have been in pain, we have as it were given birth to wind; we have not accomplished any deliverance in the earth; neither have the inhabitants of the world fallen.
B023C026V019	23	26	19	Your dead men shall live, together with my dead body shall they arise. Awake and sing, you that dwell in dust: for your dew is like the dew of herbs, and the earth shall cast out the dead.
B023C026V020	23	26	20	Come, my people, enter you into your chambers, and shut your doors about you: hide yourself as it were for a little moment, until the indignation is past.
B023C026V021	23	26	21	For, behold, the LORD comes out of his place to punish the inhabitants of the earth for their iniquity: the earth also shall disclose her bloodshed, and shall no more cover her slain.
B023C027V001	23	27	1	In that day the LORD with his hard and great and strong sword shall punish leviathan the fleeing serpent, even leviathan that twisted serpent; and he shall slay the monster that is in the sea.
