B023C027V007	23	27	7	Has he struck him, as he struck those that struck him? or is he slain according to the slaughter of them that are slain by him?
B023C027V008	23	27	8	In measure, by sending it away, you will contend with it: he removes it with his fierce blast in the day of the east wind.
B023C027V009	23	27	9	By this therefore shall the iniquity of Jacob be purged; and this is all the fruit of taking away his sin; when he makes all the stones of the altar like chalkstones that are beaten to dust, the idol poles and incense altars shall not remain standing.
B023C027V010	23	27	10	Yet the fortified city shall be desolate, and the habitation forsaken, and left like a wilderness: there shall the calf feed, and there shall he lie down, and strip its branches.
B023C027V011	23	27	11	When its boughs are withered, they shall be broken off: the women come, and set them on fire: for it is a people of no understanding: therefore he that made them will not have mercy on them, and he that formed them will show them no favor.
B023C027V012	23	27	12	And it shall come to pass in that day, that the LORD shall thresh from the channel of the river to the stream of Egypt, and you shall be gathered one by one, O you children of Israel.
B023C027V013	23	27	13	And it shall come to pass in that day, that the great trumpet shall be blown, and they shall come who were ready to perish in the land of Assyria, and the outcasts in the land of Egypt, and shall worship the LORD in the holy mount at Jerusalem.
B023C028V001	23	28	1	Woe to the crown of pride, to the drunkards of Ephraim, whose glorious beauty is a fading flower, which is on the head of the rich valleys of them that are overcome with wine!
B023C028V002	23	28	2	Behold, the Lord has a mighty and strong one, which like a tempest of hail and a destroying storm, like a flood of mighty waters overflowing, shall cast down to the earth with his hand.
B023C028V003	23	28	3	The crown of pride, the drunkards of Ephraim, shall be trodden under foot:
B023C028V004	23	28	4	And the glorious beauty, which is on the head of the rich valley, shall be a fading flower, and as the early fruit before the summer; which when he that looks upon it sees it, while it is yet in his hand he eats it up.
B023C028V005	23	28	5	In that day shall the LORD of hosts be a crown of glory, and for a diadem of beauty, unto the remnant of his people,
B023C028V006	23	28	6	And for a spirit of justice to him that sits in judgment, and for strength to them that turn back the battle at the gate.
B023C028V007	23	28	7	But they also have erred through wine, and through strong drink are out of the way; the priest and the prophet have erred through strong drink, they are swallowed up by wine, they are out of the way through strong drink; they err in vision, they stumble in judgment.
B023C028V008	23	28	8	For all tables are full of vomit and filthiness, so that there is no place clean.
B023C028V009	23	28	9	Whom shall he teach knowledge? and whom shall he make to understand doctrine? them that are weaned from the milk, and taken from the breasts.
B023C028V010	23	28	10	For precept must be upon precept, precept upon precept; line upon line, line upon line; here a little, and there a little:
B023C028V011	23	28	11	For with stammering lips and another tongue will he speak to this people.
B023C028V012	23	28	12	To whom he said, 
B023C028V013	23	28	13	But the word of the LORD was unto them precept upon precept, precept upon precept; line upon line, line upon line; here a little, and there a little; that they might go, and fall backward, and be broken, and snared, and taken.
B023C028V014	23	28	14	Therefore hear the word of the LORD, you scornful men, that rule this people who are in Jerusalem.
B023C028V015	23	28	15	Because you have said, We have made a covenant with death, and with sheol are we at agreement; when the overflowing scourge shall pass through, it shall not come unto us: for we have made lies our refuge, and under falsehood have we hid ourselves:
B023C028V016	23	28	16	Therefore thus says the Lord GOD, 
B023C028V017	23	28	17	
        
B023C028V018	23	28	18	
        
B023C028V019	23	28	19	
        
B023C028V020	23	28	20	For the bed is shorter than a man can stretch himself upon: and the covering narrower than he can wrap himself in.
B023C028V021	23	28	21	For the LORD shall rise up as on mount Perazim, he shall be angry as in the valley of Gibeon, that he may do his work, his awesome work; and bring to pass his act, his alien act.
B023C028V022	23	28	22	Now therefore be not mockers, lest your bonds be made strong: for I have heard from the Lord GOD of hosts a destruction, even determined upon the whole earth.
B023C028V023	23	28	23	Give ear, and hear my voice; hearken, and hear my speech.
B023C028V024	23	28	24	Does the plowman keep plowing all day to sow? does he keep opening and breaking the clods of his ground?
B023C028V025	23	28	25	When he has made level the face of it, does he not sow the dill, and scatter the cummin, and plant the wheat in rows and the barley and the spelt in their places?
B023C028V026	23	28	26	For his God does instruct him aright, and does teach him.
B023C028V027	23	28	27	For the dill is not threshed with a threshing sledge, neither is a cart wheel rolled over the cummin; but the dill is beaten out with a stick, and the cummin with a rod.
B023C028V028	23	28	28	Bread grain is ground; therefore he will not forever be threshing it, nor break it with the wheel of his cart, nor crush it with his horsemen.
B023C028V029	23	28	29	This also comes forth from the LORD of hosts, who is wonderful in counsel, and excellent in wisdom.
B023C029V001	23	29	1	Woe to Ariel, to Ariel, the city where David dwelt! add year to year; let feasts run their cycle.
B023C029V002	23	29	2	Yet I will distress Ariel, and there shall be heaviness and sorrow: and it shall be unto me as Ariel.
B023C029V003	23	29	3	And I will encamp against you round about, and will lay siege against you with a mound, and I will raise siegeworks against you.
B023C029V004	23	29	4	And you shall be brought down, and shall speak out of the ground, and your speech shall be low out of the dust, and your voice shall be, as of one that is a medium, out of the ground, and your speech shall whisper out of the dust.
B023C029V005	23	29	5	Moreover the multitude of your foes shall be like small dust, and the multitude of the terrible ones shall be like chaff that passes away: yea, it shall be in an instant, suddenly.
B023C029V006	23	29	6	You shall be visited by the LORD of hosts with thunder, and with earthquake, and great noise, with storm and tempest, and the flame of devouring fire.
B023C029V007	23	29	7	And the multitude of all the nations that fight against Ariel, even all that fight against her and her fortress, and that distress her, shall be as a dream of a night vision.
B023C029V008	23	29	8	It shall even be as when a hungry man dreams, and, behold, he eats; but he awakes, and his soul is empty: or as when a thirsty man dreams, and, behold, he drinks; but he awakes, and, behold, he is faint, and his soul has appetite: so shall the multitude of all the nations be, that fight against mount Zion.
B023C029V009	23	29	9	Stop, and wonder; cry you out, and cry: they are drunken, but not with wine; they stagger, but not with strong drink.
B023C029V010	23	29	10	For the LORD has poured out upon you the spirit of deep sleep, and has closed your eyes: the prophets and your rulers, the seers has he covered.
B023C029V011	23	29	11	And the vision of all has become unto you as the words of a book that is sealed, which men deliver to one that is learned, saying, Read this, I pray you: and he says, I cannot; for it is sealed:
B023C029V012	23	29	12	And the book is delivered to him that is not learned, saying, Read this, I pray you: and he says, I am not learned.
B023C029V013	23	29	13	Therefore the Lord said, 
B023C029V014	23	29	14	
        
B023C029V015	23	29	15	Woe unto them that go the depths to hide their counsel from the LORD, and their works are in the dark, and they say, Who sees us? and who knows us?
B023C029V016	23	29	16	Surely your turning of things upside down shall be esteemed as the potter's clay: for shall the thing made say of him that made it, He made me not? or shall the thing formed say of him that formed it, He had no understanding?
B023C029V017	23	29	17	Is it not yet a very little while, and Lebanon shall be turned into a fruitful field, and the fruitful field shall be esteemed as a forest?
B023C029V018	23	29	18	And in that day shall the deaf hear the words of the book, and the eyes of the blind shall see out of obscurity, and out of darkness.
B023C029V019	23	29	19	The meek also shall increase their joy in the LORD, and the poor among men shall rejoice in the Holy One of Israel.
B023C029V020	23	29	20	For the ruthless one is brought to nothing, and the scoffer is consumed, and all that watch for iniquity are cut off:
B023C029V021	23	29	21	That make a man an offender for a word, and lay a snare for him that reproves in the gate, and turn aside the just for a thing of nothing.
