B023C037V037	23	37	37	So Sennacherib king of Assyria departed, and went and returned, and dwelt at Nineveh.
B023C037V038	23	37	38	And it came to pass, as he was worshiping in the house of Nisroch his god, that Adrammelech and Sharezer his sons struck him with the sword; and they escaped into the land of Ararat: and Esarhaddon his son reigned in his stead.
B023C038V001	23	38	1	In those days was Hezekiah sick unto death. And Isaiah the prophet the son of Amoz came unto him, and said unto him, Thus says the LORD, 
B023C038V002	23	38	2	Then Hezekiah turned his face toward the wall, and prayed unto the LORD,
B023C038V003	23	38	3	And said, Remember now, O LORD, I beseech you, how I have walked before you in truth and with a perfect heart, and have done that which is good in your sight. And Hezekiah wept bitterly.
B023C038V004	23	38	4	Then came the word of the LORD to Isaiah, saying,
B023C038V005	23	38	5	
        
B023C038V006	23	38	6	
        
B023C038V007	23	38	7	
        
B023C038V008	23	38	8	
        
B023C038V009	23	38	9	The writing of Hezekiah king of Judah, when he had been sick, and was recovered of his sickness:
B023C038V010	23	38	10	I said in the cutting off of my days, I shall go to the gates of the grave: I am deprived of the rest of my years.
B023C038V011	23	38	11	I said, I shall not see the LORD, even the LORD, in the land of the living: I shall behold man no more with the inhabitants of the world.
B023C038V012	23	38	12	My age is departed, and is removed from me as a shepherd's tent: I have cut off like a weaver my life: he will cut me off from the loom: from day even to night will you make an end of me.
B023C038V013	23	38	13	I considered till morning, that, as a lion, so will he break all my bones: from day even to night will you make an end of me.
B023C038V014	23	38	14	Like a crane or a swallow, so did I chatter: I did mourn as a dove: my eyes fail with looking upward: O LORD, I am oppressed; undertake for me.
B023C038V015	23	38	15	What shall I say? he has both spoken unto me, and he himself has done it: I shall go softly all my years in the bitterness of my soul.
B023C038V016	23	38	16	O Lord, by these things men live, and in all these things is the life of my spirit: so will you restore me, and make me to live.
B023C038V017	23	38	17	Behold, for my peace I had great bitterness: but you have in love to my soul delivered it from the pit of corruption: for you have cast all my sins behind your back.
B023C038V018	23	38	18	For the grave cannot praise you, death can not celebrate you: they that go down into the pit cannot hope for your truth.
B023C038V019	23	38	19	The living, the living, he shall praise you, as I do this day: the father to the children shall make known your truth.
B023C038V020	23	38	20	The LORD was ready to save me: therefore we will sing my songs to stringed instruments all the days of our life in the house of the LORD.
B023C038V021	23	38	21	For Isaiah had said, Let them take a lump of figs, and lay it for a plaster upon the boil, and he shall recover.
B023C038V022	23	38	22	Hezekiah also had said, What is the sign that I shall go up to the house of the LORD?
B023C039V001	23	39	1	At that time Merodachbaladan, the son of Baladan, king of Babylon, sent letters and a present to Hezekiah: for he had heard that he had been sick, and was recovered.
B023C039V002	23	39	2	And Hezekiah was pleased with them, and showed them the house of his treasures, the silver, and the gold, and the spices, and the precious ointment, and all the house of his armory, and all that was found in his treasures: there was nothing in his house, nor in all his dominion, that Hezekiah showed them not.
B023C039V003	23	39	3	Then came Isaiah the prophet unto king Hezekiah, and said unto him, What said these men? and from where came they unto you? And Hezekiah said, They have come from a far country unto me, even from Babylon.
B023C039V004	23	39	4	Then said he, What have they seen in your house? And Hezekiah answered, All that is in my house have they seen: there is nothing among my treasures that I have not shown them.
B023C039V005	23	39	5	Then said Isaiah to Hezekiah, Hear the word of the LORD of hosts:
B023C039V006	23	39	6	
        
B023C039V007	23	39	7	
        
B023C039V008	23	39	8	Then said Hezekiah to Isaiah, Good is the word of the LORD which you have spoken. He said moreover, For there shall be peace and truth in my days.
B023C040V001	23	40	1	
        
B023C040V002	23	40	2	
        
B023C040V003	23	40	3	The voice of him that cries in the wilderness, Prepare you the way of the LORD, make straight in the desert a highway for our God.
B023C040V004	23	40	4	Every valley shall be exalted, and every mountain and hill shall be made low: and the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough places smooth:
B023C040V005	23	40	5	And the glory of the LORD shall be revealed, and all flesh shall see it together: for the mouth of the LORD has spoken it.
B023C040V006	23	40	6	The voice said, Cry. And he said, What shall I cry? All flesh is grass, and all its loveliness is as the flower of the field:
B023C040V007	23	40	7	The grass withers, the flower fades: because the breath of the LORD blows upon it: surely the people are grass.
B023C040V008	23	40	8	The grass withers, the flower fades: but the word of our God shall stand forever.
B023C040V009	23	40	9	O Zion, that brings good tidings, get you up into the high mountain; O Jerusalem, that brings good tidings, lift up your voice with strength; lift it up, be not afraid; say unto the cities of Judah, Behold your God!
B023C040V010	23	40	10	Behold, the Lord GOD will come with strong hand, and his arm shall rule for him: behold, his reward is with him, and his work before him.
B023C040V011	23	40	11	He shall feed his flock like a shepherd: he shall gather the lambs with his arm, and carry them in his bosom, and shall gently lead those that are with young.
B023C040V012	23	40	12	Who has measured the waters in the hollow of his hand, and measured out heaven with the span, and known the dust of the earth in a measure, and weighed the mountains in scales, and the hills in a balance?
B023C040V013	23	40	13	Who has directed the Spirit of the LORD, or being his counselor has taught him?
B023C040V014	23	40	14	With whom took he counsel, and who instructed him, and taught him in the path of justice, and taught him knowledge, and showed to him the way of understanding?
B023C040V015	23	40	15	Behold, the nations are as a drop of a bucket, and are counted as the small dust of the balance: behold, he takes up the isles as fine dust.
B023C040V016	23	40	16	And Lebanon is not sufficient to burn, nor its beasts sufficient for a burnt offering.
B023C040V017	23	40	17	All nations before him are as nothing; and they are counted to him less than nothing, and worthless.
B023C040V018	23	40	18	To whom then will you liken God? or what likeness will you compare unto him?
B023C040V019	23	40	19	The workman melts a graven image, and the goldsmith spreads it over with gold, and casts silver chains.
B023C040V020	23	40	20	He that is so impoverished that he has no offering chooses a tree that will not rot; he seeks unto him a skillful workman to prepare a graven image, that shall not move.
B023C040V021	23	40	21	Have you not known? have you not heard? has it not been told you from the beginning? have you not understood from the foundations of the earth?
B023C040V022	23	40	22	It is he that sits upon the circle of the earth, and its inhabitants are as grasshoppers; that stretches out the heavens as a curtain, and spreads them out as a tent to dwell in:
B023C040V023	23	40	23	That brings the princes to nothing; he makes the judges of the earth as nothing.
B023C040V024	23	40	24	Yea, they shall not be planted; yea, they shall not be sown: yea, their stock shall not take root in the earth: and he shall also blow upon them, and they shall wither, and the whirlwind shall take them away as stubble.
B023C040V025	23	40	25	
        
B023C040V026	23	40	26	Lift up your eyes on high, and behold who has created these things, that brings out their host by number: he calls them all by names by the greatness of his might, for he is strong in power; not one is missing.
B023C040V027	23	40	27	Why say you, O Jacob, and speak, O Israel, My way is hidden from the LORD, and my right is passed over by my God?
B023C040V028	23	40	28	Have you not known? have you not heard, that the everlasting God, the LORD, the Creator of the ends of the earth, faints not, neither is weary? there is no searching of his understanding.
B023C040V029	23	40	29	He gives power to the faint; and to them that have no might he increases strength.
B023C040V030	23	40	30	Even the youths shall faint and be weary, and the young men shall utterly fall:
B023C040V031	23	40	31	But they that wait upon the LORD shall renew their strength; they shall mount up with wings as eagles; they shall run, and not be weary; and they shall walk, and not faint.
