B023C052V008	23	52	8	Your watchmen shall lift up their voice; with the voice together shall they sing: for they shall see eye to eye, when the LORD shall bring again Zion.
B023C052V009	23	52	9	Break forth into joy, sing together, you waste places of Jerusalem: for the LORD has comforted his people, he has redeemed Jerusalem.
B023C052V010	23	52	10	The LORD has made bare his holy arm in the eyes of all the nations; and all the ends of the earth shall see the salvation of our God.
B023C052V011	23	52	11	Depart you, depart you, go out from there, touch no unclean thing; go out of the midst of her; be you clean, that bear the vessels of the LORD.
B023C052V012	23	52	12	For you shall not go out with haste, nor go by flight: for the LORD will go before you; and the God of Israel will be your rear guard.
B023C052V013	23	52	13	Behold, my servant shall deal prudently, he shall be exalted and extolled, and be very high.
B023C052V014	23	52	14	As many were astonished at you; so his appearance was so marred more than any man, and his form more than the sons of men:
B023C052V015	23	52	15	So shall he startle many nations; the kings shall shut their mouths at him: for that which had not been told them shall they see; and that which they had not heard shall they consider.
B023C053V001	23	53	1	Who has believed our report? and to whom is the arm of the LORD revealed?
B023C053V002	23	53	2	For he shall grow up before him as a tender plant, and as a root out of a dry ground: he has no stately form nor splendor; and when we shall see him, there is no beauty that we should desire him.
B023C053V003	23	53	3	He is despised and rejected of men; a man of sorrows, and acquainted with grief: and we hid as it were our faces from him; he was despised, and we esteemed him not.
B023C053V004	23	53	4	Surely he has borne our griefs, and carried our sorrows: yet we did esteem him stricken, smitten by God, and afflicted.
B023C053V005	23	53	5	But he was wounded for our transgressions, he was bruised for our iniquities: the chastisement of our peace was upon him; and with his stripes we are healed.
B023C053V006	23	53	6	All we like sheep have gone astray; we have turned everyone to his own way; and the LORD has laid on him the iniquity of us all.
B023C053V007	23	53	7	He was oppressed, and he was afflicted, yet he opened not his mouth: he is brought as a lamb to the slaughter, and as a sheep before her shearers is dumb, so he opened not his mouth.
B023C053V008	23	53	8	He was taken from prison and from judgment: and who shall declare his generation? for he was cut off out of the land of the living: for the transgression of my people was he stricken.
B023C053V009	23	53	9	And he made his grave with the wicked, and with the rich in his death; because he had done no violence, neither was any deceit in his mouth.
B023C053V010	23	53	10	Yet it pleased the LORD to bruise him; he has put him to grief: when you shall make his soul an offering for sin, he shall see his offspring, he shall prolong his days, and the will of the LORD shall prosper in his hand.
B023C053V011	23	53	11	He shall see the travail of his soul, and shall be satisfied: by his knowledge shall my righteous servant justify many; for he shall bear their iniquities.
B023C053V012	23	53	12	Therefore will I divide him a portion with the great, and he shall divide the spoil with the strong; because he has poured out his soul unto death: and he was numbered with the transgressors; and he bore the sin of many, and made intercession for the transgressors.
