B024C052V010	24	52	10	And the king of Babylon killed the sons of Zedekiah before his eyes: he killed also all the princes of Judah in Riblah.
B024C052V011	24	52	11	Then he put out the eyes of Zedekiah; and the king of Babylon bound him in chains, and carried him to Babylon, and put him in prison till the day of his death.
B024C052V012	24	52	12	Now in the fifth month, in the tenth day of the month, which was the nineteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon, came Nebuzar-adan, captain of the guard, who served the king of Babylon, into Jerusalem,
B024C052V013	24	52	13	And burned the house of the LORD, and the kingâ€™s house; and all the houses of Jerusalem, and all the houses of the great men, burned he with fire:
B024C052V014	24	52	14	And all the army of the Chaldeans, that were with the captain of the guard, broke down all the walls of Jerusalem round about.
B024C052V015	24	52	15	Then Nebuzar-adan the captain of the guard carried away captive certain of the poor of the people, and the rest of the people that remained in the city, and those that had deserted, that deserted to the king of Babylon, and the rest of the multitude.
B024C052V016	24	52	16	But Nebuzar-adan the captain of the guard left certain of the poor of the land for vinedressers and for farmers.
B024C052V017	24	52	17	Also the pillars of bronze that were in the house of the LORD, and the stands, and the bronze sea that was in the house of the LORD, the Chaldeans broke, and carried all their bronze to Babylon.
B024C052V018	24	52	18	The pots also, and the shovels, and the wick trimmers, and the basins, and the spoons, and all the vessels of bronze with which they ministered, they took away.
B024C052V019	24	52	19	And the basins, and the firepans, and the bowls, and the pots, and the lamps, and the spoons, and the cups; that which was of gold, in gold, and that which was of silver, in silver, the captain of the guard took away.
B024C052V020	24	52	20	The two pillars, one sea, and twelve bronze bulls that were under the stands, which king Solomon had made in the house of the LORD: the bronze of all these vessels was beyond weight.
B024C052V021	24	52	21	And concerning the pillars, the height of one pillar was eighteen cubits; and bands of twelve cubits did compass it; and the thickness thereof was four fingers: it was hollow.
B024C052V022	24	52	22	And a capital of bronze was upon it; and the height of one capital was five cubits, with network and pomegranates upon the capitals round about, all of bronze. The second pillar also and the pomegranates were like unto these.
B024C052V023	24	52	23	And there were ninety and six pomegranates on a side; and all the pomegranates upon the network were a hundred round about.
B024C052V024	24	52	24	And the captain of the guard took Seraiah the chief priest, and Zephaniah the second priest, and the three keepers of the door:
B024C052V025	24	52	25	He took also out of the city a eunuch, who had charge of the men of war; and seven men of them that were the kingâ€™s counsel, who were found in the city; and the principal scribe of the army, who mustered the people of the land; and threescore men of the people of the land, that were found in the midst of the city.
B024C052V026	24	52	26	So Nebuzar-adan the captain of the guard took them, and brought them to the king of Babylon to Riblah.
B024C052V027	24	52	27	And the king of Babylon struck them, and put them to death in Riblah in the land of Hamath. Thus Judah was carried away captive out of its own land.
B024C052V028	24	52	28	These are the people whom Nebuchadnezzar carried away captive: in the seventh year three thousand Jews and three and twenty:
B024C052V029	24	52	29	In the eighteenth year of Nebuchadnezzar he carried away captive from Jerusalem eight hundred thirty and two persons:
B024C052V030	24	52	30	In the three and twentieth year of Nebuchadnezzar Nebuzar-adan the captain of the guard carried away captive of the Jews seven hundred forty and five persons: all the persons were four thousand and six hundred.
B024C052V031	24	52	31	And it came to pass in the seven and thirtieth year of the captivity of Jehoiachin king of Judah, in the twelfth month, in the five and twentieth day of the month, that Evil-merodach king of Babylon in the first year of his reign lifted up the head of Jehoiachin king of Judah, and brought him forth out of prison,
B024C052V032	24	52	32	And spoke kindly unto him, and set his throne above the throne of the kings that were with him in Babylon,
B024C052V033	24	52	33	And changed his prison garments: and he did continually eat bread before him all the days of his life.
B024C052V034	24	52	34	And for his provision, there was a regular ration given him from the king of Babylon, every day a portion until the day of his death, all the days of his life.
B025C001V001	25	1	1	How does the city sit lovely, that was full of people! how has she become as a widow! she that was great among the nations, and princess among the provinces, how has she become a slave!
B025C001V002	25	1	2	She weeps bitterly in the night, and her tears are on her cheeks: among all her lovers she has none to comfort her: all her friends have dealt treacherously with her, they have become her enemies.
B025C001V003	25	1	3	Judah has gone into captivity because of affliction, and because of great servitude: she dwells among the nations, she finds no rest: all her persecutors overtook her in her distress.
B025C001V004	25	1	4	The roads to Zion do mourn, because none come to the solemn feasts: all her gates are desolate: her priests sigh, her virgins are afflicted, and she is in bitterness.
B025C001V005	25	1	5	Her adversaries have become the chief, her enemies prosper; for the LORD has afflicted her for the multitude of her transgressions: her children have gone into captivity before the enemy.
B025C001V006	25	1	6	And from the daughter of Zion all her beauty has departed: her princes have become like harts that find no pasture, and they have gone without strength before the pursuer.
B025C001V007	25	1	7	Jerusalem remembered in the days of her affliction and of her miseries all her pleasant things that she had in the days of old, when her people fell into the hand of the enemy, and none did help her: the adversaries saw her, and did mock at her sabbaths.
B025C001V008	25	1	8	Jerusalem has grievously sinned; therefore she is removed: all that honored her despise her, because they have seen her nakedness: yea, she sighs, and turns away.
B025C001V009	25	1	9	Her filthiness is in her skirts; she remembers not her latter end; therefore she came down awesomely: she had no comforter. O LORD, behold my affliction: for the enemy has magnified himself.
B025C001V010	25	1	10	The adversary has spread out his hand over all her precious things: for she has seen that the nations entered into her sanctuary, whom you did command that they should not enter into your congregation.
B025C001V011	25	1	11	All her people sigh, they seek bread; they have given their treasures for food to relieve the soul: see, O LORD, and consider; for I have become despised.
B025C001V012	25	1	12	Is it nothing to you, all you that pass by? behold, and see if there be any sorrow like unto my sorrow, which is done unto me, which the LORD has afflicted me in the day of his fierce anger.
B025C001V013	25	1	13	From above has he sent fire into my bones, and it prevails against them: he has spread a net for my feet, he has turned me back: he has made me desolate and faint all the day.
B025C001V014	25	1	14	The yoke of my transgressions is bound by his hand: they are woven together, and come up upon my neck: he has made my strength to fall, the Lord has delivered me into their hands, from whom I am not able to rise up.
B025C001V015	25	1	15	The Lord has trodden under foot all my mighty men in the midst of me: he has called an assembly against me to crush my young men: the Lord has trodden the virgin, the daughter of Judah, as in a winepress.
B025C001V016	25	1	16	For these things I weep; my eye, my eye runs down with water, because the comforter that should relieve my soul is far from me: my children are desolate, because the enemy prevailed.
B025C001V017	25	1	17	Zion spreads forth her hands, and there is none to comfort her: the LORD has commanded concerning Jacob, that his adversaries should be round about him: Jerusalem is as an unclean thing among them.
B025C001V018	25	1	18	The LORD is righteous; for I have rebelled against his commandment: hear, I pray you, all people, and behold my sorrow: my virgins and my young men have gone into captivity.
B025C001V019	25	1	19	I called for my lovers, but they deceived me: my priests and my elders died in the city, while they sought their food to relieve their souls.
B025C001V020	25	1	20	Behold, O LORD; for I am in distress: my soul is troubled; my heart is turned within me; for I have grievously rebelled: abroad the sword bereaves, at home there is as death.
B025C001V021	25	1	21	They have heard that I sigh: there is none to comfort me: all my enemies have heard of my trouble; they are glad that you have done it: you will bring the day that you have announced, and they shall be like unto me.
B025C001V022	25	1	22	Let all their wickedness come before you; and do unto them, as you have done unto me for all my transgressions: for my sighs are many, and my heart is faint.
B025C002V001	25	2	1	How the Lord has covered the daughter of Zion with a cloud in his anger, and cast down from heaven unto the earth the beauty of Israel, and remembered not his footstool in the day of his anger!
B025C002V002	25	2	2	The Lord has swallowed up all the habitations of Jacob, and has not pitied: he has thrown down in his wrath the strongholds of the daughter of Judah; he has brought them down to the ground: he has polluted the kingdom and its princes.
B025C002V003	25	2	3	He has cut off in his fierce anger all the might of Israel: he has drawn back his right hand from before the enemy, and he burned against Jacob like a flaming fire, which devours round about.
B025C002V004	25	2	4	He has bent his bow like an enemy: he stood with his right hand as an adversary, and has slain all that were pleasant to the eye in the tent of the daughter of Zion: he poured out his fury like fire.
B025C002V005	25	2	5	The Lord was as an enemy: he has swallowed up Israel, he has swallowed up all her palaces: he has destroyed his strongholds, and has increased in the daughter of Judah mourning and lamentation.
B025C002V006	25	2	6	And he has violently taken away his tabernacle, as if it were a garden: he has destroyed his places of the assembly: the LORD has caused the solemn feasts and sabbaths to be forgotten in Zion, and has despised in the indignation of his anger the king and the priest.
B025C002V007	25	2	7	The Lord has cast off his altar, he has abhorred his sanctuary, he has given up into the hand of the enemy the walls of her palaces; they have made a noise in the house of the LORD, as in the day of a solemn feast.
B025C002V008	25	2	8	The LORD has purposed to destroy the wall of the daughter of Zion: he has stretched out a line, he has not withdrawn his hand from destroying: therefore he made the rampart and the wall to lament; they languished together.
B025C002V009	25	2	9	Her gates are sunk into the ground; he has destroyed and broken her bars: her king and her princes are among the nations: the law is no more; her prophets also find no vision from the LORD.
B025C002V010	25	2	10	The elders of the daughter of Zion sit upon the ground, and keep silence: they have cast up dust upon their heads; they have girded themselves with sackcloth: the virgins of Jerusalem hang down their heads to the ground.
B025C002V011	25	2	11	My eyes do fail with tears, my soul is troubled, my heart is poured upon the earth, for the destruction of the daughter of my people; because the children and the infants faint in the streets of the city.
B025C002V012	25	2	12	They say to their mothers, Where is grain and wine? when they faint as the wounded in the streets of the city, when their soul was poured out into their mothers' bosom.
B025C002V013	25	2	13	What thing shall I take to witness for you? what thing shall I liken to you, O daughter of Jerusalem? what shall I equal to you, that I may comfort you, O virgin daughter of Zion? for your run is vast as the sea: who can heal you?
B025C002V014	25	2	14	Your prophets have seen vain and foolish things for you: and they have not uncovered your iniquity, to turn away your captivity; but have given you false oracles and causes of banishment.
B025C002V015	25	2	15	All that pass by clap their hands at you; they hiss and wag their head at the daughter of Jerusalem, saying, Is this the city that men call The perfection of beauty, The joy of the whole earth?
B025C002V016	25	2	16	All your enemies have opened their mouth against you: they hiss and gnash the teeth: they say, We have swallowed her up: certainly this is the day that we looked for; we have found, we have seen it.
B025C002V017	25	2	17	The LORD has done that which he had purposed; he has fulfilled his word that he had commanded in the days of old: he has thrown down, and has not pitied: and he has caused your enemy to rejoice over you, he has set up the might of your adversaries.
B025C002V018	25	2	18	Their heart cried unto the Lord, O wall of the daughter of Zion, let tears run down like a river day and night: give yourself no relief; let not your eyes rest.
B025C002V019	25	2	19	Arise, cry out in the night: in the beginning of the watches pour out your heart like water before the face of the Lord: lift up your hands toward him for the life of your young children, that faint for hunger at the head of every street.
B025C002V020	25	2	20	Behold, O LORD, and consider to whom you have done this. Shall the women eat their offspring, the children of their tender care? shall the priest and the prophet be slain in the sanctuary of the Lord?
B025C002V021	25	2	21	The young and the old lie on the ground in the streets: my virgins and my young men have fallen by the sword; you have slain them in the day of your anger; you have killed, and not pitied.
B025C002V022	25	2	22	You have called as in a solemn day my terrors round about, so that in the day of the LORD'S anger none escaped nor remained: those that I have cared for and brought up has my enemy consumed.
B025C003V001	25	3	1	I am the man that has seen affliction by the rod of his wrath.
B025C003V002	25	3	2	He has led me, and brought me into darkness, but not into light.
B025C003V003	25	3	3	Surely against me has he turned; he turns his hand against me all the day.
B025C003V004	25	3	4	My flesh and my skin has he made old: he has broken my bones.
B025C003V005	25	3	5	He has besieged me, and surrounded me with gall and travail.
B025C003V006	25	3	6	He has set me in dark places, like they that are long dead.
B025C003V007	25	3	7	He has hedged me in, that I cannot get out: he has made my chain heavy.
B025C003V008	25	3	8	Also when I cry and shout, he shuts out my prayer.
B025C003V009	25	3	9	He has enclosed my ways with hewn stone, he has made my paths crooked.
B025C003V010	25	3	10	He was unto me as a bear lying in wait, and as a lion in secret places.
B025C003V011	25	3	11	He has turned aside my ways, and pulled me in pieces: he has made me desolate.
B025C003V012	25	3	12	He has bent his bow, and set me as a mark for the arrow.
B025C003V013	25	3	13	He has caused the arrows of his quiver to enter into my heart.
B025C003V014	25	3	14	I was a derision to all my people; and their song all the day.
B025C003V015	25	3	15	He has filled me with bitterness, he has made me drunk with wormwood.
B025C003V016	25	3	16	He has also broken my teeth with gravel stones, he has covered me with ashes.
B025C003V017	25	3	17	And you have removed my soul far off from peace: I forgot prosperity.
B025C003V018	25	3	18	And I said, My strength and my hope has perished from the LORD:
B025C003V019	25	3	19	Remembering my affliction and my misery, the wormwood and the gall.
B025C003V020	25	3	20	My soul has them still in remembrance, and is humbled in me.
B025C003V021	25	3	21	This I recall to my mind, therefore have I hope.
B025C003V022	25	3	22	It is of the LORD'S mercies that we are not consumed, because his compassions fail not.
B025C003V023	25	3	23	They are new every morning: great is your faithfulness.
B025C003V024	25	3	24	The LORD is my portion, says my soul; therefore will I hope in him.
B025C003V025	25	3	25	The LORD is good unto them that wait for him, to the soul that seeks him.
B025C003V026	25	3	26	It is good that a man should both hope and quietly wait for the salvation of the LORD.
B025C003V027	25	3	27	It is good for a man that he bear the yoke in his youth.
B025C003V028	25	3	28	He sits alone and keeps silence, because he has borne it upon him.
B025C003V029	25	3	29	He puts his mouth in the dust; if so be there may be hope.
B025C003V030	25	3	30	He gives his cheek to him that strikes him: he is filled full with reproach.
B025C003V031	25	3	31	For the Lord will not cast off forever:
B025C003V032	25	3	32	But though he cause grief, yet will he have compassion according to the multitude of his mercies.
B025C003V033	25	3	33	For he does not afflict willingly nor grieve the children of men.
B025C003V034	25	3	34	To crush under his feet all the prisoners of the earth,
B025C003V035	25	3	35	To turn aside the right of a man before the face of the most High,
B025C003V036	25	3	36	To subvert a man in his cause, the Lord approves not.
B025C003V037	25	3	37	Who is he that says, and it comes to pass, when the Lord commands it not?
B025C003V038	25	3	38	Out of the mouth of the most High proceeds not evil and good?
B025C003V039	25	3	39	Why does a living man complain, a man for the punishment of his sins?
B025C003V040	25	3	40	Let us search and examine our ways, and turn again to the LORD.
B025C003V041	25	3	41	Let us lift up our heart with our hands unto God in the heavens.
B025C003V042	25	3	42	We have transgressed and have rebelled: you have not pardoned.
B025C003V043	25	3	43	You have covered with anger, and persecuted us: you have slain, you have not pitied.
B025C003V044	25	3	44	You have covered yourself with a cloud, that our prayer should not pass through.
B025C003V045	25	3	45	You have made us as the offscouring and refuse in the midst of the people.
B025C003V046	25	3	46	All our enemies have opened their mouths against us.
B025C003V047	25	3	47	Fear and a snare has come upon us, desolation and destruction.
B025C003V048	25	3	48	My eye runs down with rivers of water for the destruction of the daughter of my people.
B025C003V049	25	3	49	My eye flows down, and ceases not, without any intermission,
B025C003V050	25	3	50	Till the LORD looks down, and beholds from heaven.
B025C003V051	25	3	51	My eye affects my heart because of all the daughters of my city.
B025C003V052	25	3	52	My enemies chased me hard, like a bird, without cause.
B025C003V053	25	3	53	They have cut off my life in the dungeon, and cast a stone upon me.
B025C003V054	25	3	54	Waters flowed over my head; then I said, I am cut off.
B025C003V055	25	3	55	I called upon your name, O LORD, out of the lowest dungeon.
B025C003V056	25	3	56	You have heard my voice: hide not your ear at my breathing, at my cry.
B025C003V057	25	3	57	You drew near in the day that I called upon you: you said, 
B025C003V058	25	3	58	O Lord, you have pleaded the causes of my soul; you have redeemed my life.
B025C003V059	25	3	59	O LORD, you have seen my wrong: judge you my cause.
B025C003V060	25	3	60	You have seen all their vengeance and all their plots against me.
B025C003V061	25	3	61	You have heard their reproach, O LORD, and all their plots against me;
B025C003V062	25	3	62	The lips of those that rose up against me, and their whispering against me all the day.
B025C003V063	25	3	63	Behold their sitting down, and their rising up; I am their music.
B025C003V064	25	3	64	Render unto them a recompense, O LORD, according to the work of their hands.
B025C003V065	25	3	65	Give them sorrow of heart, your curse unto them.
B025C003V066	25	3	66	Persecute and destroy them in anger from under the heavens of the LORD.
B025C004V001	25	4	1	How has the gold become dim! how has the most fine gold changed! the stones of the sanctuary are poured out at the head of every street.
B025C004V002	25	4	2	The precious sons of Zion, comparable to fine gold, how are they esteemed as earthen pitchers, the work of the hands of the potter!
B025C004V003	25	4	3	Even the jackals draw out the breast, they nurse their young ones: the daughter of my people has become cruel, like the ostriches in the wilderness.
B025C004V004	25	4	4	The tongue of the nursing child clings to the roof of his mouth for thirst: the young children ask bread, and no man breaks it unto them.
B025C004V005	25	4	5	They that did eat delicacies are desolate in the streets: they that were brought up in scarlet embrace ash heaps.
B025C004V006	25	4	6	For the punishment of the iniquity of the daughter of my people is greater than the punishment of the sin of Sodom, that was overthrown as in a moment, with no hands laid on her.
B025C004V007	25	4	7	Her princes were purer than snow, they were whiter than milk, they were more ruddy in body than rubies, their appearance was of sapphire:
B025C004V008	25	4	8	Their appearance is now blacker than coal; they are not known in the streets: their skin cleaves to their bones; it is withered, it has become like a dry stick.
B025C004V009	25	4	9	They that are slain with the sword are better than they that are slain with hunger: for these pine away, stricken through for lack of the fruits of the field.
B025C004V010	25	4	10	The hands of the compassionate women have boiled their own children: they were their food in the destruction of the daughter of my people.
B025C004V011	25	4	11	The LORD has accomplished his fury; he has poured out his fierce anger, and has kindled a fire in Zion, and it has devoured its foundations.
B025C004V012	25	4	12	The kings of the earth, and all the inhabitants of the world, would not have believed that the adversary and the enemy should have entered into the gates of Jerusalem.
B025C004V013	25	4	13	For the sins of her prophets, and the iniquities of her priests, that have shed the blood of the just in the midst of her,
B025C004V014	25	4	14	They have wandered as blind men in the streets, they have polluted themselves with blood, so that men could not touch their garments.
B025C004V015	25	4	15	They cried unto them, Depart; it is unclean; depart, depart, touch not: when they fled away and wandered, they said among the nations, They shall no more sojourn there.
B025C004V016	25	4	16	The anger of the LORD has scattered them; he will no longer regard them: they respected not the persons of the priests, they favored not the elders.
B025C004V017	25	4	17	As for us, our eyes as yet failed, watching for our vain help: in our watching we have watched for a nation that could not save us.
B025C004V018	25	4	18	They hunt our steps, so that we cannot go in our streets: our end is near, our days are fulfilled; for our end has come.
B025C004V019	25	4	19	Our persecutors are swifter than the eagles of the heaven: they pursued us upon the mountains, they laid wait for us in the wilderness.
B025C004V020	25	4	20	The breath of our nostrils, the anointed of the LORD, was taken in their pits, of whom we said, Under his shadow we shall live among the nations.
B025C004V021	25	4	21	Rejoice and be glad, O daughter of Edom, that dwells in the land of Uz; the cup also shall pass through unto you: you shall be drunk, and shall make yourself naked.
B025C004V022	25	4	22	The punishment of your iniquity is accomplished, O daughter of Zion; he will no more carry you away into captivity: he will punish your iniquity, O daughter of Edom; he will uncover your sins.
B025C005V001	25	5	1	Remember, O LORD, what is come upon us: consider, and behold our reproach.
B025C005V002	25	5	2	Our inheritance is turned to strangers, our houses to aliens.
B025C005V003	25	5	3	We are orphans and fatherless, our mothers are as widows.
B025C005V004	25	5	4	We have drunk our water at a price; our wood is sold unto us.
B025C005V005	25	5	5	Our necks are under persecution: we labor, and have no rest.
B025C005V006	25	5	6	We have given the hand to the Egyptians, and to the Assyrians, to be satisfied with bread.
B025C005V007	25	5	7	Our fathers have sinned, and are not; and we have borne their iniquities.
B025C005V008	25	5	8	Servants have ruled over us: there is none that does deliver us out of their hand.
B025C005V009	25	5	9	We got our bread at the peril of our lives because of the sword in the wilderness.
B025C005V010	25	5	10	Our skin was black like an oven because of the terrible famine.
B025C005V011	25	5	11	They ravished the women in Zion, and the maidens in the cities of Judah.
B025C005V012	25	5	12	Princes were hung up by their hands: the faces of elders were not honored.
B025C005V013	25	5	13	They took the young men to grind, and the children stagger under loads of wood.
B025C005V014	25	5	14	The elders have ceased from the gate, the young men from their music.
B025C005V015	25	5	15	The joy of our heart has ceased; our dance has turned into mourning.
B025C005V016	25	5	16	The crown has fallen from our head: woe unto us, that we have sinned!
B025C005V017	25	5	17	For this our heart is faint; for these things our eyes are dim.
B025C005V018	25	5	18	Because of the mountain of Zion, which is desolate, the foxes walk upon it.
B025C005V019	25	5	19	You, O LORD, remain forever; your throne from generation to generation.
B025C005V020	25	5	20	Why do you forget us forever, and forsake us for so long a time?
B025C005V021	25	5	21	Turn us back to you, O LORD, and we shall be turned; renew our days as of old.
B025C005V022	25	5	22	But you have utterly rejected us; you are very angry against us.
B026C001V001	26	1	1	Now it came to pass in the thirtieth year, in the fourth month, in the fifth day of the month, as I was among the captives by the river of Chebar, that the heavens were opened, and I saw visions of God.
B026C001V002	26	1	2	On the fifth day of the month, which was the fifth year of king Jehoiachinâ€™s captivity,
B026C001V003	26	1	3	The word of the LORD came expressly unto Ezekiel the priest, the son of Buzi, in the land of the Chaldeans by the river Chebar; and the hand of the LORD was there upon him.
B026C001V004	26	1	4	And I looked, and, behold, a whirlwind came out of the north, a great cloud, and a fire engulfing itself, and a brightness was about it, and out of its midst as the color of amber, out of the midst of the fire.
B026C001V005	26	1	5	Also out of its midst came the likeness of four living creatures. And this was their appearance; they had the likeness of a man.
B026C001V006	26	1	6	And each one had four faces, and each one had four wings.
