B026C046V019	26	46	19	After that he brought me through the entrance, which was at the side of the gate, into the holy chambers of the priests, which faced toward the north: and, behold, there was a place on the two sides westward.
B026C046V020	26	46	20	Then said he unto me, This is the place where the priests shall boil the trespass offering and the sin offering, where they shall bake the grain offering; that they bear them not out into the outer court, to sanctify the people.
B026C046V021	26	46	21	Then he brought me forth into the outer court, and caused me to pass by the four corners of the court; and, behold, in every corner of the court there was a court.
B026C046V022	26	46	22	In the four corners of the court there were courts joined of forty cubits long and thirty wide: these four corners were of the same measure.
B026C046V023	26	46	23	And there was a row of building stones all around in them, all around the four, and it was made with boiling places under the rows of stones all around.
B026C046V024	26	46	24	Then said he unto me, These are the places of them that boil, where the ministers of the house shall boil the sacrifices of the people.
B026C047V001	26	47	1	Afterward he brought me again unto the door of the house; and, behold, waters issued out from under the threshold of the house eastward: for the front of the house faced toward the east, and the waters came down from under the right side of the house, at the south side of the altar.
B026C047V002	26	47	2	Then he brought me out by way of the north gate, and led me around the way outside to the outer gate by the way that faces eastward; and, behold, there ran out waters on the right side.
B026C047V003	26	47	3	And when the man that had the line in his hand went forth eastward, he measured a thousand cubits, and he brought me through the waters; the waters were up to the ankles.
B026C047V004	26	47	4	Again he measured a thousand, and brought me through the waters; the waters were to the knees. Again he measured a thousand, and brought me through; the waters were to the waist.
B026C047V005	26	47	5	Afterward he measured a thousand; and it was a river that I could not pass over: for the waters were risen, waters to swim in, a river that could not be passed over.
B026C047V006	26	47	6	And he said unto me, Son of man, have you seen this? Then he brought me, and caused me to return to the bank of the river.
B026C047V007	26	47	7	Now when I had returned, behold, at the bank of the river were very many trees on the one side and on the other.
B026C047V008	26	47	8	Then he said unto me, These waters issue out toward the east country, and go down into the desert, and go into the sea: which being brought forth into the sea, the waters of the sea shall be healed.
B026C047V009	26	47	9	And it shall come to pass, that everything that lives, which moves, wherever the rivers shall come, shall live: and there shall be a very great multitude of fish, because these waters shall come there: for they shall be healed; and everything shall live where the river comes.
B026C047V010	26	47	10	And it shall come to pass, that the fishermen shall stand upon it from En-gedi even unto En-eglaim; there shall be a place to spread forth nets; their fish shall be the same kinds as the fish of the great sea, exceedingly many.
B026C047V011	26	47	11	But its swamps and its marshes shall not be healed; they shall be given over to salt.
B026C047V012	26	47	12	And by the river upon its bank, on this side and on that side, shall grow all trees for food, whose leaf shall not fade, neither shall its fruit be consumed: it shall bring forth new fruit according to its months, because the waters flowed out of the sanctuary: and its fruit shall be for food, and its leaf for medicine.
B026C047V013	26	47	13	Thus says the Lord GOD; 
