B027C001V001	27	1	1	In the third year of the reign of Jehoiakim king of Judah came Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon unto Jerusalem, and besieged it.
B027C001V002	27	1	2	And the Lord gave Jehoiakim king of Judah into his hand, with part of the vessels of the house of God: which he carried into the land of Shinar to the house of his god; and he brought the vessels into the treasure house of his god.
B027C001V003	27	1	3	And the king spoke unto Ashpenaz the master of his eunuchs, that he should bring certain of the children of Israel, and of the king's descendants, and of the princes;
B027C001V004	27	1	4	Young men in whom was no blemish, but handsome, and skilful in all wisdom, and gifted in knowledge, and understanding science, and such as had ability in them to stand in the king's palace, and whom they might teach the learning and the language of the Chaldeans.
B027C001V005	27	1	5	And the king appointed them a daily provision of the king's food, and of the wine which he drank: so training them three years, that at the end of that time they might stand before the king.
B027C001V006	27	1	6	Now among these were of the children of Judah, Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah:
B027C001V007	27	1	7	Unto whom the prince of the eunuchs gave names: for he gave unto Daniel the name of Belteshazzar; and to Hananiah, of Shadrach; and to Mishael, of Meshach; and to Azariah, of Abednego.
B027C001V008	27	1	8	But Daniel purposed in his heart that he would not defile himself with the portion of the king's food, nor with the wine which he drank: therefore he requested of the prince of the eunuchs that he might not defile himself.
B027C001V009	27	1	9	Now God had brought Daniel into favor and kindness with the prince of the eunuchs.
B027C001V010	27	1	10	And the prince of the eunuchs said unto Daniel, I fear my lord the king, who has appointed your food and your drink: for why should he see your faces worse looking than the young men who are of your age? then shall you make me endanger my head to the king.
B027C001V011	27	1	11	Then said Daniel to Melzar, whom the prince of the eunuchs had set over Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah,
B027C001V012	27	1	12	Test your servants, I beseech you, ten days; and let them give us vegetables to eat, and water to drink.
B027C001V013	27	1	13	Then let our countenances be looked upon before you, and the countenance of the young men that eat of the portion of the king's food: and as you see fit, deal with your servants.
B027C001V014	27	1	14	So he consented to them in this matter, and tested them ten days.
B027C001V015	27	1	15	And at the end of ten days their countenances appeared better and fatter in flesh than all the young men who did eat the portion of the king's food.
B027C001V016	27	1	16	Thus Melzar took away the portion of their food, and the wine that they should drink; and gave them vegetables.
B027C001V017	27	1	17	As for these four young men, God gave them knowledge and skill in all learning and wisdom: and Daniel had understanding in all visions and dreams.
B027C001V018	27	1	18	Now at the end of the days that the king had said he should bring them in, then the prince of the eunuchs brought them in before Nebuchadnezzar.
B027C001V019	27	1	19	And the king spoke with them; and among them all was found none like Daniel, Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah: therefore stood they before the king.
B027C001V020	27	1	20	And in all matters of wisdom and understanding, that the king inquired of them, he found them ten times better than all the magicians and astrologers that were in all his realm.
B027C001V021	27	1	21	And Daniel continued even unto the first year of king Cyrus.
B027C002V001	27	2	1	And in the second year of the reign of Nebuchadnezzar Nebuchadnezzar dreamed dreams, by which his spirit was troubled, and his sleep went from him.
B027C002V002	27	2	2	Then the king commanded to call the magicians, and the astrologers, and the sorcerers, and the Chaldeans, to show the king his dreams. So they came and stood before the king.
B027C002V003	27	2	3	And the king said unto them, I have dreamed a dream, and my spirit was troubled to know the dream.
B027C002V004	27	2	4	Then spoke the Chaldeans to the king in Aramaic, O king, live forever: tell your servants the dream, and we will show the interpretation.
B027C002V005	27	2	5	The king answered and said to the Chaldeans, The thing is gone from me: if you will not make known unto me the dream, with its interpretation, you shall be cut in pieces, and your houses shall be made an ash heap.
B027C002V006	27	2	6	But if you show the dream, and its interpretation, you shall receive of me gifts and rewards and great honor: therefore show me the dream, and its interpretation.
B027C002V007	27	2	7	They answered again and said, Let the king tell his servants the dream, and we will show the interpretation of it.
B027C002V008	27	2	8	The king answered and said, I know of certainty that you would gain the time, because you see the thing is gone from me.
B027C002V009	27	2	9	But if you will not make known unto me the dream, there is but one decree for you: for you have prepared lying and corrupt words to speak before me, till the time be changed: therefore tell me the dream, and I shall know that you can show me its interpretation.
B027C002V010	27	2	10	The Chaldeans answered before the king, and said, There is not a man upon the earth that can tell the king's matter: therefore there is no king, lord, nor ruler, that asked such things at any magician, or astrologer, or Chaldean.
B027C002V011	27	2	11	And it is a rare thing that the king requires, and there is none other that can reveal it before the king, except the gods, whose dwelling is not with flesh.
B027C002V012	27	2	12	For this cause the king was angry and very furious, and commanded to destroy all the wise men of Babylon.
B027C002V013	27	2	13	And the decree went forth that the wise men should be slain; and they sought Daniel and his fellows to be slain.
B027C002V014	27	2	14	Then Daniel answered with counsel and wisdom to Arioch the captain of the king's guard, who had gone forth to slay the wise men of Babylon:
B027C002V015	27	2	15	He answered and said to Arioch the king's captain, Why is the decree so hasty from the king? Then Arioch made the thing known to Daniel.
B027C002V016	27	2	16	Then Daniel went in, and desired of the king that he would give him time, and that he would show the king the interpretation.
B027C002V017	27	2	17	Then Daniel went to his house, and made the thing known to Hananiah, Mishael, and Azariah, his companions:
B027C002V018	27	2	18	That they would desire mercies of the God of heaven concerning this secret; that Daniel and his fellows should not perish with the rest of the wise men of Babylon.
B027C002V019	27	2	19	Then was the secret revealed unto Daniel in a night vision. Then Daniel blessed the God of heaven.
B027C002V020	27	2	20	Daniel answered and said, Blessed be the name of God forever and ever: for wisdom and might are his:
B027C002V021	27	2	21	And he changes the times and the seasons: he removes kings, and sets up kings: he gives wisdom unto the wise, and knowledge to them that know understanding:
B027C002V022	27	2	22	He reveals the deep and secret things: he knows what is in the darkness, and the light dwells with him.
B027C002V023	27	2	23	I thank you, and praise you, O God of my fathers, who has given me wisdom and might, and has made known unto me now what we desired of you: for you have now made known unto us the king's matter.
B027C002V024	27	2	24	Therefore Daniel went in unto Arioch, whom the king had ordained to destroy the wise men of Babylon: he went and said thus unto him; Destroy not the wise men of Babylon: bring me in before the king, and I will show unto the king the interpretation.
B027C002V025	27	2	25	Then Arioch brought in Daniel before the king in haste, and said thus unto him, I have found a man of the captives of Judah, that will make known unto the king the interpretation.
B027C002V026	27	2	26	The king answered and said to Daniel, whose name was Belteshazzar, are you able to make known unto me the dream which I have seen, and its interpretation?
B027C002V027	27	2	27	Daniel answered in the presence of the king, and said, The secret which the king has demanded the wise men, the astrologers, the magicians, and the soothsayers, cannot show unto the king;
B027C002V028	27	2	28	But there is a God in heaven that reveals secrets, and makes known to king Nebuchadnezzar what shall be in the latter days. Your dream, and the visions of your head upon your bed, are these;
B027C002V029	27	2	29	As for you, O king, your thoughts came into your mind upon your bed, what should come to pass hereafter: and he that reveals secrets makes known to you what shall come to pass.
B027C002V030	27	2	30	But as for me, this secret is not revealed to me for any wisdom that I have more than anyone living, but for their sakes that shall make known the interpretation to the king, and that you might know the thoughts of your heart.
B027C002V031	27	2	31	You, O king, saw, and behold a great image. This great image, whose brightness was excellent, stood before you; and its form was frightening.
B027C002V032	27	2	32	This image's head was of fine gold, its breast and its arms of silver, its belly and its thighs of bronze,
B027C002V033	27	2	33	Its legs of iron, its feet part of iron and part of clay.
B027C002V034	27	2	34	You saw till a stone was cut out without hands, which struck the image upon its feet that were of iron and clay, and broke them to pieces.
B027C002V035	27	2	35	Then the iron, the clay, the bronze, the silver, and the gold were crushed together, and became like the chaff of the summer threshing floors; and the wind carried them away, so that no place was found for them: and the stone that struck the image became a great mountain, and filled the whole earth.
B027C002V036	27	2	36	This is the dream; and we will tell its interpretation before the king.
B027C002V037	27	2	37	You, O king, are a king of kings: for the God of heaven has given you a kingdom, power, and strength, and glory.
B027C002V038	27	2	38	And wherever the children of men dwell, the beasts of the field and the fowls of the heaven has he given into your hand, and has made you ruler over them all. You are this head of gold.
B027C002V039	27	2	39	And after you shall arise another kingdom inferior to you, and another third kingdom of bronze, which shall bear rule over all the earth.
B027C002V040	27	2	40	And the fourth kingdom shall be strong as iron: since iron breaks in pieces and subdues all things: and as iron that breaks all these, shall it break in pieces and bruise.
B027C002V041	27	2	41	And as you saw the feet and toes, part of potter's clay, and part of iron, the kingdom shall be divided; but there shall be in it the strength of the iron, just as you saw the iron mixed with miry clay.
B027C002V042	27	2	42	And as the toes of the feet were part of iron, and part of clay, so the kingdom shall be partly strong, and partly broken.
B027C002V043	27	2	43	And as you saw iron mixed with miry clay, they shall mingle themselves with the descendants of men: but they shall not hold one to another, even as iron is not mixed with clay.
B027C002V044	27	2	44	And in the days of these kings shall the God of heaven set up a kingdom, which shall never be destroyed: and the kingdom shall not be left to other people, but it shall break in pieces and consume all these kingdoms, and it shall stand forever.
B027C002V045	27	2	45	Just as you saw that the stone was cut out of the mountain without hands, and that it broke in pieces the iron, the bronze, the clay, the silver, and the gold; the great God has made known to the king what shall come to pass hereafter: and the dream is certain, and its interpretation sure.
B027C002V046	27	2	46	Then king Nebuchadnezzar fell upon his face, and worshiped Daniel, and commanded that they should offer an offering and incense unto him.
B027C002V047	27	2	47	The king answered unto Daniel, and said, Of a truth it is, that your God is God of gods, and Lord of kings, and a revealer of secrets, seeing you could reveal this secret.
