B027C004V037	27	4	37	Now I Nebuchadnezzar praise and extol and honor the King of heaven, all whose works are truth, and his ways judgment: and those that walk in pride he is able to abase.
B027C005V001	27	5	1	Belshazzar the king made a great feast to a thousand of his lords, and drank wine before the thousand.
B027C005V002	27	5	2	Belshazzar, while he tasted the wine, commanded to bring the golden and silver vessels which his father Nebuchadnezzar had taken out of the temple which was in Jerusalem; that the king, and his lords, his wives, and his concubines, might drink from them.
B027C005V003	27	5	3	Then they brought the golden vessels that were taken out of the temple of the house of God which was at Jerusalem; and the king, and his lords, his wives, and his concubines, drank from them.
B027C005V004	27	5	4	They drank wine, and praised the gods of gold, and of silver, of bronze, of iron, of wood, and of stone.
