B027C005V014	27	5	14	I have even heard of you, that the spirit of the gods is in you, and that light and understanding and excellent wisdom are found in you.
B027C005V015	27	5	15	And now the wise men, the astrologers, have been brought in before me, that they should read this writing, and make known unto me its interpretation: but they could not show the interpretation of the thing:
B027C005V016	27	5	16	And I have heard of you, that you can make interpretations, and explain doubts: now if you can read the writing, and make known to me its interpretation, you shall be clothed with scarlet, and have a chain of gold about your neck, and shall be the third ruler in the kingdom.
B027C005V017	27	5	17	Then Daniel answered and said before the king, Let your gifts be to yourself, and give your rewards to another; yet I will read the writing unto the king, and make known to him the interpretation.
B027C005V018	27	5	18	O king, the most high God gave Nebuchadnezzar your father a kingdom, and majesty, and glory, and honor:
B027C005V019	27	5	19	And for the majesty that he gave him, all people, nations, and languages, trembled and feared before him: whom he would he slew; and whom he would he kept alive; and whom he would he set up; and whom he would he put down.
B027C005V020	27	5	20	But when his heart was lifted up, and his mind hardened in pride, he was deposed from his kingly throne, and they took his glory from him:
B027C005V021	27	5	21	And he was driven from the sons of men; and his heart was made like the beasts, and his dwelling was with the wild donkeys: they fed him with grass like oxen, and his body was wet with the dew of heaven; till he knew that the most high God ruled in the kingdom of men, and that he appoints over it whomever he will.
B027C005V022	27	5	22	And you his son, O Belshazzar, have not humbled your heart, though you knew all this;
