B028C009V001	28	9	1	Rejoice not, O Israel, for joy, as other people: for you have played the harlot against your God, you have loved for hire upon every threshing floor.
B028C009V002	28	9	2	The floor and the winepress shall not feed them, and the new wine shall fail in her.
B028C009V003	28	9	3	They shall not dwell in the LORD'S land; but Ephraim shall return to Egypt, and they shall eat unclean things in Assyria.
B028C009V004	28	9	4	They shall not offer wine offerings to the LORD, neither shall they be pleasing unto him: their sacrifices shall be unto them like the bread of mourners; all that eat of it shall be defiled: for their bread for their soul shall not come into the house of the LORD.
B028C009V005	28	9	5	What will you do in the solemn day, and in the day of the feast of the LORD?
B028C009V006	28	9	6	For, lo, they are gone because of destruction: Egypt shall gather them up, Memphis shall bury them: the precious things of their silver, nettles shall possess them: thorns shall be in their tents.
B028C009V007	28	9	7	The days of punishment have come, the days of recompense have come; Israel shall know it: the prophet is a fool, the spiritual man is mad, because of the multitude of your iniquity, and the great hatred.
B028C009V008	28	9	8	The watchman of Ephraim was with my God: but the prophet is a snare of a fowler in all his ways, and hatred in the house of his God.
B028C009V009	28	9	9	They have deeply corrupted themselves, as in the days of Gibeah: therefore he will remember their iniquity, he will punish their sins.
B028C009V010	28	9	10	
        
B028C009V011	28	9	11	
        
B028C009V012	28	9	12	
        
B028C009V013	28	9	13	
        
B028C009V014	28	9	14	Give them, O LORD: what will you give? give them a miscarrying womb and dry breasts.
B028C009V015	28	9	15	
        
B028C009V016	28	9	16	
        
B028C009V017	28	9	17	My God will cast them away, because they did not hearken unto him: and they shall be wanderers among the nations.
B028C010V001	28	10	1	Israel is an empty vine, he brings forth fruit unto himself: according to the multitude of his fruit he has increased the altars; according to the goodness of his land they have made goodly images.
B028C010V002	28	10	2	Their heart is divided; now shall they be found guilty: he shall break down their altars, he shall ruin their images.
B028C010V003	28	10	3	For now they shall say, We have no king, because we feared not the LORD; what then could a king do for us?
B028C010V004	28	10	4	They have spoken words, swearing falsely in making a covenant: thus judgment springs up like hemlock in the furrows of the field.
B028C010V005	28	10	5	The inhabitants of Samaria shall fear because of the calves of Bethaven: for its people shall mourn over it, and its idolatrous priests shall wail over it, for its glory has departed from it.
B028C010V006	28	10	6	It shall be also carried unto Assyria for a present to king Jareb: Ephraim shall receive shame, and Israel shall be ashamed of his own counsel.
B028C010V007	28	10	7	As for Samaria, her king is cut off as the foam upon the water.
B028C010V008	28	10	8	The high places also of Aven, the sin of Israel, shall be destroyed: the thorn and the thistle shall come up on their altars; and they shall say to the mountains, Cover us; and to the hills, Fall on us.
