B028C011V012	28	11	12	Ephraim surrounds me with lies, and the house of Israel with deceit: but Judah yet walks with God, and is faithful with the saints.
B028C012V001	28	12	1	Ephraim feeds on wind, and follows after the east wind: he daily increases lies and desolation; and they do make a covenant with the Assyrians, and oil is carried into Egypt.
B028C012V002	28	12	2	The LORD has also a controversy with Judah, and will punish Jacob according to his ways; according to his deeds will he recompense him.
B028C012V003	28	12	3	He took his brother by the heel in the womb, and by his strength he had power with God:
B028C012V004	28	12	4	Yea, he had power over the angel, and prevailed: he wept, and made supplication unto him: he found him in Bethel, and there he spoke with us;
B028C012V005	28	12	5	Even the LORD God of hosts; the LORD is his memorial name.
B028C012V006	28	12	6	Therefore turn you to your God: keep mercy and judgment, and wait on your God continually.
B028C012V007	28	12	7	He is a merchant, the balances of deceit are in his hand: he loves to oppress.
B028C012V008	28	12	8	And Ephraim said, Yet I have become rich, I have found myself wealth: in all my labors they shall find no iniquity in me that is sin.
B028C012V009	28	12	9	
        
B028C012V010	28	12	10	
        
B028C012V011	28	12	11	Is there iniquity in Gilead? surely they are vanity: they sacrifice bullocks in Gilgal; yea, their altars are like heaps in the furrows of the fields.
B028C012V012	28	12	12	And Jacob fled into the country of Aram, and Israel served for a wife, and for a wife he kept sheep.
B028C012V013	28	12	13	And by a prophet the LORD brought Israel out of Egypt, and by a prophet was he preserved.
B028C012V014	28	12	14	Ephraim provoked him to anger most bitterly: therefore shall he leave his bloodguilt upon him, and his reproach shall his Lord return unto him.
B028C013V001	28	13	1	When Ephraim spoke trembling, he exalted himself in Israel; but when he offended through Baal worship, he died.
B028C013V002	28	13	2	And now they sin more and more, and have made them molten images of their silver, and idols according to their own understanding, all of it the work of craftsmen: they say of them, Let the men that sacrifice kiss the calves.
B028C013V003	28	13	3	Therefore they shall be as the morning cloud, and as the early dew that passes away, as the chaff that is driven with the whirlwind out of the floor, and as the smoke out of the chimney.
