B028C013V016	28	13	16	Samaria shall become desolate; for she has rebelled against her God: they shall fall by the sword: their infants shall be dashed in pieces, and their women with child shall be ripped up.
B028C014V001	28	14	1	O Israel, return unto the LORD your God; for you have fallen because of your iniquity.
B028C014V002	28	14	2	Take with you words, and turn to the LORD: say unto him, Take away all iniquity, and receive us graciously: so will we offer the sacrifices of our lips.
B028C014V003	28	14	3	Assyria shall not save us; we will not ride upon horses: neither will we say any more to the work of our hands, you are our gods: for in you the fatherless finds mercy.
