B028C014V008	28	14	8	
        
B028C014V009	28	14	9	Who is wise, and he shall understand these things? prudent, and he shall know them? for the ways of the LORD are right, and the just shall walk in them: but the transgressors shall stumble in them.
B029C001V001	29	1	1	The word of the LORD that came to Joel the son of Pethuel.
B029C001V002	29	1	2	Hear this, you aged men, and give ear, all you inhabitants of the land. Has this happened in your days, or even in the days of your fathers?
B029C001V003	29	1	3	Tell your children of it, and let your children tell their children, and their children another generation.
B029C001V004	29	1	4	That which the cutting locust has left has the swarming locust eaten; and that which the swarming locust has left has the crawling locust eaten; and that which the crawling locust has left has the consuming locust eaten.
B029C001V005	29	1	5	Awake, you drunkards, and weep; and howl, all you drinkers of wine, because of the new wine, for it is cut off from your mouth.
B029C001V006	29	1	6	For a nation has come up upon my land, strong, and without number, whose teeth are the teeth of a lion, and he has the fangs of a lioness.
B029C001V007	29	1	7	He has laid my vine waste, and splintered my fig tree: he has stripped it bare, and cast it away; its branches are made white.
B029C001V008	29	1	8	Lament like a virgin girded with sackcloth for the husband of her youth.
B029C001V009	29	1	9	The grain offering and the drink offering is cut off from the house of the LORD; the priests, the LORD'S ministers, mourn.
B029C001V010	29	1	10	The field is wasted, the land mourns; for the grain is wasted: the new wine is dried up, the oil languishes.
B029C001V011	29	1	11	Be ashamed, O you farmers; wail, O you vinedressers, for the wheat and for the barley; because the harvest of the field has perished.
B029C001V012	29	1	12	The vine is dried up, and the fig tree languishes; the pomegranate tree, the palm tree also, and the apple tree, even all the trees of the field, are withered: because joy has withered away from the sons of men.
B029C001V013	29	1	13	Gird yourselves, and lament, you priests: wail, you ministers of the altar: come, lie all night in sackcloth, you ministers of my God: for the grain offering and the drink offering is withheld from the house of your God.
B029C001V014	29	1	14	Sanctify you a fast, call a solemn assembly, gather the elders and all the inhabitants of the land into the house of the LORD your God, and cry unto the LORD.
B029C001V015	29	1	15	Alas for the day! for the day of the LORD is at hand, and as a destruction from the Almighty shall it come.
B029C001V016	29	1	16	Is not the food cut off before our eyes, yea, joy and gladness from the house of our God?
B029C001V017	29	1	17	The seed shrivels under the clods, the storehouses are laid desolate, the barns are broken down; for the grain has withered.
B029C001V018	29	1	18	How the beasts groan! the herds of cattle are perplexed, because they have no pasture; yea, the flocks of sheep are made desolate.
B029C001V019	29	1	19	O LORD, to you will I cry: for the fire has devoured the pastures of the wilderness, and the flame has burned all the trees of the field.
B029C001V020	29	1	20	The beasts of the field cry also unto you: for the rivers of waters are dried up, and the fire has devoured the pastures of the wilderness.
B029C002V001	29	2	1	Blow the trumpet in Zion, and sound an alarm in my holy mountain: let all the inhabitants of the land tremble: for the day of the LORD comes, for it is near at hand;
B029C002V002	29	2	2	A day of darkness and of gloominess, a day of clouds and of thick darkness, as the morning spread upon the mountains: a great and strong people; there has not been ever the like, neither shall be any more after it, through the years of many generations.
B029C002V003	29	2	3	A fire devours before them; and behind them a flame burns: the land is as the garden of Eden before them, and behind them a desolate wilderness; yea, and nothing shall escape them.
B029C002V004	29	2	4	The appearance of them is as the appearance of horses; and as horsemen, so shall they run.
B029C002V005	29	2	5	Like the noise of chariots on the tops of mountains shall they leap, like the noise of a flame of fire that devours the stubble, as a strong people set in battle array.
B029C002V006	29	2	6	Before their face the people shall be in great pain: all faces are drained of color.
B029C002V007	29	2	7	They shall run like mighty men; they shall climb the wall like men of war; and they shall march each one on his way, and they shall not break their ranks:
B029C002V008	29	2	8	Neither shall one jostle another; they shall walk each one in his path: and when they lunge between the swords, they shall not be wounded.
B029C002V009	29	2	9	They shall run to and fro in the city; they shall run upon the wall, they shall climb up upon the houses; they shall enter in at the windows like a thief.
B029C002V010	29	2	10	The earth shall quake before them; the heavens shall tremble: the sun and the moon shall be dark, and the stars shall withdraw their shining:
B029C002V011	29	2	11	And the LORD shall utter his voice before his army: for his camp is very great: for he is strong that executes his word: for the day of the LORD is great and very terrible; and who can endure it?
B029C002V012	29	2	12	
        
B029C002V013	29	2	13	And tear your hearts, and not your garments, and turn unto the LORD your God: for he is gracious and merciful, slow to anger, and of great kindness, and relents from sending calamity.
B029C002V014	29	2	14	Who knows if he will return and have pity, and leave a blessing behind him; even a grain offering and a drink offering unto the LORD your God?
B029C002V015	29	2	15	Blow the trumpet in Zion, sanctify a fast, call a solemn assembly:
B029C002V016	29	2	16	Gather the people, sanctify the congregation, assemble the elders, gather the children, and those that nurse: let the bridegroom go forth from his chamber, and the bride out of her chamber.
B029C002V017	29	2	17	Let the priests, the ministers of the LORD, weep between the porch and the altar, and let them say, Spare your people, O LORD, and give not your heritage to reproach, that the nations should rule over them: why should they say among the people, Where is their God?
B029C002V018	29	2	18	Then will the LORD be jealous for his land, and pity his people.
B029C002V019	29	2	19	Yea, the LORD will answer and say unto his people, 
B029C002V020	29	2	20	
        
B029C002V021	29	2	21	Fear not, O land; be glad and rejoice: for the LORD will do great things.
B029C002V022	29	2	22	Be not afraid, you beasts of the field: for the pastures of the wilderness do spring up, for the tree bears her fruit, the fig tree and the vine do yield their strength.
B029C002V023	29	2	23	Be glad then, you children of Zion, and rejoice in the LORD your God: for he has given you the former rain faithfully, and he will cause to come down for you the rain, the former rain, and the latter rain in the first month.
B029C002V024	29	2	24	And the threshing floors shall be full of wheat, and the vats shall overflow with wine and oil.
