B033C001V012	33	1	12	For the inhabitant of Maroth waited anxiously for good: but disaster came down from the LORD unto the gate of Jerusalem.
B033C001V013	33	1	13	O you inhabitant of Lachish, harness the chariot to the swift steeds: it is the beginning of sin to the daughter of Zion: for the transgressions of Israel were found in you.
B033C001V014	33	1	14	Therefore shall you give presents to Moreshethgath: the houses of Achzib shall be a deceit to the kings of Israel.
B033C001V015	33	1	15	Yet will I bring an heir unto you, O inhabitant of Mareshah: he shall come unto Adullam, the glory of Israel.
B033C001V016	33	1	16	Make yourselves bald, and cut your hair because of your precious children; enlarge your baldness like an eagle; for they shall go into captivity from you.
B033C002V001	33	2	1	Woe to them that devise iniquity, and work evil upon their beds! when the morning is light, they practice it, because it is in the power of their hand.
B033C002V002	33	2	2	And they covet fields, and take them by violence; and houses, and take them away: so they oppress a man and his house, even a man and his heritage.
B033C002V003	33	2	3	Therefore thus says the LORD; 
B033C002V004	33	2	4	
        
B033C002V005	33	2	5	Therefore you shall have none that shall determine boundaries by lot in the congregation of the LORD.
B033C002V006	33	2	6	Prophesy not, they say to them that prophesy: they shall not prophesy to them, that they shall not be shamed.
B033C002V007	33	2	7	O you that are named the house of Jacob
B033C002V008	33	2	8	
        
B033C002V009	33	2	9	
        
B033C002V010	33	2	10	
        
B033C002V011	33	2	11	
        
B033C002V012	33	2	12	
        
B033C002V013	33	2	13	
        
B033C003V001	33	3	1	And I said, Hear, I pray you, O heads of Jacob, and you rulers of the house of Israel; Is it not for you to know judgment?
B033C003V002	33	3	2	Who hate the good, and love the evil; who pluck off their skin from off them, and their flesh from off their bones;
B033C003V003	33	3	3	Who also eat the flesh of my people, and flay their skin from off them; and they break their bones, and chop them in pieces, as for the pot, and as flesh within the caldron.
B033C003V004	33	3	4	Then shall they cry unto the LORD, but he will not hear them: he will even hide his face from them at that time, as they have behaved themselves in an evil way in their deeds.
B033C003V005	33	3	5	Thus says the LORD
B033C003V006	33	3	6	
        
B033C003V007	33	3	7	
        
B033C003V008	33	3	8	But truly I am full of power by the spirit of the LORD, and of justice, and of might, to declare unto Jacob his transgression, and to Israel his sin.
B033C003V009	33	3	9	Hear this, I pray you, you heads of the house of Jacob, and rulers of the house of Israel, that abhor justice, and pervert all equity.
B033C003V010	33	3	10	They build up Zion with blood, and Jerusalem with iniquity.
B033C003V011	33	3	11	Her heads judge for reward, and her priests teach for hire, and her prophets divine for money: yet will they lean upon the LORD, and say, Is not the LORD among us? no evil can come upon us.
B033C003V012	33	3	12	Therefore shall Zion for your sake be plowed like a field, and Jerusalem shall become heaps of ruins, and the mountain of the house like the high places of the forest.
B033C004V001	33	4	1	But in the last days it shall come to pass, that the mountain of the house of the LORD shall be established on the top of the mountains, and it shall be exalted above the hills; and people shall flow unto it.
B033C004V002	33	4	2	And many nations shall come, and say, Come, and let us go up to the mountain of the LORD, and to the house of the God of Jacob; and he will teach us of his ways, and we will walk in his paths: for the law shall go forth out of Zion, and the word of the LORD from Jerusalem.
B033C004V003	33	4	3	And he shall judge between many peoples, and rebuke strong nations afar off; and they shall beat their swords into plowshares, and their spears into pruninghooks: nation shall not lift up a sword against nation, neither shall they learn war any more.
B033C004V004	33	4	4	But they shall sit every man under his vine and under his fig tree; and none shall make them afraid: for the mouth of the LORD of hosts has spoken it.
B033C004V005	33	4	5	For all people will walk every one in the name of his god, and we will walk in the name of the LORD our God forever and ever.
B033C004V006	33	4	6	
        
B033C004V007	33	4	7	
        
B033C004V008	33	4	8	
        
B033C004V009	33	4	9	Now why do you cry out aloud? is there no king in you? is your counselor perished? for pangs have taken you as a woman in travail.
B033C004V010	33	4	10	Be in pain, and labor to bring forth, O daughter of Zion, like a woman in travail: for now shall you go forth out of the city, and you shall dwell in the field, and you shall go even to Babylon; there shall you be delivered; there the LORD shall redeem you from the hand of your enemies.
B033C004V011	33	4	11	Now also many nations are gathered against you, that say, Let her be defiled, and let our eye look upon Zion.
B033C004V012	33	4	12	But they know not the thoughts of the LORD, neither understand they his counsel: for he shall gather them as the sheaves into the floor.
B033C004V013	33	4	13	
        
B033C005V001	33	5	1	Now gather yourself in troops, O daughter of troops: he has laid siege against us: they shall strike the judge of Israel with a rod upon the cheek.
B033C005V002	33	5	2	
        
B033C005V003	33	5	3	Therefore will he give them up, until the time that she who travails has brought forth: then the remnant of his brethren shall return unto the children of Israel.
B033C005V004	33	5	4	And he shall stand and feed in the strength of the LORD, in the majesty of the name of the LORD his God; and they shall abide: for now shall he be great unto the ends of the earth.
B033C005V005	33	5	5	And this one shall be the peace, when the Assyrian shall come into our land: and when he shall tread in our palaces, then shall we raise against him seven shepherds, and eight princely men.
B033C005V006	33	5	6	And they shall waste the land of Assyria with the sword, and the land of Nimrod at its entrances: thus shall he deliver us from the Assyrian, when he comes into our land, and when he treads within our borders.
B033C005V007	33	5	7	And the remnant of Jacob shall be in the midst of many people as a dew from the LORD, as the showers upon the grass, that tarries not for man, nor waits for the sons of men.
B033C005V008	33	5	8	And the remnant of Jacob shall be among the Gentiles in the midst of many people as a lion among the beasts of the forest, as a young lion among the flocks of sheep: which, if it passes through, both treads down, and tears in pieces, and none can deliver.
B033C005V009	33	5	9	Your hand shall be lifted up over your adversaries, and all your enemies shall be cut off.
B033C005V010	33	5	10	
        
B033C005V011	33	5	11	
        
B033C005V012	33	5	12	
        
B033C005V013	33	5	13	
        
B033C005V014	33	5	14	
        
B033C005V015	33	5	15	
        
B033C006V001	33	6	1	Hear you now what the LORD says; 
B033C006V002	33	6	2	
        
B033C006V003	33	6	3	
        
B033C006V004	33	6	4	
        
B033C006V005	33	6	5	
        
B033C006V006	33	6	6	With what shall I come before the LORD, and bow myself before the high God? shall I come before him with burnt offerings, with calves a year old?
B033C006V007	33	6	7	Will the LORD be pleased with thousands of rams, or with ten thousands of rivers of oil? shall I give my firstborn for my transgression, the fruit of my body for the sin of my soul?
B033C006V008	33	6	8	He has showed you, O man, what is good; and what does the LORD require of you, but to do justly, and to love mercy, and to walk humbly with your God?
B033C006V009	33	6	9	The LORD'S voice cries unto the city, and wisdom shall see your name: 
B033C006V010	33	6	10	
        
B033C006V011	33	6	11	
        
B033C006V012	33	6	12	
        
B033C006V013	33	6	13	
        
B033C006V014	33	6	14	
        
B033C006V015	33	6	15	
        
B033C006V016	33	6	16	
        
B033C007V001	33	7	1	Woe is me! for I am as when they have gathered the summer fruits, as the grape gleanings of the vintage: there is no cluster to eat: my soul desired the first ripe fruit.
B033C007V002	33	7	2	The godly man has perished out of the earth: and there is none upright among men: they all lie in wait for blood; they hunt every man his brother with a net.
B033C007V003	33	7	3	That they may do evil with both hands earnestly, the prince asks, and the judge asks for a bribe; and the great man, he utters his evil desire: so they weave it together.
B033C007V004	33	7	4	The best of them is like a brier: the most upright is sharper than a thorn hedge: the day of your watchmen and your punishment comes; now shall be their perplexity.
B033C007V005	33	7	5	Trust not in a friend, put not confidence in a companion: keep the doors of your mouth from her that lies in your bosom.
B033C007V006	33	7	6	For the son dishonors the father, the daughter rises up against her mother, the daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law; a man's enemies are the men of his own house.
B033C007V007	33	7	7	Therefore I will look unto the LORD; I will wait for the God of my salvation: my God will hear me.
B033C007V008	33	7	8	Rejoice not against me, O my enemy: when I fall, I shall arise; when I sit in darkness, the LORD shall be a light unto me.
B033C007V009	33	7	9	I will bear the indignation of the LORD, because I have sinned against him, until he pleads my cause, and executes justice for me: he will bring me forth to the light, and I shall behold his righteousness.
B033C007V010	33	7	10	Then she that is my enemy shall see it, and shame shall cover her who said unto me, Where is the LORD your God? my eyes shall behold her: now shall she be trodden down as the mire of the streets.
B033C007V011	33	7	11	In the day that your walls are to be built, in that day shall your boundaries be far extended.
B033C007V012	33	7	12	In that day also they shall come even to you from Assyria, and from the fortified cities, and from the fortress even to the river, and from sea to sea, and from mountain to mountain.
B033C007V013	33	7	13	Nevertheless the land shall be desolate because of them that dwell in it, and for the fruit of their deeds.
B033C007V014	33	7	14	Feed your people with your staff, the flock of your heritage, who dwell alone in the forest, in the midst of Carmel: let them feed in Bashan and Gilead, as in the days of old.
B033C007V015	33	7	15	
        
B033C007V016	33	7	16	The nations shall see and be ashamed at all their might: they shall lay their hand upon their mouth, their ears shall be deaf.
B033C007V017	33	7	17	They shall lick the dust like a serpent, they shall move out of their holes like worms of the earth: they shall be afraid of the LORD our God, and shall fear because of you.
B033C007V018	33	7	18	Who is a God like unto you, who pardons iniquity, and passes by the transgression of the remnant of his heritage? he retains not his anger forever, because he delights in mercy.
B033C007V019	33	7	19	He will turn again, he will have compassion upon us; he will subdue our iniquities; and you will cast all their sins into the depths of the sea.
B033C007V020	33	7	20	You will show truth to Jacob, and mercy to Abraham, which you have sworn unto our fathers from the days of old.
B034C001V001	34	1	1	The burden concerning Nineveh. The book of the vision of Nahum the Elkohshite.
B034C001V002	34	1	2	God is jealous, and the LORD avenges; the LORD avenges, and is furious; the LORD will take vengeance on his adversaries, and he reserves wrath for his enemies.
B034C001V003	34	1	3	The LORD is slow to anger, and great in power, and will not at all acquit the wicked: the LORD has his way in the whirlwind and in the storm, and the clouds are the dust of his feet.
B034C001V004	34	1	4	He rebukes the sea, and makes it dry, and dries up all the rivers: Bashan withers, and Carmel, and the flower of Lebanon fades.
B034C001V005	34	1	5	The mountains quake before him, and the hills melt, and the earth is burned at his presence, yea, the world, and all that dwell in it.
B034C001V006	34	1	6	Who can stand before his indignation? and who can abide in the fierceness of his anger? his fury is poured out like fire, and the rocks are thrown down by him.
B034C001V007	34	1	7	The LORD is good, a stronghold in the day of trouble; and he knows them that trust in him.
B034C001V008	34	1	8	But with an overrunning flood he will make an utter end of its place, and darkness shall pursue his enemies.
B034C001V009	34	1	9	What do you imagine against the LORD? he will make an utter end: affliction shall not rise up the second time.
B034C001V010	34	1	10	For while they are entangled together as thorns, and while they are drunk as drunkards, they shall be devoured as stubble fully dry.
B034C001V011	34	1	11	There has one come out of you, that imagines evil against the LORD, a wicked counselor.
B034C001V012	34	1	12	Thus says the LORD; 
B034C001V013	34	1	13	
        
B034C001V014	34	1	14	And the LORD has given a commandment concerning you: 
B034C001V015	34	1	15	Behold upon the mountains the feet of him that brings good tidings, that publishes peace! O Judah, keep your solemn feasts, perform your vows: for the wicked shall no more pass through you; he is utterly cut off.
B034C002V001	34	2	1	He that dashes in pieces has come up before your face: keep the fortress, watch the road, make your flanks strong, fortify your power mightily.
B034C002V002	34	2	2	For the LORD will restore the excellence of Jacob, as the excellence of Israel: for the plunderers have emptied them out, and marred their vine branches.
B034C002V003	34	2	3	The shield of his mighty men is made red, the valiant men are in scarlet: the chariots shall be with flaming torches in the day of his preparation, and the cypress trees shall be terribly shaken.
B034C002V004	34	2	4	The chariots shall rage in the streets, they shall jostle one against another in the broad roads: they shall seem like torches, they shall run like lightning.
B034C002V005	34	2	5	He shall recount his nobles: they shall stumble in their walk; they shall make haste to the wall, and the defense shall be prepared.
B034C002V006	34	2	6	The gates of the rivers shall be opened, and the palace shall be dissolved.
B034C002V007	34	2	7	It is decreed: she shall be led away captive, she shall be brought up, and her maidens shall lead her as with the moaning of doves, beating upon their breasts.
B034C002V008	34	2	8	Though Nineveh was of old like a pool of water: yet they shall flee away. Stand, stand, shall they cry; but none shall look back.
B034C002V009	34	2	9	Take the spoil of silver, take the spoil of gold: for there is no end of treasure or wealth out of all the precious things.
B034C002V010	34	2	10	She is empty, and void, and waste: and the heart melts, and the knees strike together, and much pain is on all sides, and the faces of them all grow pale.
B034C002V011	34	2	11	Where is the dwelling of the lions, and the feeding place of the young lions, where the lion, even the old lion, walked, and the lion's cub, and none made them afraid?
B034C002V012	34	2	12	The lion did tear in pieces enough for his cubs, and strangled for his lionesses, and filled his caves with prey, and his dens with torn flesh.
B034C002V013	34	2	13	
        
B034C003V001	34	3	1	Woe to the bloody city! it is all full of lies and robbery; the victim departs not;
B034C003V002	34	3	2	The noise of a whip, and the noise of the rattling of the wheels, and of the prancing horses, and of the jolting chariots.
B034C003V003	34	3	3	The horseman lifts up both the bright sword and the glittering spear: and there is a multitude of slain, and a great number of dead bodies; and there is no end of their corpses; they stumble over the corpses:
B034C003V004	34	3	4	Because of the multitude of the harlotries of the seductive harlot, the mistress of sorceries, that sells nations through her harlotries, and peoples through her sorceries.
B034C003V005	34	3	5	
        
B034C003V006	34	3	6	
        
B034C003V007	34	3	7	
        
B034C003V008	34	3	8	Are you better than No Amon, that was situated among the rivers, that had the waters round about it, whose rampart was the sea, and her wall was the sea?
B034C003V009	34	3	9	Ethiopia and Egypt were her strength, and it was without limit; Put and Lubim were your helpers.
B034C003V010	34	3	10	Yet was she carried away, she went into captivity: her young children also were dashed in pieces at the head of all the streets: and they cast lots for her honorable men, and all her great men were bound in chains.
B034C003V011	34	3	11	You also shall be drunk: you shall be hidden, you also shall seek refuge from the enemy.
B034C003V012	34	3	12	All your strongholds shall be like fig trees with the first ripe figs: if they are shaken, they shall even fall into the mouth of the eater.
B034C003V013	34	3	13	Behold, your troops in the midst of you are women: the gates of your land shall be set wide open unto your enemies: the fire shall devour the bars of your gates.
B034C003V014	34	3	14	Draw your water for the siege, fortify your strongholds: go into the clay, and tread the mortar, make strong the brick kiln.
B034C003V015	34	3	15	There shall the fire devour you; the sword shall cut you off, it shall eat you up like the locust: make yourself many like the locust, make yourself many like the swarming locusts.
B034C003V016	34	3	16	You have multiplied your merchants more than the stars of heaven: the locust plunders, and flies away.
B034C003V017	34	3	17	Your princes are like the locusts, and your officials like the great grasshoppers, which camp in the hedges on the cold day, but when the sun arises they flee away, and their place is not known where they are.
B034C003V018	34	3	18	Your shepherds slumber, O king of Assyria: your nobles shall dwell in the dust: your people are scattered upon the mountains, and no man gathers them.
B034C003V019	34	3	19	There is no healing of your bruise; your wound is grievous: all that hear the report of you shall clap their hands over you: for upon whom has not your wickedness passed continually?
B035C001V001	35	1	1	The burden which Habakkuk the prophet did see.
B035C001V002	35	1	2	O LORD, how long shall I cry, and you will not hear! even cry out unto you of violence, and you will not save!
B035C001V003	35	1	3	Why do you show me iniquity, and cause me to behold trouble? for plundering and violence are before me: and there are those that raise up strife and contention.
B035C001V004	35	1	4	Therefore the law is slacked, and justice does never go forth: for the wicked does surround the righteous; therefore perverse judgment proceeds.
B035C001V005	35	1	5	
        
B035C001V006	35	1	6	
        
B035C001V007	35	1	7	
        
B035C001V008	35	1	8	
        
B035C001V009	35	1	9	
        
B035C001V010	35	1	10	
        
B035C001V011	35	1	11	
        
B035C001V012	35	1	12	Are you not from everlasting, O LORD my God, my Holy One? we shall not die. O LORD, you have ordained them for judgment; and, O mighty God, you have established them for correction.
B035C001V013	35	1	13	You are of purer eyes than to behold evil, and can not look on iniquity: why do you look upon them that deal treacherously, and hold your tongue when the wicked devours the man that is more righteous than he?
B035C001V014	35	1	14	And make men like the fish of the sea, like the creeping things, that have no ruler over them?
B035C001V015	35	1	15	They take up all of them with the hook, they catch them in their net, and gather them in their dragnet: therefore they rejoice and are glad.
B035C001V016	35	1	16	Therefore they sacrifice unto their net, and burn incense unto their dragnet; because by them their portion is luxurious, and their food plentiful.
B035C001V017	35	1	17	Shall they therefore empty their net, and continually slay the nations without mercy?
B035C002V001	35	2	1	I will stand upon my watch, and set myself upon the tower, and will watch to see what he will say unto me, and what I shall answer when I am reproved.
