B035C003V001	35	3	1	A prayer of Habakkuk the prophet on Shigionoth.
B035C003V002	35	3	2	O LORD, I have heard your speech, and was afraid: O LORD, revive your work in the midst of the years, in the midst of the years make it known; in wrath remember mercy.
B035C003V003	35	3	3	God came from Teman, and the Holy One from mount Paran. Selah. His glory covered the heavens, and the earth was full of his praise.
B035C003V004	35	3	4	And his brightness was as the light; he had rays flashing out of his hand: and there was his power hidden.
B035C003V005	35	3	5	Before him went the pestilence, and burning fever went forth at his feet.
B035C003V006	35	3	6	He stood, and measured the earth: he beheld, and drove asunder the nations; and the everlasting mountains were scattered, the perpetual hills did bow: his ways are everlasting.
B035C003V007	35	3	7	I saw the tents of Cushan in affliction: and the curtains of the land of Midian did tremble.
B035C003V008	35	3	8	Was the LORD displeased against the rivers? was your anger against the rivers? was your wrath against the sea, that you did ride upon your horses and your chariots of salvation?
B035C003V009	35	3	9	Your bow was made quite ready, according to the oaths over your arrows. Selah. You did divide the earth with rivers.
B035C003V010	35	3	10	The mountains saw you, and they trembled: the overflowing of the water passed by: the deep uttered its voice, and lifted up its hands on high.
B035C003V011	35	3	11	The sun and moon stood still in their habitation: at the light of your arrows they went, and at the shining of your glittering spear.
B035C003V012	35	3	12	You did march through the land in indignation, you did trample the nations in anger.
B035C003V013	35	3	13	You went forth for the salvation of your people, even for salvation with your anointed; you wounded the head out of the house of the wicked, by laying bare from the foundation to the neck. Selah.
B035C003V014	35	3	14	You did thrust through with his own arrows the head of his villages: they came out as a whirlwind to scatter me: their rejoicing was like devouring the poor secretly.
B035C003V015	35	3	15	You did walk through the sea with your horses, through the heap of great waters.
B035C003V016	35	3	16	When I heard, my body trembled; my lips quivered at the voice: rottenness entered into my bones, and I trembled in myself, that I might rest in the day of trouble: when he comes up unto the people, he will invade them with his troops.
B035C003V017	35	3	17	Although the fig tree shall not blossom, neither shall fruit be on the vines; the labor of the olive shall fail, and the fields shall yield no food; the flock shall be cut off from the fold, and there shall be no herd in the stalls:
B035C003V018	35	3	18	Yet I will rejoice in the LORD, I will joy in the God of my salvation.
B035C003V019	35	3	19	The LORD God is my strength, and he will make my feet like deerâ€™s feet, and he will make me walk upon my high places. To the chief singer on my stringed instruments.
