B040C001V001	40	1	1	The book of the genealogy of Jesus Christ, the son of David, the son of Abraham.
B040C001V002	40	1	2	Abraham begat Isaac; and Isaac begat Jacob; and Jacob begat Judah and his brothers;
B040C001V003	40	1	3	And Judah begat Perez and Zerah of Tamar; and Perez begat Hezron and Hezron begat Ram;
B040C001V004	40	1	4	And Ram begat Amminidab; and Amminidab begat Nahshon; and Nahshon begat Salmon;
B040C001V005	40	1	5	And Salmon begat Boaz of Rahab; and Boaz begat Obed of Ruth; and Obed begat Jesse;
B040C001V006	40	1	6	And Jesse begat David the king; and David the king begat Solomon of her that had been the wife of Uriah;
B040C001V007	40	1	7	And Solomon begat Rehoboam; and Rehoboam begat Abijah; and Abijah begat Asa;
B040C001V008	40	1	8	And Asa begat Jehoshaphat; and Jehoshaphat begat Joram; and Joram begat Uzziah;
B040C001V009	40	1	9	And Uzziah begat Joatham; and Joatham begat Ahaz; and Ahaz begat Hezekiah;
B040C001V010	40	1	10	And Hezekiah begat Manasseh; and Manasseh begat Amon; and Amon begat Josiah;
B040C001V011	40	1	11	And Josiah begat Jeconiah and his brothers, about the time they were carried away to Babylon:
B040C001V012	40	1	12	And after they were brought to Babylon, Jeconiah begat Shealtiel; and Shealtiel begat Zerubbabel;
B040C001V013	40	1	13	And Zerubbabel begat Abihud; and Abihud begat Eliakim; and Eliakim begat Azor;
B040C001V014	40	1	14	And Azor begat Zadok; and Zadok begat Achim; and Achim begat Eliud;
B040C001V015	40	1	15	And Eliud begat Eleazar; and Eleazar begat Matthan; and Matthan begat Jacob;
B040C001V016	40	1	16	And Jacob begat Joseph the husband of Mary, of whom was born Jesus, who is called Christ.
B040C001V017	40	1	17	So all the generations from Abraham to David are fourteen generations; and from David until the carrying away into Babylon are fourteen generations; and from the carrying away into Babylon unto Christ are fourteen generations.
B040C001V018	40	1	18	Now the birth of Jesus Christ happened this way: When his mother Mary was espoused to Joseph, before they came together, she was found to be with child of the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V019	40	1	19	Then Joseph her husband, being a just man, and not willing to make her a public example, decided to put her away privately.
B040C001V020	40	1	20	But while he thought on these things, behold, the angel of the Lord appeared unto him in a dream, saying, Joseph, son of David, fear not to take unto you Mary your wife: for that which is conceived in her is of the Holy Spirit.
B040C001V021	40	1	21	And she shall bring forth a son, and you shall call his name JESUS: for he shall save his people from their sins.
B040C001V022	40	1	22	Now all this was done, that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying,
B040C001V023	40	1	23	Behold, a virgin shall be with child, and shall bring forth a son, and they shall call his name Emmanuel, which being interpreted is, God with us.
B040C001V024	40	1	24	Then Joseph being raised from sleep did as the angel of the Lord had bidden him, and took unto him his wife:
B040C001V025	40	1	25	And knew her not till she had brought forth her firstborn son: and he called his name JESUS.
B040C002V001	40	2	1	Now when Jesus was born in Bethlehem of Judea in the days of Herod the king, behold, there came wise men from the east to Jerusalem,
B040C002V002	40	2	2	Saying, Where is he that is born King of the Jews? for we have seen his star in the east, and are come to worship him.
B040C002V003	40	2	3	When Herod the king had heard these things, he was troubled, and all Jerusalem with him.
B040C002V004	40	2	4	And when he had gathered all the chief priests and scribes of the people together, he demanded of them where Christ should be born.
B040C002V005	40	2	5	And they said unto him, In Bethlehem of Judea: for thus it is written by the prophet,
B040C002V006	40	2	6	
        
B040C002V007	40	2	7	Then Herod, when he had privately called the wise men, inquired of them diligently what time the star appeared.
B040C002V008	40	2	8	And he sent them to Bethlehem, and said, Go and search diligently for the young child; and when you have found him, bring me word again, that I may come and worship him also.
B040C002V009	40	2	9	When they had heard the king, they departed; and, lo, the star, which they saw in the east, went before them, till it came and stood over where the young child was.
B040C002V010	40	2	10	When they saw the star, they rejoiced with exceedingly great joy.
B040C002V011	40	2	11	And when they came into the house, they saw the young child with Mary his mother, and fell down, and worshiped him: and when they had opened their treasures, they presented unto him gifts; gold, and frankincense, and myrrh.
B040C002V012	40	2	12	And being warned of God in a dream that they should not return to Herod, they departed into their own country another way.
B040C002V013	40	2	13	And when they were departed, behold, the angel of the Lord appeared to Joseph in a dream, saying, Arise, and take the young child and his mother, and flee into Egypt, and remain there until I bring you word: for Herod will seek the young child to destroy him.
B040C002V014	40	2	14	When he arose, he took the young child and his mother by night, and departed into Egypt:
B040C002V015	40	2	15	And was there until the death of Herod: that it might be fulfilled which was spoken of the Lord by the prophet, saying, 
