B041C015V001	41	15	1	And immediately in the morning the chief priests held a consultation with the elders and scribes and the whole council, and bound Jesus, and carried him away, and delivered him to Pilate.
B041C015V002	41	15	2	And Pilate asked him, Are you the King of the Jews? And he answering said unto him, 
B041C015V003	41	15	3	And the chief priests accused him of many things: but he answered nothing.
B041C015V004	41	15	4	And Pilate asked him again, saying, Answer you nothing? behold how many things they witness against you.
B041C015V005	41	15	5	But Jesus yet answered nothing; so that Pilate marveled.
B041C015V006	41	15	6	Now at that feast he released unto them one prisoner, whomsoever they desired.
B041C015V007	41	15	7	And there was one named Barabbas, who lay bound with them that had made insurrection with him, who had committed murder in the insurrection.
B041C015V008	41	15	8	And the multitude crying aloud began to desire him to do as he had always done unto them.
B041C015V009	41	15	9	But Pilate answered them, saying, Will you that I release unto you the King of the Jews?
B041C015V010	41	15	10	For he knew that the chief priests had delivered him out of envy.
B041C015V011	41	15	11	But the chief priests stirred up the people, that he should rather release Barabbas unto them.
B041C015V012	41	15	12	And Pilate answered and said again unto them, What will you then that I shall do unto him whom you call the King of the Jews?
B041C015V013	41	15	13	And they cried out again, Crucify him.
B041C015V014	41	15	14	Then Pilate said unto them, Why, what evil has he done? And they cried out the more exceedingly, Crucify him.
B041C015V015	41	15	15	And so Pilate, willing to satisfy the people, released Barabbas unto them, and delivered Jesus, when he had scourged him, to be crucified.
B041C015V016	41	15	16	And the soldiers led him away into the hall, called Praetorium; and they called together the whole band.
B041C015V017	41	15	17	And they clothed him with purple, and platted a crown of thorns, and put it about his head,
B041C015V018	41	15	18	And began to salute him, Hail, King of the Jews!
B041C015V019	41	15	19	And they struck him on the head with a reed, and did spit upon him, and bowing their knees worshiped him.
B041C015V020	41	15	20	And when they had mocked him, they took off the purple from him, and put his own clothes on him, and led him out to crucify him.
B041C015V021	41	15	21	And they compelled one Simon a Cyrenian, who passed by, coming in from the country, the father of Alexander and Rufus, to bear his cross.
B041C015V022	41	15	22	And they brought him unto the place Golgotha, which is, being interpreted, The place of a skull.
B041C015V023	41	15	23	And they gave him to drink wine mingled with myrrh: but he received it not.
B041C015V024	41	15	24	And when they had crucified him, they parted his garments, casting lots for them, what every man should take.
B041C015V025	41	15	25	And it was the third hour, and they crucified him.
B041C015V026	41	15	26	And the superscription of his accusation was written, THE KING OF THE JEWS.
B041C015V027	41	15	27	And with him they crucified two thieves; the one on his right hand, and the other on his left.
