B043C021V021	43	21	21	Peter seeing him said to Jesus, Lord, and what shall this man do?
B043C021V022	43	21	22	Jesus said unto him, 
B043C021V023	43	21	23	Then went this saying abroad among the brethren, that that disciple should not die: yet Jesus said not unto him, He shall not die; but, 
B043C021V024	43	21	24	This is the disciple who testifies of these things, and wrote these things: and we know that his testimony is true.
B043C021V025	43	21	25	And there are also many other things which Jesus did, the which, if they should be written every one, I suppose that even the world itself could not contain the books that should be written. Amen.
B044C001V001	44	1	1	The former treatise have I made, O Theophilus, of all that Jesus began both to do and teach,
B044C001V002	44	1	2	Until the day in which he was taken up, after he through the Holy Spirit had given commandments unto the apostles whom he had chosen:
B044C001V003	44	1	3	To whom also he showed himself alive after his passion by many infallible proofs, being seen of them forty days, and speaking of the things pertaining to the kingdom of God:
B044C001V004	44	1	4	And, being assembled together with them, commanded them that they should not depart from Jerusalem, but wait for the promise of the Father, 
B044C001V005	44	1	5	
        
B044C001V006	44	1	6	When they therefore were come together, they asked of him, saying, Lord, will you at this time restore again the kingdom to Israel?
B044C001V007	44	1	7	And he said unto them, 
B044C001V008	44	1	8	
        
B044C001V009	44	1	9	And when he had spoken these things, while they beheld, he was taken up; and a cloud received him out of their sight.
B044C001V010	44	1	10	And while they looked steadfastly toward heaven as he went up, behold, two men stood by them in white apparel;
B044C001V011	44	1	11	Who also said, You men of Galilee, why stand you gazing up into heaven? this same Jesus, who is taken up from you into heaven, shall so come in like manner as you have seen him go into heaven.
B044C001V012	44	1	12	Then returned they unto Jerusalem from the mount called Olivet, which is from Jerusalem a sabbath day's journey.
B044C001V013	44	1	13	And when they were come in, they went up into an upper room, where abode both Peter, and James, and John, and Andrew, Philip, and Thomas, Bartholomew, and Matthew, James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon the Zealot, and Judas the brother of James.
B044C001V014	44	1	14	These all continued with one accord in prayer and supplication, with the women, and Mary the mother of Jesus, and with his brothers.
B044C001V015	44	1	15	And in those days Peter stood up in the midst of the disciples, and said, (the number of names together were about a hundred and twenty,)
B044C001V016	44	1	16	Men and brethren, this scripture must needs have been fulfilled, which the Holy Spirit by the mouth of David spoke before concerning Judas, who was guide to them that took Jesus.
B044C001V017	44	1	17	For he was numbered with us, and had obtained part of this ministry.
B044C001V018	44	1	18	Now this man purchased a field with the reward of iniquity; and falling headlong, he burst asunder in the midst, and all his insides gushed out.
B044C001V019	44	1	19	And it was known unto all the dwellers at Jerusalem; since that field is called in their proper tongue, Akeldama, that is to say, The field of blood.
B044C001V020	44	1	20	For it is written in the book of Psalms, Let his habitation be desolate, and let no man dwell therein: and his office let another take.
B044C001V021	44	1	21	Therefore of these men who have accompanied with us all the time that the Lord Jesus went in and out among us,
B044C001V022	44	1	22	Beginning from the baptism of John, unto that same day that he was taken up from us, must one be ordained to be a witness with us of his resurrection.
B044C001V023	44	1	23	And they appointed two, Joseph called Barsabbas, who was surnamed Justus, and Matthias.
B044C001V024	44	1	24	And they prayed, and said, You, Lord, who know the hearts of all men, show which of these two you have chosen,
B044C001V025	44	1	25	That he may take part in this ministry and apostleship, from which Judas by transgression fell, that he might go to his own place.
B044C001V026	44	1	26	And they cast their lots; and the lot fell upon Matthias; and he was numbered with the eleven apostles.
B044C002V001	44	2	1	And when the day of Pentecost was fully come, they were all with one accord in one place.
B044C002V002	44	2	2	And suddenly there came a sound from heaven as of a rushing mighty wind, and it filled all the house where they were sitting.
B044C002V003	44	2	3	And there appeared unto them separated tongues like as of fire, and it sat upon each of them.
B044C002V004	44	2	4	And they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and began to speak with other tongues, as the Spirit gave them utterance.
B044C002V005	44	2	5	And there were dwelling at Jerusalem Jews, devout men, out of every nation under heaven.
B044C002V006	44	2	6	Now when this was sounded abroad, the multitude came together, and were confounded, because every man heard them speak in his own language.
B044C002V007	44	2	7	And they were all amazed and marveled, saying one to another, Behold, are not all these who speak Galileans?
B044C002V008	44	2	8	And how hear we every man in our own tongue, in which we were born?
B044C002V009	44	2	9	Parthians, and Medes, and Elamites, and the dwellers in Mesopotamia, and in Judea, and Cappadocia, in Pontus, and Asia,
B044C002V010	44	2	10	Phrygia, and Pamphylia, in Egypt, and in the parts of Libya about Cyrene, and visitors from Rome, Jews and proselytes,
B044C002V011	44	2	11	Cretans and Arabians, we do hear them speak in our tongues the wonderful works of God.
B044C002V012	44	2	12	And they were all amazed, and were in doubt, saying one to another, What means this?
B044C002V013	44	2	13	Others mocking said, These men are full of new wine.
B044C002V014	44	2	14	But Peter, standing up with the eleven, lifted up his voice, and said unto them, You men of Judea, and all you that dwell at Jerusalem, be this known unto you, and hearken to my words:
B044C002V015	44	2	15	For these are not drunken, as you suppose, seeing it is but the third hour of the day.
B044C002V016	44	2	16	But this is that which was spoken by the prophet Joel;
B044C002V017	44	2	17	
        
B044C002V018	44	2	18	
        
B044C002V019	44	2	19	
        
B044C002V020	44	2	20	
        
B044C002V021	44	2	21	
        
B044C002V022	44	2	22	You men of Israel, hear these words; Jesus of Nazareth, a man approved of God among you by miracles and wonders and signs, which God did by him in the midst of you, as you yourselves also know:
B044C002V023	44	2	23	Him, being delivered by the determinate counsel and foreknowledge of God, you have taken, and by wicked hands have crucified and slain:
B044C002V024	44	2	24	Whom God has raised up, having loosed the pains of death: because it was not possible that he should be held by it.
B044C002V025	44	2	25	For David spoke concerning him, 
B044C002V026	44	2	26	
        
B044C002V027	44	2	27	
        
B044C002V028	44	2	28	
        
B044C002V029	44	2	29	Men and brethren, let me freely speak unto you of the patriarch David, that he is both dead and buried, and his sepulcher is with us unto this day.
B044C002V030	44	2	30	Therefore being a prophet, and knowing that God had sworn with an oath to him, that of his descendants, according to the flesh, he would raise up Christ to sit on his throne;
B044C002V031	44	2	31	He seeing this before spoke of the resurrection of Christ, that his soul was not left in hades, neither his flesh did see corruption.
B044C002V032	44	2	32	This Jesus has God raised up, of which we all are witnesses.
B044C002V033	44	2	33	Therefore being by the right hand of God exalted, and having received of the Father the promise of the Holy Spirit, he has poured forth this, which you now see and hear.
B044C002V034	44	2	34	For David is not ascended into the heavens: but he said himself, The Lord said unto my Lord, 
B044C002V035	44	2	35	
        
B044C002V036	44	2	36	Therefore let all the house of Israel know assuredly, that God has made that same Jesus, whom you have crucified, both Lord and Christ.
B044C002V037	44	2	37	Now when they heard this, they were pricked in their hearts, and said unto Peter and to the rest of the apostles, Men and brethren, what shall we do?
B044C002V038	44	2	38	Then Peter said unto them, Repent, and be baptized every one of you in the name of Jesus Christ for the remission of sins, and you shall receive the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C002V039	44	2	39	For the promise is unto you, and to your children, and to all that are afar off, even as many as the Lord our God shall call.
B044C002V040	44	2	40	And with many other words did he testify and exhort, saying, Save yourselves from this corrupt generation.
B044C002V041	44	2	41	Then they that gladly received his word were baptized: and the same day there were added unto them about three thousand souls.
B044C002V042	44	2	42	And they continued steadfastly in the apostles' doctrine and fellowship, and in breaking of bread, and in prayers.
B044C002V043	44	2	43	And fear came upon every soul: and many wonders and signs were done by the apostles.
B044C002V044	44	2	44	And all that believed were together, and had all things common;
B044C002V045	44	2	45	And sold their possessions and goods, and distributed them to all men, as every man had need.
B044C002V046	44	2	46	And they, continuing daily with one accord in the temple, and breaking bread from house to house, did eat their food with gladness and sincerity of heart,
B044C002V047	44	2	47	Praising God, and having favor with all the people. And the Lord added to the church daily such as were being saved.
B044C003V001	44	3	1	Now Peter and John went up together into the temple at the hour of prayer, being the ninth hour.
B044C003V002	44	3	2	And a certain man lame from his mother's womb was carried, whom they laid daily at the gate of the temple which is called Beautiful, to ask alms of them that entered into the temple;
B044C003V003	44	3	3	Who seeing Peter and John about to go into the temple asked for alms.
B044C003V004	44	3	4	And Peter, fastening his eyes upon him with John, said, Look on us.
B044C003V005	44	3	5	And he gave heed unto them, expecting to receive something of them.
B044C003V006	44	3	6	Then Peter said, Silver and gold have I none; but such as I have I give you: In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth rise up and walk.
B044C003V007	44	3	7	And he took him by the right hand, and lifted him up: and immediately his feet and ankle bones received strength.
B044C003V008	44	3	8	And he leaping up stood, and walked, and entered with them into the temple, walking, and leaping, and praising God.
B044C003V009	44	3	9	And all the people saw him walking and praising God:
B044C003V010	44	3	10	And they knew that it was he who sat for alms at the Beautiful gate of the temple: and they were filled with wonder and amazement at that which had happened unto him.
B044C003V011	44	3	11	And as the lame man who was healed held Peter and John, all the people ran together unto them in the porch that is called Solomon's, greatly wondering.
B044C003V012	44	3	12	And when Peter saw it, he answered unto the people, You men of Israel, why marvel you at this? or why look you so earnestly on us, as though by our own power or holiness we had made this man to walk?
B044C003V013	44	3	13	The God of Abraham, and of Isaac, and of Jacob, the God of our fathers, has glorified his Son Jesus; whom you delivered up, and denied him in the presence of Pilate, when he was determined to let him go.
B044C003V014	44	3	14	But you denied the Holy One and the Just, and desired a murderer to be granted unto you;
B044C003V015	44	3	15	And killed the Prince of life, whom God has raised from the dead; of which we are witnesses.
B044C003V016	44	3	16	And his name through faith in his name has made this man strong, whom you see and know: yea, the faith which is by him has given him this perfect soundness in the presence of you all.
B044C003V017	44	3	17	And now, brethren, I know that through ignorance you did it, as did also your rulers.
B044C003V018	44	3	18	But those things, which God before had showed by the mouth of all his prophets, that Christ should suffer, he has so fulfilled.
B044C003V019	44	3	19	Repent therefore, and be converted, that your sins may be blotted out, when the times of refreshing shall come from the presence of the Lord;
B044C003V020	44	3	20	And he shall send Jesus Christ, who before was preached unto you:
B044C003V021	44	3	21	Whom the heaven must receive until the times of restitution of all things, which God has spoken by the mouth of all his holy prophets since the world began.
B044C003V022	44	3	22	For Moses truly said unto the fathers, A prophet shall the Lord your God raise up unto you of your brethren, like unto me; him shall you hear in all things whatsoever he shall say unto you.
B044C003V023	44	3	23	And it shall come to pass, that every soul, who will not hear that prophet, shall be destroyed from among the people.
B044C003V024	44	3	24	Yea, and all the prophets from Samuel and those that follow after, as many as have spoken, have likewise foretold of these days.
B044C003V025	44	3	25	You are the children of the prophets, and of the covenant which God made with our fathers, saying unto Abraham, 
B044C003V026	44	3	26	Unto you first God, having raised up his Son Jesus, sent him to bless you, in turning away every one of you from his iniquities.
B044C004V001	44	4	1	And as they spoke unto the people, the priests, and the captain of the temple, and the Sadducees, came upon them,
B044C004V002	44	4	2	Being grieved that they taught the people, and preached through Jesus the resurrection from the dead.
B044C004V003	44	4	3	And they laid hands on them, and put them in custody until the next day: for it was now evening.
B044C004V004	44	4	4	But many of them who heard the word believed; and the number of the men was about five thousand.
B044C004V005	44	4	5	And it came to pass on the next day, that their rulers, and elders, and scribes,
B044C004V006	44	4	6	And Annas the high priest, and Caiaphas, and John, and Alexander, and as many as were of the kindred of the high priest, were gathered together at Jerusalem.
B044C004V007	44	4	7	And when they had set them in the midst, they asked, By what power, or by what name, have you done this?
B044C004V008	44	4	8	Then Peter, filled with the Holy Spirit, said unto them, You rulers of the people, and elders of Israel,
B044C004V009	44	4	9	If we this day be examined of the good deed done to the crippled man, by what means he is made whole;
B044C004V010	44	4	10	Be it known unto you all, and to all the people of Israel, that by the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth, whom you crucified, whom God raised from the dead, even by him does this man stand here before you whole.
B044C004V011	44	4	11	This is the stone which was rejected by you builders, which has become the head of the corner.
B044C004V012	44	4	12	Neither is there salvation in any other: for there is no other name under heaven given among men, by which we must be saved.
B044C004V013	44	4	13	Now when they saw the boldness of Peter and John, and perceived that they were unlearned and ordinary men, they marveled; and they took knowledge of them, that they had been with Jesus.
B044C004V014	44	4	14	And beholding the man who was healed standing with them, they could say nothing against it.
B044C004V015	44	4	15	But when they had commanded them to go aside out of the council, they conferred among themselves,
B044C004V016	44	4	16	Saying, What shall we do to these men? for that indeed a notable miracle has been done by them is manifest to all them that dwell in Jerusalem; and we cannot deny it.
B044C004V017	44	4	17	But that it spread no further among the people, let us sternly threaten them, that they speak no longer to any man in this name.
B044C004V018	44	4	18	And they called them, and commanded them not to speak at all nor teach in the name of Jesus.
B044C004V019	44	4	19	But Peter and John answered and said unto them, Whether it be right in the sight of God to hearken unto you more than unto God, judge you.
B044C004V020	44	4	20	For we cannot but speak the things which we have seen and heard.
B044C004V021	44	4	21	So when they had further threatened them, they let them go, finding nothing for which they might punish them, because of the people: for all men glorified God for that which was done.
B044C004V022	44	4	22	For the man was above forty years old, on whom this miracle of healing was showed.
B044C004V023	44	4	23	And being let go, they went to their own company, and reported all that the chief priests and elders had said unto them.
B044C004V024	44	4	24	And when they heard that, they lifted up their voice to God with one accord, and said, Lord, you are God, who has made heaven, and earth, and the sea, and all that is in them:
B044C004V025	44	4	25	Who by the mouth of your servant David has said, Why did the nations rage, and the people imagine vain things?
B044C004V026	44	4	26	The kings of the earth stood up, and the rulers were gathered together against the Lord, and against his Christ.
B044C004V027	44	4	27	For of a truth against your holy child Jesus, whom you have anointed, both Herod, and Pontius Pilate, with the Gentiles, and the people of Israel, were gathered together,
B044C004V028	44	4	28	To do whatsoever your hand and your counsel determined before to be done.
B044C004V029	44	4	29	And now, Lord, behold their threatenings: and grant unto your servants, that with all boldness they may speak your word,
B044C004V030	44	4	30	By stretching forth your hand to heal; and that signs and wonders may be done by the name of your holy child Jesus.
B044C004V031	44	4	31	And when they had prayed, the place was shaken where they were assembled together; and they were all filled with the Holy Spirit, and they spoke the word of God with boldness.
B044C004V032	44	4	32	And the multitude of them that believed were of one heart and of one soul: neither said any of them that any of the things which he possessed was his own; but they had all things common.
B044C004V033	44	4	33	And with great power gave the apostles witness of the resurrection of the Lord Jesus: and great grace was upon them all.
B044C004V034	44	4	34	Neither was there any among them that lacked: for as many as were possessors of lands or houses sold them, and brought the prices of the things that were sold,
B044C004V035	44	4	35	And laid them down at the apostles' feet: and distribution was made unto every man according as he had need.
B044C004V036	44	4	36	And Joseph, who by the apostles was surnamed Barnabas, (which is, being interpreted, The son of encouragement,) a Levite, and of the country of Cyprus,
B044C004V037	44	4	37	Having land, sold it, and brought the money, and laid it at the apostles' feet.
B044C005V001	44	5	1	But a certain man named Ananias, with Sapphira his wife, sold a possession,
B044C005V002	44	5	2	And kept back part of the price, his wife also knowing it, and brought a certain part, and laid it at the apostles' feet.
B044C005V003	44	5	3	But Peter said, Ananias, why has Satan filled your heart to lie to the Holy Spirit, and to keep back part of the price of the land?
B044C005V004	44	5	4	While it remained, was it not your own? and after it was sold, was it not in your own power? why have you conceived this thing in your heart? you have not lied unto men, but unto God.
B044C005V005	44	5	5	And Ananias hearing these words fell down, and died: and great fear came on all them that heard these things.
B044C005V006	44	5	6	And the young men arose, wrapped him up, and carried him out, and buried him.
B044C005V007	44	5	7	And it was about the space of three hours later, when his wife, not knowing what was done, came in.
B044C005V008	44	5	8	And Peter said unto her, Tell me whether you sold the land for so much? And she said, Yea, for so much.
B044C005V009	44	5	9	Then Peter said unto her, How is it that you have agreed together to tempt the Spirit of the Lord? behold, the feet of them who have buried your husband are at the door, and shall carry you out.
B044C005V010	44	5	10	Then she fell down immediately at his feet, and died: and the young men came in, and found her dead, and, carrying her forth, buried her by her husband.
B044C005V011	44	5	11	And great fear came upon all the church, and upon as many as heard these things.
B044C005V012	44	5	12	And by the hands of the apostles were many signs and wonders done among the people; (and they were all with one accord in Solomon's porch.
B044C005V013	44	5	13	And of the rest dared no man join himself to them: but the people magnified them.
B044C005V014	44	5	14	And believers were the more added to the Lord, multitudes both of men and women.)
B044C005V015	44	5	15	So that they brought forth the sick into the streets, and laid them on beds and pallets, that at the least the shadow of Peter passing by might overshadow some of them.
B044C005V016	44	5	16	There came also a multitude out of the cities round about unto Jerusalem, bringing sick folks, and those who were tormented with unclean spirits: and they were healed every one.
B044C005V017	44	5	17	Then the high priest rose up, and all they that were with him, (which is the sect of the Sadducees,) and were filled with indignation,
B044C005V018	44	5	18	And laid their hands on the apostles, and put them in the common prison.
B044C005V019	44	5	19	But the angel of the Lord by night opened the prison doors, and brought them forth, and said,
B044C005V020	44	5	20	Go, stand and speak in the temple to the people all the words of this life.
B044C005V021	44	5	21	And when they heard that, they entered into the temple early in the morning, and taught. But the high priest came, and they that were with him, and called the council together, and all the senate of the children of Israel, and sent to the prison to have them brought.
B044C005V022	44	5	22	But when the officers came, and found them not in the prison, they returned, and told,
B044C005V023	44	5	23	Saying, The prison truly found we shut with all safety, and the keepers standing outside before the doors: but when we had opened it, we found no man within.
B044C005V024	44	5	24	Now when the high priest and the captain of the temple and the chief priests heard these things, they were perplexed of what might come of this.
B044C005V025	44	5	25	Then came one and told them, saying, Behold, the men whom you put in prison are standing in the temple, and teaching the people.
