B044C010V021	44	10	21	Then Peter went down to the men who were sent unto him from Cornelius; and said, Behold, I am he whom you seek: what is the cause for which you are come?
B044C010V022	44	10	22	And they said, Cornelius the centurion, a just man, and one that fears God, and of good report among all the nation of the Jews, was warned from God by a holy angel to send for you to come into his house, and to hear words from you.
B044C010V023	44	10	23	Then he called them in, and lodged them. And on the next day Peter went away with them, and certain brethren from Joppa accompanied him.
B044C010V024	44	10	24	And the next day they entered into Caesarea. And Cornelius waited for them, and had called together his kinsmen and near friends.
B044C010V025	44	10	25	And as Peter was coming in, Cornelius met him, and fell down at his feet, and worshiped him.
B044C010V026	44	10	26	But Peter took him up, saying, Stand up; I myself also am a man.
B044C010V027	44	10	27	And as he talked with him, he went in, and found many that were come together.
B044C010V028	44	10	28	And he said unto them, You know that it is an unlawful thing for a man that is a Jew to keep company, or come unto one of another nation; but God has showed me that I should not call any man common or unclean.
B044C010V029	44	10	29	Therefore I came unto you without questioning as soon as I was sent for: I ask therefore for what intent you have sent for me?
B044C010V030	44	10	30	And Cornelius said, Four days ago I was fasting until this hour; and at the ninth hour I prayed in my house, and, behold, a man stood before me in bright clothing,
B044C010V031	44	10	31	And said, Cornelius, your prayer is heard, and your alms are had in remembrance in the sight of God.
B044C010V032	44	10	32	Send therefore to Joppa, and call here Simon, whose surname is Peter; he is lodged in the house of one Simon a tanner by the seaside: who, when he comes, shall speak unto you.
B044C010V033	44	10	33	Immediately therefore I sent to you; and you have done well that you are come. Now therefore are we all here present before God, to hear all things that are commanded you of God.
B044C010V034	44	10	34	Then Peter opened his mouth, and said, Of a truth I perceive that God is no respecter of persons:
B044C010V035	44	10	35	But in every nation he that fears him, and works righteousness, is accepted with him.
B044C010V036	44	10	36	The word which God sent unto the children of Israel, preaching peace by Jesus Christ: (he is Lord of all:)
B044C010V037	44	10	37	That word, I say, you know, which was published throughout all Judea, and began from Galilee, after the baptism which John preached;
B044C010V038	44	10	38	How God anointed Jesus of Nazareth with the Holy Spirit and with power: who went about doing good, and healing all that were oppressed of the devil; for God was with him.
B044C010V039	44	10	39	And we are witnesses of all things which he did both in the land of the Jews, and in Jerusalem; whom they slew and hanged on a tree:
B044C010V040	44	10	40	Him God raised up the third day, and showed him openly;
B044C010V041	44	10	41	Not to all the people, but unto witnesses chosen before of God, even to us, who did eat and drink with him after he rose from the dead.
B044C010V042	44	10	42	And he commanded us to preach unto the people, and to testify that it is he who was ordained of God to be the Judge of the living and dead.
B044C010V043	44	10	43	To him give all the prophets witness, that through his name whosoever believes in him shall receive remission of sins.
B044C010V044	44	10	44	While Peter yet spoke these words, the Holy Spirit fell on all them who heard the word.
B044C010V045	44	10	45	And they of the circumcision who believed were astonished, as many as came with Peter, because that on the Gentiles also was poured out the gift of the Holy Spirit.
B044C010V046	44	10	46	For they heard them speak with tongues, and magnify God. Then answered Peter,
B044C010V047	44	10	47	Can any man forbid water, that these should not be baptized, who have received the Holy Spirit as well as we?
B044C010V048	44	10	48	And he commanded them to be baptized in the name of the Lord. Then they asked him to tarry certain days.
B044C011V001	44	11	1	And the apostles and brethren that were in Judea heard that the Gentiles had also received the word of God.
