B044C015V022	44	15	22	Then it pleased the apostles and elders, with the whole church, to send chosen men of their own company to Antioch with Paul and Barnabas; namely, Judas surnamed Barsabbas, and Silas, chief men among the brethren:
B044C015V023	44	15	23	And they wrote letters by them after this manner; The apostles and elders and brethren send greetings unto the brethren who are of the Gentiles in Antioch and Syria and Cilicia:
B044C015V024	44	15	24	Since we have heard that certain who went out from us have troubled you with words, unsettling your souls, saying, You must be circumcised, and keep the law: to whom we gave no such commandment:
B044C015V025	44	15	25	It seemed good unto us, being assembled with one accord, to send chosen men unto you with our beloved Barnabas and Paul,
B044C015V026	44	15	26	Men that have hazarded their lives for the name of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B044C015V027	44	15	27	We have sent therefore Judas and Silas, who shall also tell you the same things by mouth.
B044C015V028	44	15	28	For it seemed good to the Holy Spirit, and to us, to lay upon you no greater burden than these necessary things;
B044C015V029	44	15	29	That you abstain from anything offered to idols, and from blood, and from things strangled, and from fornication: from which if you keep yourselves, you shall do well. Farewell.
B044C015V030	44	15	30	So when they were dismissed, they came to Antioch: and when they had gathered the multitude together, they delivered the epistle:
B044C015V031	44	15	31	Which when they had read, they rejoiced for the exhortation.
B044C015V032	44	15	32	And Judas and Silas, being prophets also themselves, exhorted the brethren with many words, and strengthened them.
B044C015V033	44	15	33	And after they had tarried there awhile, they were let go in peace from the brethren unto the apostles.
B044C015V034	44	15	34	But it pleased Silas to abide there still.
B044C015V035	44	15	35	Paul also and Barnabas continued in Antioch, teaching and preaching the word of the Lord, with many others also.
B044C015V036	44	15	36	And some days later Paul said unto Barnabas, Let us go again and visit our brethren in every city where we have preached the word of the Lord, and see how they do.
B044C015V037	44	15	37	And Barnabas determined to take with them John, whose surname was Mark.
B044C015V038	44	15	38	But Paul thought it not good to take him with them, who departed from them from Pamphylia, and went not with them to the work.
B044C015V039	44	15	39	And the contention was so sharp between them, that they departed asunder one from the other: and so Barnabas took Mark, and sailed unto Cyprus;
B044C015V040	44	15	40	And Paul chose Silas, and departed, being commended by the brethren unto the grace of God.
B044C015V041	44	15	41	And he went through Syria and Cilicia, strengthening the churches.
B044C016V001	44	16	1	Then he came to Derbe and Lystra: and, behold, a certain disciple was there, named Timothy, the son of a certain woman, who was a Jewess, and believed; but his father was a Greek:
B044C016V002	44	16	2	Who was well reported of by the brethren that were at Lystra and Iconium.
B044C016V003	44	16	3	Him would Paul have to go forth with him; and took and circumcised him because of the Jews who were in those places: for they all knew that his father was a Greek.
B044C016V004	44	16	4	And as they went through the cities, they delivered them the decrees to keep, that were ordained of the apostles and elders who were at Jerusalem.
B044C016V005	44	16	5	And so were the churches established in the faith, and increased in number daily.
B044C016V006	44	16	6	Now when they had gone throughout Phrygia and the region of Galatia, and were forbidden of the Holy Spirit to preach the word in Asia,
B044C016V007	44	16	7	After they were come to Mysia, they attempted to go into Bithynia: but the Spirit permitted them not.
B044C016V008	44	16	8	And they passing by Mysia came down to Troas.
B044C016V009	44	16	9	And a vision appeared to Paul in the night; There stood a man of Macedonia, beseeching him, saying, Come over into Macedonia, and help us.
B044C016V010	44	16	10	And after he had seen the vision, immediately we endeavored to go into Macedonia, concluding that the Lord had called us to preach the gospel unto them.
B044C016V011	44	16	11	Therefore setting sail from Troas, we came with a straight course to Samothracia, and the next day to Neapolis;
B044C016V012	44	16	12	And from there to Philippi, which is the chief city of that part of Macedonia, and a colony: and we were in that city abiding certain days.
B044C016V013	44	16	13	And on the sabbath we went out of the city by a riverside, where prayer was accustomed to be made; and we sat down, and spoke unto the women who met there.
B044C016V014	44	16	14	And a certain woman named Lydia, a seller of purple, of the city of Thyatira, who worshiped God, heard us: whose heart the Lord opened, so that she attended unto the things which were spoken by Paul.
B044C016V015	44	16	15	And when she was baptized, and her household, she besought us, saying, If you have judged me to be faithful to the Lord, come into my house, and abide there. And she prevailed upon us.
B044C016V016	44	16	16	And it came to pass, as we went to prayer, a certain maid possessed with a spirit of divination met us, who brought her masters much gain by soothsaying:
B044C016V017	44	16	17	The same followed Paul and us, and cried, saying, These men are the servants of the most high God, who show unto us the way of salvation.
B044C016V018	44	16	18	And this did she many days. But Paul, being troubled, turned and said to the spirit, I command you in the name of Jesus Christ to come out of her. And he came out the same hour.
B044C016V019	44	16	19	And when her masters saw that the hope of their gains was gone, they caught Paul and Silas, and dragged them into the marketplace unto the rulers,
B044C016V020	44	16	20	And brought them to the magistrates, saying, These men, being Jews, do exceedingly trouble our city,
B044C016V021	44	16	21	And teach customs, which are not lawful for us to receive, neither to observe, being Romans.
B044C016V022	44	16	22	And the multitude rose up together against them: and the magistrates tore off their clothes, and commanded to beat them.
B044C016V023	44	16	23	And when they had laid many stripes upon them, they cast them into prison, charging the jailer to keep them safely:
B044C016V024	44	16	24	Who, having received such a charge, thrust them into the inner prison, and made their feet fast in the stocks.
B044C016V025	44	16	25	And at midnight Paul and Silas prayed, and sang praises unto God: and the prisoners heard them.
B044C016V026	44	16	26	And suddenly there was a great earthquake, so that the foundations of the prison were shaken: and immediately all the doors were opened, and every one's bands were loosed.
B044C016V027	44	16	27	And the keeper of the prison awaking out of his sleep, and seeing the prison doors open, he drew out his sword, and would have killed himself, supposing that the prisoners had fled.
B044C016V028	44	16	28	But Paul cried with a loud voice, saying, Do yourself no harm: for we are all here.
B044C016V029	44	16	29	Then he called for a light, and sprang in, and came trembling, and fell down before Paul and Silas,
B044C016V030	44	16	30	And brought them out, and said, Sirs, what must I do to be saved?
B044C016V031	44	16	31	And they said, Believe on the Lord Jesus Christ, and you shall be saved, and your house.
B044C016V032	44	16	32	And they spoke unto him the word of the Lord, and to all that were in his house.
B044C016V033	44	16	33	And he took them the same hour of the night, and washed their stripes; and was baptized, he and all his, immediately.
B044C016V034	44	16	34	And when he had brought them into his house, he sat food before them, and rejoiced, believing in God with all his house.
B044C016V035	44	16	35	And when it was day, the magistrates sent the officers, saying, Let those men go.
B044C016V036	44	16	36	And the keeper of the prison told this saying to Paul, The magistrates have sent to let you go: now therefore depart, and go in peace.
B044C016V037	44	16	37	But Paul said unto them, They have beaten us openly uncondemned, being Romans, and have cast us into prison; and now do they thrust us out secretly? nay verily; but let them come themselves and bring us out.
B044C016V038	44	16	38	And the officers told these words unto the magistrates: and they feared, when they heard that they were Romans.
B044C016V039	44	16	39	And they came and besought them, and brought them out, and desired them to depart out of the city.
B044C016V040	44	16	40	And they went out of the prison, and entered into the house of Lydia: and when they had seen the brethren, they comforted them, and departed.
B044C017V001	44	17	1	Now when they had passed through Amphipolis and Apollonia, they came to Thessalonica, where there was a synagogue of the Jews:
B044C017V002	44	17	2	And Paul, as his manner was, went in unto them, and three sabbath days reasoned with them out of the scriptures,
B044C017V003	44	17	3	Opening them up and alleging, that Christ must needs have suffered, and risen again from the dead; and that this Jesus, whom I preach unto you, is Christ.
B044C017V004	44	17	4	And some of them believed, and joined Paul and Silas; and of the devout Greeks a great multitude, and of the chief women not a few.
B044C017V005	44	17	5	But the Jews who believed not, moved with envy, took unto them certain wicked fellows of the rabble, and gathered a company, and set all the city in an uproar, and assaulted the house of Jason, and sought to bring them out to the people.
B044C017V006	44	17	6	And when they found them not, they drew Jason and certain brethren unto the rulers of the city, crying, These that have turned the world upside down are come here also;
B044C017V007	44	17	7	Whom Jason has received: and these all do contrary to the decrees of Caesar, saying that there is another king, one Jesus.
B044C017V008	44	17	8	And they troubled the people and the rulers of the city, when they heard these things.
B044C017V009	44	17	9	And when they had taken security of Jason, and of the other, they let them go.
B044C017V010	44	17	10	And the brethren immediately sent away Paul and Silas by night unto Berea: who coming there went into the synagogue of the Jews.
B044C017V011	44	17	11	These were more noble than those in Thessalonica, in that they received the word with all readiness of mind, and searched the scriptures daily, whether those things were so.
B044C017V012	44	17	12	Therefore many of them believed; also of honorable women who were Greeks, and of men, not a few.
B044C017V013	44	17	13	But when the Jews of Thessalonica had knowledge that the word of God was preached by Paul at Berea, they came there also, and stirred up the people.
B044C017V014	44	17	14	And then immediately the brethren sent away Paul to go as it were to the sea: but Silas and Timothy abode there still.
B044C017V015	44	17	15	And they that conducted Paul brought him unto Athens: and receiving a commandment unto Silas and Timothy to come to him with all speed, they departed.
B044C017V016	44	17	16	Now while Paul waited for them at Athens, his spirit was stirred in him, when he saw the city wholly given to idolatry.
B044C017V017	44	17	17	Therefore disputed he in the synagogue with the Jews, and with the devout persons, and in the market daily with them that met with him.
B044C017V018	44	17	18	Then certain philosophers of the Epicureans, and of the Stoics, encountered him. And some said, What will this babbler say? Others, He seems to be a setter forth of strange gods: because he preached unto them Jesus, and the resurrection.
B044C017V019	44	17	19	And they took him, and brought him unto Areopagus, saying, May we know what this new doctrine, whereof you speak, is?
B044C017V020	44	17	20	For you bring certain strange things to our ears: we would know therefore what these things mean.
B044C017V021	44	17	21	(For all the Athenians and strangers who were there spent their time in nothing else, but either to tell, or to hear some new thing.)
B044C017V022	44	17	22	Then Paul stood in the midst of Mars' hill, and said, You men of Athens, I perceive that in all things you are very religious.
B044C017V023	44	17	23	For as I passed by, and beheld your devotions, I found an altar with this inscription, TO THE UNKNOWN GOD. Whom therefore you ignorantly worship, him declare I unto you.
B044C017V024	44	17	24	God that made the world and all things therein, seeing that he is Lord of heaven and earth, dwells not in temples made with hands;
B044C017V025	44	17	25	Neither is worshiped with men's hands, as though he needed anything, seeing he gives to all life, and breath, and all things;
B044C017V026	44	17	26	And has made of one blood all nations of men to dwell on all the face of the earth, and has determined the times before appointed, and the bounds of their habitation;
B044C017V027	44	17	27	That they should seek the Lord, if perhaps they might feel after him, and find him, though he be not far from every one of us:
B044C017V028	44	17	28	For in him we live, and move, and have our being; as certain also of your own poets have said, For we are also his offspring.
B044C017V029	44	17	29	Therefore then as we are the offspring of God, we ought not to think that the Deity is like unto gold, or silver, or stone, graven by art and man's device.
B044C017V030	44	17	30	And the times of this ignorance God overlooked; but now commands all men everywhere to repent:
B044C017V031	44	17	31	Because he has appointed a day, in which he will judge the world in righteousness by that man whom he has ordained; and of this he has given assurance unto all men, in that he has raised him from the dead.
B044C017V032	44	17	32	And when they heard of the resurrection of the dead, some mocked: and others said, We will hear you again of this matter.
B044C017V033	44	17	33	So Paul departed from among them.
B044C017V034	44	17	34	But certain men joined unto him, and believed: among whom was Dionysius the Areopagite, and a woman named Damaris, and others with them.
B044C018V001	44	18	1	After these things Paul departed from Athens, and came to Corinth;
B044C018V002	44	18	2	And found a certain Jew named Aquila, born in Pontus, lately come from Italy, with his wife Priscilla; (because Claudius had commanded all Jews to depart from Rome:) and came unto them.
B044C018V003	44	18	3	And because he was of the same craft, he abode with them, and worked: for by their occupation they were tentmakers.
B044C018V004	44	18	4	And he reasoned in the synagogue every sabbath, and persuaded the Jews and the Greeks.
B044C018V005	44	18	5	And when Silas and Timothy were come from Macedonia, Paul was pressed in the word, and testified to the Jews that Jesus was the Christ.
B044C018V006	44	18	6	And when they opposed themselves, and blasphemed, he shook his clothes, and said unto them, Your blood be upon your own heads; I am clean: from henceforth I will go unto the Gentiles.
B044C018V007	44	18	7	And he departed from there, and entered into a certain man's house, named Justus, one that worshiped God, whose house was next door to the synagogue.
B044C018V008	44	18	8	And Crispus, the chief ruler of the synagogue, believed on the Lord with all his house; and many of the Corinthians hearing believed, and were baptized.
B044C018V009	44	18	9	Then spoke the Lord to Paul in the night by a vision, 
B044C018V010	44	18	10	
        
B044C018V011	44	18	11	And he continued there a year and six months, teaching the word of God among them.
B044C018V012	44	18	12	And when Gallio was the deputy of Achaia, the Jews made an attack with one accord against Paul, and brought him to the judgment seat,
B044C018V013	44	18	13	Saying, This fellow persuades men to worship God contrary to the law.
B044C018V014	44	18	14	And when Paul was now about to open his mouth, Gallio said unto the Jews, If it were a matter of wrong or wicked crime, O you Jews, reason would that I should bear with you:
B044C018V015	44	18	15	But if it be a question of words and names, and of your law, look you to it; for I will be no judge of such matters.
B044C018V016	44	18	16	And he drove them from the judgment seat.
B044C018V017	44	18	17	Then all the Greeks took Sosthenes, the chief ruler of the synagogue, and beat him before the judgment seat. And Gallio cared for none of those things.
B044C018V018	44	18	18	And Paul after this tarried there yet a good while, and then took his leave of the brethren, and sailed from there into Syria, and with him Priscilla and Aquila; having shaved his head in Cenchrea: for he had a vow.
B044C018V019	44	18	19	And he came to Ephesus, and left them there: but he himself entered into the synagogue, and reasoned with the Jews.
B044C018V020	44	18	20	When they desired him to tarry a longer time with them, he consented not;
B044C018V021	44	18	21	But bade them farewell, saying, I must by all means keep this feast that comes in Jerusalem: but I will return again unto you, if God wills. And he sailed from Ephesus.
B044C018V022	44	18	22	And when he had landed at Caesarea, having gone up, and greeted the church, he went down to Antioch.
B044C018V023	44	18	23	And after he had spent some time there, he departed, and went over all the country of Galatia and Phrygia in order, strengthening all the disciples.
B044C018V024	44	18	24	And a certain Jew named Apollos, born at Alexandria, an eloquent man, and mighty in the scriptures, came to Ephesus.
B044C018V025	44	18	25	This man was instructed in the way of the Lord; and being fervent in the spirit, he spoke and taught diligently the things of the Lord, knowing only the baptism of John.
B044C018V026	44	18	26	And he began to speak boldly in the synagogue: whom when Aquila and Priscilla had heard, they took him unto them, and expounded unto him the way of God more perfectly.
B044C018V027	44	18	27	And when he was disposed to pass into Achaia, the brethren wrote, exhorting the disciples to receive him: who, when he was come, helped them much who had believed through grace:
B044C018V028	44	18	28	For he mightily convinced the Jews, and that publicly, showing by the scriptures that Jesus was the Christ.
B044C019V001	44	19	1	And it came to pass, that, while Apollos was at Corinth, Paul having passed through the upper country came to Ephesus: and finding certain disciples,
B044C019V002	44	19	2	He said unto them, Received you the Holy Spirit when you believed? And they said unto him, We have not so much as heard whether there be any Holy Spirit.
B044C019V003	44	19	3	And he said unto them, Unto what then were you baptized? And they said, Unto John's baptism.
B044C019V004	44	19	4	Then said Paul, John verily baptized with the baptism of repentance, saying unto the people, that they should believe on him who should come after him, that is, on Christ Jesus.
B044C019V005	44	19	5	When they heard this, they were baptized in the name of the Lord Jesus.
B044C019V006	44	19	6	And when Paul had laid his hands upon them, the Holy Spirit came on them; and they spoke with tongues, and prophesied.
B044C019V007	44	19	7	And all the men were about twelve.
B044C019V008	44	19	8	And he went into the synagogue, and spoke boldly for the space of three months, arguing and persuading the things concerning the kingdom of God.
B044C019V009	44	19	9	But when some were hardened, and believed not, but spoke evil of that way before the multitude, he departed from them, and separated the disciples, arguing daily in the school of one Tyrannus.
B044C019V010	44	19	10	And this continued by the space of two years; so that all they who dwelt in Asia heard the word of the Lord Jesus, both Jews and Greeks.
B044C019V011	44	19	11	And God did special miracles by the hands of Paul:
B044C019V012	44	19	12	So that from his body were brought unto the sick handkerchiefs or aprons, and the diseases departed from them, and the evil spirits went out of them.
B044C019V013	44	19	13	Then certain of the vagabond Jews, exorcists, took upon themselves to call over them who had evil spirits the name of the Lord Jesus, saying, We adjure you by Jesus whom Paul preaches.
B044C019V014	44	19	14	And there were seven sons of one Sceva, a Jew, and chief of the priests, who did so.
B044C019V015	44	19	15	And the evil spirit answered and said, Jesus I know, and Paul I know; but who are you?
B044C019V016	44	19	16	And the man in whom the evil spirit was leaped on them, and overcame them, and prevailed against them, so that they fled out of that house naked and wounded.
B044C019V017	44	19	17	And this was known to all the Jews and Greeks also dwelling at Ephesus; and fear fell on them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified.
B044C019V018	44	19	18	And many that believed came, and confessed, and told of their deeds.
B044C019V019	44	19	19	Many of them also who used magic arts brought their books together, and burned them before all men: and they counted the price of them, and found it fifty thousand pieces of silver.
B044C019V020	44	19	20	So mightily grew the word of God and prevailed.
B044C019V021	44	19	21	After these things were ended, Paul purposed in the spirit, when he had passed through Macedonia and Achaia, to go to Jerusalem, saying, After I have been there, I must also see Rome.
B044C019V022	44	19	22	So he sent into Macedonia two of them that ministered unto him, Timothy and Erastus; but he himself stayed in Asia for a time.
B044C019V023	44	19	23	And the same time there arose no small stir about that way.
B044C019V024	44	19	24	For a certain man named Demetrius, a silversmith, who made silver shrines for Diana, brought no small gain unto the craftsmen;
B044C019V025	44	19	25	Whom he called together with the workmen of like occupation, and said, Sirs, you know that by this craft we have our wealth.
B044C019V026	44	19	26	Moreover you see and hear, that not alone at Ephesus, but almost throughout all Asia, this Paul has persuaded and turned away many people, saying that they are no gods, which are made with hands:
B044C019V027	44	19	27	So that not only this our craft is in danger to be discredited; but also that the temple of the great goddess Diana should be despised, and her magnificence should be destroyed, whom all Asia and the world worship.
B044C019V028	44	19	28	And when they heard these sayings, they were full of wrath, and cried out, saying, Great is Diana of the Ephesians.
B044C019V029	44	19	29	And the whole city was filled with confusion: and having caught Gaius and Aristarchus, men of Macedonia, Paul's companions in travel, they rushed with one accord into the theater.
B044C019V030	44	19	30	And when Paul would have entered in unto the people, the disciples allowed him not.
B044C019V031	44	19	31	And certain of the chief of Asia, who were his friends, sent unto him, begging him that he would not venture into the theater.
B044C019V032	44	19	32	Some therefore cried one thing, and some another: for the assembly was confused; and the majority knew not why they were come together.
B044C019V033	44	19	33	And they drew Alexander out of the multitude, the Jews putting him forward. And Alexander beckoned with the hand, and would have made his defense unto the people.
B044C019V034	44	19	34	But when they knew that he was a Jew, all with one voice about the space of two hours cried out, Great is Diana of the Ephesians.
B044C019V035	44	19	35	And when the town clerk had quieted the people, he said, You men of Ephesus, what man is there that knows not how that the city of the Ephesians is a worshiper of the great goddess Diana, and of the image which fell down from Jupiter?
B044C019V036	44	19	36	Seeing then that these things cannot be spoken against, you ought to be quiet, and to do nothing rashly.
B044C019V037	44	19	37	For you have brought here these men, who are neither robbers of temples, nor yet blasphemers of your goddess.
B044C019V038	44	19	38	Therefore if Demetrius, and the craftsmen who are with him, have a matter against any man, the law is open, and there are deputies: let them charge one another.
B044C019V039	44	19	39	But if you inquire anything concerning other matters, it shall be determined in a lawful assembly.
B044C019V040	44	19	40	For we are in danger to be called in question for this day's uproar, there being no cause for which we may give an account of this commotion.
B044C019V041	44	19	41	And when he had thus spoken, he dismissed the assembly.
B044C020V001	44	20	1	And after the uproar was ceased, Paul called unto him the disciples, and embraced them, and departed to go into Macedonia.
B044C020V002	44	20	2	And when he had gone through those parts, and had given them much exhortation, he came into Greece,
B044C020V003	44	20	3	And there abode three months. And when the Jews laid wait for him, as he was about to sail into Syria, he purposed to return through Macedonia.
B044C020V004	44	20	4	And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timothy; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus.
B044C020V005	44	20	5	These going before tarried for us at Troas.
B044C020V006	44	20	6	And we sailed away from Philippi after the days of unleavened bread, and came unto them at Troas in five days; where we abode seven days.
B044C020V007	44	20	7	And upon the first day of the week, when the disciples came together to break bread, Paul preached unto them, ready to depart on the next day; and continued his speech until midnight.
B044C020V008	44	20	8	And there were many lights in the upper chamber, where they were gathered together.
B044C020V009	44	20	9	And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus, being fallen into a deep sleep: and as Paul was long preaching, he sunk down with sleep, and fell down from the third loft, and was taken up dead.
B044C020V010	44	20	10	And Paul went down, and fell upon him, and embracing him said, Trouble not yourselves; for his life is in him.
B044C020V011	44	20	11	When he therefore was come up again, and had broken bread, and eaten, and talked a long while, even till break of day, so he departed.
B044C020V012	44	20	12	And they brought the young man alive, and were not a little comforted.
B044C020V013	44	20	13	And we went ahead to the ship, and sailed unto Assos, there intending to take aboard Paul: for so had he appointed, intending himself to go on foot.
B044C020V014	44	20	14	And when he met with us at Assos, we took him aboard, and came to Mitylene.
B044C020V015	44	20	15	And we sailed from there, and came the next day opposite Chios; and the next day we arrived at Samos, and tarried at Trogyllium; and the next day we came to Miletus.
B044C020V016	44	20	16	For Paul had determined to sail past Ephesus, because he would not spend the time in Asia: for he hastened, if it were possible for him, to be at Jerusalem the day of Pentecost.
B044C020V017	44	20	17	And from Miletus he sent to Ephesus, and called the elders of the church.
B044C020V018	44	20	18	And when they were come to him, he said unto them, You know, from the first day that I came into Asia, after what manner I have been with you at all times,
B044C020V019	44	20	19	Serving the Lord with all humility of mind, and with many tears, and temptations, which befell me by the lying in wait of the Jews:
B044C020V020	44	20	20	And how I kept back nothing that was profitable unto you, but have showed you, and have taught you publicly, and from house to house,
B044C020V021	44	20	21	Testifying both to the Jews, and also to the Greeks, repentance toward God, and faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ.
B044C020V022	44	20	22	And now, behold, I go bound in the spirit unto Jerusalem, not knowing the things that shall befall me there:
B044C020V023	44	20	23	Except that the Holy Spirit witnesses in every city, saying that bonds and afflictions await me.
B044C020V024	44	20	24	But none of these things move me, neither count I my life dear unto myself, so that I might finish my course with joy, and the ministry, which I have received of the Lord Jesus, to testify the gospel of the grace of God.
B044C020V025	44	20	25	And now, behold, I know that you all, among whom I have gone preaching the kingdom of God, shall see my face no more.
B044C020V026	44	20	26	Therefore I testify to you this day, that I am pure from the blood of all men.
B044C020V027	44	20	27	For I have not shunned to declare unto you all the counsel of God.
B044C020V028	44	20	28	Take heed therefore unto yourselves, and to all the flock, over which the Holy Spirit has made you overseers, to feed the church of God, which he has purchased with his own blood.
