B044C020V030	44	20	30	Also of your own selves shall men arise, speaking perverse things, to draw away disciples after them.
B044C020V031	44	20	31	Therefore watch, and remember, that by the space of three years I ceased not to warn everyone night and day with tears.
B044C020V032	44	20	32	And now, brethren, I commend you to God, and to the word of his grace, which is able to build you up, and to give you an inheritance among all them who are sanctified.
B044C020V033	44	20	33	I have coveted no man's silver, or gold, or apparel.
B044C020V034	44	20	34	Yea, you yourselves know, that these hands have ministered unto my necessities, and to them that were with me.
B044C020V035	44	20	35	I have showed you all things, how that so laboring you ought to support the weak, and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus, how he said, 
B044C020V036	44	20	36	And when he had thus spoken, he kneeled down, and prayed with them all.
B044C020V037	44	20	37	And they all wept much, and fell on Paul's neck, and kissed him,
B044C020V038	44	20	38	Sorrowing most of all for the words which he spoke, that they should see his face no more. And they accompanied him unto the ship.
B044C021V001	44	21	1	And it came to pass, that after we were parted from them, and had set sail, we came with a straight course unto Cos, and the day following unto Rhodes, and from there unto Patara:
B044C021V002	44	21	2	And finding a ship sailing over unto Phoenicia, we went aboard, and set forth.
