B044C024V001	44	24	1	And after five days Ananias the high priest descended with the elders, and with a certain orator named Tertullus, who informed the governor against Paul.
B044C024V002	44	24	2	And when he was called forth, Tertullus began to accuse him, saying, Seeing that by you we enjoy great quietness, and that very worthy deeds are done unto this nation by your provision,
B044C024V003	44	24	3	We accept it always, and in all places, most noble Felix, with all thankfulness.
B044C024V004	44	24	4	Nevertheless, that I be not further tedious unto you, I pray you that you would hear us in your kindness a few words.
B044C024V005	44	24	5	For we have found this man a pestilent fellow, and a mover of sedition among all the Jews throughout the world, and a ringleader of the sect of the Nazarenes:
B044C024V006	44	24	6	Who also has gone about to profane the temple: whom we took, and would have judged according to our law.
