B058C005V014	58	5	14	But solid food belongs to them that are of full age, even those who by reason of use have their senses exercised to discern both good and evil.
B058C006V001	58	6	1	Therefore leaving the principles of the doctrine of Christ, let us go on unto maturity; not laying again the foundation of repentance from dead works, and of faith toward God,
B058C006V002	58	6	2	Of the doctrine of baptisms, and of laying on of hands, and of resurrection of the dead, and of eternal judgment.
B058C006V003	58	6	3	And this will we do, if God permits.
