B058C011V001	58	11	1	Now faith is the substance of things hoped for, the evidence of things not seen.
B058C011V002	58	11	2	For by it the elders obtained approval.
B058C011V003	58	11	3	Through faith we understand that the worlds were framed by the word of God, so that things which are seen were not made of things which do appear.
B058C011V004	58	11	4	By faith Abel offered unto God a more excellent sacrifice than Cain, by which he obtained witness that he was righteous, God testifying of his gifts: and by it he being dead yet speaks.
B058C011V005	58	11	5	By faith Enoch was translated that he should not see death; and was not found, because God had translated him: for before his translation he had this testimony, that he pleased God.
B058C011V006	58	11	6	But without faith it is impossible to please him: for he that comes to God must believe that he is, and that he is a rewarder of them that diligently seek him.
B058C011V007	58	11	7	By faith Noah, being warned of God of things not seen as yet, moved by fear, prepared an ark to the saving of his house; by which he condemned the world, and became heir of the righteousness which is by faith.
B058C011V008	58	11	8	By faith Abraham, when he was called to go out into a place which he should later receive for an inheritance, obeyed; and he went out, not knowing where he went.
B058C011V009	58	11	9	By faith he sojourned in the land of promise, as in a foreign land, dwelling in tents with Isaac and Jacob, the heirs with him of the same promise:
B058C011V010	58	11	10	For he looked for a city which has foundations, whose builder and maker is God.
B058C011V011	58	11	11	Through faith also Sara herself received strength to conceive, and was delivered of a child when she was past age, because she judged him faithful who had promised.
B058C011V012	58	11	12	Therefore sprang there even of one, and him as good as dead, so many as the stars of the sky in multitude, and as the sand which is by the seashore innumerable.
B058C011V013	58	11	13	These all died in faith, not having received the promises, but having seen them afar off, and were persuaded of them, and embraced them, and confessed that they were strangers and exiles on the earth.
B058C011V014	58	11	14	For they that say such things declare plainly that they seek a country.
B058C011V015	58	11	15	And truly, if they had been mindful of that country from which they came out, they might have had opportunity to have returned.
B058C011V016	58	11	16	But now they desire a better country, that is, a heavenly: therefore God is not ashamed to be called their God: for he has prepared for them a city.
B058C011V017	58	11	17	By faith Abraham, when he was tested, offered up Isaac: and he that had received the promises offered up his only begotten son.
B058C011V018	58	11	18	Of whom it was said, 
B058C011V019	58	11	19	Accounting that God was able to raise him up, even from the dead; from which also he received him in a figure.
B058C011V020	58	11	20	By faith Isaac blessed Jacob and Esau concerning things to come.
B058C011V021	58	11	21	By faith Jacob, when he was dying, blessed both the sons of Joseph; and worshiped, leaning upon the top of his staff.
B058C011V022	58	11	22	By faith Joseph, when he died, made mention of the departing of the children of Israel; and gave commandment concerning his bones.
B058C011V023	58	11	23	By faith Moses, when he was born, was hid three months by his parents, because they saw he was a beautiful child; and they were not afraid of the king's commandment.
B058C011V024	58	11	24	By faith Moses, when he was grown up, refused to be called the son of Pharaoh's daughter;
B058C011V025	58	11	25	Choosing rather to suffer affliction with the people of God, than to enjoy the pleasures of sin for a time;
B058C011V026	58	11	26	Esteeming the reproach of the Christ greater riches than the treasures in Egypt: for he looked for the recompense of the reward.
B058C011V027	58	11	27	By faith he forsook Egypt, not fearing the wrath of the king: for he endured, as seeing him who is invisible.
B058C011V028	58	11	28	Through faith he kept the passover, and the sprinkling of blood, lest he that destroyed the firstborn should touch them.
B058C011V029	58	11	29	By faith they passed through the Red sea as on dry land: which the Egyptians attempting to do were drowned.
B058C011V030	58	11	30	By faith the walls of Jericho fell down, after they were encircled seven days.
B058C011V031	58	11	31	By faith the harlot Rahab perished not with them that believed not, when she had received the spies with peace.
B058C011V032	58	11	32	And what shall I say more? for the time would fail me to tell of Gideon, and of Barak, and of Samson, and of Jephthah; of David also, and Samuel, and of the prophets:
B058C011V033	58	11	33	Who through faith subdued kingdoms, worked righteousness, obtained promises, stopped the mouths of lions,
B058C011V034	58	11	34	Quenched the violence of fire, escaped the edge of the sword, out of weakness were made strong, became valiant in war, turned to flight the armies of foreigners.
B058C011V035	58	11	35	Women received their dead raised to life again: and others were tortured, not accepting deliverance; that they might obtain a better resurrection:
B058C011V036	58	11	36	And others had trial of cruel mockings and scourgings, yea, moreover of bonds and imprisonment:
B058C011V037	58	11	37	They were stoned, they were sawn asunder, were tempted, were slain with the sword: they wandered about in sheepskins and goatskins; being destitute, afflicted, tormented;
B058C011V038	58	11	38	(Of whom the world was not worthy:) they wandered in deserts, and in mountains, and in dens and caves of the earth.
B058C011V039	58	11	39	And these all, having obtained a good report through faith, received not the promise:
B058C011V040	58	11	40	God having provided some better thing for us, that they without us should not be made perfect.
B058C012V001	58	12	1	Therefore seeing we also are surrounded with so great a cloud of witnesses, let us lay aside every weight, and the sin which does so easily ensnare us, and let us run with patience the race that is set before us,
B058C012V002	58	12	2	Looking unto Jesus the author and perfecter of our faith; who for the joy that was set before him endured the cross, despising the shame, and is seated at the right hand of the throne of God.
B058C012V003	58	12	3	For consider him that endured such hostility of sinners against himself, lest you be wearied and faint in your minds.
B058C012V004	58	12	4	You have not yet resisted unto blood, striving against sin.
B058C012V005	58	12	5	And you have forgotten the exhortation which speaks unto you as unto children, My son, despise not the chastening of the Lord, nor faint when you are rebuked of him:
B058C012V006	58	12	6	For whom the Lord loves he chastens, and scourges every son whom he receives.
B058C012V007	58	12	7	If you endure chastening, God deals with you as with sons; for what son is he whom the father chastens not?
B058C012V008	58	12	8	But if you be without chastisement, of which all are partakers, then are you illegitimate children, and not sons.
B058C012V009	58	12	9	Furthermore we have had fathers of our flesh who corrected us, and we gave them reverence: shall we not much rather be in subjection unto the Father of spirits, and live?
B058C012V010	58	12	10	For they verily for a few days chastened us after their own pleasure; but he for our profit, that we might be partakers of his holiness.
B058C012V011	58	12	11	Now no chastening for the present seems to be joyous, but grievous: nevertheless afterward it yields the peaceable fruit of righteousness unto them who are trained by it.
B058C012V012	58	12	12	Therefore lift up the hands which hang down, and the feeble knees;
B058C012V013	58	12	13	And make straight paths for your feet, lest that which is lame be turned out of the way; but let it rather be healed.
B058C012V014	58	12	14	Follow peace with all men, and holiness, without which no man shall see the Lord:
B058C012V015	58	12	15	Looking diligently lest any man fall short of the grace of God; lest any root of bitterness springing up trouble you, and thereby many be defiled;
B058C012V016	58	12	16	Lest there be any immoral, or profane person, as Esau, who for one morsel of food sold his birthright.
B058C012V017	58	12	17	For you know how that afterward, when he would have inherited the blessing, he was rejected: for he found no place of repentance, though he sought it carefully with tears.
B058C012V018	58	12	18	For you are not come unto the mount that might be touched, and that burned with fire, nor unto blackness, and darkness, and tempest,
B058C012V019	58	12	19	And the sound of a trumpet, and the voice of words; which voice they that heard entreated that the word should not be spoken to them any more:
B058C012V020	58	12	20	(For they could not endure that which was commanded, 
B058C012V021	58	12	21	And so terrible was the sight, that Moses said, I exceedingly fear and quake:)
B058C012V022	58	12	22	But you are come unto mount Zion, and unto the city of the living God, the heavenly Jerusalem, and to an innumerable company of angels,
B058C012V023	58	12	23	To the general assembly and church of the firstborn, who are written in heaven, and to God the Judge of all, and to the spirits of just men made perfect,
B058C012V024	58	12	24	And to Jesus the mediator of the new covenant, and to the blood of sprinkling, that speaks better things than that of Abel.
B058C012V025	58	12	25	See that you refuse not him that speaks. For if they escaped not who refused him that spoke on earth, much more shall we not escape, if we turn away from him that speaks from heaven:
B058C012V026	58	12	26	Whose voice then shook the earth: but now he has promised, saying, 
B058C012V027	58	12	27	And this word, 
B058C012V028	58	12	28	Therefore we receiving a kingdom which cannot be moved, let us have grace, by which we may serve God acceptably with reverence and godly fear:
B058C012V029	58	12	29	For our God is a consuming fire.
B058C013V001	58	13	1	Let brotherly love continue.
B058C013V002	58	13	2	Be not forgetful to entertain strangers: for thereby some have entertained angels unawares.
B058C013V003	58	13	3	Remember them that are in bonds, as bound with them; and them who suffer adversity, as being yourselves also in the body.
B058C013V004	58	13	4	Let marriage be held in honor by all, and the bed undefiled: but fornicators and adulterers God will judge.
B058C013V005	58	13	5	Let your conduct be without covetousness; and be content with such things as you have: for he has said, 
B058C013V006	58	13	6	So that we may boldly say, The Lord is my helper, and I will not fear what man shall do unto me.
B058C013V007	58	13	7	Remember them who have the rule over you, who have spoken unto you the word of God: whose faith follow, considering the end of their manner of life.
B058C013V008	58	13	8	Jesus Christ the same yesterday, and today, and forever.
B058C013V009	58	13	9	Be not carried about with various and strange doctrines. For it is a good thing that the heart be established with grace; not with foods, which have not profited them that have been observing them.
B058C013V010	58	13	10	We have an altar, of which they have no right to eat who serve the tabernacle.
B058C013V011	58	13	11	For the bodies of those animals, whose blood is brought into the sanctuary by the high priest for sin, are burned outside the camp.
B058C013V012	58	13	12	Therefore Jesus also, that he might sanctify the people with his own blood, suffered outside the gate.
B058C013V013	58	13	13	Let us go forth therefore unto him outside the camp, bearing his reproach.
B058C013V014	58	13	14	For here have we no continuing city, but we seek one to come.
B058C013V015	58	13	15	By him therefore let us offer the sacrifice of praise to God continually, that is, the fruit of our lips giving thanks to his name.
B058C013V016	58	13	16	But to do good and to share forget not: for with such sacrifices God is well pleased.
B058C013V017	58	13	17	Obey them that have the rule over you, and submit yourselves: for they watch for your souls, as they that must give account, that they may do it with joy, and not with grief: for that is unprofitable for you.
B058C013V018	58	13	18	Pray for us: for we trust we have a good conscience, in all things willing to live honestly.
B058C013V019	58	13	19	But I beseech you rather to do this, that I may be restored to you the sooner.
B058C013V020	58	13	20	Now the God of peace, that brought again from the dead our Lord Jesus, that great shepherd of the sheep, through the blood of the everlasting covenant,
B058C013V021	58	13	21	Make you complete in every good work to do his will, working in you that which is well pleasing in his sight, through Jesus Christ; to whom be glory forever and ever. Amen.
B058C013V022	58	13	22	And I beseech you, brethren, bear with the word of exhortation: for I have written a letter unto you in few words.
B058C013V023	58	13	23	Know that our brother Timothy is set at liberty; with whom, if he comes shortly, I will see you.
B058C013V024	58	13	24	Greet all them that have the rule over you, and all the saints. They of Italy greet you.
B058C013V025	58	13	25	Grace be with you all. Amen.
B059C001V001	59	1	1	James, a servant of God and of the Lord Jesus Christ, to the twelve tribes which are scattered abroad, greeting.
B059C001V002	59	1	2	My brethren, count it all joy when you fall into various trials;
B059C001V003	59	1	3	Knowing this, that the trying of your faith works patience.
B059C001V004	59	1	4	But let patience have her perfect work, that you may be perfect and entire, lacking in nothing.
B059C001V005	59	1	5	If any of you lacks wisdom, let him ask of God, who gives to all men liberally, and reproaches not; and it shall be given him.
B059C001V006	59	1	6	But let him ask in faith, nothing wavering. For he that wavers is like a wave of the sea driven with the wind and tossed.
B059C001V007	59	1	7	For let not that man think that he shall receive anything of the Lord.
B059C001V008	59	1	8	A double-minded man is unstable in all his ways.
B059C001V009	59	1	9	Let the brother of low degree rejoice in that he is exalted:
B059C001V010	59	1	10	But the rich, in that he is made low: because as the flower of the grass he shall pass away.
B059C001V011	59	1	11	For the sun is no sooner risen with a burning heat, but it withers the grass, and its flower falls, and the beauty of the appearance of it perishes: so also shall the rich man fade away in his ways.
B059C001V012	59	1	12	Blessed is the man that endures trial: for when he is tried, he shall receive the crown of life, which the Lord has promised to them that love him.
B059C001V013	59	1	13	Let no man say when he is tempted, I am tempted of God: for God cannot be tempted with evil, neither tempts he any man:
B059C001V014	59	1	14	But every man is tempted, when he is drawn away of his own lust, and enticed.
B059C001V015	59	1	15	Then when lust has conceived, it brings forth sin: and sin, when it is finished, brings forth death.
B059C001V016	59	1	16	Do not err, my beloved brethren.
B059C001V017	59	1	17	Every good gift and every perfect gift is from above, and comes down from the Father of lights, with whom is no variableness, neither shadow of turning.
B059C001V018	59	1	18	Of his own will begat he us with the word of truth, that we should be a kind of firstfruits of his creatures.
B059C001V019	59	1	19	Therefore, my beloved brethren, let every man be swift to hear, slow to speak, slow to anger:
B059C001V020	59	1	20	For the anger of man works not the righteousness of God.
B059C001V021	59	1	21	Therefore put away all filthiness and extreme wickedness, and receive with meekness the engrafted word, which is able to save your souls.
B059C001V022	59	1	22	But be you doers of the word, and not hearers only, deceiving your own selves.
B059C001V023	59	1	23	For if any be a hearer of the word, and not a doer, he is like unto a man beholding his natural face in a mirror:
B059C001V024	59	1	24	For he beholds himself, and goes his way, and immediately forgets what manner of man he was.
B059C001V025	59	1	25	But whoever looks into the perfect law of liberty, and continues in it, he being not a forgetful hearer, but a doer of the work, this man shall be blessed in his deed.
B059C001V026	59	1	26	If any man among you seems to be religious, and bridles not his tongue, but deceives his own heart, this man's religion is vain.
B059C001V027	59	1	27	Pure religion and undefiled before God the Father is this, To visit the fatherless and widows in their affliction, and to keep himself unspotted from the world.
B059C002V001	59	2	1	My brethren, have not the faith of our Lord Jesus Christ, the Lord of glory, with respect of persons.
B059C002V002	59	2	2	For if there come unto your assembly a man with a gold ring, in fine apparel, and there come in also a poor man in shabby clothing;
B059C002V003	59	2	3	And you have respect to him that wears the fine clothing, and say unto him, Sit here in a good place; and say to the poor, Stand there, or sit here under my footstool:
B059C002V004	59	2	4	Are you not then partial in yourselves, and are become judges of evil thoughts?
B059C002V005	59	2	5	Hearken, my beloved brethren, Has not God chosen the poor of this world rich in faith, and heirs of the kingdom which he has promised to them that love him?
B059C002V006	59	2	6	But you have despised the poor. Do not rich men oppress you, and draw you before the judges?
B059C002V007	59	2	7	Do not they blaspheme that worthy name by which you are called?
B059C002V008	59	2	8	If you fulfill the royal law according to the scripture, 
B059C002V009	59	2	9	But if you have respect to persons, you commit sin, and are convicted of the law as transgressors.
B059C002V010	59	2	10	For whosoever shall keep the whole law, and yet offend in one point, he is guilty of all.
B059C002V011	59	2	11	For he that said, 
B059C002V012	59	2	12	So speak, and so do, as they that shall be judged by the law of liberty.
B059C002V013	59	2	13	For he shall have judgment without mercy, that has showed no mercy; and mercy triumphs over judgment.
B059C002V014	59	2	14	What does it profit, my brethren, though a man says he has faith, and has not works? can faith save him?
B059C002V015	59	2	15	If a brother or sister be naked, and destitute of daily food,
B059C002V016	59	2	16	And one of you say unto them, Depart in peace, be warmed and filled; yet you give them not those things which are needful to the body; what does it profit?
B059C002V017	59	2	17	Even so faith, if it has not works, is dead, being alone.
B059C002V018	59	2	18	Yea, a man may say, You have faith, and I have works: show me your faith without your works, and I will show you my faith by my works.
B059C002V019	59	2	19	You believe that there is one God; you do well: the demons also believe, and tremble.
B059C002V020	59	2	20	But will you know, O vain man, that faith without works is dead?
B059C002V021	59	2	21	Was not Abraham our father justified by works, when he had offered Isaac his son upon the altar?
B059C002V022	59	2	22	See how faith worked with his works, and by works was faith made perfect?
B059C002V023	59	2	23	And the scripture was fulfilled which says, Abraham believed God, and it was imputed unto him for righteousness: and he was called the Friend of God.
B059C002V024	59	2	24	You see then how that by works a man is justified, and not by faith only.
B059C002V025	59	2	25	Likewise also was not Rahab the harlot justified by works, when she had received the messengers, and had sent them out another way?
B059C002V026	59	2	26	For as the body without the spirit is dead, so faith without works is dead also.
B059C003V001	59	3	1	My brethren, be not many teachers, knowing that we shall receive the severer judgment.
B059C003V002	59	3	2	For in many things we all offend. If any man offend not in word, the same is a perfect man, and able also to bridle the whole body.
B059C003V003	59	3	3	Behold, we put bits in the horses' mouths, that they may obey us; and we turn about their whole body.
B059C003V004	59	3	4	Behold also the ships, which though they be so great, and are driven by fierce winds, yet are they turned about with a very small rudder, wherever the pilot desires.
B059C003V005	59	3	5	Even so the tongue is a little member, and boasts great things. Behold, how great a forest a little fire kindles!
B059C003V006	59	3	6	And the tongue is a fire, a world of iniquity: so is the tongue among our members, that it defiles the whole body, and sets on fire the course of nature; and it is set on fire by hell.
B059C003V007	59	3	7	For every kind of beasts, and of birds, and of serpents, and of things in the sea, is tamed, and has been tamed by mankind:
B059C003V008	59	3	8	But the tongue can no man tame; it is an unruly evil, full of deadly poison.
B059C003V009	59	3	9	With this bless we God, even the Father; and with this curse we men, who are made after the similitude of God.
B059C003V010	59	3	10	Out of the same mouth proceeds blessing and cursing. My brethren, these things ought not so to be.
B059C003V011	59	3	11	Does a fountain send forth at the same place sweet water and bitter?
B059C003V012	59	3	12	Can the fig tree, my brethren, bear olive berries? either a vine, figs? so can no fountain both yield salt water and fresh.
B059C003V013	59	3	13	Who is a wise man and endued with knowledge among you? let him show out of a good life his works with meekness of wisdom.
B059C003V014	59	3	14	But if you have bitter envying and strife in your hearts, boast not, and lie not against the truth.
B059C003V015	59	3	15	This wisdom descends not from above, but is earthly, sensual, demonic.
B059C003V016	59	3	16	For where envying and strife is, there is confusion and every evil work.
B059C003V017	59	3	17	But the wisdom that is from above is first pure, then peaceable, gentle, and compliant, full of mercy and good fruits, without partiality, and without hypocrisy.
B059C003V018	59	3	18	And the fruit of righteousness is sown in peace by them that make peace.
B059C004V001	59	4	1	From where come wars and fightings among you? come they not from here, even of your lusts that war in your members?
B059C004V002	59	4	2	You lust, and have not: you kill, and desire to have, and cannot obtain: you fight and war, yet you have not, because you ask not.
B059C004V003	59	4	3	You ask, and receive not, because you ask amiss, that you may spend it upon your lusts.
B059C004V004	59	4	4	You adulterers and adulteresses, know you not that the friendship of the world is enmity with God? whosoever therefore will be a friend of the world is the enemy of God.
B059C004V005	59	4	5	Do you think that the scripture says in vain, The spirit that dwells in us lusts to envy?
B059C004V006	59	4	6	But he gives more grace. Therefore he says, 
B059C004V007	59	4	7	Submit yourselves therefore to God. Resist the devil, and he will flee from you.
B059C004V008	59	4	8	Draw near to God, and he will draw near to you. Cleanse your hands, you sinners; and purify your hearts, you double-minded.
B059C004V009	59	4	9	Be afflicted, and mourn, and weep: let your laughter be turned to mourning, and your joy to heaviness.
B059C004V010	59	4	10	Humble yourselves in the sight of the Lord, and he shall lift you up.
B059C004V011	59	4	11	Speak not evil one of another, brethren. He that speaks evil of his brother, and judges his brother, speaks evil of the law, and judges the law: but if you judge the law, you are not a doer of the law, but a judge.
B059C004V012	59	4	12	There is one lawgiver, who is able to save and to destroy: who are you that judge another?
B059C004V013	59	4	13	Come now, you that say, Today or tomorrow we will go into such a city, and continue there a year, and buy and sell, and get gain:
B059C004V014	59	4	14	Whereas you know not what shall be tomorrow. For what is your life? It is even a vapor, that appears for a little time, and then vanishes away.
B059C004V015	59	4	15	For you ought to say, If the Lord wills, we shall live, and do this, or that.
B059C004V016	59	4	16	But now you rejoice in your boastings: all such rejoicing is evil.
B059C004V017	59	4	17	Therefore to him that knows to do good, and does it not, to him it is sin.
B059C005V001	59	5	1	Come now, you rich men, weep and howl for your miseries that shall come upon you.
B059C005V002	59	5	2	Your riches are corrupted, and your garments are moth-eaten.
B059C005V003	59	5	3	Your gold and silver is rusted; and the rust of them shall be a witness against you, and shall eat your flesh as if it were fire. You have heaped treasure together for the last days.
B059C005V004	59	5	4	Behold, the hire of the laborers who have reaped down your fields, which is of you kept back by fraud, cries: and the cries of them who have reaped are entered into the ears of the Lord of hosts.
B059C005V005	59	5	5	You have lived in pleasure on the earth, and been wanton; you have nourished your hearts, as in a day of slaughter.
B059C005V006	59	5	6	You have condemned and killed the just; and he does not resist you.
B059C005V007	59	5	7	Be patient therefore, brethren, unto the coming of the Lord. Behold, the farmer waits for the precious fruit of the earth, and has long patience for it, until he receives the early and latter rain.
B059C005V008	59	5	8	Be also patient; establish your hearts: for the coming of the Lord draws near.
B059C005V009	59	5	9	Murmur not one against another, brethren, lest you be judged: behold, the judge stands before the door.
B059C005V010	59	5	10	Take, my brethren, the prophets, who have spoken in the name of the Lord, for an example of suffering affliction, and of patience.
B059C005V011	59	5	11	Behold, we count them happy who endure. You have heard of the patience of Job, and have seen the end of the Lord; that the Lord is very compassionate, and of tender mercy.
B059C005V012	59	5	12	But above all things, my brethren, swear not, neither by heaven, neither by the earth, neither by any other oath: but let your yea be yea; and your nay, nay; lest you fall under judgment.
B059C005V013	59	5	13	Is any among you afflicted? let him pray. Is any merry? let him sing psalms.
B059C005V014	59	5	14	Is any sick among you? let him call for the elders of the church; and let them pray over him, anointing him with oil in the name of the Lord:
B059C005V015	59	5	15	And the prayer of faith shall deliver the sick, and the Lord shall raise him up; and if he has committed sins, they shall be forgiven him.
B059C005V016	59	5	16	Confess your faults one to another, and pray one for another, that you may be healed. The effectual fervent prayer of a righteous man avails much.
B059C005V017	59	5	17	Elijah was a man subject to like passions as we are, and he prayed earnestly that it might not rain: and it rained not on the earth for three years and six months.
B059C005V018	59	5	18	And he prayed again, and the heavens gave rain, and the earth brought forth its fruit.
B059C005V019	59	5	19	Brethren, if any of you do err from the truth, and one convert him;
B059C005V020	59	5	20	Let him know, that he who converts the sinner from the error of his way shall save a soul from death, and shall hide a multitude of sins.
B060C001V001	60	1	1	Peter, an apostle of Jesus Christ, to the exiles scattered throughout Pontus, Galatia, Cappadocia, Asia, and Bithynia,
B060C001V002	60	1	2	Elect according to the foreknowledge of God the Father, through sanctification of the Spirit, unto obedience and sprinkling of the blood of Jesus Christ: Grace unto you, and peace, be multiplied.
B060C001V003	60	1	3	Blessed be the God and Father of our Lord Jesus Christ, who according to his abundant mercy has begotten us again unto a living hope by the resurrection of Jesus Christ from the dead,
B060C001V004	60	1	4	To an inheritance incorruptible, and undefiled, and that fades not away, reserved in heaven for you,
B060C001V005	60	1	5	Who are kept by the power of God through faith unto salvation ready to be revealed in the last time.
B060C001V006	60	1	6	In which you greatly rejoice, though now for a little while, if need be, you are in heaviness through manifold trials:
B060C001V007	60	1	7	That the trial of your faith, being much more precious than of gold that perishes, though it be tried with fire, might be found unto praise and honor and glory at the appearing of Jesus Christ:
B060C001V008	60	1	8	Whom having not seen, you love; in whom, though now you see him not, yet believing, you rejoice with joy unspeakable and full of glory:
B060C001V009	60	1	9	Receiving the end of your faith, even the salvation of your souls.
B060C001V010	60	1	10	Of which salvation the prophets have inquired and searched diligently, who prophesied of the grace that should come unto you:
B060C001V011	60	1	11	Searching what, or what manner of time the Spirit of Christ which was in them did signify, when he testified beforehand the sufferings of Christ, and the glory that should follow.
B060C001V012	60	1	12	Unto whom it was revealed, that not unto themselves, but unto us they did minister the things, which are now reported unto you by them that have preached the gospel unto you with the Holy Spirit sent down from heaven; which things the angels desire to look into.
B060C001V013	60	1	13	Therefore gird up the loins of your mind, be sober, and hope to the end for the grace that is to be brought unto you at the revelation of Jesus Christ;
B060C001V014	60	1	14	As obedient children, not fashioning yourselves according to the former lusts in your ignorance:
B060C001V015	60	1	15	But as he who has called you is holy, so be holy in all manner of conduct;
B060C001V016	60	1	16	Because it is written, 
B060C001V017	60	1	17	And if you call on the Father, who without respect of persons judges according to every man's work, pass the time of your exile here in fear:
B060C001V018	60	1	18	Since you know that you were not redeemed with corruptible things, as silver and gold, from your vain manner of life received by tradition from your fathers;
B060C001V019	60	1	19	But with the precious blood of Christ, as of a lamb without blemish and without spot:
B060C001V020	60	1	20	Who verily was foreordained before the foundation of the world, but was manifest in these last times for you,
B060C001V021	60	1	21	Who by him do believe in God, that raised him up from the dead, and gave him glory; that your faith and hope might be in God.
B060C001V022	60	1	22	Seeing you have purified your souls in obeying the truth through the Spirit unto sincere love of the brethren, see that you love one another with a pure heart fervently:
B060C001V023	60	1	23	Being born again, not of corruptible seed, but of incorruptible, by the word of God, which lives and abides forever.
B060C001V024	60	1	24	For all flesh is as grass, and all the glory of man as the flower of grass. The grass withers, and the flower thereof falls away:
B060C001V025	60	1	25	But the word of the Lord endures forever. And this is the word which by the gospel is preached unto you.
B060C002V001	60	2	1	Therefore laying aside all malice, and all guile, and hypocrisies, and envies, and all evil speaking,
B060C002V002	60	2	2	As newborn babes, desire the pure milk of the word, that you may grow thereby:
B060C002V003	60	2	3	If so be you have tasted that the Lord is gracious.
B060C002V004	60	2	4	To whom coming, as unto a living stone, rejected indeed of men, but chosen of God, and precious,
B060C002V005	60	2	5	You also, as living stones, are built up into a spiritual house, a holy priesthood, to offer up spiritual sacrifices, acceptable to God by Jesus Christ.
B060C002V006	60	2	6	Therefore also it is contained in the scripture, 
B060C002V007	60	2	7	Unto you therefore who believe he is precious: but unto them who are disobedient, the stone which the builders rejected, the same is made the head of the corner,
B060C002V008	60	2	8	And, 
B060C002V009	60	2	9	But you are a chosen generation, a royal priesthood, a holy nation, a people for his own; that you should show forth the praises of him who has called you out of darkness into his marvelous light:
B060C002V010	60	2	10	Who in time past were not a people, but are now the people of God: who had not obtained mercy, but now have obtained mercy.
B060C002V011	60	2	11	Dearly beloved, I beseech you as aliens and exiles, abstain from fleshly lusts, which war against the soul;
B060C002V012	60	2	12	Having your conduct honest among the Gentiles: that, whereas they speak against you as evildoers, they may by your good works, which they shall behold, glorify God in the day of visitation.
B060C002V013	60	2	13	Submit yourselves to every ordinance of man for the Lord's sake: whether it be to the king, as supreme;
B060C002V014	60	2	14	Or unto governors, as unto them that are sent by him for the punishment of evildoers, and for the praise of them that do well.
B060C002V015	60	2	15	For so is the will of God, that with well doing you may put to silence the ignorance of foolish men:
B060C002V016	60	2	16	As free, and not using your liberty for a cloak of maliciousness, but as the servants of God.
B060C002V017	60	2	17	Honor all men. Love the brotherhood. Fear God. Honor the king.
B060C002V018	60	2	18	Servants, be subject to your masters with all fear; not only to the good and gentle, but also to the harsh.
B060C002V019	60	2	19	For this is commendable, if a man for conscience toward God endures grief, suffering wrongfully.
B060C002V020	60	2	20	For what glory is it, if, when you be buffeted for your faults, you shall take it patiently? but if, when you do well, and suffer for it, you take it patiently, this is commendable with God.
B060C002V021	60	2	21	For even to this were you called: because Christ also suffered for us, leaving us an example, that you should follow his steps:
B060C002V022	60	2	22	Who did no sin, neither was guile found in his mouth:
B060C002V023	60	2	23	Who, when he was reviled, reviled not again; when he suffered, he threatened not; but committed himself to him that judges righteously:
B060C002V024	60	2	24	Who his own self bore our sins in his own body on the tree, that we, being dead to sins, should live unto righteousness: by whose stripes you were healed.
B060C002V025	60	2	25	For you were as sheep going astray; but are now returned unto the Shepherd and Bishop of your souls.
B060C003V001	60	3	1	Likewise, you wives, be in subjection to your own husbands; that, if any obey not the word, they also may without the word be won by the conduct of the wives;
B060C003V002	60	3	2	While they behold your chaste behavior coupled with fear.
B060C003V003	60	3	3	Whose adorning let it not be that outward adorning of braiding the hair, and of wearing of gold, or of putting on of apparel;
B060C003V004	60	3	4	But let it be the hidden man of the heart, in that which is not corruptible, even the ornament of a meek and quiet spirit, which is in the sight of God of great price.
B060C003V005	60	3	5	For after this manner in former times the holy women also, who trusted in God, adorned themselves, being in subjection unto their own husbands:
B060C003V006	60	3	6	Even as Sara obeyed Abraham, calling him lord: whose daughters you are, as long as you do well, and are not afraid with any terror.
B060C003V007	60	3	7	Likewise, you husbands, dwell with them according to knowledge, giving honor unto the wife, as unto the weaker vessel, and as being heirs together of the grace of life; that your prayers be not hindered.
B060C003V008	60	3	8	Finally, be all of one mind, having compassion one with another, love as brethren, be tender hearted, be courteous:
B060C003V009	60	3	9	Not rendering evil for evil, or railing for railing: but on the contrary blessing; knowing that you are unto this called, that you should inherit a blessing.
B060C003V010	60	3	10	For he that will love life, and see good days, let him refrain his tongue from evil, and his lips that they speak no guile:
B060C003V011	60	3	11	Let him turn away from evil, and do good; let him seek peace, and pursue it.
B060C003V012	60	3	12	For the eyes of the Lord are over the righteous, and his ears are open unto their prayers: but the face of the Lord is against them that do evil.
B060C003V013	60	3	13	And who is he that will harm you, if you be followers of that which is good?
B060C003V014	60	3	14	But if you suffer for righteousness' sake, happy are you: and, 
B060C003V015	60	3	15	But sanctify the Lord God in your hearts: and be ready always to give an answer to every man that asks you a reason of the hope that is in you with meekness and fear:
B060C003V016	60	3	16	Having a good conscience; that, whereas they speak evil of you, as of evildoers, they may be ashamed that falsely accuse your good behavior in Christ.
B060C003V017	60	3	17	For it is better, if the will of God be so, that you suffer for well doing, than for evil doing.
B060C003V018	60	3	18	For Christ also has once suffered for sins, the just for the unjust, that he might bring us to God, being put to death in the flesh, but made alive by the Spirit:
B060C003V019	60	3	19	By whom also he went and preached unto the spirits in prison;
B060C003V020	60	3	20	Who formerly were disobedient, when once the longsuffering of God waited in the days of Noah, while the ark was being prepared, by which a few, that is, eight souls were saved through water.
B060C003V021	60	3	21	The like figure unto which even baptism does also now save us (not the putting away of the filth of the flesh, but the answer of a good conscience toward God,) by the resurrection of Jesus Christ:
B060C003V022	60	3	22	Who is gone into heaven, and is on the right hand of God; angels and authorities and powers being made subject unto him.
B060C004V001	60	4	1	Since therefore Christ has suffered for us in the flesh, arm yourselves likewise with the same mind: for he that has suffered in the flesh has ceased from sin;
B060C004V002	60	4	2	That he no longer should live the rest of his time in the flesh to the lusts of men, but to the will of God.
B060C004V003	60	4	3	For the time past of our life will suffice us to have done the will of the Gentiles, when we walked in licentiousness, lusts, excess of wine, reveling, carousing, and abominable idolatries:
B060C004V004	60	4	4	In which they think it strange that you run not with them to the same excess of dissipation, speaking evil of you:
B060C004V005	60	4	5	Who shall give account to him that is ready to judge the living and the dead.
B060C004V006	60	4	6	For this cause was the gospel preached also to them that are dead, that they might be judged according to men in the flesh, but live according to God in the spirit.
B060C004V007	60	4	7	But the end of all things is at hand: be therefore sober minded, and watch unto prayer.
B060C004V008	60	4	8	And above all things have fervent love among yourselves: for love shall cover a multitude of sins.
B060C004V009	60	4	9	Practice hospitality one to another without grudging.
B060C004V010	60	4	10	As every man has received a gift, even so minister the same one to another, as good stewards of the manifold grace of God.
B060C004V011	60	4	11	If any man speaks, let him speak as the oracles of God; if any man ministers, let him do it as of the ability which God gives: that God in all things may be glorified through Jesus Christ, to whom be praise and dominion forever and ever. Amen.
B060C004V012	60	4	12	Beloved, think it not strange concerning the fiery trial which is to test you, as though some strange thing happened unto you:
B060C004V013	60	4	13	But rejoice, since you are partakers of Christ's sufferings; that, when his glory shall be revealed, you may be glad also with exceeding joy.
B060C004V014	60	4	14	If you be reproached for the name of Christ, happy are you; for the spirit of glory and of God rests upon you: on their part he is evil spoken of, but on your part he is glorified.
B060C004V015	60	4	15	But let none of you suffer as a murderer, or as a thief, or as an evildoer, or as a busybody in other men's matters.
B060C004V016	60	4	16	Yet if any man suffers as a Christian, let him not be ashamed; but let him glorify God on this behalf.
B060C004V017	60	4	17	For the time is come that judgment must begin at the house of God: and if it first begins with us, what shall the end be of them that obey not the gospel of God?
B060C004V018	60	4	18	And if the righteous scarcely be saved, where shall the ungodly and the sinner appear?
B060C004V019	60	4	19	Therefore let them that suffer according to the will of God commit the keeping of their souls to him in well doing, as unto a faithful Creator.
B060C005V001	60	5	1	The elders who are among you I exhort, who am also an elder, and a witness of the sufferings of Christ, and also a partaker of the glory that shall be revealed:
B060C005V002	60	5	2	Feed the flock of God which is among you, taking the oversight thereof, not by constraint, but willingly; not for dishonest gain, but of a ready mind;
B060C005V003	60	5	3	Neither as being lords over God's heritage, but being examples to the flock.
B060C005V004	60	5	4	And when the chief Shepherd shall appear, you shall receive a crown of glory that fades not away.
B060C005V005	60	5	5	Likewise, you younger, submit yourselves unto the elder. Yea, all of you be subject one to another, and be clothed with humility: for 
B060C005V006	60	5	6	Humble yourselves therefore under the mighty hand of God, that he may exalt you in due time:
B060C005V007	60	5	7	Casting all your care upon him; for he cares for you.
B060C005V008	60	5	8	Be sober, be vigilant; because your adversary the devil, as a roaring lion, walks about, seeking whom he may devour:
B060C005V009	60	5	9	Whom resist steadfast in the faith, knowing that the same afflictions are accomplished in your brethren that are in the world.
B060C005V010	60	5	10	But the God of all grace, who has called us unto his eternal glory by Christ Jesus, after that you have suffered a while, restore, establish, strengthen, settle you.
B060C005V011	60	5	11	To him be glory and dominion forever and ever. Amen.
B060C005V012	60	5	12	By Silas, a faithful brother unto you, as I regard, I have written briefly, exhorting, and testifying that this is the true grace of God in which you stand.
B060C005V013	60	5	13	The church that is at Babylon, elected together with you, greets you; and so does Mark my son.
B060C005V014	60	5	14	Greet one another with a kiss of love. Peace be with you all that are in Christ Jesus. Amen.
B061C001V001	61	1	1	Simon Peter, a servant and an apostle of Jesus Christ, to them that have obtained like precious faith with us through the righteousness of God and our Savior Jesus Christ:
B061C001V002	61	1	2	Grace and peace be multiplied unto you through the knowledge of God, and of Jesus our Lord,
B061C001V003	61	1	3	According as his divine power has given unto us all things that pertain unto life and godliness, through the knowledge of him who has called us to glory and virtue:
B061C001V004	61	1	4	By which are given unto us exceedingly great and precious promises: that by these you might be partakers of the divine nature, having escaped the corruption that is in the world through lust.
B061C001V005	61	1	5	And for this reason, giving all diligence, add to your faith virtue; and to virtue knowledge;
B061C001V006	61	1	6	And to knowledge self control; and to self control patience; and to patience godliness;
B061C001V007	61	1	7	And to godliness brotherly kindness; and to brotherly kindness love.
B061C001V008	61	1	8	For if these things be in you, and abound, they make you that you shall neither be barren nor unfruitful in the knowledge of our Lord Jesus Christ.
B061C001V009	61	1	9	But he that lacks these things is blind, and cannot see afar off, and has forgotten that he was purged from his old sins.
B061C001V010	61	1	10	Therefore rather, brethren, give diligence to make your calling and election sure: for if you do these things, you shall never fall:
B061C001V011	61	1	11	For so an entrance shall be provided unto you abundantly into the everlasting kingdom of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ.
B061C001V012	61	1	12	Therefore I will not be negligent to put you always in remembrance of these things, though you know them, and are established in the present truth.
B061C001V013	61	1	13	Yea, I think it right, as long as I am in this tabernacle, to stir you up by putting you in remembrance;
B061C001V014	61	1	14	Knowing that shortly I must put off this my tabernacle, even as our Lord Jesus Christ has showed me.
B061C001V015	61	1	15	Moreover I will endeavor that you may be able after my departure to have these things always in remembrance.
B061C001V016	61	1	16	For we have not followed cunningly devised myths, when we made known unto you the power and coming of our Lord Jesus Christ, but were eyewitnesses of his majesty.
B061C001V017	61	1	17	For he received from God the Father honor and glory, when there came such a voice to him from the excellent glory, 
B061C001V018	61	1	18	And this voice which came from heaven we heard, when we were with him in the holy mount.
B061C001V019	61	1	19	We have also a more sure word of prophecy; to which you do well that you take heed, as unto a light that shines in a dark place, until the day dawn, and the day star arise in your hearts:
B061C001V020	61	1	20	Knowing this first, that no prophecy of the scripture is of oneâ€™s own interpretation.
B061C001V021	61	1	21	For the prophecy came not in old time by the will of man: but holy men of God spoke as they were moved by the Holy Spirit.
B061C002V001	61	2	1	But there were false prophets also among the people, even as there shall be false teachers among you, who shall secretly bring in destructive heresies, even denying the Lord that bought them, and bring upon themselves swift destruction.
B061C002V002	61	2	2	And many shall follow their shameful ways; by reason of whom the way of truth shall be evil spoken of.
B061C002V003	61	2	3	And through covetousness shall they with false words exploit you: whose judgment of old now lingers not, and their destruction slumbers not.
B061C002V004	61	2	4	For if God spared not the angels that sinned, but cast them down to hell, and delivered them into chains of darkness, to be reserved unto judgment;
B061C002V005	61	2	5	And spared not the ancient world, but saved Noah the eighth person, a preacher of righteousness, bringing in the flood upon the world of the ungodly;
B061C002V006	61	2	6	And turning the cities of Sodom and Gomorrah into ashes condemned them by a catastrophe, making them an example unto those that later should live ungodly;
B061C002V007	61	2	7	And delivered just Lot, vexed with the filthy behavior of the wicked:
B061C002V008	61	2	8	(For that righteous man dwelling among them, in seeing and hearing, vexed his righteous soul from day to day with their unlawful deeds;)
B061C002V009	61	2	9	The Lord knows how to deliver the godly out of temptations, and to reserve the unjust unto the day of judgment to be punished:
B061C002V010	61	2	10	But chiefly them that walk after the flesh in the lust of uncleanness, and despise authority. Presumptuous are they, self-willed, they are not afraid to speak evil of the glorious ones.
B061C002V011	61	2	11	Whereas angels, who are greater in power and might, bring not railing accusation against them before the Lord.
B061C002V012	61	2	12	But these, as natural brute beasts, made to be taken and destroyed, speak evil of the things that they understand not; and shall utterly perish in their own corruption;
B061C002V013	61	2	13	And shall receive the reward of unrighteousness, as they that count it pleasure to revel in the daytime. Spots they are and blemishes, reveling themselves with their own deceivings while they feast with you;
B061C002V014	61	2	14	Having eyes full of adultery, and that cannot cease from sin; beguiling unstable souls: a heart they have exercised with covetous practices; cursed children:
B061C002V015	61	2	15	Who have forsaken the right way, and are gone astray, following the way of Balaam the son of Beor, who loved the wages of unrighteousness;
B061C002V016	61	2	16	But was rebuked for his iniquity: the dumb donkey speaking with man's voice restrained the madness of the prophet.
B061C002V017	61	2	17	These are wells without water, clouds that are carried with a tempest; to whom the mist of darkness is reserved forever.
B061C002V018	61	2	18	For when they speak great swelling words of vanity, they allure through the lusts of the flesh, through much wantonness, those that have just escaped from them who live in error.
B061C002V019	61	2	19	While they promise them liberty, they themselves are the servants of corruption: for of whom a man is overcome, of the same is he brought in bondage.
B061C002V020	61	2	20	For if after they have escaped the defilements of the world through the knowledge of the Lord and Savior Jesus Christ, they are again entangled therein, and overcome, the latter end is worse with them than the beginning.
B061C002V021	61	2	21	For it had been better for them not to have known the way of righteousness, than, after they have known it, to turn from the holy commandment delivered unto them.
B061C002V022	61	2	22	But it is happened unto them according to the true proverb, The dog has turned to his own vomit again; and the sow that was washed to her wallowing in the mire.
B061C003V001	61	3	1	This second epistle, beloved, I now write unto you; in both of which I stir up your pure minds by way of remembrance:
B061C003V002	61	3	2	That you may be mindful of the words which were spoken before by the holy prophets, and of the commandment of us the apostles of the Lord and Savior:
B061C003V003	61	3	3	Knowing this first, that there shall come in the last days scoffers, walking after their own lusts,
B061C003V004	61	3	4	And saying, Where is the promise of his coming? for since the fathers fell asleep, all things continue as they were from the beginning of the creation.
B061C003V005	61	3	5	For this they willingly are ignorant of, that by the word of God the heavens were of old, and the earth standing out of the water and in the water:
B061C003V006	61	3	6	By which the world that then was, being overflowed with water, perished:
B061C003V007	61	3	7	But the heavens and the earth, which now are, by the same word are kept in store, reserved unto fire against the day of judgment and destruction of ungodly men.
B061C003V008	61	3	8	But, beloved, be not ignorant of this one thing, that one day is with the Lord as a thousand years, and a thousand years as one day.
B061C003V009	61	3	9	The Lord is not slack concerning his promise, as some men count slackness; but is longsuffering toward us, not willing that any should perish, but that all should come to repentance.
B061C003V010	61	3	10	But the day of the Lord will come as a thief in the night; in which the heavens shall pass away with a great noise, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat, the earth also and the works that are therein shall be burned up.
B061C003V011	61	3	11	Seeing then that all these things shall be dissolved, what manner of persons ought you to be in all holy conduct and godliness,
B061C003V012	61	3	12	Looking for and hastening unto the coming of the day of God, in which the heavens being on fire shall be dissolved, and the elements shall melt with fervent heat?
B061C003V013	61	3	13	Nevertheless we, according to his promise, look for new heavens and a new earth, in which dwells righteousness.
B061C003V014	61	3	14	Therefore, beloved, seeing that you look for such things, be diligent that you may be found of him in peace, without spot, and blameless.
B061C003V015	61	3	15	And account that the longsuffering of our Lord is salvation; even as our beloved brother Paul also according to the wisdom given unto him has written unto you;
B061C003V016	61	3	16	As also in all his epistles, speaking in them of these things; in which are some things hard to be understood, which they that are unlearned and unstable twist, as they do also the other scriptures, unto their own destruction.
B061C003V017	61	3	17	You therefore, beloved, seeing you know these things beforehand, beware lest you also, being led away with the error of the wicked, fall from your own steadfastness.
B061C003V018	61	3	18	But grow in grace, and in the knowledge of our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ. To him be glory both now and forever. Amen.
B062C001V001	62	1	1	That which was from the beginning, which we have heard, which we have seen with our eyes, which we have looked upon, and our hands have handled, of the Word of life;
B062C001V002	62	1	2	(For the life was manifested, and we have seen it, and bear witness, and show unto you that eternal life, which was with the Father, and was manifested unto us;)
B062C001V003	62	1	3	That which we have seen and heard declare we unto you, that you also may have fellowship with us: and truly our fellowship is with the Father, and with his Son Jesus Christ.
B062C001V004	62	1	4	And these things write we unto you, that your joy may be full.
B062C001V005	62	1	5	This then is the message which we have heard of him, and declare unto you, that God is light, and in him is no darkness at all.
B062C001V006	62	1	6	If we say that we have fellowship with him, and walk in darkness, we lie, and do not the truth:
B062C001V007	62	1	7	But if we walk in the light, as he is in the light, we have fellowship one with another, and the blood of Jesus Christ his Son cleanses us from all sin.
B062C001V008	62	1	8	If we say that we have no sin, we deceive ourselves, and the truth is not in us.
B062C001V009	62	1	9	If we confess our sins, he is faithful and just to forgive us our sins, and to cleanse us from all unrighteousness.
B062C001V010	62	1	10	If we say that we have not sinned, we make him a liar, and his word is not in us.
B062C002V001	62	2	1	My little children, these things write I unto you, that you sin not. And if any man sin, we have an advocate with the Father, Jesus Christ the righteous:
B062C002V002	62	2	2	And he is the propitiation for our sins: and not for ours only, but also for the sins of the whole world.
B062C002V003	62	2	3	And by this we know that we know him, if we keep his commandments.
B062C002V004	62	2	4	He that says, I know him, and keeps not his commandments, is a liar, and the truth is not in him.
B062C002V005	62	2	5	But whoever keeps his word, in him verily is the love of God perfected: by this we know that we are in him.
B062C002V006	62	2	6	He that says he abides in him ought himself also so to walk, even as he walked.
B062C002V007	62	2	7	Brethren, I write no new commandment unto you, but an old commandment which you had from the beginning. The old commandment is the word which you have heard from the beginning.
B062C002V008	62	2	8	Again, a new commandment I write unto you, which thing is true in him and in you: because the darkness is past, and the true light now shines.
B062C002V009	62	2	9	He that says he is in the light, and hates his brother, is in darkness even until now.
B062C002V010	62	2	10	He that loves his brother abides in the light, and there is no occasion of stumbling in him.
B062C002V011	62	2	11	But he that hates his brother is in darkness, and walks in darkness, and knows not where he goes, because that darkness has blinded his eyes.
B062C002V012	62	2	12	I write unto you, little children, because your sins are forgiven you for his name's sake.
B062C002V013	62	2	13	I write unto you, fathers, because you have known him who is from the beginning. I write unto you, young men, because you have overcome the wicked one. I write unto you, little children, because you have known the Father.
B062C002V014	62	2	14	I have written unto you, fathers, because you have known him who is from the beginning. I have written unto you, young men, because you are strong, and the word of God abides in you, and you have overcome the wicked one.
B062C002V015	62	2	15	Love not the world, neither the things that are in the world. If any man loves the world, the love of the Father is not in him.
B062C002V016	62	2	16	For all that is in the world, the lust of the flesh, and the lust of the eyes, and the pride of life, is not of the Father, but is of the world.
B062C002V017	62	2	17	And the world passes away, and the lust thereof: but he that does the will of God abides forever.
B062C002V018	62	2	18	Little children, it is the last time: and as you have heard that antichrist shall come, even now are there many antichrists; by which we know that it is the last time.
B062C002V019	62	2	19	They went out from us, but they were not of us; for if they had been of us, they would no doubt have continued with us: but they went out, that they might be made manifest that they were not all of us.
B062C002V020	62	2	20	But you have an anointing from the Holy One, and you know all things.
B062C002V021	62	2	21	I have not written unto you because you know not the truth, but because you know it, and that no lie is of the truth.
B062C002V022	62	2	22	Who is a liar but he that denies that Jesus is the Christ? He is antichrist, that denies the Father and the Son.
B062C002V023	62	2	23	Whosoever denies the Son, the same has not the Father: 
B062C002V024	62	2	24	Let that therefore abide in you, which you have heard from the beginning. If that which you have heard from the beginning shall remain in you, you also shall continue in the Son, and in the Father.
B062C002V025	62	2	25	And this is the promise that he has promised us, even eternal life.
B062C002V026	62	2	26	These things have I written unto you concerning them that deceive you.
B062C002V027	62	2	27	But the anointing which you have received of him abides in you, and you need not that any man teach you: but as the same anointing teaches you of all things, and is truth, and is no lie, and even as it has taught you, you shall abide in him.
B062C002V028	62	2	28	And now, little children, abide in him; that, when he shall appear, we may have confidence, and not be ashamed before him at his coming.
B062C002V029	62	2	29	If you know that he is righteous, you know that everyone that does righteousness is born of him.
B062C003V001	62	3	1	Behold, what manner of love the Father has bestowed upon us, that we should be called the children of God: therefore the world knows us not, because it knew him not.
B062C003V002	62	3	2	Beloved, now are we the children of God, and it does not yet appear what we shall be: but we know that, when he shall appear, we shall be like him; for we shall see him as he is.
B062C003V003	62	3	3	And every man that has this hope in him purifies himself, even as he is pure.
B062C003V004	62	3	4	Whosoever commits sin transgresses also the law: for sin is the transgression of the law.
B062C003V005	62	3	5	And you know that he was manifested to take away our sins; and in him is no sin.
B062C003V006	62	3	6	Whosoever abides in him sins not: whosoever sins has not seen him, neither known him.
B062C003V007	62	3	7	Little children, let no man deceive you: he that does righteousness is righteous, even as he is righteous.
B062C003V008	62	3	8	He that commits sin is of the devil; for the devil sins from the beginning. For this purpose the Son of God was manifested, that he might destroy the works of the devil.
B062C003V009	62	3	9	Whosoever is born of God does not commit sin; for his nature remains in him: and he cannot sin, because he is born of God.
B062C003V010	62	3	10	In this the children of God are manifest, and the children of the devil: whosoever does not righteousness is not of God, neither he that loves not his brother.
B062C003V011	62	3	11	For this is the message that you heard from the beginning, that we should love one another.
B062C003V012	62	3	12	Not as Cain, who was of that wicked one, and slew his brother. And why slew he him? Because his own works were evil, and his brother's righteous.
B062C003V013	62	3	13	Marvel not, my brethren, if the world hates you.
B062C003V014	62	3	14	We know that we have passed from death unto life, because we love the brethren. He that loves not his brother abides in death.
B062C003V015	62	3	15	Whosoever hates his brother is a murderer: and you know that no murderer has eternal life abiding in him.
B062C003V016	62	3	16	By this perceive we the love of God, because he laid down his life for us: and we ought to lay down our lives for the brethren.
B062C003V017	62	3	17	But whoever has this world's goods, and sees his brother have need, and shuts up his heart of compassion from him, how dwells the love of God in him?
B062C003V018	62	3	18	My little children, let us not love in word, neither in tongue; but in deed and in truth.
B062C003V019	62	3	19	And by this we know that we are of the truth, and shall assure our hearts before him.
B062C003V020	62	3	20	For if our heart condemns us, God is greater than our heart, and knows all things.
B062C003V021	62	3	21	Beloved, if our heart condemns us not, then have we confidence toward God.
B062C003V022	62	3	22	And whatsoever we ask, we receive of him, because we keep his commandments, and do those things that are pleasing in his sight.
B062C003V023	62	3	23	And this is his commandment, That we should believe on the name of his Son Jesus Christ, and love one another, as he gave us commandment.
B062C003V024	62	3	24	And he that keeps his commandments dwells in him, and he in him. And by this we know that he abides in us, by the Spirit whom he has given us.
B062C004V001	62	4	1	Beloved, believe not every spirit, but test the spirits whether they are of God: because many false prophets are gone out into the world.
B062C004V002	62	4	2	By this you know the Spirit of God: Every spirit that confesses that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is of God:
B062C004V003	62	4	3	And every spirit that confesses not that Jesus Christ is come in the flesh is not of God: and this is that spirit of antichrist, of which you have heard that it should come; and even now already is it in the world.
B062C004V004	62	4	4	You are of God, little children, and have overcome them: because greater is he that is in you, than he that is in the world.
B062C004V005	62	4	5	They are of the world: therefore they speak of the world, and the world hears them.
B062C004V006	62	4	6	We are of God: he that knows God hears us; he that is not of God hears not us. By this we know the spirit of truth, and the spirit of error.
B062C004V007	62	4	7	Beloved, let us love one another: for love is of God; and everyone that loves is born of God, and knows God.
B062C004V008	62	4	8	He that loves not knows not God; for God is love.
B062C004V009	62	4	9	In this was manifested the love of God toward us, because God sent his only begotten Son into the world, that we might live through him.
B062C004V010	62	4	10	In this is love, not that we loved God, but that he loved us, and sent his Son to be the propitiation for our sins.
B062C004V011	62	4	11	Beloved, if God so loved us, we ought also to love one another.
B062C004V012	62	4	12	No man has seen God at any time. If we love one another, God dwells in us, and his love is perfected in us.
B062C004V013	62	4	13	By this we know that we dwell in him, and he in us, because he has given us of his Spirit.
B062C004V014	62	4	14	And we have seen and do testify that the Father sent the Son to be the Savior of the world.
B062C004V015	62	4	15	Whosoever shall confess that Jesus is the Son of God, God dwells in him, and he in God.
B062C004V016	62	4	16	And we have known and believed the love that God has for us. God is love; and he that dwells in love dwells in God, and God in him.
B062C004V017	62	4	17	In this is our love made perfect, that we may have boldness in the day of judgment: because as he is, so are we in this world.
B062C004V018	62	4	18	There is no fear in love; but perfect love casts out fear: because fear has to do with punishment. He that fears is not made perfect in love.
B062C004V019	62	4	19	We love him, because he first loved us.
B062C004V020	62	4	20	If a man says, I love God, and hates his brother, he is a liar: for he that loves not his brother whom he has seen, how can he love God whom he has not seen?
B062C004V021	62	4	21	And this commandment have we from him, That he who loves God love his brother also.
B062C005V001	62	5	1	Whosoever believes that Jesus is the Christ is born of God: and everyone that loves him that begat loves him also that is begotten of him.
B062C005V002	62	5	2	By this we know that we love the children of God, when we love God, and keep his commandments.
B062C005V003	62	5	3	For this is the love of God, that we keep his commandments: and his commandments are not burdensome.
B062C005V004	62	5	4	For whoever is born of God overcomes the world: and this is the victory that overcomes the world, even our faith.
B062C005V005	62	5	5	Who is he that overcomes the world, but he that believes that Jesus is the Son of God?
B062C005V006	62	5	6	This is he that came by water and blood, even Jesus Christ; not by water only, but by water and blood. And it is the Spirit that bears witness, because the Spirit is truth.
B062C005V007	62	5	7	For there are three that bear witness in heaven, the Father, the Word, and the Holy Spirit: and these three are one.
B062C005V008	62	5	8	And there are three that bear witness in earth, the Spirit, and the water, and the blood: and these three agree in one.
B062C005V009	62	5	9	If we receive the witness of men, the witness of God is greater: for this is the witness of God which he has testified of his Son.
B062C005V010	62	5	10	He that believes on the Son of God has the witness in himself: he that believes not God has made him a liar; because he believes not the witness that God gave of his Son.
B062C005V011	62	5	11	And this is the witness, that God has given to us eternal life, and this life is in his Son.
B062C005V012	62	5	12	He that has the Son has life; and he that has not the Son of God has not life.
B062C005V013	62	5	13	These things have I written unto you that believe on the name of the Son of God; that you may know that you have eternal life, and that you may believe on the name of the Son of God.
B062C005V014	62	5	14	And this is the confidence that we have in him, that, if we ask anything according to his will, he hears us:
B062C005V015	62	5	15	And if we know that he hears us, whatsoever we ask, we know that we have the requests that we desired of him.
B062C005V016	62	5	16	If any man see his brother sin a sin which is not unto death, he shall ask, and he shall give him life for them that sin not unto death. There is a sin unto death: I do not say that he shall pray for it.
B062C005V017	62	5	17	All unrighteousness is sin: and there is a sin not unto death.
B062C005V018	62	5	18	We know that whosoever is born of God sins not; but he that is begotten of God keeps himself, and that wicked one touches him not.
B062C005V019	62	5	19	And we know that we are of God, and the whole world lies in wickedness.
B062C005V020	62	5	20	And we know that the Son of God is come, and has given us an understanding, that we may know him that is true, and we are in him that is true, even in his Son Jesus Christ. This is the true God, and eternal life.
B062C005V021	62	5	21	Little children, keep yourselves from idols. Amen.
B063C001V001	63	1	1	The elder unto the elect lady and her children, whom I love in the truth; and not I only, but also all they that have known the truth;
B063C001V002	63	1	2	For the truth's sake, which dwells in us, and shall be with us forever.
B063C001V003	63	1	3	Grace be with you, mercy, and peace, from God the Father, and from the Lord Jesus Christ, the Son of the Father, in truth and love.
B063C001V004	63	1	4	I rejoiced greatly that I found some of your children walking in truth, as we have received a commandment from the Father.
B063C001V005	63	1	5	And now I beseech you, lady, not as though I wrote a new commandment unto you, but that which we had from the beginning, that we love one another.
B063C001V006	63	1	6	And this is love, that we walk after his commandments. This is the commandment, That, as you have heard from the beginning, you should walk in it.
B063C001V007	63	1	7	For many deceivers are entered into the world, who confess not that Jesus Christ has come in the flesh. This is a deceiver and an antichrist.
B063C001V008	63	1	8	Look to yourselves, that we lose not those things which we have worked for, but that we receive a full reward.
B063C001V009	63	1	9	Whoever goes beyond, and abides not in the doctrine of Christ, has not God. He that abides in the doctrine of Christ, he has both the Father and the Son.
B063C001V010	63	1	10	If there come any unto you, and bring not this doctrine, receive him not into your house, neither bid him God speed:
B063C001V011	63	1	11	For he that bids him God speed is partaker of his evil deeds.
B063C001V012	63	1	12	Having many things to write unto you, I would not write with paper and ink: but I trust to come unto you, and speak face to face, that our joy may be full.
B063C001V013	63	1	13	The children of your elect sister greet you. Amen.
B064C001V001	64	1	1	The elder unto the well beloved Gaius, whom I love in the truth.
B064C001V002	64	1	2	Beloved, I wish above all things that you may prosper and be in health, even as your soul prospers.
B064C001V003	64	1	3	For I rejoiced greatly, when the brethren came and testified of the truth that is in you, even as you walk in the truth.
B064C001V004	64	1	4	I have no greater joy than to hear that my children walk in truth.
B064C001V005	64	1	5	Beloved, you do faithfully whatsoever you do for the brethren, and for strangers;
B064C001V006	64	1	6	Who have borne witness of your love before the church: whom if you send forward on their journey in a godly manner, you shall do well:
B064C001V007	64	1	7	Because for his name's sake they went forth, taking nothing of the Gentiles.
B064C001V008	64	1	8	We therefore ought to receive such, that we might be fellow helpers to the truth.
B064C001V009	64	1	9	I wrote unto the church: but Diotrephes, who loves to have the preeminence among them, receives us not.
B064C001V010	64	1	10	Therefore, if I come, I will remember his deeds which he does, speaking against us with malicious words: and not content with that, neither does he himself receive the brethren, and forbids them that would, and casts them out of the church.
B064C001V011	64	1	11	Beloved, follow not that which is evil, but that which is good. He that does good is of God: but he that does evil has not seen God.
B064C001V012	64	1	12	Demetrius has good report of all men, and of the truth itself: yea, and we also bear witness; and you know that our witness is true.
B064C001V013	64	1	13	I had many things to write, but I will not with ink and pen write unto you:
B064C001V014	64	1	14	But I trust I shall shortly see you, and we shall speak face to face. Peace be to you. Our friends greet you. Greet the friends by name.
B065C001V001	65	1	1	Jude, the servant of Jesus Christ, and brother of James, to them that are sanctified by God the Father, and preserved in Jesus Christ, and called:
B065C001V002	65	1	2	Mercy unto you, and peace and love, be multiplied.
B065C001V003	65	1	3	Beloved, when I gave all diligence to write unto you of the common salvation, it was necessary for me to write unto you, and exhort you that you should earnestly contend for the faith which was once delivered unto the saints.
B065C001V004	65	1	4	For there are certain men crept in unawares, who were before of old ordained to this condemnation, ungodly men, turning the grace of our God into licentiousness, and denying the only Lord God, and our Lord Jesus Christ.
B065C001V005	65	1	5	I will therefore put you in remembrance, though you once knew this, how that the Lord, having saved the people out of the land of Egypt, afterward destroyed them that believed not.
B065C001V006	65	1	6	And the angels who kept not their first estate, but left their own habitation, he has reserved in everlasting chains under darkness unto the judgment of the great day.
B065C001V007	65	1	7	Even as Sodom and Gomorrah, and the cities about them in like manner, giving themselves over to fornication, and going after unnatural lust, are set forth for an example, suffering the vengeance of eternal fire.
B065C001V008	65	1	8	Likewise also these filthy dreamers defile the flesh, despise authority, and speak evil of the glorious ones.
B065C001V009	65	1	9	Yet Michael the archangel, when contending with the devil as he disputed about the body of Moses, dared not bring against him a railing accusation, but said, The Lord rebuke you.
B065C001V010	65	1	10	But these speak evil of those things which they know not: but what they know naturally, as brute beasts, in those things they corrupt themselves.
B065C001V011	65	1	11	Woe unto them! for they have gone in the way of Cain, and ran greedily after the error of Balaam for reward, and perished in the rebellion of Korah.
B065C001V012	65	1	12	These are spots in your love feasts, when they feast with you, feeding themselves without fear: clouds they are without water, carried about by winds; trees whose fruit withers, without fruit, twice dead, plucked up by the roots;
B065C001V013	65	1	13	Raging waves of the sea, foaming out their own shame; wandering stars, to whom is reserved the blackness of darkness forever.
B065C001V014	65	1	14	And Enoch also, the seventh from Adam, prophesied of these, saying, Behold, the Lord comes with ten thousands of his saints,
B065C001V015	65	1	15	To execute judgment upon all, and to convict all that are ungodly among them of all their ungodly deeds which they have ungodly committed, and of all their hard speeches which ungodly sinners have spoken against him.
B065C001V016	65	1	16	These are murmurers, complainers, walking after their own lusts; and their mouth speaks great swelling words, holding men in admiration for the sake of advantage.
B065C001V017	65	1	17	But you, beloved, remember the words which were spoken before by the apostles of our Lord Jesus Christ;
B065C001V018	65	1	18	How that they told you there should be mockers in the last time, who should walk after their own ungodly lusts.
B065C001V019	65	1	19	These are they who separate themselves, sensual, having not the Spirit.
B065C001V020	65	1	20	But you, beloved, building up yourselves in your most holy faith, praying in the Holy Spirit,
B065C001V021	65	1	21	Keep yourselves in the love of God, looking for the mercy of our Lord Jesus Christ unto eternal life.
B065C001V022	65	1	22	And on some have compassion, making a difference:
B065C001V023	65	1	23	And others save with fear, pulling them out of the fire; hating even the garment spotted by the flesh.
B065C001V024	65	1	24	Now unto him who is able to keep you from falling, and to present you faultless before the presence of his glory with exceeding joy,
B065C001V025	65	1	25	To the only wise God our Savior, be glory and majesty, dominion and power, both now and forever. Amen.
B066C001V001	66	1	1	The Revelation of Jesus Christ, which God gave unto him, to show unto his servants things which must shortly come to pass; and he sent and revealed it by his angel unto his servant John:
B066C001V002	66	1	2	Who bore witness of the word of God, and of the testimony of Jesus Christ, and of all things that he saw.
B066C001V003	66	1	3	Blessed is he that reads, and they that hear the words of this prophecy, and keep those things which are written therein: for the time is at hand.
B066C001V004	66	1	4	John to the seven churches which are in Asia: Grace be unto you, and peace, from him who is, and who was, and who is to come; and from the seven Spirits who are before his throne;
B066C001V005	66	1	5	And from Jesus Christ, who is the faithful witness, and the first begotten of the dead, and the prince of the kings of the earth. Unto him that loves us, and washed us from our sins in his own blood,
B066C001V006	66	1	6	And has made us a kingdom and priests unto God and his Father; to him be glory and dominion forever and ever. Amen.
B066C001V007	66	1	7	Behold, he comes with clouds; and every eye shall see him, and they also who pierced him: and all tribes of the earth shall wail because of him. Even so, Amen.
B066C001V008	66	1	8	
        
B066C001V009	66	1	9	I John, who also am your brother, and companion in tribulation, and in the kingdom and patience of Jesus Christ, was in the isle that is called Patmos, for the word of God, and for the testimony of Jesus Christ.
B066C001V010	66	1	10	I was in the Spirit on the Lord's day, and heard behind me a great voice, as of a trumpet,
B066C001V011	66	1	11	Saying, 
B066C001V012	66	1	12	And I turned to see the voice that spoke with me. And being turned, I saw seven golden lampstands;
B066C001V013	66	1	13	And in the midst of the seven lampstands one like unto the Son of man, clothed with a garment down to the foot, and girded about the breast with a golden belt.
B066C001V014	66	1	14	His head and his hair were white like wool, as white as snow; and his eyes were as a flame of fire;
B066C001V015	66	1	15	And his feet like unto fine bronze, as if they burned in a furnace; and his voice as the sound of many waters.
B066C001V016	66	1	16	And he had in his right hand seven stars: and out of his mouth went a sharp two edged sword: and his countenance was as the sun shines in its strength.
B066C001V017	66	1	17	And when I saw him, I fell at his feet as dead. And he laid his right hand upon me, saying unto me, 
