B066C015V001	66	15	1	And I saw another sign in heaven, great and marvelous, seven angels having the seven last plagues; for in them is completed the wrath of God.
B066C015V002	66	15	2	And I saw as it were a sea of glass mingled with fire: and them that had gotten the victory over the beast, and over his image, and over his mark, and over the number of his name, stand on the sea of glass, having the harps of God.
B066C015V003	66	15	3	And they sing the song of Moses the servant of God, and the song of the Lamb, saying, Great and marvelous are your works, Lord God Almighty; just and true are your ways, you King of saints.
B066C015V004	66	15	4	Who shall not fear you, O Lord, and glorify your name? for you only are holy: for all nations shall come and worship before you; for your judgments are made manifest.
B066C015V005	66	15	5	And after that I looked, and, behold, the temple of the tabernacle of the testimony in heaven was opened:
B066C015V006	66	15	6	And the seven angels came out of the temple, having the seven plagues, clothed in pure and white linen, and having their breasts girded with golden sashes.
B066C015V007	66	15	7	And one of the four living creatures gave unto the seven angels seven golden bowls full of the wrath of God, who lives forever and ever.
B066C015V008	66	15	8	And the temple was filled with smoke from the glory of God, and from his power; and no man was able to enter into the temple, till the seven plagues of the seven angels were fulfilled.
B066C016V001	66	16	1	And I heard a great voice out of the temple saying to the seven angels, 
B066C016V002	66	16	2	And the first went, and poured out his bowl upon the earth; and there fell foul and evil sores upon the men who had the mark of the beast, and upon them who worshiped his image.
B066C016V003	66	16	3	And the second angel poured out his bowl upon the sea; and it became as the blood of a dead man; and every living thing died in the sea.
B066C016V004	66	16	4	And the third angel poured out his bowl upon the rivers and fountains of waters; and they became blood.
B066C016V005	66	16	5	And I heard the angel of the waters say, You are righteous, O Lord, who is, and was, and shall be, because you have judged thus.
B066C016V006	66	16	6	For they have shed the blood of saints and prophets, and you have given them blood to drink; for they are deserving of it.
B066C016V007	66	16	7	And I heard another out of the altar say, Even so, Lord God Almighty, true and righteous are your judgments.
B066C016V008	66	16	8	And the fourth angel poured out his bowl upon the sun; and power was given unto it to scorch men with fire.
B066C016V009	66	16	9	And men were scorched with great heat, and blasphemed the name of God, who has power over these plagues: and they repented not to give him glory.
B066C016V010	66	16	10	And the fifth angel poured out his bowl upon the throne of the beast; and his kingdom was full of darkness; and they gnawed their tongues for pain,
B066C016V011	66	16	11	And blasphemed the God of heaven because of their pains and their sores, and repented not of their deeds.
B066C016V012	66	16	12	And the sixth angel poured out his bowl upon the great river Euphrates; and its water was dried up, that the way of the kings of the east might be prepared.
B066C016V013	66	16	13	And I saw three unclean spirits like frogs come out of the mouth of the dragon, and out of the mouth of the beast, and out of the mouth of the false prophet.
B066C016V014	66	16	14	For they are the spirits of demons, working miracles, who go forth unto the kings of the earth and of the whole world, to gather them to the battle of that great day of God Almighty.
B066C016V015	66	16	15	
        
B066C016V016	66	16	16	And he gathered them together into a place called in the Hebrew tongue Armageddon.
B066C016V017	66	16	17	And the seventh angel poured out his bowl into the air; and there came a great voice out of the temple of heaven, from the throne, saying, 
B066C016V018	66	16	18	And there were voices, and thunders, and lightnings; and there was a great earthquake, such as was not since men were upon the earth, so mighty an earthquake, and so great.
B066C016V019	66	16	19	And the great city was divided into three parts, and the cities of the nations fell: and great Babylon came in remembrance before God, to give unto her the cup of the wine of the fierceness of his wrath.
B066C016V020	66	16	20	And every island fled away, and the mountains were not found.
B066C016V021	66	16	21	And there fell upon men a great hail out of heaven, every stone about the weight of a talent: and men blasphemed God because of the plague of the hail; for the plague thereof was exceedingly great.
B066C017V001	66	17	1	And there came one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls, and talked with me, saying unto me, Come here; I will show unto you the judgment of the great harlot that sits upon many waters:
B066C017V002	66	17	2	With whom the kings of the earth have committed fornication, and the inhabitants of the earth have been made drunk with the wine of her fornication.
B066C017V003	66	17	3	So he carried me away in the spirit into the wilderness: and I saw a woman sitting upon a scarlet colored beast, full of names of blasphemy, having seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V004	66	17	4	And the woman was arrayed in purple and scarlet color, and adorned with gold and precious stones and pearls, having a golden cup in her hand full of abominations and filthiness of her fornication:
B066C017V005	66	17	5	And upon her forehead was a name written, MYSTERY, BABYLON THE GREAT, THE MOTHER OF HARLOTS AND ABOMINATIONS OF THE EARTH.
B066C017V006	66	17	6	And I saw the woman drunken with the blood of the saints, and with the blood of the martyrs of Jesus: and when I saw her, I wondered with great wonder.
B066C017V007	66	17	7	And the angel said unto me, Why did you marvel? I will tell you the mystery of the woman, and of the beast that carries her, which has the seven heads and ten horns.
B066C017V008	66	17	8	The beast that you saw was, and is not; and shall ascend out of the bottomless pit, and go into perdition: and they that dwell on the earth shall wonder, whose names were not written in the book of life from the foundation of the world, when they behold the beast that was, and is not, and yet is.
B066C017V009	66	17	9	And here is the mind which has wisdom. The seven heads are seven mountains, on which the woman sits.
B066C017V010	66	17	10	And there are seven kings: five are fallen, and one is, and the other is not yet come; and when he comes, he must continue a short time.
B066C017V011	66	17	11	And the beast that was, and is not, even he is the eighth, and is of the seven, and goes into perdition.
B066C017V012	66	17	12	And the ten horns which you saw are ten kings, who have received no kingdom as yet; but receive power as kings one hour with the beast.
B066C017V013	66	17	13	These have one mind, and shall give their power and strength unto the beast.
B066C017V014	66	17	14	These shall make war with the Lamb, and the Lamb shall overcome them: for he is Lord of lords, and King of kings: and they that are with him are called, and chosen, and faithful.
B066C017V015	66	17	15	And he said unto me, The waters which you saw, where the harlot sits, are peoples, and multitudes, and nations, and tongues.
B066C017V016	66	17	16	And the ten horns which you saw upon the beast, these shall hate the harlot, and shall make her desolate and naked, and shall eat her flesh, and burn her with fire.
B066C017V017	66	17	17	For God has put in their hearts to fulfill his will, and to agree, and give their kingdom unto the beast, until the words of God shall be fulfilled.
B066C017V018	66	17	18	And the woman whom you saw is that great city, which reigns over the kings of the earth.
B066C018V001	66	18	1	And after these things I saw another angel come down from heaven, having great power; and the earth was made bright with his glory.
B066C018V002	66	18	2	And he cried mightily with a strong voice, saying, Babylon the great is fallen, is fallen, and is become the habitation of demons, and the haunt of every foul spirit, and a cage of every unclean and hateful bird.
B066C018V003	66	18	3	For all nations have drunk of the wine of the wrath of her fornication, and the kings of the earth have committed fornication with her, and the merchants of the earth have grown rich through the abundance of her luxury.
B066C018V004	66	18	4	And I heard another voice from heaven, saying, 
B066C018V005	66	18	5	For her sins have reached unto heaven, and God has remembered her iniquities.
B066C018V006	66	18	6	Reward her even as she rewarded you, and double unto her double according to her works: in the cup which she has filled, fill to her double.
B066C018V007	66	18	7	So much as she has glorified herself, and lived luxuriously, so much torment and sorrow give her: for she says in her heart, I sit a queen, and am no widow, and shall see no sorrow.
B066C018V008	66	18	8	Therefore shall her plagues come in one day, death, and mourning, and famine; and she shall be utterly burned with fire: for strong is the Lord God who judges her.
B066C018V009	66	18	9	And the kings of the earth, who have committed fornication and lived in luxury with her, shall bewail her, and lament for her, when they shall see the smoke of her burning,
B066C018V010	66	18	10	Standing afar off for the fear of her torment, saying, Alas, alas that great city Babylon, that mighty city! for in one hour is your judgment come.
B066C018V011	66	18	11	And the merchants of the earth shall weep and mourn over her; for no man buys their merchandise any more:
B066C018V012	66	18	12	The merchandise of gold, and silver, and precious stones, and of pearls, and fine linen, and purple, and silk, and scarlet, and all citron wood, and all manner of vessels of ivory, and all manner of vessels of most precious wood, and of bronze, and iron, and marble,
B066C018V013	66	18	13	And cinnamon, and incense, and myrrh, and frankincense, and wine, and oil, and fine flour, and wheat, and cattle, and sheep, and horses, and chariots, and slaves, and souls of men.
B066C018V014	66	18	14	And the fruits that your soul lusted after are departed from you, and all things which were luxurious and splendid are departed from you, and you shall find them no more at all.
B066C018V015	66	18	15	The merchants of these things, who were made rich by her, shall stand afar off for the fear of her torment, weeping and wailing,
B066C018V016	66	18	16	And saying, Alas, alas, that great city, that was clothed in fine linen, and purple, and scarlet, and adorned with gold, and precious stones, and pearls!
B066C018V017	66	18	17	For in one hour such great riches is come to nothing. And every shipmaster, and all seafarers, and sailors, and as many as trade by sea, stood afar off,
B066C018V018	66	18	18	And cried when they saw the smoke of her burning, saying, What city is like unto this great city!
B066C018V019	66	18	19	And they cast dust on their heads, and cried, weeping and wailing, saying, Alas, alas, that great city, in which were made rich all that had ships in the sea by reason of her wealth! for in one hour is she made desolate.
B066C018V020	66	18	20	Rejoice over her, you heaven, and you holy apostles and prophets; for God has avenged you on her.
B066C018V021	66	18	21	And a mighty angel took up a stone like a great millstone, and cast it into the sea, saying, Thus with violence shall that great city Babylon be thrown down, and shall be found no more at all.
B066C018V022	66	18	22	And the voice of harpers, and musicians, and of flutists, and trumpeters, shall be heard no more at all in you; and no craftsman, of whatsoever craft he may be, shall be found any more in you; and the sound of a millstone shall be heard no more at all in you;
B066C018V023	66	18	23	And the light of a lamp shall shine no more at all in you; and the voice of the bridegroom and of the bride shall be heard no more at all in you: for your merchants were the great men of the earth; for by your sorceries were all nations deceived.
B066C018V024	66	18	24	And in her was found the blood of prophets, and of saints, and of all that were slain upon the earth.
B066C019V001	66	19	1	And after these things I heard a great voice of many people in heaven, saying, Alleluia; Salvation, and glory, and honor, and power, unto the Lord our God:
B066C019V002	66	19	2	For true and righteous are his judgments: for he has judged the great harlot, who did corrupt the earth with her fornication, and has avenged the blood of his servants at her hand.
B066C019V003	66	19	3	And again they said, Alleluia. And her smoke rose up forever and ever.
B066C019V004	66	19	4	And the four and twenty elders and the four living creatures fell down and worshiped God that sat on the throne, saying, Amen; Alleluia.
B066C019V005	66	19	5	And a voice came out of the throne, saying, Praise our God, all you his servants, and you that fear him, both small and great.
B066C019V006	66	19	6	And I heard as it were the voice of a great multitude, and as the voice of many waters, and as the voice of mighty thunderings, saying, Alleluia: for the Lord God omnipotent reigns.
B066C019V007	66	19	7	Let us be glad and rejoice, and give honor to him: for the marriage of the Lamb has come, and his wife has made herself ready.
B066C019V008	66	19	8	And to her was granted that she should be arrayed in fine linen, clean and white: for the fine linen is the righteous acts of saints.
B066C019V009	66	19	9	And he said unto me, Write, Blessed are they who are called unto the marriage supper of the Lamb. And he said unto me, These are the true sayings of God.
B066C019V010	66	19	10	And I fell at his feet to worship him. And he said unto me, See you do it not: I am your fellow servant, and of your brethren that have the testimony of Jesus: worship God: for the testimony of Jesus is the spirit of prophecy.
B066C019V011	66	19	11	And I saw heaven opened, and behold a white horse; and he that sat upon it was called Faithful and True, and in righteousness he does judge and make war.
B066C019V012	66	19	12	His eyes were as a flame of fire, and on his head were many crowns; and he had a name written, that no man knew, but he himself.
B066C019V013	66	19	13	And he was clothed with a robe dipped in blood: and his name is called The Word of God.
B066C019V014	66	19	14	And the armies which were in heaven followed him upon white horses, clothed in fine linen, white and clean.
B066C019V015	66	19	15	And out of his mouth goes forth a sharp sword, that with it he should smite the nations: and he shall rule them with a rod of iron: and he treads the winepress of the fierceness and wrath of Almighty God.
B066C019V016	66	19	16	And he has on his robe and on his thigh a name written, KING OF KINGS, AND LORD OF LORDS.
B066C019V017	66	19	17	And I saw an angel standing in the sun; and he cried with a loud voice, saying to all the fowls that fly in midheaven, Come and gather yourselves together unto the supper of the great God;
B066C019V018	66	19	18	That you may eat the flesh of kings, and the flesh of captains, and the flesh of mighty men, and the flesh of horses, and of them that sit on them, and the flesh of all men, both free and slave, both small and great.
B066C019V019	66	19	19	And I saw the beast, and the kings of the earth, and their armies, gathered together to make war against him that sat on the horse, and against his army.
B066C019V020	66	19	20	And the beast was taken, and with him the false prophet that worked miracles before him, with which he deceived them that had received the mark of the beast, and them that worshiped his image. These both were cast alive into a lake of fire burning with brimstone.
B066C019V021	66	19	21	And the rest were slain with the sword of him that sat upon the horse, which sword proceeded out of his mouth: and all the fowls were filled with their flesh.
B066C020V001	66	20	1	And I saw an angel come down from heaven, having the key of the bottomless pit and a great chain in his hand.
B066C020V002	66	20	2	And he laid hold on the dragon, that old serpent, who is the Devil, and Satan, and bound him a thousand years,
B066C020V003	66	20	3	And cast him into the bottomless pit, and shut him up, and set a seal upon him, that he should deceive the nations no more, till the thousand years should be fulfilled: and after that he must be loosed a little while.
B066C020V004	66	20	4	And I saw thrones, and they sat upon them, and judgment was given unto them: and I saw the souls of them that were beheaded for the witness of Jesus, and for the word of God, and who had not worshiped the beast, neither his image, neither had received his mark upon their foreheads, or in their hands; and they lived and reigned with Christ a thousand years.
B066C020V005	66	20	5	But the rest of the dead lived not again until the thousand years were finished. This is the first resurrection.
B066C020V006	66	20	6	Blessed and holy is he that has part in the first resurrection: on such the second death has no power, but they shall be priests of God and of Christ, and shall reign with him a thousand years.
B066C020V007	66	20	7	And when the thousand years are ended, Satan shall be loosed out of his prison,
B066C020V008	66	20	8	And shall go out to deceive the nations which are in the four quarters of the earth, Gog and Magog, to gather them together to battle: the number of whom is as the sand of the sea.
B066C020V009	66	20	9	And they went up over the breadth of the earth, and encircled the camp of the saints, and the beloved city: and fire came down from God out of heaven, and devoured them.
B066C020V010	66	20	10	And the devil that deceived them was cast into the lake of fire and brimstone, where the beast and the false prophet are, and shall be tormented day and night forever and ever.
B066C020V011	66	20	11	And I saw a great white throne, and him that sat on it, from whose face the earth and the heaven fled away; and there was found no place for them.
B066C020V012	66	20	12	And I saw the dead, small and great, stand before God; and the books were opened: and another book was opened, which is the book of life: and the dead were judged out of those things which were written in the books, according to their works.
B066C020V013	66	20	13	And the sea gave up the dead who were in it; and death and hades delivered up the dead who were in them: and they were judged every man according to their works.
B066C020V014	66	20	14	And death and hades were cast into the lake of fire. This is the second death.
B066C020V015	66	20	15	And whosoever was not found written in the book of life was cast into the lake of fire.
B066C021V001	66	21	1	And I saw a new heaven and a new earth: for the first heaven and the first earth were passed away; and there was no more sea.
B066C021V002	66	21	2	And I John saw the holy city, new Jerusalem, coming down from God out of heaven, prepared as a bride adorned for her husband.
B066C021V003	66	21	3	And I heard a great voice out of heaven saying, Behold, the tabernacle of God is with men, and he will dwell with them, and they shall be his people, and God himself shall be with them, and be their God.
B066C021V004	66	21	4	And God shall wipe away all tears from their eyes; and there shall be no more death, neither sorrow, nor crying, neither shall there be any more pain: for the former things are passed away.
B066C021V005	66	21	5	And he that sat upon the throne said, 
B066C021V006	66	21	6	And he said unto me, 
B066C021V007	66	21	7	
        
B066C021V008	66	21	8	
        
B066C021V009	66	21	9	And there came unto me one of the seven angels who had the seven bowls full of the seven last plagues, and talked with me, saying, Come here, I will show you the bride, the Lamb's wife.
B066C021V010	66	21	10	And he carried me away in the spirit to a great and high mountain, and showed me that great city, the holy Jerusalem, descending out of heaven from God,
B066C021V011	66	21	11	Having the glory of God: and its radiance was like unto a stone most precious, even like a jasper stone, clear as crystal;
B066C021V012	66	21	12	And having a wall great and high, and having twelve gates, and at the gates twelve angels, and names written thereon, which are the names of the twelve tribes of the children of Israel:
B066C021V013	66	21	13	On the east three gates; on the north three gates; on the south three gates; and on the west three gates.
B066C021V014	66	21	14	And the wall of the city had twelve foundations, and in them the names of the twelve apostles of the Lamb.
B066C021V015	66	21	15	And he that talked with me had a golden reed to measure the city, and the gates thereof, and the wall thereof.
B066C021V016	66	21	16	And the city lies foursquare, and the length is as large as the breadth: and he measured the city with the reed, twelve thousand furlongs. The length and the breadth and the height of it are equal.
B066C021V017	66	21	17	And he measured the wall thereof, a hundred and forty and four cubits, according to the measure of a man, that is, of the angel.
B066C021V018	66	21	18	And the building of the wall of it was of jasper: and the city was pure gold, like unto clear glass.
B066C021V019	66	21	19	And the foundations of the wall of the city were adorned with all manner of precious stones. The first foundation was jasper; the second, sapphire; the third, a chalcedony; the fourth, an emerald;
B066C021V020	66	21	20	The fifth, sardonyx; the sixth, carnelian; the seventh, chrysolyte; the eighth, beryl; the ninth, a topaz; the tenth, a chrysoprase; the eleventh, a jacinth; the twelfth, an amethyst.
B066C021V021	66	21	21	And the twelve gates were twelve pearls: each of the gates was a single pearl: and the street of the city was pure gold, as it were transparent glass.
B066C021V022	66	21	22	And I saw no temple in it: for the Lord God Almighty and the Lamb are the temple of it.
B066C021V023	66	21	23	And the city had no need of the sun, neither of the moon, to shine in it: for the glory of God is its light, and the Lamb is its lamp.
B066C021V024	66	21	24	And the nations of them who are saved shall walk in the light of it: and the kings of the earth do bring their glory and honor into it.
B066C021V025	66	21	25	And the gates of it shall not be shut at all by day: for there shall be no night there.
B066C021V026	66	21	26	And they shall bring the glory and honor of the nations into it.
B066C021V027	66	21	27	And there shall in no way enter into it anything that defiles, neither whatsoever works abomination, or makes a lie: but they who are written in the Lamb's book of life.
B066C022V001	66	22	1	And he showed me a pure river of water of life, clear as crystal, proceeding out of the throne of God and of the Lamb.
B066C022V002	66	22	2	In the midst of the street of it, and on either side of the river, was there the tree of life, which bore twelve manner of fruit, and yielded its fruit every month: and the leaves of the tree were for the healing of the nations.
B066C022V003	66	22	3	And there shall be no more curse: but the throne of God and of the Lamb shall be in it; and his servants shall serve him:
B066C022V004	66	22	4	And they shall see his face; and his name shall be on their foreheads.
B066C022V005	66	22	5	And there shall be no night there; and they need no lamp, neither light of the sun; for the Lord God gives them light: and they shall reign forever and ever.
B066C022V006	66	22	6	And he said unto me, These words are faithful and true: and the Lord God of the holy prophets sent his angel to show unto his servants the things which must shortly be done.
B066C022V007	66	22	7	
        
B066C022V008	66	22	8	And I John saw these things, and heard them. And when I had heard and seen, I fell down to worship before the feet of the angel who showed me these things.
B066C022V009	66	22	9	Then he said unto me, See you do it not: for I am your fellow servant, and of your brethren the prophets, and of them who keep the words of this book: worship God.
B066C022V010	66	22	10	And he said unto me, Seal not the words of the prophecy of this book: for the time is at hand.
B066C022V011	66	22	11	He that is unjust, let him be unjust still: and he that is filthy, let him be filthy still: and he that is righteous, let him be righteous still: and he that is holy, let him be holy still.
B066C022V012	66	22	12	
        
B066C022V013	66	22	13	
        
B066C022V014	66	22	14	Blessed are they that do his commandments, that they may have right to the tree of life, and may enter in through the gates into the city.
B066C022V015	66	22	15	For outside are dogs, and sorcerers, and fornicators, and murderers, and idolaters, and whosoever loves and makes a lie.
B066C022V016	66	22	16	
        
B066C022V017	66	22	17	And the Spirit and the bride say, 
B066C022V018	66	22	18	For I testify unto every man that hears the words of the prophecy of this book, If any man shall add unto these things, God shall add unto him the plagues that are written in this book:
B066C022V019	66	22	19	And if any man shall take away from the words of the book of this prophecy, God shall take away his part out of the book of life, and out of the holy city, and from the things which are written in this book.
B066C022V020	66	22	20	He who testifies these things says, 
B066C022V021	66	22	21	The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ be with you all. Amen.
